WEBVTT

00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:17.579
Scholastic Audio presents Wings of Fire

00:00:17.579 --> 00:00:18.600
Book 4.

00:00:19.320 --> 00:00:20.879
The Dark Secret.

00:00:21.000 --> 00:00:23.100
By 2AT Sutherland.

00:00:23.160 --> 00:00:25.679
Read by Shannon McManus.

00:00:43.740 --> 00:00:46.619
The Dragonette Prophecy.

00:00:46.679 --> 00:00:50.759
When the war has lasted 20 years, the

00:00:50.759 --> 00:00:53.880
dragonettes will come, when the land is

00:00:53.880 --> 00:00:56.520
soaked in blood and tears, the

00:00:56.520 --> 00:00:57.719
dragonettes will come.

00:00:57.840 --> 00:01:01.740
Find the sea wing egg of deepest blue

00:01:01.740 --> 00:01:04.319
wings of night shall come to you.

00:01:04.379 --> 00:01:08.339
The largest egg in mountain high will

00:01:08.339 --> 00:01:09.959
give to you the wings of sky.

00:01:10.019 --> 00:01:13.620
For wings of earth, search through the

00:01:13.620 --> 00:01:16.379
mud, for an egg the color of dragon

00:01:16.379 --> 00:01:16.980
blood.

00:01:17.099 --> 00:01:20.640
And hidden alone from the rival queens.

00:01:20.700 --> 00:01:23.700
The sand wing egg awaits unseen.

00:01:23.760 --> 00:01:28.379
Of 3 queens who blister and blaze and

00:01:28.379 --> 00:01:28.799
burn.

00:01:28.859 --> 00:01:33.239
Two shall die, and one shall learn, If

00:01:33.239 --> 00:01:35.519
she bows to a fate that is stronger and

00:01:35.519 --> 00:01:38.700
higher, Shall have the power of wings of

00:01:38.700 --> 00:01:39.000
fire.

00:01:39.060 --> 00:01:43.739
Five eggs to hatch on brightest night

00:01:43.739 --> 00:01:46.439
five dragons born to end the fight.

00:01:46.560 --> 00:01:50.159
Darkness will rise to bring the light.

00:01:50.219 --> 00:01:53.340
The dragonettes are coming.

00:02:05.400 --> 00:02:10.020
Prologue.

00:02:10.139 --> 00:02:13.259
The ice dragons came out of nowhere.

00:02:13.319 --> 00:02:15.599
It should have been a quiet night.

00:02:15.659 --> 00:02:18.120
They shouldn't have seen anyone but Sky

00:02:18.120 --> 00:02:20.219
Wings and other mud wings on their patrol

00:02:20.219 --> 00:02:21.780
along the mountainous border between

00:02:21.780 --> 00:02:22.439
their kingdoms.

00:02:22.500 --> 00:02:24.419
There hadn't been a battle near their

00:02:24.419 --> 00:02:26.039
village since the one where they lost

00:02:26.039 --> 00:02:28.080
Crane, 16 days ago.

00:02:28.139 --> 00:02:31.020
Reed still couldn't think about that

00:02:31.020 --> 00:02:33.840
battle without feeling a huge pit open

00:02:33.840 --> 00:02:34.680
inside his chest.

00:02:34.740 --> 00:02:38.099
Sometimes he wanted to close his eyes and

00:02:38.099 --> 00:02:39.900
fall into that pit and never come out.

00:02:39.960 --> 00:02:41.699
But he couldn't.

00:02:41.759 --> 00:02:44.219
He had 4 other brothers and sisters who

00:02:44.219 --> 00:02:44.939
depended on him.

00:02:45.000 --> 00:02:46.680
He was their leader.

00:02:46.740 --> 00:02:48.060
Their big wings.

00:02:48.180 --> 00:02:50.520
Even though he knew now that he wasn't

00:02:50.520 --> 00:02:51.180
supposed to be.

00:02:51.300 --> 00:02:53.819
It should have been their brother, Clay

00:02:53.819 --> 00:02:55.740
whose egg was stolen before they all

00:02:55.740 --> 00:02:56.520
hatched.

00:02:56.759 --> 00:02:58.080
Did you hear that?

00:02:58.139 --> 00:02:59.819
Umber whispered.

00:02:59.879 --> 00:03:01.560
Darting up to fly beside him.

00:03:01.620 --> 00:03:04.439
The smallest dragon in their mud wing

00:03:04.439 --> 00:03:06.539
troop of siblings, Umber was also the

00:03:06.539 --> 00:03:07.199
most observant.

00:03:07.259 --> 00:03:10.080
Reid knew by now that it was always worth

00:03:10.080 --> 00:03:10.860
listening to him.

00:03:10.979 --> 00:03:12.719
What?

00:03:12.840 --> 00:03:15.539
Reed whispered back, tilting his head and

00:03:15.539 --> 00:03:16.319
straining his ears.

00:03:16.379 --> 00:03:19.259
His wings caught the air currents as they

00:03:19.259 --> 00:03:21.539
both soared higher, and he studied the

00:03:21.539 --> 00:03:23.639
dark, jagged shapes of the claws of the

00:03:23.639 --> 00:03:24.360
clouds mountains.

00:03:24.419 --> 00:03:27.180
He couldn't see any movement or hear any

00:03:27.180 --> 00:03:27.780
wing beats.

00:03:27.900 --> 00:03:31.139
Still, he twisted around to check on his

00:03:31.139 --> 00:03:33.419
brothers and sisters, calling them closer

00:03:33.419 --> 00:03:34.319
with a flick of his tail.

00:03:34.379 --> 00:03:38.460
In a moment, Pheasant, Sora, and Marsh

00:03:38.460 --> 00:03:40.139
were flying in a close formation behind

00:03:40.139 --> 00:03:40.439
him.

00:03:40.500 --> 00:03:44.460
I thought I heard hissing, Umber said

00:03:44.460 --> 00:03:45.599
somewhere close by.

00:03:45.659 --> 00:03:49.080
Reed glanced down uneasily at the shadowy

00:03:49.080 --> 00:03:50.639
trees that covered the mountain slope

00:03:50.639 --> 00:03:51.000
below them.

00:03:51.060 --> 00:03:53.039
Anything could be hiding in there.

00:03:53.099 --> 00:03:55.500
But the only sound he heard was the

00:03:55.500 --> 00:03:58.199
sandwing general up ahead, calling it top

00:03:58.199 --> 00:04:01.199
volume, as if stealth patrol were only a

00:04:01.199 --> 00:04:02.400
funny name for what they were doing.

00:04:02.460 --> 00:04:06.240
Move it, Mudwings. bellowed the sand

00:04:06.240 --> 00:04:06.719
dragon.

00:04:06.780 --> 00:04:10.259
His squadron of 7 sandwings, all fiercely

00:04:10.259 --> 00:04:12.240
loyal to Queen Byrne, hovered behind him

00:04:12.240 --> 00:04:12.900
grunting.

00:04:12.960 --> 00:04:15.479
I want to wrap up this patrol and get

00:04:15.479 --> 00:04:16.259
some sleep tonight.

00:04:16.319 --> 00:04:20.339
It was probably nothing, Umber said to

00:04:20.339 --> 00:04:20.639
read.

00:04:20.699 --> 00:04:24.120
And that was when the 9 ice dragons

00:04:24.120 --> 00:04:26.040
suddenly shot out of the forest and

00:04:26.040 --> 00:04:27.240
attacked the sand wings.

00:04:27.300 --> 00:04:31.199
It was so fast, so calculated, and swift

00:04:31.199 --> 00:04:33.779
and sudden, that 2 sand wings were sent

00:04:33.779 --> 00:04:35.879
spiraling toward the ground with shredded

00:04:35.879 --> 00:04:37.680
wings and blood pouring from their

00:04:37.680 --> 00:04:39.660
throats before Reed could even process

00:04:39.660 --> 00:04:41.040
that this was a real attack.

00:04:41.100 --> 00:04:44.519
Marsh shrieked with terror and grabbed

00:04:44.519 --> 00:04:46.740
Reed, nearly tumbling the big wings out

00:04:46.740 --> 00:04:47.220
of the sky.

00:04:47.279 --> 00:04:49.860
Marsh had never really recovered from

00:04:49.860 --> 00:04:52.019
their 1st battle, where he'd seen their

00:04:52.019 --> 00:04:53.519
sister crane die in front of him.

00:04:53.579 --> 00:04:55.860
I need to do something about that.

00:04:55.920 --> 00:04:58.319
Reed thought, but not right now.

00:04:58.379 --> 00:05:02.519
Marsh, keep it together, he shouted

00:05:02.519 --> 00:05:03.839
pulling his wing free.

00:05:03.899 --> 00:05:05.939
Come on, quick, we have to help.

00:05:06.000 --> 00:05:09.360
He saw the hesitation on all their faces

00:05:09.360 --> 00:05:12.600
and caught himself wondering, again, what

00:05:12.600 --> 00:05:14.160
Clay would have done in this situation

00:05:14.160 --> 00:05:16.139
and whether the others would have been

00:05:16.139 --> 00:05:19.680
happier and safer following him, and also

00:05:19.680 --> 00:05:21.600
wondering whether they were wondering

00:05:21.600 --> 00:05:22.319
that too.

00:05:22.620 --> 00:05:24.660
But no one said what they must be

00:05:24.660 --> 00:05:24.959
thinking.

00:05:25.019 --> 00:05:27.420
It's a suicide mission.

00:05:27.480 --> 00:05:28.920
What help can we be?

00:05:28.980 --> 00:05:31.259
I don't want to lose another sibling.

00:05:31.319 --> 00:05:35.279
Instead, they formed up behind him and

00:05:35.279 --> 00:05:37.139
dove toward the writhing dragons.

00:05:37.199 --> 00:05:40.079
Reed hated fighting ice wings.

00:05:40.139 --> 00:05:42.720
Their serrated claws seemed 10 times

00:05:42.720 --> 00:05:45.180
sharper than normal claws, and their whip

00:05:45.180 --> 00:05:47.339
thin tails left stinging marks across the

00:05:47.339 --> 00:05:48.300
snout and wings.

00:05:48.360 --> 00:05:51.240
Worst of all, they could just breathe on

00:05:51.240 --> 00:05:51.839
you and kill you.

00:05:51.959 --> 00:05:54.420
He shot a burst of fire at the biggest

00:05:54.420 --> 00:05:56.699
ice wing, who was grappling with the sand

00:05:56.699 --> 00:05:57.480
wing general.

00:05:57.540 --> 00:06:00.240
Her teeth snapped shut and she hissed at

00:06:00.240 --> 00:06:01.920
him, but she was too busy with the

00:06:01.920 --> 00:06:03.060
sandwing to come after Reed.

00:06:03.120 --> 00:06:06.300
He spun in the air, lashing out at

00:06:06.300 --> 00:06:08.939
silvery white scales as another ice wing

00:06:08.939 --> 00:06:09.660
attacked his flank.

00:06:09.720 --> 00:06:11.759
They clutched each other with fierce

00:06:11.759 --> 00:06:14.040
talons for a moment, the wind buffeting

00:06:14.040 --> 00:06:14.459
their wings.

00:06:14.519 --> 00:06:17.040
Finally, Reed managed to cough out

00:06:17.040 --> 00:06:19.319
another bolt of flames, and the ice wing

00:06:19.319 --> 00:06:21.899
jerked away, narrowly avoiding a singed

00:06:21.899 --> 00:06:22.319
nose.

00:06:22.439 --> 00:06:25.439
Reed spotted an ice wing diving toward

00:06:25.439 --> 00:06:27.240
umber, and leads to knock his brother

00:06:27.240 --> 00:06:29.399
aside, catching the brunt of the white

00:06:29.399 --> 00:06:31.560
dragon's momentum against his chest.

00:06:31.560 --> 00:06:34.199
As he staggered back, he saw another ice

00:06:34.199 --> 00:06:36.180
wing wrap her dangerous claws around

00:06:36.180 --> 00:06:39.000
Sora's neck, and he roared with fury.

00:06:39.060 --> 00:06:42.060
Pheasant was there in an instant, throwing

00:06:42.060 --> 00:06:44.579
the ice wing off Sora, but the ice dragon

00:06:44.579 --> 00:06:46.319
came back at them with her mouth open to

00:06:46.319 --> 00:06:47.339
shoot her frost breath.

00:06:47.399 --> 00:06:49.740
I can't lose anyone else.

00:06:49.800 --> 00:06:51.240
Reed thought.

00:06:51.300 --> 00:06:52.500
It'll kill me.

00:06:52.560 --> 00:06:55.860
He smashed into the ice wing's side and

00:06:55.860 --> 00:06:58.139
sliced his claws across her throat while

00:06:58.139 --> 00:06:59.519
she was twisting to breathe on him.

00:06:59.579 --> 00:07:02.459
Her eyes went wide, and she made an

00:07:02.459 --> 00:07:05.220
agonized, gargling noise as blood bubbled

00:07:05.220 --> 00:07:06.120
from the wounds.

00:07:06.300 --> 00:07:08.459
When he let go of her, the ice wing

00:07:08.459 --> 00:07:10.740
soldier fell toward the dark forest, her

00:07:10.740 --> 00:07:12.779
wings twitching feebly, like a dying

00:07:12.779 --> 00:07:13.560
grasshopper.

00:07:13.560 --> 00:07:15.480
Retreat!

00:07:15.600 --> 00:07:17.339
A voice suddenly howled.

00:07:17.399 --> 00:07:19.920
Reed's heart jumped hopefully, thinking

00:07:19.920 --> 00:07:22.259
the ice wings were giving up, but then he

00:07:22.259 --> 00:07:24.180
realized it was the sand wing general.

00:07:24.300 --> 00:07:25.800
Retreat!

00:07:25.860 --> 00:07:27.540
The sand dragon yelled again.

00:07:27.600 --> 00:07:30.000
Reed thought they might defeat the ice

00:07:30.000 --> 00:07:32.279
wing so they kept fighting, but it wasn't

00:07:32.279 --> 00:07:33.180
worth the risk.

00:07:33.240 --> 00:07:36.000
Every moment was another opportunity for

00:07:36.000 --> 00:07:37.860
an ice wing to kill one of his brothers

00:07:37.860 --> 00:07:38.639
or sisters.

00:07:38.699 --> 00:07:41.040
Retreating meant keeping them alive.

00:07:41.100 --> 00:07:45.120
Retreat, he echoed the general, grabbing

00:07:45.120 --> 00:07:46.139
umber and pulling him back.

00:07:46.199 --> 00:07:47.459
Fall back.

00:07:47.519 --> 00:07:49.139
Pheasant, you too.

00:07:49.199 --> 00:07:51.480
He scanned the struggling shapes in the

00:07:51.480 --> 00:07:53.759
moonlight, and picked out his troop, all

00:07:53.759 --> 00:07:55.500
still alive, for now.

00:07:55.620 --> 00:07:58.379
His sister sank her teeth into her

00:07:58.379 --> 00:08:00.360
opponent's forearm, and he released her

00:08:00.360 --> 00:08:01.259
with a shriek of pain.

00:08:01.319 --> 00:08:04.860
In a flash, she was at Reed's side, and

00:08:04.860 --> 00:08:06.839
they soared up into the sky with Marsh

00:08:06.839 --> 00:08:08.639
Sora, and Umber right beside them.

00:08:08.699 --> 00:08:11.399
Reed saw the sand wings take off toward

00:08:11.399 --> 00:08:11.879
the mountains.

00:08:11.939 --> 00:08:14.160
Most of the ice wings shot after them.

00:08:14.220 --> 00:08:17.220
Only 2 turned to pursue him and his

00:08:17.220 --> 00:08:17.759
siblings.

00:08:17.819 --> 00:08:21.420
This way, he cried, diving for the

00:08:21.420 --> 00:08:21.779
forest.

00:08:21.839 --> 00:08:24.360
If ice wings could hide in there, so

00:08:24.360 --> 00:08:27.240
could his dragons, he wasn't obligated to

00:08:27.240 --> 00:08:28.199
follow the sand wings.

00:08:28.259 --> 00:08:30.360
They'd probably make a run for the Sky

00:08:30.360 --> 00:08:32.460
Palace anyway, and he didn't want to lead

00:08:32.460 --> 00:08:34.259
the ice wings back to his village.

00:08:34.679 --> 00:08:37.259
Pine branches whipped against his face as

00:08:37.259 --> 00:08:38.459
he hit the trees.

00:08:38.519 --> 00:08:40.620
His brothers and sisters had practiced a

00:08:40.620 --> 00:08:41.399
formation like this.

00:08:41.460 --> 00:08:43.860
Zipping through an overgrown forest while

00:08:43.860 --> 00:08:46.379
staying together, he had to trust that

00:08:46.379 --> 00:08:48.179
they'd remember and be close behind him.

00:08:48.240 --> 00:08:50.879
He heard the sound of thrashing wings

00:08:50.879 --> 00:08:53.159
farther back, and risked a glance over

00:08:53.159 --> 00:08:53.820
his shoulder.

00:08:53.879 --> 00:08:56.820
Even in the shadows, he recognized the

00:08:56.820 --> 00:08:58.379
shape of how his brothers and sisters

00:08:58.379 --> 00:08:58.799
flew.

00:08:58.860 --> 00:09:00.059
They were all there.

00:09:00.120 --> 00:09:02.700
It must be the ice wings who'd gotten

00:09:02.700 --> 00:09:03.779
caught in the upper branches.

00:09:03.840 --> 00:09:06.600
Reed took a chance and landed.

00:09:06.659 --> 00:09:09.240
The others dropped to the ground with him

00:09:09.240 --> 00:09:11.100
and they all immediately flattened

00:09:11.100 --> 00:09:13.019
themselves with wings outstretched

00:09:13.019 --> 00:09:15.059
becoming puddles of shadow on the dark

00:09:15.059 --> 00:09:15.779
forest floor.

00:09:15.840 --> 00:09:18.000
Silence fell.

00:09:18.059 --> 00:09:19.679
No one breathed.

00:09:19.799 --> 00:09:23.159
The branches creaked overhead, and small

00:09:23.159 --> 00:09:24.779
night animals skittered through the

00:09:24.779 --> 00:09:25.320
bushes around them.

00:09:25.379 --> 00:09:28.500
Reed felt a squirrel dart over his foot

00:09:28.500 --> 00:09:29.759
but he didn't move a muscle.

00:09:29.820 --> 00:09:33.720
After a long while, they heard a far away

00:09:33.720 --> 00:09:35.820
whistle, and the sound of wings in the

00:09:35.820 --> 00:09:37.860
distance, as if the ice wings had

00:09:37.860 --> 00:09:39.000
reassembled to fly away.

00:09:39.059 --> 00:09:41.399
Reed still didn't move.

00:09:41.460 --> 00:09:44.820
He waited for almost an hour until he

00:09:44.820 --> 00:09:46.919
couldn't hold his breath any longer, until

00:09:46.919 --> 00:09:49.139
any and all dragon noises had faded long

00:09:49.139 --> 00:09:49.379
ago.

00:09:49.440 --> 00:09:53.759
Then, very carefully and quietly, he

00:09:53.759 --> 00:09:55.980
inhaled, he heard the others do the

00:09:55.980 --> 00:09:56.159
same.

00:09:56.279 --> 00:09:58.559
Is anyone hurt?

00:09:58.679 --> 00:10:00.299
Reed asked softly.

00:10:00.360 --> 00:10:04.379
That was awful, Marsh whispered.

00:10:04.440 --> 00:10:06.059
I thought we were all going to die.

00:10:06.120 --> 00:10:09.240
I'm fine, Pheasant said.

00:10:09.299 --> 00:10:10.860
Nothing that won't heal soon.

00:10:10.919 --> 00:10:12.960
I'm all right, too.

00:10:13.019 --> 00:10:14.879
Sora said hoarsely.

00:10:14.940 --> 00:10:18.779
Umber, Reed said, when the smallest

00:10:18.779 --> 00:10:19.980
dragonette didn't respond.

00:10:20.039 --> 00:10:23.759
I hate this war, Umber burst out.

00:10:23.820 --> 00:10:25.740
I don't understand what we're even

00:10:25.740 --> 00:10:26.340
fighting for.

00:10:26.399 --> 00:10:29.340
Who cares who the sand wing queen is?

00:10:29.399 --> 00:10:31.919
I've never met Bern and I don't want to.

00:10:31.980 --> 00:10:34.559
Why am I fighting an ice wing over a

00:10:34.559 --> 00:10:36.600
throne that has nothing to do with either

00:10:36.600 --> 00:10:37.080
of us?

00:10:37.139 --> 00:10:40.259
Because our queen says we have to.

00:10:40.320 --> 00:10:43.799
Pheasant said, with a little more sarcasm

00:10:43.799 --> 00:10:45.779
than Reed thought was safe, even if there

00:10:45.779 --> 00:10:46.919
was no one to overhear.

00:10:46.980 --> 00:10:49.799
Queen Moorhead must have a good reason

00:10:49.799 --> 00:10:52.019
for aligning with Burne in the Sky Wings

00:10:52.019 --> 00:10:53.159
Reed said.

00:10:53.220 --> 00:10:54.120
We shouldn't doubt her.

00:10:54.179 --> 00:10:57.840
Besides, the war will be over soon.

00:10:57.899 --> 00:11:00.659
Sora said unexpectedly.

00:11:00.720 --> 00:11:04.500
She hardly ever spoke, and she'd spoken

00:11:04.500 --> 00:11:06.059
even less since Crane's death.

00:11:06.120 --> 00:11:09.480
Reed turned and saw her eyes reflecting

00:11:09.480 --> 00:11:10.379
the glow of the moonlight.

00:11:10.440 --> 00:11:13.139
Clay is going to end it.

00:11:13.200 --> 00:11:16.080
There was something about the way she

00:11:16.080 --> 00:11:18.480
said Clay's name that made Reed want to

00:11:18.480 --> 00:11:20.220
sink into a mud puddle and stay there for

00:11:20.220 --> 00:11:20.519
a month.

00:11:20.580 --> 00:11:23.580
She sounded as if she believed in him so

00:11:23.580 --> 00:11:23.759
much.

00:11:23.820 --> 00:11:26.039
A dragon they'd barely met.

00:11:26.100 --> 00:11:29.159
They followed Reed, and they loved him.

00:11:29.220 --> 00:11:30.120
He knew that.

00:11:30.179 --> 00:11:32.580
But surely they must wonder what could

00:11:32.580 --> 00:11:32.940
have been.

00:11:33.059 --> 00:11:36.419
And whether Crane might still be alive, if

00:11:36.419 --> 00:11:38.340
Clay were their big wings all along.

00:11:38.340 --> 00:11:42.779
That's true, Umber said, lifting his

00:11:42.779 --> 00:11:42.899
head.

00:11:42.960 --> 00:11:45.899
Clay and his friends, they're going to

00:11:45.899 --> 00:11:46.620
save us soon.

00:11:46.740 --> 00:11:48.600
How soon?

00:11:48.720 --> 00:11:50.039
Marsh asked.

00:11:50.159 --> 00:11:52.500
I thought the prophecy said 20 years.

00:11:52.559 --> 00:11:54.600
Doesn't that mean 2 more years before

00:11:54.600 --> 00:11:55.379
they end the war?

00:11:55.440 --> 00:11:58.620
Actually, Pheasant said.

00:11:58.679 --> 00:12:00.840
Some dragons think it depends on when you

00:12:00.840 --> 00:12:01.980
start counting.

00:12:02.039 --> 00:12:04.259
If you count from the 1st battle, then

00:12:04.259 --> 00:12:05.639
it's only been 18 years.

00:12:05.700 --> 00:12:07.559
But if you go back to the death of Queen

00:12:07.559 --> 00:12:09.720
Oasis, which is really when this whole

00:12:09.720 --> 00:12:12.360
thing started, then it's been almost 20.

00:12:12.720 --> 00:12:15.360
She caught the tilt of Reed's head and

00:12:15.360 --> 00:12:15.840
shrugged.

00:12:15.899 --> 00:12:18.240
I've been reading about the prophecy

00:12:18.240 --> 00:12:19.919
since we realized clay is in it.

00:12:19.980 --> 00:12:23.159
There was a pause, as they all had their

00:12:23.159 --> 00:12:24.360
own thoughts about clay.

00:12:24.419 --> 00:12:26.580
The war, and the prophecy.

00:12:26.639 --> 00:12:30.419
If you're all unhappy, Reed said

00:12:30.419 --> 00:12:35.100
tentatively, we could, I mean, we could

00:12:35.100 --> 00:12:36.659
try to find the talons of peace.

00:12:36.720 --> 00:12:39.360
Pheasant let out a shocked hiss.

00:12:39.480 --> 00:12:42.659
I may not like this war, but that doesn't

00:12:42.659 --> 00:12:43.980
mean we should leave our tribe and our

00:12:43.980 --> 00:12:44.340
home.

00:12:44.399 --> 00:12:45.899
We are mud wings.

00:12:45.960 --> 00:12:48.059
We belong in our village.

00:12:48.120 --> 00:12:51.000
Unless you think we should leave.

00:12:51.120 --> 00:12:54.480
Marsh said, leaning against Reed's side.

00:12:54.539 --> 00:12:56.340
I'll do whatever you decide.

00:12:56.399 --> 00:12:58.559
We all will.

00:12:58.620 --> 00:12:59.879
Umber said.

00:12:59.940 --> 00:13:03.419
Reed knew they would, but should they?

00:13:03.480 --> 00:13:05.159
He had no idea what to do.

00:13:05.220 --> 00:13:08.279
Betray his tribe or keep risking his

00:13:08.279 --> 00:13:09.299
siblings' lives.

00:13:09.360 --> 00:13:13.320
You don't have to decide tonight, Pheasant

00:13:13.320 --> 00:13:14.399
said, more gently.

00:13:14.460 --> 00:13:16.440
We just had a narrow escape.

00:13:16.500 --> 00:13:18.779
Let's go home and sleep.

00:13:18.840 --> 00:13:20.460
Will all feel better in the morning.

00:13:20.519 --> 00:13:24.179
Reed nodded, and they gathered themselves

00:13:24.179 --> 00:13:26.220
stretching their cramped wings as best

00:13:26.220 --> 00:13:27.419
they could under the trees.

00:13:27.480 --> 00:13:30.179
Showers of pine needles slid across their

00:13:30.179 --> 00:13:32.220
scales, smelling of winter fires.

00:13:32.279 --> 00:13:35.399
What were those ice wings doing here

00:13:35.399 --> 00:13:35.820
anyway?

00:13:35.879 --> 00:13:38.159
Marsh asked, stamping his feet.

00:13:38.279 --> 00:13:41.159
I have no idea, Reed said.

00:13:41.220 --> 00:13:42.960
It seemed as though they were lying in

00:13:42.960 --> 00:13:45.179
wait for us, but it's not like we're an

00:13:45.179 --> 00:13:45.899
important patrol.

00:13:46.019 --> 00:13:48.179
Perhaps they were here for something else

00:13:48.179 --> 00:13:50.159
and we were unlucky enough to attract

00:13:50.159 --> 00:13:50.580
their attention.

00:13:50.700 --> 00:13:53.700
Maybe they were here for the scavenger

00:13:53.700 --> 00:13:55.259
den, Umber said.

00:13:55.320 --> 00:13:57.779
What scavenger den?

00:13:57.840 --> 00:13:59.639
Reed glanced at him?

00:13:59.700 --> 00:14:00.360
Surprised?

00:14:00.419 --> 00:14:02.159
Can't you smell it?

00:14:02.220 --> 00:14:03.419
Umber asked.

00:14:03.480 --> 00:14:05.279
We flew over part of it too.

00:14:05.340 --> 00:14:07.379
It's pretty well hidden in the forest.

00:14:07.440 --> 00:14:10.799
How do you notice something like that in

00:14:10.799 --> 00:14:12.539
the middle of a frantic escape?

00:14:12.600 --> 00:14:13.799
Pheasant demanded.

00:14:13.860 --> 00:14:15.360
Umber shrugged.

00:14:15.419 --> 00:14:18.480
Why would the ice wings care about a

00:14:18.480 --> 00:14:19.440
scavenger den?

00:14:19.500 --> 00:14:21.120
Sora asked softly.

00:14:21.179 --> 00:14:23.519
They all thought for a moment, then

00:14:23.519 --> 00:14:24.240
looked at Reed.

00:14:24.299 --> 00:14:26.039
I don't know.

00:14:26.100 --> 00:14:27.779
He said helplessly.

00:14:27.899 --> 00:14:29.879
It felt like he was saying that all the

00:14:29.879 --> 00:14:30.659
time these days.

00:14:30.720 --> 00:14:34.620
Well, Pheasant said, spreading her

00:14:34.620 --> 00:14:35.580
wings.

00:14:35.639 --> 00:14:36.419
It doesn't matter.

00:14:36.480 --> 00:14:38.759
What matters is we survived another

00:14:38.759 --> 00:14:40.440
battle, thanks to Reed.

00:14:40.500 --> 00:14:45.179
I wonder if they really feel that way, he

00:14:45.179 --> 00:14:45.419
thought.

00:14:45.539 --> 00:14:47.279
I certainly don't.

00:14:47.340 --> 00:14:51.120
I hope we survived the next one, Marsh

00:14:51.120 --> 00:14:52.080
said gloomily.

00:14:52.200 --> 00:14:54.480
I hope we don't have to.

00:14:54.539 --> 00:14:55.860
Umber said.

00:14:55.919 --> 00:14:59.220
I hope Clay fulfills the prophecy and

00:14:59.220 --> 00:15:01.379
ends the war and saves the world really

00:15:01.379 --> 00:15:03.960
soon. before we have to do any more

00:15:03.960 --> 00:15:04.440
fighting.

00:15:04.500 --> 00:15:05.940
Don't you think?

00:15:06.000 --> 00:15:07.320
Maybe he will.

00:15:07.379 --> 00:15:09.480
Maybe.

00:15:09.539 --> 00:15:10.559
Pheasant said.

00:15:10.620 --> 00:15:11.820
I hope so.

00:15:11.879 --> 00:15:15.360
I do too, Reed said.

00:15:15.419 --> 00:15:17.340
He looked up at the stars.

00:15:17.399 --> 00:15:20.340
Before the war takes anyone else I care

00:15:20.340 --> 00:15:22.980
about. before our village is destroyed

00:15:22.980 --> 00:15:25.740
before I have to choose between loyalty

00:15:25.740 --> 00:15:27.840
to my tribe and the safety of my brothers

00:15:27.840 --> 00:15:28.320
and sisters.

00:15:28.440 --> 00:15:31.200
Before we have to kill anyone else.

00:15:31.259 --> 00:15:33.840
I hope so too.

00:15:33.899 --> 00:15:40.200
Part one, the secret plan.
420
00:15:40,259 --> 00:15:43,019	Chapter one.

00:15:43.080 --> 00:15:45.720
Where is she?

00:15:45.779 --> 00:15:48.779
Starflight suspected that he might be

00:15:48.779 --> 00:15:51.179
dead, except that everything hurts so

00:15:51.179 --> 00:15:53.940
much, darkness pressed against his eyes

00:15:53.940 --> 00:15:55.320
whenever he tried to open them.

00:15:55.379 --> 00:15:58.740
His nose and throat ached in a fierce, raw

00:15:58.740 --> 00:16:01.139
way as if they'd been scraped out with a

00:16:01.139 --> 00:16:01.919
crocodile tail.

00:16:01.980 --> 00:16:04.019
Is she all right?

00:16:04.080 --> 00:16:07.379
He couldn't remember what he'd dreamed

00:16:07.379 --> 00:16:07.980
and what was real?

00:16:08.039 --> 00:16:10.799
Perhaps he was still under the mountain.

00:16:10.919 --> 00:16:13.019
Perhaps his friends had never tried to

00:16:13.019 --> 00:16:13.980
escape their guardians.

00:16:14.039 --> 00:16:17.340
Maybe this was one long nightmare that

00:16:17.340 --> 00:16:19.500
had started with a threat of Maru Seer's

00:16:19.500 --> 00:16:19.679
visit.

00:16:19.740 --> 00:16:22.019
But Starflight was sure he could remember

00:16:22.019 --> 00:16:23.940
the large night wing taking him aside.

00:16:24.000 --> 00:16:27.299
There was a lecture about how Nightwings

00:16:27.299 --> 00:16:29.580
have a reputation to uphold, and

00:16:29.580 --> 00:16:33.179
Nightwings are natural leaders, and you

00:16:33.179 --> 00:16:35.399
must make the others respect you, fear

00:16:35.399 --> 00:16:37.679
you, and follow you, or you'll be the

00:16:37.679 --> 00:16:39.419
greatest disappointment our tribe has

00:16:39.419 --> 00:16:39.960
ever produced.

00:16:40.080 --> 00:16:42.840
Starflight couldn't have conjured that

00:16:42.840 --> 00:16:43.559
from his own brain.

00:16:43.620 --> 00:16:46.019
That was all real.

00:16:46.200 --> 00:16:49.320
He crawled onto his side and felt jagged

00:16:49.320 --> 00:16:50.580
rocks press into his scales.

00:16:50.700 --> 00:16:53.159
Was the Skywing Palace reel?

00:16:53.220 --> 00:16:55.799
The dragonettes captured before even

00:16:55.799 --> 00:16:56.879
tasting sunlight?

00:16:56.940 --> 00:17:00.059
The prison on the tower of rock, the

00:17:00.059 --> 00:17:02.639
baking hot arena sands that smelled of

00:17:02.639 --> 00:17:03.600
blood and terror.

00:17:03.659 --> 00:17:06.720
Queen Scarlet's delight at capturing him

00:17:06.720 --> 00:17:09.480
a real night wing out in the world, and

00:17:09.480 --> 00:17:11.700
her plans to make him fight, and her

00:17:11.700 --> 00:17:13.319
excitement about the prospect of watching

00:17:13.319 --> 00:17:13.740
him die.

00:17:13.859 --> 00:17:18.119
No, that had to be real, because

00:17:18.119 --> 00:17:20.459
Starflight remembered being rescued by

00:17:20.459 --> 00:17:21.239
the night wings.

00:17:21.299 --> 00:17:23.700
He remembered watching his friends turn

00:17:23.700 --> 00:17:26.579
into small dots below him, blue and brown

00:17:26.579 --> 00:17:29.160
and bright, and he knew it was real

00:17:29.160 --> 00:17:32.940
because it felt so much like this felt, as

00:17:32.940 --> 00:17:34.920
if he were a scroll ripped in half down

00:17:34.920 --> 00:17:37.200
the middle, so none of the words made any

00:17:37.200 --> 00:17:37.799
sense anymore.

00:17:37.859 --> 00:17:40.920
Will I ever see her again?

00:17:40.980 --> 00:17:43.259
I hope she's not here.

00:17:43.319 --> 00:17:45.180
I hope she's safe somewhere.

00:17:45.240 --> 00:17:47.940
I think there's something wrong with

00:17:47.940 --> 00:17:48.180
him.

00:17:48.240 --> 00:17:49.920
Was that a voice?

00:17:50.039 --> 00:17:52.920
He tried to listen, but his dreams

00:17:52.920 --> 00:17:54.119
dragged him back down.

00:17:54.180 --> 00:17:56.880
There had been another stern lecture for

00:17:56.880 --> 00:17:57.720
Morrow Seer.

00:17:57.779 --> 00:18:00.480
It was essential for Starflight to be the

00:18:00.480 --> 00:18:01.799
leader of the Dragonettes.

00:18:01.859 --> 00:18:04.259
Everything depended on him.

00:18:04.380 --> 00:18:06.900
And a new order.

00:18:06.960 --> 00:18:09.480
He must convince the others to choose

00:18:09.480 --> 00:18:11.819
blister as the next sandwing queen.

00:18:11.880 --> 00:18:15.180
Maybe, they killed him by accident.

00:18:15.240 --> 00:18:16.440
That'd be all right.

00:18:16.500 --> 00:18:19.019
Maybe I'll get to be in the prophecy

00:18:19.019 --> 00:18:19.319
instead.

00:18:19.380 --> 00:18:23.039
I don't think that's how it works, fierce

00:18:23.039 --> 00:18:23.400
teeth.

00:18:23.460 --> 00:18:26.279
And then there was the kingdom of the

00:18:26.279 --> 00:18:26.460
sea.

00:18:26.579 --> 00:18:28.380
No one would listen to him.

00:18:28.440 --> 00:18:29.940
He couldn't lead anyone.

00:18:30.000 --> 00:18:32.220
His friend practically laughed at him

00:18:32.220 --> 00:18:33.720
when he tried to support blister.

00:18:33.779 --> 00:18:35.099
Another prison.

00:18:35.160 --> 00:18:38.099
Another escape where Starflight did just

00:18:38.099 --> 00:18:40.440
about nothing to help, and then the

00:18:40.440 --> 00:18:42.839
rainforest, and the strange, unnatural

00:18:42.839 --> 00:18:45.720
tunnels, one to the kingdom of sand, and

00:18:45.720 --> 00:18:48.720
one, apparently, to the secret home of

00:18:48.720 --> 00:18:49.500
the night wings.

00:18:49.559 --> 00:18:52.200
That, Starflight remembered.

00:18:52.259 --> 00:18:54.779
He remembered staring up at it.

00:18:54.839 --> 00:18:57.480
The dark hole in the tree that led to a

00:18:57.480 --> 00:18:58.440
home he'd never seen.

00:18:58.500 --> 00:19:01.920
I bet he'd wake up if I bit him.

00:19:01.980 --> 00:19:05.339
I bet Morrow seer would throw you in the

00:19:05.339 --> 00:19:07.380
volcano if he found toothmarks on his

00:19:07.380 --> 00:19:08.279
prophecy pet.

00:19:08.339 --> 00:19:11.160
I bet my mum would have him for lunch if

00:19:11.160 --> 00:19:11.640
he tried.

00:19:11.700 --> 00:19:14.279
He was definitely hearing voices.

00:19:14.339 --> 00:19:16.740
Unfamiliar voices very close by.

00:19:16.799 --> 00:19:19.319
The memory of the rainforest was

00:19:19.319 --> 00:19:19.859
blurring.

00:19:19.920 --> 00:19:22.079
Starflight tried to fix his mind on it.

00:19:22.140 --> 00:19:24.660
On those last moments, guarding the

00:19:24.660 --> 00:19:26.220
tunnel so the night wings wouldn't come

00:19:26.220 --> 00:19:27.779
through and attack the rain wings.

00:19:27.839 --> 00:19:29.039
What had happened?

00:19:29.099 --> 00:19:33.000
Well, he'd better wake up and be

00:19:33.000 --> 00:19:35.519
interesting soon, or Mo see it will take

00:19:35.519 --> 00:19:37.140
him away again before we get to ask him

00:19:37.140 --> 00:19:37.440
anything.

00:19:37.500 --> 00:19:40.980
Ooh, I have an idea.

00:19:41.099 --> 00:19:44.220
Claus scrabbled on rock, and then there

00:19:44.220 --> 00:19:44.759
was quiet.

00:19:44.819 --> 00:19:47.400
Starflights eyelids felt too heavy to

00:19:47.400 --> 00:19:50.039
open, as if extra scales were piled on

00:19:50.039 --> 00:19:50.579
top of them.

00:19:50.640 --> 00:19:52.920
He let the darkness drift up over him

00:19:52.920 --> 00:19:53.160
again.

00:19:53.220 --> 00:19:57.599
Right, guarding the hole with clay.

00:19:57.660 --> 00:20:00.059
Morning sunbeams flickering through the

00:20:00.059 --> 00:20:02.279
green leaves, octopus blue flowers

00:20:02.279 --> 00:20:03.839
turning their heads up to the light.

00:20:03.900 --> 00:20:06.720
Sunny was back in the village, with

00:20:06.720 --> 00:20:09.240
tsunami, watching glory try to become

00:20:09.240 --> 00:20:11.460
queen of the rain wings, of all things.

00:20:11.519 --> 00:20:13.920
Sonny had brought them food the night

00:20:13.920 --> 00:20:16.440
before, her golden scales brushing

00:20:16.440 --> 00:20:18.480
against his dark wings as she passed him

00:20:18.480 --> 00:20:20.220
strange little purple fruits.

00:20:20.279 --> 00:20:23.819
I love you, he would never say.

00:20:23.880 --> 00:20:26.339
Don't hate me because of what the other

00:20:26.339 --> 00:20:27.359
night wings have done.

00:20:27.420 --> 00:20:29.579
Don't think I'm like my tribe.

00:20:29.640 --> 00:20:32.339
Don't listen to Glory's description of my

00:20:32.339 --> 00:20:35.220
kingdom, the smoke and the fire, and the

00:20:35.220 --> 00:20:37.680
smell and the death, and the trapped

00:20:37.680 --> 00:20:40.380
tortured rain wings, and the cruel black

00:20:40.380 --> 00:20:40.740
dragons.

00:20:40.859 --> 00:20:43.019
Don't look at me like I'm one of them.

00:20:43.079 --> 00:20:45.420
Like I could ever do what they've done.

00:20:45.480 --> 00:20:46.500
Please.

00:20:46.559 --> 00:20:49.799
And then she'd glanced up at him and

00:20:49.799 --> 00:20:52.559
smiled, and in Sonny's eyes, he could see

00:20:52.559 --> 00:20:55.440
himself as Starflight, just find the way

00:20:55.440 --> 00:20:55.859
he was.

00:20:55.980 --> 00:20:57.420
Her friend.

00:20:57.480 --> 00:21:00.599
Which made everything better and worse

00:21:00.599 --> 00:21:01.980
all at the same time.

00:21:02.039 --> 00:21:03.900
Careful.

00:21:03.960 --> 00:21:05.880
Oh, I'm not going back for more of you

00:21:05.880 --> 00:21:06.720
spill it, idiot.

00:21:06.779 --> 00:21:09.480
Get your great honking wings out of my

00:21:09.480 --> 00:21:10.440
way then, fathead.

00:21:10.500 --> 00:21:12.359
The voices again.

00:21:12.420 --> 00:21:15.059
Starflight caught at the memories, trying

00:21:15.059 --> 00:21:16.500
to remember the last thing that had

00:21:16.500 --> 00:21:17.940
happened before everything went dark.

00:21:18.000 --> 00:21:21.000
He'd been staring at the hole, wondering

00:21:21.000 --> 00:21:22.619
what the other night wings were really

00:21:22.619 --> 00:21:25.079
like, wondering if they were all as scary

00:21:25.079 --> 00:21:26.400
as morrow seer.

00:21:26.460 --> 00:21:28.799
Wondering if he went through and talked

00:21:28.799 --> 00:21:30.720
to them, whether they would listen.

00:21:30.779 --> 00:21:33.359
What if he could stop the night wings and

00:21:33.359 --> 00:21:34.500
rain wings from fighting?

00:21:34.559 --> 00:21:37.440
What if his tribe understood him and

00:21:37.440 --> 00:21:38.220
believed in him?

00:21:38.279 --> 00:21:40.259
What if they thought it was better to be

00:21:40.259 --> 00:21:41.460
smart than brave?

00:21:41.519 --> 00:21:43.740
What if they didn't care that he had no

00:21:43.740 --> 00:21:45.180
special night wing powers?

00:21:45.240 --> 00:21:48.119
What would Sonny think of me then?

00:21:48.180 --> 00:21:51.720
She'd probably think, who are you?

00:21:51.779 --> 00:21:53.700
And what have you done with Starflight?

00:21:53.759 --> 00:21:56.460
Because there was no way he'd ever be

00:21:56.460 --> 00:21:58.140
brave enough to go through that tunnel on

00:21:58.140 --> 00:21:58.500
his own.

00:21:58.559 --> 00:22:01.920
And then Clay had yelped, did you see

00:22:01.920 --> 00:22:02.099
that?

00:22:02.160 --> 00:22:03.779
I think it was a boar.

00:22:03.839 --> 00:22:04.859
I'll be right back.

00:22:04.980 --> 00:22:08.160
And poor Ever Hungry Clay had charged off

00:22:08.160 --> 00:22:10.559
into the trees, leaving Starflight to

00:22:10.559 --> 00:22:11.339
watch the hole alone.

00:22:11.400 --> 00:22:15.359
In a heartbeat, Dark Wings had boiled out

00:22:15.359 --> 00:22:16.380
of the hole.

00:22:16.440 --> 00:22:18.960
Dark claws had circled his snout.

00:22:19.019 --> 00:22:21.059
A dark voice had hissed in his ear.

00:22:21.119 --> 00:22:22.559
Silence.

00:22:22.619 --> 00:22:24.900
If you want your friend to live.

00:22:25.019 --> 00:22:28.920
Another dark voice, better saved than

00:22:28.920 --> 00:22:29.400
sorry.

00:22:29.519 --> 00:22:32.400
Although he had made a sound, and he'd

00:22:32.400 --> 00:22:33.900
known it would hurt right before the blow

00:22:33.900 --> 00:22:36.480
struck his head, and pain blazed through

00:22:36.480 --> 00:22:38.700
him, and that was the last thing he

00:22:38.700 --> 00:22:40.440
splash.

00:22:40.500 --> 00:22:44.039
Starflight jolted up with a yell, his

00:22:44.039 --> 00:22:46.680
eyes popped open, freezing salt water

00:22:46.680 --> 00:22:49.259
cascaded over his snout, and snaked down

00:22:49.259 --> 00:22:51.299
his neck, seeping into his scales.

00:22:51.359 --> 00:22:54.119
The muddled, heavy feeling vanished in an

00:22:54.119 --> 00:22:54.779
instant.

00:22:54.839 --> 00:22:57.779
It worked, cheered one of the unfamiliar

00:22:57.779 --> 00:22:58.440
voices.

00:22:58.500 --> 00:23:00.839
Trat, said another.

00:23:00.900 --> 00:23:02.700
I really thought he was dead.

00:23:02.759 --> 00:23:05.400
Starflight shook his head, and the pain

00:23:05.400 --> 00:23:06.720
ricocheted around inside.

00:23:06.839 --> 00:23:09.779
He rubbed at a snout, trying to clear the

00:23:09.779 --> 00:23:12.960
ocean water from his stinging eyes. 6 or

00:23:12.960 --> 00:23:15.480
7 or maybe 8 dark blurry shapes

00:23:15.480 --> 00:23:16.200
surrounded him.

00:23:16.259 --> 00:23:19.799
Beyond them, glowing red light pulsed in

00:23:19.799 --> 00:23:20.819
lines along the walls.

00:23:20.880 --> 00:23:23.400
The freezing water had cleared his nose

00:23:23.400 --> 00:23:26.039
for a moment, but heavy smoky air was

00:23:26.039 --> 00:23:27.000
already pressing back in.

00:23:27.059 --> 00:23:29.460
Who are you?

00:23:29.519 --> 00:23:31.799
Starflight gasped or tried to?

00:23:31.920 --> 00:23:33.599
Huh.

00:23:33.660 --> 00:23:36.779
I thought he might attack us, said a 3rd

00:23:36.779 --> 00:23:37.079
voice.

00:23:37.200 --> 00:23:38.579
That's what I would do.

00:23:38.640 --> 00:23:42.539
He doesn't look very dangerous, said

00:23:42.539 --> 00:23:43.799
another voice skeptically.

00:23:43.859 --> 00:23:46.140
They should have picked someone bigger

00:23:46.140 --> 00:23:47.099
don't you think?

00:23:47.160 --> 00:23:49.859
Bigger, and scarier, and fiercer.

00:23:49.920 --> 00:23:54.059
Like me. said the voice, who had hoped

00:23:54.059 --> 00:23:54.900
Starflight was dead.

00:23:54.960 --> 00:23:59.279
You all have tiny rain wing brains.

00:23:59.339 --> 00:24:01.019
Said yet another voice.

00:24:01.079 --> 00:24:02.880
Starfly was losing count.

00:24:02.940 --> 00:24:05.579
He was still inside his egg when they

00:24:05.579 --> 00:24:05.940
took him.

00:24:06.000 --> 00:24:08.460
They didn't know if he'd be big or scary

00:24:08.460 --> 00:24:11.579
or even if he'd be male or female.

00:24:11.640 --> 00:24:13.440
Otherwise, of course, they would have

00:24:13.440 --> 00:24:14.579
picked a girl, obviously.

00:24:14.640 --> 00:24:17.160
Like me.

00:24:17.279 --> 00:24:19.799
Hello?

00:24:19.859 --> 00:24:21.299
Starflight coughed.

00:24:21.359 --> 00:24:22.319
Hello?

00:24:22.380 --> 00:24:25.319
One of the shapes came close enough for

00:24:25.319 --> 00:24:27.299
him to make out the features. of a

00:24:27.299 --> 00:24:29.460
disgruntled looking dragonette a year or

00:24:29.460 --> 00:24:30.660
2 older than himself.

00:24:30.779 --> 00:24:33.180
She poked at his mouth and peered at his

00:24:33.180 --> 00:24:35.880
teeth, jabbed at his chest so he coughed

00:24:35.880 --> 00:24:38.700
again, inspected his claws, and sighed

00:24:38.700 --> 00:24:39.119
huffily.

00:24:39.180 --> 00:24:41.579
Weak, she declared.

00:24:41.640 --> 00:24:43.440
I'd have sent him back too.

00:24:43.500 --> 00:24:47.279
You're just saying that because you're

00:24:47.279 --> 00:24:49.980
hoping they'll pick you instead, said

00:24:49.980 --> 00:24:51.539
another dragonette, pushing forward.

00:24:51.660 --> 00:24:54.299
He padded Starflight's head in an almost

00:24:54.299 --> 00:24:54.960
friendly way.

00:24:55.019 --> 00:24:58.319
But prophecies don't work like that.

00:24:58.380 --> 00:25:02.039
We'll see, she muttered.

00:25:02.099 --> 00:25:05.880
That's fierce teeth, said the friendlier

00:25:05.880 --> 00:25:07.019
dragonette to Starflight.

00:25:07.079 --> 00:25:08.160
Don't mind her.

00:25:08.220 --> 00:25:10.859
Older sisters always think they can do

00:25:10.859 --> 00:25:12.420
whatever you're doing better than you

00:25:12.420 --> 00:25:13.019
can.

00:25:13.079 --> 00:25:13.740
I know.

00:25:13.799 --> 00:25:14.519
I've got one too.

00:25:14.640 --> 00:25:17.039
I'm mighty Claus, by the way.

00:25:17.160 --> 00:25:19.500
Older sister?

00:25:19.559 --> 00:25:22.200
Starfly echoed, blinking at fierce

00:25:22.200 --> 00:25:22.500
teeth.

00:25:22.619 --> 00:25:23.759
Yes.

00:25:23.819 --> 00:25:27.180
This is the touching family reunion

00:25:27.180 --> 00:25:27.599
part.

00:25:27.720 --> 00:25:28.619
She said.

00:25:28.680 --> 00:25:30.599
Say mother, different fathers, we

00:25:30.599 --> 00:25:30.960
assume.

00:25:31.019 --> 00:25:32.579
How do you feel?

00:25:32.640 --> 00:25:35.160
She eyed him from horns to tail.

00:25:35.220 --> 00:25:37.619
Ill, very ill.

00:25:37.740 --> 00:25:39.720
Dying, perhaps?

00:25:39.779 --> 00:25:43.140
What part of brightest night are you

00:25:43.140 --> 00:25:43.920
having trouble with?

00:25:44.039 --> 00:25:46.200
Said another dragonette behind fierce

00:25:46.200 --> 00:25:46.500
teeth.

00:25:46.559 --> 00:25:48.599
Haven't you been listening in class?

00:25:48.660 --> 00:25:50.759
Events have to march the prophecies.

00:25:50.819 --> 00:25:53.880
Hi, strange dragon, I'm mind reader, but

00:25:53.880 --> 00:25:54.420
don't worry.

00:25:54.480 --> 00:25:56.279
I promise I'll stay out of your head.

00:25:56.400 --> 00:25:58.920
The older dragonette's in the room

00:25:58.920 --> 00:26:01.259
laughed uproariously, as if this was the

00:26:01.259 --> 00:26:03.420
most hilarious joke in Pyrea history.

00:26:03.480 --> 00:26:05.759
The 3 dragonettes who looked younger than

00:26:05.759 --> 00:26:07.980
Starfly rolled their eyes, like they were

00:26:07.980 --> 00:26:09.480
used to hearing jokes that made no sense

00:26:09.480 --> 00:26:10.140
from that group.

00:26:10.200 --> 00:26:12.779
Starflight rubbed his wet scales

00:26:12.779 --> 00:26:13.440
confused.

00:26:13.559 --> 00:26:16.440
Now that his site was clearing, he could

00:26:16.440 --> 00:26:18.660
see that he was in a long, narrow cave

00:26:18.660 --> 00:26:20.880
lined with indentations in the rock at

00:26:20.880 --> 00:26:23.519
regular intervals, all the right size for

00:26:23.519 --> 00:26:24.539
dragonette beds.

00:26:24.599 --> 00:26:27.599
He was curled on one of these, not far

00:26:27.599 --> 00:26:29.400
from a large archway that seemed to be

00:26:29.400 --> 00:26:30.539
the only exit from the room.

00:26:30.599 --> 00:26:33.359
Next to him on the floor was a large

00:26:33.359 --> 00:26:35.640
hollow stone, which was apparently what

00:26:35.640 --> 00:26:37.319
the dragonettes had used to collect the

00:26:37.319 --> 00:26:39.180
seawater they'd just poured all over

00:26:39.180 --> 00:26:39.420
him.

00:26:39.480 --> 00:26:41.640
It didn't look like a prison.

00:26:41.700 --> 00:26:43.920
It looked like a dormitory.

00:26:44.039 --> 00:26:47.519
Hot coals smoldered in alcoves in the

00:26:47.519 --> 00:26:49.559
walls, lending a red glow to the room.

00:26:49.680 --> 00:26:52.319
A skylight at each end of a cave allowed

00:26:52.319 --> 00:26:54.180
a bit of dim gray light to filter in.

00:26:54.240 --> 00:26:57.059
There were at least 50 sleeping spots

00:26:57.059 --> 00:26:59.460
that Starflight could see, but only about

00:26:59.460 --> 00:27:00.960
11 of them looked slept in.

00:27:01.019 --> 00:27:03.660
Several had rough blankets heaped on them

00:27:03.660 --> 00:27:05.759
in messy piles, while others were

00:27:05.759 --> 00:27:07.380
scattered with objects that looked like

00:27:07.380 --> 00:27:09.539
seashells and twisted bits of rock.

00:27:09.599 --> 00:27:12.180
A few of the blanket covered beds had a

00:27:12.180 --> 00:27:14.160
scroll lying next to them, which made

00:27:14.160 --> 00:27:16.319
Starflights claws itch with longing.

00:27:16.380 --> 00:27:18.240
But most of the beds were completely

00:27:18.240 --> 00:27:18.720
bare.

00:27:18.839 --> 00:27:22.440
Places for dragonettes, but no

00:27:22.440 --> 00:27:23.759
dragonettes to fill them.

00:27:23.819 --> 00:27:27.420
Starflight remembered something Maro Seer

00:27:27.420 --> 00:27:29.579
had said offhandedly, shortly after

00:27:29.579 --> 00:27:31.680
rescuing Starflight from the Sky Wings.

00:27:31.740 --> 00:27:35.519
He said, We can't afford to lose any

00:27:35.519 --> 00:27:36.299
night wings.

00:27:36.359 --> 00:27:39.000
Even peculiar little ones.

00:27:39.059 --> 00:27:42.779
Maybe there is something wrong with my

00:27:42.779 --> 00:27:43.019
tribe.

00:27:43.200 --> 00:27:44.579
Starflight thought.

00:27:44.640 --> 00:27:47.759
Maybe they're losing Dragonette somehow.

00:27:47.880 --> 00:27:50.339
Or not having enough of them in the 1st

00:27:50.339 --> 00:27:50.579
place.

00:27:50.700 --> 00:27:53.940
Everything smelled like sulfur and

00:27:53.940 --> 00:27:54.779
decaying animals.

00:27:54.839 --> 00:27:57.599
As fierce teeth leaned over and jabbed

00:27:57.599 --> 00:27:58.319
his stomach again.

00:27:58.380 --> 00:28:00.960
Starflight realized that a lot of the

00:28:00.960 --> 00:28:02.400
decaying smell came from the

00:28:02.400 --> 00:28:03.119
dragonettes.

00:28:03.180 --> 00:28:05.880
They all had horrendously bad breath.

00:28:05.940 --> 00:28:08.160
Moro Seaer's breath had never been

00:28:08.160 --> 00:28:10.140
wonderful either, but this was much

00:28:10.140 --> 00:28:10.440
worse.

00:28:10.500 --> 00:28:13.319
It took all of Starflight's willpower not

00:28:13.319 --> 00:28:14.700
to recoil when they spoke to him.

00:28:14.759 --> 00:28:17.519
They were all so shockingly thin.

00:28:17.579 --> 00:28:20.400
Every one of them with narrow chests

00:28:20.400 --> 00:28:22.559
bloodshot eyes, and hacking coughs.

00:28:22.619 --> 00:28:25.859
Even the dragonettes who survive are in

00:28:25.859 --> 00:28:26.759
pretty bad shape.

00:28:26.819 --> 00:28:28.859
Starflight thought.

00:28:28.920 --> 00:28:31.859
He stretched gingerly, eyeing the door.

00:28:31.920 --> 00:28:34.079
It didn't seem to be barricaded in any

00:28:34.079 --> 00:28:34.319
way.

00:28:34.380 --> 00:28:37.440
As far as Starflight could tell, he could

00:28:37.440 --> 00:28:39.240
walk right out into the caves beyond.

00:28:39.299 --> 00:28:43.859
There's probably a guard, he thought, or

00:28:43.859 --> 00:28:46.440
lots of guards, or maybe something really

00:28:46.440 --> 00:28:49.200
creepy, like Queen Coral's electric

00:28:49.200 --> 00:28:49.920
eels.

00:28:49.980 --> 00:28:53.339
Or a lava river, like the one that keeps

00:28:53.339 --> 00:28:55.019
the rain wings trapped in their prison

00:28:55.019 --> 00:28:55.740
caves.

00:28:55.799 --> 00:28:58.440
A shiver of fear ran down his spine.

00:28:58.500 --> 00:29:00.720
Why am I here?

00:29:00.779 --> 00:29:01.799
He blurted.

00:29:01.859 --> 00:29:04.799
The little crowd of dragonettes exchanged

00:29:04.799 --> 00:29:05.460
glances.

00:29:05.519 --> 00:29:09.779
Because you failed, fierce teeth offered

00:29:09.779 --> 00:29:11.099
I assume.

00:29:11.880 --> 00:29:14.700
We don't know that. mighty Claus

00:29:14.700 --> 00:29:17.460
interjected, a couple of the big dragons

00:29:17.460 --> 00:29:19.440
dropped you here a few hours ago, and

00:29:19.440 --> 00:29:21.000
you've been muttering and thrashing

00:29:21.000 --> 00:29:21.900
around ever since.

00:29:21.960 --> 00:29:26.579
Yeah, lots of worrying about Sonny, who's

00:29:26.579 --> 00:29:26.819
Sonny?

00:29:26.940 --> 00:29:28.859
One of the other dragonets demanded.

00:29:28.920 --> 00:29:31.380
Starfight considered throwing himself

00:29:31.380 --> 00:29:32.279
into the volcano.

00:29:32.339 --> 00:29:35.579
Another dragonette, he mumbled.

00:29:35.640 --> 00:29:37.380
I hope she's safe.

00:29:37.440 --> 00:29:40.319
I want to hear about the mainland.

00:29:40.380 --> 00:29:42.180
Mind reader said eagerly.

00:29:42.240 --> 00:29:43.980
Tell us everything.

00:29:44.039 --> 00:29:46.859
We've heard there are trees taller than

00:29:46.859 --> 00:29:49.259
dragons, and that in some places, the sky

00:29:49.259 --> 00:29:49.859
is blue.

00:29:49.920 --> 00:29:50.880
True?

00:29:50.880 --> 00:29:51.960
False?

00:29:52.019 --> 00:29:54.119
What's the coolest thing you've seen?

00:29:54.180 --> 00:29:55.980
What's the best thing you've eaten?

00:29:56.039 --> 00:29:59.279
You've never been to the mainland?

00:29:59.339 --> 00:30:00.599
Starflight said.

00:30:00.720 --> 00:30:03.660
Dragonettes aren't allowed to leave the

00:30:03.660 --> 00:30:06.420
island until we're 10 years old, Mighty

00:30:06.420 --> 00:30:06.960
Claus said.

00:30:07.019 --> 00:30:09.539
Apparently we can't be trusted to keep

00:30:09.539 --> 00:30:11.339
all the night wing secrets until then.

00:30:11.400 --> 00:30:15.059
Almost in unison, all the dragonettes

00:30:15.059 --> 00:30:16.259
snorted impatiently.

00:30:16.380 --> 00:30:19.019
You're the only exception.

00:30:19.140 --> 00:30:22.019
Fierce teeth said, in a voice dripping

00:30:22.019 --> 00:30:22.559
with scorn.

00:30:22.680 --> 00:30:26.880
Him and the other one, Mind Reader said.

00:30:26.940 --> 00:30:28.740
I heard my mom say there was another.

00:30:28.799 --> 00:30:32.099
I don't know any night wing secrets

00:30:32.099 --> 00:30:33.180
Starflight said.

00:30:33.240 --> 00:30:35.940
Oh, said mighty Claus.

00:30:36.000 --> 00:30:37.980
I guess that's one way to make sure you

00:30:37.980 --> 00:30:38.339
keep them.

00:30:38.400 --> 00:30:41.519
The scrabble of claws in the hall outside

00:30:41.519 --> 00:30:44.160
heralded the appearance. of a dragonette

00:30:44.160 --> 00:30:46.440
smaller than the others, perhaps 3 years

00:30:46.440 --> 00:30:47.099
old.

00:30:47.160 --> 00:30:49.799
She raced into the room and gasped, he's

00:30:49.799 --> 00:30:50.039
coming.

00:30:50.099 --> 00:30:53.279
Immediately the dragonettes scattered to

00:30:53.279 --> 00:30:54.779
their sleeping spots.

00:30:54.839 --> 00:30:56.579
Half of them dove into their blankets and

00:30:56.579 --> 00:30:57.539
pretended to be asleep.

00:30:57.599 --> 00:31:00.000
A few of them grabbed their scrolls and

00:31:00.000 --> 00:31:00.779
looked studious.

00:31:00.839 --> 00:31:03.240
Others fussed busily with the objects

00:31:03.240 --> 00:31:03.900
around their beds.

00:31:03.960 --> 00:31:07.319
Fierce teeth sat down on her bed, folded

00:31:07.319 --> 00:31:09.299
her wings, and glared at the doorway.

00:31:09.359 --> 00:31:12.180
Starflight wished he was unconscious

00:31:12.180 --> 00:31:14.339
again, as he heard heavy footsteps

00:31:14.339 --> 00:31:16.740
tramping toward the room, he glanced up

00:31:16.740 --> 00:31:18.660
at the skylight, wondering if he could

00:31:18.660 --> 00:31:20.279
fit through it, but knowing perfectly

00:31:20.279 --> 00:31:21.900
well he was too terrified to try.

00:31:22.019 --> 00:31:26.039
With a scraping, hissing sound, Maro Seer

00:31:26.039 --> 00:31:26.819
slithered into the room.

00:31:26.880 --> 00:31:29.759
He frowned at fierce teeth, then looked

00:31:29.759 --> 00:31:32.099
coldly down his long nose at Starflight.

00:31:32.160 --> 00:31:35.039
Up, he snarled.

00:31:35.099 --> 00:31:38.400
The queen of the night wings wants to see

00:31:38.400 --> 00:31:38.700
you.
875
00:31:38,819 --> 00:31:43,140	Chapter 2.

00:31:43.380 --> 00:31:47.519
Starflights experience with Dragon Queens

00:31:47.519 --> 00:31:49.079
thus far, had not been exactly

00:31:49.079 --> 00:31:49.680
wonderful.

00:31:49.740 --> 00:31:51.839
Me?

00:31:51.900 --> 00:31:52.799
He stammered.

00:31:52.920 --> 00:31:53.700
Now?

00:31:53.759 --> 00:31:55.259
You mean right now?

00:31:55.319 --> 00:31:56.579
Shouldn't I?

00:31:57.000 --> 00:32:00.119
I mean, I'm not really prepared to, or I

00:32:00.119 --> 00:32:02.460
I don't really look to see a queen.

00:32:02.519 --> 00:32:06.839
I mean, maybe stop blithering and follow

00:32:06.839 --> 00:32:07.259
me.

00:32:07.319 --> 00:32:10.259
Morosira swept out of the cave with a

00:32:10.259 --> 00:32:10.619
growl.

00:32:10.680 --> 00:32:13.019
Go, go, go.

00:32:13.079 --> 00:32:15.900
Mighty Claus hissed, flapping his wings

00:32:15.900 --> 00:32:17.099
as Starflight hesitated.

00:32:17.220 --> 00:32:20.460
Starflights claws caught on small holes

00:32:20.460 --> 00:32:23.279
on the rocky floor, and he stumbled as he

00:32:23.279 --> 00:32:24.839
chased after the giant night wing.

00:32:24.900 --> 00:32:29.160
Volcanic rock, he thought, peering at the

00:32:29.160 --> 00:32:29.759
walls around him.

00:32:29.819 --> 00:32:32.279
I wonder when it last erupted.

00:32:32.339 --> 00:32:35.400
From the rumbling under his talons, and

00:32:35.400 --> 00:32:37.500
the heat rising through the floor, it

00:32:37.500 --> 00:32:39.000
didn't seem like the most dormant

00:32:39.000 --> 00:32:39.539
volcano.

00:32:39.599 --> 00:32:42.839
Moro Seer led the way up a winding tunnel

00:32:42.839 --> 00:32:43.440
without looking back.

00:32:43.500 --> 00:32:47.279
My friends, Starflight started to say

00:32:47.279 --> 00:32:50.160
Sonny and the others, are they?

00:32:50.339 --> 00:32:52.200
The large black dragon didn't turn

00:32:52.200 --> 00:32:52.440
around.

00:32:52.500 --> 00:32:55.380
Starflight kept walking for a few minutes

00:32:55.380 --> 00:32:57.660
then took a deep breath and tried again.

00:32:57.720 --> 00:32:59.339
When can I go back?

00:32:59.400 --> 00:33:02.880
His only answer was a snort of disgust.

00:33:02.940 --> 00:33:05.700
Starflight swallowed his questions, and

00:33:05.700 --> 00:33:06.960
nervously tucked his wings in.

00:33:07.019 --> 00:33:08.880
The walls felt like they were getting

00:33:08.880 --> 00:33:09.359
closer.

00:33:09.420 --> 00:33:12.839
He didn't see any guards, or rivers of

00:33:12.839 --> 00:33:13.259
lava.

00:33:13.319 --> 00:33:15.299
He didn't see any other night wings at

00:33:15.299 --> 00:33:15.480
all.

00:33:15.599 --> 00:33:18.240
But as they moved along the tunnel

00:33:18.240 --> 00:33:21.000
Starfight heard something up ahead, a

00:33:21.000 --> 00:33:23.759
hissing, murmuring sound that grew louder

00:33:23.759 --> 00:33:24.779
as they approached.

00:33:24.839 --> 00:33:28.380
Dragon voices, jumbled and arguing.

00:33:28.440 --> 00:33:31.500
Dread prickled through every scale on

00:33:31.500 --> 00:33:32.640
Starflight's body.

00:33:32.700 --> 00:33:35.039
If he hadn't been more terrified of what

00:33:35.039 --> 00:33:37.200
Maro Seer would do to him, he would have

00:33:37.200 --> 00:33:38.819
turned and bolted back down the tunnel.

00:33:38.880 --> 00:33:42.720
Finally, Morrow Seer and Starflight

00:33:42.720 --> 00:33:44.519
stepped through an archway into a cave

00:33:44.519 --> 00:33:45.779
full of dragons.

00:33:45.839 --> 00:33:48.720
The walls were packed with dragon wings

00:33:48.720 --> 00:33:51.180
with night wings hanging from crags and

00:33:51.180 --> 00:33:52.920
rocks and the ceiling like bats.

00:33:53.039 --> 00:33:56.759
One by one, dark scaled dragon heads

00:33:56.759 --> 00:33:57.779
turned toward them.

00:33:57.839 --> 00:34:00.359
They gathered night wings fell silent.

00:34:00.420 --> 00:34:04.559
A last voice cried, We should attack

00:34:04.559 --> 00:34:05.099
now.

00:34:05.160 --> 00:34:07.740
We should have attacked yesterday before

00:34:07.740 --> 00:34:09.300
cutting off abruptly as the speaker

00:34:09.300 --> 00:34:10.619
noticed Starflight.

00:34:10.679 --> 00:34:12.959
Starflight wondered again if he was

00:34:12.959 --> 00:34:15.299
dreaming, because this was his biggest

00:34:15.299 --> 00:34:18.479
nightmare come to life, a room full of

00:34:18.479 --> 00:34:21.479
angry night wings, all of them glaring at

00:34:21.479 --> 00:34:21.899
him.

00:34:22.139 --> 00:34:23.339
Watch it.

00:34:23.460 --> 00:34:26.639
Marcio growled, a Starflight stumbled

00:34:26.639 --> 00:34:28.980
into him, and then Starflight saw what

00:34:28.980 --> 00:34:30.059
lay ahead of their talons.

00:34:30.119 --> 00:34:33.960
A few steps into the cave, the rocky path

00:34:33.960 --> 00:34:36.659
abruptly fell away on either side, leaving

00:34:36.659 --> 00:34:38.760
only a thin strip of stone to stand on.

00:34:38.880 --> 00:34:42.239
Below him, was a bubbling lake of glowing

00:34:42.239 --> 00:34:43.380
orange lava.

00:34:43.440 --> 00:34:46.380
He could feel the heat crackling along

00:34:46.380 --> 00:34:46.920
his scales.

00:34:47.039 --> 00:34:49.980
Moro Seer stepped back to the safety of

00:34:49.980 --> 00:34:52.260
the doorway and prodded Starflight

00:34:52.260 --> 00:34:54.480
forward, so the dragonette was left alone

00:34:54.480 --> 00:34:57.239
on the spur of rock surrounded by lava.

00:34:57.300 --> 00:35:00.539
Lava, and night wings.

00:35:00.599 --> 00:35:03.599
And they're all reading my mind.

00:35:03.719 --> 00:35:06.539
He thought, with another jolt of terror.

00:35:06.599 --> 00:35:08.460
They can see all my thoughts.

00:35:08.519 --> 00:35:11.340
They know I'm terrified and weak and

00:35:11.340 --> 00:35:13.500
useless, and that I don't think blister

00:35:13.500 --> 00:35:15.599
should be the next sand wing queen, and

00:35:15.599 --> 00:35:17.579
that I think this is a horrible place to

00:35:17.579 --> 00:35:20.400
live, and stop thinking about all the

00:35:20.400 --> 00:35:21.960
things I don't want them to see in my

00:35:21.960 --> 00:35:22.199
head.

00:35:22.260 --> 00:35:25.860
With a massive effort, Starflight focused

00:35:25.860 --> 00:35:27.480
on the details of the room around him.

00:35:27.539 --> 00:35:29.400
Think about what you see.

00:35:29.460 --> 00:35:31.619
Don't think about anything else.

00:35:31.679 --> 00:35:35.579
First, there weren't actually 100s of

00:35:35.579 --> 00:35:36.840
dragons staring at him.

00:35:36.900 --> 00:35:39.659
He did a quick estimate, hiding his other

00:35:39.659 --> 00:35:41.340
thoughts inside mountains of numbers.

00:35:41.400 --> 00:35:43.260
Maybe 40.

00:35:43.500 --> 00:35:46.619
About 40 black dragons filled the cave

00:35:46.619 --> 00:35:49.199
most of them as large as Marosir, which

00:35:49.199 --> 00:35:50.579
meant they must be quite old.

00:35:50.639 --> 00:35:53.639
They were all as thin as the dragonettes

00:35:53.639 --> 00:35:55.739
in the dormitory, and many of them had

00:35:55.739 --> 00:35:58.739
worn patches on their scales, sores on

00:35:58.739 --> 00:36:01.260
their snouts and wings and traces of

00:36:01.260 --> 00:36:02.460
blood around their nostrils.

00:36:02.519 --> 00:36:05.699
These dragons looked like the tribal

00:36:05.699 --> 00:36:07.739
opposite of the colorful, healthy, well

00:36:07.739 --> 00:36:08.820
fed rain wings.

00:36:08.880 --> 00:36:11.699
There was a clear spot on the cave walls

00:36:11.699 --> 00:36:12.659
right across from him.

00:36:12.719 --> 00:36:15.059
It looked like a circle had been carved

00:36:15.059 --> 00:36:17.400
into the rock as wide across as

00:36:17.400 --> 00:36:19.800
Starflight's wingspan, and then jabbed

00:36:19.800 --> 00:36:22.320
full of small holes, none of them bigger

00:36:22.320 --> 00:36:23.280
than a dragon's eye.

00:36:23.340 --> 00:36:26.039
The other dragons kept glancing at this

00:36:26.039 --> 00:36:27.900
circle, as if waiting for it to do

00:36:27.900 --> 00:36:28.679
something.

00:36:28.860 --> 00:36:31.800
On a ledge beside the circle, perched a

00:36:31.800 --> 00:36:33.900
dragon with a scar rippling down her

00:36:33.900 --> 00:36:34.139
chest.

00:36:34.260 --> 00:36:37.860
Her wings drooped in an odd way as if

00:36:37.860 --> 00:36:39.900
they were weighted down with rocks, and

00:36:39.900 --> 00:36:41.639
she wore a cluster of diamonds around her

00:36:41.639 --> 00:36:41.880
neck.

00:36:41.940 --> 00:36:44.579
Another chain of smaller teardrop

00:36:44.579 --> 00:36:46.860
diamonds was wound around the horns on

00:36:46.860 --> 00:36:47.159
her head.

00:36:47.219 --> 00:36:50.099
But that can't be the queen?

00:36:50.159 --> 00:36:51.659
Starflight thought.

00:36:51.719 --> 00:36:54.239
She didn't have authority in her bones.

00:36:54.300 --> 00:36:56.699
She didn't radiate power all the way

00:36:56.699 --> 00:36:58.619
through her wingtips, like the other

00:36:58.619 --> 00:36:59.639
queens he'd met.

00:36:59.699 --> 00:37:02.159
It took him only a moment of puzzling

00:37:02.159 --> 00:37:04.440
this out before he realized that there

00:37:04.440 --> 00:37:06.480
must be a dragon behind the screen

00:37:06.539 --> 00:37:08.880
staring through those holes at him.

00:37:08.940 --> 00:37:11.820
A chill sliced through his scales.

00:37:11.880 --> 00:37:15.300
Nobody could see her, but her presence

00:37:15.300 --> 00:37:16.800
filled the cave like heavy smoke.

00:37:16.860 --> 00:37:20.159
The queen of the night wings.

00:37:20.219 --> 00:37:23.340
The scrolls always referred to her as

00:37:23.340 --> 00:37:26.219
mysterious and unknown, but Starflight

00:37:26.219 --> 00:37:27.599
hadn't imagined that she would keep

00:37:27.599 --> 00:37:30.300
herself hidden even from her own tribe.

00:37:30.360 --> 00:37:31.260
Why?

00:37:31.380 --> 00:37:35.579
Because it's extra terrifying, he

00:37:35.579 --> 00:37:36.179
answered himself.

00:37:36.239 --> 00:37:40.800
This is him, barked one of the dragons.

00:37:40.860 --> 00:37:44.400
Yes, Maro Sio growled.

00:37:44.460 --> 00:37:47.579
We snatched Jim from the rain forest this

00:37:47.579 --> 00:37:48.000
morning.

00:37:48.059 --> 00:37:51.239
Wings rustled uneasily all around the

00:37:51.239 --> 00:37:51.659
cave.

00:37:51.719 --> 00:37:54.420
Has he told us anything?

00:37:54.480 --> 00:37:56.340
asked another dragon.

00:37:56.400 --> 00:37:57.960
What do they know?

00:37:58.019 --> 00:38:00.480
What are they planning?

00:38:00.539 --> 00:38:03.539
How soon will they attack?

00:38:03.599 --> 00:38:05.039
growled another.

00:38:05.099 --> 00:38:08.400
And how did that rain wing escape?

00:38:08.460 --> 00:38:11.280
Another one shouted, as several dragons

00:38:11.280 --> 00:38:12.539
began to speak at once.

00:38:12.599 --> 00:38:15.840
We've heard reports that there was a mud

00:38:15.840 --> 00:38:17.940
wing with her, a mud wing.

00:38:18.000 --> 00:38:19.260
How did he get here?

00:38:19.320 --> 00:38:21.599
Why didn't we kill them before they got

00:38:21.599 --> 00:38:21.840
away?

00:38:21.900 --> 00:38:25.380
They're talking about glory and clay.

00:38:25.559 --> 00:38:27.659
Starflight thought with a shudder.

00:38:27.719 --> 00:38:31.619
That's the rain wing I warned you about

00:38:31.619 --> 00:38:33.119
Morrisier snarled.

00:38:33.179 --> 00:38:36.900
The one that Talons of Peace got to

00:38:36.900 --> 00:38:39.420
replace the Sky Wing, they lost.

00:38:39.480 --> 00:38:41.099
He spat into the lava.

00:38:41.159 --> 00:38:45.599
This is exactly why I told them to kill

00:38:45.599 --> 00:38:45.960
her.

00:38:46.019 --> 00:38:50.519
A rain wing, of all things.

00:38:50.579 --> 00:38:52.619
Said the dragon with the diamonds.

00:38:52.739 --> 00:38:55.380
What an unfortunate mistake.

00:38:55.500 --> 00:38:59.880
We had her. said a dragon with twisted

00:38:59.880 --> 00:39:00.300
horns.

00:39:00.420 --> 00:39:03.719
Here, in our talons, and nobody killed

00:39:03.719 --> 00:39:04.019
her.

00:39:04.139 --> 00:39:07.320
Who knows what she saw?

00:39:07.320 --> 00:39:08.940
cried another dragon.

00:39:09.000 --> 00:39:10.980
If she warns the rain wings what we're

00:39:10.980 --> 00:39:13.739
planning, she can't possibly know that.

00:39:13.860 --> 00:39:15.300
Marasir said.

00:39:15.360 --> 00:39:18.360
She knows about the tunnel between our

00:39:18.360 --> 00:39:18.900
kingdoms.

00:39:19.019 --> 00:39:21.780
Challenged a dragon from the far wall.

00:39:21.840 --> 00:39:24.119
And that little one escaped with her.

00:39:24.179 --> 00:39:26.579
She'll have told her everything she saw

00:39:26.579 --> 00:39:27.300
in the fortress.

00:39:27.360 --> 00:39:29.159
What if they figure it out?

00:39:29.219 --> 00:39:31.980
A clamor of voices filled the cave.

00:39:32.039 --> 00:39:34.440
Figure what out?

00:39:34.500 --> 00:39:38.280
Starflight looked down at his talons and

00:39:38.280 --> 00:39:40.079
wished they weren't shaking so much.

00:39:40.139 --> 00:39:42.719
He was half afraid that he'd tremble

00:39:42.719 --> 00:39:45.659
himself off balance and into the lava, but

00:39:45.659 --> 00:39:47.639
that wasn't even in the top 20 things he

00:39:47.639 --> 00:39:48.659
was worrying about right now.

00:39:48.719 --> 00:39:50.760
What are they planning?

00:39:50.820 --> 00:39:54.000
He glanced up at the screen where the

00:39:54.000 --> 00:39:54.719
queen was hidden.

00:39:54.780 --> 00:39:57.780
She hadn't spoken at all yet, but he

00:39:57.780 --> 00:39:58.739
could feel her watching.

00:39:58.739 --> 00:40:01.380
From the way his skin prickled, he

00:40:01.380 --> 00:40:03.059
thought she hadn't taken her eyes off him

00:40:03.059 --> 00:40:04.260
since he'd entered the cave.

00:40:04.320 --> 00:40:07.980
All at once, the dragon with the diamonds

00:40:07.980 --> 00:40:10.019
leaned toward the screen, tilting her

00:40:10.019 --> 00:40:10.199
head.

00:40:10.260 --> 00:40:12.840
A hush fell instantly around the room.

00:40:12.900 --> 00:40:16.320
Nothing moved, except the bloop bloop of

00:40:16.320 --> 00:40:17.280
bubbles in the lava.

00:40:17.340 --> 00:40:20.159
Every night wing present seemed to be

00:40:20.159 --> 00:40:21.300
holding his or her breath.

00:40:21.420 --> 00:40:24.000
Starfly didn't hear anything.

00:40:24.059 --> 00:40:27.000
No queen's voice issuing regally from her

00:40:27.000 --> 00:40:29.639
hiding spot, but the diamond dragon

00:40:29.639 --> 00:40:31.380
nodded and straightened up again.

00:40:31.440 --> 00:40:35.699
Queen Battle winners as to shut up and

00:40:35.699 --> 00:40:36.300
ask him.

00:40:36.360 --> 00:40:38.940
To his horror, she pointed at

00:40:38.940 --> 00:40:39.480
Starflight.

00:40:39.539 --> 00:40:41.760
That's why he is here.

00:40:41.820 --> 00:40:45.599
Make him tell us what they know and what

00:40:45.599 --> 00:40:46.679
they're going to do next.

00:40:46.739 --> 00:40:49.800
The listening dragons all swiveled their

00:40:49.800 --> 00:40:50.519
heads toward him.

00:40:50.579 --> 00:40:53.820
Falling into the lava suddenly sounded

00:40:53.820 --> 00:40:54.840
like a pretty great option.

00:40:54.900 --> 00:40:59.219
Um, Starflight stammered several times.

00:40:59.280 --> 00:41:04.500
I, I, um, speak.

00:41:04.559 --> 00:41:06.659
Or I kill you right now.

00:41:06.719 --> 00:41:09.239
Morrisio growled behind him.

00:41:09.300 --> 00:41:11.460
Starflight pressed his front talons

00:41:11.460 --> 00:41:13.139
together and took a deep breath.

00:41:13.199 --> 00:41:16.260
Her name is Glory, he blurted.

00:41:16.320 --> 00:41:18.239
The dragons all hissed.

00:41:18.300 --> 00:41:20.699
This was not something they cared about.

00:41:20.760 --> 00:41:24.840
She, she said you have rain wing

00:41:24.840 --> 00:41:25.260
prisoners.

00:41:25.380 --> 00:41:27.599
Please tell me she's wrong.

00:41:27.659 --> 00:41:29.639
Tell me it's all a mistake.

00:41:29.760 --> 00:41:32.579
But no one corrected him.

00:41:32.699 --> 00:41:36.539
Should he tell them glory's plan, that

00:41:36.539 --> 00:41:37.980
she was trying to become queen of the

00:41:37.980 --> 00:41:40.500
rain wings, so she could build an army to

00:41:40.500 --> 00:41:43.380
come rescue their lost dragons, that they

00:41:43.380 --> 00:41:44.699
shouldn't underestimate her?

00:41:44.760 --> 00:41:48.239
Would he be betraying his friends if he

00:41:48.239 --> 00:41:49.860
said all that to the night wings?

00:41:49.920 --> 00:41:52.619
Or would he be betraying his tribe if he

00:41:52.619 --> 00:41:52.980
didn't?

00:41:53.039 --> 00:41:56.219
The close smoky air of the cave pressed

00:41:56.219 --> 00:41:57.599
down around Starflight?

00:41:57.659 --> 00:42:00.239
What if I can fix everything?

00:42:00.300 --> 00:42:03.059
This is the chance you wanted.

00:42:03.119 --> 00:42:05.579
You ask Lori to let you talk to the night

00:42:05.579 --> 00:42:06.119
wings.

00:42:06.179 --> 00:42:08.099
You wanted to give them a chance to

00:42:08.099 --> 00:42:08.880
explain themselves.

00:42:08.940 --> 00:42:12.480
You want to define a peaceful solution, so

00:42:12.480 --> 00:42:14.159
you wouldn't have to pick sides in a

00:42:14.159 --> 00:42:14.519
war.

00:42:14.579 --> 00:42:18.119
But now that he was here, facing their

00:42:18.119 --> 00:42:20.639
dark eyes, He couldn't find any of the

00:42:20.639 --> 00:42:22.320
brilliant words he'd meant to use.

00:42:22.380 --> 00:42:25.380
Suddenly, one of the nearest dragons

00:42:25.380 --> 00:42:27.900
snapped, just tell us that they're

00:42:27.900 --> 00:42:28.559
planning an attack.

00:42:28.619 --> 00:42:31.320
Yes, Starflight blurted.

00:42:31.380 --> 00:42:33.780
I mean, I think so.

00:42:33.840 --> 00:42:36.840
This met with such an uproar that

00:42:36.840 --> 00:42:38.699
Starflight had to sit down and cover his

00:42:38.699 --> 00:42:39.599
head with his wings.

00:42:39.659 --> 00:42:42.059
He'd said the worst possible thing.

00:42:42.119 --> 00:42:45.059
He'd made everything worse for glory and

00:42:45.059 --> 00:42:46.920
the rain wings, and he couldn't even

00:42:46.920 --> 00:42:48.840
bring himself to speak up and try that

00:42:48.840 --> 00:42:51.239
famous diplomacy he'd always thought was

00:42:51.239 --> 00:42:52.019
such a good idea.

00:42:52.079 --> 00:42:55.019
They wouldn't listen to me anyway.

00:42:55.139 --> 00:42:58.139
He told himself, but he didn't know if

00:42:58.139 --> 00:42:58.559
that was true.

00:42:58.619 --> 00:43:00.840
He wasn't brave enough to find out.

00:43:00.900 --> 00:43:03.480
It doesn't matter.

00:43:03.539 --> 00:43:06.239
Rasped a hoarse, wet voice.

00:43:06.300 --> 00:43:09.960
Rain wings are no match for us.

00:43:10.079 --> 00:43:13.920
A horribly disfigured dragon pushed past

00:43:13.920 --> 00:43:16.980
Morrow's ear, slithered into the cave, and

00:43:16.980 --> 00:43:18.719
glowered at the other dragons.

00:43:18.719 --> 00:43:22.079
His snout was twisted and deformed by a

00:43:22.079 --> 00:43:24.480
terrible scar that had closed one nostril

00:43:24.480 --> 00:43:27.599
melted several scales, and left nasty

00:43:27.599 --> 00:43:29.519
oozing bubbles along his jawline.

00:43:29.639 --> 00:43:32.039
The dragon with the diamonds frowned.

00:43:32.159 --> 00:43:33.900
Vengeance.

00:43:33.960 --> 00:43:36.539
You are not invited to this council.

00:43:36.659 --> 00:43:40.920
Yeah, I noticed, he hissed.

00:43:40.980 --> 00:43:44.880
And yet I know more than any dragon about

00:43:44.880 --> 00:43:47.039
rain wings and what they can do.

00:43:47.159 --> 00:43:49.320
He gestured to his face.

00:43:49.380 --> 00:43:53.159
And I can tell you that this was a

00:43:53.159 --> 00:43:53.699
fluke.

00:43:53.760 --> 00:43:57.840
Brain wings are too stupid and cowardly

00:43:57.840 --> 00:43:58.559
to be dangerous.

00:43:58.619 --> 00:44:01.320
Most of you know I got this when I

00:44:01.320 --> 00:44:02.340
grabbed their queen.

00:44:02.460 --> 00:44:06.719
Well, turns out, just one of their queens

00:44:06.719 --> 00:44:08.400
stupid tribe.

00:44:08.460 --> 00:44:11.639
And she had no idea what she was doing, or

00:44:11.639 --> 00:44:12.539
I'd be dead.

00:44:12.599 --> 00:44:15.659
She didn't even mean to spray me.

00:44:15.719 --> 00:44:17.699
They never do.

00:44:17.760 --> 00:44:21.420
Vengeance shook his head, breathing

00:44:21.420 --> 00:44:22.440
loudly through his mouth.

00:44:22.500 --> 00:44:27.719
They have Pyre's most powerful weapon, and

00:44:27.719 --> 00:44:29.940
they're too pathetic to use it.

00:44:30.000 --> 00:44:34.320
Maybe they were, before this glory came

00:44:34.320 --> 00:44:36.780
along, said one of the other dragons.

00:44:36.840 --> 00:44:39.179
From what Morosia says about her.

00:44:39.239 --> 00:44:41.219
She is not as weak as the rest of them.

00:44:41.280 --> 00:44:45.480
You have no idea, Starflight thought.

00:44:45.539 --> 00:44:49.199
And it's your fault they found out about

00:44:49.199 --> 00:44:49.500
us.

00:44:49.559 --> 00:44:51.719
The Diamond Dragon said.

00:44:51.900 --> 00:44:53.880
You're the one who brought her here.

00:44:54.000 --> 00:44:56.760
Even though Death Bringer warned us the

00:44:56.760 --> 00:44:58.739
dragonettes were in the forest, and that

00:44:58.739 --> 00:45:00.480
we should stay away until they were gone

00:45:00.599 --> 00:45:02.940
death bring her.

00:45:03.000 --> 00:45:04.800
Vengeance smirked.

00:45:04.920 --> 00:45:06.000
Oh, yeah.

00:45:06.059 --> 00:45:09.480
How is your pet greatness?

00:45:09.539 --> 00:45:13.199
I've heard a very interesting story about

00:45:13.199 --> 00:45:13.559
him.

00:45:13.619 --> 00:45:16.500
He turned and beckoned with his tail.

00:45:16.559 --> 00:45:19.500
Starflight recognized the Nightwing

00:45:19.500 --> 00:45:21.300
assassin who was dragged into the cave by

00:45:21.300 --> 00:45:22.619
4 guards.

00:45:22.679 --> 00:45:24.360
It was starting to get crowded on the

00:45:24.360 --> 00:45:25.079
ledge by the door.

00:45:25.139 --> 00:45:28.559
Vengeance seized Deathbringer's ear and

00:45:28.559 --> 00:45:30.300
virtually threw him onto the stone

00:45:30.300 --> 00:45:31.440
outcropping with Starflight.

00:45:31.500 --> 00:45:33.900
They knocked into each other and flung

00:45:33.900 --> 00:45:34.860
out their wings for balance.

00:45:34.920 --> 00:45:37.800
Deathbringer wasn't much bigger than

00:45:37.800 --> 00:45:38.820
Starflight after all.

00:45:38.880 --> 00:45:41.940
He'd looked larger when he was attacking

00:45:41.940 --> 00:45:43.559
Queen Blaze and threatening glory.

00:45:43.679 --> 00:45:46.739
But here, in the same lava predicament as

00:45:46.739 --> 00:45:49.019
Starflight, with everyone looking just as

00:45:49.019 --> 00:45:51.719
displeased with him, he seemed a lot less

00:45:51.719 --> 00:45:52.440
intimidating.

00:45:52.500 --> 00:45:56.280
Ah, he said to Starflight in a friendly

00:45:56.280 --> 00:45:56.519
way.

00:45:56.579 --> 00:45:58.019
You're here too.

00:45:58.079 --> 00:46:00.599
His eyes looked as if he wanted to ask

00:46:00.599 --> 00:46:01.980
something, but didn't dare.

00:46:02.039 --> 00:46:07.139
This dragon, vengeance bellowed, pointing

00:46:07.139 --> 00:46:07.860
a death bringer.

00:46:07.920 --> 00:46:12.900
This pet assassin of princess greatness

00:46:12.900 --> 00:46:17.039
was actually conspiring with the enemy.

00:46:17.099 --> 00:46:20.760
He is the one who brought the mud wing

00:46:20.760 --> 00:46:23.639
here, and he helped them both to escape.

00:46:23.699 --> 00:46:27.480
Princess, Starfight thought.

00:46:27.539 --> 00:46:32.699
So, the Diamond Dragon, greatness, speaks

00:46:32.699 --> 00:46:34.139
for her mother for some reason.

00:46:34.199 --> 00:46:38.820
Hang on, Deathbringer said, hopping

00:46:38.820 --> 00:46:41.039
neatly over Starflight's head, so the

00:46:41.039 --> 00:46:42.420
dragonette was between him and

00:46:42.420 --> 00:46:43.260
vengeance.

00:46:43.320 --> 00:46:45.780
He looked around at the other dragons and

00:46:45.780 --> 00:46:47.579
spread his wings with an innocent air.

00:46:47.639 --> 00:46:49.860
Conspiring with the enemy.

00:46:49.920 --> 00:46:51.420
Do you have any proof?

00:46:51.480 --> 00:46:52.980
Yeah.

00:46:53.039 --> 00:46:56.579
I have witnesses, vengeance hissed.

00:46:56.639 --> 00:46:59.699
One of the gods she attacked on the way

00:46:59.699 --> 00:47:01.679
out, saw you helping them.

00:47:01.800 --> 00:47:05.099
And the gods you distracted from the

00:47:05.099 --> 00:47:05.579
tunnel.

00:47:05.639 --> 00:47:08.039
So the mud wing could come through.

00:47:08.099 --> 00:47:10.980
They can tell us all about that.

00:47:11.039 --> 00:47:14.159
A terrible silence followed.

00:47:14.219 --> 00:47:16.320
Starflight wondered whether they were all

00:47:16.320 --> 00:47:18.539
searching Deathbringers' mind to find out

00:47:18.539 --> 00:47:19.079
what was true.

00:47:19.139 --> 00:47:22.380
He kept his own mind carefully blank, just

00:47:22.380 --> 00:47:22.800
in case.

00:47:22.920 --> 00:47:27.599
Death bringer. said greatness, twisting

00:47:27.599 --> 00:47:29.519
her diamond necklace in her front claws.

00:47:29.579 --> 00:47:32.039
That kind of betrayal.

00:47:32.099 --> 00:47:35.039
The punishment is death.

00:47:35.099 --> 00:47:38.460
The Nightwing assassin spread his wings

00:47:38.460 --> 00:47:40.619
and bowed deeply toward the queen.

00:47:40.679 --> 00:47:43.800
I swear, I have only ever done what I

00:47:43.800 --> 00:47:45.179
thought would be best for my tribe.

00:47:45.239 --> 00:47:47.460
Oh, yeah.

00:47:47.519 --> 00:47:49.619
Vengeance coughed wetly.

00:47:49.679 --> 00:47:51.300
So why?

00:47:51.360 --> 00:47:54.420
Or all the dragonettes still alive then?

00:47:54.480 --> 00:47:57.960
Deathbringer glanced under his wing and

00:47:57.960 --> 00:47:59.400
met Starflight's eyes.

00:47:59.460 --> 00:48:02.159
There was a question in them, and this

00:48:02.159 --> 00:48:03.840
time Starflight guessed what it was.

00:48:03.900 --> 00:48:05.219
Are they?

00:48:05.280 --> 00:48:06.780
All still alive.

00:48:06.900 --> 00:48:10.500
Starflight nodded as imperceptibly as he

00:48:10.500 --> 00:48:12.719
could, and a look of relief flitted

00:48:12.719 --> 00:48:14.940
across Deathbringer's face, then was

00:48:14.940 --> 00:48:15.420
gone.

00:48:15.480 --> 00:48:18.239
My mission is not complete.

00:48:18.300 --> 00:48:18.960
It's true.

00:48:19.079 --> 00:48:20.280
Deathbringer said.

00:48:20.400 --> 00:48:22.199
I need to return to the rainforest

00:48:22.199 --> 00:48:23.340
and...

00:48:23.340 --> 00:48:27.000
And betray us some more, vengeance

00:48:27.000 --> 00:48:27.480
suggested.

00:48:27.539 --> 00:48:29.340
I bet you do.

00:48:29.400 --> 00:48:32.639
Starflight noticed greatness leaning

00:48:32.639 --> 00:48:34.739
toward the screen again, but most of the

00:48:34.739 --> 00:48:36.599
dragons were staring at Deathbringer and

00:48:36.599 --> 00:48:37.500
didn't notice this time.

00:48:37.559 --> 00:48:41.760
I assure you, I'm a loyal night wing.

00:48:41.820 --> 00:48:44.280
Deathbringer said, his voice rising.

00:48:44.340 --> 00:48:47.159
Perhaps I think it's worth discussing.

00:48:47.280 --> 00:48:49.679
Whether we really need to kill these

00:48:49.679 --> 00:48:53.940
dragonettes, but you see, roared

00:48:53.940 --> 00:48:54.420
vengeance.

00:48:54.480 --> 00:48:55.440
He's...

00:48:55.440 --> 00:48:57.000
Vengeance.

00:48:57.059 --> 00:48:59.519
Greatness shouted, cutting him off.

00:48:59.579 --> 00:49:01.920
She stood up on her ledge and spread her

00:49:01.920 --> 00:49:04.679
wings, revealing the silver scales

00:49:04.679 --> 00:49:06.480
glittering underneath like echoes of her

00:49:06.480 --> 00:49:06.900
diamonds.

00:49:06.960 --> 00:49:09.780
She puffed up her chest, and contorted

00:49:09.780 --> 00:49:11.820
her face, as if she was trying to appear

00:49:11.820 --> 00:49:14.340
menacing and regal, but it looked like a

00:49:14.340 --> 00:49:14.760
performance.

00:49:14.880 --> 00:49:17.519
Starflight still couldn't see a future

00:49:17.519 --> 00:49:18.300
queen in her.

00:49:18.360 --> 00:49:24.059
The queen has spoken, greatness said, into

00:49:24.059 --> 00:49:27.179
the perilous silence, vengeance.

00:49:27.239 --> 00:49:30.000
You endangered the whole tribe.

00:49:30.059 --> 00:49:32.280
You disobeyed orders.

00:49:32.340 --> 00:49:35.820
You brought a viper to us, disguised as a

00:49:35.820 --> 00:49:37.019
simple garden snake.

00:49:37.139 --> 00:49:40.500
Wait, vengeance cried.

00:49:40.559 --> 00:49:42.300
What he did was worse.

00:49:42.420 --> 00:49:45.300
I just grabbed a rain wing, same as

00:49:45.300 --> 00:49:45.719
always.

00:49:45.780 --> 00:49:47.460
How could I know?

00:49:47.639 --> 00:49:49.440
She didn't look no different than the

00:49:49.440 --> 00:49:49.679
others?

00:49:49.800 --> 00:49:55.619
And in addition, said greatness, you are

00:49:55.619 --> 00:49:56.940
irritating the queen.

00:49:57.000 --> 00:50:00.420
She flicked her tail, just the tiniest

00:50:00.420 --> 00:50:02.460
movement at the guards in the doorway.

00:50:02.460 --> 00:50:05.340
No, shrieked vengeance.

00:50:05.400 --> 00:50:08.219
His wings flapped open, but he'd barely

00:50:08.219 --> 00:50:10.619
lifted off when the 4 guards grabbed him

00:50:10.619 --> 00:50:13.500
with one swift heave, before Starflight

00:50:13.500 --> 00:50:14.639
even had time to blink.

00:50:14.699 --> 00:50:17.519
They hurled the scarred dragon into the

00:50:17.519 --> 00:50:18.420
lake of lava.
1362
00:50:18,480 --> 00:50:22,619	Chapter 3.

00:50:22.920 --> 00:50:26.519
Death bringer shot up and out of the way

00:50:26.519 --> 00:50:28.260
as lava splashed all around them.

00:50:28.320 --> 00:50:31.500
Starfly didn't move fast enough, and a

00:50:31.500 --> 00:50:33.659
bright orange droplet splattered on his

00:50:33.659 --> 00:50:33.840
foot.

00:50:33.900 --> 00:50:37.559
Burning pain flared through him, and he

00:50:37.559 --> 00:50:38.159
thought he might faint.

00:50:38.219 --> 00:50:41.639
Then a shape surged out of the lava.

00:50:41.699 --> 00:50:44.940
Vengeance, screaming and trying to escape

00:50:44.940 --> 00:50:46.139
as he was boiled alive.

00:50:46.199 --> 00:50:49.679
Death bringer's talons yanked Starflight

00:50:49.679 --> 00:50:50.880
into the air just in time.

00:50:50.940 --> 00:50:54.300
Lava sprayed in all directions as the

00:50:54.300 --> 00:50:56.699
dying dragon flailed his wings.

00:50:56.760 --> 00:50:58.199
Don't do this.

00:50:58.260 --> 00:50:59.760
Save me.

00:50:59.820 --> 00:51:01.500
Vengeance howled.

00:51:01.559 --> 00:51:03.900
The guard stepped forward with

00:51:03.900 --> 00:51:04.980
expressionless faces.

00:51:05.039 --> 00:51:07.079
They were wearing a sort of armor

00:51:07.079 --> 00:51:09.480
including helmets and thick plates over

00:51:09.480 --> 00:51:11.460
their underbellies, and they were all

00:51:11.460 --> 00:51:13.739
carrying wicked, pronged spears like the

00:51:13.739 --> 00:51:15.059
one glory had brought back to the

00:51:15.059 --> 00:51:15.900
rainforest.

00:51:15.960 --> 00:51:19.199
It was these spears they used to shove

00:51:19.199 --> 00:51:21.659
vengeance back under the lava, and to

00:51:21.659 --> 00:51:23.639
hold him there, until the thrashing

00:51:23.639 --> 00:51:25.559
stopped, and the dark shape of the

00:51:25.559 --> 00:51:28.199
scarred dragon finally sank all the way

00:51:28.199 --> 00:51:31.320
below the bright gold red surface, and

00:51:31.320 --> 00:51:31.739
disappeared.

00:51:31.800 --> 00:51:35.460
After a long moment, Starflight

00:51:35.460 --> 00:51:36.360
remembered to breathe again.

00:51:36.420 --> 00:51:39.539
He glanced at Death Bringer, hovering in

00:51:39.539 --> 00:51:40.139
the air beside him.

00:51:40.199 --> 00:51:43.320
There was an unusually somber look on the

00:51:43.320 --> 00:51:46.139
assassin's face, as if he'd just seen a

00:51:46.139 --> 00:51:48.719
glimpse of his possible future, and not

00:51:48.719 --> 00:51:50.760
in a magical, prophetic vision sort of

00:51:50.760 --> 00:51:50.940
way.

00:51:51.000 --> 00:51:53.639
Thank you, majesty.

00:51:53.699 --> 00:51:57.000
Death bringer said at last, bowing toward

00:51:57.000 --> 00:51:57.960
the hidden queen.

00:51:58.199 --> 00:52:00.420
Don't, death bringer.

00:52:00.480 --> 00:52:03.300
Greatness said, her voice cracking.

00:52:03.360 --> 00:52:05.639
She cleared her throat and looked away.

00:52:05.639 --> 00:52:07.920
We're not done with you.

00:52:07.980 --> 00:52:10.320
She had addressed the guards.

00:52:10.380 --> 00:52:12.539
Take him to the dungeon.

00:52:12.599 --> 00:52:15.900
We'll investigate the charges, and then

00:52:15.900 --> 00:52:18.119
Her Majesty will decide what to do.

00:52:18.239 --> 00:52:21.719
Deathbringer flew down to the guards, and

00:52:21.719 --> 00:52:23.099
allowed them to push him out the door

00:52:23.099 --> 00:52:25.619
only glancing back once to meet

00:52:25.619 --> 00:52:28.500
Starflight's eyes, with a look Starflight

00:52:28.500 --> 00:52:29.219
couldn't decode.

00:52:29.280 --> 00:52:32.340
Maybe he expects me to have mind reading

00:52:32.340 --> 00:52:33.000
abilities.

00:52:33.059 --> 00:52:35.400
Maybe he's trying to send me a message.

00:52:35.460 --> 00:52:39.119
If so, sorry, Deathbringer.

00:52:39.179 --> 00:52:40.980
You picked the wrong dragon.

00:52:41.039 --> 00:52:44.219
Greatness rubbed the ridges above our

00:52:44.219 --> 00:52:45.539
eyes, looking tired.

00:52:45.599 --> 00:52:47.460
All right.

00:52:47.519 --> 00:52:48.840
We need a break.

00:52:48.900 --> 00:52:52.079
If it's your turn to eat this week, go do

00:52:52.079 --> 00:52:54.719
that now, and we'll reconvene tonight.

00:52:54.780 --> 00:52:57.780
She glanced around the room, leaned

00:52:57.780 --> 00:53:00.239
toward the screen again, and added, The

00:53:00.239 --> 00:53:02.460
queen says to a turn at dusk with

00:53:02.460 --> 00:53:04.380
possible defensive and offensive

00:53:04.380 --> 00:53:05.039
strategies.

00:53:05.099 --> 00:53:06.780
Morosia.

00:53:06.840 --> 00:53:09.119
See if you can claw some more information

00:53:09.119 --> 00:53:11.159
out of the dragonette before then.

00:53:11.219 --> 00:53:14.699
Morosier dipped his head, flexing his

00:53:14.699 --> 00:53:15.179
talons.

00:53:15.239 --> 00:53:17.760
Starflight hoped uneasily that she meant

00:53:17.760 --> 00:53:20.219
claw in a metaphorical way.

00:53:20.280 --> 00:53:23.039
The night wings began to disperse.

00:53:23.099 --> 00:53:25.440
Most of them threw holes in the ceiling.

00:53:25.500 --> 00:53:28.619
Marosier jerked his head, and Starflight

00:53:28.619 --> 00:53:30.179
reluctantly followed him back into the

00:53:30.179 --> 00:53:30.539
tunnels.

00:53:30.599 --> 00:53:33.539
The mention of eating had reminded him of

00:53:33.539 --> 00:53:36.059
how hungry he was, although he couldn't

00:53:36.059 --> 00:53:37.679
really worry about food when he wasn't

00:53:37.679 --> 00:53:40.260
even sure if he was a prisoner or a spy

00:53:40.260 --> 00:53:41.820
or just a failure.

00:53:41.880 --> 00:53:43.800
And after what had happened to

00:53:43.800 --> 00:53:44.340
vengeance.

00:53:44.400 --> 00:53:46.679
Starflight was pretty nervous about what

00:53:46.679 --> 00:53:48.420
the night wings might do with a failure.

00:53:48.480 --> 00:53:51.780
Maru Sears wings billowed like

00:53:51.780 --> 00:53:53.880
thunderclouds as he stormed ahead of

00:53:53.880 --> 00:53:54.480
Starflight.

00:53:54.539 --> 00:53:57.179
Soon Starflight realized that they

00:53:57.179 --> 00:53:58.500
weren't going back to the dormitory.

00:53:58.559 --> 00:54:02.099
Marosir had taken a turn somewhere, and

00:54:02.099 --> 00:54:03.960
now Starflight could see dim gray light

00:54:03.960 --> 00:54:04.860
up ahead.

00:54:04.920 --> 00:54:07.920
They emerged onto a shelf of rock that

00:54:07.920 --> 00:54:09.599
jutted from the side of the fortress.

00:54:09.659 --> 00:54:12.960
Below them was a weird landscape of rocks

00:54:12.960 --> 00:54:15.840
that looked like giant, lumpy gray black

00:54:15.840 --> 00:54:18.300
dragon scales, with a fiery orange

00:54:18.300 --> 00:54:20.519
glowing underneath, filling in the

00:54:20.519 --> 00:54:20.820
cracks.

00:54:20.880 --> 00:54:22.980
A lava field.

00:54:23.039 --> 00:54:24.480
Starflight thought.

00:54:24.539 --> 00:54:27.480
He remembered a little about volcanoes

00:54:27.480 --> 00:54:29.519
from one of the scrolls he'd studied back

00:54:29.519 --> 00:54:30.179
under the mountain.

00:54:30.239 --> 00:54:32.099
What felt like a lifetime ago.

00:54:32.219 --> 00:54:34.619
But there weren't any active volcanoes on

00:54:34.619 --> 00:54:36.900
the mainland of Pyria, so he hadn't

00:54:36.900 --> 00:54:38.219
memorized it like the other scrolls.

00:54:38.340 --> 00:54:40.320
It had never occurred to him that the

00:54:40.320 --> 00:54:42.420
Night Wings, who'd written most of the

00:54:42.420 --> 00:54:44.760
scrolls might have firsthand knowledge of

00:54:44.760 --> 00:54:48.539
volcanoes, might, in fact, be living on

00:54:48.539 --> 00:54:48.780
one.

00:54:48.840 --> 00:54:52.320
Starflight couldn't see any caves or a

00:54:52.320 --> 00:54:54.059
lava river like the one glory had

00:54:54.059 --> 00:54:56.340
described, so he guessed they were on the

00:54:56.340 --> 00:54:58.920
other side of the volcano, but the air

00:54:58.920 --> 00:55:01.679
was as smoky and gray as she'd said, and

00:55:01.679 --> 00:55:02.639
as hard to breathe.

00:55:02.699 --> 00:55:05.760
He still felt that raw, scraped feeling

00:55:05.760 --> 00:55:07.199
all the way down his throat.

00:55:07.260 --> 00:55:10.260
Far overhead in the ashy sky.

00:55:10.320 --> 00:55:12.539
A pair of black dragons wheeled and

00:55:12.539 --> 00:55:15.119
circled, around and around, like

00:55:15.119 --> 00:55:15.719
vultures.

00:55:15.840 --> 00:55:18.119
Starflight wondered if they could see the

00:55:18.119 --> 00:55:18.960
mainland from up there.

00:55:19.019 --> 00:55:21.780
How far was the island from the rest of

00:55:21.780 --> 00:55:22.320
Pyria?

00:55:22.380 --> 00:55:24.480
Did the night wings have a way to get

00:55:24.480 --> 00:55:24.659
there?

00:55:24.719 --> 00:55:27.659
Other than the secret animus made tunnels

00:55:27.659 --> 00:55:28.440
to the rainforest?

00:55:28.500 --> 00:55:30.420
So many questions.

00:55:30.480 --> 00:55:33.480
His whole life, he'd been full of

00:55:33.480 --> 00:55:35.400
questions about the night wings and their

00:55:35.400 --> 00:55:36.179
secret home.

00:55:36.239 --> 00:55:38.699
And now, perhaps, they could all be

00:55:38.699 --> 00:55:39.000
answered.

00:55:39.119 --> 00:55:42.599
He took a moment to think, I'm here.

00:55:42.659 --> 00:55:44.400
This is my home.

00:55:44.460 --> 00:55:46.199
This is my tribe.

00:55:46.260 --> 00:55:48.539
This is what I was looking for.

00:55:48.599 --> 00:55:50.639
But it didn't feel true.

00:55:50.699 --> 00:55:53.820
This awful place was nothing like the

00:55:53.820 --> 00:55:56.219
Nightwing utopia he'd always imagined.

00:55:56.280 --> 00:55:58.500
He'd pictured a beautiful hidden place

00:55:58.500 --> 00:56:01.619
full of art and music, and dragons who

00:56:01.619 --> 00:56:04.380
loved to read, with spires reaching to

00:56:04.380 --> 00:56:07.739
the clouds, and waterfalls, and sunlight

00:56:07.739 --> 00:56:09.179
and a library around every corner.

00:56:09.239 --> 00:56:10.980
Not this.

00:56:11.039 --> 00:56:15.480
The smoke and stench, and hostility, and

00:56:15.480 --> 00:56:16.559
gloomy surroundings.

00:56:16.679 --> 00:56:20.460
And even a 1000000 answers, even all the

00:56:20.460 --> 00:56:22.139
answers to all the questions he could

00:56:22.139 --> 00:56:24.239
think of, wouldn't be able to take the

00:56:24.239 --> 00:56:25.739
place of Sonny and the other

00:56:25.739 --> 00:56:26.940
dragonettes.

00:56:27.000 --> 00:56:29.760
Maro Seer stared across the lava field

00:56:29.760 --> 00:56:33.059
and inhaled several times, his nostrils

00:56:33.059 --> 00:56:35.400
flaring and his tongue slithering in and

00:56:35.400 --> 00:56:35.579
out.

00:56:35.639 --> 00:56:38.340
He did this for so long that Starflight

00:56:38.340 --> 00:56:39.539
began to wonder if there was something

00:56:39.539 --> 00:56:40.320
wrong with his nose.

00:56:40.380 --> 00:56:44.400
Um, Starflight squeaked at last.

00:56:44.460 --> 00:56:47.280
Maro Sier glared at him in the middle of

00:56:47.280 --> 00:56:48.179
a giant sniff.

00:56:48.239 --> 00:56:51.900
Just, um, Starflight said.

00:56:51.960 --> 00:56:54.179
I just want you to know, I don't know

00:56:54.179 --> 00:56:56.400
anything else, really, about the rain

00:56:56.400 --> 00:56:57.179
wings attacking.

00:56:57.239 --> 00:57:00.300
Almost immediately, his traitorous brain

00:57:00.300 --> 00:57:03.119
started clamoring, except the glory might

00:57:03.119 --> 00:57:05.699
be queen by now, and that rain wings are

00:57:05.699 --> 00:57:08.760
normally pacifists, and he fixed his eyes

00:57:08.760 --> 00:57:11.039
on the mountain behind them, and tried to

00:57:11.039 --> 00:57:12.420
think of nothing but lava.

00:57:12.480 --> 00:57:14.699
Maro seer snorted.

00:57:14.760 --> 00:57:18.420
That doesn't surprise me, he said.

00:57:18.480 --> 00:57:21.179
You know, just about the most useless spy

00:57:21.179 --> 00:57:21.960
I've ever met.

00:57:22.079 --> 00:57:24.659
He spread his wings and inhaled once

00:57:24.659 --> 00:57:24.900
more.

00:57:24.960 --> 00:57:26.340
Let's go.

00:57:26.400 --> 00:57:29.219
His tail nearly knocked Starflight off

00:57:29.219 --> 00:57:30.780
the ledge as he leaped into the sky.

00:57:30.840 --> 00:57:33.059
Down there?

00:57:33.119 --> 00:57:36.059
Starflight called, glancing at the molten

00:57:36.059 --> 00:57:37.199
cracks in the rocks below them.

00:57:37.320 --> 00:57:38.699
Is it safe?

00:57:38.760 --> 00:57:41.219
He flapped to catch up tomorrow's year.

00:57:41.280 --> 00:57:43.679
Of course it isn't.

00:57:43.739 --> 00:57:44.639
Marosira snapped.

00:57:44.699 --> 00:57:47.579
Several dragons have made the mistake of

00:57:47.579 --> 00:57:50.280
trying to land down there, only to break

00:57:50.280 --> 00:57:52.139
the crust and fall right through.

00:57:52.199 --> 00:57:55.440
He nodded at a white shape sticking out

00:57:55.440 --> 00:57:55.860
of the rocks.

00:57:55.920 --> 00:57:58.619
Starflight peered at it until he realized

00:57:58.619 --> 00:58:00.900
what it was, and then wished he hadn't.

00:58:00.960 --> 00:58:03.599
His stomach twisted as he spotted a few

00:58:03.599 --> 00:58:03.840
others.

00:58:03.900 --> 00:58:05.760
Dragon skulls.

00:58:05.820 --> 00:58:08.579
Their mouths open in an eternal scream.

00:58:08.639 --> 00:58:12.360
I wouldn't suggest a closer look.

00:58:12.360 --> 00:58:14.639
Marosier said dryly.

00:58:14.699 --> 00:58:16.199
We're going over there.

00:58:16.320 --> 00:58:19.019
He nodded to the far side of the lava

00:58:19.019 --> 00:58:21.420
rocks, where Starflight now saw a tangle

00:58:21.420 --> 00:58:22.860
of gray ash covered trees.

00:58:22.920 --> 00:58:26.519
So, Starflight cleared his throat.

00:58:26.579 --> 00:58:30.119
When greatness said, if it's your turn to

00:58:30.119 --> 00:58:32.280
eat this week, what did that mean?

00:58:32.340 --> 00:58:34.920
Maro Seer hissed.

00:58:34.980 --> 00:58:37.559
There's a rotating schedule.

00:58:37.619 --> 00:58:40.139
All night wings are allowed to hunt or

00:58:40.139 --> 00:58:42.179
gather for about 5 days out of every

00:58:42.179 --> 00:58:42.480
month.

00:58:42.539 --> 00:58:45.360
Naturally, I am exempt.

00:58:45.480 --> 00:58:47.159
Naturally?

00:58:47.219 --> 00:58:48.599
Starflight echoed.

00:58:48.659 --> 00:58:50.940
Although he hadn't meant for it to sound

00:58:50.940 --> 00:58:51.960
so much like a question.

00:58:52.079 --> 00:58:54.719
Only 5 days a month?

00:58:54.780 --> 00:58:57.000
No wonder they're all so thin.

00:58:57.059 --> 00:58:59.579
They must be running out of food on this

00:58:59.579 --> 00:58:59.880
island.

00:58:59.940 --> 00:59:03.420
The older dragon frowned down at him.

00:59:03.539 --> 00:59:08.340
My role in the tribe's future makes me

00:59:08.340 --> 00:59:09.239
indispensable.

00:59:09.300 --> 00:59:13.920
Oh, Starflight said, not daring to ask

00:59:13.920 --> 00:59:14.579
any more questions.

00:59:14.639 --> 00:59:18.539
As they got closer to the trees, it

00:59:18.539 --> 00:59:20.039
turned out to be a bigger forest than

00:59:20.039 --> 00:59:22.380
Starfly had expected, covering about a

00:59:22.380 --> 00:59:24.420
quarter of the island, from the edge of

00:59:24.420 --> 00:59:25.440
the lava to the ocean.

00:59:25.500 --> 00:59:29.039
I see, he said with relief.

00:59:29.159 --> 00:59:31.139
I wondered where you hunted.

00:59:31.199 --> 00:59:33.780
Surely there couldn't be much prey on an

00:59:33.780 --> 00:59:34.800
active volcano.

00:59:34.860 --> 00:59:39.719
Here, when we have to, Marosier spat.

00:59:39.780 --> 00:59:42.539
For instance, when we can't get to the

00:59:42.539 --> 00:59:44.820
rainforest or the kingdom of sand.

00:59:44.940 --> 00:59:47.760
His forked black tongue hissed in and

00:59:47.760 --> 00:59:48.000
out.

00:59:48.059 --> 00:59:49.800
Oh.

00:59:49.860 --> 00:59:52.260
That must be another reason they're so

00:59:52.260 --> 00:59:52.920
angry right now.

00:59:52.980 --> 00:59:55.679
They've been using their rainforest to

00:59:55.679 --> 00:59:59.039
find extra prey, he thought, like that

00:59:59.039 --> 01:00:01.019
sloth Glory Clay and I found by the

01:00:01.019 --> 01:00:01.320
river.

01:00:01.380 --> 01:00:04.260
He'd had trouble getting the stench of

01:00:04.260 --> 01:00:05.940
that dying sloth out of his nose.

01:00:06.000 --> 01:00:08.519
For a moment, Starflight thought the

01:00:08.519 --> 01:00:10.139
memory of it had brought this smell back

01:00:10.139 --> 01:00:12.840
until he realized a similar smell of

01:00:12.840 --> 01:00:14.579
decay was coming from the forest below

01:00:14.579 --> 01:00:14.760
him.

01:00:14.820 --> 01:00:18.659
The whole island was like this when we

01:00:18.659 --> 01:00:20.699
got here, Morrisier said.

01:00:20.760 --> 01:00:23.519
You mean covered with trees?

01:00:23.579 --> 01:00:24.960
Starflight asked.

01:00:25.019 --> 01:00:26.280
What happened?

01:00:26.340 --> 01:00:27.420
The volcano?

01:00:27.480 --> 01:00:29.519
Stupid question.

01:00:29.579 --> 01:00:31.500
Of course it was the volcano.

01:00:31.559 --> 01:00:34.320
He looked back at the mountain, which

01:00:34.320 --> 01:00:36.239
must have sent a river of lava this way

01:00:36.239 --> 01:00:39.179
that covered almost all the trees, turning

01:00:39.179 --> 01:00:40.800
the island into a mostly barren

01:00:40.800 --> 01:00:41.460
rockscape.

01:00:41.519 --> 01:00:43.739
Marasir didn't answer him.

01:00:43.800 --> 01:00:46.320
They circled overhead once, and

01:00:46.320 --> 01:00:48.059
Starflight spotted a few other night

01:00:48.059 --> 01:00:49.500
wings prowling through the trees.

01:00:49.559 --> 01:00:52.800
Morosier glowered at them, then flicked

01:00:52.800 --> 01:00:53.760
his tail at Starflight.

01:00:53.820 --> 01:00:57.780
Quickly, he snapped, before one of them

01:00:57.780 --> 01:00:58.920
finds my prey.

01:00:59.039 --> 01:01:03.599
Your Starflight started curiously, but

01:01:03.599 --> 01:01:05.159
Mario Sierra had already tucked his wings

01:01:05.159 --> 01:01:07.440
and was arrowing down to a patch of

01:01:07.440 --> 01:01:08.940
stunted trees not far from the beach.

01:01:09.000 --> 01:01:12.480
The older dragon landed with a thud that

01:01:12.480 --> 01:01:14.340
sent gray dust billowing around his

01:01:14.340 --> 01:01:16.559
talons, and immediately dropped his nose

01:01:16.559 --> 01:01:17.099
to the ground.

01:01:17.159 --> 01:01:20.340
With a horrible snorting noise, he

01:01:20.340 --> 01:01:22.860
charged across the clearing, taking deep

01:01:22.860 --> 01:01:25.079
breaths, and flicking his tongue rapidly

01:01:25.079 --> 01:01:25.559
in and out.

01:01:25.619 --> 01:01:28.500
Starflight had never seen hunting like

01:01:28.500 --> 01:01:28.739
this.

01:01:28.800 --> 01:01:31.380
Duna taught them what he could in the

01:01:31.380 --> 01:01:33.599
caves under the mountain, and sometimes

01:01:33.599 --> 01:01:35.400
it had involved scent trails.

01:01:35.460 --> 01:01:38.460
Starfight was always decent at those, but

01:01:38.460 --> 01:01:40.380
usually it also involved being quiet

01:01:40.380 --> 01:01:42.840
waiting to spot your target, and then

01:01:42.840 --> 01:01:44.820
attacking swiftly before they even knew

01:01:44.820 --> 01:01:45.360
you were there.

01:01:45.360 --> 01:01:48.480
But from the noise Moroser was making

01:01:48.480 --> 01:01:50.579
Starfly thought every animal on the

01:01:50.579 --> 01:01:52.079
island must know he was coming.

01:01:52.139 --> 01:01:55.019
He followed the large black dragon

01:01:55.019 --> 01:01:56.940
thinking about Dune and his hunting

01:01:56.940 --> 01:01:57.360
lessons.

01:01:57.420 --> 01:02:00.000
Their sand wing guardian hadn't been

01:02:00.000 --> 01:02:02.099
particularly kind to the dragonettes

01:02:02.099 --> 01:02:04.019
although he'd never been as cruel as

01:02:04.019 --> 01:02:07.260
Kestrel, but he'd always noticed how hard

01:02:07.260 --> 01:02:09.960
Starflight studied, and sometimes he gave

01:02:09.960 --> 01:02:11.880
him special tutorials on scrolls that

01:02:11.880 --> 01:02:13.139
Starflight found confusing.

01:02:13.199 --> 01:02:16.739
Their other guardian, webs, had often

01:02:16.739 --> 01:02:18.599
made an effort to bring back more scrolls

01:02:18.599 --> 01:02:20.280
for Starflight on his trips outside.

01:02:20.340 --> 01:02:22.800
They'd both been more cautious with him

01:02:22.800 --> 01:02:25.500
than the other dragonettes, perhaps wary

01:02:25.500 --> 01:02:27.239
that his nightwing mind reading or

01:02:27.239 --> 01:02:29.159
prophecy skills might suddenly manifest.

01:02:29.219 --> 01:02:33.300
Something I'm still waiting for, he

01:02:33.300 --> 01:02:34.920
thought, hunching his wings.

01:02:35.039 --> 01:02:37.619
Morosier made a guttural, triumphant

01:02:37.619 --> 01:02:40.079
noise and swiped a leafless bush out of

01:02:40.079 --> 01:02:40.380
his way.

01:02:40.440 --> 01:02:43.380
Underneath it was something half dead.

01:02:43.500 --> 01:02:47.760
More than half dead, Starflight thought

01:02:47.760 --> 01:02:49.800
almost all the way dead.

01:02:49.860 --> 01:02:52.800
It looked like a pile of gray and white

01:02:52.800 --> 01:02:55.199
feathers, as big as a dragon's head.

01:02:55.260 --> 01:02:57.840
When the giant night wing hooked one claw

01:02:57.840 --> 01:03:00.599
in it to drag it out, it let out an awful

01:03:00.599 --> 01:03:01.679
pathetic squawk.

01:03:01.739 --> 01:03:03.780
What is it?

01:03:03.840 --> 01:03:06.599
Starfly asked, trying to remember a bird

01:03:06.599 --> 01:03:07.860
like this from his scrolls.

01:03:07.920 --> 01:03:10.320
His curiosity made him forget about being

01:03:10.320 --> 01:03:11.039
too afraid to talk.

01:03:11.159 --> 01:03:14.219
It's bigger than any seagull I've seen.

01:03:14.280 --> 01:03:17.579
A giant albatross.

01:03:17.639 --> 01:03:19.980
Morrisier said, flipping it over.

01:03:20.039 --> 01:03:23.280
I was sure it would be dead by now.

01:03:23.400 --> 01:03:25.199
With a shrug.

01:03:25.260 --> 01:03:27.119
He sliced one claw across the bird's

01:03:27.119 --> 01:03:27.480
throat.

01:03:27.539 --> 01:03:29.880
Starflight covered his snout with one of

01:03:29.880 --> 01:03:30.239
his wings.

01:03:30.300 --> 01:03:32.940
The toxic smell of the dead bird was

01:03:32.940 --> 01:03:33.900
almost overwhelming.

01:03:33.960 --> 01:03:37.079
He wanted to run to the ocean, and bury

01:03:37.079 --> 01:03:38.400
his head in the salt water to make it go

01:03:38.400 --> 01:03:38.639
away.

01:03:38.699 --> 01:03:41.760
As Maro Sierra prodded it a few more

01:03:41.760 --> 01:03:44.340
times, Starflight spotted a bite on the

01:03:44.340 --> 01:03:46.139
bird's neck, like the one on the dead

01:03:46.139 --> 01:03:48.360
sloth in the rainforest, it looked

01:03:48.360 --> 01:03:50.940
infected and disgusting, crawling with

01:03:50.940 --> 01:03:51.420
insects.

01:03:51.539 --> 01:03:54.480
Are you sure that's safe to eat?

01:03:54.539 --> 01:03:55.440
He asked.

01:03:55.500 --> 01:03:59.340
I'm the one who killed it, Marosio

01:03:59.340 --> 01:03:59.880
growled.

01:03:59.940 --> 01:04:01.860
I'm certainly going to eat it.

01:04:01.920 --> 01:04:04.559
But won't it make you sick?

01:04:04.619 --> 01:04:07.139
Marosier gave him a dark look.

01:04:07.199 --> 01:04:09.780
Night wings don't get sick.

01:04:09.900 --> 01:04:13.199
Don't tell me you have a weak stomach.

01:04:13.260 --> 01:04:15.539
In addition to everything else wrong with

01:04:15.539 --> 01:04:15.659
you.

01:04:15.780 --> 01:04:18.780
No, I don't think so.

01:04:18.840 --> 01:04:21.780
Starflight said, hoping he wasn't about

01:04:21.780 --> 01:04:23.400
to throw up and prove himself wrong.

01:04:23.460 --> 01:04:26.340
But look, there's probably horrible

01:04:26.340 --> 01:04:27.719
bacteria all through that wound.

01:04:27.840 --> 01:04:31.980
Of course, there is, Marasier said.

01:04:32.039 --> 01:04:33.539
How do you think it died?

01:04:33.599 --> 01:04:35.699
My bite infected it.

01:04:35.760 --> 01:04:37.079
That's...

01:04:37.079 --> 01:04:39.539
He paused, frowning at Starflight.

01:04:39.599 --> 01:04:42.420
Isn't this how you hunt too?

01:04:42.480 --> 01:04:45.059
Starflight glanced down at the horrible

01:04:45.059 --> 01:04:46.139
smelling bird.

01:04:46.199 --> 01:04:48.300
He had a feeling he shouldn't admit that

01:04:48.300 --> 01:04:50.519
so far, Clay had done most of the hunting

01:04:50.519 --> 01:04:52.679
since they left the mountain, but he also

01:04:52.679 --> 01:04:54.539
didn't want to admit that he didn't

01:04:54.539 --> 01:04:55.440
understand this at all.

01:04:55.500 --> 01:04:59.159
Use your brain, he told himself.

01:04:59.219 --> 01:05:00.599
You can figure this out.

01:05:00.659 --> 01:05:06.539
You bite your prey, he said slowly, and

01:05:06.539 --> 01:05:07.800
then you wait for it to die.

01:05:07.920 --> 01:05:10.800
And then you find it, and eat it.

01:05:10.860 --> 01:05:13.260
Once it's already dead and rotting.

01:05:13.320 --> 01:05:15.480
But it doesn't make you sick.

01:05:15.539 --> 01:05:18.300
He squinted at Maru Seer's teeth.

01:05:18.360 --> 01:05:20.699
There's something in your mouth that

01:05:20.699 --> 01:05:22.500
kills them, even if the bite itself

01:05:22.500 --> 01:05:23.219
wasn't fatal.

01:05:23.280 --> 01:05:24.599
Is it venom?

01:05:24.659 --> 01:05:26.579
Marusir shook his head.

01:05:26.639 --> 01:05:29.820
Some night wings think so.

01:05:29.880 --> 01:05:34.079
But none of our scientists have been able

01:05:34.079 --> 01:05:37.079
to find any when they examine our tribe's

01:05:37.079 --> 01:05:39.900
corpses, nor have we had any success

01:05:39.900 --> 01:05:42.300
replicating rain wing venom shooting.

01:05:42.360 --> 01:05:45.360
He scowled at the bird, and abruptly

01:05:45.360 --> 01:05:46.440
ripped off one of its wings.

01:05:46.500 --> 01:05:50.699
You may have this, he said ungenerously

01:05:50.699 --> 01:05:52.320
tossing it at Starflight.

01:05:52.380 --> 01:05:54.599
Starflight jumped back to avoid catching

01:05:54.599 --> 01:05:56.699
it, and the wing splattered to the ground

01:05:56.699 --> 01:05:57.360
in front of him.

01:05:57.420 --> 01:06:00.179
Several wrigley things crawled out of it

01:06:00.179 --> 01:06:01.679
and he closed his eyes quickly.

01:06:01.739 --> 01:06:04.260
Um, he said.

01:06:04.320 --> 01:06:05.579
No, thank you.

01:06:05.639 --> 01:06:08.820
Morosea already had his teeth buried in

01:06:08.820 --> 01:06:10.559
the underbelly of the albatross.

01:06:10.679 --> 01:06:12.599
He tore off a mouthful and chewed for a

01:06:12.599 --> 01:06:14.880
moment, staring narrowly at Starflight.

01:06:14.940 --> 01:06:17.639
What do you think you're going to eat?

01:06:17.699 --> 01:06:18.780
He barked.

01:06:18.840 --> 01:06:21.179
This is the Nightwing Way.

01:06:21.239 --> 01:06:25.019
I'll catch something else, Starflight

01:06:25.019 --> 01:06:25.380
said.

01:06:25.440 --> 01:06:26.639
He glanced around.

01:06:26.699 --> 01:06:28.980
A turtle or a lizard or something.

01:06:29.039 --> 01:06:32.639
I'm starting to see why you're so

01:06:32.639 --> 01:06:33.659
useless.

01:06:33.659 --> 01:06:35.280
Marasier hissed.

01:06:35.340 --> 01:06:37.559
No one's ever taught you to be a night

01:06:37.559 --> 01:06:37.860
wing.

01:06:37.920 --> 01:06:41.039
We assumed you'd be born superior like

01:06:41.039 --> 01:06:43.920
the rest of us, but perhaps you're

01:06:43.920 --> 01:06:44.460
defective.

01:06:44.519 --> 01:06:48.179
Well, you don't have time for delicate

01:06:48.179 --> 01:06:50.400
sensibilities, and a lengthy turtle

01:06:50.400 --> 01:06:50.699
hunt.

01:06:50.760 --> 01:06:53.400
Eat the wing or starve.

01:06:53.519 --> 01:06:56.940
Star of Light was too intrigued by this

01:06:56.940 --> 01:06:59.579
strange biological phenomenon to register

01:06:59.579 --> 01:07:01.619
that he'd just been called defective as

01:07:01.619 --> 01:07:02.400
well as useless.

01:07:02.460 --> 01:07:06.719
Listen, it might not make you sick, but I

01:07:06.719 --> 01:07:09.000
think it would make me sick, Starflight

01:07:09.000 --> 01:07:09.239
said.

01:07:09.300 --> 01:07:11.219
He wished he could write all this down.

01:07:11.280 --> 01:07:13.559
Were there any scrolls about nightwing

01:07:13.559 --> 01:07:15.059
bites and what they did to their prey?

01:07:15.119 --> 01:07:18.119
Maybe he could study the tribe and write

01:07:18.119 --> 01:07:18.719
the 1st one.

01:07:18.780 --> 01:07:22.079
I'm not used to eating infected carrion.

01:07:22.139 --> 01:07:24.780
Scientifically, I would assume it's

01:07:24.780 --> 01:07:26.460
something you have to adjust to over time

01:07:26.460 --> 01:07:28.260
as your dragonettes will have done

01:07:28.260 --> 01:07:30.599
growing up with a diet like this, but I

01:07:30.599 --> 01:07:32.159
won't have the correct antibodies to keep

01:07:32.159 --> 01:07:32.460
me safe.

01:07:32.519 --> 01:07:34.320
It's not worth the risk.

01:07:34.380 --> 01:07:38.039
The enormous black dragon had paused mid

01:07:37.320 --> 01:07:39.659
bite, and was staring at Starflight with

01:07:39.659 --> 01:07:40.139
his mouth open.

01:07:40.199 --> 01:07:45.300
Well, he said after a long moment, that

01:07:45.300 --> 01:07:46.679
answers that question.

01:07:46.739 --> 01:07:48.539
What question?

01:07:48.659 --> 01:07:49.800
Starfight asked.

01:07:49.920 --> 01:07:52.500
Maro Seer picked at his teeth with one

01:07:52.500 --> 01:07:54.420
claw and lashed his tail.

01:07:54.480 --> 01:07:57.960
Now I know who your father is.
1847
01:07:58,019 --> 01:08:02,219	Chapter 4.

01:08:02.519 --> 01:08:06.059
The wind off the ocean seized the tree

01:08:06.059 --> 01:08:07.739
branches and rattled them fiercely.

01:08:07.800 --> 01:08:10.139
Starflight dug his talons into the

01:08:10.139 --> 01:08:10.320
ground.

01:08:10.380 --> 01:08:13.019
It wasn't that he'd forgotten to wonder

01:08:13.019 --> 01:08:14.099
who his parents were.

01:08:14.159 --> 01:08:16.439
It was more that he was terrified to hear

01:08:16.439 --> 01:08:16.920
the answer.

01:08:16.979 --> 01:08:21.719
A father like Maroser, or vengeance, or a

01:08:21.719 --> 01:08:24.059
mother like greatness, or fierce teeth.

01:08:24.180 --> 01:08:26.100
Perhaps it would be better never to find

01:08:26.100 --> 01:08:29.100
out, rather than have his dreams meet the

01:08:29.100 --> 01:08:30.239
inevitably awful reality.

01:08:30.359 --> 01:08:34.499
But suddenly, the idea that a real dragon

01:08:34.499 --> 01:08:37.259
somewhere on this island, was connected

01:08:37.259 --> 01:08:40.079
to him, and might care about him was

01:08:40.079 --> 01:08:41.219
almost too much to bear.

01:08:41.279 --> 01:08:44.699
It's what Sonny and I always talked about

01:08:44.699 --> 01:08:46.319
finding our parents.

01:08:46.380 --> 01:08:48.539
My father?

01:08:48.659 --> 01:08:49.560
He whispered.

01:08:49.680 --> 01:08:52.260
Didn't you know who he was before?

01:08:52.319 --> 01:08:56.279
There were a few possibilities.

01:08:56.279 --> 01:09:00.059
Maro seer said grimly, but only one other

01:09:00.059 --> 01:09:02.159
dragon I know talks like you.

01:09:02.279 --> 01:09:05.159
He talks like me.

01:09:05.220 --> 01:09:09.659
Well, this is guaranteed to make him even

01:09:09.659 --> 01:09:10.800
more insufferable.

01:09:10.859 --> 01:09:13.559
Maro Sierr muttered, shredding the other

01:09:13.559 --> 01:09:15.599
albatross wing and stuffing scraps of

01:09:15.599 --> 01:09:16.199
meat in his mouth.

01:09:16.260 --> 01:09:20.100
He's been claiming it was his egg for the

01:09:20.100 --> 01:09:20.819
last 6 years.

01:09:20.880 --> 01:09:23.460
Can I meet him?

01:09:23.520 --> 01:09:24.779
Starflight asked.

01:09:24.840 --> 01:09:27.539
Oh, there's no getting out of that.

01:09:27.659 --> 01:09:30.300
Morris here's tail twitched.

01:09:30.359 --> 01:09:32.579
I'm surprised he didn't track you down

01:09:32.579 --> 01:09:34.139
the moment you were dragged in.

01:09:34.199 --> 01:09:36.420
Must be in the middle of another big

01:09:36.420 --> 01:09:37.439
experiment.

01:09:37.500 --> 01:09:41.399
Nose in his scrolls, probably hasn't even

01:09:41.399 --> 01:09:43.020
noticed that we're about to go to war.

01:09:43.079 --> 01:09:45.479
He wants to meet me.

01:09:45.600 --> 01:09:47.100
He'll be looking for me.

01:09:47.159 --> 01:09:49.739
What about my mother?

01:09:49.800 --> 01:09:51.180
Starflight asked.

01:09:51.239 --> 01:09:53.399
Could I meet her?

01:09:53.460 --> 01:09:57.659
No, Marasir said, plucking a feather off

01:09:57.659 --> 01:09:58.140
his tongue.

01:09:58.260 --> 01:10:01.140
Dead. died a few years ago.

01:10:01.199 --> 01:10:02.880
Oh.

01:10:03.000 --> 01:10:05.880
Starfly didn't understand the wave of

01:10:05.880 --> 01:10:08.159
sadness that seemed to punch him in the

01:10:08.159 --> 01:10:08.699
chest.

01:10:08.760 --> 01:10:09.960
He had known her.

01:10:10.020 --> 01:10:12.239
She'd agreed to give up her egg for the

01:10:12.239 --> 01:10:14.159
prophecy, so she couldn't have been very

01:10:14.159 --> 01:10:14.819
attached to him.

01:10:14.880 --> 01:10:17.819
She was probably as bad as Coral or

01:10:17.819 --> 01:10:18.659
Clay's mother.

01:10:18.720 --> 01:10:22.619
Still, how did she die?

01:10:22.680 --> 01:10:25.380
Starflight tried not to look at the mess

01:10:25.619 --> 01:10:27.899
Maro Seer was making of the albatross.

01:10:27.960 --> 01:10:30.119
Dune and Kestrel had always insisted on

01:10:30.119 --> 01:10:32.220
strict table manners and cleanliness

01:10:32.220 --> 01:10:34.260
since they were all trapped under the

01:10:34.260 --> 01:10:36.539
mountain together, in just a few caves

01:10:36.539 --> 01:10:38.819
with nowhere to escape to if someone ate

01:10:38.819 --> 01:10:40.680
their prey in a loud, annoying way.

01:10:40.800 --> 01:10:44.460
She got herself involved in a battle.

01:10:44.520 --> 01:10:47.220
Tried to help a sea wing had been

01:10:47.220 --> 01:10:48.779
attacked by two sky wings.

01:10:48.840 --> 01:10:50.760
Marosea grunted.

01:10:50.939 --> 01:10:52.079
Idiot.

01:10:52.140 --> 01:10:54.840
So obviously, you didn't get that brain

01:10:54.840 --> 01:10:55.500
from her.

01:10:55.560 --> 01:10:58.739
He narrowed his eyes at Starflight. and

01:10:58.739 --> 01:11:00.359
waved one of the bird bones at him.

01:11:00.479 --> 01:11:01.979
Enough.

01:11:02.039 --> 01:11:04.380
I have questions for you.

01:11:04.439 --> 01:11:08.460
I really don't know anything, Starflight

01:11:08.460 --> 01:11:09.060
said in a hurry.

01:11:09.119 --> 01:11:12.720
How dangerous is that rain wing?

01:11:12.779 --> 01:11:15.119
Marasier asked, ignoring him.

01:11:15.180 --> 01:11:19.560
Our studies indicate that most rain wings

01:11:19.560 --> 01:11:21.720
care only about themselves and prefer

01:11:21.720 --> 01:11:22.859
everything to be easy.

01:11:22.979 --> 01:11:24.600
Accurate.

01:11:24.659 --> 01:11:26.520
Starflight nodded.

01:11:26.579 --> 01:11:28.739
He really desperately didn't want to

01:11:28.739 --> 01:11:31.319
betray glory in any way, but he couldn't

01:11:31.319 --> 01:11:33.300
think of a way to avoid Morris Seer's

01:11:33.300 --> 01:11:35.640
questions or lied to him when Morris Seer

01:11:35.640 --> 01:11:37.199
was sure to read the truth in his mind.

01:11:37.260 --> 01:11:40.619
To his surprise, Moros Sears shoulders

01:11:40.619 --> 01:11:41.159
relaxed.

01:11:41.220 --> 01:11:43.619
That's what I thought.

01:11:43.680 --> 01:11:44.880
He said.

01:11:44.939 --> 01:11:47.460
So perhaps they won't do anything.

01:11:47.579 --> 01:11:50.279
Perhaps they'll roll over and go back to

01:11:50.279 --> 01:11:50.579
sleep.

01:11:50.640 --> 01:11:54.479
Starflight realized that Marosier had

01:11:54.479 --> 01:11:55.199
misunderstood him.

01:11:55.260 --> 01:11:58.020
He'd only meant that laziness was true of

01:11:58.020 --> 01:12:00.539
most rain wings, but the Night Wing had

01:12:00.539 --> 01:12:01.979
heard that it was true of glory as well.

01:12:02.039 --> 01:12:06.000
Maybe, he said non-committally.

01:12:06.060 --> 01:12:08.159
He tried not to think about how glory

01:12:08.159 --> 01:12:10.380
would never let this go, how she would

01:12:10.380 --> 01:12:12.359
fight tooth and claw to rescue the rain

01:12:12.359 --> 01:12:13.140
wing prisoners.

01:12:13.199 --> 01:12:15.960
It had been strange seeing her like that

01:12:15.960 --> 01:12:18.840
as if she'd borrowed tsunami's ferocity

01:12:18.840 --> 01:12:19.380
for a day.

01:12:19.439 --> 01:12:21.840
For years, Glory had acted as though she

01:12:21.840 --> 01:12:22.619
didn't care about anything.

01:12:22.680 --> 01:12:25.619
But apparently, imprisoning and torturing

01:12:25.619 --> 01:12:27.420
members of her tribe was one way to get

01:12:27.420 --> 01:12:27.840
her attention.

01:12:27.899 --> 01:12:30.840
He remembered what a council had said.

01:12:30.899 --> 01:12:33.899
What plan was the council talking about?

01:12:34.020 --> 01:12:34.979
He asked.

01:12:35.039 --> 01:12:38.520
What is it we don't want the rain wings

01:12:38.520 --> 01:12:38.760
to know?

01:12:38.880 --> 01:12:42.060
He stumbled over the words, trying to say

01:12:42.060 --> 01:12:44.399
we, as if he could be part of this

01:12:44.399 --> 01:12:44.880
tribe.

01:12:44.939 --> 01:12:47.399
But he wanted Marosier to feel as if

01:12:47.399 --> 01:12:49.680
Starflight was on his side, that he could

01:12:49.680 --> 01:12:50.159
be trusted.

01:12:50.220 --> 01:12:53.039
It was a trick he'd seen Sonny use a few

01:12:53.039 --> 01:12:54.659
times when glory and tsunami were

01:12:54.659 --> 01:12:54.960
fighting.

01:12:55.020 --> 01:12:57.659
Why are we mad at tsunami today?

01:12:57.779 --> 01:12:59.819
Now, what has glory done to us?

01:12:59.880 --> 01:13:01.680
And it often worked.

01:13:01.739 --> 01:13:03.300
Not this time, though.

01:13:03.359 --> 01:13:07.680
The less you know, the better, Morrisier

01:13:07.680 --> 01:13:08.159
snapped.

01:13:08.220 --> 01:13:10.319
You'll get less trouble that way.

01:13:10.380 --> 01:13:13.439
That wasn't generally Starflight's

01:13:13.439 --> 01:13:13.859
philosophy.

01:13:13.920 --> 01:13:16.319
He'd say knowing more was always better

01:13:16.319 --> 01:13:17.100
than knowing less.

01:13:17.159 --> 01:13:20.279
Moro Seer ripped the last chunk of flesh

01:13:20.279 --> 01:13:22.199
off the bird and spat out several more

01:13:22.199 --> 01:13:22.619
feathers.

01:13:22.680 --> 01:13:26.880
If you're determined to starve, he

01:13:26.880 --> 01:13:29.039
muttered, and devour the wing, he'd

01:13:29.039 --> 01:13:30.720
thrown to Starflight in a few bites.

01:13:30.779 --> 01:13:33.539
Very well, he grumbled.

01:13:33.600 --> 01:13:36.000
Let's go see mastermind.

01:13:36.060 --> 01:13:38.159
He flung the remains of the bird into the

01:13:38.159 --> 01:13:40.079
bushes and jumped into the sky.

01:13:40.140 --> 01:13:43.920
Then I'll take you to the alternate. he

01:13:43.920 --> 01:13:44.640
said over his shoulder.

01:13:44.699 --> 01:13:46.439
The what?

01:13:46.500 --> 01:13:47.819
Starflight asked.

01:13:47.880 --> 01:13:50.399
But Maro Seer was winging away quickly

01:13:50.399 --> 01:13:51.479
and didn't look back.

01:13:51.539 --> 01:13:54.539
Starflight followed him, still thinking

01:13:54.539 --> 01:13:56.100
about the way Nightwings hunted.

01:13:56.159 --> 01:13:58.979
It explained a few things, including the

01:13:58.979 --> 01:14:00.899
bad breath on all the dragonettes in the

01:14:00.899 --> 01:14:01.439
dormitory.

01:14:01.500 --> 01:14:04.260
Oddly, Deathbringer didn't seem to have

01:14:04.260 --> 01:14:04.859
the same smell.

01:14:04.920 --> 01:14:08.039
Starflight wondered if the assassin spent

01:14:08.039 --> 01:14:09.479
more time on the continent than other

01:14:09.479 --> 01:14:11.399
night wings and had learned to prefer

01:14:11.399 --> 01:14:13.560
live prey over carrion, like most

01:14:13.560 --> 01:14:14.460
dragons.

01:14:14.520 --> 01:14:17.399
Ahead of them, the Nightwing Fortress

01:14:17.399 --> 01:14:19.680
loomed. black against the gray sky.

01:14:19.739 --> 01:14:22.680
It was massive, built in layers that

01:14:22.680 --> 01:14:24.720
wrapped halfway around the mountain, but

01:14:24.720 --> 01:14:27.300
it also looked somehow precarious, as if

01:14:27.300 --> 01:14:29.819
one rock shelf could shift underneath it

01:14:29.819 --> 01:14:31.380
and the whole thing might suddenly slide

01:14:31.380 --> 01:14:32.520
all the way into the ocean.

01:14:32.579 --> 01:14:36.479
In fact, Starflight squinted.

01:14:36.539 --> 01:14:38.399
It was hard to see at first.

01:14:38.460 --> 01:14:41.939
Black on black in the dark, smoky air, but

01:14:41.939 --> 01:14:43.680
as they got closer, he was sure.

01:14:43.739 --> 01:14:46.800
Part of the fortress had been swallowed

01:14:46.800 --> 01:14:50.100
by lava, clearly some time ago, a whole

01:14:50.100 --> 01:14:52.199
corner of the building, at least as big

01:14:52.199 --> 01:14:54.840
as Queen Scarlet's Gladiator Arena, was

01:14:54.840 --> 01:14:56.880
covered by a hardened mass of black rock

01:14:56.880 --> 01:14:57.359
bubbles.

01:14:57.420 --> 01:15:00.119
It looked like a giant dragon had reached

01:15:00.119 --> 01:15:02.220
out of the mountain and slammed its

01:15:02.220 --> 01:15:03.479
talons down over the walls.

01:15:03.539 --> 01:15:07.380
Starflight glanced up uneasily, had the

01:15:07.380 --> 01:15:09.300
plume of steam rising from the top of the

01:15:09.300 --> 01:15:09.840
volcano.

01:15:09.899 --> 01:15:13.680
Orange gold fire glowed from inside, and

01:15:13.680 --> 01:15:15.720
he knew that streams of molten lava ran

01:15:15.720 --> 01:15:17.399
down at least one face of the mountain

01:15:17.399 --> 01:15:19.739
toward the caves where the rain wings

01:15:19.739 --> 01:15:21.720
were trapped, if Glory's description was

01:15:21.720 --> 01:15:21.899
right.

01:15:21.960 --> 01:15:24.720
Surely another eruption could come any

01:15:24.720 --> 01:15:27.000
time, endangering the rest of the

01:15:27.000 --> 01:15:27.600
fortress.

01:15:27.659 --> 01:15:30.479
That thought made him even more nervous

01:15:30.479 --> 01:15:33.180
about following Morrisier back inside, but

01:15:33.180 --> 01:15:34.020
he didn't have much choice.

01:15:34.079 --> 01:15:36.720
The large night wing ducked into a mouth

01:15:36.720 --> 01:15:38.640
like opening on the highest level of the

01:15:38.640 --> 01:15:39.180
fortress.

01:15:39.239 --> 01:15:41.520
The tunnels here were lit with hanging

01:15:41.520 --> 01:15:43.979
chandeliers of torches, as well as the

01:15:43.979 --> 01:15:45.960
niches of coals Starflight had seen

01:15:45.960 --> 01:15:46.619
before.

01:15:46.680 --> 01:15:49.500
The stone under his talons felt smoother

01:15:49.500 --> 01:15:51.600
and more polished, as if it was

01:15:51.600 --> 01:15:53.880
frequently swept or mopped, unlike the

01:15:53.880 --> 01:15:54.539
lower tunnels.

01:15:54.600 --> 01:15:57.359
Starflight thought of the gold dragon

01:15:57.359 --> 01:15:58.739
prints in the sky palace.

01:15:58.800 --> 01:16:01.500
The emerald studded throne in the kingdom

01:16:01.500 --> 01:16:04.020
of the sea, and the colorful flowers that

01:16:04.020 --> 01:16:06.000
wound all around the rain wing village.

01:16:06.060 --> 01:16:07.739
There was nothing like that here.

01:16:07.800 --> 01:16:10.260
Nothing to break out the monotony of the

01:16:10.260 --> 01:16:12.659
stone walls, nothing to showcase the

01:16:12.659 --> 01:16:14.279
wealth and power of the night wings.

01:16:14.340 --> 01:16:17.880
Then again, I guess no one ever comes

01:16:17.880 --> 01:16:19.140
here, he thought.

01:16:19.199 --> 01:16:21.600
Instead of trying to impress other

01:16:21.600 --> 01:16:24.300
dragons with opulence, they do it with

01:16:24.300 --> 01:16:25.079
mystery.

01:16:25.140 --> 01:16:27.359
He could see how that would make sense.

01:16:27.420 --> 01:16:29.340
But it would have been nice to see

01:16:29.340 --> 01:16:31.560
something besides fire and rock in all

01:16:31.560 --> 01:16:32.699
directions.

01:16:32.760 --> 01:16:35.279
As they turned a corner, Starflight

01:16:35.279 --> 01:16:36.600
paused and looked back.

01:16:36.659 --> 01:16:39.720
He thought he'd heard, but maybe he was

01:16:39.720 --> 01:16:40.500
imagining things.

01:16:40.560 --> 01:16:45.239
But, It had sounded like claws, tip

01:16:45.239 --> 01:16:46.380
tapping on the stone behind them.

01:16:46.500 --> 01:16:50.100
He stared along the dark tunnel, and

01:16:50.100 --> 01:16:52.020
suddenly had a shivery feeling of hope.

01:16:52.079 --> 01:16:54.840
Maybe it's glory, he thought.

01:16:54.899 --> 01:16:58.439
Maybe she's here, and camouflaged.

01:16:58.500 --> 01:17:00.539
Maybe she's come to rescue me.

01:17:00.600 --> 01:17:03.180
He couldn't imagine how she would have

01:17:03.180 --> 01:17:05.399
gotten past the Nightwing guards who must

01:17:05.399 --> 01:17:06.539
be posted around the hole.

01:17:06.600 --> 01:17:10.260
In fact, if he were in charge, he just

01:17:10.260 --> 01:17:12.060
took a night wing in the tunnel at all

01:17:12.060 --> 01:17:14.279
times, just to be sure no one could

01:17:14.279 --> 01:17:15.539
invisibly squeeze by.

01:17:15.600 --> 01:17:17.939
But maybe the night wings weren't that

01:17:17.939 --> 01:17:18.180
smart.

01:17:18.239 --> 01:17:20.279
There it was again.

01:17:20.340 --> 01:17:22.739
Tap, tap, tap.

01:17:22.800 --> 01:17:24.720
Definitely talent.

01:17:24.779 --> 01:17:27.300
Although whoever it was wasn't doing a

01:17:27.300 --> 01:17:28.739
terrific job of being stealthy.

01:17:28.800 --> 01:17:31.920
Glory is much better at sneaking than

01:17:31.920 --> 01:17:32.159
that.

01:17:32.220 --> 01:17:33.960
Maybe clay?

01:17:34.020 --> 01:17:36.720
It was awful how much his chest hurt with

01:17:36.720 --> 01:17:37.079
hope.

01:17:37.199 --> 01:17:39.479
If only it were clay.

01:17:39.539 --> 01:17:41.880
If only that big brown head would poke

01:17:41.880 --> 01:17:44.279
around the band, see him, and grin.

01:17:44.399 --> 01:17:47.399
Starflight promised the universe that he

01:17:47.399 --> 01:17:49.739
would never, ever make fun of clay again

01:17:49.739 --> 01:17:51.899
if only the mud wing would suddenly be

01:17:51.899 --> 01:17:53.399
here, rescuing him.

01:17:53.460 --> 01:17:55.260
Keep up.

01:17:55.319 --> 01:17:57.539
Morrisio growled from up ahead.

01:17:57.600 --> 01:18:00.300
Starflight realized that he was really

01:18:00.300 --> 01:18:01.140
being an idiot.

01:18:01.199 --> 01:18:03.180
If someone were trying to sneak up behind

01:18:03.180 --> 01:18:04.859
them to rescue him.

01:18:04.920 --> 01:18:06.960
It wouldn't much help if Starflight stood

01:18:06.960 --> 01:18:07.859
there staring at them.

01:18:07.920 --> 01:18:10.739
He started to turn to follow Morris ear

01:18:10.739 --> 01:18:13.800
but just then, a head did poke around the

01:18:13.800 --> 01:18:14.220
last corner.

01:18:14.340 --> 01:18:20.220
It wasn't clay, or glory, or tsunami, or

01:18:20.220 --> 01:18:20.640
sunny.

01:18:20.699 --> 01:18:23.699
It was just a Nightwing Dragonette.

01:18:23.819 --> 01:18:26.220
She stared right at him for a startled

01:18:26.220 --> 01:18:28.140
moment, and then he shrugged and turned

01:18:28.140 --> 01:18:28.439
away.

01:18:28.500 --> 01:18:31.260
But at the same time, she yelped, oh my

01:18:31.260 --> 01:18:34.140
gosh, it's you. and bolted up to him

01:18:34.140 --> 01:18:35.699
grabbing his front talons.

01:18:35.760 --> 01:18:37.500
I had a vision about you.

01:18:37.619 --> 01:18:39.600
She declared grandly.

01:18:39.659 --> 01:18:41.819
He froze in the act of trying to pull his

01:18:41.819 --> 01:18:42.479
talons away.

01:18:42.539 --> 01:18:44.760
Have you had any visions about me?

01:18:44.819 --> 01:18:46.800
You did?

01:18:46.859 --> 01:18:48.840
Starflight said, blinking.

01:18:48.899 --> 01:18:50.760
She appeared to be his own age.

01:18:50.819 --> 01:18:53.460
So if she was having visions, that meant

01:18:53.460 --> 01:18:55.439
Dragonette did develop their powers

01:18:55.439 --> 01:18:57.600
before they were full grown, which meant

01:18:57.600 --> 01:18:59.640
Starflight should have something by now.

01:18:59.699 --> 01:19:01.140
But he didn't.

01:19:01.260 --> 01:19:03.659
Whenever he tried to read minds or see

01:19:03.659 --> 01:19:05.760
the future, it was like staring into the

01:19:05.760 --> 01:19:08.939
night sky, empty and cold and

01:19:08.939 --> 01:19:10.140
meaningless.

01:19:10.199 --> 01:19:12.539
He hadn't admitted that tomorrow, see her

01:19:12.539 --> 01:19:12.720
yet.

01:19:12.779 --> 01:19:14.939
Speaking of whom?

01:19:15.000 --> 01:19:17.939
The floor now trembled ominously, as the

01:19:17.939 --> 01:19:19.619
older night wing came thundering back

01:19:19.619 --> 01:19:22.260
along the tunnel to them, his eyes nearly

01:19:22.260 --> 01:19:23.939
popped out of his skull when he saw the

01:19:23.939 --> 01:19:24.779
new dragonette.

01:19:24.779 --> 01:19:26.819
Fate, speaker.

01:19:26.880 --> 01:19:29.939
He roared so loud, the Starflight thought

01:19:29.939 --> 01:19:31.619
the volcano might erupt right then.

01:19:31.619 --> 01:19:35.159
I told you to stay in your cave with the

01:19:35.159 --> 01:19:35.460
others.

01:19:35.520 --> 01:19:38.939
I know, I heard you, she said cheerfully

01:19:38.939 --> 01:19:41.399
but I got bored, and I wanted to explore

01:19:41.399 --> 01:19:43.439
and I saw you flying by, so I thought I'd

01:19:43.439 --> 01:19:43.800
come too.

01:19:43.859 --> 01:19:46.020
I can't believe I'm in the Nightwing

01:19:46.020 --> 01:19:46.859
Fortress at last.

01:19:46.920 --> 01:19:50.100
I have had lots of prophetic dreams about

01:19:50.100 --> 01:19:50.640
it, you know.

01:19:50.760 --> 01:19:53.760
She said conspiratorially to Starflight.

01:19:53.819 --> 01:19:56.100
She still had his front talons pressed

01:19:56.100 --> 01:19:56.640
between hers.

01:19:56.760 --> 01:19:59.159
Although, in those, it was actually

01:19:59.159 --> 01:20:01.859
bigger and lighter, and smelled way less

01:20:01.859 --> 01:20:04.199
terrible, plus it had a lot more treasure

01:20:04.199 --> 01:20:07.020
and seriously less grouchy dragons.

01:20:07.079 --> 01:20:08.819
She thought for a moment.

01:20:08.880 --> 01:20:09.840
Hmm.

01:20:09.960 --> 01:20:12.359
Maybe they were just regular dreams.

01:20:12.420 --> 01:20:14.880
Fate speaker.

01:20:14.939 --> 01:20:16.920
Maro Seer hissed.

01:20:16.979 --> 01:20:20.039
What did I say about keeping your visions

01:20:20.039 --> 01:20:20.760
to yourself?

01:20:20.819 --> 01:20:24.119
You said, shut up about your visions.

01:20:24.180 --> 01:20:25.260
I'm not remotely interested.

01:20:25.319 --> 01:20:28.319
Fate speaker answered, but that doesn't

01:20:28.319 --> 01:20:30.779
mean this dragon isn't interested.

01:20:30.840 --> 01:20:31.739
Aren't you interested?

01:20:31.800 --> 01:20:33.479
she said to Starflight.

01:20:33.539 --> 01:20:36.899
He was, but he did not think it would be

01:20:36.899 --> 01:20:39.060
wise to admit that in front of Marosier

01:20:39.060 --> 01:20:41.460
who had smoke rising from his nostrils.

01:20:41.520 --> 01:20:44.220
Starfly tried to study the dragonette

01:20:44.220 --> 01:20:45.359
without obviously staring.

01:20:45.420 --> 01:20:48.720
Fate speaker's black scales shimmered

01:20:48.720 --> 01:20:50.460
with underscales of deep blue and

01:20:50.460 --> 01:20:50.880
purple.

01:20:51.000 --> 01:20:52.859
Like Starflight's wings.

01:20:52.920 --> 01:20:55.260
Hers were scattered with silver scales on

01:20:55.260 --> 01:20:57.359
the underside, so they looked like part

01:20:57.359 --> 01:21:00.300
of the night sky, but unlike his, face

01:21:00.300 --> 01:21:02.460
speaker had several extra silver scales

01:21:02.460 --> 01:21:05.460
one at the outside corner of each eye, a

01:21:05.460 --> 01:21:08.100
band circling one ankle, and a few lone

01:21:08.100 --> 01:21:10.319
ones sparkling along her tail like starry

01:21:10.319 --> 01:21:10.800
freckles.

01:21:10.859 --> 01:21:14.100
Anyway, I just know you're terribly

01:21:14.100 --> 01:21:16.859
important, she said to him, releasing his

01:21:16.859 --> 01:21:19.140
talons and that we have a great destiny

01:21:19.140 --> 01:21:19.560
together.

01:21:19.619 --> 01:21:21.720
We do?

01:21:21.779 --> 01:21:23.340
He thought, hopefully.

01:21:23.399 --> 01:21:25.560
Perhaps he was going to survive the

01:21:25.560 --> 01:21:26.699
Nightwing Fortress after all.

01:21:26.819 --> 01:21:29.699
Am I actually useful in this great

01:21:29.699 --> 01:21:30.420
destiny?

01:21:30.479 --> 01:21:32.039
Are my friends there?

01:21:32.100 --> 01:21:33.479
Am I with Sonny?

01:21:33.539 --> 01:21:35.819
He wished to get asked her questions

01:21:35.819 --> 01:21:37.979
without Morrow's seer breathing furiously

01:21:37.979 --> 01:21:38.520
over their heads.

01:21:38.579 --> 01:21:41.399
Go back to the others.

01:21:41.399 --> 01:21:43.079
Maro seer ordered.

01:21:43.140 --> 01:21:44.939
Oh, can't I come with you?

01:21:45.000 --> 01:21:46.560
Fate speaker asked.

01:21:46.619 --> 01:21:48.659
She gave Marosia a pleading look.

01:21:48.720 --> 01:21:51.840
I foresee that I'll be really helpful

01:21:51.840 --> 01:21:53.520
with whatever you're about to do.

01:21:53.579 --> 01:21:55.439
Also, that I'll find it totally

01:21:55.439 --> 01:21:56.100
interesting.

01:21:56.159 --> 01:22:00.899
I don't think that counts as foreseeing

01:22:00.899 --> 01:22:02.039
Starflight said.

01:22:02.100 --> 01:22:03.899
It sounds more like guessing.

01:22:04.020 --> 01:22:07.140
Mario CR growled deep in his throat.

01:22:07.199 --> 01:22:08.640
Very well.

01:22:08.699 --> 01:22:12.359
Keep your mouth shut, and don't get in

01:22:12.359 --> 01:22:12.720
the way.

01:22:12.779 --> 01:22:17.159
As if I would, fate speaker said happily

01:22:17.159 --> 01:22:19.079
immediately tripping Starflight with her

01:22:19.079 --> 01:22:19.319
tail.

01:22:19.380 --> 01:22:23.039
Maro Seer stomped away, muttering, Fate

01:22:23.039 --> 01:22:25.319
speaker gave Starflight an enormous smile

01:22:25.319 --> 01:22:27.000
that reminded him of Sonny.

01:22:27.060 --> 01:22:29.880
He wondered if Sonny missed him, and

01:22:29.880 --> 01:22:31.680
whether she felt anything like the ache

01:22:31.680 --> 01:22:33.420
that filled his chest whenever he thought

01:22:33.420 --> 01:22:33.779
of her.

01:22:33.840 --> 01:22:36.840
Oh my, sad face.

01:22:36.899 --> 01:22:40.140
Fate speaker said, nudging Starflight's

01:22:40.140 --> 01:22:41.340
wing as they walked.

01:22:41.399 --> 01:22:41.880
Cheer up.

01:22:41.939 --> 01:22:42.840
What's your name?

01:22:42.899 --> 01:22:45.720
That wasn't in your vision?

01:22:45.840 --> 01:22:48.119
Starflight tilted his head curiously.

01:22:48.180 --> 01:22:50.579
He'd always wondered how much detail the

01:22:50.579 --> 01:22:51.180
visions had.

01:22:51.239 --> 01:22:53.880
The prophecy Morrow Seer had delivered

01:22:53.880 --> 01:22:56.760
years ago was remarkably cryptic, but

01:22:56.760 --> 01:22:58.260
perhaps there was more information in the

01:22:58.260 --> 01:23:00.539
seer's head that he hadn't shared.

01:23:00.600 --> 01:23:04.500
Um, Fate speaker wobbled her head back

01:23:04.500 --> 01:23:06.420
and forth, squinting thoughtfully at

01:23:06.420 --> 01:23:06.600
him.

01:23:06.659 --> 01:23:08.520
Oh, of course.

01:23:08.579 --> 01:23:09.899
Big toes.

01:23:09.960 --> 01:23:11.220
What?

01:23:11.340 --> 01:23:14.460
Starflight glanced down at his talons, a

01:23:14.460 --> 01:23:15.180
little offended.

01:23:15.239 --> 01:23:18.060
No, no, it's Starflight.

01:23:18.119 --> 01:23:20.100
Oh, she said.

01:23:20.159 --> 01:23:21.119
Are you sure?

01:23:21.180 --> 01:23:22.920
Quite sure.

01:23:23.039 --> 01:23:24.960
She shrugged.

01:23:25.020 --> 01:23:26.399
Well, I was close.

01:23:26.460 --> 01:23:28.979
Hi, Starflight, I'm fate speaker.

01:23:29.039 --> 01:23:30.600
You're probably wondering why you've

01:23:30.600 --> 01:23:31.380
never seen me before.

01:23:31.439 --> 01:23:34.439
Starflight paused midstep and frowned at

01:23:34.439 --> 01:23:34.619
her.

01:23:34.680 --> 01:23:35.819
Am I?

01:23:35.880 --> 01:23:37.739
It's because I didn't grow up here.

01:23:37.800 --> 01:23:41.039
She carried on blithely, without noticing

01:23:41.039 --> 01:23:41.520
his reaction.

01:23:41.640 --> 01:23:44.460
Moro Seeor's growl echoed down the

01:23:44.460 --> 01:23:46.439
corridor, and they both started walking

01:23:46.439 --> 01:23:46.920
faster.

01:23:46.979 --> 01:23:49.380
I only got to the island yesterday.

01:23:49.439 --> 01:23:52.380
I know this is going to sound crazy, but

01:23:52.380 --> 01:23:54.659
I was raised by the talons of peace.

01:23:54.720 --> 01:23:57.899
Starflight, walked straight into a

01:23:57.899 --> 01:23:58.619
chandelier.

01:23:58.680 --> 01:24:00.779
He staggered back, his head spinning.

01:24:00.899 --> 01:24:04.500
Oh, ouch, fate speaker said.

01:24:04.560 --> 01:24:06.479
She patted his shoulder gingerly.

01:24:06.539 --> 01:24:07.920
That looked painful.

01:24:07.979 --> 01:24:10.800
Anyway, so it turns out I'm part of that

01:24:10.800 --> 01:24:12.960
big dragonette prophecy everyone is so

01:24:12.960 --> 01:24:13.739
excited about.

01:24:13.800 --> 01:24:14.819
Can you believe it?

01:24:14.880 --> 01:24:18.420
No, Starflight thought.

01:24:18.479 --> 01:24:22.260
I'm the wings of night, she said

01:24:22.260 --> 01:24:22.739
proudly.

01:24:22.800 --> 01:24:25.260
Morris here says it's up to me to stop

01:24:25.260 --> 01:24:25.560
the war.

01:24:25.619 --> 01:24:28.260
For some reason, he seems kind of grumpy

01:24:28.260 --> 01:24:28.859
about that.

01:24:28.920 --> 01:24:32.819
Starflight felt all his hope, flicker, and

01:24:32.819 --> 01:24:33.119
go out.

01:24:33.180 --> 01:24:36.600
He'd been praying quietly that maybe this

01:24:36.600 --> 01:24:38.220
was another night wing intervention to

01:24:38.220 --> 01:24:39.359
point him in the right direction.

01:24:39.420 --> 01:24:42.359
He'd hoped, perhaps, he'd be given

01:24:42.359 --> 01:24:44.640
another lecture, and then sent back to

01:24:44.640 --> 01:24:45.060
his friends.

01:24:45.119 --> 01:24:48.239
But apparently, fierce teeth was right.

01:24:48.359 --> 01:24:50.520
He was here because he'd failed.

01:24:50.579 --> 01:24:54.000
And fate speaker was his replacement.
2329
01:24:54,060 --> 01:24:58,260	Chapter 5.

01:24:58.619 --> 01:25:00.960
It made sense.

01:25:01.020 --> 01:25:04.020
Fate speaker had powers, and Starflight

01:25:04.020 --> 01:25:04.380
did not.

01:25:04.439 --> 01:25:07.079
He'd failed to follow Morris here's

01:25:07.079 --> 01:25:07.979
orders more than once.

01:25:08.039 --> 01:25:11.399
He was a useless night wing and a useless

01:25:11.399 --> 01:25:12.300
dragonette of destiny.

01:25:12.359 --> 01:25:14.039
Wow.

01:25:14.100 --> 01:25:17.220
Fate speaker said, finally noticing his

01:25:17.220 --> 01:25:17.640
expression.

01:25:17.760 --> 01:25:20.760
You look like someone just ate your only

01:25:20.760 --> 01:25:21.720
walrus.

01:25:21.779 --> 01:25:22.859
Are you all right?

01:25:22.920 --> 01:25:26.460
I, Starfight began.

01:25:26.520 --> 01:25:27.779
I just thought...

01:25:27.779 --> 01:25:30.600
They came around a bend in the tunnel, and

01:25:30.600 --> 01:25:32.460
nearly stepped on Morrow Seer's tail.

01:25:32.520 --> 01:25:34.979
He gave them a glare that shut Starflight

01:25:34.979 --> 01:25:35.579
up in a hurry.

01:25:35.640 --> 01:25:38.640
Fate speaker, however, was undaunted.

01:25:38.760 --> 01:25:41.100
Labs.

01:25:41.159 --> 01:25:43.260
She read off the door in front of them.

01:25:43.319 --> 01:25:45.659
Ooh, what does that mean?

01:25:45.720 --> 01:25:48.960
It means don't touch anything?

01:25:49.020 --> 01:25:51.539
Moro seer said grimly.

01:25:51.600 --> 01:25:55.380
We are here, so Starflight can meet his

01:25:55.380 --> 01:25:55.739
father.

01:25:55.800 --> 01:26:00.180
If we're very unlucky, he'll have time to

01:26:00.180 --> 01:26:01.859
give us a tour of all the experiments

01:26:01.859 --> 01:26:04.199
he's working on, he hissed.

01:26:04.260 --> 01:26:06.479
Let's get this over with.

01:26:06.539 --> 01:26:09.600
The door swung open to reveal a huge

01:26:09.600 --> 01:26:10.020
room.

01:26:10.079 --> 01:26:13.380
More brightly lit and cleanly kept than

01:26:13.380 --> 01:26:14.880
any other part of the fortress that

01:26:14.880 --> 01:26:16.380
Starflight had seen.

01:26:16.439 --> 01:26:17.939
They were standing on a balcony.

01:26:18.000 --> 01:26:20.520
There was a level above them, and a level

01:26:20.520 --> 01:26:22.859
below them, and a crisscrossing network

01:26:22.859 --> 01:26:25.380
of strange pipes stretching across the

01:26:25.380 --> 01:26:26.159
space in front of them.

01:26:26.220 --> 01:26:29.399
No, no, cried a voice.

01:26:29.460 --> 01:26:32.100
A whip thin black dragon shot down from

01:26:32.100 --> 01:26:33.899
the top level and hovered in front of

01:26:33.899 --> 01:26:34.079
them.

01:26:34.140 --> 01:26:36.720
He wore an odd helmet over his whole head

01:26:36.720 --> 01:26:39.180
with only a few small holes poked in it

01:26:39.180 --> 01:26:41.460
for him to see out, rather like the

01:26:41.460 --> 01:26:43.619
queen's council screen Starfly thought.

01:26:43.680 --> 01:26:45.720
I must not be interrupted.

01:26:45.779 --> 01:26:48.479
This experiment is at a critical juncture

01:26:48.479 --> 01:26:51.119
and greatness says I might be shut down

01:26:51.119 --> 01:26:51.720
at any moment.

01:26:51.779 --> 01:26:53.640
Everyone, please leave.

01:26:53.699 --> 01:26:56.579
He flapped his wings and front talons at

01:26:56.579 --> 01:26:56.760
them.

01:26:56.819 --> 01:27:01.199
Mastermind, Maro Seer said coolly.

01:27:01.260 --> 01:27:03.659
It seems you are right all along.

01:27:03.779 --> 01:27:07.560
The dragonette from Bar Sights Egg is

01:27:07.560 --> 01:27:10.859
apparently your son, and he's here now, so

01:27:10.859 --> 01:27:12.000
I've brought him to meet you.

01:27:12.060 --> 01:27:15.720
Starfight tensed, expecting the other

01:27:15.720 --> 01:27:17.699
dragon to shrug and chew them away.

01:27:17.760 --> 01:27:20.699
But instead, Mastermind reached up and

01:27:20.699 --> 01:27:22.979
removed his helmet, revealing a snout

01:27:22.979 --> 01:27:25.680
pockmarked with little scars and curious

01:27:25.680 --> 01:27:26.399
bloodshot eyes.

01:27:26.460 --> 01:27:28.319
My son?

01:27:28.319 --> 01:27:29.399
he said.

01:27:29.460 --> 01:27:32.159
And Starflight felt a happy shiver at the

01:27:32.159 --> 01:27:33.359
tone of wonder in his voice.

01:27:33.420 --> 01:27:36.180
Mastermind landed on the balcony beside

01:27:36.180 --> 01:27:38.819
them, set his helmet on the floor, and

01:27:38.819 --> 01:27:40.619
took Starflight's shoulders in his

01:27:40.619 --> 01:27:41.100
talons.

01:27:41.220 --> 01:27:43.979
Three moons, he said.

01:27:44.039 --> 01:27:46.140
What a handsome dragonette.

01:27:46.199 --> 01:27:47.699
It does look like me.

01:27:47.760 --> 01:27:48.840
I knew he would.

01:27:48.899 --> 01:27:50.220
As I suspected.

01:27:50.279 --> 01:27:52.680
This jaw line is genetically dominant.

01:27:52.739 --> 01:27:55.380
He gestured to the same spot on himself

01:27:55.380 --> 01:27:56.640
and on Starflight.

01:27:56.699 --> 01:28:00.840
Ah, and yes, see the way the star scales

01:28:00.840 --> 01:28:03.539
on our wings spray outward like a splash

01:28:03.539 --> 01:28:04.140
of water.

01:28:04.199 --> 01:28:06.779
Whereas Morrow sears, for instance, curl

01:28:06.779 --> 01:28:08.760
inward, more like a snail shell.

01:28:08.819 --> 01:28:11.760
He flared one of his wings, and then

01:28:11.760 --> 01:28:13.920
reached for Maro's ears, but the larger

01:28:13.920 --> 01:28:15.779
night wing batted him away with a snarl.

01:28:15.840 --> 01:28:18.420
Whole theories at this point, of course.

01:28:18.539 --> 01:28:21.659
Mastermind said, and Starflight found

01:28:21.659 --> 01:28:23.579
himself smiling back at his father's

01:28:23.579 --> 01:28:24.420
toothy grin.

01:28:24.479 --> 01:28:27.420
A larger data set would naturally be

01:28:27.420 --> 01:28:30.300
essential for proving anything, but one

01:28:30.300 --> 01:28:31.680
is much better than none.

01:28:31.800 --> 01:28:35.399
Entirely wonderful, in fact, especially

01:28:35.399 --> 01:28:37.380
compared to most of the rest of the tribe

01:28:37.380 --> 01:28:40.020
including yourself, right, Mauricio?

01:28:40.079 --> 01:28:41.520
No dragonettes.

01:28:41.579 --> 01:28:42.300
As yet.

01:28:42.359 --> 01:28:45.420
Maro Sear's face indicated he did not

01:28:45.420 --> 01:28:47.279
intend to dignify that with a response.

01:28:47.340 --> 01:28:50.760
But I have a son.

01:28:50.880 --> 01:28:55.140
Mastermind said proudly, I, of all

01:28:55.140 --> 01:28:55.800
dragons.

01:28:55.859 --> 01:28:58.500
Let's see strong wings laugh now.

01:28:58.560 --> 01:29:01.739
Just wait until everyone sees my handsome

01:29:01.739 --> 01:29:02.220
offspring.

01:29:02.279 --> 01:29:05.340
He clapped Starflight's shoulder again.

01:29:05.399 --> 01:29:07.500
So strong and healthy.

01:29:07.560 --> 01:29:10.020
You can be the assistant I've been

01:29:10.020 --> 01:29:10.439
looking for.

01:29:10.500 --> 01:29:12.420
What are you interested in, son?

01:29:12.539 --> 01:29:14.460
Son.

01:29:14.520 --> 01:29:17.579
Starflight's needs felt as if they might

01:29:17.579 --> 01:29:19.140
not hold them up very well for much

01:29:19.140 --> 01:29:19.439
longer.

01:29:19.500 --> 01:29:23.520
Um, everything, he stammered.

01:29:23.579 --> 01:29:24.539
Scrolls.

01:29:24.600 --> 01:29:25.560
I like scrolls.

01:29:25.619 --> 01:29:28.859
Fantastic, mastermind said.

01:29:28.920 --> 01:29:30.359
I've lots of scrolls.

01:29:30.479 --> 01:29:32.579
How about desellenization?

01:29:32.640 --> 01:29:33.539
Know anything about it?

01:29:33.659 --> 01:29:35.460
Starflight perked up?

01:29:35.520 --> 01:29:36.720
A little.

01:29:36.779 --> 01:29:39.060
Taking the salt out of seawater to make

01:29:39.060 --> 01:29:39.960
it potable, right?

01:29:40.020 --> 01:29:41.640
Potable?

01:29:41.699 --> 01:29:43.619
Fate speaker interjected?

01:29:43.680 --> 01:29:45.840
She was watching them with wide, startled

01:29:45.840 --> 01:29:48.300
eyes, and Starlight remembered that she

01:29:48.300 --> 01:29:50.279
didn't know yet that he'd been raised

01:29:50.279 --> 01:29:51.600
away from the island too.

01:29:51.659 --> 01:29:54.840
Drinkable, Starfight explained.

01:29:54.899 --> 01:29:56.880
Is that what those pipes are for?

01:29:57.000 --> 01:30:01.020
Very good. said mastermind, waving his

01:30:01.020 --> 01:30:01.920
talons excitedly.

01:30:01.979 --> 01:30:04.920
We have only one freshwater source on the

01:30:04.920 --> 01:30:06.420
island, and it's become rather

01:30:06.420 --> 01:30:08.460
contaminated with ash over the last few

01:30:08.460 --> 01:30:08.760
years.

01:30:08.819 --> 01:30:11.880
So I invented this magnificent

01:30:11.880 --> 01:30:14.460
contraption to provide safe water for the

01:30:14.460 --> 01:30:15.119
entire tribe.

01:30:15.180 --> 01:30:19.199
He talked on and on, pointing to the

01:30:19.199 --> 01:30:20.760
various pipes and explaining the science

01:30:20.760 --> 01:30:22.140
behind the process.

01:30:22.199 --> 01:30:24.239
Starflight listened with a fascination.

01:30:24.300 --> 01:30:26.760
He'd never met a dragon who seemed so

01:30:26.760 --> 01:30:28.800
full of information, like a walking

01:30:28.800 --> 01:30:30.180
library of scrolls.

01:30:30.239 --> 01:30:32.100
Come, come.

01:30:32.159 --> 01:30:34.979
Mastermind said eagerly, gathering his

01:30:34.979 --> 01:30:36.420
helmet and leaping off the balcony.

01:30:36.479 --> 01:30:38.460
I'll show you what else I'm working on.

01:30:38.520 --> 01:30:41.460
Starflight glanced at Mario Cia for

01:30:41.460 --> 01:30:43.380
permission, and the large Nightwing

01:30:43.380 --> 01:30:44.939
rolled his eyes and sat down with a

01:30:44.939 --> 01:30:45.359
yawn.

01:30:45.420 --> 01:30:47.460
Fate speaker didn't wait to be invited.

01:30:47.520 --> 01:30:50.039
She flew behind them as mastermind led

01:30:50.039 --> 01:30:51.060
the way down to the bottom level.

01:30:51.180 --> 01:30:55.439
Here is where I do all my volcanology, he

01:30:55.439 --> 01:30:58.380
said, striding between tables laden with

01:30:58.380 --> 01:31:01.020
cauldrons of lava and steaming holes dug

01:31:01.020 --> 01:31:01.619
right into the ground.

01:31:01.680 --> 01:31:05.039
Well, I'm testing full materials that can

01:31:05.039 --> 01:31:07.739
withstand eruptions and working on scale

01:31:07.739 --> 01:31:10.140
models of barriers and outlining possible

01:31:10.140 --> 01:31:12.060
implementation systems.

01:31:12.119 --> 01:31:13.859
No wonder I need an assistant, right?

01:31:13.920 --> 01:31:18.180
This place is pretty cool, fate speaker

01:31:18.180 --> 01:31:20.579
said, glancing around at the volcano

01:31:20.579 --> 01:31:21.300
experiments.

01:31:21.359 --> 01:31:24.479
It's amazing, Starflight said.

01:31:24.600 --> 01:31:26.939
He peered down at the smoke issuing from

01:31:26.939 --> 01:31:27.659
a deep hole.

01:31:27.720 --> 01:31:30.119
He wanted to study each section of the

01:31:30.119 --> 01:31:31.439
lab in careful detail.

01:31:31.500 --> 01:31:33.720
There was a strange contraption in the

01:31:33.720 --> 01:31:35.460
corner that looked as if it was designed

01:31:35.460 --> 01:31:38.399
to fit entirely around a dragon and then

01:31:38.399 --> 01:31:39.300
be filled with something.

01:31:39.359 --> 01:31:40.800
Water maybe?

01:31:40.859 --> 01:31:42.779
He couldn't even imagine.

01:31:42.840 --> 01:31:46.260
He already had a 1000000 questions, and a

01:31:46.260 --> 01:31:48.060
couple of ideas about lava that might be

01:31:48.060 --> 01:31:50.220
worth testing, if his dad didn't mind

01:31:50.220 --> 01:31:51.000
some suggestions.

01:31:51.060 --> 01:31:54.359
Mastermind flicked his tail at a corner

01:31:54.359 --> 01:31:56.640
of the lab where tiny versions of the

01:31:56.640 --> 01:31:58.560
mountain had been constructed, with

01:31:58.560 --> 01:32:00.180
little fortresses stuck on the side.

01:32:00.239 --> 01:32:02.760
Several of them were already smoldering

01:32:02.760 --> 01:32:03.180
ruins.

01:32:03.239 --> 01:32:06.300
Not going well, as you can see.

01:32:06.359 --> 01:32:09.180
He laughed a little, almost nervously.

01:32:09.239 --> 01:32:12.479
Queen Battle Winner isn't pleased about

01:32:12.479 --> 01:32:12.720
that.

01:32:12.779 --> 01:32:13.739
Of course.

01:32:13.800 --> 01:32:15.720
She has her own ideas about where I

01:32:15.720 --> 01:32:17.039
should be focusing my attention.

01:32:17.100 --> 01:32:18.060
Come, come.

01:32:18.119 --> 01:32:20.279
He lifted off toward the top level.

01:32:20.340 --> 01:32:22.500
Starflight took one more look around

01:32:22.500 --> 01:32:24.359
wondering what could be more interesting

01:32:24.359 --> 01:32:26.880
or important than protecting the tribe

01:32:26.880 --> 01:32:27.720
from the volcano.

01:32:27.779 --> 01:32:31.140
I wonder if he's done any research on

01:32:31.140 --> 01:32:33.300
Nightwings infecting the prey they bite.

01:32:33.359 --> 01:32:35.220
Maybe I could help him study it.

01:32:35.340 --> 01:32:37.619
He shook himself, blinking.

01:32:37.680 --> 01:32:40.199
Sounds like I'm planning to stay.

01:32:40.319 --> 01:32:43.560
He glanced at fate speaker, then quickly

01:32:43.560 --> 01:32:45.600
away at one of the smoking jars of lava.

01:32:45.659 --> 01:32:48.180
I might not have any choice about that.

01:32:48.239 --> 01:32:51.539
But they have to let me see Sonny again.

01:32:51.600 --> 01:32:54.479
If I'm trapped here forever, without her

01:32:54.479 --> 01:32:56.819
without even a chance to say goodbye?

01:32:56.880 --> 01:32:58.619
Come on.

01:32:58.680 --> 01:33:01.020
Fate speaker interrupted his thoughts

01:33:01.020 --> 01:33:02.340
tugging him into the air.

01:33:02.399 --> 01:33:05.159
They hurried after mastermind, and

01:33:05.159 --> 01:33:07.020
discovered that the 3rd level was another

01:33:07.020 --> 01:33:09.539
balcony, with several doors ranged around

01:33:09.539 --> 01:33:12.119
it, each one marked with 3 or 4 different

01:33:12.119 --> 01:33:12.659
symbols.

01:33:12.720 --> 01:33:15.659
Starflight's father stopped in front of

01:33:15.659 --> 01:33:17.699
one door and rubbed his front talons

01:33:17.699 --> 01:33:18.060
together.

01:33:18.119 --> 01:33:21.899
About a year ago, we discovered a truly

01:33:21.899 --> 01:33:24.539
truly astonishing natural phenomenon.

01:33:24.600 --> 01:33:26.460
You won't know about this.

01:33:26.520 --> 01:33:28.260
The talons of peace have no idea.

01:33:28.319 --> 01:33:30.359
None of the other tribes do.

01:33:30.420 --> 01:33:33.180
Our understanding of this biological

01:33:33.180 --> 01:33:37.020
anomaly. is as yet so new and incomplete

01:33:37.020 --> 01:33:39.060
that we haven't even put it in any

01:33:39.060 --> 01:33:39.840
scrolls.

01:33:39.960 --> 01:33:42.359
Certainly not the ones we distribute on

01:33:42.359 --> 01:33:44.880
the mainland, but also not even the ones

01:33:44.880 --> 01:33:47.579
that are for night wing eyes only.

01:33:47.640 --> 01:33:50.520
I'm preparing a treatise on the subject

01:33:50.520 --> 01:33:53.100
but there's still so much to learn that I

01:33:53.100 --> 01:33:55.020
have no idea when I'll think it's ready

01:33:55.020 --> 01:33:55.560
for publication.

01:33:55.619 --> 01:34:01.020
You see, he said, leaning toward them, it

01:34:01.020 --> 01:34:03.960
turns out one tribe of dragons has

01:34:03.960 --> 01:34:06.180
evolved in unusual defense mechanism.

01:34:06.239 --> 01:34:11.100
They can shoot venom from their fangs.

01:34:11.159 --> 01:34:14.880
Deadly toxic venom that essentially melts

01:34:14.880 --> 01:34:17.460
any animal or plant matter, it comes in

01:34:17.460 --> 01:34:20.520
contact with, and you'll never believe

01:34:20.520 --> 01:34:21.659
which tribe.

01:34:21.779 --> 01:34:24.180
He didn't wait for them to guess.

01:34:24.300 --> 01:34:25.859
Rain wings.

01:34:25.920 --> 01:34:28.020
Rain wings?

01:34:28.140 --> 01:34:30.420
Fate speaker echoed in a surprised

01:34:30.420 --> 01:34:30.899
voice.

01:34:30.960 --> 01:34:32.819
Starflight's heart was sinking.

01:34:32.880 --> 01:34:35.039
He suddenly had a feeling he really did

01:34:35.039 --> 01:34:36.479
not want to see what was behind these

01:34:36.479 --> 01:34:36.840
doors.

01:34:36.960 --> 01:34:38.880
Let's see.

01:34:38.939 --> 01:34:42.000
We'll start here, Mastermind said.

01:34:42.060 --> 01:34:44.220
He opened one of the doors to reveal a

01:34:44.220 --> 01:34:45.659
long, narrow stone room.

01:34:45.720 --> 01:34:48.180
A set of silver shackles with very short

01:34:48.180 --> 01:34:50.579
chains was bolted to the floor near the

01:34:50.579 --> 01:34:53.100
entrance, and all along the length of the

01:34:53.100 --> 01:34:55.619
room, black marks scarred the floor and

01:34:55.619 --> 01:34:57.840
walls, with indecipherable notes

01:34:57.840 --> 01:34:59.699
scribbled beside each one in chalk.

01:34:59.760 --> 01:35:03.300
Starflight stared at the shackles, feeling

01:35:03.300 --> 01:35:03.720
ill.

01:35:03.779 --> 01:35:07.619
Mastermind hopped down the room, avoiding

01:35:07.619 --> 01:35:09.539
the black patches, although they all

01:35:09.539 --> 01:35:11.340
seemed to be hardened and harmless, like

01:35:11.340 --> 01:35:12.000
old lava.

01:35:12.119 --> 01:35:14.819
This was one of our 1st questions

01:35:14.819 --> 01:35:15.720
naturally.

01:35:15.779 --> 01:35:18.420
When we 1st learned that rain wings could

01:35:18.420 --> 01:35:19.020
shoot venom.

01:35:19.079 --> 01:35:19.979
How far?

01:35:20.039 --> 01:35:22.680
Was it a short range weapon or a long

01:35:22.680 --> 01:35:23.399
range weapon?

01:35:23.520 --> 01:35:26.039
Would we be able to approach and

01:35:26.039 --> 01:35:28.439
incapacitate them if we developed

01:35:28.439 --> 01:35:30.600
projectiles that could be fired from a

01:35:30.600 --> 01:35:31.140
safe distance?

01:35:31.199 --> 01:35:34.680
He stopped at the far end of the room and

01:35:34.680 --> 01:35:35.939
indicated a mark on the floor.

01:35:36.000 --> 01:35:39.659
This is as far as I've seen any one

01:35:39.659 --> 01:35:40.739
dragon shoot.

01:35:40.859 --> 01:35:42.840
An older male rain wing.

01:35:42.899 --> 01:35:46.500
So my hypothesis is that it's a skill

01:35:46.500 --> 01:35:48.539
that gets stronger as they age.

01:35:48.600 --> 01:35:51.479
He rubbed the horns on his head, frowning

01:35:51.479 --> 01:35:51.899
in thought.

01:35:51.960 --> 01:35:54.779
I wonder if they have any elderly dragons

01:35:54.779 --> 01:35:56.399
we could bring over and test.

01:35:56.460 --> 01:35:58.319
Bring over.

01:35:58.439 --> 01:36:01.619
Starflight thought bitterly, as if their

01:36:01.619 --> 01:36:04.020
invited guests instead of abducted

01:36:04.020 --> 01:36:04.439
prisoners.

01:36:04.500 --> 01:36:07.260
Fate speaker was eyeing the shackles

01:36:07.260 --> 01:36:09.539
nervously too, she looked as if she

01:36:09.539 --> 01:36:11.159
didn't know quite how to ask about them.

01:36:11.220 --> 01:36:14.579
The next obvious question is, what

01:36:14.579 --> 01:36:16.800
materials aren't affected by the venom?

01:36:16.859 --> 01:36:19.619
Anything we could use as armor or

01:36:19.619 --> 01:36:20.039
shield?

01:36:20.100 --> 01:36:23.399
Mastermind went on, hopping back up the

01:36:23.399 --> 01:36:23.939
room toward them.

01:36:24.060 --> 01:36:25.079
Come, come.

01:36:25.140 --> 01:36:27.180
He ushered them out and over to the next

01:36:27.180 --> 01:36:27.420
door.

01:36:27.479 --> 01:36:30.239
We had to devise ways to study the

01:36:30.239 --> 01:36:32.579
dragons without placing ourselves in

01:36:32.579 --> 01:36:33.779
danger naturally.

01:36:33.899 --> 01:36:36.239
Very few rain wings have ever

01:36:36.239 --> 01:36:38.039
deliberately tried to shoot their venom

01:36:38.039 --> 01:36:40.680
at us, but it goes very badly when they

01:36:40.680 --> 01:36:40.920
do.

01:36:40.979 --> 01:36:43.140
It's quite horrifying, really.

01:36:43.260 --> 01:36:46.380
He opened the door and swept his talent

01:36:46.380 --> 01:36:47.220
toward the tables inside.

01:36:47.340 --> 01:36:50.279
Items of different shapes, sizes, and

01:36:50.279 --> 01:36:52.199
materials were arranged in related

01:36:52.199 --> 01:36:52.619
groups.

01:36:52.619 --> 01:36:55.380
One table contained a gathering of sad

01:36:55.380 --> 01:36:57.960
little plants and pots, drooping yellow

01:36:57.960 --> 01:36:59.220
flowers dripping with black.

01:36:59.340 --> 01:37:02.340
Another was all rocks, and a 3rd.

01:37:02.399 --> 01:37:05.039
Starflight looked away quickly when you

01:37:05.039 --> 01:37:07.199
realized that the trays all contained

01:37:07.199 --> 01:37:10.739
remains of living things, sloths, lizards

01:37:10.739 --> 01:37:11.279
fish.

01:37:11.340 --> 01:37:13.859
It hadn't survived the experimental

01:37:13.859 --> 01:37:14.279
process.

01:37:14.340 --> 01:37:16.319
Ew.

01:37:16.380 --> 01:37:17.880
Fate speaker cried.

01:37:18.000 --> 01:37:20.819
We've tested it on everything.

01:37:20.880 --> 01:37:22.680
Mastermind said proudly.

01:37:22.739 --> 01:37:26.220
Turns out it doesn't affect metal, so, he

01:37:26.220 --> 01:37:28.260
banged on his helmet, which gave out a

01:37:28.260 --> 01:37:29.699
muffled clang in response.

01:37:29.760 --> 01:37:33.659
But to anything alive, plant or animal, it

01:37:33.659 --> 01:37:34.500
just destroys.

01:37:34.560 --> 01:37:36.840
If it gets in your eyes or your

01:37:36.840 --> 01:37:38.939
bloodstream, you're dead within minutes.

01:37:39.000 --> 01:37:41.939
If it only hits your scales, you'll wish

01:37:41.939 --> 01:37:42.359
you were.

01:37:42.420 --> 01:37:45.359
We have a couple of recent victims.

01:37:45.420 --> 01:37:46.979
I'll be getting to study as soon as

01:37:46.979 --> 01:37:48.180
they're released from the healers.

01:37:48.239 --> 01:37:50.699
He rubbed his talons together again.

01:37:50.760 --> 01:37:53.640
If you're lucky, I'll let you take a peek

01:37:53.640 --> 01:37:56.520
he said to Starflight, a once in a

01:37:56.520 --> 01:37:58.739
lifetime opportunity to see what rain

01:37:58.739 --> 01:37:59.939
wing venom can do.

01:38:00.000 --> 01:38:02.279
I know what he can do.

01:38:02.340 --> 01:38:04.079
Starflight choked out.

01:38:04.140 --> 01:38:06.779
I've seen it kill 2 dragons.

01:38:06.840 --> 01:38:10.260
Possibly 3 if Queen Scarlet is dead.

01:38:10.319 --> 01:38:12.539
He thought of Fjord.

01:38:12.600 --> 01:38:15.060
The 1st Dragon Glory's venom had killed

01:38:15.060 --> 01:38:17.699
the Ice Wing, who had been about to kill

01:38:17.699 --> 01:38:18.779
Clay in the arena.

01:38:18.840 --> 01:38:21.420
Some of the poison had landed on the open

01:38:21.420 --> 01:38:22.920
wounds on Fjord's neck.

01:38:22.979 --> 01:38:24.840
That must have been why it killed him so

01:38:24.840 --> 01:38:25.140
quickly.

01:38:25.199 --> 01:38:27.359
And crocodile.

01:38:27.420 --> 01:38:30.000
The mudwing who had betrayed the talons

01:38:30.000 --> 01:38:32.100
of peace, and led the enemy right to the

01:38:32.100 --> 01:38:33.659
summer palace.

01:38:33.720 --> 01:38:35.039
When glory killed her so they could

01:38:35.039 --> 01:38:35.399
escape.

01:38:35.460 --> 01:38:37.500
Her venom had gone right into the

01:38:37.500 --> 01:38:38.220
dragon's eyes.

01:38:38.279 --> 01:38:40.439
But Queen Scarlet.

01:38:40.560 --> 01:38:42.600
He shifted uneasily.

01:38:42.659 --> 01:38:46.079
If he remembered right, Gloria's spray of

01:38:46.079 --> 01:38:47.460
venom had landed on the side of the

01:38:47.460 --> 01:38:48.359
queen's face.

01:38:48.420 --> 01:38:51.779
So she really might still be alive, alive

01:38:51.779 --> 01:38:55.140
and looking like vengeance, which didn't

01:38:55.140 --> 01:38:56.699
bode well for the dragonettes.

01:38:56.760 --> 01:38:59.520
Mastermind stared at him avidly.

01:38:59.579 --> 01:39:02.880
Two dragons killed them.

01:39:02.939 --> 01:39:04.140
Are you sure?

01:39:04.260 --> 01:39:05.819
How incredibly careless.

01:39:05.880 --> 01:39:08.220
We haven't picked up any rain wings with

01:39:08.220 --> 01:39:09.000
that little control yet.

01:39:09.119 --> 01:39:11.340
It wasn't careless.

01:39:11.399 --> 01:39:14.460
It was on purpose, Starflight said

01:39:14.460 --> 01:39:16.319
annoyed on Glory's behalf.

01:39:16.380 --> 01:39:19.020
Fate speaker sucked in an astonished

01:39:19.020 --> 01:39:19.619
breath.

01:39:19.680 --> 01:39:22.079
Well, I never.

01:39:22.199 --> 01:39:23.640
Are you sure?

01:39:23.699 --> 01:39:25.739
His father's wings flared.

01:39:25.800 --> 01:39:28.079
He looked equal parts alarmed and

01:39:28.079 --> 01:39:28.859
enthralled.

01:39:28.920 --> 01:39:31.439
That changes things entirely.

01:39:31.500 --> 01:39:33.479
A variable I hadn't considered.

01:39:33.539 --> 01:39:35.520
You'll have to tell me all about it.

01:39:35.579 --> 01:39:38.460
What prompted the attack, what it looked

01:39:38.460 --> 01:39:40.979
like, how long it took the victims to die

01:39:40.979 --> 01:39:42.720
whether there was any time to fight

01:39:42.720 --> 01:39:43.020
back.

01:39:43.079 --> 01:39:46.859
Starfight realized, too late, that he

01:39:46.859 --> 01:39:47.520
shouldn't have said anything.

01:39:47.579 --> 01:39:49.859
If this information got back to the

01:39:49.859 --> 01:39:52.319
council, they'd know how dangerous glory

01:39:52.319 --> 01:39:52.619
was.

01:39:52.619 --> 01:39:55.560
He had to hope that mastermind was too

01:39:55.560 --> 01:39:57.180
wrapped up in his experiments to tell

01:39:57.180 --> 01:39:58.140
anyone.

01:39:58.199 --> 01:40:00.479
My, my, my.

01:40:00.539 --> 01:40:03.720
Mastermind headed toward the next door.

01:40:03.840 --> 01:40:06.960
Well, knowing the venom only worked on

01:40:06.960 --> 01:40:09.180
certain substances, led us to the next

01:40:09.180 --> 01:40:12.060
project, constructing armor that could

01:40:12.060 --> 01:40:13.979
withstand a rain wing attack, if

01:40:13.979 --> 01:40:14.460
necessary.

01:40:14.520 --> 01:40:16.920
But it isn't necessary.

01:40:16.979 --> 01:40:18.840
Fate speaker chimed in.

01:40:18.899 --> 01:40:21.239
Rain wings don't attack other dragons.

01:40:21.300 --> 01:40:22.199
Everyone knows that.

01:40:22.319 --> 01:40:24.239
She looked at Starflight.

01:40:24.300 --> 01:40:27.180
Well, they're not supposed to.

01:40:27.239 --> 01:40:30.779
Even a rain wing will defend herself

01:40:30.779 --> 01:40:31.380
sometimes.

01:40:31.439 --> 01:40:32.880
Starflight said.

01:40:32.939 --> 01:40:37.020
Hmm, not often, in my experience, said

01:40:37.020 --> 01:40:37.800
Mastermind.

01:40:37.859 --> 01:40:40.619
But why don't you stand back, just in

01:40:40.619 --> 01:40:40.800
case.

01:40:40.859 --> 01:40:43.260
He waved them a few steps away.

01:40:43.319 --> 01:40:45.600
Settled his helmet over his head again

01:40:45.600 --> 01:40:46.859
and flung open the door.

01:40:46.979 --> 01:40:51.359
Inside, a dragon was pinned to the wall.
2778
01:40:51,420 --> 01:40:55,979	Chapter 6.

01:40:56.039 --> 01:40:59.279
Starflight was lucky his stomach was

01:40:59.279 --> 01:40:59.699
empty.

01:40:59.760 --> 01:41:02.640
It heaved perilously, and he had to cover

01:41:02.640 --> 01:41:04.439
his eyes and take a few deep breaths

01:41:04.439 --> 01:41:05.819
before he could speak again.

01:41:05.880 --> 01:41:09.539
The rain wing was the sad gray color of

01:41:09.539 --> 01:41:12.119
the chains that had bound Starflight in

01:41:12.119 --> 01:41:12.899
the Sky Kingdom.

01:41:12.960 --> 01:41:15.359
The 1st time he'd been separated from

01:41:15.359 --> 01:41:15.779
Sonny.

01:41:15.840 --> 01:41:19.260
She drooped against the wall, her wings

01:41:19.260 --> 01:41:21.180
outstretched and secured in place.

01:41:21.239 --> 01:41:24.479
When he was able to look again, he saw

01:41:24.479 --> 01:41:26.100
that what he thought were pins were

01:41:26.100 --> 01:41:28.319
actually clamps, holding her where she

01:41:28.319 --> 01:41:30.359
was, but not going straight through her

01:41:30.359 --> 01:41:31.680
wings as he'd 1st thought.

01:41:31.739 --> 01:41:34.800
Not that anything about this is all

01:41:34.800 --> 01:41:35.100
right.

01:41:35.159 --> 01:41:37.979
What are you doing to her?

01:41:38.039 --> 01:41:39.539
Fate speaker cried.

01:41:39.600 --> 01:41:41.880
She bolted into the room and lifted their

01:41:41.880 --> 01:41:43.979
rain wings, snout gently in her talons.

01:41:44.039 --> 01:41:46.619
The trapped dragon barely responded.

01:41:46.680 --> 01:41:49.260
This one is done for the day.

01:41:49.319 --> 01:41:50.760
Mastermind said.

01:41:50.880 --> 01:41:53.340
We were testing to see whether they run

01:41:53.340 --> 01:41:55.680
out of venom at some point, if they shoot

01:41:55.680 --> 01:41:56.579
it for long enough.

01:41:56.640 --> 01:41:58.920
But she fainted before we could get any

01:41:58.920 --> 01:41:59.880
really useful data.

01:42:00.000 --> 01:42:03.960
She needs water, fate speaker said

01:42:03.960 --> 01:42:05.880
glancing around the room, then looking

01:42:05.880 --> 01:42:07.020
straight at Starflight.

01:42:07.079 --> 01:42:10.439
He hesitated, remembering Fjord and

01:42:10.439 --> 01:42:11.399
Crocodile again.

01:42:11.460 --> 01:42:14.399
If this dragon did suddenly spray venom

01:42:14.399 --> 01:42:15.899
at them, he wouldn't blame her.

01:42:15.960 --> 01:42:17.939
But he didn't want to be in the way when

01:42:17.939 --> 01:42:18.359
it happened.

01:42:18.420 --> 01:42:23.039
Starflight, fate speaker said, and the

01:42:23.039 --> 01:42:24.840
tone of her voice reminded him again so

01:42:24.840 --> 01:42:27.060
much of Sonny that he couldn't say no to

01:42:27.060 --> 01:42:27.300
her.

01:42:27.300 --> 01:42:29.279
I'll get some.

01:42:29.340 --> 01:42:31.680
He flew to one of the pipes on the

01:42:31.680 --> 01:42:34.079
desalinization machine where he'd seen a

01:42:34.079 --> 01:42:36.659
faucet earlier, found an empty cauldron

01:42:36.659 --> 01:42:38.399
that smelled clean, and filled it up.

01:42:38.460 --> 01:42:41.340
Fate speaker had one of the prisoner's

01:42:41.340 --> 01:42:43.500
wings unclamped by the time Starflight

01:42:43.500 --> 01:42:43.800
got back.

01:42:43.859 --> 01:42:47.100
Mastermind stood in the doorway, watching

01:42:47.100 --> 01:42:48.720
through the holes in his helmet, but

01:42:48.720 --> 01:42:50.939
neither interfering nor helping.

01:42:51.000 --> 01:42:52.260
It was hard to know what he was thinking

01:42:52.260 --> 01:42:53.699
with his face completely hidden.

01:42:53.760 --> 01:42:57.239
Starflight brushed past him and set the

01:42:57.239 --> 01:42:59.520
cauldron down, then unclamped the

01:42:59.520 --> 01:43:00.420
dragon's other wing.

01:43:00.479 --> 01:43:03.659
She slumped forward so suddenly that both

01:43:03.659 --> 01:43:05.880
fate speaker and Starflight were nearly

01:43:05.880 --> 01:43:08.039
knocked over, but they managed to catch

01:43:08.039 --> 01:43:09.779
her and lean her wings over their

01:43:09.779 --> 01:43:10.260
shoulders.

01:43:10.319 --> 01:43:13.199
Fate speaker held a cauldronap, and the

01:43:13.199 --> 01:43:14.579
rain wing revived enough to drink a

01:43:14.579 --> 01:43:14.760
little.

01:43:14.819 --> 01:43:16.920
What's your name?

01:43:16.979 --> 01:43:18.600
Starflight Aster.

01:43:18.659 --> 01:43:21.479
She coughed and looked sideways at him.

01:43:21.720 --> 01:43:25.619
No, Nightwing, has ever asked my name

01:43:25.619 --> 01:43:28.020
before, she whispered hoarsely.

01:43:28.079 --> 01:43:30.180
It's orchid.

01:43:30.239 --> 01:43:34.800
Oh, Starflight gasped, then closed his

01:43:34.800 --> 01:43:36.420
mouth quickly and glanced at the door.

01:43:36.479 --> 01:43:39.600
Mastermind was leaning into the hallway

01:43:39.600 --> 01:43:42.479
yelling, strong wings, strong wings, you

01:43:42.479 --> 01:43:43.500
blockhead, get up here.

01:43:43.619 --> 01:43:46.500
Mangrove is looking for you.

01:43:46.560 --> 01:43:48.779
Starflight whispered hurriedly.

01:43:48.840 --> 01:43:50.039
He hasn't given up.

01:43:50.100 --> 01:43:52.020
He'll be here to rescue you soon.

01:43:52.079 --> 01:43:55.800
Fate speakers stared at him, as if he'd

01:43:55.800 --> 01:43:57.960
just peeled off his scales and revealed a

01:43:57.960 --> 01:44:00.659
hippo underneath, but Orchid lifted her

01:44:00.659 --> 01:44:02.699
head, her eyes flooding with hope.

01:44:02.760 --> 01:44:05.760
A shimmering rose pink spread over her

01:44:05.760 --> 01:44:08.460
starting on her chest, and drifting out

01:44:08.460 --> 01:44:09.300
to her wingtips.

01:44:09.359 --> 01:44:12.659
Soon, she said softly.

01:44:12.720 --> 01:44:16.020
Then I can hang on until he comes.

01:44:16.079 --> 01:44:19.260
I hope it'll be soon.

01:44:19.319 --> 01:44:20.340
Starflight thought.

01:44:20.460 --> 01:44:22.680
I hope he doesn't die on his way here.

01:44:22.739 --> 01:44:24.840
I hope glory survives too.

01:44:24.960 --> 01:44:27.420
I hope my friends are planning to rescue

01:44:27.420 --> 01:44:27.899
me as well.

01:44:27.960 --> 01:44:31.920
Fate speakers expression was 10 kinds of

01:44:31.920 --> 01:44:32.340
confused.

01:44:32.460 --> 01:44:34.680
She tilted her head as if she was

01:44:34.680 --> 01:44:36.899
listening, and Starflight realized, with

01:44:36.899 --> 01:44:38.939
a jolt of panic, that he'd been having

01:44:38.939 --> 01:44:41.159
several unguarded thoughts since they'd

01:44:41.159 --> 01:44:42.359
started this part of the tour.

01:44:42.420 --> 01:44:43.560
He'd forgotten.

01:44:43.619 --> 01:44:45.060
How could I forget?

01:44:45.119 --> 01:44:47.699
To worry about having his mind read.

01:44:47.760 --> 01:44:50.340
But his father hadn't reacted to any of

01:44:50.340 --> 01:44:50.699
his thoughts.

01:44:50.760 --> 01:44:53.819
Mastermind looked as pleased as ever.

01:44:53.880 --> 01:44:56.699
Not a mind reader then, perhaps.

01:44:56.760 --> 01:44:59.760
Maybe those kinds of powers aren't

01:44:59.760 --> 01:45:01.500
genetically dominant in us.

01:45:01.560 --> 01:45:04.199
Maybe it is enough just to be smart like

01:45:04.199 --> 01:45:04.439
him.

01:45:04.500 --> 01:45:07.920
He'd always thought all Night Wings could

01:45:07.920 --> 01:45:10.260
read minds, and all Night Wings could see

01:45:10.260 --> 01:45:10.619
the future.

01:45:10.680 --> 01:45:12.779
That's what it sounded like in the

01:45:12.779 --> 01:45:13.619
scrolls he'd read.

01:45:13.680 --> 01:45:16.079
But Glory thought maybe it was only some

01:45:16.079 --> 01:45:17.760
of them, and perhaps she was right.

01:45:17.819 --> 01:45:21.239
Maybe I'm not completely defective.

01:45:21.300 --> 01:45:23.760
Three moons.

01:45:23.819 --> 01:45:25.859
Mastermind barked from the doorway.

01:45:25.979 --> 01:45:28.619
How did you turn her that pink color?

01:45:28.680 --> 01:45:30.420
I've never seen any of them look like

01:45:30.420 --> 01:45:30.840
that before.

01:45:30.899 --> 01:45:34.439
That's because it's the color of

01:45:34.439 --> 01:45:36.840
happiness, and there's no happiness on

01:45:36.840 --> 01:45:37.680
this twisted island.

01:45:37.739 --> 01:45:41.100
Starflight met fate speaker's eyes.

01:45:41.159 --> 01:45:44.039
I think she's just grateful for the water

01:45:44.039 --> 01:45:46.739
fate speaker said, blinking at him.

01:45:46.859 --> 01:45:49.380
He didn't have to read minds to guess she

01:45:49.380 --> 01:45:51.779
was thinking, we'll be talking about this

01:45:51.779 --> 01:45:52.739
later.

01:45:52.800 --> 01:45:55.380
Fascinating.

01:45:55.500 --> 01:45:58.619
Mastermind came over and prodded the

01:45:58.619 --> 01:46:00.600
scales on Orchid's neck with one claw.

01:46:00.659 --> 01:46:02.039
She closed her eyes.

01:46:02.100 --> 01:46:03.659
Her color didn't change.

01:46:03.720 --> 01:46:06.479
Utterly fascinating.

01:46:06.539 --> 01:46:09.600
A burly night wing slouched grumpily in

01:46:09.600 --> 01:46:10.319
from the balcony.

01:46:10.380 --> 01:46:12.659
Half a lizard hung from one corner of his

01:46:12.659 --> 01:46:15.119
mouth, and his shoulders were almost too

01:46:15.119 --> 01:46:16.619
wide for his wings to fit through the

01:46:16.619 --> 01:46:16.800
door.

01:46:16.859 --> 01:46:18.840
What?

01:46:18.840 --> 01:46:20.220
he mumbled, chewing.

01:46:20.279 --> 01:46:23.819
This one can go back, said Mastermind.

01:46:23.880 --> 01:46:26.279
Oh, and strong wings, guess what?

01:46:26.340 --> 01:46:28.680
This is my son.

01:46:28.739 --> 01:46:31.680
He waved gleefully at Starflight.

01:46:31.739 --> 01:46:34.260
Starflight wished he could go back half

01:46:34.260 --> 01:46:37.079
an hour in time to when he'd been just as

01:46:37.079 --> 01:46:39.060
happy about those words as mastermind

01:46:39.060 --> 01:46:39.300
was.

01:46:39.359 --> 01:46:42.600
Strongwings gave Starflight a dubious

01:46:42.600 --> 01:46:42.899
look.

01:46:42.960 --> 01:46:45.180
Huh, he said.

01:46:45.239 --> 01:46:46.199
All right.

01:46:46.260 --> 01:46:48.239
So when do I get a helmet like that?

01:46:48.300 --> 01:46:51.300
He nodded at the thing on Mastermind's

01:46:51.300 --> 01:46:51.539
head.

01:46:51.600 --> 01:46:55.319
This is just a prototype, Mastermind

01:46:55.319 --> 01:46:55.619
said.

01:46:55.680 --> 01:46:57.180
He turned to Starflight.

01:46:57.239 --> 01:47:00.000
As you can imagine, the hardest part of

01:47:00.000 --> 01:47:02.460
creating venom resistant armor is coming

01:47:02.460 --> 01:47:05.039
up with a solution that protects the eyes

01:47:05.039 --> 01:47:06.539
but still allows one to see.

01:47:06.600 --> 01:47:09.720
I'd love to hear your thoughts, because I

01:47:09.720 --> 01:47:11.220
must admit I'm stymied.

01:47:11.279 --> 01:47:13.739
This is a thoroughly imperfect solution.

01:47:13.859 --> 01:47:16.619
He tapped on the helmet with his talons.

01:47:16.680 --> 01:47:20.220
Peripheral vision is negligible at best

01:47:20.220 --> 01:47:22.500
and of course, venom could still splash

01:47:22.500 --> 01:47:24.300
through the holes if one were unlucky.

01:47:24.359 --> 01:47:25.560
He shook his head.

01:47:25.619 --> 01:47:28.380
There must be a more ingenious approach.

01:47:28.439 --> 01:47:30.359
Whatever.

01:47:30.420 --> 01:47:32.340
Strong wings grunt.

01:47:32.399 --> 01:47:33.840
Where's her band?

01:47:33.899 --> 01:47:37.140
Mastermind waved to the corner, and the

01:47:37.140 --> 01:47:38.939
muscular Nightwing picked up a heap of

01:47:38.939 --> 01:47:40.020
metal in one of the spears.

01:47:40.079 --> 01:47:42.359
He brought it over and fitted a kind of

01:47:42.359 --> 01:47:44.819
muzzle around Orchid's mouth, twisting

01:47:44.819 --> 01:47:46.859
the lock into place, with a practiced

01:47:46.859 --> 01:47:48.119
flick of the spear tips.

01:47:48.180 --> 01:47:50.640
Then he shooed Starflight and fate

01:47:50.640 --> 01:47:52.979
speaker aside, snapped a chain around the

01:47:52.979 --> 01:47:54.960
rain wings neck, and gave it a yank.

01:47:55.020 --> 01:47:57.779
Without protesting, or could follow him

01:47:57.779 --> 01:47:58.260
out of the room.

01:47:58.319 --> 01:48:00.899
But why are you doing this?

01:48:00.960 --> 01:48:02.579
Starflight blurted.

01:48:02.640 --> 01:48:04.500
Why study their venom at all?

01:48:04.560 --> 01:48:07.739
Mastermind pulled off the helmet and gave

01:48:07.739 --> 01:48:08.819
him a confused look.

01:48:08.880 --> 01:48:10.859
It's science.

01:48:10.920 --> 01:48:13.800
We're expanding dragon knowledge.

01:48:13.859 --> 01:48:16.560
There's got to be more to it than that.

01:48:16.619 --> 01:48:17.939
Starflight said.

01:48:18.000 --> 01:48:19.800
Why is this so important?

01:48:19.859 --> 01:48:22.739
Why do you need venom resistant armor?

01:48:22.800 --> 01:48:25.199
The rain wings would never have bothered

01:48:25.199 --> 01:48:26.039
you if you left them alone.

01:48:26.100 --> 01:48:28.859
His father shrugged.

01:48:28.920 --> 01:48:31.079
The queen has her reasons.

01:48:31.140 --> 01:48:32.220
I have mine.

01:48:32.279 --> 01:48:34.560
I don't get involved in her plans.

01:48:34.619 --> 01:48:35.640
For me.

01:48:35.699 --> 01:48:37.800
Scientific discovery is reason enough.

01:48:37.859 --> 01:48:40.739
Starflight looked at the clams on the

01:48:40.739 --> 01:48:42.960
wall, then down at the floor, too

01:48:42.960 --> 01:48:44.399
sickened to ask any more questions.

01:48:44.460 --> 01:48:48.600
Well, I wish I had time to show you more

01:48:48.600 --> 01:48:50.279
Mastermind said.

01:48:50.340 --> 01:48:52.319
Setting his helmet up on a shelf.

01:48:52.380 --> 01:48:54.840
But my daily scheduled meeting with a

01:48:54.840 --> 01:48:55.859
queen is upon me.

01:48:55.920 --> 01:48:58.199
Do you get to see her?

01:48:58.260 --> 01:48:59.399
Starflight asked.

01:48:59.460 --> 01:49:03.659
No, no, said Mastermind. 3 moons, no.

01:49:03.720 --> 01:49:05.760
No one sees the queen.

01:49:05.819 --> 01:49:08.159
Not for the last 9 years or so.

01:49:08.220 --> 01:49:09.779
She's very private.

01:49:09.840 --> 01:49:11.939
Really?

01:49:12.060 --> 01:49:13.439
Starflight thought.

01:49:13.500 --> 01:49:16.619
I wish I had some more progress to report

01:49:16.619 --> 01:49:19.680
Mastermind mused, but telling her about

01:49:19.680 --> 01:49:21.119
you will certainly be a triumph.

01:49:21.239 --> 01:49:23.340
Come back tomorrow, and we can get to

01:49:23.340 --> 01:49:24.539
know each other better, yes?

01:49:24.600 --> 01:49:27.000
He wrapped his wings around Starflight

01:49:27.000 --> 01:49:28.680
and hugged him, not waiting for an

01:49:28.680 --> 01:49:28.920
answer.

01:49:29.039 --> 01:49:31.739
It was fantastic to meet you, son.

01:49:31.800 --> 01:49:34.140
I am so very proud.

01:49:34.199 --> 01:49:36.539
He ushered them out the door and locked

01:49:36.539 --> 01:49:39.000
it, then slid away toward a tunnel at the

01:49:39.000 --> 01:49:40.079
far end of the balcony.

01:49:40.140 --> 01:49:42.779
Starflight glanced along the row of doors

01:49:42.779 --> 01:49:45.420
imagining tortured rain wings behind each

01:49:45.420 --> 01:49:45.779
one.

01:49:45.840 --> 01:49:49.380
Wow, Fate speaker said.

01:49:49.439 --> 01:49:53.340
So, turns out we might be horrible.

01:49:53.399 --> 01:49:55.979
I did not foresee that at all.

01:49:56.100 --> 01:49:59.819
Starflight sat down, his shoulders

01:49:59.819 --> 01:50:00.779
slumping.

01:50:00.840 --> 01:50:02.880
I believed everything I read.

01:50:03.000 --> 01:50:06.300
About Nightwings being so noble and

01:50:06.300 --> 01:50:07.500
brilliant and perfect.

01:50:07.560 --> 01:50:10.800
This, I can't understand this.

01:50:10.859 --> 01:50:13.920
So, where have you been?

01:50:13.979 --> 01:50:15.659
She asked curiously.

01:50:15.720 --> 01:50:17.159
You're not like them.

01:50:17.220 --> 01:50:19.140
And who's mangrove?

01:50:19.199 --> 01:50:22.739
I was raised by the talons of peace too

01:50:22.739 --> 01:50:25.260
he said. hoping he could avoid the

01:50:25.260 --> 01:50:27.000
mangrove question by distracting her.

01:50:27.060 --> 01:50:31.260
Actually, I'm the one in the prophecy, or

01:50:31.260 --> 01:50:31.859
I was.

01:50:31.920 --> 01:50:34.800
I guess I'm expendable, since they're

01:50:34.800 --> 01:50:35.640
replacing me with you.

01:50:35.699 --> 01:50:37.260
What?

01:50:37.380 --> 01:50:40.020
She took a step back. fluttering her

01:50:40.020 --> 01:50:40.319
wings.

01:50:40.380 --> 01:50:43.260
Wait, I never saw you.

01:50:43.319 --> 01:50:45.000
I lived right in the talons of peace

01:50:45.000 --> 01:50:45.359
camp.

01:50:45.420 --> 01:50:49.800
We were kept hidden, Starfly explained.

01:50:49.859 --> 01:50:51.300
Under a mountain.

01:50:51.359 --> 01:50:53.220
No one was supposed to find us.

01:50:53.279 --> 01:50:55.500
There you are.

01:50:55.560 --> 01:50:58.739
Maro seer landed beside them with a

01:50:58.739 --> 01:50:59.100
thump.

01:50:59.220 --> 01:51:02.100
If you're quite finished with your little

01:51:02.100 --> 01:51:02.640
chat.

01:51:02.699 --> 01:51:05.100
There are other pressing matters we could

01:51:05.100 --> 01:51:05.579
attend to.

01:51:05.640 --> 01:51:09.539
I'm not finished, face speaker said

01:51:09.600 --> 01:51:10.800
whirling toward him.

01:51:10.859 --> 01:51:13.979
He's all special and chosen too?

01:51:14.039 --> 01:51:15.479
How can we both be in the prophecy?

01:51:15.539 --> 01:51:20.100
Only one of you will be, said Maru Seer

01:51:20.100 --> 01:51:22.920
but that's why you're both here, so that

01:51:22.920 --> 01:51:24.180
we can decide which one.

01:51:24.239 --> 01:51:28.319
So there's still a chance, Starflight

01:51:28.319 --> 01:51:28.619
thought.

01:51:28.680 --> 01:51:30.479
Don't you know?

01:51:30.539 --> 01:51:33.539
Didn't you deliver that prophecy?

01:51:33.600 --> 01:51:36.600
Fate speaker asked, wrinkling her nose?

01:51:36.659 --> 01:51:40.260
Prophecies can be complicated.

01:51:40.380 --> 01:51:42.600
Maro seer said coldly.

01:51:42.659 --> 01:51:45.899
Ooh, fate speaker said.

01:51:45.960 --> 01:51:46.979
Good comeback.

01:51:47.039 --> 01:51:48.720
I should write that down and use it on

01:51:48.720 --> 01:51:49.079
Viper.

01:51:49.140 --> 01:51:51.359
The real problem.

01:51:51.420 --> 01:51:54.840
Moro Cyr went on, is that neither of you

01:51:54.840 --> 01:51:57.600
are suitable candidates whatsoever, but

01:51:57.600 --> 01:51:59.460
we have no other dragonettes of the right

01:51:59.460 --> 01:52:00.539
age we could use.

01:52:00.600 --> 01:52:03.899
So it must be one of you.

01:52:03.960 --> 01:52:05.340
He growled.

01:52:05.399 --> 01:52:09.779
We apparently made a grave error, allowing

01:52:09.779 --> 01:52:12.659
you to be raised outside the tribe, where

01:52:12.659 --> 01:52:17.100
we thought you'd be safe from, well, just

01:52:17.100 --> 01:52:17.579
in case.

01:52:17.699 --> 01:52:20.880
It has always been our assumption that

01:52:20.880 --> 01:52:23.220
night wing superiority is something every

01:52:23.220 --> 01:52:24.600
night wing is hatched with.

01:52:24.659 --> 01:52:27.359
He looked down his nose at the 2

01:52:27.359 --> 01:52:28.140
dragonettes.

01:52:28.199 --> 01:52:30.899
Evidently, we were wrong.

01:52:30.960 --> 01:52:33.779
But why aren't I suitable?

01:52:33.840 --> 01:52:35.520
Starflight asked.

01:52:35.579 --> 01:52:38.460
He hated the plaintive tone in his voice

01:52:38.460 --> 01:52:39.720
but he couldn't seem to quash it.

01:52:39.779 --> 01:52:41.640
What have I done?

01:52:41.699 --> 01:52:45.659
You have no leadership qualities.

01:52:45.720 --> 01:52:47.159
Morrisier said.

01:52:47.220 --> 01:52:50.159
You make night wings look like cowards

01:52:50.159 --> 01:52:53.880
and followers, and you antagonized our

01:52:53.880 --> 01:52:54.479
ally.

01:52:54.539 --> 01:52:56.579
Blister?

01:52:56.640 --> 01:52:59.159
Starflight said, uncomfortably

01:52:59.159 --> 01:53:00.840
remembering his interaction with her in

01:53:00.840 --> 01:53:01.800
the kingdom of the sea.

01:53:01.859 --> 01:53:05.039
He'd tried to find reasons to support her

01:53:05.039 --> 01:53:06.840
as the next sand wing queen.

01:53:06.899 --> 01:53:10.020
Really, he tried, but she was too

01:53:10.020 --> 01:53:12.239
manipulative and too untrustworthy.

01:53:12.300 --> 01:53:14.220
And he didn't like the way she'd looked

01:53:14.220 --> 01:53:16.500
at Sunny, as if the little dragonette

01:53:16.500 --> 01:53:17.699
would make an excellent snack.

01:53:17.819 --> 01:53:22.319
You, have placed our whole plan in

01:53:22.319 --> 01:53:24.600
jeopardy, Marasier said.

01:53:24.659 --> 01:53:26.340
What plan?

01:53:26.460 --> 01:53:27.840
Starfly cried.

01:53:27.899 --> 01:53:30.000
How am I supposed to make anything happen

01:53:30.000 --> 01:53:31.920
when I don't even know what you really

01:53:31.920 --> 01:53:32.279
want?

01:53:32.340 --> 01:53:34.319
To his surprise.

01:53:34.380 --> 01:53:36.479
Mario Seer actually paused and thought

01:53:36.479 --> 01:53:36.779
about that.

01:53:36.840 --> 01:53:38.760
No.

01:53:38.819 --> 01:53:40.560
He rumbled finally.

01:53:40.619 --> 01:53:43.500
Dragonettes can't be trusted with

01:53:43.500 --> 01:53:43.979
secrets.

01:53:44.039 --> 01:53:47.460
Perhaps if you are the one chosen.

01:53:47.520 --> 01:53:49.199
We can reveal more.

01:53:49.260 --> 01:53:52.920
But all you should really need to know is

01:53:52.920 --> 01:53:54.119
how to follow orders.

01:53:54.180 --> 01:53:55.619
He scowled.

01:53:55.680 --> 01:53:57.000
Now come.

01:53:57.060 --> 01:54:00.840
Morosera swept away, lashing his tail.

01:54:00.899 --> 01:54:04.199
Starflight and fate speaker exchanged

01:54:04.199 --> 01:54:04.859
glances.

01:54:04.920 --> 01:54:07.619
Have your visions given you any hints?

01:54:07.739 --> 01:54:10.619
Starflight asked about whatever their

01:54:10.619 --> 01:54:11.760
secret plan is, I mean?

01:54:11.819 --> 01:54:15.119
She scratched her neck, the anklet of

01:54:15.119 --> 01:54:16.800
silver scales glittering as she moved.

01:54:16.859 --> 01:54:18.600
Let me think.

01:54:18.659 --> 01:54:21.239
She closed her eyes for a moment, then

01:54:21.239 --> 01:54:22.140
open them again.

01:54:22.199 --> 01:54:23.880
Oh, absolutely.

01:54:23.939 --> 01:54:27.239
It involves us, but both of us, and we're

01:54:27.239 --> 01:54:29.279
going to be heroes, and the whole tribe

01:54:29.279 --> 01:54:31.380
will help us stop the war, and maybe

01:54:31.380 --> 01:54:33.659
they'll even make us king and queen.

01:54:33.779 --> 01:54:36.119
Startled, he blinked at her.

01:54:36.180 --> 01:54:37.859
King and queen.

01:54:37.920 --> 01:54:39.359
But he couldn't.

01:54:39.420 --> 01:54:40.859
She wasn't.

01:54:41.340 --> 01:54:43.680
Well, she wasn't sunny.

01:54:43.739 --> 01:54:46.260
And he'd been in love with one dragon his

01:54:46.260 --> 01:54:46.680
whole life.

01:54:46.739 --> 01:54:51.479
Move now, or I will kill you both

01:54:51.479 --> 01:54:53.220
prophecy or no prophecy.

01:54:53.279 --> 01:54:55.619
Morosier bellowed from the tunnel.

01:54:55.680 --> 01:54:58.079
The dragonette scrambled up and hurried

01:54:58.079 --> 01:54:59.699
after him, tripping over each other.

01:54:59.819 --> 01:55:03.060
Fate speaker bounded into the lead, and

01:55:03.060 --> 01:55:05.579
Starflight was left trailing behind, his

01:55:05.579 --> 01:55:06.840
mind a whirl of confusion.

01:55:06.960 --> 01:55:09.539
He didn't want to think about a possible

01:55:09.539 --> 01:55:12.600
future as fate speaker's king, so he

01:55:12.600 --> 01:55:14.039
focused on his father's experiments

01:55:14.039 --> 01:55:14.460
instead.

01:55:14.520 --> 01:55:17.699
Why are they torturing the rain wings?

01:55:17.760 --> 01:55:19.739
I can figure this out.

01:55:19.800 --> 01:55:21.539
Think, Starflight.

01:55:21.600 --> 01:55:22.199
Think.

01:55:22.319 --> 01:55:25.260
His 1st guess was that the Nightwings

01:55:25.260 --> 01:55:27.539
wanted to use Rainwing Venom themselves.

01:55:27.600 --> 01:55:30.720
As vengeance had said, it was one of the

01:55:30.720 --> 01:55:32.340
most powerful weapons in Pyria.

01:55:32.399 --> 01:55:35.340
If they could somehow replicate the Venom

01:55:35.340 --> 01:55:38.939
or adapt it for their own purposes, that

01:55:38.939 --> 01:55:41.159
plus their telepathy and precognition

01:55:41.159 --> 01:55:43.260
would make the night wings unstoppable.

01:55:43.319 --> 01:55:47.340
Maybe their secret plan involved joining

01:55:47.340 --> 01:55:47.760
the war.

01:55:47.819 --> 01:55:50.100
Once they had this new kind of weapon for

01:55:50.100 --> 01:55:50.579
themselves.

01:55:50.640 --> 01:55:53.579
Starflight already knew they'd chosen a

01:55:53.579 --> 01:55:56.819
side, blisters, although why her?

01:55:56.819 --> 01:55:58.800
and why they were thinking of fighting

01:55:58.800 --> 01:56:01.439
the war now, 18 years into it, he

01:56:01.439 --> 01:56:02.159
couldn't figure out.

01:56:02.220 --> 01:56:04.739
Perhaps Blister had promised them

01:56:04.739 --> 01:56:05.100
something.

01:56:05.159 --> 01:56:07.859
The way Blaze was giving up territory to

01:56:07.859 --> 01:56:09.479
the ice wings in exchange for their

01:56:09.479 --> 01:56:09.779
help.

01:56:09.840 --> 01:56:11.819
Territory.

01:56:11.880 --> 01:56:14.640
Starflight stopped in the middle of their

01:56:14.640 --> 01:56:17.340
rocky tunnel, as understanding flooded

01:56:17.340 --> 01:56:17.640
over him.

01:56:17.699 --> 01:56:19.800
That's what they need.

01:56:19.859 --> 01:56:23.100
More than anything, the Nightwings need a

01:56:23.100 --> 01:56:23.460
new home.

01:56:23.520 --> 01:56:26.760
The volcano was extremely dangerous.

01:56:26.819 --> 01:56:29.699
Maybe it had been dormant when the tribe

01:56:29.699 --> 01:56:31.500
moved here, but it certainly wasn't

01:56:31.500 --> 01:56:31.859
anymore.

01:56:31.920 --> 01:56:34.380
The night wings were living under its

01:56:34.380 --> 01:56:37.500
threat every day, and the island was a

01:56:37.500 --> 01:56:38.460
horrible place to live.

01:56:38.520 --> 01:56:41.520
They must be running out of prey, with

01:56:41.520 --> 01:56:44.340
hardly any fresh water to drink, no view

01:56:44.340 --> 01:56:46.319
of the sky through the thick cloud cover

01:56:46.319 --> 01:56:48.779
and nowhere to go except through the

01:56:48.779 --> 01:56:49.920
tunnel to the rainforest.

01:56:49.979 --> 01:56:53.340
The rainforest, which was the opposite of

01:56:53.340 --> 01:56:55.739
here, the perfect place to live.

01:56:55.800 --> 01:56:57.840
That's their plan.

01:56:57.960 --> 01:57:00.479
Starflight clutched his head.

01:57:00.539 --> 01:57:02.819
Why hadn't he figured it out sooner?

01:57:02.880 --> 01:57:04.859
The Night Wings weren't trying to

01:57:04.859 --> 01:57:05.880
reproduce the venom.

01:57:05.939 --> 01:57:08.159
Masterminds experiments were all about

01:57:08.159 --> 01:57:10.560
how to defend against it, because the

01:57:10.560 --> 01:57:12.119
night wings were planning to invade the

01:57:12.119 --> 01:57:14.579
rainforest and steal it from the rain

01:57:14.579 --> 01:57:16.920
wings, but they were afraid of the rain

01:57:16.920 --> 01:57:17.880
wings fighting back.

01:57:17.939 --> 01:57:20.699
Even the famously peaceful tribe would

01:57:20.699 --> 01:57:22.439
surely have to defend their home.

01:57:22.680 --> 01:57:25.260
So the night wings were figuring out how

01:57:25.260 --> 01:57:27.420
to protect themselves from rain wing

01:57:27.420 --> 01:57:29.760
venom, in preparation for the day when

01:57:29.760 --> 01:57:32.039
they stormed into the rainforest and took

01:57:32.039 --> 01:57:32.760
it over for themselves.

01:57:32.819 --> 01:57:36.239
Is that what blister has promised them?

01:57:36.359 --> 01:57:39.239
The tunnel from the rainforest to the

01:57:39.239 --> 01:57:40.079
kingdom of sand.

01:57:40.199 --> 01:57:43.079
That's for a sandwing army.

01:57:43.140 --> 01:57:46.319
Once she is queen, so they can comb

01:57:46.319 --> 01:57:47.939
through and help the night wings fight

01:57:47.939 --> 01:57:49.739
their rain wings, if need be.

01:57:49.800 --> 01:57:52.800
The rain wings were an awful danger.

01:57:52.859 --> 01:57:55.380
This wasn't a matter of a few dragons

01:57:55.380 --> 01:57:56.640
disappearing here or there.

01:57:56.699 --> 01:58:00.479
Glory was right, and Queen Magnificent

01:58:00.479 --> 01:58:01.020
was wrong.

01:58:01.079 --> 01:58:04.079
They have to fight back, or soon they'll

01:58:04.079 --> 01:58:04.859
all be dead.

01:58:04.920 --> 01:58:07.380
And I'm the only one who knows.

01:58:07.439 --> 01:58:12.000
But he was just Starflight, the weakest

01:58:12.000 --> 01:58:14.159
most cowardly dragon ever chosen for a

01:58:14.159 --> 01:58:14.699
prophecy.

01:58:14.760 --> 01:58:17.159
How could he save the rain wings?

01:58:17.220 --> 01:58:19.619
How could he stop his own tribe from

01:58:19.619 --> 01:58:20.399
destroying them?

01:58:20.460 --> 01:58:23.279
Fate speaker came charging back down the

01:58:23.279 --> 01:58:23.699
tunnel?

01:58:23.760 --> 01:58:26.699
I keep thinking he can't get any more

01:58:26.699 --> 01:58:29.640
grumpy, and then he does, she said.

01:58:29.699 --> 01:58:31.140
Come on, hurry up.

01:58:31.199 --> 01:58:33.600
He says you have to meet the others in

01:58:33.600 --> 01:58:35.039
case you're the dragonette in the

01:58:35.039 --> 01:58:36.000
prophecy instead of me.

01:58:36.060 --> 01:58:38.340
She waved her talons in front of his

01:58:38.340 --> 01:58:38.520
face.

01:58:38.579 --> 01:58:40.920
Wake up, dreamy face.

01:58:41.039 --> 01:58:43.739
Starflight shook himself as hard as he

01:58:43.739 --> 01:58:43.979
could.

01:58:44.039 --> 01:58:46.439
Coming, he said.

01:58:46.560 --> 01:58:48.840
Although he felt like he could barely

01:58:48.840 --> 01:58:49.739
string words together.

01:58:49.800 --> 01:58:51.659
Maybe I'm wrong.

01:58:51.720 --> 01:58:53.579
But he knew he wasn't.

01:58:53.640 --> 01:58:56.340
All the pieces fit together too well.

01:58:56.399 --> 01:59:00.359
I figured out the Nightwing's secret plan

01:59:00.359 --> 01:59:01.319
he thought.

01:59:01.380 --> 01:59:04.500
But now, what do I do about it?

01:59:04.560 --> 01:59:08.939
Part two.

01:59:09.000 --> 01:59:11.460
The Queen's Secret.
3285
01:59:11,520 --> 01:59:14,460	Chapter 7.

01:59:14.579 --> 01:59:16.619
Others.

01:59:16.739 --> 01:59:20.220
What fate speaker had said didn't sink in

01:59:20.220 --> 01:59:22.140
until Starflight was actually standing in

01:59:22.140 --> 01:59:24.239
the cave a short flight from the fortress

01:59:24.239 --> 01:59:27.840
facing 4 unfamiliar and unfriendly faces

01:59:27.840 --> 01:59:31.800
red, green, brown, and white gold.

01:59:31.920 --> 01:59:35.939
They have a sky wing, Starflight

01:59:35.939 --> 01:59:36.359
Thought.

01:59:36.420 --> 01:59:38.880
And a sand wing who looks like a real

01:59:38.880 --> 01:59:39.659
sand wing.

01:59:39.720 --> 01:59:42.899
He hadn't met many sand wings in his life

01:59:42.899 --> 01:59:45.180
but this one's scowl and restless

01:59:45.180 --> 01:59:47.279
hostility made her look like the opposite

01:59:47.279 --> 01:59:48.000
of sunny.

01:59:48.060 --> 01:59:52.500
The alternate dragonets of destiny.

01:59:52.560 --> 01:59:55.979
Mario Cyr growled, scanning them with a

01:59:55.979 --> 01:59:56.880
displeased expression.

01:59:57.000 --> 01:59:58.979
Who is that?

01:59:59.100 --> 02:00:02.100
Said the emerald green seawing, squinting

02:00:02.100 --> 02:00:02.880
at Starflight.

02:00:02.939 --> 02:00:04.619
Looks like her.

02:00:04.680 --> 02:00:06.840
Is he going to be annoying like her?

02:00:06.899 --> 02:00:09.119
He jerked his head at fade speaker.

02:00:09.180 --> 02:00:11.520
This is Starflight.

02:00:11.579 --> 02:00:14.579
Starflight, these are my friends, fate

02:00:14.579 --> 02:00:16.859
speaker said, blithely ignoring him.

02:00:16.920 --> 02:00:19.800
The Sky Wing snorted, and the sand wing

02:00:19.800 --> 02:00:20.340
rolled her eyes.

02:00:20.399 --> 02:00:22.439
Over there is Flame.

02:00:22.500 --> 02:00:23.819
The sky wing, obviously.

02:00:23.880 --> 02:00:26.880
The fat mud wing is ogre, the sand wing

02:00:26.880 --> 02:00:29.039
with the sour expression is viper, and

02:00:29.039 --> 02:00:30.899
the shrimpy sea wing is squid.

02:00:30.960 --> 02:00:33.180
Did she get in trouble?

02:00:33.239 --> 02:00:35.159
Squid asked Morrow Seer.

02:00:35.220 --> 02:00:37.380
I told her she'd get in trouble if she

02:00:37.380 --> 02:00:38.460
left a cave.

02:00:38.520 --> 02:00:39.359
I hope you thumped her.

02:00:39.420 --> 02:00:42.300
Where have you been?

02:00:42.359 --> 02:00:44.460
Viper demanded at the same time?

02:00:44.520 --> 02:00:46.859
Jabbing her poisonous tail toward

02:00:46.859 --> 02:00:47.640
Morrisier.

02:00:47.699 --> 02:00:50.460
We've been here for a whole day and a

02:00:50.460 --> 02:00:53.279
half, and no one has checked on us or fed

02:00:53.279 --> 02:00:55.380
us anything, but what appears to be

02:00:55.380 --> 02:00:57.899
leftovers from a meal 3 months ago.

02:00:57.960 --> 02:01:01.079
Most of which he threw up.

02:01:01.140 --> 02:01:04.079
Flame said darkly, pointing at Okre.

02:01:04.140 --> 02:01:07.800
It was awful, Ogre said.

02:01:07.859 --> 02:01:09.779
Probably food poisoning.

02:01:09.840 --> 02:01:12.060
You're lucky I'm still alive.

02:01:12.119 --> 02:01:16.619
Quite lucky, agreed Flame, since I was

02:01:16.619 --> 02:01:17.880
extremely tempted to kill him.

02:01:17.939 --> 02:01:21.539
That's why it smells so bad in here, fate

02:01:21.539 --> 02:01:22.199
speaker offered.

02:01:22.260 --> 02:01:25.439
Can we move to a different cave, or ooh

02:01:25.439 --> 02:01:26.159
into the fortress?

02:01:26.220 --> 02:01:29.159
If there's a whole other set of

02:01:29.159 --> 02:01:31.859
dragonettes, with all the elements that

02:01:31.859 --> 02:01:34.199
are really in the prophecy, then nobody

02:01:34.199 --> 02:01:34.920
needs us at all.

02:01:34.979 --> 02:01:37.560
Starflight's head was spinning.

02:01:37.619 --> 02:01:40.380
But if the talents of peace had these all

02:01:40.380 --> 02:01:42.960
along, then why treat us the way they

02:01:42.960 --> 02:01:43.140
did?

02:01:43.140 --> 02:01:44.819
Why keep us around?

02:01:44.880 --> 02:01:47.579
And why would the Nightwings send an

02:01:47.579 --> 02:01:48.420
assassin after us?

02:01:48.479 --> 02:01:51.659
Pieces started to fall into place in his

02:01:51.659 --> 02:01:51.840
head.

02:01:51.899 --> 02:01:55.319
They wanted us dead, so they could

02:01:55.319 --> 02:01:56.640
replace us with these five.

02:01:56.699 --> 02:01:59.460
It wouldn't do to have 2 sets of

02:01:59.460 --> 02:02:01.199
dragonettes running around claiming

02:02:01.199 --> 02:02:01.619
destiny.

02:02:01.680 --> 02:02:05.039
Then he thought about the timing, and a

02:02:05.039 --> 02:02:06.659
shudder ran through his scales.

02:02:06.779 --> 02:02:10.680
We had a chance until we angered blister

02:02:10.680 --> 02:02:12.539
until I angered her.

02:02:12.600 --> 02:02:15.720
It was after that, when they decided to

02:02:15.720 --> 02:02:16.079
kill us.

02:02:16.199 --> 02:02:18.659
Because I failed to convince the others

02:02:18.659 --> 02:02:20.100
to pick her as the Queen.

02:02:20.159 --> 02:02:23.100
Maro Sierra was watching his face

02:02:23.100 --> 02:02:25.680
intently, as if he might be listening to

02:02:25.680 --> 02:02:27.420
the thoughts running through Starflight's

02:02:27.420 --> 02:02:27.659
mind.

02:02:27.720 --> 02:02:31.380
So Deathbringer was coming for all of us

02:02:31.380 --> 02:02:35.279
Starflight said to him, His primary

02:02:35.279 --> 02:02:38.100
target was the rain wing. said Maru

02:02:38.100 --> 02:02:38.520
Seer.

02:02:38.579 --> 02:02:41.520
Secondary, the sea wing.

02:02:41.579 --> 02:02:45.359
The rest of you are still negotiable.

02:02:45.420 --> 02:02:47.460
Starflight shook his head.

02:02:47.520 --> 02:02:50.340
You can't kill glory and tsunami.

02:02:50.399 --> 02:02:52.739
I won't do anything you say if that

02:02:52.739 --> 02:02:52.979
happens.

02:02:53.100 --> 02:02:56.460
His talons trembled, as if the volcano

02:02:56.460 --> 02:02:57.659
were rumbling under his feet.

02:02:57.720 --> 02:03:00.600
He half expected Morrow's there to slash

02:03:00.600 --> 02:03:01.439
his throat right then.

02:03:01.500 --> 02:03:03.659
We'll see.

02:03:03.720 --> 02:03:05.819
Said Morrow Seer.

02:03:05.880 --> 02:03:07.380
He didn't look very worried.

02:03:07.500 --> 02:03:10.500
Your real problem is that my friends are

02:03:10.500 --> 02:03:12.239
never going to let you replace me.

02:03:12.300 --> 02:03:14.520
Fate speaker said tomorrow, seer.

02:03:14.579 --> 02:03:16.140
We were raised together.

02:03:16.199 --> 02:03:17.520
We're loyal to each other.

02:03:17.579 --> 02:03:19.920
They'll fight back if you try to take me

02:03:19.920 --> 02:03:20.819
out and put someone else in.

02:03:20.880 --> 02:03:22.920
Replace her?

02:03:22.979 --> 02:03:24.600
Viper said alertly.

02:03:24.659 --> 02:03:25.920
We can do that.

02:03:25.979 --> 02:03:28.619
Do it, said Flame.

02:03:28.680 --> 02:03:29.579
I vote yes.

02:03:29.640 --> 02:03:32.880
Me too, said Ogre.

02:03:32.939 --> 02:03:34.319
He looks quiet.

02:03:34.380 --> 02:03:36.119
Quiet would be great.

02:03:36.180 --> 02:03:39.479
Can I be the one to shove her off the

02:03:39.479 --> 02:03:39.899
cliff?

02:03:39.960 --> 02:03:41.039
Squid asked.

02:03:41.100 --> 02:03:43.979
Fate speaker gave them all an injured

02:03:43.979 --> 02:03:44.460
look.

02:03:44.520 --> 02:03:46.619
Very funny, guys.

02:03:46.680 --> 02:03:49.020
Starflight got the distinct impression

02:03:49.020 --> 02:03:50.460
that they weren't joking.

02:03:50.520 --> 02:03:53.220
Poor fate speaker, he thought.

02:03:53.279 --> 02:03:55.439
She really thinks they're her friends.

02:03:55.500 --> 02:03:58.680
Do you have annoying visions all the time

02:03:58.680 --> 02:03:58.979
too?

02:03:59.039 --> 02:04:00.840
Squid asked Starflight.

02:04:00.899 --> 02:04:04.020
Starflight shuffled his talons awkwardly

02:04:04.020 --> 02:04:06.539
but Mario Seer cut him off before he had

02:04:06.539 --> 02:04:06.960
to answer.

02:04:07.020 --> 02:04:13.140
You may all be replaced, he said, as if

02:04:13.140 --> 02:04:15.000
the word tasted disagreeable in his

02:04:15.000 --> 02:04:15.300
mouth.

02:04:15.359 --> 02:04:18.000
Except for you.

02:04:18.119 --> 02:04:20.279
He nodded at flame.

02:04:20.340 --> 02:04:22.680
The Skywing Dragonette puffed out his

02:04:22.680 --> 02:04:23.039
chest.

02:04:23.100 --> 02:04:24.119
Ha!

02:04:24.180 --> 02:04:25.619
And don't you all forget it?

02:04:25.680 --> 02:04:27.659
Viper hissed at him.

02:04:27.720 --> 02:04:29.819
Then why'd you bring us here?

02:04:29.880 --> 02:04:31.739
She asked Morrow Seer.

02:04:31.800 --> 02:04:34.079
And when can we go back?

02:04:34.140 --> 02:04:35.340
Squid asked.

02:04:35.399 --> 02:04:37.680
Maro C.R. frowned at Squid.

02:04:37.739 --> 02:04:39.840
Starflight could sense that he found the

02:04:39.840 --> 02:04:41.520
sea wing unusually irritating.

02:04:41.579 --> 02:04:44.039
He wondered if that meant the night wings

02:04:44.039 --> 02:04:45.840
might change their minds about tsunami.

02:04:45.899 --> 02:04:47.460
If they kept her alive.

02:04:47.520 --> 02:04:48.960
They wouldn't have to deal with this

02:04:48.960 --> 02:04:50.039
dragon as the alternative.

02:04:50.100 --> 02:04:53.220
Then again, tsunami could be pretty

02:04:53.220 --> 02:04:54.600
unusually irritating too.

02:04:54.720 --> 02:04:57.779
Too bad it didn't work out more neatly

02:04:57.779 --> 02:04:58.859
for Morrow's here.

02:04:58.920 --> 02:05:01.560
Starflight thought, with a twinge of

02:05:01.560 --> 02:05:05.579
satisfaction. 2 unsuitable night wings, 2

02:05:05.579 --> 02:05:08.520
annoying sea wings, but 2 perfectly fine

02:05:08.520 --> 02:05:10.380
mud wings and sand wings.

02:05:10.439 --> 02:05:13.500
He thought Sunny was more than perfectly

02:05:13.500 --> 02:05:14.939
fine, of course.

02:05:15.000 --> 02:05:16.800
Who needed a poisonous tail when she was

02:05:16.800 --> 02:05:19.800
funny, smart, and kinder than any other

02:05:19.800 --> 02:05:20.640
dragon in the world.

02:05:20.699 --> 02:05:25.140
If you want to be part of this, what I

02:05:25.140 --> 02:05:28.439
need to see from all of you, Marcio

02:05:28.439 --> 02:05:31.979
growled, is that you can take orders, work

02:05:31.979 --> 02:05:34.439
together, and do as you're told.

02:05:34.500 --> 02:05:38.159
Take orders and do as you're told are the

02:05:38.159 --> 02:05:38.399
same thing.

02:05:38.520 --> 02:05:40.260
Fate speaker said to him.

02:05:40.319 --> 02:05:41.760
He glared at her.

02:05:41.819 --> 02:05:45.060
That's how important it is.

02:05:45.119 --> 02:05:48.420
His dark eyes scanned the dragonettes in

02:05:48.420 --> 02:05:48.779
front of him.

02:05:48.840 --> 02:05:54.539
So, your 1st test, you, he said to

02:05:54.539 --> 02:05:55.140
Starflight.

02:05:55.260 --> 02:05:56.880
All you have to do.

02:05:57.000 --> 02:05:59.399
If you can, is stay alive.

02:05:59.460 --> 02:06:01.380
What?

02:06:01.500 --> 02:06:02.460
Starflight said.

02:06:02.520 --> 02:06:05.460
The rest of you, said Marosir.

02:06:05.520 --> 02:06:06.720
Kill him.

02:06:06.779 --> 02:06:09.239
He flicked his tail at Starflight.

02:06:09.300 --> 02:06:13.020
The dragonettes all stared at him for a

02:06:13.020 --> 02:06:14.100
long, awful moment.

02:06:14.159 --> 02:06:17.159
Can't we kill her instead?

02:06:17.220 --> 02:06:20.159
Viper asked, pointing at fate speaker.

02:06:20.220 --> 02:06:23.699
Ooh, yes, I volunteer, said Flame.

02:06:23.760 --> 02:06:24.840
No.

02:06:24.899 --> 02:06:26.819
Morosier nearly shouted.

02:06:26.880 --> 02:06:28.680
What are you waiting for?

02:06:28.739 --> 02:06:30.479
That was an order.

02:06:30.539 --> 02:06:31.920
I said kill him.

02:06:32.039 --> 02:06:33.960
He's serious.

02:06:34.020 --> 02:06:37.439
Starflight realized, and then Viper

02:06:37.439 --> 02:06:38.340
lunged at him.

02:06:38.399 --> 02:06:40.800
Her poisonous tail arching forward like a

02:06:40.800 --> 02:06:41.579
scorpion's.

02:06:41.579 --> 02:06:45.060
On his other side, Ocher's claws slashed

02:06:45.060 --> 02:06:47.100
at his wing, missing by hair.

02:06:47.159 --> 02:06:49.920
And Flame made the fire is coming hissing

02:06:49.920 --> 02:06:51.960
sound, Star Light remembered from his

02:06:51.960 --> 02:06:53.699
terrible training sessions with Kestrel.

02:06:53.760 --> 02:06:56.640
Maru Cyr was probably hoping to see

02:06:56.640 --> 02:06:58.619
Starflight's fighting skills in action

02:06:58.619 --> 02:07:00.000
but Starfly didn't care.

02:07:00.060 --> 02:07:02.460
He knew better than to rely on those.

02:07:02.520 --> 02:07:04.380
He also knew he couldn't do what he

02:07:04.380 --> 02:07:06.720
normally did, which was freeze and hope

02:07:06.720 --> 02:07:07.560
nobody noticed him.

02:07:07.619 --> 02:07:10.319
Starflight ducked under Oker's wing

02:07:10.319 --> 02:07:13.140
shoved squid into Viper, dodged around

02:07:13.140 --> 02:07:15.239
fate speaker, and leaped out of the

02:07:15.239 --> 02:07:15.539
cave.

02:07:15.600 --> 02:07:18.720
Wind whistled through his wings as he

02:07:18.720 --> 02:07:19.619
sailed down the cliff.

02:07:19.680 --> 02:07:22.079
The shouts of the dragonettes echoed

02:07:22.079 --> 02:07:22.380
behind him.

02:07:22.500 --> 02:07:24.600
He knew they'd be right on his tail.

02:07:24.659 --> 02:07:27.000
He had to find somewhere to hide.
3513
02:07:27,060 --> 02:07:31,500	Chapter 8.

02:07:31.560 --> 02:07:35.100
Starflight shot down the cliffside and

02:07:35.100 --> 02:07:36.239
banked toward the ocean.

02:07:36.300 --> 02:07:38.640
His eyes scanned the ground below him

02:07:38.640 --> 02:07:39.239
frantically.

02:07:39.300 --> 02:07:42.060
The good news was, if he'd understood

02:07:42.060 --> 02:07:44.220
them right, the dragonheads hadn't been

02:07:44.220 --> 02:07:46.020
on the island very long, and probably

02:07:46.020 --> 02:07:47.520
didn't know its geography at all.

02:07:47.579 --> 02:07:50.220
The bad news was, neither did he.

02:07:50.279 --> 02:07:53.279
Right now, he was on the other side of

02:07:53.279 --> 02:07:54.840
the volcano from the forest.

02:07:54.899 --> 02:07:56.880
Here, there were no trees.

02:07:57.000 --> 02:08:00.060
Everything below him was dark rocks, or

02:08:00.060 --> 02:08:02.520
rivers of glowing lava, nothing to hide

02:08:02.520 --> 02:08:02.880
behind.

02:08:02.939 --> 02:08:05.399
Ahead of him, there was a strip of black

02:08:05.399 --> 02:08:07.800
sand beach that seemed to circle the

02:08:07.800 --> 02:08:07.979
island.

02:08:08.100 --> 02:08:10.319
He remembered Glory saying that the

02:08:10.319 --> 02:08:12.180
tunnel to the rainforest was in a cave

02:08:12.180 --> 02:08:13.680
above a black sand beach.

02:08:13.739 --> 02:08:16.020
He wandered for a moment if he could find

02:08:16.020 --> 02:08:18.000
it, but there wasn't time with the

02:08:18.000 --> 02:08:19.380
dragonettes coming after him.

02:08:19.439 --> 02:08:21.659
He couldn't outfly them for long either.

02:08:21.720 --> 02:08:25.500
Flame, like most sky wings, had enormous

02:08:25.500 --> 02:08:27.539
wings, which made them faster than

02:08:27.539 --> 02:08:28.859
dragons from any other tribe.

02:08:28.920 --> 02:08:32.520
He risked a glance over his shoulder and

02:08:32.520 --> 02:08:34.920
saw the bright colors of 4 dragonettes

02:08:34.920 --> 02:08:37.020
flash through the sky, much closer than

02:08:37.020 --> 02:08:37.859
he would have liked.

02:08:37.920 --> 02:08:39.359
Only four.

02:08:39.420 --> 02:08:42.300
Fate speaker was nowhere to be seen.

02:08:42.359 --> 02:08:45.840
Disobeying orders, or sneaking up on me

02:08:45.840 --> 02:08:46.439
some other way.

02:08:46.500 --> 02:08:49.140
He didn't have time to think about it

02:08:49.140 --> 02:08:51.779
Starflight twisted into a dive and

02:08:51.779 --> 02:08:53.460
swooped as close to the ground as he

02:08:53.460 --> 02:08:53.939
dared.

02:08:54.000 --> 02:08:56.399
His black scales would make him harder to

02:08:56.399 --> 02:08:58.319
see against the rocks than if he were up

02:08:58.319 --> 02:08:58.680
in the sky.

02:08:58.739 --> 02:09:02.399
A blast of steam shot out of one of the

02:09:02.399 --> 02:09:04.439
vents in the ground, and he flapped

02:09:04.439 --> 02:09:06.779
hastily aside, barely avoiding the heat.

02:09:06.840 --> 02:09:09.960
From this close, the rocks below looked

02:09:09.960 --> 02:09:12.720
even more like black dragon scales, but

02:09:12.720 --> 02:09:14.159
all melted and fused together.

02:09:14.220 --> 02:09:17.939
Like mine will be, if Flame and Viper get

02:09:17.939 --> 02:09:18.539
their claws on me.

02:09:18.600 --> 02:09:22.199
The problem was, the dragonettes were so

02:09:22.199 --> 02:09:24.600
close behind him that they'd see anything

02:09:24.600 --> 02:09:24.960
he did.

02:09:25.020 --> 02:09:27.300
They'd be able to follow him straight to

02:09:27.300 --> 02:09:28.380
any hiding place.

02:09:28.439 --> 02:09:31.020
It was too risky to try to lose them in

02:09:31.020 --> 02:09:33.420
the water or the clouds, not with a sea

02:09:33.420 --> 02:09:35.100
wing and a sky wing among them.

02:09:35.159 --> 02:09:38.100
He beat his wings faster, trying to

02:09:38.100 --> 02:09:38.399
think.

02:09:38.460 --> 02:09:40.920
Use your brain, Starflight.

02:09:40.979 --> 02:09:42.180
That's all you've got.

02:09:42.239 --> 02:09:45.840
There was only one place to hide, the

02:09:45.840 --> 02:09:46.380
fortress.

02:09:46.439 --> 02:09:48.720
Maybe he'd find a room he could lock

02:09:48.720 --> 02:09:51.180
himself into, or maybe his father would

02:09:51.180 --> 02:09:51.600
help him.

02:09:51.659 --> 02:09:54.359
He swooped into an arc, heading toward it

02:09:54.359 --> 02:09:56.399
hoping the Dragonettes wouldn't cut him

02:09:56.399 --> 02:09:57.239
off before he reached it.

02:09:57.300 --> 02:10:00.720
Another blaze of heat brushed his tail

02:10:00.720 --> 02:10:02.939
and he twisted to see where the steam had

02:10:02.939 --> 02:10:03.539
come from this time.

02:10:03.600 --> 02:10:07.439
To his horror, Flame was only a few wing

02:10:07.439 --> 02:10:09.960
beats behind him, with fire curling out

02:10:09.960 --> 02:10:10.680
of his nose.

02:10:10.739 --> 02:10:13.140
The sight of the sky wing propelled

02:10:13.140 --> 02:10:15.300
Starflight forward, the dragonette

02:10:15.300 --> 02:10:18.060
beating his wings as hard as he could, but

02:10:18.060 --> 02:10:20.220
his muscles already ached with exhaustion

02:10:20.220 --> 02:10:22.020
and he knew he'd never make it to the

02:10:22.020 --> 02:10:23.399
fortress before Flame caught up.

02:10:23.460 --> 02:10:26.640
Then he spotted the caves that lined the

02:10:26.640 --> 02:10:27.539
lava river below.

02:10:27.600 --> 02:10:30.000
The rain wing prisons.

02:10:30.060 --> 02:10:32.520
Glory had described hers in vivid

02:10:32.520 --> 02:10:32.880
detail.

02:10:32.939 --> 02:10:37.079
Suddenly, a blast of thick smoke shot out

02:10:37.079 --> 02:10:38.460
of a vent in the ground below him.

02:10:38.520 --> 02:10:41.340
This was a chance he couldn't miss.

02:10:41.399 --> 02:10:44.460
He dropped behind the smoke, hoping it

02:10:44.460 --> 02:10:45.960
looked as though he was still aiming for

02:10:45.960 --> 02:10:48.420
the fortress, and then spiraled tightly

02:10:48.420 --> 02:10:50.460
down and dove into the 1st cave he

02:10:50.460 --> 02:10:50.699
found.

02:10:50.760 --> 02:10:53.640
A nightwing guard was lying across the

02:10:53.640 --> 02:10:54.060
entrance.

02:10:54.119 --> 02:10:57.479
Starflight shot over her head and tumbled

02:10:57.479 --> 02:10:58.319
onto the stone floor.

02:10:58.380 --> 02:11:01.979
The guard sat up in a hurry, blinking, as

02:11:01.979 --> 02:11:02.819
if she'd been asleep.

02:11:02.880 --> 02:11:06.000
Farther into the cave, Starflight heard

02:11:06.000 --> 02:11:08.520
scales shifting as the imprisoned rain

02:11:08.520 --> 02:11:09.840
wing peeked out of the commotion.

02:11:09.899 --> 02:11:12.600
Hey, said the guard.

02:11:12.659 --> 02:11:13.859
What are you doing here?

02:11:13.920 --> 02:11:16.920
She lashed your tail. looking very large

02:11:16.920 --> 02:11:19.800
all of a sudden, despite the ribs visible

02:11:19.800 --> 02:11:20.760
through her underscales.

02:11:20.819 --> 02:11:23.579
Starflight staggered up to his feet again

02:11:23.579 --> 02:11:26.100
trying to look calm and ordinary and like

02:11:26.100 --> 02:11:27.420
he wasn't being chased.

02:11:27.479 --> 02:11:31.920
I, I, I came to see the rain wing

02:11:31.920 --> 02:11:33.119
Starflight stammered.

02:11:33.239 --> 02:11:34.619
The prisoner.

02:11:34.680 --> 02:11:36.600
The guard frowned suspiciously.

02:11:36.659 --> 02:11:37.680
Why?

02:11:37.739 --> 02:11:39.600
Um.

02:11:39.779 --> 02:11:42.539
Starflight flipped through scrolls in his

02:11:42.539 --> 02:11:43.680
head as fast as he could.

02:11:43.739 --> 02:11:45.720
There were a few stories about

02:11:45.720 --> 02:11:48.420
dragonettes and his favorite scroll, Tales

02:11:48.420 --> 02:11:49.319
of the Night Wings.

02:11:49.380 --> 02:11:52.859
This couldn't possibly work, but school

02:11:52.859 --> 02:11:53.579
project?

02:11:53.640 --> 02:11:54.539
He tried.

02:11:54.600 --> 02:11:57.840
To his astonishment, the guard completely

02:11:57.840 --> 02:11:58.439
relaxed.

02:11:58.500 --> 02:12:00.659
Ah, she said.

02:12:00.720 --> 02:12:03.779
Assignment for mastermind, right?

02:12:03.840 --> 02:12:07.140
That weirdo is all about field studies

02:12:07.140 --> 02:12:09.659
and live observation, drives my daughter

02:12:09.659 --> 02:12:10.140
crazy.

02:12:10.199 --> 02:12:11.520
All right, go ahead.

02:12:11.579 --> 02:12:12.840
Just be careful.

02:12:12.899 --> 02:12:15.899
Starflight bowed gratefully and fled

02:12:15.899 --> 02:12:17.340
toward the back of the cave.

02:12:17.399 --> 02:12:19.979
The rain wing prisoner was chained to the

02:12:19.979 --> 02:12:22.500
floor and the wall, and a snout was

02:12:22.500 --> 02:12:24.659
wrapped in an iron band, like the one

02:12:24.659 --> 02:12:26.279
strong wings had put on orchid.

02:12:26.340 --> 02:12:29.220
He watched Starflight with a resigned

02:12:29.220 --> 02:12:30.060
mournful expression.

02:12:30.119 --> 02:12:32.819
His scales were gray and dark blue.

02:12:32.880 --> 02:12:35.939
Starflight wondered if extra chains had

02:12:35.939 --> 02:12:38.399
been added to all the dragons after glory

02:12:38.399 --> 02:12:40.380
and kinkaju escaped.

02:12:40.439 --> 02:12:42.479
As far as he remembered, glory had been

02:12:42.479 --> 02:12:44.399
muzzled, but not chained to the wall.

02:12:44.460 --> 02:12:47.640
He was tempted to tell the sad rain wing

02:12:47.640 --> 02:12:49.560
that he would be rescued soon too.

02:12:49.619 --> 02:12:52.020
But it was dangerous enough that he'd

02:12:52.020 --> 02:12:52.619
told Orchid.

02:12:52.680 --> 02:12:55.079
He had no idea whether rain wings could

02:12:55.079 --> 02:12:57.239
keep secrets, and if the night wings

02:12:57.239 --> 02:12:58.680
found out that he'd been going around

02:12:58.680 --> 02:13:00.359
saying reassuring things to their

02:13:00.359 --> 02:13:00.840
prisoners.

02:13:00.899 --> 02:13:03.840
Well, he couldn't imagine they'd like it

02:13:03.840 --> 02:13:04.140
very much.

02:13:04.199 --> 02:13:07.500
A commotion of wings sounded outside.

02:13:07.560 --> 02:13:10.140
Starflight turned to the back of the cave

02:13:10.140 --> 02:13:12.659
which overlooked a huge dark abyss.

02:13:12.720 --> 02:13:15.600
Glory had said that all the prison caves

02:13:15.600 --> 02:13:17.880
were connected by this chasm, which was

02:13:17.880 --> 02:13:19.439
how Kinkachu got from one to the other.

02:13:19.500 --> 02:13:22.079
The last thing Starflight wanted to do

02:13:22.079 --> 02:13:23.220
was jump into that darkness.

02:13:23.340 --> 02:13:25.140
Well, no.

02:13:25.199 --> 02:13:27.720
The very last thing he wanted to do was

02:13:27.720 --> 02:13:30.479
face Flame and Viper in talented talent

02:13:30.479 --> 02:13:30.960
combat.

02:13:31.020 --> 02:13:34.500
So, given those choices, leaping off a

02:13:34.500 --> 02:13:36.300
cliff into the pitch black was the clear

02:13:36.300 --> 02:13:36.779
winner.

02:13:36.840 --> 02:13:39.479
He spread his wings and hopped off the

02:13:39.479 --> 02:13:41.699
edge, flapping to lower himself down

02:13:41.699 --> 02:13:42.300
slowly.

02:13:42.359 --> 02:13:44.760
He kept thinking he was about to crash

02:13:44.760 --> 02:13:47.460
into something sharp and pointy, but only

02:13:47.460 --> 02:13:50.460
empty space yawned below him, as if it

02:13:50.460 --> 02:13:51.479
were trying to suck him down.

02:13:51.539 --> 02:13:55.319
Finally, several dragon lengths down from

02:13:55.319 --> 02:13:57.960
the top, he felt a shallow ledge below

02:13:57.960 --> 02:14:01.020
him and gently rested his talons on it

02:14:01.020 --> 02:14:01.800
folding his wings in.

02:14:01.859 --> 02:14:05.220
Even if someone peered into the chasm, his

02:14:05.220 --> 02:14:07.260
black scales should keep him well hidden

02:14:07.260 --> 02:14:07.859
in the shadows.

02:14:07.920 --> 02:14:10.619
Voices started shouting up above.

02:14:10.680 --> 02:14:12.779
Where is he?

02:14:12.840 --> 02:14:14.460
That sounded like flame.

02:14:14.520 --> 02:14:16.260
Who are you?

02:14:16.319 --> 02:14:17.880
roared the night wing god.

02:14:17.939 --> 02:14:18.899
Intruders?

02:14:18.960 --> 02:14:19.859
A Sky Wing?

02:14:19.920 --> 02:14:20.819
Hunter Mudwing.

02:14:20.880 --> 02:14:22.079
They've come back for the rest of our

02:14:22.079 --> 02:14:22.619
prisoners.

02:14:22.680 --> 02:14:25.739
She started banging on some kind of metal

02:14:25.739 --> 02:14:28.560
alarm gong that reverberated painfully

02:14:28.560 --> 02:14:30.180
off the rocks around Starflight.

02:14:30.239 --> 02:14:33.479
He covered his ears, but even over all

02:14:33.479 --> 02:14:35.159
the noise, he could still hear flame

02:14:35.159 --> 02:14:37.680
bellowing, no, we're supposed to be here

02:14:37.680 --> 02:14:39.600
and ocher.

02:14:39.659 --> 02:14:41.399
We're with Morrow seer.

02:14:41.460 --> 02:14:43.859
We're trying to kill a nightwing

02:14:43.859 --> 02:14:45.479
dragonette, Flame shouted.

02:14:45.539 --> 02:14:47.100
Did you see where he went?

02:14:47.159 --> 02:14:48.239
Wow.

02:14:48.300 --> 02:14:51.180
That was the wrong thing to say.

02:14:51.300 --> 02:14:52.500
Starflight thought.

02:14:52.560 --> 02:14:55.739
They're here to kill our dragonettes!

02:14:55.859 --> 02:14:57.539
shrieked the night wing guard.

02:14:57.600 --> 02:15:01.680
An almighty crash followed, as if she'd

02:15:01.680 --> 02:15:03.600
smashed the gong over Flame's head.

02:15:03.659 --> 02:15:06.239
Starflight hoped she had.

02:15:06.359 --> 02:15:08.640
Every time he thought of the Sky Wing's

02:15:08.640 --> 02:15:11.100
smug face, he thought of how flame was

02:15:11.100 --> 02:15:12.840
meant to take glory's place in the

02:15:12.840 --> 02:15:13.260
prophecy.

02:15:13.319 --> 02:15:16.500
Marusir has been trying to have glory

02:15:16.500 --> 02:15:19.800
killed since the 1st moment he saw her, he

02:15:19.800 --> 02:15:20.100
thought.

02:15:20.159 --> 02:15:23.460
Because she's a rain wing, and he was

02:15:23.460 --> 02:15:25.920
afraid she'd figure out the plan and warn

02:15:25.920 --> 02:15:26.399
her tribe.

02:15:26.460 --> 02:15:29.039
It's not that he thinks she's weak and

02:15:29.039 --> 02:15:29.579
useless.

02:15:29.640 --> 02:15:31.500
He's actually worried about what she

02:15:31.500 --> 02:15:31.979
might do.

02:15:32.039 --> 02:15:34.260
As he should be.

02:15:34.319 --> 02:15:37.680
The crashing and shouting finally ended

02:15:37.680 --> 02:15:39.239
with sounds of what appeared to be

02:15:39.239 --> 02:15:41.399
several guards arriving and carting off

02:15:41.399 --> 02:15:42.539
flame and ocher.

02:15:42.600 --> 02:15:45.359
Starflight hoped Viper and Squid had met

02:15:45.359 --> 02:15:47.579
a similar fate, maybe searching for him

02:15:47.579 --> 02:15:48.539
in the fortress.

02:15:48.600 --> 02:15:51.479
Just in case, he decided to stay hidden

02:15:51.479 --> 02:15:52.140
for a while longer.

02:15:52.199 --> 02:15:55.739
I could try to escape, he thought.

02:15:55.859 --> 02:15:58.319
Now, while no one is watching me.

02:15:58.380 --> 02:16:00.840
I could try to get back to the rainforest

02:16:00.840 --> 02:16:02.100
to warn glory and the others.

02:16:02.159 --> 02:16:05.760
I have an idea where the tunnel is, but

02:16:05.760 --> 02:16:07.380
surely it's guarded.

02:16:07.439 --> 02:16:10.260
And surely they'd stop me, and even more

02:16:10.260 --> 02:16:10.739
Shirley.

02:16:10.800 --> 02:16:14.100
Marsir would be furious, and most likely

02:16:14.100 --> 02:16:15.359
he'd kill me himself.

02:16:15.479 --> 02:16:19.319
He closed his eyes, picturing the island

02:16:19.319 --> 02:16:21.479
or I could fly away across the ocean.

02:16:21.539 --> 02:16:23.819
Just pick a direction and go.

02:16:23.880 --> 02:16:27.060
He already knew he'd never be brave

02:16:27.060 --> 02:16:27.600
enough to try that.

02:16:27.659 --> 02:16:29.880
There was no way to know where the

02:16:29.880 --> 02:16:32.459
nearest land was, or how to find the

02:16:32.459 --> 02:16:33.299
mainland from here.

02:16:33.360 --> 02:16:35.819
This island had not been on any of the

02:16:35.819 --> 02:16:37.620
maps of Pyria he'd ever seen.

02:16:37.680 --> 02:16:38.700
That was for sure.

02:16:38.760 --> 02:16:41.399
Starflight wrapped his wings around his

02:16:41.399 --> 02:16:43.739
talons. rested his head against the rock

02:16:43.739 --> 02:16:45.659
wall behind him, and sighed.

02:16:45.719 --> 02:16:47.399
Starflight?

02:16:47.520 --> 02:16:49.319
A voice whispered above him.

02:16:49.379 --> 02:16:50.519
He froze.

02:16:50.579 --> 02:16:52.620
The shadows would hide him if he kept

02:16:52.620 --> 02:16:52.979
still.

02:16:53.040 --> 02:16:57.120
Starflight, it's me, fate speaker.

02:16:57.180 --> 02:16:58.440
She called softly.

02:16:58.500 --> 02:17:01.079
He realized her voice wasn't coming from

02:17:01.079 --> 02:17:02.280
the cave he'd come through.

02:17:02.340 --> 02:17:04.440
She must be in the cave next to it.

02:17:04.500 --> 02:17:06.659
Also overlooking the abyss.

02:17:06.780 --> 02:17:09.360
I'm pretty sure you're down there?

02:17:09.360 --> 02:17:10.079
she said.

02:17:10.139 --> 02:17:13.019
Because it's a crazy smart and crazy

02:17:13.019 --> 02:17:14.939
brave thing to do, which sounds like

02:17:14.939 --> 02:17:15.119
you.

02:17:15.239 --> 02:17:17.340
Ha!

02:17:17.399 --> 02:17:18.420
Starfly thought.

02:17:18.479 --> 02:17:21.059
Crazy Brave is the opposite of me.

02:17:21.120 --> 02:17:23.280
Crazy Brave is tsunami.

02:17:23.399 --> 02:17:26.159
Crazy Brave would have been turning

02:17:26.159 --> 02:17:28.500
around to fight all 4 dragonettes at once

02:17:28.500 --> 02:17:29.879
which is what she would have done.

02:17:29.940 --> 02:17:33.120
Sitting in a dark hole, waiting for

02:17:33.120 --> 02:17:34.440
someone else to deal with my problem.

02:17:34.500 --> 02:17:36.420
She's right about one thing.

02:17:36.479 --> 02:17:38.159
That does sound like me.

02:17:38.280 --> 02:17:42.180
Fate speaker sat quietly for a moment, but

02:17:42.180 --> 02:17:43.739
he could still hear her breathing.

02:17:43.799 --> 02:17:47.159
Of course, if you're not down there, I

02:17:47.159 --> 02:17:49.919
sound totally insane right now, she

02:17:49.919 --> 02:17:50.159
said.

02:17:50.219 --> 02:17:52.679
There's a rain wing sitting next to me

02:17:52.679 --> 02:17:55.259
who is giving me the weirdest looks.

02:17:55.319 --> 02:17:56.340
Hey there.

02:17:56.399 --> 02:17:57.299
What's happening?

02:17:57.360 --> 02:17:59.819
Nothing weird, just talking to a pit.

02:17:59.879 --> 02:18:01.559
Carry on looking miserable.

02:18:01.680 --> 02:18:02.280
Don't mind me.

02:18:02.340 --> 02:18:03.659
Ooh.

02:18:03.780 --> 02:18:05.700
His ears went a little yellow.

02:18:05.760 --> 02:18:07.079
She reported.

02:18:07.139 --> 02:18:09.959
Does that mean amused or terribly

02:18:09.959 --> 02:18:10.439
annoyed?

02:18:10.500 --> 02:18:11.399
What do you think?

02:18:11.459 --> 02:18:13.499
Amused.

02:18:13.559 --> 02:18:15.059
Starflight thought.

02:18:15.120 --> 02:18:18.059
If his very limited study of rain wing

02:18:18.059 --> 02:18:19.379
scale shifting was any guide.

02:18:19.440 --> 02:18:24.239
I wish I could let you go, sad dragon, she

02:18:24.239 --> 02:18:25.200
said to the rain wing.

02:18:25.260 --> 02:18:27.899
I'd need one of those long pointy sticks

02:18:27.899 --> 02:18:28.020
though.

02:18:28.079 --> 02:18:30.600
Starflight, come on.

02:18:30.659 --> 02:18:32.760
Get up here so we can talk about how to

02:18:32.760 --> 02:18:34.200
help all these sad dragons.

02:18:34.260 --> 02:18:37.079
I checked a few of the other caves, and

02:18:37.079 --> 02:18:38.579
there are at least 10 of them here.

02:18:38.700 --> 02:18:39.840
Can you imagine?

02:18:39.899 --> 02:18:43.680
14, according to Kingaju.

02:18:43.739 --> 02:18:47.100
Oh, I promise I'm not going to kill you

02:18:47.100 --> 02:18:49.559
she added, is that what you're worried

02:18:49.559 --> 02:18:49.739
about?

02:18:49.799 --> 02:18:53.099
My visions say we're going to do amazing

02:18:53.099 --> 02:18:53.939
things together.

02:18:54.000 --> 02:18:56.340
That's hardly going to happen if you're

02:18:56.340 --> 02:18:56.819
dead, right?

02:18:56.879 --> 02:18:59.339
I don't mind telling Morrow, seer, that

02:18:59.339 --> 02:19:02.099
my prophecies are just as good as his

02:19:02.099 --> 02:19:05.699
prophecies and my prophecies say you get

02:19:05.699 --> 02:19:08.219
to live forever.

02:19:08.280 --> 02:19:08.520
So there.

02:19:08.579 --> 02:19:11.219
Starflight smiled into the dark.

02:19:11.340 --> 02:19:13.680
He would love to be present for that

02:19:13.680 --> 02:19:14.280
conversation.

02:19:14.399 --> 02:19:18.540
All right, he said, I'm coming.

02:19:18.600 --> 02:19:21.719
Together, they flew back to the cave

02:19:21.719 --> 02:19:24.120
where Viper and Squid were huddled

02:19:24.120 --> 02:19:26.639
sullenly against the wall, and Marosier

02:19:26.639 --> 02:19:27.719
was pacing back and forth.

02:19:27.780 --> 02:19:31.680
Oh, did you lose some dragonettes?

02:19:31.799 --> 02:19:34.259
Fate speaker said to him, with mock

02:19:34.259 --> 02:19:34.859
sympathy?

02:19:34.920 --> 02:19:36.780
Morrisier glared at her.

02:19:36.840 --> 02:19:38.459
It's not funny.

02:19:38.520 --> 02:19:39.959
Squid hissed.

02:19:40.020 --> 02:19:42.540
There were about a 1000 night wing guards

02:19:42.540 --> 02:19:43.200
chasing me.

02:19:43.319 --> 02:19:45.540
Viper rolled her eyes.

02:19:45.659 --> 02:19:48.180
Try four, she said.

02:19:48.239 --> 02:19:50.879
They nearly burned my tail.

02:19:50.940 --> 02:19:53.159
One of their spears could have taken an

02:19:53.159 --> 02:19:53.579
eye out.

02:19:53.639 --> 02:19:56.280
And when I told them I was a dragonette

02:19:56.280 --> 02:19:58.559
of destiny, they got even more mad.

02:19:58.620 --> 02:20:00.360
I want to go home.

02:20:00.420 --> 02:20:03.420
Squid folded his wings and sulked.

02:20:03.479 --> 02:20:06.239
Plus, I haven't seen any sign of the

02:20:06.239 --> 02:20:07.440
treasure I was promised.

02:20:07.500 --> 02:20:11.100
We keep our treasures safe.

02:20:11.219 --> 02:20:13.079
Marosia rumbled.

02:20:13.139 --> 02:20:16.500
Instead of on an ostentatious display

02:20:16.500 --> 02:20:17.940
like the other tribes.

02:20:18.059 --> 02:20:19.799
He rubbed his forehead.

02:20:19.860 --> 02:20:22.799
Perhaps I could have done a better job of

02:20:22.799 --> 02:20:25.020
warning my tribe that you were here.

02:20:25.079 --> 02:20:27.299
Perhaps you could have.

02:20:27.360 --> 02:20:29.219
Viper snapped.

02:20:29.280 --> 02:20:32.340
The council has been told.

02:20:32.399 --> 02:20:35.100
But apparently the news hasn't spread.

02:20:35.159 --> 02:20:38.159
It's going to take some explaining to get

02:20:38.159 --> 02:20:40.620
flame and ochre out of the dungeon.

02:20:40.680 --> 02:20:43.379
Maro Seer tapped his claws on the rocks

02:20:43.379 --> 02:20:45.420
and tipped his head at Starflight.

02:20:45.479 --> 02:20:49.680
A clever way to foil your tuckers. whether

02:20:49.680 --> 02:20:50.819
you intended it or not.

02:20:50.879 --> 02:20:53.639
It's not what I would have done, but it

02:20:53.639 --> 02:20:53.879
worked.

02:20:54.000 --> 02:20:57.420
Now can we kill fate speaker instead?

02:20:57.479 --> 02:20:58.739
Viper asked.

02:20:58.799 --> 02:21:02.459
Sometimes, you're just horrible, fate

02:21:02.459 --> 02:21:03.420
speaker said to her.

02:21:03.540 --> 02:21:07.559
Seems like you had an opportunity to kill

02:21:07.559 --> 02:21:09.180
him and didn't take it.

02:21:09.239 --> 02:21:11.399
Marasir said darkly.

02:21:11.520 --> 02:21:14.819
Look, destiny is destiny.

02:21:14.879 --> 02:21:16.020
Fate speaker said.

02:21:16.079 --> 02:21:18.000
I don't know why you're so worried about

02:21:18.000 --> 02:21:19.200
who's in the prophecy.

02:21:19.260 --> 02:21:20.399
You delivered it.

02:21:20.459 --> 02:21:22.200
Now you can sit back and watch it

02:21:22.200 --> 02:21:22.680
happen.

02:21:22.739 --> 02:21:24.959
Whether it's me or Starflight, who

02:21:24.959 --> 02:21:25.260
cares?

02:21:25.379 --> 02:21:30.299
The night wings, care, said Maro Seer.

02:21:30.360 --> 02:21:33.600
The queen has decreed that I should

02:21:33.600 --> 02:21:36.360
choose one of you and then kill the

02:21:36.360 --> 02:21:36.600
other.

02:21:36.659 --> 02:21:39.959
Fate speaker opened and closed her mouth

02:21:39.959 --> 02:21:40.559
a few times.

02:21:40.620 --> 02:21:42.239
Really?

02:21:42.299 --> 02:21:45.120
She finally said, in a small voice.

02:21:45.180 --> 02:21:47.219
Starflight felt sorry for her.

02:21:47.280 --> 02:21:49.979
Starting with what glory had told him in

02:21:49.979 --> 02:21:51.959
the rainforest, he'd had a few days to

02:21:51.959 --> 02:21:54.000
adjust to how different night wings were

02:21:54.000 --> 02:21:55.079
from his expectations.

02:21:55.200 --> 02:21:57.780
Fate speaker was getting it all thrown at

02:21:57.780 --> 02:21:58.260
her at once.

02:21:58.319 --> 02:22:02.159
Not today, though. said Morrow Seer.

02:22:02.219 --> 02:22:04.500
For now, I'm moving you all to the

02:22:04.500 --> 02:22:06.780
fortress, so I can keep an eye on you.

02:22:06.840 --> 02:22:09.659
He ended up dumping them in the same

02:22:09.659 --> 02:22:11.879
dormitory where Starflight had 1st woken

02:22:11.879 --> 02:22:12.540
up.

02:22:12.600 --> 02:22:15.899
Then, to Starflight's relief, Marosier

02:22:15.899 --> 02:22:17.399
stomped off to the evening council

02:22:17.399 --> 02:22:18.059
meeting without him.

02:22:18.120 --> 02:22:20.879
Are you sure you don't want to take me?

02:22:21.000 --> 02:22:22.739
Fate speaker asked him.

02:22:22.799 --> 02:22:25.319
Starflight guest, she was hoping to meet

02:22:25.319 --> 02:22:27.600
other night wings, ones whom I'd give her

02:22:27.600 --> 02:22:29.219
a better impression of the tribe than

02:22:29.219 --> 02:22:30.780
Morrow Seer and mastermind.

02:22:30.840 --> 02:22:32.760
Very sure.

02:22:32.819 --> 02:22:34.319
Stay here.

02:22:34.440 --> 02:22:37.979
Marcio growled at her, and try to speak

02:22:37.979 --> 02:22:39.659
as little as possible.

02:22:39.780 --> 02:22:41.879
She watched him leave.

02:22:41.940 --> 02:22:43.559
Her wings drooping.

02:22:43.620 --> 02:22:47.100
I was hoping to see the queen, she said

02:22:47.100 --> 02:22:47.700
to Starflight.

02:22:47.760 --> 02:22:49.920
You heard mastermind.

02:22:49.979 --> 02:22:51.479
Nobody sees the queen.

02:22:51.540 --> 02:22:53.040
He shook his head.

02:22:53.100 --> 02:22:55.680
It looked to me like she does everything

02:22:55.680 --> 02:22:57.659
through her daughter, greatness.

02:22:57.719 --> 02:23:00.239
Which was something else Starflight

02:23:00.239 --> 02:23:01.559
needed more time to think about.

02:23:01.620 --> 02:23:03.780
He suspected there was more to that

02:23:03.780 --> 02:23:04.079
story.

02:23:04.139 --> 02:23:07.020
He wondered if he should try talking to

02:23:07.020 --> 02:23:09.239
fate speaker about the night wings plan.

02:23:09.299 --> 02:23:11.520
Maybe she'd be willing to help him stop

02:23:11.520 --> 02:23:11.760
it.

02:23:11.819 --> 02:23:14.340
He knew she felt sorry for the trapped

02:23:14.340 --> 02:23:16.920
rain wing she'd seen, but no matter how

02:23:16.920 --> 02:23:19.379
sympathetic she was, would she be willing

02:23:19.379 --> 02:23:20.340
to betray her tribe?

02:23:20.459 --> 02:23:23.340
There was no time to talk to her anyway.

02:23:23.399 --> 02:23:26.700
As soon as Maro Seer was gone, Starflight

02:23:26.700 --> 02:23:29.579
and Fate Speaker and Viper and Squid were

02:23:29.579 --> 02:23:31.680
swarmed by the Nightwing dragonettes who

02:23:31.680 --> 02:23:33.180
lived in the dormitory.

02:23:33.239 --> 02:23:35.579
Hello, fate speaker chirped.

02:23:35.639 --> 02:23:37.079
Hi, hi.

02:23:37.139 --> 02:23:38.399
It's so nice to meet you all.

02:23:38.459 --> 02:23:40.260
Oh.

02:23:40.319 --> 02:23:43.559
So you're the other one, fierce teeth

02:23:43.559 --> 02:23:44.940
said, sniffing her.

02:23:45.000 --> 02:23:46.920
You don't look that great either.

02:23:46.979 --> 02:23:51.600
Look at all the colors, mind readers said

02:23:51.600 --> 02:23:54.540
poking squid's green wings, shiny.

02:23:54.600 --> 02:23:57.659
Don't touch me, he whined.

02:23:57.719 --> 02:23:59.700
Viper, make them stop.

02:23:59.819 --> 02:24:01.860
The sand wing ignored him.

02:24:01.920 --> 02:24:04.020
She brandished her tail until the

02:24:04.020 --> 02:24:05.700
Nightwing Dragonettes got out of her way

02:24:05.700 --> 02:24:08.280
then stormed to a sleeping spot at the

02:24:08.280 --> 02:24:10.379
farthest end of the dormitory and curled

02:24:10.379 --> 02:24:11.219
up on the stone.

02:24:11.219 --> 02:24:14.340
Exhaustion was starting to overwhelm

02:24:14.340 --> 02:24:15.059
Starflight.

02:24:15.120 --> 02:24:17.280
He left fate speaker while she was

02:24:17.280 --> 02:24:19.620
introducing herself to everyone. and lay

02:24:19.620 --> 02:24:21.360
down in the same place where he'd woken

02:24:21.360 --> 02:24:24.360
up a few hours before, He missed his

02:24:24.360 --> 02:24:24.600
friends.

02:24:24.659 --> 02:24:27.540
He wanted to be eating boar with clay

02:24:27.540 --> 02:24:30.540
arguing with tsunami, telling glory about

02:24:30.540 --> 02:24:32.819
all his strange new discoveries, and

02:24:32.819 --> 02:24:34.620
warning her about the night wings.

02:24:34.680 --> 02:24:37.139
But mostly, he missed Sonny.

02:24:37.200 --> 02:24:40.260
He missed her warm scales leaning against

02:24:40.260 --> 02:24:40.680
his.

02:24:40.739 --> 02:24:42.959
Her green eyes watching him while he

02:24:42.959 --> 02:24:43.260
talked.

02:24:43.319 --> 02:24:45.479
He wanted to tell her about everything

02:24:45.479 --> 02:24:47.760
that had happened today, about the

02:24:47.760 --> 02:24:49.979
strange hunting habits of the night wings

02:24:49.979 --> 02:24:52.799
the terrifying council chamber, the

02:24:52.799 --> 02:24:55.319
mysterious behavior of the queen, and

02:24:55.319 --> 02:24:56.819
what he'd figured out about their secret

02:24:56.819 --> 02:24:57.659
plan.

02:24:57.719 --> 02:25:00.000
He wanted to tell her all about his

02:25:00.000 --> 02:25:03.479
father. and the alternate dragonettes, and

02:25:03.479 --> 02:25:07.200
his eyes closed, and sleep came for him.
4018
02:25:07,260 --> 02:25:11,700	Chapter 9.

02:25:11.819 --> 02:25:15.899
Starflight was dreaming, but it wasn't so

02:25:15.899 --> 02:25:17.219
much a dream as a memory.

02:25:17.280 --> 02:25:20.280
He was waiting by the cave entrance.

02:25:20.340 --> 02:25:22.620
When Webbs rolled the boulder aside and

02:25:22.620 --> 02:25:22.920
came in.

02:25:22.979 --> 02:25:26.579
His wings unfurled, and he leaned forward

02:25:26.579 --> 02:25:28.799
trying to see the guardian's claws.

02:25:28.860 --> 02:25:31.260
Just one this time.

02:25:31.319 --> 02:25:35.040
Web said, untangling a scroll from the

02:25:35.040 --> 02:25:36.659
net full of fish he was carrying.

02:25:36.780 --> 02:25:39.959
He tossed it to Starflight, who caught it

02:25:39.959 --> 02:25:41.399
and turned it reverently between his

02:25:41.399 --> 02:25:41.879
talons.

02:25:41.940 --> 02:25:44.879
It was damp around the edges, and smelled

02:25:44.879 --> 02:25:46.620
like fish, but he didn't care.

02:25:46.680 --> 02:25:50.100
He carried it to the study cave, and

02:25:50.100 --> 02:25:52.379
found Sonny curled in a small beam of

02:25:52.379 --> 02:25:53.760
sunlight that came through the hole in

02:25:53.760 --> 02:25:54.239
the roof.

02:25:54.299 --> 02:25:57.059
His heart skipped a beat, as she opened

02:25:57.059 --> 02:25:59.100
her green eyes and smiled at him.

02:25:59.159 --> 02:26:00.540
A new scroll?

02:26:00.540 --> 02:26:01.200
she said.

02:26:01.260 --> 02:26:02.940
What's this one about?

02:26:03.000 --> 02:26:05.700
He sat down next to her and unrolled it

02:26:05.700 --> 02:26:06.120
carefully.

02:26:06.180 --> 02:26:08.159
It's about us.

02:26:08.219 --> 02:26:11.040
His eyes scanned the text quickly.

02:26:11.100 --> 02:26:13.379
Oh, weird.

02:26:13.500 --> 02:26:15.600
This must have been written recently.

02:26:15.659 --> 02:26:18.959
It's all theories about where we are, and

02:26:18.959 --> 02:26:20.879
who might be part of the prophecy and how

02:26:20.879 --> 02:26:21.899
it might come true.

02:26:22.139 --> 02:26:24.719
Sonny sat up and peered over his

02:26:24.719 --> 02:26:25.020
shoulder.

02:26:25.079 --> 02:26:27.780
Her warm golden scales pressing against

02:26:27.780 --> 02:26:28.139
his.

02:26:28.200 --> 02:26:31.620
Wow, I'd like to know all that myself.

02:26:31.680 --> 02:26:35.459
It says there were 17 sea wing

02:26:35.459 --> 02:26:37.260
dragonettes who hatched on the brightest

02:26:37.260 --> 02:26:39.899
night, but only 6 of them were from blue

02:26:39.899 --> 02:26:42.420
eggs, and maybe it's none of them because

02:26:42.420 --> 02:26:45.000
perhaps there were other sea wing eggs

02:26:45.000 --> 02:26:47.639
outside the kingdom of the sea, like

02:26:47.639 --> 02:26:49.379
children of the talons of peace, it

02:26:49.379 --> 02:26:49.559
says.

02:26:49.620 --> 02:26:53.040
Or an egg that was stolen by the talons

02:26:53.040 --> 02:26:54.180
Sonny pointed out.

02:26:54.239 --> 02:26:55.559
Right.

02:26:55.620 --> 02:26:57.600
It doesn't mention that possibility.

02:26:57.659 --> 02:26:59.700
Starflight went quiet.

02:26:59.760 --> 02:27:01.079
Reading a little further.

02:27:01.139 --> 02:27:04.739
Does it say anything about the sand wing

02:27:04.739 --> 02:27:04.979
egg?

02:27:05.100 --> 02:27:06.600
She asked nervously.

02:27:06.659 --> 02:27:09.719
The author seems confused about that.

02:27:09.780 --> 02:27:12.780
Starflight rolled the scroll along

02:27:12.780 --> 02:27:15.299
searching for references to sandwings.

02:27:15.299 --> 02:27:18.840
He says, if a sandwing dragonette hatched

02:27:18.840 --> 02:27:21.059
on its own in the desert somewhere, it

02:27:21.059 --> 02:27:23.340
couldn't have survived, so it must be

02:27:23.340 --> 02:27:24.239
someone's egg.

02:27:24.299 --> 02:27:26.819
Maybe from the talons of peace again.

02:27:26.879 --> 02:27:30.180
That would explain hidden away from the

02:27:30.180 --> 02:27:31.440
rival queens.

02:27:31.500 --> 02:27:34.500
I wish the guardians would tell us more

02:27:34.500 --> 02:27:37.260
about where our eggs came from, Sonny

02:27:37.260 --> 02:27:37.920
said with a sigh.

02:27:38.040 --> 02:27:40.920
Maybe I should skip ahead to the part

02:27:40.920 --> 02:27:42.000
about stopping the war.

02:27:42.059 --> 02:27:44.940
Starflight said, rolling the scroll

02:27:44.940 --> 02:27:46.079
through his talons.

02:27:46.079 --> 02:27:47.459
Good idea.

02:27:47.520 --> 02:27:50.459
We're taking suggestions, she joked.

02:27:50.520 --> 02:27:52.680
Any war stopping tips are welcome over

02:27:52.680 --> 02:27:52.860
here.

02:27:52.920 --> 02:27:56.340
Starflight paused on the word Sky Wing.

02:27:56.399 --> 02:28:00.000
It says something about how there aren't

02:28:00.000 --> 02:28:02.040
any sky wings left who are hatched on the

02:28:02.040 --> 02:28:02.579
brightest night.

02:28:02.639 --> 02:28:03.899
What?

02:28:03.959 --> 02:28:05.579
That's weird.

02:28:05.639 --> 02:28:08.100
There must be some in the Sky Kingdom.

02:28:08.159 --> 02:28:10.680
Maybe this author doesn't know what he's

02:28:10.680 --> 02:28:11.040
talking about.

02:28:11.100 --> 02:28:14.520
He kept reading, hoping to keep Sonny

02:28:14.520 --> 02:28:16.079
close to him for as long as possible.

02:28:16.139 --> 02:28:19.379
We don't need a sky wing anyway, she

02:28:19.379 --> 02:28:19.739
said.

02:28:19.799 --> 02:28:21.059
We've got glory.

02:28:21.120 --> 02:28:23.639
Isn't it exciting that there are dragons

02:28:23.639 --> 02:28:25.860
talking about us all over Pyria?

02:28:25.979 --> 02:28:27.479
She added dreamily.

02:28:27.540 --> 02:28:30.719
Right now, there are soldiers camped on

02:28:30.719 --> 02:28:32.940
battlefields talking about how we're the

02:28:32.940 --> 02:28:34.440
ones who'll save them from the endless

02:28:34.440 --> 02:28:34.920
fighting.

02:28:34.979 --> 02:28:37.379
They're dragonettes who want their

02:28:37.379 --> 02:28:39.840
mothers and fathers to come home, and

02:28:39.840 --> 02:28:41.280
they know we're the ones who'll make it

02:28:41.280 --> 02:28:41.520
happen.

02:28:41.579 --> 02:28:44.399
We are going to make so many dragons

02:28:44.399 --> 02:28:45.360
happy Starflight.

02:28:45.479 --> 02:28:48.780
She shifted her wings and shrugged, like

02:28:48.780 --> 02:28:49.979
she was trying not to sound too

02:28:49.979 --> 02:28:50.459
dramatic.

02:28:50.520 --> 02:28:52.920
I mean, I don't know.

02:28:52.979 --> 02:28:55.139
It's just nice to know for sure that

02:28:55.139 --> 02:28:57.180
we're here for a reason, and we're going

02:28:57.180 --> 02:28:58.139
to do something important.

02:28:58.200 --> 02:29:01.500
Starflight liked the way Sonny thought

02:29:01.500 --> 02:29:02.280
about the prophecy.

02:29:02.340 --> 02:29:05.040
The idea of that many dragons relying on

02:29:05.040 --> 02:29:06.899
him always made Starflight feel

02:29:06.899 --> 02:29:08.159
overwhelmed and anxious.

02:29:08.280 --> 02:29:11.819
But for Sunny, the prophecy was a promise

02:29:11.819 --> 02:29:12.959
not an order.

02:29:13.020 --> 02:29:15.299
Listening to our talk about it was

02:29:15.299 --> 02:29:15.719
comforting.

02:29:15.780 --> 02:29:18.120
Here, he said.

02:29:18.180 --> 02:29:20.940
Possible ways for the Dragonettes to

02:29:20.940 --> 02:29:21.840
fulfill the prophecy.

02:29:21.899 --> 02:29:24.540
Um, all right.

02:29:24.600 --> 02:29:27.000
The 1st theory is that all the

02:29:27.000 --> 02:29:29.340
dragonettes are royal daughters, so

02:29:29.340 --> 02:29:31.139
they'll all become queens of their tribes

02:29:31.139 --> 02:29:32.399
and stop the war that way.

02:29:32.459 --> 02:29:34.920
Sonny smothered a giggle.

02:29:34.979 --> 02:29:38.100
I can totally see clay as a mudwing

02:29:38.100 --> 02:29:38.459
princess.

02:29:38.579 --> 02:29:40.079
He grinned back.

02:29:40.139 --> 02:29:42.840
It doesn't make sense, though, without an

02:29:42.840 --> 02:29:45.780
ice wing, and it means you'd have to be

02:29:45.780 --> 02:29:47.340
the next sand wing queen.

02:29:47.399 --> 02:29:51.420
No, thank you, Sonny said firmly.

02:29:51.479 --> 02:29:53.159
I'm not tsunami.

02:29:53.219 --> 02:29:55.020
I would never want to be Queen.

02:29:55.079 --> 02:29:58.020
Starfly didn't like the idea either.

02:29:58.079 --> 02:30:00.360
Although the part that bothered him was

02:30:00.360 --> 02:30:02.280
the thought of Sonny being challenged by

02:30:02.280 --> 02:30:04.920
vicious sandwings who wanted to be queen

02:30:04.920 --> 02:30:05.340
in her place.

02:30:05.399 --> 02:30:09.540
All right, let's find the next, he

02:30:09.540 --> 02:30:11.760
started, when suddenly a commotion of

02:30:11.760 --> 02:30:13.559
running claws sounded from the tunnel.

02:30:13.620 --> 02:30:16.620
They both looked up, as Kestrel burst

02:30:16.620 --> 02:30:18.479
into the room with Dune and Webbs right

02:30:18.479 --> 02:30:18.899
behind her.

02:30:18.959 --> 02:30:23.280
Give me that, Kestrel snarled, snatching

02:30:23.280 --> 02:30:25.979
the scroll out of Starflight's talons, he

02:30:25.979 --> 02:30:27.959
let out a cry of dismay as it tore

02:30:27.959 --> 02:30:28.680
between their claws.

02:30:28.739 --> 02:30:31.020
The Skywing peered at the scroll.

02:30:31.139 --> 02:30:33.420
Then whipped around to glare at webs.

02:30:33.479 --> 02:30:35.219
What were you thinking?

02:30:35.280 --> 02:30:37.920
Handing them any piece of trash you find

02:30:37.920 --> 02:30:38.459
on the beach?

02:30:38.520 --> 02:30:41.280
The fish trader gave it to me.

02:30:41.340 --> 02:30:43.260
Web sent offensively.

02:30:43.319 --> 02:30:45.180
She knows I'm always looking for new

02:30:45.180 --> 02:30:45.719
scrolls.

02:30:45.840 --> 02:30:48.000
I didn't have time to read it, but I

02:30:48.000 --> 02:30:49.319
didn't think it sounded that bad.

02:30:49.379 --> 02:30:53.520
Where are the dragonettes of destiny?

02:30:53.579 --> 02:30:55.500
Kestrel read off the title.

02:30:55.559 --> 02:30:58.680
That doesn't sound dangerous to you

02:30:58.680 --> 02:31:01.020
filling their heads with questions and

02:31:01.020 --> 02:31:01.799
ideas.

02:31:01.860 --> 02:31:04.500
Our heads are already full of questions

02:31:04.500 --> 02:31:05.280
and ideas.

02:31:05.340 --> 02:31:06.840
Sonny piped up.

02:31:06.899 --> 02:31:09.780
We'll tell you what you need to know

02:31:09.780 --> 02:31:10.860
about the prophecy.

02:31:10.920 --> 02:31:14.100
Kestrel growled at Sonny and Starflight.

02:31:14.219 --> 02:31:17.159
You don't need a pile of gossip and

02:31:17.159 --> 02:31:19.799
rumors and speculation cluttering up your

02:31:19.799 --> 02:31:20.879
tiny little minds.

02:31:21.000 --> 02:31:24.659
Starflight's mind isn't at all tiny or

02:31:24.659 --> 02:31:24.959
little.

02:31:25.079 --> 02:31:26.340
Sonny objected.

02:31:26.399 --> 02:31:29.100
She glanced at Starflight, and when he

02:31:29.100 --> 02:31:31.500
didn't say anything, she whispered, hey

02:31:31.500 --> 02:31:33.840
your line is, neither is Sonny's.

02:31:33.899 --> 02:31:36.479
Starflight knew she was trying to make

02:31:36.479 --> 02:31:38.459
him feel better, but he was too nervous

02:31:38.459 --> 02:31:38.760
to speak.

02:31:38.819 --> 02:31:41.159
Why were the guardians so mad?

02:31:41.219 --> 02:31:42.959
Had he done something wrong?

02:31:43.020 --> 02:31:46.500
This is not for you.

02:31:46.500 --> 02:31:49.559
Kestrel snapped. waving the scroll.

02:31:49.620 --> 02:31:51.479
She pointed it at Starflight.

02:31:51.540 --> 02:31:54.540
You, battle training, now.

02:31:54.600 --> 02:31:57.360
She turned and stomped out of the cave

02:31:57.360 --> 02:31:59.159
with the other guardians close behind

02:31:59.159 --> 02:32:00.059
her.

02:32:00.120 --> 02:32:02.399
Sonny ran to the entrance way, then

02:32:02.399 --> 02:32:04.079
turned back to Starflight with a

02:32:04.079 --> 02:32:05.819
comically outraged look on her face.

02:32:05.879 --> 02:32:08.399
Are you just going to let her do that?

02:32:08.459 --> 02:32:09.360
she said.

02:32:09.420 --> 02:32:11.579
She took your scroll?

02:32:11.639 --> 02:32:12.299
That so unfair.

02:32:12.360 --> 02:32:14.639
Starvlight thought so too.

02:32:14.700 --> 02:32:16.799
But he definitely was not going to argue

02:32:16.799 --> 02:32:17.579
with Kestrel.

02:32:17.639 --> 02:32:21.420
It's all right, he said, looking down at

02:32:21.420 --> 02:32:23.280
the gray rocks below his talons.

02:32:23.340 --> 02:32:25.680
Hopefully webs will bring a new scroll

02:32:25.680 --> 02:32:26.340
next week.

02:32:26.399 --> 02:32:28.620
Oh, Starflight.

02:32:28.680 --> 02:32:30.180
I know you're trying to hide it.

02:32:30.239 --> 02:32:33.420
But you're so sad now, Sonny said.

02:32:33.479 --> 02:32:36.180
She came and sat in front of him, reaching

02:32:36.180 --> 02:32:37.440
to touch his tail with her own.

02:32:37.500 --> 02:32:40.799
Listen, that scroll wasn't going to have

02:32:40.799 --> 02:32:41.760
all the answers anyway.

02:32:41.819 --> 02:32:43.079
You know that, right?

02:32:43.139 --> 02:32:45.840
Nobody knows how the prophecy will

02:32:45.840 --> 02:32:46.379
unfold.

02:32:46.440 --> 02:32:48.780
We just have to always do what we think

02:32:48.780 --> 02:32:51.120
is right, and fate will take us in the

02:32:51.120 --> 02:32:51.540
right direction.

02:32:51.600 --> 02:32:54.899
Maybe, he said.

02:32:54.959 --> 02:32:57.659
But a map on how to get there would be

02:32:57.659 --> 02:32:57.959
helpful.

02:32:58.020 --> 02:33:00.840
You don't need a map, she said.

02:33:00.899 --> 02:33:02.940
When you have excellent traveling

02:33:02.940 --> 02:33:05.760
companions, like clay, and tsunami, and

02:33:05.760 --> 02:33:08.100
glory, and of course, me.

02:33:08.219 --> 02:33:10.079
She beamed at him.

02:33:10.139 --> 02:33:14.219
That's true, he said, feeling again how

02:33:14.219 --> 02:33:14.940
lucky he was.

02:33:15.000 --> 02:33:18.899
Of all the caves and all of Pyria, of all

02:33:18.899 --> 02:33:20.760
the eggs that could have been chosen

02:33:20.760 --> 02:33:23.459
somehow his and hers had wound up here

02:33:23.459 --> 02:33:26.100
and 2 dragons who never should have met

02:33:26.100 --> 02:33:27.000
were together.

02:33:27.059 --> 02:33:31.379
And that's how we'll always be, he

02:33:31.379 --> 02:33:31.680
thought.

02:33:31.739 --> 02:33:35.399
Starflight woke up to find a claw poking

02:33:35.399 --> 02:33:36.059
his snout.

02:33:36.120 --> 02:33:38.040
He mumbled.

02:33:38.100 --> 02:33:40.260
Everything was still and dark in the

02:33:40.260 --> 02:33:40.739
dormitory.

02:33:40.799 --> 02:33:44.040
The coals smoldered and the wall niches

02:33:44.040 --> 02:33:45.959
like the half closed eyes of slumbering

02:33:45.959 --> 02:33:46.440
dragons.

02:33:46.500 --> 02:33:49.139
The skylight looked out onto a night with

02:33:49.139 --> 02:33:49.680
no stars.

02:33:49.739 --> 02:33:52.500
The warmth from his dream faded

02:33:52.500 --> 02:33:52.979
instantly.

02:33:53.040 --> 02:33:56.100
Sonny was far away. and he had no idea

02:33:56.100 --> 02:33:57.299
when he'd ever see her again.

02:33:57.360 --> 02:34:01.260
I can't sleep, fate speaker whispered in

02:34:01.260 --> 02:34:01.559
the dark.

02:34:01.620 --> 02:34:04.559
Her wings rustled as she edged closer to

02:34:04.559 --> 02:34:06.479
him and poked his shoulder again.

02:34:06.479 --> 02:34:07.680
What are you doing?

02:34:07.739 --> 02:34:11.940
Home, said Starflight. sleeping?

02:34:12.000 --> 02:34:14.819
Let's go explore, she said.

02:34:14.879 --> 02:34:17.159
I want to know more about our tribe, don't

02:34:17.159 --> 02:34:17.280
you?

02:34:17.399 --> 02:34:19.739
We can go look around the whole fortress

02:34:19.739 --> 02:34:20.579
while they're asleep.

02:34:20.639 --> 02:34:23.219
He rubbed his eyes and blanked at her.

02:34:23.340 --> 02:34:25.200
When we get in trouble.

02:34:25.260 --> 02:34:26.700
Why?

02:34:26.819 --> 02:34:27.540
She said.

02:34:27.600 --> 02:34:29.219
Nobody's told us not to.

02:34:29.280 --> 02:34:31.020
We're night wings, aren't we?

02:34:31.079 --> 02:34:33.000
Isn't this our fortress too?

02:34:33.059 --> 02:34:35.399
Let's explore it before someone tells us

02:34:35.399 --> 02:34:35.879
we can't.

02:34:35.940 --> 02:34:38.760
There was a kind of logic to that.

02:34:38.819 --> 02:34:41.760
Although Starflight wasn't sure Marosir

02:34:41.760 --> 02:34:43.920
would agree with it, but really, she was

02:34:43.920 --> 02:34:44.159
right.

02:34:44.219 --> 02:34:46.500
Why should they get in trouble for acting

02:34:46.500 --> 02:34:47.459
like they belonged here?

02:34:47.520 --> 02:34:50.819
Besides, it was what tsunami would do.

02:34:50.879 --> 02:34:52.920
And wasn't he always thinking he wanted

02:34:52.920 --> 02:34:53.579
to be more like her?

02:34:53.639 --> 02:34:56.879
He rolled off the bed onto the floor next

02:34:56.879 --> 02:34:59.219
to fate speaker, and they padded softly

02:34:59.219 --> 02:35:00.540
out into the tunnels.

02:35:00.600 --> 02:35:02.700
She picked a direction, apparently at

02:35:02.700 --> 02:35:04.559
random, and they started to walk the

02:35:04.559 --> 02:35:05.159
empty halls.

02:35:05.219 --> 02:35:07.799
The only sound was the tapping of their

02:35:07.799 --> 02:35:09.959
own claws and the slithering of their

02:35:09.959 --> 02:35:10.739
tails on the stone.

02:35:10.799 --> 02:35:14.760
Don't be scared, Starfight told himself

02:35:14.760 --> 02:35:17.100
and then told himself again, a few more

02:35:17.100 --> 02:35:17.399
times.

02:35:17.459 --> 02:35:19.739
You're not doing anything wrong.

02:35:19.799 --> 02:35:22.200
There aren't any dangers lying in wait

02:35:22.200 --> 02:35:22.500
for you.

02:35:22.559 --> 02:35:24.479
You're not being treated like a

02:35:24.479 --> 02:35:24.899
prisoner.

02:35:24.959 --> 02:35:26.940
You're a night wing dragonette.

02:35:27.000 --> 02:35:28.680
This is your tribe.

02:35:28.739 --> 02:35:31.260
This is where you could have grown up.

02:35:31.319 --> 02:35:34.920
He glanced to the bare walls, not so very

02:35:34.920 --> 02:35:36.360
different from the cave where he had

02:35:36.360 --> 02:35:36.899
grown up.

02:35:36.959 --> 02:35:39.600
This is where you're supposed to be.

02:35:39.719 --> 02:35:43.739
No, I'm supposed to be where Sonny is.

02:35:43.799 --> 02:35:45.780
I'm supposed to be helping my friends

02:35:45.780 --> 02:35:46.739
stop the war.

02:35:46.860 --> 02:35:49.440
He stopped walking for a minute to take a

02:35:49.440 --> 02:35:49.979
deep breath.

02:35:50.040 --> 02:35:52.079
Then hurried after fate speaker.

02:35:52.139 --> 02:35:55.680
All the torches had been extinguished, so

02:35:55.680 --> 02:35:57.540
the only light came from the glowing red

02:35:57.540 --> 02:35:58.680
coals on the walls.

02:35:58.739 --> 02:36:01.260
Starflight couldn't even see any of the

02:36:01.260 --> 02:36:02.760
moons when he looked out the windows.

02:36:02.819 --> 02:36:05.579
The sky was too hidden by clouds and

02:36:05.579 --> 02:36:06.719
smoke from the volcano.

02:36:06.780 --> 02:36:09.299
He knew they wouldn't find much that

02:36:09.299 --> 02:36:11.280
might be useful, unless he was brave

02:36:11.280 --> 02:36:13.799
enough to open a door sometime, but he

02:36:13.799 --> 02:36:15.299
was terrified of waking up any sleeping

02:36:15.299 --> 02:36:16.079
night wings.

02:36:16.139 --> 02:36:18.659
He kept imagining walking straight into

02:36:18.659 --> 02:36:20.940
Maro Seer's room, and stepping on his

02:36:20.940 --> 02:36:23.280
tail by accident, and the death or

02:36:23.280 --> 02:36:25.680
dismemberment, or both that would no

02:36:25.680 --> 02:36:26.760
doubt inevitably follow.

02:36:26.819 --> 02:36:29.639
He was glad to see that fate speaker

02:36:29.639 --> 02:36:31.020
wasn't going in the direction of his

02:36:31.020 --> 02:36:31.979
father's lab.

02:36:32.040 --> 02:36:34.500
Mastermind was surely sleeping like the

02:36:34.500 --> 02:36:36.719
rest of the tribe, but Starfly didn't

02:36:36.719 --> 02:36:39.180
want to risk encountering him, or get any

02:36:39.180 --> 02:36:41.219
closer to the things he'd seen in there.

02:36:41.280 --> 02:36:44.520
Every once in a while, as they walked

02:36:44.520 --> 02:36:46.739
they heard a quiet snore from the rooms

02:36:46.739 --> 02:36:47.399
they were passing.

02:36:47.459 --> 02:36:50.219
But they saw no one awake, no guards

02:36:50.219 --> 02:36:50.639
anywhere.

02:36:50.700 --> 02:36:53.700
I guess they're used to not needing

02:36:53.700 --> 02:36:55.860
guards, Starflight whispered.

02:36:55.920 --> 02:36:57.959
Since no other tribe could find this

02:36:57.959 --> 02:36:58.260
place.

02:36:58.319 --> 02:37:00.299
They were always safe from attack.

02:37:00.420 --> 02:37:02.280
He thought for a minute.

02:37:02.340 --> 02:37:05.100
And even now that they might be attacked

02:37:05.100 --> 02:37:07.440
they only need to post guards at the

02:37:07.440 --> 02:37:07.739
tunnel.

02:37:07.799 --> 02:37:11.280
I'm surprised everyone is asleep, though

02:37:11.280 --> 02:37:12.959
fate speaker whispered back.

02:37:13.020 --> 02:37:15.420
I always thought being a nightwing meant

02:37:15.420 --> 02:37:16.739
you wanted to be awake all night.

02:37:16.799 --> 02:37:19.079
I mean, that's true of me.

02:37:19.139 --> 02:37:22.200
I can never wake up in the morning, but

02:37:22.200 --> 02:37:23.940
once it's dark, I'm full of energy.

02:37:24.000 --> 02:37:25.500
Does that happen to you?

02:37:25.559 --> 02:37:27.899
I really thought that was a night wing

02:37:27.899 --> 02:37:28.200
thing.

02:37:28.260 --> 02:37:30.959
But maybe my friends are right, and I'm

02:37:30.959 --> 02:37:31.319
just weird.

02:37:31.379 --> 02:37:34.559
She kicked a rock sticking out of a crack

02:37:34.559 --> 02:37:35.040
in the floor.

02:37:35.100 --> 02:37:38.940
Or maybe it is a night wing thing, and

02:37:38.940 --> 02:37:40.379
they're all muddled here because they

02:37:40.379 --> 02:37:42.120
can't really see the night sky anymore.

02:37:42.180 --> 02:37:43.559
Starflight said.

02:37:43.620 --> 02:37:45.899
Maybe you're more of a night wing than

02:37:45.899 --> 02:37:46.260
any of them.

02:37:46.379 --> 02:37:49.079
She fluttered her wings, looking

02:37:49.079 --> 02:37:49.739
skeptical.

02:37:49.799 --> 02:37:53.639
As for me, I lived in a cave with no sky

02:37:53.639 --> 02:37:54.479
most of my life.

02:37:54.540 --> 02:37:57.000
So I was on whatever schedule our

02:37:57.000 --> 02:37:58.020
guardians told us to be.

02:37:58.079 --> 02:37:59.700
But once we were free.

02:37:59.819 --> 02:38:03.540
Well, it's been a strange few weeks, so

02:38:03.540 --> 02:38:04.860
it's hard to say.

02:38:04.920 --> 02:38:07.020
But I do feel more alive when the stars

02:38:07.020 --> 02:38:07.500
are out.

02:38:07.559 --> 02:38:09.000
Does that make sense?

02:38:09.059 --> 02:38:11.879
It does, she said.

02:38:11.940 --> 02:38:13.079
Smiling at him.

02:38:13.139 --> 02:38:16.379
She paused at an intersection, thinking

02:38:16.379 --> 02:38:17.639
and then purposefully turned right.

02:38:17.700 --> 02:38:19.739
Are we going somewhere?

02:38:19.799 --> 02:38:20.879
He asked her.

02:38:20.940 --> 02:38:23.579
Did you see the part of the fortress that

02:38:23.579 --> 02:38:24.180
collapsed?

02:38:24.239 --> 02:38:24.840
she asked.

02:38:24.899 --> 02:38:27.000
I want to see what it looks like from

02:38:27.000 --> 02:38:27.479
inside.

02:38:27.540 --> 02:38:30.299
He stopped, his heart rattling

02:38:30.299 --> 02:38:30.840
nervously.

02:38:30.899 --> 02:38:32.879
Wait, he said.

02:38:32.940 --> 02:38:35.340
It collapsed because it was covered in

02:38:35.340 --> 02:38:35.760
lava.

02:38:35.819 --> 02:38:37.920
That can't be safe to explore.

02:38:37.979 --> 02:38:40.860
She flicked his nose with her tail.

02:38:40.920 --> 02:38:42.540
Oh, stop worrying.

02:38:42.600 --> 02:38:45.479
Mighty Claus told me it happened like 11

02:38:45.479 --> 02:38:46.079
years ago.

02:38:46.139 --> 02:38:48.840
It's just a bunch of rocks now, and he

02:38:48.840 --> 02:38:50.040
said it's kind of neat looking.

02:38:50.159 --> 02:38:52.200
I guess it covered the part of the

02:38:52.200 --> 02:38:53.520
fortress where they used to keep their

02:38:53.520 --> 02:38:56.040
treasure, so they had to blast tunnels

02:38:56.040 --> 02:38:57.719
into it to get their treasure out.

02:38:57.840 --> 02:39:00.540
Tunnels in lava rocks.

02:39:00.600 --> 02:39:01.680
It'll be awesome.

02:39:01.739 --> 02:39:02.700
Come on.

02:39:02.760 --> 02:39:05.579
She bounded ahead and he followed.

02:39:05.639 --> 02:39:08.760
More slowly, wishing he'd listened to his

02:39:08.760 --> 02:39:10.620
original stay in bed instincts.

02:39:10.680 --> 02:39:13.500
Fate speaker's sense of direction turned

02:39:13.500 --> 02:39:14.879
out to be better than her sense about

02:39:14.879 --> 02:39:17.459
dragons, and before long, they found

02:39:17.459 --> 02:39:19.079
themselves in a part of the fortress

02:39:19.079 --> 02:39:20.399
where the roof was partly gone.

02:39:20.520 --> 02:39:23.520
What looked like thick black bubbles of

02:39:23.520 --> 02:39:25.319
rock filled the hall ahead of them.

02:39:25.559 --> 02:39:27.780
Chili air whistled through the gaps in

02:39:27.780 --> 02:39:29.940
the walls, battling with the heat from

02:39:29.940 --> 02:39:31.379
the volcano below their talons.

02:39:31.440 --> 02:39:35.819
There, fate speaker whispered, darting up

02:39:35.819 --> 02:39:37.739
to where the petrified lava met the

02:39:37.739 --> 02:39:37.979
wall.

02:39:38.040 --> 02:39:41.040
A tunnel just big enough for a dragon had

02:39:41.040 --> 02:39:43.500
been chiseled and blasted and dug out of

02:39:43.500 --> 02:39:43.979
the rocks.

02:39:44.040 --> 02:39:46.620
Without any hesitation, she headed

02:39:46.620 --> 02:39:46.860
inside.

02:39:46.979 --> 02:39:49.559
What am I doing?

02:39:49.620 --> 02:39:51.540
Starfight asked himself.

02:39:51.659 --> 02:39:54.180
He really desperately wanted to melt into

02:39:54.180 --> 02:39:56.219
the shadows and stay there waiting for

02:39:56.219 --> 02:39:56.399
her.

02:39:56.459 --> 02:39:58.860
But he also felt as though she couldn't

02:39:58.860 --> 02:39:59.940
go in there alone.

02:40:00.059 --> 02:40:02.520
And this time, there was no clay or

02:40:02.520 --> 02:40:04.680
tsunami or glory to do the brave thing

02:40:04.680 --> 02:40:05.040
for him.

02:40:05.100 --> 02:40:08.100
He was the only dragon fate speaker had.

02:40:08.159 --> 02:40:10.260
Taking a deep breath.

02:40:10.319 --> 02:40:12.540
He forced himself to step into the small

02:40:12.540 --> 02:40:12.959
tunnel.

02:40:13.020 --> 02:40:16.319
Jagged rock pressed in from all sides

02:40:16.319 --> 02:40:18.479
scraping his wings and the top of his

02:40:18.479 --> 02:40:19.260
head.

02:40:19.319 --> 02:40:22.440
The tunnel twisted quickly downward, so

02:40:22.440 --> 02:40:24.239
they had to dig their claws in to avoid

02:40:24.239 --> 02:40:24.780
sliding.

02:40:24.840 --> 02:40:27.600
Fate speaker breathe a small plume of

02:40:27.600 --> 02:40:27.899
fire.

02:40:27.959 --> 02:40:30.780
But all that did was illuminate the thick

02:40:30.780 --> 02:40:32.159
dark walls that encircled them.

02:40:32.219 --> 02:40:35.219
The air was hot and stuffy, and

02:40:35.219 --> 02:40:37.079
Starflight began to wonder if anyone had

02:40:37.079 --> 02:40:38.879
ever died exploring these tunnels.

02:40:38.940 --> 02:40:42.540
Suddenly, the tunnel turned directly down

02:40:42.540 --> 02:40:44.940
and dumped them out into an empty space.

02:40:45.000 --> 02:40:47.879
Fate speaker fell first, letting out a

02:40:47.879 --> 02:40:48.780
shout of surprise.

02:40:48.840 --> 02:40:51.360
So Starflight had a minute's warning and

02:40:51.360 --> 02:40:53.340
was able to open his wings as soon as his

02:40:53.340 --> 02:40:55.139
claws lost their grip on the floor.

02:40:55.200 --> 02:40:58.379
Still, he tumbled several feet and landed

02:40:58.379 --> 02:40:58.920
on top of her.

02:40:58.979 --> 02:41:01.260
Oof, she said.

02:41:01.260 --> 02:41:04.079
He scrambled away, and they both lit up

02:41:04.079 --> 02:41:05.459
the air with their fire at the same

02:41:05.459 --> 02:41:05.639
time.

02:41:05.700 --> 02:41:09.180
The room was small, but intact.

02:41:09.239 --> 02:41:12.059
The lava had crushed the upper floors, but

02:41:12.059 --> 02:41:13.200
left this one preserved.

02:41:13.260 --> 02:41:15.540
Starflight could see a small hallway

02:41:15.540 --> 02:41:17.940
outside the door, with more rooms beyond

02:41:17.940 --> 02:41:18.120
that.

02:41:18.180 --> 02:41:21.600
He looked up uneasily, thinking about the

02:41:21.600 --> 02:41:22.920
weight of everything above them.

02:41:22.979 --> 02:41:26.100
Fate speaker was already hurrying to the

02:41:26.100 --> 02:41:28.379
doorway as their fire faded into complete

02:41:28.379 --> 02:41:28.799
darkness.

02:41:28.860 --> 02:41:31.860
Mighty Claus said the old treasure room

02:41:31.860 --> 02:41:33.299
is 3 doors down on the left.

02:41:33.360 --> 02:41:34.139
Come on.

02:41:34.260 --> 02:41:36.600
But isn't it empty?

02:41:36.659 --> 02:41:38.040
Starflight asked.

02:41:38.100 --> 02:41:40.200
Following her with his front talons

02:41:40.200 --> 02:41:40.799
outstretched.

02:41:40.920 --> 02:41:43.200
Are we just going to look at an empty

02:41:43.200 --> 02:41:43.739
room?

02:41:43.799 --> 02:41:47.579
A fascinating empty room, she insisted.

02:41:47.639 --> 02:41:50.219
It used to be full of treasure.

02:41:50.280 --> 02:41:51.659
Just imagine.

02:41:51.719 --> 02:41:54.180
I've never even seen any treasure

02:41:54.180 --> 02:41:54.540
before.

02:41:54.659 --> 02:41:57.959
Oh, right, Starflight said.

02:41:58.020 --> 02:42:00.360
The talons of peace wouldn't have any, I

02:42:00.360 --> 02:42:02.520
guess, unless some dragons brought it

02:42:02.520 --> 02:42:03.840
with them when they left their tribes.

02:42:03.899 --> 02:42:07.559
If anyone did, they keep it hidden, she

02:42:07.559 --> 02:42:07.799
said.

02:42:07.860 --> 02:42:10.680
He felt her tail flick against his snout

02:42:10.680 --> 02:42:12.899
accidentally, as they both felt their way

02:42:12.899 --> 02:42:13.559
along the walls.

02:42:13.620 --> 02:42:16.379
You didn't have treasure in your hiding

02:42:16.379 --> 02:42:18.000
under the mountain place, did you?

02:42:18.120 --> 02:42:19.680
No.

02:42:19.739 --> 02:42:22.620
But I've been to the Sky Kingdom. and the

02:42:22.620 --> 02:42:24.840
kingdom of the sea, Starflight said.

02:42:24.899 --> 02:42:27.299
And I saw enough treasure there to know

02:42:27.299 --> 02:42:29.520
that having lots of treasure doesn't make

02:42:29.520 --> 02:42:31.559
you a good queen or a happy tribe.

02:42:31.620 --> 02:42:35.219
I thought Queen Coral was a good queen

02:42:35.219 --> 02:42:38.040
fate speaker said, sounding surprised.

02:42:38.159 --> 02:42:41.819
Well, keep in mind, she wrote a lot of

02:42:41.819 --> 02:42:43.260
the scrolls you've probably read about

02:42:43.260 --> 02:42:46.139
her, Starflight said, but she's not

02:42:46.139 --> 02:42:46.500
terrible.

02:42:46.559 --> 02:42:49.139
She's better than Queen Scarlet, that's

02:42:49.139 --> 02:42:49.379
for sure.

02:42:49.440 --> 02:42:51.180
Or blister.

02:42:51.239 --> 02:42:54.360
He shuddered, remembering the sandwing

02:42:54.360 --> 02:42:56.399
dragon who'd been so disgusted with him.

02:42:56.399 --> 02:42:59.340
I bet the sandwings would be happier if

02:42:59.340 --> 02:43:00.600
they could find the treasure that

02:43:00.600 --> 02:43:02.760
scavenger stole, though, fate speaker

02:43:02.760 --> 02:43:03.059
said.

02:43:03.120 --> 02:43:06.120
Maybe, Starflight said.

02:43:06.180 --> 02:43:08.700
There were some really famous pieces of

02:43:08.700 --> 02:43:10.799
treasure in there, including stuff that

02:43:10.799 --> 02:43:12.420
was rumored to be animus touched.

02:43:12.479 --> 02:43:14.459
Animus touched?

02:43:14.520 --> 02:43:17.399
Fate speaker stopped and breathed fire

02:43:17.399 --> 02:43:17.819
again.

02:43:17.879 --> 02:43:20.879
They were standing under a tall archway

02:43:20.879 --> 02:43:23.340
with 2 black metal doors, one of which

02:43:23.340 --> 02:43:25.020
was propped open just enough for a

02:43:25.020 --> 02:43:26.040
dragonette to slip through.

02:43:26.159 --> 02:43:30.059
Animus Touched means an object that's

02:43:30.059 --> 02:43:31.799
been magicked by an animus dragon

02:43:31.799 --> 02:43:34.500
Starflight explained, and the helpful

02:43:34.500 --> 02:43:36.299
teacher voice he sometimes used with his

02:43:36.299 --> 02:43:36.659
friends.

02:43:36.719 --> 02:43:39.239
So the object is left with some kind of

02:43:39.239 --> 02:43:41.700
power, like a necklace that can make you

02:43:41.700 --> 02:43:44.100
invisible, or a stone that can find

02:43:44.100 --> 02:43:45.120
anyone you're looking for.

02:43:45.180 --> 02:43:49.559
Or a statue that'll kill any heir to the

02:43:49.559 --> 02:43:51.540
sea wing throne can get its claws on.

02:43:51.600 --> 02:43:54.959
It's sort of an archaic term because

02:43:54.959 --> 02:43:57.299
supposedly there aren't any animus

02:43:57.299 --> 02:43:59.459
dragons anymore, but that's clearly not

02:43:59.459 --> 02:43:59.700
true.

02:43:59.760 --> 02:44:02.520
There's at least one among the sea wings

02:44:02.520 --> 02:44:04.500
and there must have been one not long ago

02:44:04.500 --> 02:44:05.819
among the night wings.

02:44:05.879 --> 02:44:07.139
Really?

02:44:07.200 --> 02:44:10.200
Fate speaker pushed lightly on the metal

02:44:10.200 --> 02:44:12.719
door, and it groaned open another inch.

02:44:12.780 --> 02:44:15.479
He realized he didn't know how much she

02:44:15.479 --> 02:44:17.340
knew about the Nightwing Island.

02:44:17.399 --> 02:44:20.459
Yes, there's a tunnel from here to the

02:44:20.459 --> 02:44:23.159
rainforest, and one from the rainforest

02:44:23.159 --> 02:44:25.500
to the kingdom of sand, which must have

02:44:25.500 --> 02:44:27.719
been made by an animus dragon, he said.

02:44:27.780 --> 02:44:30.420
I guess I can't be sure how long ago it

02:44:30.420 --> 02:44:32.700
was, but none of the rain wings knew

02:44:32.700 --> 02:44:32.940
about them.

02:44:33.000 --> 02:44:34.920
Isn't that how you got here?

02:44:34.979 --> 02:44:36.780
She shook her head.

02:44:36.899 --> 02:44:38.760
We flew across the ocean.

02:44:38.819 --> 02:44:42.120
It was so long and so boring.

02:44:42.239 --> 02:44:44.879
I swear, I nearly fell asleep and ended

02:44:44.879 --> 02:44:46.260
up in the sea a couple of times.

02:44:46.319 --> 02:44:49.979
He perked up, full of geography questions

02:44:49.979 --> 02:44:52.020
but she was already squeezing into the

02:44:52.020 --> 02:44:54.659
room and making ooh noises.

02:44:54.719 --> 02:44:56.819
He squashed himself through the door

02:44:56.819 --> 02:44:59.579
behind her and saw, in the plume of fire

02:44:59.579 --> 02:45:01.860
she sent out, a couple of wooden sticks

02:45:01.860 --> 02:45:02.280
on the floor.

02:45:02.340 --> 02:45:05.399
He picked one up and lit it so they could

02:45:05.399 --> 02:45:06.239
look around more easily.

02:45:06.299 --> 02:45:09.420
But when he lifted it up, the 1st things

02:45:09.420 --> 02:45:12.059
they both saw were the shriveled corpses

02:45:12.059 --> 02:45:13.500
of 2 dead dragons.
4608
02:45:13,559 --> 02:45:17,760	Chapter 10.

02:45:18.059 --> 02:45:21.959
Starflight clapped his talons over fate

02:45:21.959 --> 02:45:23.340
speaker's mouth, mid-shriek.

02:45:23.399 --> 02:45:25.979
You'll bring the mountain down on top of

02:45:25.979 --> 02:45:28.559
us, he whispered, and she snapped her

02:45:28.559 --> 02:45:28.979
mouth shut.

02:45:29.040 --> 02:45:31.739
He glanced down at the 2 midnight black

02:45:31.739 --> 02:45:32.219
bodies.

02:45:32.340 --> 02:45:33.959
Don't worry.

02:45:34.020 --> 02:45:36.840
These 2 have been dead a long time, he

02:45:36.840 --> 02:45:37.200
added.

02:45:37.260 --> 02:45:39.659
Probably since the volcano erupted.

02:45:39.719 --> 02:45:42.959
When he released her, she whispered, how

02:45:42.959 --> 02:45:43.500
did they die?

02:45:43.559 --> 02:45:46.500
Starflight lifted the torch again and

02:45:46.500 --> 02:45:48.540
peered a little closer, although he

02:45:48.540 --> 02:45:49.500
really didn't want to.

02:45:49.559 --> 02:45:52.260
A spear lay beside one of the night wings

02:45:52.260 --> 02:45:55.200
but it was an ordinary spear, not the

02:45:55.200 --> 02:45:57.420
creepy, hooked and pronged kind all the

02:45:57.420 --> 02:45:58.139
guards carried now.

02:45:58.200 --> 02:46:00.479
Neither of them wore armor either.

02:46:00.540 --> 02:46:03.959
Suffocation, I bet, he answered.

02:46:04.020 --> 02:46:08.280
Or starvation, or heat, although dragons

02:46:08.280 --> 02:46:09.780
can withstand a fair amount of heat.

02:46:09.840 --> 02:46:12.780
My guess is they were guarding the

02:46:12.780 --> 02:46:14.579
treasure when the eruption happened, and

02:46:14.579 --> 02:46:15.299
they were trapped here.

02:46:15.360 --> 02:46:17.879
Nobody could come find them until the

02:46:17.879 --> 02:46:19.799
lava cooled enough to make the tunnel we

02:46:19.799 --> 02:46:22.260
crawled through, and by then, it was too

02:46:22.260 --> 02:46:22.440
late.

02:46:22.559 --> 02:46:25.979
Fate speaker shook herself from horns to

02:46:25.979 --> 02:46:26.340
tail.

02:46:26.399 --> 02:46:28.500
How incredibly awful.

02:46:28.559 --> 02:46:31.739
Starflight turned to look around the room

02:46:31.739 --> 02:46:34.260
which, as he'd predicted, was otherwise

02:46:34.260 --> 02:46:34.559
empty.

02:46:34.680 --> 02:46:38.040
Bare shelves lined all the walls, reaching

02:46:38.040 --> 02:46:40.739
up to the ceiling, and large urns stood

02:46:40.739 --> 02:46:41.760
in the 2 back corners.

02:46:41.819 --> 02:46:44.219
He could imagine that they had once been

02:46:44.219 --> 02:46:47.100
filled to the brim with gold and jewels.

02:46:47.159 --> 02:46:50.159
He caught himself thinking, a giant urn

02:46:50.159 --> 02:46:52.559
full of gold and jewels would be kind of

02:46:52.559 --> 02:46:53.100
cool to have.

02:46:53.159 --> 02:46:55.379
Which was ridiculous.

02:46:55.440 --> 02:46:58.200
Just his dragon instincts talking.

02:46:58.260 --> 02:46:59.940
What would he do without much gold?

02:47:00.000 --> 02:47:02.040
Unless it could get him back to his

02:47:02.040 --> 02:47:04.079
friends or stop the war, it would be

02:47:04.079 --> 02:47:04.799
useless to him.

02:47:04.860 --> 02:47:08.879
Something went ping at the back of his

02:47:08.879 --> 02:47:11.159
mind, but before he could figure it out

02:47:11.159 --> 02:47:14.040
fate speaker said, maybe we should go.

02:47:14.159 --> 02:47:17.399
I think so, Starflight said.

02:47:17.459 --> 02:47:19.559
I don't know how much air is down here

02:47:19.559 --> 02:47:21.719
but I don't want to find out by running

02:47:21.719 --> 02:47:22.200
out of it.

02:47:22.260 --> 02:47:24.899
Yikes, she said.

02:47:24.959 --> 02:47:26.159
Her eyes widening.

02:47:26.219 --> 02:47:27.479
That's all you had to say.

02:47:27.540 --> 02:47:30.120
She turned and scooted out of the room

02:47:30.120 --> 02:47:31.680
faster than he'd ever seen her move

02:47:31.680 --> 02:47:32.040
before.

02:47:32.100 --> 02:47:35.219
He took a step to follow her, and the

02:47:35.219 --> 02:47:37.200
torchlight flashed on something small and

02:47:37.200 --> 02:47:39.120
bright in one of the corpse's talons.

02:47:39.180 --> 02:47:41.340
Starflight hesitated.

02:47:41.399 --> 02:47:43.979
A piece of treasure that was left

02:47:43.979 --> 02:47:44.760
behind?

02:47:44.819 --> 02:47:46.200
Something they missed?

02:47:46.200 --> 02:47:48.059
Because who would want to search a

02:47:48.059 --> 02:47:48.719
corpse?

02:47:48.780 --> 02:47:50.520
Well, not him.

02:47:50.579 --> 02:47:52.079
Not particularly.

02:47:52.139 --> 02:47:55.500
But he felt as if it was calling to him.

02:47:55.559 --> 02:47:57.899
As if it had been waiting for him these

02:47:57.899 --> 02:48:00.659
11 years, hiding from anyone else who

02:48:00.659 --> 02:48:02.399
came along until the right dragon

02:48:02.399 --> 02:48:03.000
arrived.

02:48:03.059 --> 02:48:06.780
Now you sound like Sonny, with her faith

02:48:06.780 --> 02:48:09.479
in fate, and destiny, and signs and

02:48:09.479 --> 02:48:09.899
magic.

02:48:09.959 --> 02:48:13.559
So, if taking the Lost Jewel was what

02:48:13.559 --> 02:48:16.620
she'd want him to do, he braced himself

02:48:16.620 --> 02:48:19.559
reached down and plucked it from the dead

02:48:19.559 --> 02:48:23.219
guard's claws, rough dead scales scraped

02:48:23.219 --> 02:48:25.799
against his, and he shuddered so badly, he

02:48:25.799 --> 02:48:28.440
nearly dropped the gemstone, but instead

02:48:28.440 --> 02:48:29.940
he gripped it harder and jumped back

02:48:29.940 --> 02:48:32.280
knocking against the shelves behind him.

02:48:32.340 --> 02:48:35.579
The claws were left clutching the air, as

02:48:35.579 --> 02:48:37.260
if hanging on to the memory of treasure

02:48:37.260 --> 02:48:38.459
would have to be enough.

02:48:38.520 --> 02:48:42.299
Now Starflight felt fairly sick, but when

02:48:42.299 --> 02:48:44.579
he held up the torch and glanced down, he

02:48:44.579 --> 02:48:46.139
realized he'd done the right thing.

02:48:46.200 --> 02:48:49.379
The blue star shaped sapphire glinted in

02:48:49.379 --> 02:48:51.959
his talons with a tiny inner spark of its

02:48:51.959 --> 02:48:52.319
own light.

02:48:52.379 --> 02:48:54.420
He'd only ever read about these.

02:48:54.479 --> 02:48:57.239
There were supposedly 3 of them in the

02:48:57.239 --> 02:49:00.719
world, all lost, all created 100s of

02:49:00.719 --> 02:49:04.260
years ago by a sandwing animus dragon, a

02:49:04.260 --> 02:49:05.040
dream visitor.

02:49:05.040 --> 02:49:07.500
He closed his claws around it.

02:49:07.559 --> 02:49:09.899
With this, he could see his friends

02:49:09.899 --> 02:49:10.200
again.

02:49:10.260 --> 02:49:12.239
Starflight?

02:49:12.239 --> 02:49:13.680
Fate speaker called.

02:49:13.739 --> 02:49:15.959
Coming, he said.

02:49:16.020 --> 02:49:18.299
He couldn't risk anyone finding the dream

02:49:18.299 --> 02:49:19.680
visitor and taking it from him.

02:49:19.739 --> 02:49:22.139
Not even fate speaker could know about

02:49:22.139 --> 02:49:22.319
it.

02:49:22.379 --> 02:49:25.799
He put it in his mouth, tucked down

02:49:25.799 --> 02:49:27.719
between his teeth and his scales, and

02:49:27.719 --> 02:49:28.739
pressed his tongue over it.

02:49:28.799 --> 02:49:31.799
On the way back to the dormitory, Fate

02:49:31.799 --> 02:49:34.379
speaker asked why he was so quiet, but he

02:49:34.379 --> 02:49:36.239
just shook his head and mumbled that he

02:49:36.239 --> 02:49:36.600
was tired.

02:49:36.659 --> 02:49:39.180
She shrugged and headed off to her own

02:49:39.180 --> 02:49:40.379
bed once they were back inside.

02:49:40.440 --> 02:49:43.799
Starflight pulled out the rough blanket

02:49:43.799 --> 02:49:45.840
he'd been given, and arranged it so he

02:49:45.840 --> 02:49:46.739
could huddle underneath it.

02:49:46.799 --> 02:49:49.440
The heavy brown fabric caught on his

02:49:49.440 --> 02:49:52.139
horns and smelled like smoke, but it

02:49:52.139 --> 02:49:53.700
would keep him hidden from any eyes that

02:49:53.700 --> 02:49:55.260
might still be awake.

02:49:55.319 --> 02:49:57.420
He cupped the dream visitor in his talons

02:49:57.420 --> 02:49:59.879
and stared at it, trying to remember if

02:49:59.879 --> 02:50:01.079
he'd read anything about how they

02:50:01.079 --> 02:50:01.379
worked.

02:50:01.440 --> 02:50:05.459
Perhaps I just think of the dragon whose

02:50:05.459 --> 02:50:06.479
dreams I want to visit?

02:50:06.540 --> 02:50:10.079
Surely Sonny would be asleep right now, in

02:50:10.079 --> 02:50:10.920
the middle of the night.

02:50:10.979 --> 02:50:13.500
If he remembered right, he should be able

02:50:13.500 --> 02:50:15.120
to step into whatever she was already

02:50:15.120 --> 02:50:17.520
dreaming about, and if she were in the

02:50:17.520 --> 02:50:20.100
deepest level of dream sleep, she'd see

02:50:20.100 --> 02:50:22.139
him, and they could talk to each other.

02:50:22.200 --> 02:50:24.479
But if her sleep was shallow or uneasy.

02:50:24.540 --> 02:50:27.299
He might be able to see in, but she

02:50:27.299 --> 02:50:28.379
wouldn't know he was really there.

02:50:28.440 --> 02:50:31.500
And if she were awake, it wouldn't work

02:50:31.500 --> 02:50:32.159
at all, of course.

02:50:32.219 --> 02:50:36.299
He closed his eyes and pictured Sonny, her

02:50:36.299 --> 02:50:38.159
laugh that made everyone else laugh too.

02:50:38.219 --> 02:50:40.799
Her flares of temper that vanished as

02:50:40.799 --> 02:50:43.920
quickly as they came, her small claws, and

02:50:43.920 --> 02:50:45.299
fierce protective face.

02:50:45.360 --> 02:50:48.780
Her scales like rippled sunshine, the way

02:50:48.780 --> 02:50:50.700
she looked like no other dragon on

02:50:50.700 --> 02:50:51.299
Pyrea.

02:50:51.360 --> 02:50:54.059
If she were here, she'd know exactly what

02:50:54.059 --> 02:50:56.340
to say about his father, she'd tell him

02:50:56.340 --> 02:50:58.020
what to tell the night wings about glory

02:50:58.020 --> 02:51:00.180
and how to talk them out of herding rain

02:51:00.180 --> 02:51:00.959
wings forever.

02:51:01.020 --> 02:51:04.440
But no matter how hard he concentrated

02:51:04.440 --> 02:51:06.540
his mind stayed firmly in the night wing

02:51:06.540 --> 02:51:08.520
dormitory instead of finding her dreams.

02:51:08.579 --> 02:51:10.620
Maybe she was awake.

02:51:10.680 --> 02:51:13.620
Maybe she was in the rainforest somewhere

02:51:13.620 --> 02:51:16.319
looking at the moons, and wondering if he

02:51:16.319 --> 02:51:17.100
was looking at them too.

02:51:17.219 --> 02:51:21.600
He tried glory next, then clay, then

02:51:21.600 --> 02:51:22.260
tsunami.

02:51:22.319 --> 02:51:23.639
Nothing happened.

02:51:23.700 --> 02:51:25.260
He couldn't reach any of them.

02:51:25.319 --> 02:51:28.319
Starflight squeezed the dream visitor

02:51:28.319 --> 02:51:31.200
between his claws, grinding his teeth.

02:51:31.260 --> 02:51:34.020
This had to work. unless it wasn't really

02:51:34.020 --> 02:51:36.239
a dream visitor. it certainly looked like

02:51:36.239 --> 02:51:36.479
one.

02:51:36.540 --> 02:51:39.059
Try rain wing.

02:51:39.120 --> 02:51:40.559
They're always asleep.

02:51:40.620 --> 02:51:43.620
The 1st rain wing who came to mind was

02:51:43.620 --> 02:51:46.079
Kinkaju, the little dragonette glory had

02:51:46.079 --> 02:51:47.280
rescued from the night wings.

02:51:47.340 --> 02:51:49.979
Starflight focused on her enormous dark

02:51:49.979 --> 02:51:52.020
eyes and quick changing scales.

02:51:52.079 --> 02:51:54.360
He pressed the dream visitor to his

02:51:54.360 --> 02:51:56.219
forehead, praying that this would work.

02:51:56.280 --> 02:51:59.579
And suddenly, he was perched on a branch

02:51:59.579 --> 02:52:00.479
in the rainforest.

02:52:00.540 --> 02:52:03.840
Starflight took a deep, relieved breath

02:52:03.840 --> 02:52:06.540
but he still inhaled the smoke of the

02:52:06.540 --> 02:52:07.139
dormitory.

02:52:07.200 --> 02:52:09.899
He could see the rainforest, but he

02:52:09.899 --> 02:52:10.500
couldn't smell it.

02:52:10.559 --> 02:52:12.000
Unfortunately for him.

02:52:12.059 --> 02:52:15.059
Kinkachu was curled on a giant leaf

02:52:15.059 --> 02:52:17.340
beside him with her eyes closed.

02:52:17.399 --> 02:52:19.440
There was a bandage of soft leaves and

02:52:19.440 --> 02:52:21.719
moss wrapped around one of her wings, and

02:52:21.719 --> 02:52:23.879
piles of red and yellow and purple fruits

02:52:23.879 --> 02:52:25.979
all around her, like offerings to a

02:52:25.979 --> 02:52:26.280
statue.

02:52:26.399 --> 02:52:29.639
Her scales were a strangely pale shade of

02:52:29.639 --> 02:52:31.860
blue in the moonlight, and she breathed

02:52:31.860 --> 02:52:34.739
shallowly, as if, even in her sleep, she

02:52:34.739 --> 02:52:36.239
knew a deeper breath would make something

02:52:36.239 --> 02:52:36.659
hurt.

02:52:36.719 --> 02:52:38.760
What happened to you?

02:52:38.819 --> 02:52:42.180
Starflight wondered aloud, but she didn't

02:52:42.180 --> 02:52:42.479
wake up.

02:52:42.540 --> 02:52:45.659
He turned to find another dragon staring

02:52:45.659 --> 02:52:46.200
right through him.

02:52:46.260 --> 02:52:48.959
For a startled, terrifying moment

02:52:48.959 --> 02:52:50.819
Starflight thought the dragon could see

02:52:50.819 --> 02:52:53.700
him, but then he realized she was just

02:52:53.700 --> 02:52:54.899
watching Kinkachu.

02:52:54.959 --> 02:52:57.780
She was old, older than any of the

02:52:57.780 --> 02:53:00.540
guardians or queens he'd met so far, and

02:53:00.540 --> 02:53:02.219
she had that royal elegance about her

02:53:02.219 --> 02:53:04.260
that he'd noticed greatness lacking.

02:53:04.319 --> 02:53:07.139
Starflight turned back to kinkaju.

02:53:07.200 --> 02:53:08.940
How could he get inside her dreams?

02:53:09.000 --> 02:53:11.700
He looked down at the dream visitor and

02:53:11.700 --> 02:53:12.840
remembered pressing it to his own

02:53:12.840 --> 02:53:13.319
forehead.

02:53:13.379 --> 02:53:16.739
Carefully, he leaned over and rested the

02:53:16.739 --> 02:53:18.780
sapphire between Kinkaju's eyes.

02:53:18.840 --> 02:53:21.659
The 1st time he tried, he nearly fell

02:53:21.659 --> 02:53:23.639
right through her. since he wasn't really

02:53:23.639 --> 02:53:23.940
there.

02:53:24.000 --> 02:53:26.459
He couldn't touch her or anything around

02:53:26.459 --> 02:53:26.760
her.

02:53:26.819 --> 02:53:30.000
But when he tried a 2nd time, holding the

02:53:30.000 --> 02:53:31.379
dream visitor where he thought it should

02:53:31.379 --> 02:53:31.680
go.

02:53:31.739 --> 02:53:34.620
He felt a therm of energy radiate from

02:53:34.620 --> 02:53:37.020
Kinkachu through the jewel to him and

02:53:37.020 --> 02:53:39.899
back again, and then he saw what she

02:53:39.899 --> 02:53:40.139
saw.

02:53:40.260 --> 02:53:44.219
In Kinkajoo's dream, she was standing in

02:53:44.219 --> 02:53:46.860
bright sunlight, in a wide green bowl

02:53:46.860 --> 02:53:49.500
laced with brightly colored flowers

02:53:49.500 --> 02:53:52.620
surrounded by 1000s of rain wings, more

02:53:52.620 --> 02:53:54.420
rain wings than there can possibly be on

02:53:54.420 --> 02:53:56.819
the whole continent, all of them staring

02:53:56.819 --> 02:53:59.280
at her with expressions of disdain, that

02:53:59.280 --> 02:54:01.440
Starflight had never seen in real life on

02:54:01.440 --> 02:54:02.459
any rain wing.

02:54:02.520 --> 02:54:05.819
Glory was there in the center of the bowl

02:54:05.819 --> 02:54:08.819
but this glory was impossibly big and

02:54:08.819 --> 02:54:10.979
impossibly beautiful, and a crown of

02:54:10.979 --> 02:54:13.979
orange hibiscus, gold chain, and rubies

02:54:13.979 --> 02:54:15.180
sparkled atop her head.

02:54:15.239 --> 02:54:19.200
That's how Kinkaju sees her, Starflight

02:54:19.200 --> 02:54:19.559
thought.

02:54:19.620 --> 02:54:23.040
This glory smiled more too, at least at

02:54:23.040 --> 02:54:24.059
Kinkaju.

02:54:24.120 --> 02:54:26.639
A crown, he thought suddenly.

02:54:26.700 --> 02:54:28.620
Does that mean glory won?

02:54:28.680 --> 02:54:30.899
Is she now queen of the rain wings?

02:54:30.959 --> 02:54:32.819
Or is this a wishful dream?

02:54:32.879 --> 02:54:36.059
Kingetu backed away from the stares of

02:54:36.059 --> 02:54:38.159
the dragons until she reached the far

02:54:38.159 --> 02:54:39.420
edge of the bowl?

02:54:39.479 --> 02:54:41.520
Suddenly she turned and leaped off

02:54:41.520 --> 02:54:44.159
spreading her wings, but instead of

02:54:44.159 --> 02:54:46.440
soaring away through the trees, she fell

02:54:46.440 --> 02:54:48.540
plummeting like a coconut toward the

02:54:48.540 --> 02:54:50.639
ground below, her wings flapped

02:54:50.639 --> 02:54:52.739
helplessly, and when she twisted to look

02:54:52.739 --> 02:54:55.319
at them, giant holes appeared all over

02:54:55.319 --> 02:54:58.379
her wings, spreading, as though acid was

02:54:58.379 --> 02:54:58.979
eating them away.

02:54:59.040 --> 02:55:02.159
Kinkaju screamed and clawed at the air.

02:55:02.219 --> 02:55:05.340
Starflight watched helplessly from above

02:55:05.340 --> 02:55:07.139
as the greenery swallowed her up.

02:55:07.200 --> 02:55:08.940
It's just a dream.

02:55:09.000 --> 02:55:12.059
He told himself, that his racing heart

02:55:12.059 --> 02:55:12.780
didn't believe him.

02:55:12.840 --> 02:55:14.639
Just a dream.

02:55:14.700 --> 02:55:15.959
Nothing you could do.

02:55:16.020 --> 02:55:18.120
She didn't even see you here.

02:55:18.180 --> 02:55:21.239
He wouldn't be able to reach her in a

02:55:21.239 --> 02:55:23.459
dream like this, where her emotions were

02:55:23.459 --> 02:55:23.819
so strong.

02:55:23.940 --> 02:55:26.639
It was really strange to be in someone

02:55:26.639 --> 02:55:29.040
else's nightmare, so different from the

02:55:29.040 --> 02:55:30.600
ones he had almost every night.

02:55:30.659 --> 02:55:33.600
His own anxiety dreams usually involved

02:55:33.600 --> 02:55:35.700
the night wing queen telling him that

02:55:35.700 --> 02:55:38.399
dragonets who weren't telepathic were not

02:55:38.399 --> 02:55:39.239
welcome in the tribe.

02:55:39.299 --> 02:55:42.719
The dreamscape around him shuddered, and

02:55:42.719 --> 02:55:43.680
then suddenly went dark.

02:55:43.739 --> 02:55:45.840
She's waking up.

02:55:45.959 --> 02:55:48.899
Starfly dug his talons into the tree

02:55:48.899 --> 02:55:51.059
branch below him, even though he couldn't

02:55:51.059 --> 02:55:53.219
see it now, and he also knew it wasn't

02:55:53.219 --> 02:55:53.639
really there.

02:55:53.700 --> 02:55:56.579
Or rather, he wasn't really there.

02:55:56.639 --> 02:55:59.579
He wanted to hold on to the rainforest as

02:55:59.579 --> 02:56:00.239
long as he could.

02:56:00.299 --> 02:56:02.639
He didn't want to go back to the gloomy

02:56:02.639 --> 02:56:03.899
nightwing dormitory.

02:56:03.959 --> 02:56:06.780
Stay asleep, he thought desperately.

02:56:06.840 --> 02:56:08.280
Please see me.

02:56:08.399 --> 02:56:10.920
I need to send a message to my friends.

02:56:10.979 --> 02:56:14.459
Now he could see faint outlines of shapes

02:56:14.459 --> 02:56:16.620
in the darkness. as if it was very early

02:56:16.620 --> 02:56:18.959
morning, and the sun was rising far

02:56:18.959 --> 02:56:19.379
away.

02:56:19.500 --> 02:56:20.940
In front of him.

02:56:21.000 --> 02:56:23.459
Kinkaju was curled on the leaf again

02:56:23.459 --> 02:56:26.100
still asleep, but twitching restlessly.

02:56:26.159 --> 02:56:29.100
A silvery shaft of moonlight lit up the

02:56:29.100 --> 02:56:30.780
expression of pain on her face.

02:56:30.840 --> 02:56:33.600
She'd snapped out of the nightmare into a

02:56:33.600 --> 02:56:36.059
shallow sleep with no dreams, where she

02:56:36.059 --> 02:56:37.559
was half aware of everything around her

02:56:37.559 --> 02:56:38.879
without being fully awake.

02:56:38.940 --> 02:56:41.579
He could be here, but she wouldn't see

02:56:41.579 --> 02:56:41.819
him.

02:56:41.940 --> 02:56:42.840
Not now.

02:56:42.899 --> 02:56:45.059
Another nightmare?

02:56:45.180 --> 02:56:47.100
Said a quiet voice behind him.

02:56:47.159 --> 02:56:50.219
Starflight whirled around, his heart

02:56:50.219 --> 02:56:51.360
leaping into his throat.

02:56:51.420 --> 02:56:52.860
Sonny.

02:56:52.979 --> 02:56:55.799
The sand wing was just landing on the

02:56:55.799 --> 02:56:57.899
branch beside the queenly rain wing.

02:56:57.959 --> 02:57:00.540
Her golden wings folded in, and she

02:57:00.540 --> 02:57:02.520
flipped her tail over her back talons the

02:57:02.520 --> 02:57:03.180
way she always did.

02:57:03.239 --> 02:57:06.719
A moment later, a glint of blue scales

02:57:06.719 --> 02:57:08.700
appeared through the trees behind Sonny.

02:57:08.760 --> 02:57:11.639
Tsunami, flapping down to land next to

02:57:11.639 --> 02:57:11.819
her.

02:57:11.879 --> 02:57:15.959
I think so, said the older rain wing.

02:57:16.020 --> 02:57:18.180
I wasn't sure whether to wake her.

02:57:18.239 --> 02:57:19.860
How is the queen?

02:57:19.920 --> 02:57:22.680
Mad, said Sonny.

02:57:22.739 --> 02:57:24.299
Super mad.

02:57:24.420 --> 02:57:26.280
I keep telling her there's no way

02:57:26.520 --> 02:57:28.139
Starflight went to the Night Wings on his

02:57:28.139 --> 02:57:30.479
own, but she's convinced he's betrayed

02:57:30.479 --> 02:57:30.600
us.

02:57:30.719 --> 02:57:33.719
Shock rippled through Starflight's

02:57:33.719 --> 02:57:34.079
wings.

02:57:34.139 --> 02:57:36.059
It hadn't occurred to him that his

02:57:36.059 --> 02:57:37.319
friends would think he'd left them on

02:57:37.319 --> 02:57:37.680
purpose.

02:57:37.739 --> 02:57:39.899
The queen.

02:57:39.959 --> 02:57:41.459
Does she mean glory?

02:57:41.520 --> 02:57:43.979
Glory thinks I betrayed them?

02:57:44.040 --> 02:57:47.219
Then he remembered telling the night wing

02:57:47.219 --> 02:57:48.959
council that the rain wings were planning

02:57:48.959 --> 02:57:51.899
to attack, and his scales felt hot with

02:57:51.899 --> 02:57:52.200
shame.

02:57:52.260 --> 02:57:55.440
He may have been abducted, but he hadn't

02:57:55.440 --> 02:57:56.879
done anything to help his friends since

02:57:56.879 --> 02:57:57.479
he got here.

02:57:57.540 --> 02:57:59.399
He hadn't tried to escape.

02:57:59.459 --> 02:58:03.059
He hadn't even argued with Morrow seer, or

02:58:03.059 --> 02:58:04.440
tried to stop the night wings.

02:58:04.500 --> 02:58:06.899
Maybe he really didn't belong in the

02:58:06.899 --> 02:58:07.379
prophecy.

02:58:07.500 --> 02:58:10.020
Maybe fate speaker was the better dragon

02:58:10.020 --> 02:58:10.799
to save the world.

02:58:10.920 --> 02:58:13.319
Starflight?

02:58:13.379 --> 02:58:14.760
Tsunami snorted.

02:58:14.819 --> 02:58:17.639
Of all dragons, like he'd ever betray

02:58:17.639 --> 02:58:17.940
us.

02:58:18.000 --> 02:58:20.040
Can you actually imagine how it could

02:58:20.040 --> 02:58:20.520
have happened?

02:58:20.579 --> 02:58:22.620
First, making a decision.

02:58:22.680 --> 02:58:25.860
Not exactly Starflight's forte, then

02:58:25.860 --> 02:58:28.559
actually doing something instead of

02:58:28.559 --> 02:58:30.180
sitting and waiting for it to happen to

02:58:30.180 --> 02:58:33.299
him, and not just anything, jumping into

02:58:33.299 --> 02:58:35.399
a dark hole with angry dragons on the

02:58:35.399 --> 02:58:37.500
other side, Starflight?

02:58:37.559 --> 02:58:39.000
Are you kidding me?

02:58:39.059 --> 02:58:40.620
Starflight?

02:58:40.680 --> 02:58:44.280
Oh my gosh, stop it, Sonny said.

02:58:44.340 --> 02:58:46.440
You've been arguing with glory all day.

02:58:46.500 --> 02:58:48.420
You don't have to convince me that

02:58:48.420 --> 02:58:49.680
Starflight wouldn't do something like

02:58:49.680 --> 02:58:49.860
this.

02:58:49.979 --> 02:58:53.940
She hopped down to Kinkaju's side, nearly

02:58:53.940 --> 02:58:55.559
passing right through Starflight.

02:58:55.620 --> 02:58:57.719
He shivered and leaned toward her.

02:58:57.780 --> 02:59:00.239
He could almost imagine he felt the

02:59:00.239 --> 02:59:01.920
warmth of her scales as she went by.

02:59:01.979 --> 02:59:05.940
You don't think he chose to go to the

02:59:05.940 --> 02:59:06.659
night kingdom?

02:59:06.659 --> 02:59:09.239
asked the dragon Starfly didn't know.

02:59:09.299 --> 02:59:11.819
Sonny looked up at the 2 moons that were

02:59:11.819 --> 02:59:13.799
visible through the canopy, then back

02:59:13.799 --> 02:59:14.700
down at Kinkachu.

02:59:14.760 --> 02:59:17.879
If he went, then I'm sure it was for a

02:59:17.879 --> 02:59:20.100
good reason, but if he didn't choose to

02:59:20.100 --> 02:59:22.440
go, then he needs our help, right

02:59:22.440 --> 02:59:23.100
tsunami?

02:59:23.159 --> 02:59:24.659
Isn't that the important thing?

02:59:24.719 --> 02:59:27.899
Shouldn't we go get him right now before

02:59:27.899 --> 02:59:29.340
something terrible happens to him?

02:59:29.399 --> 02:59:32.159
She bent to examine the bandage on

02:59:32.159 --> 02:59:33.180
Kinkachu's wing.

02:59:33.239 --> 02:59:36.420
Yes, Starflight thought frantically.

02:59:36.479 --> 02:59:37.979
Please hurry.

02:59:38.040 --> 02:59:41.700
If it were up to me, the 4 of us would be

02:59:41.700 --> 02:59:43.680
there now. tearing that place apart.

02:59:43.799 --> 02:59:46.860
Tsunami growled, instead of wasting our

02:59:46.860 --> 02:59:47.219
time here.

02:59:47.280 --> 02:59:51.840
Combat training didn't go well. asked the

02:59:51.840 --> 02:59:52.319
other dragon.

02:59:52.379 --> 02:59:55.260
Tsunami lashed her tails so hard, she

02:59:55.260 --> 02:59:56.340
nearly fell off the branch.

02:59:56.399 --> 02:59:58.799
General, may I take a nap?

02:59:58.860 --> 03:00:01.979
General, I need a papaya.

03:00:02.040 --> 03:00:03.959
General, my claws are tired.

03:00:04.020 --> 03:00:06.899
General, look, a butterfly.

03:00:06.959 --> 03:00:09.299
Somebody is getting stabbed in the face

03:00:09.299 --> 03:00:10.680
if you don't shut up.

03:00:10.739 --> 03:00:13.680
Sunny smothered a giggle.

03:00:13.739 --> 03:00:16.860
When does the queen want to attack?

03:00:16.920 --> 03:00:20.040
The older dragon bared her teeth as

03:00:20.040 --> 03:00:21.420
though she was ready to go right now.

03:00:21.479 --> 03:00:25.680
Oh, look, Sonny interrupted, touching her

03:00:25.680 --> 03:00:27.780
front talon lightly to Kinkaju's head.

03:00:27.899 --> 03:00:29.280
She's waking up.

03:00:29.340 --> 03:00:30.899
No.

03:00:30.959 --> 03:00:34.260
Starflight saw Kinkaju's eyes flutter.

03:00:34.319 --> 03:00:37.139
He reached out, holding the dream visitor

03:00:37.139 --> 03:00:39.540
trying to send her back into dream sleep

03:00:39.540 --> 03:00:40.559
but it was too late.

03:00:40.620 --> 03:00:43.500
With a wrenching, sideways jolt.

03:00:43.559 --> 03:00:47.340
The rainforest, and Kinkaju, and Tsunami

03:00:47.340 --> 03:00:49.020
and Sunny, was ripped away.

03:00:49.079 --> 03:00:51.659
And Starflight found himself lying on

03:00:51.659 --> 03:00:52.920
cold stone once again.

03:00:52.979 --> 03:00:56.159
The thick canvas lay heavy on his horns

03:00:56.159 --> 03:00:58.680
and the dim red light of the coals pulsed

03:00:58.680 --> 03:01:00.719
beyond it, making his eyes ache.

03:01:00.780 --> 03:01:04.319
Sonny had been right there, inches from

03:01:04.319 --> 03:01:06.180
him, so close.

03:01:06.239 --> 03:01:08.639
And yet she might as well have been on

03:01:08.639 --> 03:01:09.420
one of the moons.

03:01:09.479 --> 03:01:12.719
He stared down at the dream visitor that

03:01:12.719 --> 03:01:14.940
glowed faintly in his talons.

03:01:15.000 --> 03:01:17.040
Seeing them had somehow been even worse

03:01:17.040 --> 03:01:18.780
than not seeing them.

03:01:18.840 --> 03:01:21.059
My friends think I betrayed them.

03:01:21.120 --> 03:01:24.180
Or if they don't, they think it's because

03:01:24.180 --> 03:01:26.040
I'm too much of a coward to do something

03:01:26.040 --> 03:01:26.639
like that.

03:01:26.700 --> 03:01:30.899
He closed his eyes, feeling lonelier than

03:01:30.899 --> 03:01:32.219
he had ever felt in his life.
5067
03:01:32,280 --> 03:01:36,659	Chapter 11.

03:01:36.959 --> 03:01:40.379
The blanket was ripped off Starflight's

03:01:40.379 --> 03:01:42.540
head with such force that he tumbled onto

03:01:42.540 --> 03:01:43.020
the floor.

03:01:43.079 --> 03:01:46.559
His head spun for a moment, but his 1st

03:01:46.559 --> 03:01:48.360
thought was that he was glad he'd hidden

03:01:48.360 --> 03:01:49.979
the dream visitor well the night before.

03:01:50.040 --> 03:01:53.639
Oh, Maro CR snarled.

03:01:53.700 --> 03:01:55.739
His breath was fiercely awful this

03:01:55.739 --> 03:01:56.100
morning.

03:01:56.159 --> 03:01:58.559
At least Starflight assumed it was

03:01:58.559 --> 03:02:00.600
morning, although the sky was barely

03:02:00.600 --> 03:02:01.799
lighter than it had been the night

03:02:01.799 --> 03:02:02.100
before.

03:02:02.159 --> 03:02:05.639
Flame and ochre stood sullenly behind the

03:02:05.639 --> 03:02:08.700
giant night wing, glaring at Starflight.

03:02:08.760 --> 03:02:10.440
He hoped they had had to spend the night

03:02:10.440 --> 03:02:11.159
in the dungeon.

03:02:11.219 --> 03:02:14.040
Fate speaker came bounding over to join

03:02:14.040 --> 03:02:16.739
them, followed more slowly by Viper and

03:02:16.739 --> 03:02:17.219
Squid.

03:02:17.280 --> 03:02:19.979
All around the dormitory, Nightwing

03:02:19.979 --> 03:02:21.600
Dragonettes were poking their heads out

03:02:21.600 --> 03:02:23.219
of their blankets, watching.

03:02:23.280 --> 03:02:26.100
Fierce teeth looked openly envious.

03:02:26.159 --> 03:02:28.979
Smoke rose from her snout, and her tail

03:02:28.979 --> 03:02:29.940
twitched angrily.

03:02:30.059 --> 03:02:32.459
Maro Seer didn't even look at the other

03:02:32.459 --> 03:02:33.719
night wing dragonettes.

03:02:33.780 --> 03:02:36.420
Let's go. he ordered.

03:02:36.479 --> 03:02:39.000
His tail nearly knocked Starflight over

03:02:39.000 --> 03:02:40.860
as he turned and swept out of the room.

03:02:40.979 --> 03:02:43.139
Where are we going?

03:02:43.200 --> 03:02:45.059
Fate speaker asked cheerfully.

03:02:45.120 --> 03:02:47.100
She seemed to have recovered from the

03:02:47.100 --> 03:02:49.200
news that either she or Starflight were

03:02:49.200 --> 03:02:49.799
slated for death.

03:02:49.920 --> 03:02:53.340
To see if it's worth spending any more

03:02:53.340 --> 03:02:54.000
time on you.

03:02:54.120 --> 03:02:55.860
Said Morris here.

03:02:55.920 --> 03:02:58.620
Certain dragons think we should lock you

03:02:58.620 --> 03:03:01.559
all up until we sort out our rain wing

03:03:01.559 --> 03:03:02.340
problem.

03:03:02.520 --> 03:03:04.979
But I think you need as much training as

03:03:04.979 --> 03:03:07.079
possible starting as soon as possible.

03:03:07.139 --> 03:03:12.239
So today, we'll have another test.

03:03:12.299 --> 03:03:14.639
A test?

03:03:14.700 --> 03:03:17.819
Starflight echoed, flapping his wings.

03:03:17.879 --> 03:03:18.239
On what?

03:03:18.360 --> 03:03:19.979
We haven't had time to study.

03:03:20.040 --> 03:03:22.139
Shouldn't we review the material first?

03:03:22.200 --> 03:03:24.840
Maro Seer looked over his shoulder at

03:03:24.840 --> 03:03:25.559
Starflight.

03:03:25.620 --> 03:03:27.120
Sometimes.

03:03:27.180 --> 03:03:30.899
It is very hard not to bite you, he

03:03:30.899 --> 03:03:31.319
growled.

03:03:31.379 --> 03:03:35.459
Well, that's hardly fair, Starflight

03:03:35.459 --> 03:03:37.500
thought, but he decided not to say

03:03:37.500 --> 03:03:37.979
anything else.

03:03:38.040 --> 03:03:40.979
Usually he was pretty good at tests.

03:03:41.040 --> 03:03:43.440
Maybe this was finally his chance to earn

03:03:43.440 --> 03:03:44.700
a place in the prophecy.

03:03:44.760 --> 03:03:46.920
Especially if it's about history.

03:03:46.979 --> 03:03:49.739
I read all the history scrolls several

03:03:49.739 --> 03:03:50.280
times each.

03:03:50.340 --> 03:03:53.459
He noticed that Flame was still glaring

03:03:53.459 --> 03:03:55.260
at him with resentful orange eyes.

03:03:55.319 --> 03:03:58.379
Carefully, Starflight maneuvered so that

03:03:58.379 --> 03:04:00.420
fate speaker was walking between him and

03:04:00.420 --> 03:04:02.219
the hostile Skywing Dragonette.

03:04:02.340 --> 03:04:05.520
The 6 of them trailed after Maroseare all

03:04:05.520 --> 03:04:07.500
the way to a roof of the fortress that

03:04:07.500 --> 03:04:09.180
faced the small island forest.

03:04:09.239 --> 03:04:12.239
Morosea spread his wings and narrowed his

03:04:12.239 --> 03:04:15.180
eyes at the sky, which was dark gray, and

03:04:15.180 --> 03:04:16.680
flickered with faraway lightning.

03:04:16.739 --> 03:04:19.920
In the distance, the clouds seemed to be

03:04:19.920 --> 03:04:21.000
pouring down into the ocean.

03:04:21.059 --> 03:04:23.760
A storm out at sea.

03:04:23.879 --> 03:04:25.139
Starflight thought.

03:04:25.200 --> 03:04:27.899
He shuddered, remembering the storm that

03:04:27.899 --> 03:04:29.459
had nearly flooded the cave in the

03:04:29.459 --> 03:04:30.299
kingdom of the sea.

03:04:30.360 --> 03:04:33.299
Clay had been chained to the wall, and

03:04:33.299 --> 03:04:35.159
Glory and Sonny had been so determined

03:04:35.159 --> 03:04:35.879
not to leave him.

03:04:35.940 --> 03:04:38.760
If tsunami hadn't come for them, they

03:04:38.760 --> 03:04:40.200
probably would have decided to drown

03:04:40.200 --> 03:04:41.159
along with clay.

03:04:41.219 --> 03:04:43.379
Starflight wasn't sure he'd have been

03:04:43.379 --> 03:04:43.920
able to do that.

03:04:43.979 --> 03:04:46.440
He'd been too scared to say anything

03:04:46.440 --> 03:04:49.079
watching the water slowly rising toward

03:04:49.079 --> 03:04:49.440
them.

03:04:49.500 --> 03:04:52.020
Stay close to me.

03:04:52.079 --> 03:04:54.239
Marosio growled.

03:04:54.299 --> 03:04:56.520
He jabbed Starflight in the neck with one

03:04:56.520 --> 03:04:57.659
claw.

03:04:57.719 --> 03:04:58.799
Don't try anything.

03:04:58.920 --> 03:05:01.860
And then he lifted into the sky without

03:05:01.860 --> 03:05:03.959
any more explanation or instructions.

03:05:04.079 --> 03:05:07.200
It took Starflight a moment to figure out

03:05:07.200 --> 03:05:08.399
that they were leaving the island.

03:05:08.459 --> 03:05:10.379
Back to the mainland?

03:05:10.500 --> 03:05:13.799
He leaped into the air, his heart jumping

03:05:13.799 --> 03:05:14.760
hopefully at the same time.

03:05:14.819 --> 03:05:19.079
Wait, Squid called in a complaining whine

03:05:19.079 --> 03:05:20.879
flapping after Morrow's here.

03:05:20.940 --> 03:05:22.979
We haven't even had breakfast.

03:05:23.040 --> 03:05:25.139
You're not going to make me fly on an

03:05:25.139 --> 03:05:26.280
empty stomach, are you?

03:05:26.340 --> 03:05:27.840
Because I will die.

03:05:28.020 --> 03:05:29.819
I will literally die.

03:05:29.879 --> 03:05:32.399
You won't, actually.

03:05:32.459 --> 03:05:34.979
Not for a while, Starflight informed

03:05:34.979 --> 03:05:35.100
him.

03:05:35.159 --> 03:05:38.219
Most dragons can naturally survive for up

03:05:38.219 --> 03:05:40.440
to a month without eating, if necessary

03:05:40.440 --> 03:05:42.420
according to a natural history of

03:05:42.420 --> 03:05:43.979
unnatural dragon abilities.

03:05:44.040 --> 03:05:46.860
Listen to the scroll worm.

03:05:46.920 --> 03:05:48.719
Flame said nastily.

03:05:48.780 --> 03:05:49.920
Isn't he clever?

03:05:49.979 --> 03:05:53.100
I will never, never.

03:05:53.159 --> 03:05:56.819
Never go a whole month without eating

03:05:56.819 --> 03:05:59.100
Okre said passionately.

03:05:59.159 --> 03:06:02.399
Is one of the unnatural abilities being

03:06:02.399 --> 03:06:05.639
really annoying, Viper asked, because

03:06:05.639 --> 03:06:07.379
there should be a whole chapter on you

03:06:07.379 --> 03:06:08.340
and fate speaker.

03:06:08.399 --> 03:06:11.879
You don't even know me, Starflight

03:06:11.879 --> 03:06:12.360
pointed out.

03:06:12.420 --> 03:06:14.340
I was just trying to help.

03:06:14.459 --> 03:06:17.459
I thought it was interesting, fate

03:06:17.459 --> 03:06:19.620
speaker said. and probably useful.

03:06:19.680 --> 03:06:22.260
If the Night Wings keep feeding us the

03:06:22.260 --> 03:06:23.879
horrible stuff they've been bringing so

03:06:23.879 --> 03:06:24.059
far.

03:06:24.120 --> 03:06:27.120
Oh, I have a theory about that.

03:06:27.180 --> 03:06:29.940
As they flew over the forest and out

03:06:29.940 --> 03:06:32.219
across the ocean, Starflight told her

03:06:32.219 --> 03:06:34.440
about how the night wings hunted, and his

03:06:34.440 --> 03:06:36.420
ideas about the bacteria in their mouths

03:06:36.420 --> 03:06:38.399
and how he and fate speaker probably

03:06:38.399 --> 03:06:40.500
didn't have it, since they'd grown up

03:06:40.500 --> 03:06:43.319
eating live or recently killed prey, and

03:06:43.319 --> 03:06:45.239
hadn't developed the bacteria like the

03:06:45.239 --> 03:06:46.440
night wing dragonettes on the island

03:06:46.440 --> 03:06:46.920
would have.

03:06:46.979 --> 03:06:51.420
Wow, said fate speaker, looking genuinely

03:06:51.420 --> 03:06:52.020
fascinated.

03:06:52.079 --> 03:06:54.360
Is this the test?

03:06:54.420 --> 03:06:55.620
Viper asked.

03:06:55.680 --> 03:06:57.719
Listen to you for as long as we can

03:06:57.719 --> 03:06:59.219
without dying of boredom.

03:06:59.280 --> 03:07:02.579
Nobody's talking to you, Viper, fate

03:07:02.579 --> 03:07:03.239
speaker said.

03:07:03.299 --> 03:07:05.219
Go be grumpy at squid and leave

03:07:05.219 --> 03:07:06.000
Starflight alone.

03:07:06.059 --> 03:07:09.059
Starflight glanced down at the waves

03:07:09.059 --> 03:07:09.780
rushing below him.

03:07:09.840 --> 03:07:12.299
The island was disappearing behind them

03:07:12.299 --> 03:07:14.819
visible only as a red glow in the sky.

03:07:14.879 --> 03:07:17.700
Ahead of them was nothing but sea as far

03:07:17.700 --> 03:07:18.840
as the distant horizon.

03:07:18.899 --> 03:07:21.239
He had no idea how Maro Zero was

03:07:21.239 --> 03:07:21.719
navigating.

03:07:21.780 --> 03:07:24.299
There were no landmarks, and the sky was

03:07:24.299 --> 03:07:25.440
still hidden behind the clouds.

03:07:25.500 --> 03:07:29.040
I should pay attention so I can fly this

03:07:29.040 --> 03:07:30.840
way if I ever get a chance to escape.

03:07:30.899 --> 03:07:34.500
Actually, what he should do was try to

03:07:34.500 --> 03:07:36.360
escape once they reached the mainland.

03:07:36.420 --> 03:07:40.500
Just fly away, hide, try to get back to

03:07:40.500 --> 03:07:41.159
the rainforest.

03:07:41.219 --> 03:07:44.219
He could not in a 1000000 years imagine

03:07:44.219 --> 03:07:45.840
doing any of that by himself.

03:07:45.899 --> 03:07:48.959
Maybe with tsunami and clay and glory and

03:07:48.959 --> 03:07:50.459
sunny, but alone?

03:07:50.520 --> 03:07:52.739
It sounded much safer to stay with the

03:07:52.739 --> 03:07:54.479
night wings and hope someone came to

03:07:54.479 --> 03:07:54.959
rescue him.

03:07:55.020 --> 03:07:57.120
Rain began to fall.

03:07:57.180 --> 03:08:00.239
Or rather, they reached the edge of the

03:08:00.239 --> 03:08:03.000
storm, and Starflight realized that

03:08:03.000 --> 03:08:04.979
Marosier planned to fly right through

03:08:04.979 --> 03:08:05.819
it.

03:08:05.879 --> 03:08:08.159
My wings are getting wet.

03:08:08.219 --> 03:08:09.659
Squid griped.

03:08:09.719 --> 03:08:12.719
Boo hoo, you poor sea wing.

03:08:12.780 --> 03:08:14.040
Flame snapped.

03:08:14.159 --> 03:08:16.079
Starflight wasn't about to say anything

03:08:16.079 --> 03:08:18.360
aloud, but the rain made his wings

03:08:18.360 --> 03:08:20.520
heavier, and it was much harder to fly.

03:08:20.579 --> 03:08:22.620
He didn't have the strongest flying

03:08:22.620 --> 03:08:23.399
muscles anyway.

03:08:23.459 --> 03:08:26.040
Being raised in a cave meant not much

03:08:26.040 --> 03:08:27.120
opportunity to practice.

03:08:27.180 --> 03:08:29.879
He clenched his jaw and flew on.

03:08:29.940 --> 03:08:32.940
If this was the test, he refused to

03:08:32.940 --> 03:08:33.239
fail.

03:08:33.299 --> 03:08:36.600
He would fly until his wings gave out, and

03:08:36.600 --> 03:08:38.159
he would not let anyone see how much it

03:08:38.159 --> 03:08:38.340
hurt.

03:08:38.399 --> 03:08:40.440
Think of Sonny.

03:08:40.500 --> 03:08:42.780
Think about being the dragon, you want

03:08:42.780 --> 03:08:43.680
her to think you are.

03:08:43.739 --> 03:08:47.520
The sea kept getting closer, which he

03:08:47.520 --> 03:08:48.719
knew meant he was drooping.

03:08:48.780 --> 03:08:51.719
The rain pelted down harder and harder

03:08:51.719 --> 03:08:54.059
battering his scales, and making it

03:08:54.059 --> 03:08:56.219
almost impossible to see ochre flying

03:08:56.219 --> 03:08:56.819
just ahead of him.

03:08:56.879 --> 03:08:59.879
Maroser was a dark blur in the clouds.

03:08:59.940 --> 03:09:02.280
Starflight hoped they didn't lose him.

03:09:02.399 --> 03:09:05.159
He hoped Maro Seer wasn't trying to lose

03:09:05.159 --> 03:09:07.379
them because it wouldn't be hard in this

03:09:07.379 --> 03:09:07.559
weather.

03:09:07.620 --> 03:09:10.920
A bolt of lightning sizzled through the

03:09:10.920 --> 03:09:13.319
sky, followed instantly by the loudest

03:09:13.319 --> 03:09:15.239
thunderclap Starflight had ever heard.

03:09:15.360 --> 03:09:17.040
His whole body shook with the

03:09:17.040 --> 03:09:17.579
vibrations.

03:09:17.639 --> 03:09:19.860
I hope we get there soon.

03:09:19.920 --> 03:09:22.200
I hope we get there soon.

03:09:22.260 --> 03:09:25.739
He blinked away raindrops, and realized

03:09:25.739 --> 03:09:28.139
with a sickening lurch that the sky ahead

03:09:28.139 --> 03:09:28.799
of him was empty.

03:09:28.860 --> 03:09:31.200
Where are the other dragons?

03:09:31.319 --> 03:09:34.440
For horrible moment, he was completely

03:09:34.440 --> 03:09:34.860
lost.

03:09:34.920 --> 03:09:38.340
Then fate speaker appeared at his side

03:09:38.340 --> 03:09:39.719
and nudged his wing.

03:09:39.840 --> 03:09:42.959
Down there. she shouted over the wind.

03:09:43.020 --> 03:09:46.020
What looked like a small smudge on the

03:09:46.020 --> 03:09:48.360
ocean turned out to be a tiny rocky

03:09:48.360 --> 03:09:49.500
island.

03:09:49.559 --> 03:09:51.360
Marosir and the others were perched there

03:09:51.360 --> 03:09:51.659
already.

03:09:51.780 --> 03:09:55.200
Starflight landed awkwardly next to Squid

03:09:55.200 --> 03:09:57.659
who had his wings over his head and was

03:09:57.659 --> 03:09:58.559
muttering angrily.

03:09:58.620 --> 03:10:02.520
Halfway there, fate speaker grinned at

03:10:02.520 --> 03:10:02.819
him.

03:10:02.879 --> 03:10:04.620
Only halfway?

03:10:04.620 --> 03:10:07.860
Starflight's resolution wavered, and he

03:10:07.860 --> 03:10:09.239
stared down at his claws.

03:10:09.299 --> 03:10:12.299
He was too exhausted even to ask all the

03:10:12.299 --> 03:10:13.799
questions brimming inside him.

03:10:13.860 --> 03:10:16.079
How had the night wings found their

03:10:16.079 --> 03:10:18.120
island, if it was this far from the

03:10:18.120 --> 03:10:18.600
mainland?

03:10:18.659 --> 03:10:21.000
How often did they go to the mainland?

03:10:21.120 --> 03:10:23.459
And did they usually use the tunnel to

03:10:23.459 --> 03:10:25.739
the rainforest, or fly over the sea like

03:10:25.739 --> 03:10:25.920
this?

03:10:25.979 --> 03:10:29.040
He guessed most of them would choose the

03:10:29.040 --> 03:10:31.319
tunnel if they could, rather than risk

03:10:31.319 --> 03:10:32.340
this exhausting flight.

03:10:32.399 --> 03:10:35.579
Marasier allowed them to rest for a short

03:10:35.579 --> 03:10:35.879
while.

03:10:35.940 --> 03:10:36.840
He didn't speak.

03:10:36.899 --> 03:10:40.379
His dark eyes glowered at all of them, and

03:10:40.379 --> 03:10:42.059
occasionally he glanced back in the

03:10:42.059 --> 03:10:43.319
direction of the volcano.

03:10:43.379 --> 03:10:46.139
All too soon, he gathered himself and

03:10:46.139 --> 03:10:48.180
said, let's go.

03:10:48.299 --> 03:10:50.579
And then they were all flying once

03:10:50.579 --> 03:10:51.000
again.

03:10:51.059 --> 03:10:56.100
Rain, thunder, aching wings, raindrops

03:10:56.100 --> 03:10:58.620
filled Starflight's eyes, lightning

03:10:58.620 --> 03:11:00.180
blazed too close to his tail.

03:11:00.239 --> 03:11:03.299
Off to his left, squid was complaining

03:11:03.299 --> 03:11:05.520
loudly, but no one could hear him over

03:11:05.520 --> 03:11:07.920
the storm, or else no one had any energy

03:11:07.920 --> 03:11:08.639
to respond.

03:11:08.700 --> 03:11:11.100
Starflight was starting to think that

03:11:11.100 --> 03:11:12.899
drowning wouldn't be such a bad way to go

03:11:12.899 --> 03:11:15.719
after all, when he saw Mario Seer tilt

03:11:15.719 --> 03:11:17.819
his wings and begin sailing downward.

03:11:17.879 --> 03:11:20.040
Land had appeared in front of them quite

03:11:20.040 --> 03:11:20.520
suddenly.

03:11:20.520 --> 03:11:22.920
Starflight hadn't been able to see it

03:11:22.920 --> 03:11:24.059
through the clouds and rain.

03:11:24.120 --> 03:11:26.639
Now I saw a coast lined with jagged

03:11:26.639 --> 03:11:29.760
cliffs, steep and rocky and plunging

03:11:29.760 --> 03:11:30.540
straight into the sea.

03:11:30.600 --> 03:11:33.780
Behind them jetted sharp peaks like

03:11:33.780 --> 03:11:36.120
dragons' teeth, some of them tipped with

03:11:36.120 --> 03:11:38.520
snow, extending in a relentless line

03:11:38.520 --> 03:11:39.540
across the horizon.

03:11:39.600 --> 03:11:42.659
The claws of the clouds mountains.

03:11:42.719 --> 03:11:44.639
His heart sank.

03:11:44.700 --> 03:11:46.739
He'd hoped they were near the southern

03:11:46.739 --> 03:11:49.559
coast and the rainforest, but this had to

03:11:49.559 --> 03:11:52.379
be Pyria's northern edge, where the sky

03:11:52.379 --> 03:11:54.600
wings rolled, too close to Queen

03:11:54.600 --> 03:11:57.540
Scarlet's palace, too far for him to fly

03:11:57.540 --> 03:11:58.440
back to his friends.

03:11:58.500 --> 03:12:01.620
It would take days, and he'd have to

03:12:01.620 --> 03:12:03.899
travel alone through the Sky Kingdom and

03:12:03.899 --> 03:12:04.620
the Mud Kingdom.

03:12:04.680 --> 03:12:06.659
I'm sorry, Sonny.

03:12:06.780 --> 03:12:08.159
I can't do it.

03:12:08.219 --> 03:12:10.260
I can't find my way back to you.

03:12:10.319 --> 03:12:14.399
His wings felt like glaciers, slow and

03:12:14.399 --> 03:12:17.100
heavy, and dragging him down, as he

03:12:17.100 --> 03:12:18.959
followed Marosir and the others to the

03:12:18.959 --> 03:12:20.520
cliff top in the driving rain.

03:12:20.579 --> 03:12:23.639
Bare rocks scraped beneath his claws when

03:12:23.639 --> 03:12:26.159
he landed, and he bent forward, gasping

03:12:26.159 --> 03:12:26.760
for breath.

03:12:26.940 --> 03:12:29.819
Squid sprawled out flat on his back

03:12:29.819 --> 03:12:33.000
groaning with pain, and Ogre immediately

03:12:33.000 --> 03:12:35.280
began sniffing the rocks, as if he were

03:12:35.280 --> 03:12:36.659
hoping to startle out some prey.

03:12:36.719 --> 03:12:39.479
Flame was the only dragonette who wasn't

03:12:39.479 --> 03:12:40.079
breathing heavily.

03:12:40.139 --> 03:12:43.319
Starflight looked up and caught Maro Seer

03:12:43.319 --> 03:12:44.700
studying the sea behind them again.

03:12:44.760 --> 03:12:47.340
He had a weird flash of intuition that

03:12:47.340 --> 03:12:47.879
made no sense.

03:12:47.940 --> 03:12:51.540
Is someone following us?

03:12:51.600 --> 03:12:53.399
he asked Maru Seer.

03:12:53.459 --> 03:12:55.979
That's none of your concern.

03:12:56.100 --> 03:12:58.079
Maro Seer answered.

03:12:58.139 --> 03:13:00.180
He spread his wings and pointed down the

03:13:00.180 --> 03:13:00.659
coast.

03:13:00.659 --> 03:13:03.420
Through the storm, Starfly could barely

03:13:03.420 --> 03:13:05.340
see the glow of firelight coming from a

03:13:05.340 --> 03:13:06.239
cave in the cliffside.

03:13:06.299 --> 03:13:08.100
What is it?

03:13:08.159 --> 03:13:09.719
Fate speaker asked.

03:13:09.780 --> 03:13:13.920
The most remote outpost of the Sky Wing

03:13:13.920 --> 03:13:15.959
army, said Marisir.

03:13:16.079 --> 03:13:19.260
Their assignment is to guard against

03:13:19.260 --> 03:13:21.959
attacks from the north, in case Queen

03:13:21.959 --> 03:13:24.600
Glacier ever decides to try this approach

03:13:24.600 --> 03:13:25.139
to the palace.

03:13:25.200 --> 03:13:28.620
There are no other dragons for miles.

03:13:28.680 --> 03:13:31.319
This is your test.

03:13:31.440 --> 03:13:34.979
They all stared at him, uncomprehending.

03:13:35.040 --> 03:13:39.000
What is, Starflight finally asked, the

03:13:39.000 --> 03:13:40.260
wind ripped his voice away.

03:13:40.319 --> 03:13:44.459
You want us to kill them, Viper guessed.

03:13:44.520 --> 03:13:47.040
She arched her poisonous tail and flexed

03:13:47.040 --> 03:13:47.760
her claws.

03:13:47.819 --> 03:13:48.840
All of them?

03:13:48.959 --> 03:13:52.559
I don't want to, Squid whined.

03:13:52.620 --> 03:13:54.059
What if someone bites me?

03:13:54.180 --> 03:13:58.739
Shut up, or I'll bite you, Flame said.

03:13:58.799 --> 03:14:01.680
He looked deeply rattled, as if he'd

03:14:01.680 --> 03:14:03.120
never expected to be asked to kill

03:14:03.120 --> 03:14:04.139
members of his own tribe.

03:14:04.200 --> 03:14:06.959
Starflight wondered suddenly where all

03:14:06.959 --> 03:14:09.000
their parents were, and whether these

03:14:09.000 --> 03:14:11.280
dragonettes dreamed of home and family

03:14:11.280 --> 03:14:12.600
the way his friends had.

03:14:12.659 --> 03:14:18.299
No, you're not here to kill them, Marosier

03:14:18.299 --> 03:14:18.659
snapped.

03:14:18.719 --> 03:14:20.579
You're the dragonettes of the great

03:14:20.579 --> 03:14:21.719
prophecy, remember.

03:14:21.780 --> 03:14:24.719
Your test is to act like it.

03:14:24.780 --> 03:14:27.180
He pointed to the outpost.

03:14:27.239 --> 03:14:28.739
Go in there.

03:14:28.799 --> 03:14:32.100
Tell the guards that you are the real

03:14:32.100 --> 03:14:35.760
prophesied dragonettes, and convince them

03:14:35.760 --> 03:14:38.399
to switch their alliance from burn to

03:14:38.399 --> 03:14:38.879
blister.

03:14:38.940 --> 03:14:42.780
In the shocked silence that followed, a

03:14:42.780 --> 03:14:45.659
hurricane forest wind came howling up and

03:14:45.659 --> 03:14:47.340
tried to throw them all off the cliff.

03:14:47.459 --> 03:14:50.399
Starflight dug in his talons and made

03:14:50.399 --> 03:14:51.600
himself as small as he could.

03:14:51.659 --> 03:14:55.200
Just convince them?

03:14:55.319 --> 03:14:58.559
Piper shouted at Maru's ear, raindrops

03:14:58.559 --> 03:14:59.700
flying as she shook her head.

03:14:59.760 --> 03:15:02.280
A bunch of strange sky wings?

03:15:02.399 --> 03:15:04.739
So instead of killing them, we're going

03:15:04.739 --> 03:15:05.879
to ask them to kill us.

03:15:05.940 --> 03:15:09.659
I foresee that this is going to go really

03:15:09.659 --> 03:15:10.500
really badly.

03:15:10.559 --> 03:15:13.079
Fate speaker yelled over the wind.

03:15:13.139 --> 03:15:16.139
Me too, cried Ogre.

03:15:16.200 --> 03:15:19.020
Maybe I have special night wing powers

03:15:19.020 --> 03:15:19.379
too.

03:15:19.440 --> 03:15:23.520
They're going to kill me, Squid shouted.

03:15:23.579 --> 03:15:25.500
Sea Wings and Sky Wings are enemies.

03:15:25.559 --> 03:15:27.719
If you send me in there, I'm dead.

03:15:27.780 --> 03:15:31.500
Morrisier's expression suggested that he

03:15:31.500 --> 03:15:33.059
wouldn't be terribly devastated by that.

03:15:33.120 --> 03:15:38.159
If you can't survive this, he rumbled.

03:15:38.219 --> 03:15:40.799
And you're useless for the prophecy

03:15:40.799 --> 03:15:41.159
anyway.

03:15:41.219 --> 03:15:43.620
He pointed at fate's speaker.

03:15:43.680 --> 03:15:45.059
You stay here.

03:15:45.120 --> 03:15:49.139
Well, see how well that one does, this

03:15:49.139 --> 03:15:49.500
time.

03:15:49.559 --> 03:15:52.200
He flicked a claw at Starflight.

03:15:52.260 --> 03:15:54.360
Starflight wanted to melt into the

03:15:54.360 --> 03:15:54.719
rocks.

03:15:54.780 --> 03:15:57.059
He wanted to leap off the cliff into the

03:15:57.059 --> 03:15:57.360
sea.

03:15:57.420 --> 03:15:59.819
He wondered how far he would get if he

03:15:59.819 --> 03:16:01.979
bolted for the mountains right now.

03:16:02.040 --> 03:16:03.899
With a journey to the rainforest to be

03:16:03.899 --> 03:16:06.420
any worse, then walking into a sky wing

03:16:06.420 --> 03:16:08.819
guardhouse and announcing himself as one

03:16:08.819 --> 03:16:11.100
of the dragonettes Queen Scarlet had lost

03:16:11.100 --> 03:16:11.940
not long ago.

03:16:12.000 --> 03:16:15.180
Won't they just take us prisoner?

03:16:15.239 --> 03:16:18.059
he asked Morrow Seer, and take us back to

03:16:18.059 --> 03:16:18.959
the Sky Palace?

03:16:19.020 --> 03:16:23.340
Oh, if you're convincing enough, Maris

03:16:23.340 --> 03:16:25.200
here said, bearing his teeth.

03:16:25.260 --> 03:16:26.879
Now go.

03:16:26.940 --> 03:16:30.180
He shot a blast of fire at squid, who

03:16:30.180 --> 03:16:31.920
barely leaped out of the way in time.

03:16:31.979 --> 03:16:36.239
I don't want to, Squid complained again.

03:16:36.299 --> 03:16:38.459
But Viper and Flame were already shoving

03:16:38.459 --> 03:16:38.879
him forward.

03:16:38.940 --> 03:16:42.000
Oker trailed after them, and Starflight

03:16:42.000 --> 03:16:43.379
reluctantly brought up the rear.

03:16:43.440 --> 03:16:46.739
He glanced back once, and saw fate

03:16:46.739 --> 03:16:49.260
speaker huddled into her wings, a small

03:16:49.260 --> 03:16:51.840
drenched shape beside the vast bulk of

03:16:51.840 --> 03:16:52.500
Marosir.

03:16:52.559 --> 03:16:54.959
He hoped his friends would welcome her as

03:16:54.959 --> 03:16:56.399
the new night wing when he was gone.

03:16:56.459 --> 03:16:58.860
I'm about to die.

03:16:58.920 --> 03:17:00.120
He thought.

03:17:00.180 --> 03:17:02.579
And I never got to tell Sonny I love

03:17:02.579 --> 03:17:02.819
her.

03:17:02.879 --> 03:17:05.340
I'm going to die without saving the

03:17:05.340 --> 03:17:05.700
world.

03:17:05.700 --> 03:17:09.120
Without stopping the war, without ever

03:17:09.120 --> 03:17:11.159
doing one brave thing in my life.
5504
03:17:11,219 --> 03:17:15,479	Chapter 12.

03:17:15.840 --> 03:17:19.079
As they approached the firelight

03:17:19.079 --> 03:17:21.059
Starflight's dread grew heavier and

03:17:21.059 --> 03:17:21.479
heavier.

03:17:21.540 --> 03:17:25.139
Loud dragon voices spilled from the cave

03:17:25.139 --> 03:17:27.540
along with a column of smoke that rose

03:17:27.540 --> 03:17:28.979
from a hole in the stone wall.

03:17:29.040 --> 03:17:31.500
What if someone's on watch?

03:17:31.559 --> 03:17:34.139
Starflight whispered when they were a few

03:17:34.139 --> 03:17:34.680
lengths away.

03:17:34.739 --> 03:17:36.420
They all froze.

03:17:36.479 --> 03:17:39.180
Starflight searched the darkness around

03:17:39.180 --> 03:17:41.459
them with his eyes, trying to move as

03:17:41.459 --> 03:17:42.239
little as possible.

03:17:42.299 --> 03:17:45.659
Lightning flashed, and Starflight's heart

03:17:45.659 --> 03:17:46.139
seized up.

03:17:46.200 --> 03:17:49.260
Perched on a cliff top above them, was a

03:17:49.260 --> 03:17:51.600
dragon with enormous wings staring out to

03:17:51.600 --> 03:17:51.780
sea.

03:17:51.840 --> 03:17:54.659
There, he whispered.

03:17:54.719 --> 03:17:56.399
Surely he could see them.

03:17:56.459 --> 03:17:58.440
Why hadn't he called out to warn the

03:17:58.440 --> 03:17:59.100
other soldiers yet?

03:17:59.219 --> 03:18:03.000
Starflight squinted at the shape, at the

03:18:03.000 --> 03:18:04.979
rise and fall of its shoulders and the

03:18:04.979 --> 03:18:07.620
curve of its neck, and it realized that

03:18:07.620 --> 03:18:08.819
the guard was asleep.

03:18:08.879 --> 03:18:11.340
Despite the rain pouring down on him

03:18:11.340 --> 03:18:14.159
despite the booming thunder, despite his

03:18:14.159 --> 03:18:15.659
whole job being to stay awake.

03:18:15.659 --> 03:18:19.020
We're all right, he whispered to the

03:18:19.020 --> 03:18:19.260
others.

03:18:19.319 --> 03:18:22.620
They crept toward the cave, staying

03:18:22.620 --> 03:18:24.959
closer to the shadows now, a wooden door

03:18:24.959 --> 03:18:25.860
blocked the entrance.

03:18:25.920 --> 03:18:28.680
Wait, Starflight whispered.

03:18:28.739 --> 03:18:31.620
Flame paused with his front talons raised

03:18:31.620 --> 03:18:32.040
to knock.

03:18:32.100 --> 03:18:33.899
He frowned at Starflight.

03:18:33.959 --> 03:18:37.319
Let's be smart about this, Starflight

03:18:37.319 --> 03:18:37.620
said.

03:18:37.680 --> 03:18:39.840
We don't have to charge right in.

03:18:39.899 --> 03:18:42.780
Let's listen for a minute and see if we

03:18:42.780 --> 03:18:43.979
hear anything that might be useful.

03:18:44.040 --> 03:18:46.440
Fine by me.

03:18:46.500 --> 03:18:48.239
Okre said with a shrug.

03:18:48.299 --> 03:18:50.399
But it's wet out here.

03:18:50.520 --> 03:18:51.959
Squid grumbled.

03:18:52.020 --> 03:18:54.780
Flame and Viper exchanged glances.

03:18:54.840 --> 03:18:57.479
And then, to Starflight's surprise, they

03:18:57.479 --> 03:18:58.260
both nodded.

03:18:58.319 --> 03:19:00.719
Perhaps fear made them more agreeable.

03:19:00.780 --> 03:19:02.940
The 2 of them put their ears up to the

03:19:02.940 --> 03:19:05.159
wooden door, so he crept along the wall

03:19:05.159 --> 03:19:07.020
and crouched below the smoke hole.

03:19:07.079 --> 03:19:09.360
He tried to arrange his wings in a way

03:19:09.360 --> 03:19:10.739
that would shield him at least a little

03:19:10.739 --> 03:19:11.399
bit from the rain.

03:19:11.459 --> 03:19:14.219
There seemed to be several arguments

03:19:14.219 --> 03:19:14.819
going on inside.

03:19:14.879 --> 03:19:17.700
Starflight could only catch snatches of

03:19:17.700 --> 03:19:19.020
one that seemed to be closest to the

03:19:19.020 --> 03:19:19.260
fire.

03:19:19.319 --> 03:19:22.680
Your queen, Ruby, says we can return to

03:19:22.680 --> 03:19:24.479
the palace, you better believe I'm going

03:19:24.479 --> 03:19:26.639
home. growled one dragon.

03:19:26.700 --> 03:19:29.579
You'd be obeying the orders of a false

03:19:29.579 --> 03:19:31.139
queen, snarled another.

03:19:31.260 --> 03:19:33.899
Queen Scarlet is still alive, and she'll

03:19:33.899 --> 03:19:35.280
have us all killed if we abandon our

03:19:35.280 --> 03:19:35.579
posts.

03:19:35.700 --> 03:19:37.979
Then where is she?

03:19:38.040 --> 03:19:39.899
Challenged a 3rd voice.

03:19:39.959 --> 03:19:42.299
What kind of queen leaves her kingdom in

03:19:42.299 --> 03:19:43.139
chaos like this?

03:19:43.200 --> 03:19:45.659
It's not chaos.

03:19:45.719 --> 03:19:48.959
We have Ruby now, said the 1st voice, and

03:19:48.959 --> 03:19:50.159
she says we can leave.

03:19:50.280 --> 03:19:54.239
But Queen Byrne says we shouldn't, said

03:19:54.239 --> 03:19:54.899
another dragon.

03:19:54.959 --> 03:19:58.440
She's not our queen, snapped more than

03:19:58.440 --> 03:19:58.860
one voice.

03:19:58.920 --> 03:20:00.659
That's enough.

03:20:00.719 --> 03:20:02.639
No one's going anywhere today.

03:20:02.700 --> 03:20:05.579
Boomed someone authoritative sounding.

03:20:05.639 --> 03:20:07.739
The hubbub of voice is stilled.

03:20:07.799 --> 03:20:09.059
Not in this storm.

03:20:09.120 --> 03:20:10.620
We'll discuss it again tomorrow.

03:20:10.680 --> 03:20:14.280
After a moment, a murmur of grumbling and

03:20:14.280 --> 03:20:15.959
muttering started, but nothing that

03:20:15.959 --> 03:20:16.920
Starflight could pick out.

03:20:16.979 --> 03:20:19.379
He crept back to Flame and Viper.

03:20:19.500 --> 03:20:21.180
Useless.

03:20:21.239 --> 03:20:22.440
Flame hissed.

03:20:22.559 --> 03:20:25.440
Perhaps not, Starflight said.

03:20:25.500 --> 03:20:27.420
Did you hear how some of them are

03:20:27.420 --> 03:20:28.620
dissatisfied with burn?

03:20:28.680 --> 03:20:30.180
We can press that, I think.

03:20:30.299 --> 03:20:33.000
If she's trying to act like she's their

03:20:33.000 --> 03:20:33.600
new queen.

03:20:33.659 --> 03:20:36.059
I bet a whole lot of Skywings would be

03:20:36.059 --> 03:20:37.500
willing to reconsider their alliance.

03:20:37.559 --> 03:20:42.360
Fancy talk, said Viper, flicking our tail

03:20:42.360 --> 03:20:42.719
at him.

03:20:42.780 --> 03:20:44.940
Now let's see you actually do it.

03:20:45.000 --> 03:20:48.000
She shoved squid away from the shadow of

03:20:48.000 --> 03:20:49.500
her wings, where he was trying to

03:20:49.500 --> 03:20:50.040
huddle.

03:20:50.100 --> 03:20:52.379
Flame wrapped on the door before

03:20:52.379 --> 03:20:54.360
Starflight could think of another way to

03:20:54.360 --> 03:20:54.719
delay.

03:20:54.780 --> 03:20:58.200
All the noise inside abruptly stopped.

03:20:58.260 --> 03:21:01.079
Stamping feet approached the door, and it

03:21:01.079 --> 03:21:02.040
was flung wide open.

03:21:02.159 --> 03:21:05.459
Starflight found himself facing a room

03:21:05.459 --> 03:21:06.659
full of sky wings.

03:21:06.719 --> 03:21:09.479
Most of them were clumped in small groups

03:21:09.479 --> 03:21:12.600
eating, or rolling prey bones in games of

03:21:12.600 --> 03:21:13.020
luck.

03:21:13.079 --> 03:21:16.379
Red, orange, and gold scales gleamed in

03:21:16.379 --> 03:21:16.979
the firelight.

03:21:17.040 --> 03:21:19.860
Savage looking spears, leaned casually

03:21:19.860 --> 03:21:22.139
against the wall, and a map next to the

03:21:22.139 --> 03:21:24.479
fireplace showed the continent of Pyrea

03:21:24.479 --> 03:21:26.700
with an X where the outpost was located

03:21:26.700 --> 03:21:29.280
and arrows showing possible attack routes

03:21:29.280 --> 03:21:30.059
from the ice kingdom.

03:21:30.120 --> 03:21:32.819
What in the?

03:21:32.819 --> 03:21:34.860
said the guard who'd answered the door.

03:21:34.920 --> 03:21:36.780
He trailed off, staring at them.

03:21:36.840 --> 03:21:38.040
The whole room.

03:21:38.100 --> 03:21:40.979
About 17 dragons, Starflight estimated

03:21:40.979 --> 03:21:42.239
turned to stare as well.

03:21:42.360 --> 03:21:45.059
Starflike could easily imagine how they

03:21:45.059 --> 03:21:45.479
looked.

03:21:45.540 --> 03:21:49.260
Five bedraggled dragonettes, soaking wet

03:21:49.260 --> 03:21:51.840
and exhausted, in 5 different colors that

03:21:51.840 --> 03:21:53.219
were normally not seen together.

03:21:53.280 --> 03:21:55.920
One of the sky wings inhaled sharply.

03:21:55.979 --> 03:21:58.739
It's them, he hissed.

03:21:58.799 --> 03:22:01.440
It can't be, said another.

03:22:01.500 --> 03:22:04.680
For some reason, Flame, Viper, and Oak

03:22:04.680 --> 03:22:07.139
are all glanced at Starflight, but his

03:22:07.139 --> 03:22:08.940
power of speech had abandoned him.

03:22:09.000 --> 03:22:11.219
All he could think about was the cold

03:22:11.219 --> 03:22:13.799
spire where he'd been imprisoned by Sky

03:22:13.799 --> 03:22:16.680
Wing Guards, just like these, only a

03:22:16.680 --> 03:22:17.579
short time before.

03:22:17.579 --> 03:22:19.979
He wanted to cower behind the other's

03:22:19.979 --> 03:22:22.139
wings the way Squid was doing.

03:22:22.200 --> 03:22:24.899
Flame let out a small snort of fire, and

03:22:24.899 --> 03:22:26.639
drew himself up as tall as he could get.

03:22:26.700 --> 03:22:29.280
It is us, he said.

03:22:29.340 --> 03:22:30.659
From the prophecy.

03:22:30.780 --> 03:22:35.159
The dragonettes of destiny, said one

03:22:35.159 --> 03:22:38.760
soldier, in an awe struck voice, wow.

03:22:38.819 --> 03:22:41.399
Dragons actually call us that?

03:22:41.459 --> 03:22:42.420
Viper said.

03:22:42.479 --> 03:22:43.559
Lame.

03:22:43.620 --> 03:22:45.959
I hereby forbid anyone to use that phrase

03:22:45.959 --> 03:22:46.260
again.

03:22:46.319 --> 03:22:49.920
Is that a roasted seagull?

03:22:49.979 --> 03:22:51.239
Ocher asked?

03:22:51.299 --> 03:22:53.520
Shoving his way forward and pointing at a

03:22:53.520 --> 03:22:55.020
half eaten carcass on one of the tables?

03:22:55.079 --> 03:22:57.959
Is anyone going to finish that?

03:22:58.079 --> 03:23:00.840
Without waiting for an answer, he

03:23:00.840 --> 03:23:02.760
snatched the bird and sank his teeth into

03:23:02.760 --> 03:23:02.940
it.

03:23:03.000 --> 03:23:06.479
Behind Starflight, Squid let out a small

03:23:06.479 --> 03:23:07.020
whimper.

03:23:07.139 --> 03:23:10.620
A few of the sky wings exchanged glances

03:23:10.620 --> 03:23:12.600
looking a little more skeptical than they

03:23:12.600 --> 03:23:14.879
had a moment ago, Starflight could feel

03:23:14.879 --> 03:23:17.219
panic rising in his chest, he had to

03:23:17.219 --> 03:23:17.579
speak up.

03:23:17.639 --> 03:23:20.819
He had to be convincing, but his jaw felt

03:23:20.819 --> 03:23:21.840
like it was welded shut.

03:23:21.899 --> 03:23:24.479
Why are you here?

03:23:24.600 --> 03:23:26.340
asked one of the soldiers.

03:23:26.399 --> 03:23:29.639
After you escaped, why come back?

03:23:29.700 --> 03:23:31.440
To hear of all places.

03:23:31.500 --> 03:23:34.739
And what did you do to the sea wings?

03:23:34.799 --> 03:23:36.000
asked another.

03:23:36.059 --> 03:23:39.420
No attacks, no raids, no sign of them

03:23:39.420 --> 03:23:41.040
since we destroyed their summer palace.

03:23:41.100 --> 03:23:43.620
We know plenty of them must have survived

03:23:43.620 --> 03:23:45.540
so where's the counterattack?

03:23:45.600 --> 03:23:48.899
Do you have Queen Scarlet?

03:23:48.959 --> 03:23:51.239
demanded a dragon leaning on the wall by

03:23:51.239 --> 03:23:51.659
the fire.

03:23:51.719 --> 03:23:53.459
What have you done with her?

03:23:53.579 --> 03:23:57.299
Flame waved his front talons, as if none

03:23:57.299 --> 03:23:58.440
of these questions were important.

03:23:58.500 --> 03:24:02.040
We're here to tell you, you're supporting

03:24:02.040 --> 03:24:02.940
the wrong sand wing.

03:24:03.000 --> 03:24:05.399
He tilted his head arrogantly.

03:24:05.459 --> 03:24:08.819
Burn isn't going to be queen, like the

03:24:08.819 --> 03:24:10.799
prophecy says, she's going to die.

03:24:10.860 --> 03:24:12.659
We've chosen blister.

03:24:12.780 --> 03:24:15.719
The uproar was immediate.

03:24:15.780 --> 03:24:18.239
Several dragons sprang to their feet

03:24:18.239 --> 03:24:20.579
knocking over tables and scattering bones

03:24:20.579 --> 03:24:21.540
and ashes everywhere.

03:24:21.600 --> 03:24:24.059
How dare you?

03:24:24.120 --> 03:24:25.319
somebody shouted.

03:24:25.379 --> 03:24:27.840
We're not taking orders from some puny

03:24:27.840 --> 03:24:28.680
dragonettes.

03:24:28.739 --> 03:24:30.959
We'll never let the sea wings win.

03:24:31.020 --> 03:24:33.899
One of the guards shoved flame in the

03:24:33.899 --> 03:24:34.379
chest.

03:24:34.440 --> 03:24:35.760
Traitor.

03:24:35.819 --> 03:24:39.059
The red dragonette stumbled back, stepping

03:24:39.059 --> 03:24:40.620
on Starfly's claws.

03:24:40.680 --> 03:24:44.579
Blister killed my brother, roared another

03:24:44.579 --> 03:24:44.940
soldier.

03:24:45.000 --> 03:24:46.799
She will never be queen.

03:24:46.920 --> 03:24:49.200
Her fate is to die beneath my talent.

03:24:49.319 --> 03:24:52.500
We're the dragons from the prophecy.

03:24:52.559 --> 03:24:54.299
Viper yelled over the din.

03:24:54.420 --> 03:24:55.920
You have to listen to us.

03:24:55.979 --> 03:24:57.899
No, you're not.

03:24:57.959 --> 03:25:00.299
Said the same authoritative voice

03:25:00.299 --> 03:25:02.100
Starflight had heard from outside.

03:25:02.159 --> 03:25:05.040
An orange dragon with a long, scarred

03:25:05.040 --> 03:25:07.799
neck stepped forward, peering intently at

03:25:07.799 --> 03:25:08.579
the dragonettes.

03:25:08.639 --> 03:25:11.100
Starflight had a feeling he'd seen the

03:25:11.100 --> 03:25:13.500
sky wing before, probably in the queen's

03:25:13.500 --> 03:25:13.979
palace.

03:25:14.040 --> 03:25:17.879
The other Skywings quieted as the soldier

03:25:17.879 --> 03:25:20.639
reached around Starflight, seized Squid's

03:25:20.639 --> 03:25:22.379
ear, and dragged him into the middle of

03:25:22.379 --> 03:25:22.739
the room.

03:25:22.799 --> 03:25:25.920
Squid yelped with pain, flung his wings

03:25:25.920 --> 03:25:28.559
over his head, and sat down, gibbering.

03:25:28.680 --> 03:25:32.760
That is not the sea wing we captured

03:25:32.760 --> 03:25:35.040
before. said the orange dragon

03:25:35.040 --> 03:25:35.879
contemptuously.

03:25:35.940 --> 03:25:38.579
You saw the marks she left on the guards

03:25:38.579 --> 03:25:41.399
she fought with, and I do mean she.

03:25:41.459 --> 03:25:44.760
Also, she was blue.

03:25:44.819 --> 03:25:48.180
This sniveling creature is no dragonette

03:25:48.180 --> 03:25:48.899
of destiny.

03:25:48.959 --> 03:25:51.719
He looked around at the others, his eyes

03:25:51.719 --> 03:25:53.100
gleaming with suspicion.

03:25:53.159 --> 03:25:54.719
I say we kill him.

03:25:54.780 --> 03:25:57.299
Perhaps we kill them all.

03:25:57.360 --> 03:26:00.420
No, Starflight blurted.

03:26:00.479 --> 03:26:02.760
I am the knight wing the queen held

03:26:02.760 --> 03:26:03.360
prisoner.

03:26:03.420 --> 03:26:04.559
I swear I am.

03:26:04.620 --> 03:26:07.260
Remember, she had me fight scavengers.

03:26:07.319 --> 03:26:09.180
And then the other night wings came and

03:26:09.180 --> 03:26:09.479
took me.

03:26:09.600 --> 03:26:11.100
He held his breath.

03:26:11.159 --> 03:26:13.079
Please believe me.

03:26:13.139 --> 03:26:16.440
The dragon breathed a plume of smell at

03:26:16.440 --> 03:26:19.079
him, then narrowed his eyes at ocher, who

03:26:19.079 --> 03:26:21.059
had moved on to gnawing on a large leg

03:26:21.059 --> 03:26:22.200
bone he'd found on the floor.

03:26:22.260 --> 03:26:26.940
I suppose that could be the mud wing, he

03:26:26.940 --> 03:26:27.360
muttered.

03:26:27.420 --> 03:26:30.540
And we never saw the sand wing or the sky

03:26:30.540 --> 03:26:30.959
wing.

03:26:31.079 --> 03:26:33.420
He studied Flame and Viper.

03:26:33.479 --> 03:26:35.879
We assumed the queen was holding them

03:26:35.879 --> 03:26:38.040
elsewhere in the palace in case they

03:26:38.040 --> 03:26:39.780
could be fixed and allowed to rejoin us.

03:26:39.840 --> 03:26:42.360
His gaze stopped on flame.

03:26:42.420 --> 03:26:45.899
But perhaps, living with the talons of

03:26:45.899 --> 03:26:48.719
peace will ruin any dragon, even from the

03:26:48.719 --> 03:26:49.620
best of tribes.

03:26:49.739 --> 03:26:54.059
He jabbed squid sharply with his tail, and

03:26:54.059 --> 03:26:56.219
the small green dragon moaned unhappily.

03:26:56.280 --> 03:26:59.219
If you are the night wing from the palace

03:26:59.219 --> 03:27:00.959
he said to Starflight.

03:27:01.020 --> 03:27:03.420
What happened to the sea wing who was

03:27:03.420 --> 03:27:03.899
with you before?

03:27:03.959 --> 03:27:06.659
She's...

03:27:06.659 --> 03:27:08.940
Starflight felt hopelessly stupid.

03:27:09.000 --> 03:27:11.459
Why hadn't Moros here guessed this might

03:27:11.459 --> 03:27:11.760
happen?

03:27:11.879 --> 03:27:14.280
Did he think this outpost was so remote

03:27:14.280 --> 03:27:16.319
that no one from the palace would be

03:27:16.319 --> 03:27:16.500
here?

03:27:16.559 --> 03:27:18.899
But if he really wanted to replace

03:27:18.899 --> 03:27:21.420
tsunami with squid, he had to know

03:27:21.420 --> 03:27:24.180
someone would notice and object sooner or

03:27:24.180 --> 03:27:24.360
later.

03:27:24.479 --> 03:27:27.540
He knew he should act like Squid was the

03:27:27.540 --> 03:27:28.920
real prophecy dragonette.

03:27:29.040 --> 03:27:30.899
Especially if they all wanted to get out

03:27:30.899 --> 03:27:33.360
of this cave alive, but he couldn't bring

03:27:33.360 --> 03:27:36.239
himself to betray tsunami, who, if you

03:27:36.239 --> 03:27:39.120
asked him, in all of Pireo was the dragon

03:27:39.120 --> 03:27:41.159
most likely to fulfill a prophecy and

03:27:41.159 --> 03:27:41.520
save the world.

03:27:41.639 --> 03:27:44.700
He braced himself and looked the orange

03:27:44.700 --> 03:27:45.540
dragon in the eye.

03:27:45.600 --> 03:27:47.819
She's gathering an army.

03:27:47.879 --> 03:27:49.620
This was true.

03:27:49.680 --> 03:27:52.500
No need to mention that it was an army of

03:27:52.500 --> 03:27:53.100
rain wings.

03:27:53.159 --> 03:27:55.260
We're going to end this war.

03:27:55.319 --> 03:27:57.959
He turned to the other sky wings in the

03:27:57.959 --> 03:27:58.319
cave.

03:27:58.379 --> 03:28:01.079
Soon you'll be able to go home to your

03:28:01.079 --> 03:28:01.620
families.

03:28:01.680 --> 03:28:03.659
Soon you will all be safe.

03:28:03.719 --> 03:28:05.280
Soon there will be peace.

03:28:05.399 --> 03:28:08.280
He caught a look of longing on some of

03:28:08.280 --> 03:28:08.879
their faces.

03:28:08.940 --> 03:28:12.000
Even the fierce, bad tempered, sky wing

03:28:12.000 --> 03:28:13.379
tribe wanted a chance to live

03:28:13.379 --> 03:28:14.040
peacefully.

03:28:14.100 --> 03:28:15.420
He was sure of it.

03:28:15.479 --> 03:28:17.520
Was that a prophecy?

03:28:17.579 --> 03:28:19.739
One of the soldiers whispered to

03:28:19.739 --> 03:28:19.979
another.

03:28:20.040 --> 03:28:21.899
Starflight shook his head.

03:28:21.959 --> 03:28:25.079
It was a promise, he said.

03:28:25.139 --> 03:28:27.719
Viper let out a muffled, impatient

03:28:27.719 --> 03:28:28.200
snort.

03:28:28.319 --> 03:28:31.319
Starflight knew even his real friends got

03:28:31.319 --> 03:28:33.479
fed up with a way he sounded like an epic

03:28:33.479 --> 03:28:35.579
scroll sometimes, but he couldn't help

03:28:35.579 --> 03:28:35.760
it.

03:28:35.819 --> 03:28:37.979
When he thought about prophecies and

03:28:37.979 --> 03:28:39.000
acting like a hero.

03:28:39.059 --> 03:28:40.620
That's how he thought they should all

03:28:40.620 --> 03:28:40.920
sound.

03:28:40.979 --> 03:28:43.620
But what about blister?

03:28:43.739 --> 03:28:45.540
asked the orange dragon.

03:28:45.600 --> 03:28:47.159
Have you really chosen her?

03:28:47.219 --> 03:28:50.100
Is she the next sandwing queen?

03:28:50.159 --> 03:28:53.459
Several of the Skywings hissed, rattling

03:28:53.459 --> 03:28:54.000
their wings.

03:28:54.059 --> 03:28:58.020
Flame and viper and squid, and even ogre

03:28:58.020 --> 03:28:59.340
were watching Starflight now.

03:28:59.399 --> 03:29:01.620
He could guess that they were willing him

03:29:01.620 --> 03:29:03.840
to say the right thing here, to convince

03:29:03.840 --> 03:29:05.819
everyone that blister was the choice of

03:29:05.819 --> 03:29:08.700
destiny, that she was going to win, and

03:29:08.700 --> 03:29:09.899
nobody could do anything about it.

03:29:09.959 --> 03:29:13.260
But he remembered blisters menacing

03:29:13.260 --> 03:29:15.659
stillness, and the glint of evil in her

03:29:15.659 --> 03:29:16.079
eyes.

03:29:16.139 --> 03:29:18.780
He remembered the way she manipulated the

03:29:18.780 --> 03:29:21.120
sea wing queen, and he remembered that

03:29:21.120 --> 03:29:23.340
she'd killed Kestrel and tried to kill

03:29:23.340 --> 03:29:25.500
Webbs, although there wasn't any good

03:29:25.500 --> 03:29:25.979
reason why.

03:29:26.040 --> 03:29:28.379
Oh.

03:29:28.440 --> 03:29:31.440
He glanced at the alternate dragonettes.

03:29:31.500 --> 03:29:34.500
If blister wanted to pick and choose her

03:29:34.500 --> 03:29:36.959
dragonettes of destiny, she needed the

03:29:36.959 --> 03:29:39.420
original guardians dead, so they couldn't

03:29:39.420 --> 03:29:40.739
dispute her version of history.

03:29:40.799 --> 03:29:42.600
His mind was racing.

03:29:42.719 --> 03:29:45.840
She knew about glory when we met her.

03:29:45.899 --> 03:29:49.139
She even said she had Nightwing friends.

03:29:49.200 --> 03:29:51.540
She's conspiring with them.

03:29:51.659 --> 03:29:55.319
Which meant she was almost certainly part

03:29:55.319 --> 03:29:57.180
of the plan to assassinate glory and

03:29:57.180 --> 03:29:57.959
tsunami too.

03:29:58.079 --> 03:30:00.000
He coiled his tail.

03:30:00.059 --> 03:30:03.059
He couldn't make her the next queen of

03:30:03.059 --> 03:30:03.719
the sand wings.

03:30:03.780 --> 03:30:05.879
If his voice had any power.

03:30:05.940 --> 03:30:07.440
He couldn't let her use it.

03:30:07.500 --> 03:30:12.120
No, he said, wincing as his voice

03:30:12.120 --> 03:30:12.659
cracked.

03:30:12.719 --> 03:30:15.239
He sounded like a one year old dragonette

03:30:15.239 --> 03:30:16.319
pretending to be a queen.

03:30:16.379 --> 03:30:18.840
We haven't chosen anyone yet.

03:30:18.899 --> 03:30:22.379
So choose burn, said one of the

03:30:22.379 --> 03:30:22.860
soldiers.

03:30:22.920 --> 03:30:24.420
Several others nodded.

03:30:24.479 --> 03:30:27.840
Burn is cruel, Starflight said.

03:30:27.899 --> 03:30:29.040
You know she is.

03:30:29.100 --> 03:30:30.899
She lives for war.

03:30:30.959 --> 03:30:32.520
Even if she wins.

03:30:32.579 --> 03:30:34.379
She won't stop killing and fighting.

03:30:34.440 --> 03:30:36.899
She'll probably turn on all of you and

03:30:36.899 --> 03:30:38.219
try to take your kingdom next.

03:30:38.280 --> 03:30:42.180
There was no uproar this time, only

03:30:42.180 --> 03:30:43.079
shocked silence.

03:30:43.139 --> 03:30:45.600
They may not have wanted to admit it to

03:30:45.600 --> 03:30:47.940
themselves, but what he'd said was true.

03:30:48.000 --> 03:30:51.600
Burn was not a safe ally to have, and

03:30:51.600 --> 03:30:53.639
she'd be a very dangerous queen of the

03:30:53.639 --> 03:30:54.239
sand wings.

03:30:54.299 --> 03:30:59.040
Yeah, Flame said half heartedly, what he

03:30:59.040 --> 03:30:59.340
said.

03:30:59.399 --> 03:31:03.479
So, was that a prophecy?

03:31:03.540 --> 03:31:05.459
The same soldier whispered.

03:31:05.520 --> 03:31:09.299
Let's take them back to the palace, said

03:31:09.299 --> 03:31:10.799
the orange dragon decisively.

03:31:10.860 --> 03:31:13.500
We'll turn them over to Queen Ruby and

03:31:13.500 --> 03:31:14.219
let her decide.

03:31:14.280 --> 03:31:16.020
If they know anything about Queen

03:31:16.020 --> 03:31:18.600
Scarlet's whereabouts, she'll get it out

03:31:18.600 --> 03:31:18.899
of them.

03:31:18.959 --> 03:31:20.819
He lashed his tail.

03:31:20.879 --> 03:31:24.659
No, Starflight thought, backing toward

03:31:24.659 --> 03:31:25.079
the door.

03:31:25.200 --> 03:31:27.420
Back to the Sky Wing Palace.

03:31:27.479 --> 03:31:29.219
That would be even worse than staying

03:31:29.219 --> 03:31:30.239
with the night wings.

03:31:30.239 --> 03:31:32.700
Queen Scarlet had tried to make him fight

03:31:32.700 --> 03:31:34.079
to the death in her arena.

03:31:34.139 --> 03:31:36.719
He still had nightmares about scavengers

03:31:36.719 --> 03:31:38.940
with sharp weapons climbing his neck

03:31:38.940 --> 03:31:42.059
determined to stab out his eyes, or about

03:31:42.059 --> 03:31:44.040
a horde of ice wings descending to

03:31:44.040 --> 03:31:46.680
destroy him, even though Marosir had

03:31:46.680 --> 03:31:48.180
taken him away before that happened in

03:31:48.180 --> 03:31:48.479
reality.

03:31:48.600 --> 03:31:51.120
But this wasn't a dream.

03:31:51.180 --> 03:31:53.940
The sky wind claws reaching for him were

03:31:53.940 --> 03:31:56.520
real, and his legs really were not moving

03:31:56.520 --> 03:31:58.319
and he couldn't remember a single

03:31:58.319 --> 03:31:59.940
training move that might help him fight

03:31:59.940 --> 03:32:02.459
back, and he was about to be captured and

03:32:02.459 --> 03:32:03.360
imprisoned once more.

03:32:03.479 --> 03:32:08.219
And then, the door burst open, and the

03:32:08.219 --> 03:32:10.079
night wings came blazing in.
5932
03:32:10,139 --> 03:32:14,760	Chapter 13.

03:32:14.940 --> 03:32:19.440
That who was following us, Starflight

03:32:19.440 --> 03:32:22.440
thought, with a jolt of shock, as 8 night

03:32:22.440 --> 03:32:25.079
wings came to the door, breathing flames

03:32:25.079 --> 03:32:25.860
in all directions.

03:32:25.920 --> 03:32:28.920
He saw the tables and the map catch fire

03:32:28.920 --> 03:32:30.840
and he saw flames engulf the orange

03:32:30.840 --> 03:32:33.659
dragon, and then he felt talons seize his

03:32:33.659 --> 03:32:35.399
tail, and he was dragged out the door

03:32:35.399 --> 03:32:36.899
into the pounding rain outside.

03:32:36.959 --> 03:32:41.399
Flame, viper, ochre, and squid were

03:32:41.399 --> 03:32:43.200
tossed on top of him, howling.

03:32:43.260 --> 03:32:46.079
By the time Starflight struggled free and

03:32:46.079 --> 03:32:48.120
looked up, the door of the outpost was

03:32:48.120 --> 03:32:48.659
ablaze.

03:32:48.719 --> 03:32:52.440
Inside the cave, fire raged from wall to

03:32:52.440 --> 03:32:52.860
wall.

03:32:52.920 --> 03:32:55.620
Skywings were shrieking in agony.

03:32:55.739 --> 03:32:57.959
A troop of black dragons blocked the way

03:32:57.959 --> 03:33:00.120
out, killing any soldier who tried to

03:33:00.120 --> 03:33:00.420
escape.

03:33:00.479 --> 03:33:03.420
No, Starfight yelled.

03:33:03.479 --> 03:33:06.000
I promised them, I promised them.

03:33:06.059 --> 03:33:08.399
He flung himself at the back of the

03:33:08.399 --> 03:33:10.319
nearest night wing, but the dragon

03:33:10.319 --> 03:33:11.399
shrugged him off easily.

03:33:11.459 --> 03:33:12.840
You can't kill them.

03:33:12.899 --> 03:33:15.360
Starflight hadn't wanted to be taken

03:33:15.360 --> 03:33:17.819
prisoner, but these soldiers were just

03:33:17.819 --> 03:33:20.520
ordinary dragons, following their queen

03:33:20.520 --> 03:33:21.360
and doing their jobs.

03:33:21.420 --> 03:33:23.760
They wanted peace as much as he did.

03:33:23.819 --> 03:33:26.280
They didn't deserve to die like this.

03:33:26.399 --> 03:33:28.379
Morris here.

03:33:28.500 --> 03:33:29.520
Starflight cried.

03:33:29.579 --> 03:33:31.020
Stop them.

03:33:31.139 --> 03:33:34.260
You are peculiar.

03:33:34.319 --> 03:33:36.540
Morris here said from the shadows right

03:33:36.540 --> 03:33:37.139
beside him.

03:33:37.200 --> 03:33:38.399
Starflight jumped.

03:33:38.459 --> 03:33:41.639
They're only a handful of sky wings.

03:33:41.700 --> 03:33:42.899
Why would you care?

03:33:42.959 --> 03:33:45.180
Can't you spare them?

03:33:45.299 --> 03:33:47.159
Starflight said desperately.

03:33:47.219 --> 03:33:49.500
Please, let them live.

03:33:49.559 --> 03:33:52.379
It's much too late for that.

03:33:52.440 --> 03:33:54.299
Said Morris here.

03:33:54.360 --> 03:33:57.360
Starflight turned to face the flames. and

03:33:57.360 --> 03:34:00.180
realized that this had been Mario Seer's

03:34:00.180 --> 03:34:01.200
plan all along.

03:34:01.260 --> 03:34:03.840
That's why he'd chosen a remote location

03:34:03.840 --> 03:34:05.639
with a limited number of dragons.

03:34:05.700 --> 03:34:08.219
That's why he didn't care if the soldiers

03:34:08.219 --> 03:34:09.719
questioned Squid's presence.

03:34:09.780 --> 03:34:11.459
It was all part of the test.

03:34:11.520 --> 03:34:14.340
But whether the Dragonettes passed or

03:34:14.340 --> 03:34:17.159
failed, he'd planned to kill all the Sky

03:34:17.159 --> 03:34:18.479
Wings, no matter what.

03:34:18.540 --> 03:34:21.959
To erase any evidence that we were here

03:34:21.959 --> 03:34:24.540
by murdering any witnesses who might

03:34:24.540 --> 03:34:25.200
wreck our story.

03:34:25.260 --> 03:34:28.200
He stared hopelessly into the fire

03:34:28.200 --> 03:34:30.540
certain that he'd be hearing dragons

03:34:30.540 --> 03:34:32.520
screaming in his dreams for the rest of

03:34:32.520 --> 03:34:32.879
his life.

03:34:32.940 --> 03:34:35.700
They nearly killed me.

03:34:35.760 --> 03:34:39.000
Squid shouted at Maru Seer, just like I

03:34:39.000 --> 03:34:39.659
said they would.

03:34:39.719 --> 03:34:40.680
I quit.

03:34:40.739 --> 03:34:42.600
I don't want to be in the prophecy

03:34:42.600 --> 03:34:43.020
anymore.

03:34:43.079 --> 03:34:45.659
There's no treasure and it's boring and

03:34:45.659 --> 03:34:46.200
stupid.

03:34:46.319 --> 03:34:49.139
I'm hungry and I hate your island.

03:34:49.200 --> 03:34:49.920
I wanna go home.

03:34:49.979 --> 03:34:51.840
Fine.

03:34:51.959 --> 03:34:54.959
Maro Cyr snarled coldly at him.

03:34:55.020 --> 03:34:58.739
I've never met Dragonette more pointless

03:34:58.739 --> 03:34:59.159
than you.

03:34:59.219 --> 03:35:02.459
Go sniveling back to the talons of

03:35:02.459 --> 03:35:02.700
peace.

03:35:02.760 --> 03:35:05.040
See if you can find them by yourself.

03:35:05.100 --> 03:35:07.500
I hope you die on the way.

03:35:07.559 --> 03:35:10.799
He shoved squid forcefully in the chest.

03:35:10.860 --> 03:35:12.299
Get out of here.

03:35:12.360 --> 03:35:16.739
Go. Squid stumbled back, slipping on the

03:35:16.739 --> 03:35:17.399
wet rocks.

03:35:17.459 --> 03:35:19.500
It took him a moment before he could

03:35:19.500 --> 03:35:19.739
talk.

03:35:19.799 --> 03:35:22.260
By myself?

03:35:22.319 --> 03:35:23.459
He squeaked.

03:35:23.579 --> 03:35:27.540
But, but you wouldn't, my dad is the

03:35:27.540 --> 03:35:28.739
leader of the talents.

03:35:28.860 --> 03:35:30.719
You have to be nice to me.

03:35:30.780 --> 03:35:32.340
You can't send me off.

03:35:32.399 --> 03:35:34.680
I certainly can.

03:35:34.799 --> 03:35:37.020
Morrissier hissed.

03:35:37.079 --> 03:35:39.360
Lightning flashed in the sky above him

03:35:39.360 --> 03:35:41.819
illuminating the dark mountains looming

03:35:41.819 --> 03:35:42.299
over them all.

03:35:42.360 --> 03:35:43.920
Leave.

03:35:43.979 --> 03:35:45.959
Oh, I will kill you.

03:35:46.020 --> 03:35:48.420
I never want to see you again.

03:35:48.479 --> 03:35:52.500
Three moons, Starfly thought.

03:35:52.559 --> 03:35:54.540
He really hates squid.

03:35:54.600 --> 03:35:59.100
Wait, fate speaker said, reaching toward

03:35:59.100 --> 03:35:59.879
the sea wing.

03:35:59.940 --> 03:36:01.500
Marcier, wait.

03:36:01.559 --> 03:36:02.459
He's one of us.

03:36:02.520 --> 03:36:03.899
We can't lose him.

03:36:04.020 --> 03:36:06.299
Squid grabbed your front talons and

03:36:06.299 --> 03:36:08.040
squeezed, looking desperate.

03:36:08.159 --> 03:36:10.500
We have another one.

03:36:10.559 --> 03:36:12.360
Morris here said.

03:36:12.420 --> 03:36:14.639
We just have to retrieve her from the

03:36:14.639 --> 03:36:15.420
rainforest.

03:36:15.479 --> 03:36:17.879
But she's clearly made an impression on

03:36:17.879 --> 03:36:20.579
any dragons who run into her, so we're

03:36:20.579 --> 03:36:21.059
stuck with her.

03:36:21.120 --> 03:36:24.059
Whereas this one is nothing but useless.

03:36:24.120 --> 03:36:26.280
It's not fair.

03:36:26.340 --> 03:36:27.780
Squid whined.

03:36:27.840 --> 03:36:29.219
It's not my fault.

03:36:29.280 --> 03:36:30.899
Some other sea wing is better than me.

03:36:30.959 --> 03:36:34.319
That's true, Starflight thought.

03:36:34.379 --> 03:36:36.959
Feeling an unexpected stab of pity for

03:36:36.959 --> 03:36:38.760
the sniveling green dragonette.

03:36:38.819 --> 03:36:41.040
No one could live up to tsunami.

03:36:41.100 --> 03:36:43.260
You can't do this!

03:36:43.379 --> 03:36:44.940
Bates speaker cried.

03:36:45.000 --> 03:36:46.079
Flame.

03:36:46.139 --> 03:36:47.520
Viper, tell him.

03:36:47.639 --> 03:36:51.120
Viper shrugged, and Flame hunched his

03:36:51.120 --> 03:36:51.420
wings.

03:36:51.479 --> 03:36:54.120
His eyes were fixed on the cave where his

03:36:54.120 --> 03:36:55.559
fellow sky wings were burning.

03:36:55.620 --> 03:36:58.799
He said he doesn't want to be in the

03:36:58.799 --> 03:36:59.819
prophecy anyway.

03:36:59.879 --> 03:37:02.040
Ogre said to fate speaker.

03:37:02.100 --> 03:37:05.340
I didn't mean it, Squid cried.

03:37:05.399 --> 03:37:07.620
Maro Seer whipped his tail around and

03:37:07.620 --> 03:37:09.479
smacked Squid hard over the head.

03:37:09.540 --> 03:37:12.239
Leave now.

03:37:12.299 --> 03:37:15.360
Be grateful I'm not killing you instead.

03:37:15.420 --> 03:37:19.620
Whimpering, Squid backed away, spread his

03:37:19.620 --> 03:37:22.079
wings, and lifted into the storm soaked

03:37:22.079 --> 03:37:22.440
sky.

03:37:22.500 --> 03:37:25.680
Starflight watched him flap slowly toward

03:37:25.680 --> 03:37:27.360
the claws of the clouds mountains.

03:37:27.420 --> 03:37:30.840
A sea wing, alone in sky wing territory.

03:37:30.899 --> 03:37:32.940
Squid wouldn't last a day.

03:37:33.000 --> 03:37:36.120
Starflights had pounded, and he felt

03:37:36.120 --> 03:37:36.659
nauseous.

03:37:36.719 --> 03:37:38.940
Every time he thought he'd seen the worst

03:37:38.940 --> 03:37:40.739
of Maro seer and the night wings.

03:37:40.799 --> 03:37:42.540
They did something even more horrible.

03:37:42.600 --> 03:37:45.299
Fate speaker was crying.

03:37:45.360 --> 03:37:48.180
Tears and raindrops together soaking her

03:37:48.180 --> 03:37:48.420
face.

03:37:48.479 --> 03:37:51.719
She pressed her talons to her eyes, as if

03:37:51.719 --> 03:37:53.040
she wished she could claw them out.

03:37:53.100 --> 03:37:56.219
Starfly put one of his wings around her

03:37:56.219 --> 03:37:57.719
and she leaned into his shoulder

03:37:57.719 --> 03:37:59.100
shaking.

03:37:59.159 --> 03:38:02.280
Maybe he'll be all right, he whispered.

03:38:02.340 --> 03:38:04.799
Sometimes dragons surprise you.

03:38:04.860 --> 03:38:07.500
Don't get comfortable.

03:38:07.559 --> 03:38:10.079
Marosir said to Starflight.

03:38:10.139 --> 03:38:13.440
You are running out of chances to show me

03:38:13.440 --> 03:38:15.000
you can obey orders.

03:38:15.059 --> 03:38:18.479
Starflight wound his tail around fate

03:38:18.479 --> 03:38:20.819
speakers thinking, why should I have to?

03:38:20.940 --> 03:38:23.700
Who decided you get to order me around?

03:38:23.819 --> 03:38:27.180
He realized he didn't even care if Maro

03:38:27.180 --> 03:38:29.639
Seer read his mind, and he stared at the

03:38:29.639 --> 03:38:31.319
big dragon, waiting for a reaction.

03:38:31.440 --> 03:38:34.020
Mara seer looked away first.

03:38:34.079 --> 03:38:36.719
Back to the island.

03:38:36.780 --> 03:38:37.860
He ordered.

03:38:37.920 --> 03:38:39.959
The others will clean up this mess.

03:38:40.020 --> 03:38:42.840
He flicked his tail at the ruined

03:38:42.840 --> 03:38:45.180
guardhouse, then leaped into the sky.

03:38:45.239 --> 03:38:48.120
Fate speaker turned toward the mountains

03:38:48.120 --> 03:38:50.100
as if she was thinking about going after

03:38:50.100 --> 03:38:50.700
squid.

03:38:50.760 --> 03:38:53.159
Starflight wished he were that kind of

03:38:53.159 --> 03:38:53.639
dragon.

03:38:53.700 --> 03:38:57.059
Would he disobey Maro seer, and chase

03:38:57.059 --> 03:38:58.979
after one of his friends, if this had

03:38:58.979 --> 03:38:59.639
happened to them?

03:38:59.700 --> 03:39:01.799
He thought he would for Sonny.

03:39:01.860 --> 03:39:04.079
He would never let her fly away alone

03:39:04.079 --> 03:39:04.799
into death.

03:39:04.860 --> 03:39:07.319
He thought perhaps he could be brave for

03:39:07.319 --> 03:39:09.059
her, if he ever needed to be.

03:39:09.120 --> 03:39:12.479
Not brave enough to escape right now

03:39:12.479 --> 03:39:14.159
though, he realized.

03:39:14.219 --> 03:39:16.739
But maybe they're coming to rescue me.

03:39:16.799 --> 03:39:18.959
Maybe I should wait for them anyway.

03:39:19.020 --> 03:39:20.639
Or maybe.

03:39:20.760 --> 03:39:23.579
I'm looking for excuses to do nothing.

03:39:23.639 --> 03:39:28.440
Come on, before anything worse happens, he

03:39:28.440 --> 03:39:29.760
said gently to fate speaker.

03:39:29.819 --> 03:39:32.579
She wiped her eyes and followed him into

03:39:32.579 --> 03:39:33.780
the rain soaked sky.

03:39:33.840 --> 03:39:37.680
The flight back to the island was even

03:39:37.680 --> 03:39:40.079
more exhausting than the flight out, and

03:39:40.079 --> 03:39:42.780
the storm was relentless the entire way.

03:39:42.840 --> 03:39:45.299
Starflight's whole body felt numb by the

03:39:45.299 --> 03:39:46.860
time they touched down in the Nightwing

03:39:46.860 --> 03:39:47.280
fortress.

03:39:47.340 --> 03:39:50.280
None of the dragonettes spoke as they

03:39:50.280 --> 03:39:51.899
trudged back to the dormitory behind

03:39:51.899 --> 03:39:52.860
Morrow Seer.

03:39:52.920 --> 03:39:57.299
Training at dawn tomorrow, Morris here

03:39:57.299 --> 03:39:58.920
said, stopping at the doorway.

03:39:58.979 --> 03:40:00.420
The room was empty.

03:40:00.479 --> 03:40:02.760
The other night wing dragonettes were

03:40:02.760 --> 03:40:03.360
nowhere to be seen.

03:40:03.420 --> 03:40:06.600
He eyed Starflight and fate speaker, then

03:40:06.600 --> 03:40:07.139
turned to go.

03:40:07.260 --> 03:40:10.920
So, nothing to eat?

03:40:10.979 --> 03:40:14.219
Okre ventured in a woebegone voice.

03:40:14.280 --> 03:40:17.399
It had now been days since Starflight's

03:40:17.399 --> 03:40:21.540
last meal, tiring energy sucking days, but

03:40:21.540 --> 03:40:22.860
he didn't think he had the strength to

03:40:22.860 --> 03:40:23.879
eat anything tonight anyway.

03:40:23.940 --> 03:40:27.299
He just wanted to close his eyes and

03:40:27.299 --> 03:40:29.579
tried to forget the sad, dripping shape

03:40:29.579 --> 03:40:31.319
of squid flapping away into the

03:40:31.319 --> 03:40:31.799
mountains.

03:40:31.860 --> 03:40:36.540
No, Marosia rumbled, and then he was

03:40:36.540 --> 03:40:36.840
gone.

03:40:36.899 --> 03:40:39.120
Ogre sighed pitifully.

03:40:39.180 --> 03:40:41.639
Viper hissed and marched to the sleeping

03:40:41.639 --> 03:40:44.399
hollow she'd chosen, burying herself

03:40:44.399 --> 03:40:46.559
immediately in a thick canvas blanket.

03:40:46.620 --> 03:40:49.319
Flame lashed his tail for a moment

03:40:49.319 --> 03:40:50.280
studying the room.

03:40:50.399 --> 03:40:54.120
Not much better than last night's dungeon

03:40:54.120 --> 03:40:55.139
he muttered.

03:40:55.200 --> 03:40:58.139
He and Ocher found spots beside Viper at

03:40:58.139 --> 03:41:00.479
the far end of the room, and soon the mud

03:41:00.479 --> 03:41:02.819
wing was snoring, but the Sky Wing

03:41:02.819 --> 03:41:05.100
Dragonette sat and stared into the coals

03:41:05.100 --> 03:41:06.000
unmoving.

03:41:06.120 --> 03:41:09.659
Starflipe was half asleep already, but

03:41:09.659 --> 03:41:11.760
the minute he curled onto his bed, fate

03:41:11.760 --> 03:41:12.840
speaker hopped up beside him.

03:41:12.959 --> 03:41:16.739
Starflight objected sleepily.

03:41:16.799 --> 03:41:19.379
I know what we have to do, she

03:41:19.379 --> 03:41:19.860
whispered.

03:41:19.920 --> 03:41:21.719
We have to talk to the queen.

03:41:21.780 --> 03:41:23.639
We?

03:41:23.700 --> 03:41:24.840
Starflight asked.

03:41:24.899 --> 03:41:27.420
You and me, without Morrow's here.

03:41:27.479 --> 03:41:30.299
Maybe she has no idea how awful he is.

03:41:30.360 --> 03:41:32.520
I bet he's lying about her ordering him

03:41:32.520 --> 03:41:33.239
to kill one of us.

03:41:33.299 --> 03:41:35.459
I bet he came up with that himself.

03:41:35.520 --> 03:41:39.000
Starflight coiled his tail, feeling

03:41:39.000 --> 03:41:39.600
uneasy.

03:41:39.659 --> 03:41:42.479
He wondered how involved Queen Battle

03:41:42.479 --> 03:41:44.040
Winner was in decisions about the

03:41:44.040 --> 03:41:46.139
dragonettes and the prophecy.

03:41:46.200 --> 03:41:48.299
Had she ordered their trip to the

03:41:48.299 --> 03:41:50.399
mainland, and the deaths of those

03:41:50.399 --> 03:41:51.299
Skywings?

03:41:51.360 --> 03:41:56.040
I bet, fate speaker said fiercely, that

03:41:56.040 --> 03:41:58.139
she won't be too happy with Morrow Seer

03:41:58.139 --> 03:41:59.100
for sending Squid away.

03:41:59.219 --> 03:42:03.479
Maybe she trusts him, Starflight pointed

03:42:03.479 --> 03:42:03.659
out.

03:42:03.719 --> 03:42:06.239
Maybe she lets him do what he wants

03:42:06.239 --> 03:42:09.360
without direct orders, in which case, we

03:42:09.360 --> 03:42:11.219
could get in really big trouble for going

03:42:11.219 --> 03:42:12.360
behind his back.

03:42:12.600 --> 03:42:15.420
Or maybe she has no idea what he's up

03:42:15.420 --> 03:42:15.659
to.

03:42:15.719 --> 03:42:17.579
Fate speaker pointed out.

03:42:17.639 --> 03:42:20.700
And maybe if we talk to her, she'll let

03:42:20.700 --> 03:42:23.700
us both live, free the rain wings, stop

03:42:23.700 --> 03:42:25.920
the experiments, and let the prophecy

03:42:25.920 --> 03:42:28.139
happen however it's supposed to, without

03:42:28.139 --> 03:42:30.299
Marosir ruining everyone's lives.

03:42:30.360 --> 03:42:33.299
Starflight tilted his head at her.

03:42:33.420 --> 03:42:36.540
That's a lot of hope piled onto a very

03:42:36.540 --> 03:42:37.620
slim possibility.

03:42:37.739 --> 03:42:41.100
It's worth a try, she insisted.

03:42:41.159 --> 03:42:43.440
He thought for a moment.

03:42:43.500 --> 03:42:45.959
His brain felt sluggish and confused.

03:42:46.020 --> 03:42:49.620
He needed real food, and he needed sleep

03:42:49.620 --> 03:42:51.420
and he really needed his friends.

03:42:51.479 --> 03:42:54.959
Maybe we can ask for a private audience

03:42:54.959 --> 03:42:55.319
tomorrow.

03:42:55.379 --> 03:42:56.639
He suggested.

03:42:56.700 --> 03:42:59.399
No, fate speaker said.

03:42:59.459 --> 03:43:01.200
Maro Sier won't allow it.

03:43:01.260 --> 03:43:02.879
We have to go find her ourselves.

03:43:02.940 --> 03:43:06.000
She doesn't want to be found.

03:43:06.120 --> 03:43:07.860
Starflight pointed out.

03:43:07.920 --> 03:43:10.680
Maybe she keeps herself hidden for a

03:43:10.680 --> 03:43:10.860
reason.

03:43:10.920 --> 03:43:13.680
He hadn't come up with any good theories

03:43:13.680 --> 03:43:14.280
about that yet.

03:43:14.399 --> 03:43:15.840
Right.

03:43:15.899 --> 03:43:17.940
And maybe we need to know what that

03:43:17.940 --> 03:43:20.280
reason is, fate speaker said.

03:43:20.340 --> 03:43:21.840
She had a point.

03:43:21.899 --> 03:43:23.879
More knowledge would make them more

03:43:23.879 --> 03:43:24.360
powerful.

03:43:24.420 --> 03:43:26.700
If they found out something they could

03:43:26.700 --> 03:43:26.940
use.

03:43:27.059 --> 03:43:30.959
Oh, right, he said with a sigh.

03:43:31.020 --> 03:43:32.520
We'll go look for her.

03:43:32.579 --> 03:43:35.100
Fate speaker shook out her wings and

03:43:35.100 --> 03:43:35.760
smiled at him.

03:43:35.879 --> 03:43:39.479
Tonight, she said, tonight?

03:43:39.540 --> 03:43:41.879
Starflight covered his head with his

03:43:41.879 --> 03:43:42.780
aching wings.

03:43:42.840 --> 03:43:45.719
Don't make me leave this bed before dawn

03:43:45.719 --> 03:43:46.319
please.

03:43:46.379 --> 03:43:49.200
This is important, Starflight.

03:43:49.260 --> 03:43:50.940
Sleep now, and I'll wake you later.

03:43:51.000 --> 03:43:51.600
Deal?

03:43:51.719 --> 03:43:53.159
He sighed again.

03:43:53.280 --> 03:43:54.600
Deal.

03:43:54.659 --> 03:43:58.680
He felt her hop off the bed. listening to

03:43:58.680 --> 03:44:00.120
her footsteps patter away.

03:44:00.180 --> 03:44:02.280
His tired brain began spinning in

03:44:02.280 --> 03:44:03.899
hypothetical circles.

03:44:03.959 --> 03:44:06.299
What is the queen's secret?

03:44:06.360 --> 03:44:08.579
Why doesn't she let herself be seen?

03:44:08.639 --> 03:44:12.239
He thought of Queen Glacier, and how she

03:44:12.239 --> 03:44:15.479
kept her sandwing ally Blaze, cozily

03:44:15.479 --> 03:44:17.639
confined in a fortress built just for her

03:44:17.639 --> 03:44:20.219
under instructions never to leave or do

03:44:20.219 --> 03:44:21.000
anything risky.

03:44:21.120 --> 03:44:24.360
What if Queen Battle Winners being

03:44:24.360 --> 03:44:25.379
controlled by someone?

03:44:25.440 --> 03:44:27.059
Like blazes?

03:44:27.120 --> 03:44:29.340
What if staying hidden isn't her own

03:44:29.340 --> 03:44:29.639
choice?

03:44:29.700 --> 03:44:33.239
If something was wrong, if he could help

03:44:33.239 --> 03:44:35.520
battle winner, maybe she could help him

03:44:35.520 --> 03:44:36.000
in return.

03:44:36.120 --> 03:44:39.180
Stop thinking and sleep.

03:44:39.239 --> 03:44:41.100
He told himself.

03:44:41.159 --> 03:44:43.620
He could see the thin trail of smoke from

03:44:43.620 --> 03:44:46.379
where Flame sat, hunched and brooding

03:44:46.379 --> 03:44:47.219
just like he was.

03:44:47.280 --> 03:44:50.459
But despite the exhaustion that seemed to

03:44:50.459 --> 03:44:53.280
weigh down every bone in his body, sleep

03:44:53.280 --> 03:44:55.559
was a long time coming for both of them.
6286
03:44:55,620 --> 03:45:00,120	Chapter 14.

03:45:00.360 --> 03:45:04.260
Starflight was surrounded by scrolls

03:45:04.260 --> 03:45:07.680
stacks of scrolls, walls of scrolls as

03:45:07.680 --> 03:45:11.100
high as 10 dragons, scrolls as far as he

03:45:11.100 --> 03:45:13.020
could see in every direction.

03:45:13.079 --> 03:45:16.860
His intense joy, so much to read.

03:45:16.920 --> 03:45:19.079
Surely everything you could wish for had

03:45:19.079 --> 03:45:19.620
to be in here.

03:45:19.680 --> 03:45:23.639
All the answers to all his questions, ward

03:45:23.639 --> 03:45:25.680
with deep, paralyzing anxiety.

03:45:25.739 --> 03:45:28.379
How would he ever learn all this?

03:45:28.440 --> 03:45:30.420
How could he possibly get through it all

03:45:30.420 --> 03:45:31.079
before the test?

03:45:31.200 --> 03:45:33.659
What was the test?

03:45:33.719 --> 03:45:36.059
Something about wings of fire.

03:45:36.180 --> 03:45:38.520
There had to be a scroll on wings of fire

03:45:38.520 --> 03:45:38.940
in here.

03:45:39.000 --> 03:45:43.260
Whoops, said a voice from the next aisle

03:45:43.260 --> 03:45:45.420
as a pile of scrolls went tumbling

03:45:45.420 --> 03:45:47.639
scattering all around Starflight's

03:45:47.639 --> 03:45:47.940
talons.

03:45:48.059 --> 03:45:51.000
Clay's face poked out of the wreckage, and

03:45:51.000 --> 03:45:52.139
he grinned at Starflight.

03:45:52.200 --> 03:45:54.719
Oh, hey, there you are.

03:45:54.780 --> 03:45:58.139
Clay, be careful, Starflight said.

03:45:58.200 --> 03:46:00.600
He started picking up scrolls and

03:46:00.600 --> 03:46:02.520
restacking them as neatly as he could.

03:46:02.579 --> 03:46:03.899
We need all this.

03:46:03.959 --> 03:46:05.819
Do we?

03:46:05.879 --> 03:46:07.920
Clay wrinkled his snout.

03:46:07.979 --> 03:46:11.819
Does the prophecy say a bunch of scrolls

03:46:11.819 --> 03:46:13.079
are coming to save the day?

03:46:13.139 --> 03:46:14.520
Funny?

03:46:14.579 --> 03:46:16.020
I don't remember that part.

03:46:16.079 --> 03:46:19.379
Starflight gave him a look and picked up

03:46:19.379 --> 03:46:20.219
the next scroll.

03:46:20.280 --> 03:46:23.040
How to free the rain wing prisoners.

03:46:23.100 --> 03:46:24.239
See?

03:46:24.239 --> 03:46:26.520
he said, waving it at clay.

03:46:26.579 --> 03:46:28.020
All the answers we need.

03:46:28.139 --> 03:46:31.559
He unrolled it eagerly, only to find it

03:46:31.559 --> 03:46:33.659
completely blank inside.

03:46:33.719 --> 03:46:36.180
Smooth empty parchment stared back at him

03:46:36.180 --> 03:46:38.040
indifferent to his disappointment.

03:46:38.100 --> 03:46:40.500
Come on outside.

03:46:40.559 --> 03:46:42.959
Clay said, we could use your help.

03:46:43.020 --> 03:46:45.180
I can't.

03:46:45.239 --> 03:46:46.559
I have to read all of these first.

03:46:46.620 --> 03:46:49.620
Starflight started to spread his wings

03:46:49.620 --> 03:46:52.500
knocked over another stack of scrolls and

03:46:52.500 --> 03:46:54.059
turned in an agitated circle.

03:46:54.120 --> 03:46:56.879
Had the walls of scrolls gotten taller?

03:46:56.940 --> 03:46:58.799
He picked up another scroll.

03:46:58.860 --> 03:47:01.020
Secrets of the night wings.

03:47:01.079 --> 03:47:04.979
That's what I need, he muttered, rolling

03:47:04.979 --> 03:47:06.899
it open, but it was blank too.

03:47:06.959 --> 03:47:09.239
Clay was still waiting.

03:47:09.299 --> 03:47:12.239
I can't help you until I know everything

03:47:12.239 --> 03:47:13.620
Starflight told him.

03:47:13.739 --> 03:47:15.239
I should stay in here.

03:47:15.299 --> 03:47:16.440
It won't take long.

03:47:16.500 --> 03:47:18.780
Soon I'll know a lot more than I do now.

03:47:18.899 --> 03:47:20.760
But I can't go out there yet.

03:47:20.819 --> 03:47:23.819
He pulled a shimmering golden scroll out

03:47:23.819 --> 03:47:24.299
of a pile.

03:47:24.360 --> 03:47:27.120
Surely something so beautiful had to have

03:47:27.120 --> 03:47:27.959
something useful in it.

03:47:28.020 --> 03:47:30.659
How to tell Sonny that you love her.

03:47:30.719 --> 03:47:32.879
Starflight sighed.

03:47:32.940 --> 03:47:34.860
He knew before he unrolled it.

03:47:34.920 --> 03:47:36.899
Blank, blank, blank.

03:47:36.959 --> 03:47:40.620
Starflight, Clay said.

03:47:40.680 --> 03:47:43.860
Starflight, come on, hurry.

03:47:43.979 --> 03:47:45.540
Starflight.

03:47:45.600 --> 03:47:46.680
He's going somewhere.

03:47:46.739 --> 03:47:47.100
Come on.

03:47:47.159 --> 03:47:49.680
It wasn't Clay's voice anymore.

03:47:49.739 --> 03:47:52.680
And someone was shaking his shoulder, and

03:47:52.680 --> 03:47:54.959
Starflight blinked awake, muddled and

03:47:54.959 --> 03:47:55.500
still sleepy.

03:47:55.559 --> 03:47:57.360
Come on.

03:47:57.420 --> 03:47:59.280
Fate speaker whispered again.

03:47:59.340 --> 03:48:01.079
Flame just snuck out.

03:48:01.139 --> 03:48:02.940
Let's follow him, quick.

03:48:03.000 --> 03:48:04.559
Why?

03:48:04.620 --> 03:48:07.200
Starflight mumbled, rubbing his eyes.

03:48:07.260 --> 03:48:09.659
He won't know where the queen is.

03:48:09.719 --> 03:48:12.120
But fate speaker was already hurrying to

03:48:12.120 --> 03:48:12.600
the doorway.

03:48:12.659 --> 03:48:15.780
He stretched, knowing he definitely had

03:48:15.780 --> 03:48:17.700
not gotten enough sleep, and followed

03:48:17.700 --> 03:48:17.879
her.

03:48:17.940 --> 03:48:21.299
Flame's red tail was just disappearing

03:48:21.299 --> 03:48:22.680
around a corner at the far end of the

03:48:22.680 --> 03:48:23.100
hallway.

03:48:23.159 --> 03:48:26.040
Fate speaker and Starflight scurried

03:48:26.040 --> 03:48:26.819
quietly after him.

03:48:26.879 --> 03:48:30.000
She didn't speak, so he kept silent as

03:48:30.000 --> 03:48:30.180
well.

03:48:30.239 --> 03:48:33.059
His dream had left him feeling disturbed

03:48:33.059 --> 03:48:35.040
like he'd forgotten something really

03:48:35.040 --> 03:48:35.579
important.

03:48:35.639 --> 03:48:37.620
Someone he had to warn.

03:48:37.739 --> 03:48:41.280
Soon Flame found a long staircase that

03:48:41.280 --> 03:48:45.180
wound down, and down through the fortress

03:48:45.180 --> 03:48:48.180
each level darker than the last, despite

03:48:48.180 --> 03:48:49.620
the cold glowering in the walls.

03:48:49.680 --> 03:48:52.920
He stopped a few times, listening, and

03:48:52.920 --> 03:48:55.260
fate speaker and Starflight stopped too

03:48:55.260 --> 03:48:57.420
ducking their heads and letting the

03:48:57.420 --> 03:48:59.579
shadows envelop their black scales.

03:48:59.639 --> 03:49:01.860
Finally they reached the bottom of the

03:49:01.860 --> 03:49:04.260
staircase, and Flame chose one of the

03:49:04.260 --> 03:49:06.420
tunnels, which seemed to lead directly

03:49:06.420 --> 03:49:07.799
into the rock of the volcano.

03:49:07.860 --> 03:49:11.100
Heat pulsed beneath their claws.

03:49:11.159 --> 03:49:13.379
Starflight paused to touch the walls.

03:49:13.440 --> 03:49:15.719
Worried that he was feeling rumbles of

03:49:15.719 --> 03:49:17.219
movement from deep within the earth.

03:49:17.280 --> 03:49:19.979
And then they came to the 1st cage.

03:49:20.040 --> 03:49:21.780
It was empty.

03:49:21.840 --> 03:49:24.120
The Starflight could guess what the bars

03:49:24.120 --> 03:49:25.319
and the shackles were four.

03:49:25.379 --> 03:49:28.440
This was the Nightwing Dungeon, where

03:49:28.440 --> 03:49:30.059
Flame and Ogre had been imprisoned

03:49:30.059 --> 03:49:30.479
overnight.

03:49:30.540 --> 03:49:33.959
Most of the cages were empty, but in the

03:49:33.959 --> 03:49:36.659
4th one was a skeletal, drab gray rain

03:49:36.659 --> 03:49:38.340
wing, fast asleep.

03:49:38.399 --> 03:49:40.860
Fate speaker and Starflight paused

03:49:40.860 --> 03:49:42.540
outside her cage, looking in.

03:49:42.600 --> 03:49:45.420
Starflight wondered why this rain wing

03:49:45.420 --> 03:49:47.040
was kept separate from the others in the

03:49:47.040 --> 03:49:47.639
caves outside.

03:49:47.700 --> 03:49:50.100
What are you doing here?

03:49:50.159 --> 03:49:53.100
Flame's accusing face appeared from the

03:49:53.100 --> 03:49:55.079
shadows, making Starflight jump.

03:49:55.139 --> 03:49:57.180
Following you?

03:49:57.239 --> 03:49:58.739
Fate speaker said breezily.

03:49:58.799 --> 03:50:01.020
What in the 3 moons are you up to?

03:50:01.079 --> 03:50:03.059
None of your business.

03:50:03.120 --> 03:50:04.860
Flame snapped.

03:50:04.920 --> 03:50:05.219
Go away.

03:50:05.280 --> 03:50:08.040
What if a guard catches you down here?

03:50:08.100 --> 03:50:09.780
Starflight pointed out.

03:50:09.840 --> 03:50:12.059
You'll be in much more trouble as a

03:50:12.059 --> 03:50:14.520
skywing alone prowling the fortress than

03:50:14.520 --> 03:50:15.899
if you're with 2 night wings.

03:50:15.959 --> 03:50:18.540
The Red Dragonette considered that for a

03:50:18.540 --> 03:50:18.840
moment.

03:50:18.899 --> 03:50:21.120
Smoke rising from his nostrils.

03:50:21.180 --> 03:50:25.200
Fine, he said ungraciously, do whatever

03:50:25.200 --> 03:50:25.620
you want.

03:50:25.680 --> 03:50:26.579
I don't care.

03:50:26.639 --> 03:50:28.860
He turned and stomped away.

03:50:28.979 --> 03:50:31.739
Fate speaker and Starflight exchanged a

03:50:31.739 --> 03:50:32.399
glance and followed him.

03:50:32.459 --> 03:50:35.579
The last cage in the hallway contained a

03:50:35.579 --> 03:50:35.940
night wing.

03:50:36.000 --> 03:50:38.819
This was where flames stopped, and

03:50:38.819 --> 03:50:40.500
wrapped on the bars with one claw.

03:50:40.559 --> 03:50:44.219
Not just any night wing, death bringer.

03:50:44.280 --> 03:50:47.280
The assassin lifted his head and regarded

03:50:47.280 --> 03:50:47.459
them.

03:50:47.520 --> 03:50:50.280
His wings rose and fell as he breathed

03:50:50.280 --> 03:50:52.620
and the cage seemed too small for him.

03:50:52.680 --> 03:50:54.840
Hello, Skywing.

03:50:54.899 --> 03:50:57.120
Glad to see you on the outside of the

03:50:57.120 --> 03:50:57.840
cages this time.

03:50:57.899 --> 03:51:01.079
What does it take to become an assassin?

03:51:01.139 --> 03:51:02.520
Flame blurted.

03:51:02.579 --> 03:51:04.500
I want to know the best way to kill

03:51:04.500 --> 03:51:05.940
another dragon fast.

03:51:06.000 --> 03:51:08.579
Deathbringer stood up and took a step

03:51:08.579 --> 03:51:09.360
toward the bars.

03:51:09.420 --> 03:51:12.899
You mean the best way to kill another

03:51:12.899 --> 03:51:15.719
dragon. and not care, he said.

03:51:15.780 --> 03:51:18.719
Flame hissed and lashed his tail.

03:51:18.840 --> 03:51:22.020
You have to be doing it for really good

03:51:22.020 --> 03:51:24.000
reason, said Deathbringer.

03:51:24.059 --> 03:51:26.219
And you have to believe in that reason

03:51:26.219 --> 03:51:26.879
completely.

03:51:26.940 --> 03:51:29.760
You also should avoid talking to your

03:51:29.760 --> 03:51:31.979
targets, in case you find out that

03:51:31.979 --> 03:51:33.600
they're beautiful, sarcastic, and

03:51:33.600 --> 03:51:35.040
fascinating, for instance.

03:51:35.100 --> 03:51:37.440
Is that what happened to you?

03:51:37.500 --> 03:51:39.360
Flame masked with a snort?

03:51:39.420 --> 03:51:40.979
Is that why you're in here?

03:51:41.040 --> 03:51:44.159
The silver scales under Deathbringers

03:51:44.159 --> 03:51:46.200
wings glinted faintly in the torchlight

03:51:46.200 --> 03:51:46.920
as he shrugged.

03:51:46.979 --> 03:51:48.780
Perhaps.

03:51:48.899 --> 03:51:51.540
But it's not a terrible thing to question

03:51:51.540 --> 03:51:53.459
your orders, if you ask me.

03:51:53.520 --> 03:51:56.700
Flame flicked his tail and fidgeted with

03:51:56.700 --> 03:51:57.180
one of his wings.

03:51:57.239 --> 03:51:59.340
What orders?

03:51:59.399 --> 03:52:01.979
Fate speaker asked Flame and Starflight.

03:52:02.040 --> 03:52:03.180
Who is this?

03:52:03.239 --> 03:52:06.239
Can't one of your visions tell you that?

03:52:06.360 --> 03:52:08.399
Flame asked Snidely.

03:52:08.459 --> 03:52:11.760
This is Deathbringer, Starflight

03:52:11.760 --> 03:52:12.180
explained.

03:52:12.239 --> 03:52:14.940
He was sent to kill my friends, but

03:52:14.940 --> 03:52:16.979
instead he let us go, and he saved glory

03:52:16.979 --> 03:52:18.059
from the other night wings.

03:52:18.180 --> 03:52:20.520
Three moons.

03:52:20.579 --> 03:52:21.719
Keep your voice down.

03:52:21.780 --> 03:52:24.420
Deathbringer said, looking nervous for

03:52:24.420 --> 03:52:24.959
the 1st time.

03:52:25.020 --> 03:52:27.899
I think I'm the only dragon down here

03:52:27.899 --> 03:52:30.780
apart from Queen Splendor, but you never

03:52:30.780 --> 03:52:30.959
know.

03:52:31.020 --> 03:52:33.299
That's Queen Splendor?

03:52:33.360 --> 03:52:34.620
Starflight ass.

03:52:34.680 --> 03:52:37.620
The 1st rain wing captured by the tribe

03:52:37.620 --> 03:52:39.180
said Deathbringer.

03:52:39.239 --> 03:52:41.639
She's the one who accidentally scarred

03:52:41.639 --> 03:52:42.299
vengeance.

03:52:42.360 --> 03:52:45.120
The idea was, once we had their queen

03:52:45.120 --> 03:52:46.680
they do whatever we wanted.

03:52:46.739 --> 03:52:49.319
Little did we know that not only do they

03:52:49.319 --> 03:52:50.459
have multiple queens.

03:52:50.520 --> 03:52:52.920
Apparently they can go for months without

03:52:52.920 --> 03:52:54.360
noticing one is missing either.

03:52:54.420 --> 03:52:57.840
Yikes, said fate speaker.

03:52:57.899 --> 03:53:00.959
Doesn't surprise me, Flame said.

03:53:01.020 --> 03:53:04.680
That's all going to change, Starflight

03:53:04.680 --> 03:53:04.920
said.

03:53:04.979 --> 03:53:06.840
Glory will make sure of it.

03:53:06.899 --> 03:53:10.799
Because of glory, Deathbringer asked.

03:53:10.860 --> 03:53:13.559
Starflight jumped, had the other dragon

03:53:13.559 --> 03:53:14.219
read his mind?

03:53:14.280 --> 03:53:16.860
They stared at each other for a moment.

03:53:16.920 --> 03:53:20.340
Yes, Starflight said finally.

03:53:20.399 --> 03:53:22.860
The look on Deathbringer's face was so

03:53:22.860 --> 03:53:23.280
obvious.

03:53:23.340 --> 03:53:27.059
So real and sad, that Starflight had the

03:53:27.059 --> 03:53:28.620
weird experience of being able to see

03:53:28.620 --> 03:53:30.719
what his own expression must be every

03:53:30.719 --> 03:53:32.219
time he thought of Sonny.

03:53:32.280 --> 03:53:33.780
Whose glory?

03:53:33.899 --> 03:53:35.340
Fate speaker asked.

03:53:35.399 --> 03:53:38.639
That's a long story.

03:53:38.700 --> 03:53:40.260
Starflight said.

03:53:40.319 --> 03:53:42.479
I'm going back to bed.

03:53:42.540 --> 03:53:43.979
Flame growled.

03:53:44.040 --> 03:53:46.680
A small burst of fire curled out of his

03:53:46.680 --> 03:53:49.079
snout as he pushed past fate speaker.

03:53:49.139 --> 03:53:51.420
This is pointless.

03:53:51.479 --> 03:53:54.479
Wait, Deathbringer said.

03:53:54.540 --> 03:53:57.959
Just remember that you're your own

03:53:57.959 --> 03:53:58.500
dragon.

03:53:58.559 --> 03:54:00.479
You don't have to do what you're told.

03:54:00.540 --> 03:54:02.940
You can at least ask questions.

03:54:03.000 --> 03:54:06.840
So I can end up like you, Flame snapped.

03:54:06.899 --> 03:54:09.719
Behind bars, soon to be dumped into a pit

03:54:09.719 --> 03:54:10.500
of lava?

03:54:10.620 --> 03:54:12.239
That does sound like great advice.

03:54:12.299 --> 03:54:14.760
Death bringer shrugged.

03:54:14.819 --> 03:54:16.739
A ghost of a smile crossed his face.

03:54:16.799 --> 03:54:19.079
It could be worse.

03:54:19.139 --> 03:54:23.100
Like, if you'd killed any of my friends

03:54:23.100 --> 03:54:26.100
Starflight said, that would be worse.

03:54:26.159 --> 03:54:29.340
Flame snorted again and slithered away up

03:54:29.340 --> 03:54:29.879
the tunnel.

03:54:29.940 --> 03:54:32.159
Starflight watched the flickers of fire

03:54:32.159 --> 03:54:33.840
around his snout moving through the

03:54:33.840 --> 03:54:36.899
shadows, past Splendor's cage, and back

03:54:36.899 --> 03:54:37.620
to the stairs.

03:54:37.680 --> 03:54:40.979
So, glory's all right.

03:54:41.040 --> 03:54:43.139
Deathbringer said to Starflight.

03:54:43.200 --> 03:54:44.700
She made it back.

03:54:44.819 --> 03:54:46.860
Starflight nodded.

03:54:46.920 --> 03:54:49.680
But she's pretty mad about all the

03:54:49.680 --> 03:54:50.940
imprisoned rain wings.

03:54:51.000 --> 03:54:53.879
He hesitated, thinking that he really

03:54:53.879 --> 03:54:55.860
shouldn't trust this night wing, no

03:54:55.860 --> 03:54:57.180
matter how much he'd helped them.

03:54:57.239 --> 03:55:01.379
Of course she is, said Deathbringer, with

03:55:01.379 --> 03:55:02.219
another half smile.

03:55:02.280 --> 03:55:05.040
I never thought that was a good idea for

03:55:05.040 --> 03:55:05.520
the record.

03:55:05.579 --> 03:55:08.399
The niches for the coals down here were

03:55:08.399 --> 03:55:08.819
rough.

03:55:08.940 --> 03:55:11.219
Hacked out of the jagged rock walls

03:55:11.219 --> 03:55:13.319
instead of neatly carved and chiseled

03:55:13.319 --> 03:55:14.879
like the ones on the upper floors.

03:55:14.940 --> 03:55:18.420
So the shadows all had sharp edges, like

03:55:18.420 --> 03:55:20.219
talons trying to claw their way out of

03:55:20.219 --> 03:55:20.579
the stone.

03:55:20.639 --> 03:55:23.700
The heat was even worse than the blazing

03:55:23.700 --> 03:55:24.899
sun in the kingdom of sand.

03:55:24.959 --> 03:55:27.120
And Starflight's head was starting to

03:55:27.120 --> 03:55:27.540
ache.

03:55:27.659 --> 03:55:29.399
You don't?

03:55:29.579 --> 03:55:33.719
Um, you don't seem fate speakers started

03:55:33.719 --> 03:55:34.979
then trailed off.

03:55:35.159 --> 03:55:37.500
Like a typical assassin.

03:55:37.559 --> 03:55:39.299
Deathbringer finished for her.

03:55:39.360 --> 03:55:42.479
Well, a lot of energy went into training

03:55:42.479 --> 03:55:42.959
me.

03:55:43.020 --> 03:55:45.059
But then I was sent to the continent, and

03:55:45.059 --> 03:55:47.639
my guess when you're on your own for a

03:55:47.639 --> 03:55:47.940
while.

03:55:48.000 --> 03:55:49.739
You start thinking your own thoughts

03:55:49.739 --> 03:55:50.940
instead of anyone else's.

03:55:51.059 --> 03:55:53.399
I'm afraid that makes me quite a

03:55:53.399 --> 03:55:54.600
disappointment to the queen.

03:55:54.719 --> 03:55:57.299
Fate speaker grabbed the bars.

03:55:57.360 --> 03:55:58.979
You've met a queen?

03:55:59.040 --> 03:56:00.899
He tilted his head at her.

03:56:00.959 --> 03:56:03.899
No, not face to face, of course.

03:56:03.959 --> 03:56:07.079
She watches us through screens and speaks

03:56:07.079 --> 03:56:08.520
through her daughter, greatness.

03:56:08.579 --> 03:56:11.940
It's been like that as long as I've been

03:56:11.940 --> 03:56:12.719
alive anyway.

03:56:12.780 --> 03:56:15.600
Starflight's scales prickled.

03:56:15.659 --> 03:56:18.000
What if the queen had screens like that

03:56:18.000 --> 03:56:19.200
all over the fortress?

03:56:19.260 --> 03:56:21.659
What if she was always watching her try

03:56:21.659 --> 03:56:23.520
without any of them realizing she was

03:56:23.520 --> 03:56:23.760
there?

03:56:23.819 --> 03:56:27.420
He looked around uneasily, thinking that

03:56:27.420 --> 03:56:29.459
the dungeon shadows could easily hide a

03:56:29.459 --> 03:56:30.360
few holes in the walls.

03:56:30.420 --> 03:56:33.959
We need to talk to her, fate speaker

03:56:33.959 --> 03:56:34.319
said.

03:56:34.379 --> 03:56:35.579
How can we find her?

03:56:35.700 --> 03:56:37.799
I've spent all night searching the whole

03:56:37.799 --> 03:56:40.020
Moon's begotten fortress, and I can't

03:56:40.020 --> 03:56:40.860
figure out where she might be.

03:56:40.920 --> 03:56:42.959
You have?

03:56:43.020 --> 03:56:45.000
Starflight said, surprised.

03:56:45.059 --> 03:56:47.639
While you were sleeping, she said.

03:56:48.059 --> 03:56:50.340
I told you, I'm wide awake at night.

03:56:50.399 --> 03:56:51.540
I wanted to get started.

03:56:51.600 --> 03:56:53.879
I'm the same way.

03:56:53.940 --> 03:56:55.739
Deathbringer said to her.

03:56:55.799 --> 03:56:58.739
Listen, it's not safe to seek out the

03:56:58.739 --> 03:56:59.100
queen.

03:56:59.159 --> 03:57:00.540
She wouldn't like it.

03:57:00.600 --> 03:57:03.659
We don't have to invade her magical

03:57:03.659 --> 03:57:06.299
privacy or whatever, fate speaker said.

03:57:06.360 --> 03:57:07.920
Does she have a throne room?

03:57:08.040 --> 03:57:10.079
Somewhere we could talk through the wall

03:57:10.079 --> 03:57:11.280
and probably find her?

03:57:11.340 --> 03:57:13.319
Deathbringer hesitated.

03:57:13.379 --> 03:57:15.959
This isn't a good idea.

03:57:16.020 --> 03:57:17.879
I don't think she'll help you.

03:57:17.940 --> 03:57:21.719
I think she will, fate speaker said.

03:57:21.780 --> 03:57:23.940
She pressed her front talons to her

03:57:23.940 --> 03:57:24.899
forehead dramatically.

03:57:25.020 --> 03:57:26.459
I saw it.

03:57:26.520 --> 03:57:28.200
In a vision.

03:57:28.260 --> 03:57:31.739
Deathbringer gave her an extremely odd

03:57:31.739 --> 03:57:32.159
look.

03:57:32.219 --> 03:57:33.899
Really?

03:57:34.020 --> 03:57:36.360
My visions are never wrong.

03:57:36.420 --> 03:57:39.600
Fate speaker said breezily, although I

03:57:39.600 --> 03:57:41.040
wish they'd warn me about more useful

03:57:41.040 --> 03:57:41.940
things sometimes.

03:57:42.000 --> 03:57:44.819
She glanced down at her claws, and

03:57:44.819 --> 03:57:46.319
Starflight guessed she was thinking of

03:57:46.319 --> 03:57:46.739
squid.

03:57:46.860 --> 03:57:50.879
Well, Deathbringer said slowly.

03:57:50.940 --> 03:57:53.879
If you really want to try the throne

03:57:53.879 --> 03:57:54.120
room.

03:57:54.180 --> 03:57:56.639
It's on the far side of the fortress from

03:57:56.639 --> 03:57:59.280
here. 2 doors past the library for coming

03:57:59.280 --> 03:58:00.299
from the council chamber.

03:58:00.420 --> 03:58:03.000
But even if she's behind that screen in

03:58:03.000 --> 03:58:05.100
the middle of the night, which she won't

03:58:05.100 --> 03:58:05.280
be.

03:58:05.340 --> 03:58:07.440
She won't speak to without greatness

03:58:07.440 --> 03:58:07.680
there.

03:58:07.799 --> 03:58:11.459
She doesn't have to speak, Fate speaker

03:58:11.459 --> 03:58:13.680
said passionately, she has to listen.

03:58:13.739 --> 03:58:17.520
Deathbringer met Starflight's eyes, and

03:58:17.520 --> 03:58:18.299
then shrugged again.

03:58:18.420 --> 03:58:22.920
Well, good luck, but hurry, it'll be dull

03:58:22.920 --> 03:58:23.280
soon.

03:58:23.340 --> 03:58:25.260
How can you tell?

03:58:25.379 --> 03:58:26.819
Starflight asked.

03:58:26.879 --> 03:58:28.979
There were no windows in the dungeon

03:58:28.979 --> 03:58:31.020
nothing to mark the passage of time

03:58:31.020 --> 03:58:33.360
nothing but pockmarked black rock

03:58:33.360 --> 03:58:34.559
surrounded the prisoners.

03:58:34.620 --> 03:58:38.159
I can sense it, Deathbringer said.

03:58:38.219 --> 03:58:40.500
Spend a few months sleeping out in the

03:58:40.500 --> 03:58:42.059
open, and you'll get the knock of it

03:58:42.059 --> 03:58:42.239
too.

03:58:42.299 --> 03:58:44.940
What were you doing on your own on the

03:58:44.940 --> 03:58:45.959
continent for so long?

03:58:46.020 --> 03:58:47.459
Starflight asked.

03:58:47.579 --> 03:58:50.819
I had a list, Deathbringer said.

03:58:50.879 --> 03:58:53.100
And regular meetings to receive new

03:58:53.100 --> 03:58:53.520
orders.

03:58:53.579 --> 03:58:55.920
Did you ever notice that whenever one

03:58:55.920 --> 03:58:57.420
side appeared to be winning the war?

03:58:57.540 --> 03:58:59.879
One of their top generals would

03:58:59.879 --> 03:59:00.840
mysteriously die.

03:59:00.899 --> 03:59:03.239
Not that I am taking credit for anything

03:59:03.239 --> 03:59:03.479
of course.

03:59:03.540 --> 03:59:05.760
I did notice that.

03:59:05.819 --> 03:59:07.260
Starflight said.

03:59:07.319 --> 03:59:09.780
At least, from what I could figure out

03:59:09.780 --> 03:59:11.399
from the newest history scrolls.

03:59:11.459 --> 03:59:15.180
But if that was you, well, it seemed to

03:59:15.180 --> 03:59:18.120
happen to all 3 sides, so I thought it

03:59:18.120 --> 03:59:19.079
had to be a coincidence.

03:59:19.139 --> 03:59:21.780
Deathbringer spread his wings.

03:59:21.899 --> 03:59:24.540
We only chose a side recently.

03:59:24.600 --> 03:59:25.979
He paused.

03:59:26.040 --> 03:59:28.860
I was not consulted in that choice.

03:59:28.979 --> 03:59:31.680
You don't like blister either.

03:59:31.739 --> 03:59:33.299
Starflight realized.

03:59:33.420 --> 03:59:35.639
Starflight, we have to go.

03:59:35.700 --> 03:59:38.520
Face speaker said, tugging on his tail.

03:59:38.579 --> 03:59:41.459
I want to find a queen tonight, before a

03:59:41.459 --> 03:59:43.200
Maro seer can do anything else awful.

03:59:43.260 --> 03:59:44.700
Come on.

03:59:44.760 --> 03:59:47.219
Starflight stepped back reluctantly.

03:59:47.280 --> 03:59:49.559
He felt as if he still had so many

03:59:49.559 --> 03:59:51.899
questions for Deathbringer, and this

03:59:51.899 --> 03:59:53.639
might be the first night wing who would

03:59:53.639 --> 03:59:54.840
actually give him real answers.

03:59:54.899 --> 03:59:58.920
I'll come back, he promised, soon.

03:59:58.979 --> 04:00:01.440
I'll, I'll see what I can do to help

04:00:01.440 --> 04:00:01.620
you.

04:00:01.680 --> 04:00:05.340
Don't get in trouble said Deathbringer.

04:00:05.459 --> 04:00:06.780
I'll be all right.

04:00:06.840 --> 04:00:08.219
Good luck.

04:00:08.280 --> 04:00:11.040
He tipped his wings toward fate speaker.

04:00:11.100 --> 04:00:13.559
Starflight wished he could do something.

04:00:13.620 --> 04:00:16.020
You should try to save Deathbringer the

04:00:16.020 --> 04:00:18.360
way the Nightwing had saved glory, both

04:00:18.360 --> 04:00:20.520
from assassination and from the prison

04:00:20.520 --> 04:00:21.000
caves.

04:00:21.059 --> 04:00:23.879
He should do something brave, something

04:00:23.879 --> 04:00:27.840
bold and kind and heroic, but he had no

04:00:27.840 --> 04:00:29.040
idea how to even begin.

04:00:29.100 --> 04:00:32.579
Instead, he followed fate speaker back

04:00:32.579 --> 04:00:34.620
into the fortress, back through the

04:00:34.620 --> 04:00:36.899
tunnels and hallways, in search of the

04:00:36.899 --> 04:00:39.360
throne room, and the queen who might or

04:00:39.360 --> 04:00:41.940
might not be there, who might or might

04:00:41.940 --> 04:00:44.100
not listen, and who almost certainly

04:00:44.100 --> 04:00:45.420
would not help them.
6736
04:00:45,420 --> 04:00:49,979	Chapter 15.

04:00:50.280 --> 04:00:53.700
Tudors past the library.

04:00:53.760 --> 04:00:55.319
Fate speaker muttered.

04:00:55.379 --> 04:00:57.959
Something about a council chamber.

04:00:58.020 --> 04:01:01.079
She paused in an intersection, looking

04:01:01.079 --> 04:01:03.059
down both tunnels and pressing our claws

04:01:03.059 --> 04:01:03.360
together.

04:01:03.420 --> 04:01:06.659
I think I remember where the council

04:01:06.659 --> 04:01:08.700
chamber is, Starflight said.

04:01:08.819 --> 04:01:10.860
He'd been trying to create a map of the

04:01:10.860 --> 04:01:12.659
fortress in his head every time they left

04:01:12.659 --> 04:01:13.440
the dormitory.

04:01:13.559 --> 04:01:16.020
That way, if I'm right.

04:01:16.079 --> 04:01:17.219
He pointed.

04:01:17.280 --> 04:01:19.860
Then we go this way, she said.

04:01:19.920 --> 04:01:22.079
I think we'll pass the library this way.

04:01:22.139 --> 04:01:24.420
Library.

04:01:24.600 --> 04:01:27.239
Starflight echoed, finally hearing what

04:01:27.239 --> 04:01:28.379
Deathbringer had said.

04:01:28.440 --> 04:01:30.180
There's a library.

04:01:30.239 --> 04:01:32.399
Fate speaker, have you seen it?

04:01:32.459 --> 04:01:34.020
How many scrolls do they have?

04:01:34.079 --> 04:01:37.020
Like a million, she said.

04:01:37.079 --> 04:01:39.180
A million.

04:01:39.239 --> 04:01:42.479
Starflight felt momentarily faint

04:01:42.479 --> 04:01:44.879
thinking of a 1000000 scrolls he'd never

04:01:44.879 --> 04:01:45.239
read.

04:01:45.299 --> 04:01:47.579
It would be just like his dream.

04:01:47.639 --> 04:01:50.879
That wasn't a real guess, fate speaker

04:01:50.879 --> 04:01:53.040
said, stopping to give him an amused

04:01:53.040 --> 04:01:53.459
grin.

04:01:53.520 --> 04:01:55.680
I just meant lots, really.

04:01:55.739 --> 04:01:57.000
I didn't try to count them.

04:01:57.120 --> 04:02:01.200
Lots is exciting too, Starflight said.

04:02:01.260 --> 04:02:03.719
He felt a little silly getting so excited

04:02:03.719 --> 04:02:06.180
over scrolls, but there had never been

04:02:06.180 --> 04:02:07.319
enough of them under the mountain.

04:02:07.440 --> 04:02:10.680
He'd read the same ones over and over and

04:02:10.680 --> 04:02:11.280
over again.

04:02:11.340 --> 04:02:13.739
Something new, something with more

04:02:13.739 --> 04:02:15.959
answers, more of the information he

04:02:15.959 --> 04:02:16.319
needed.

04:02:16.379 --> 04:02:18.299
That would be everything.

04:02:18.360 --> 04:02:21.659
Here it is, fate speaker said.

04:02:21.719 --> 04:02:23.940
Pausing at a tall, open archway.

04:02:24.059 --> 04:02:26.879
Starflight peered inside, his heart

04:02:26.879 --> 04:02:27.420
pounding.

04:02:27.479 --> 04:02:30.780
The room was cavernous, even bigger than

04:02:30.780 --> 04:02:31.680
the council chamber.

04:02:31.739 --> 04:02:34.379
Instead of coals lying open in wall

04:02:34.379 --> 04:02:36.719
niches, here the light came from fire

04:02:36.719 --> 04:02:38.579
that was carefully trapped in metal

04:02:38.579 --> 04:02:40.620
globes and kept away from the scrolls.

04:02:40.739 --> 04:02:43.500
Square nooks were carved out of the wall

04:02:43.500 --> 04:02:46.020
all the way up to the ceiling, and in

04:02:46.020 --> 04:02:48.239
each square there were between 3 and 6

04:02:48.239 --> 04:02:51.239
scrolls, neatly rolled and labeled and

04:02:51.239 --> 04:02:53.340
organized, organized.

04:02:53.399 --> 04:02:56.399
With a mark next to the square, and a

04:02:56.399 --> 04:02:58.260
large scroll rolled out on a main table

04:02:58.260 --> 04:02:59.280
as a catalog.

04:02:59.340 --> 04:03:01.379
He could see how it worked in the 1st

04:03:01.379 --> 04:03:04.020
glance, and his talons ached to rush

04:03:04.020 --> 04:03:05.100
inside and start reading.

04:03:05.159 --> 04:03:08.040
You are so cute.

04:03:08.159 --> 04:03:09.360
Fate speaker said.

04:03:09.420 --> 04:03:10.620
Look at your face.

04:03:10.680 --> 04:03:12.719
Like someone just opened up a giant

04:03:12.719 --> 04:03:14.340
treasure box and it's all for you.

04:03:14.399 --> 04:03:18.059
That was exactly how Starflight felt

04:03:18.059 --> 04:03:19.920
looking at all these scrolls.

04:03:19.979 --> 04:03:22.920
He took a tentative step inside, and Fate

04:03:22.920 --> 04:03:24.540
speaker immediately grabbed his tail.

04:03:24.600 --> 04:03:27.780
Oh, no, you don't. she said.

04:03:27.840 --> 04:03:29.219
We find a queen first.

04:03:29.280 --> 04:03:31.620
You can come back and moon over scrolls

04:03:31.620 --> 04:03:31.920
tomorrow.

04:03:32.040 --> 04:03:34.860
If Maru Seer lets me.

04:03:34.920 --> 04:03:36.959
Starflight said wistfully.

04:03:37.020 --> 04:03:39.780
Fate speaker dragged him away from the

04:03:39.780 --> 04:03:42.540
library and stopped 2 doors down in front

04:03:42.540 --> 04:03:44.459
of a round stone room that was completely

04:03:44.459 --> 04:03:47.459
empty, with no windows and no furniture

04:03:47.459 --> 04:03:49.739
and only one niche for glowing coals.

04:03:49.799 --> 04:03:52.379
The wall opposite the door was a strange

04:03:52.379 --> 04:03:54.780
lattice of stone studded with diamond

04:03:54.780 --> 04:03:56.819
shaped holes no bigger than ladybugs.

04:03:56.879 --> 04:04:00.600
I did see this room, fate speaker said.

04:04:00.659 --> 04:04:02.459
I just didn't guess it was the throne

04:04:02.459 --> 04:04:02.700
room.

04:04:02.760 --> 04:04:05.159
Shouldn't a throne room have a throne in

04:04:05.159 --> 04:04:07.620
it, even if no one plans to sit on it?

04:04:07.680 --> 04:04:10.559
Maybe there's a throne behind the screen

04:04:10.559 --> 04:04:12.239
Starflight suggested.

04:04:12.299 --> 04:04:14.579
Hmm, she said.

04:04:14.639 --> 04:04:16.620
Still seems like it shouldn't get to be

04:04:16.620 --> 04:04:17.819
called at throne room then.

04:04:17.940 --> 04:04:20.819
She stalked up to the lattice wall and

04:04:20.819 --> 04:04:22.440
pressed one eye to one of the holes.

04:04:22.500 --> 04:04:26.459
Fate speaker, Starflight said, shocked.

04:04:26.520 --> 04:04:28.860
We're not supposed to try and look at

04:04:28.860 --> 04:04:28.979
her.

04:04:29.040 --> 04:04:31.500
Don't panic, she said.

04:04:31.620 --> 04:04:33.479
It's all dark back there anyway.

04:04:33.540 --> 04:04:36.000
She tilted her head and tried another

04:04:36.000 --> 04:04:36.899
hole lower down.

04:04:36.959 --> 04:04:40.620
Maybe there's something glowing, but it

04:04:40.620 --> 04:04:41.280
just looks like fire.

04:04:41.340 --> 04:04:43.079
I can't see the queen.

04:04:43.139 --> 04:04:44.819
Do you think she's there?

04:04:44.879 --> 04:04:46.799
She rapped on the screen.

04:04:46.860 --> 04:04:49.139
Hello, your majesty?

04:04:49.200 --> 04:04:51.420
Silence from the wall.

04:04:51.479 --> 04:04:53.700
Queen Battle Winner?

04:04:53.760 --> 04:04:55.559
Fate speaker tried again.

04:04:55.680 --> 04:04:57.540
We really need to talk to you.

04:04:57.600 --> 04:04:58.620
It's us.

04:04:58.680 --> 04:05:00.600
The dragonettes from the prophecy.

04:05:00.659 --> 04:05:04.319
Whoa, the 2 night wing options.

04:05:04.379 --> 04:05:05.700
Starflight amended.

04:05:05.760 --> 04:05:08.879
Hello, fate speaker said.

04:05:08.940 --> 04:05:10.500
Nothing.

04:05:10.559 --> 04:05:12.959
Fate speaker knocked and kicked the wall

04:05:12.959 --> 04:05:15.180
a few times, but there was no response.

04:05:15.239 --> 04:05:19.799
That is so frustrating, she growled.

04:05:19.860 --> 04:05:21.180
Your majesty?

04:05:21.239 --> 04:05:22.799
I'm not impressed.

04:05:22.860 --> 04:05:25.979
It is the middle of the night.

04:05:26.040 --> 04:05:27.780
Starflight pointed out.

04:05:27.840 --> 04:05:29.579
She's probably not even there.

04:05:29.639 --> 04:05:31.500
She must sleep somewhere.

04:05:31.559 --> 04:05:34.860
Fate speaker hunched your wings, then

04:05:34.860 --> 04:05:35.760
sighed and nodded.

04:05:35.819 --> 04:05:37.260
All right.

04:05:37.319 --> 04:05:39.719
We'll sneak away from MaroCer and try

04:05:39.719 --> 04:05:40.260
again tomorrow.

04:05:40.319 --> 04:05:43.440
Starfly did not love the sound of that

04:05:43.440 --> 04:05:46.079
plan, but he already knew better than to

04:05:46.079 --> 04:05:47.700
try arguing with fate speaker.

04:05:47.760 --> 04:05:50.760
They turned to go, but just then

04:05:50.760 --> 04:05:52.440
Starflight heard a noise.

04:05:52.500 --> 04:05:55.319
A noise like scraping coming from behind

04:05:55.319 --> 04:05:55.739
the wall.

04:05:55.799 --> 04:05:58.319
He looked at face speaker and saw that

04:05:58.319 --> 04:05:59.100
she'd heard it too.

04:05:59.159 --> 04:06:01.200
They both returned to the screen.

04:06:01.260 --> 04:06:03.299
Your majesty?

04:06:03.360 --> 04:06:04.799
Fate speaker said.

04:06:04.860 --> 04:06:07.440
When there was still no answer, Starflight

04:06:07.440 --> 04:06:10.319
said, if she's back there, she doesn't

04:06:10.319 --> 04:06:10.979
want to talk to us.

04:06:11.100 --> 04:06:13.920
Fate speaker folded her wings in close

04:06:13.920 --> 04:06:14.760
and scowled.

04:06:14.819 --> 04:06:17.340
Then we should make her see us.

04:06:17.399 --> 04:06:20.219
She started pacing along the wall with a

04:06:20.219 --> 04:06:20.459
screen.

04:06:20.520 --> 04:06:22.500
There must be a door here somewhere.

04:06:22.559 --> 04:06:24.959
She has to get in and out somehow, right?

04:06:25.079 --> 04:06:28.319
Unless she always stays in the same room

04:06:28.319 --> 04:06:29.760
Starflight said.

04:06:29.879 --> 04:06:32.100
His mental map of the fortress started

04:06:32.100 --> 04:06:32.700
clicking together.

04:06:32.760 --> 04:06:36.299
I think, I think the room behind this

04:06:36.299 --> 04:06:38.100
wall could also overlook the council

04:06:38.100 --> 04:06:38.520
chamber.

04:06:38.579 --> 04:06:40.260
Maybe that's where she lives.

04:06:40.379 --> 04:06:43.920
So we just have to find a way into it

04:06:43.920 --> 04:06:46.979
fate speaker said, charging into the

04:06:46.979 --> 04:06:47.340
hallway.

04:06:47.399 --> 04:06:49.680
Is that a good idea?

04:06:49.739 --> 04:06:51.180
Starflight asked.

04:06:51.239 --> 04:06:53.159
His claws caught on the rocks as he

04:06:53.159 --> 04:06:53.819
hurried behind her.

04:06:53.879 --> 04:06:56.280
I'm pretty sure she won't be pleased.

04:06:56.340 --> 04:06:59.879
Too bad, fate speaker cried.

04:06:59.940 --> 04:07:01.500
We're her subjects too.

04:07:01.559 --> 04:07:02.940
She has to listen to us.

04:07:03.000 --> 04:07:06.000
Clearly, fate speaker didn't know very

04:07:06.000 --> 04:07:08.219
much about queens or tribes and how they

04:07:08.219 --> 04:07:08.459
worked.

04:07:08.520 --> 04:07:11.399
Perhaps the talons of Peace Cam was a

04:07:11.399 --> 04:07:12.840
little more open to input from all

04:07:12.840 --> 04:07:13.979
dragons.

04:07:14.040 --> 04:07:15.959
Or perhaps fate speaker would have been

04:07:15.959 --> 04:07:17.280
like this no matter where she was

04:07:17.280 --> 04:07:17.819
raised.

04:07:17.879 --> 04:07:20.760
She stopped abruptly, frowning and

04:07:20.760 --> 04:07:22.079
tipping her head from side to side.

04:07:22.139 --> 04:07:25.500
How do we get there?

04:07:25.559 --> 04:07:27.120
She muttered to herself.

04:07:27.180 --> 04:07:29.459
She closed her eyes and took a deep

04:07:29.459 --> 04:07:29.819
breath.

04:07:29.879 --> 04:07:31.920
Having a vision?

04:07:31.979 --> 04:07:34.620
Starflight asked, recognizing the

04:07:34.620 --> 04:07:35.459
expression on her face.

04:07:35.520 --> 04:07:38.340
Trying to she said.

04:07:38.399 --> 04:07:40.920
But all I can see is walls.

04:07:40.979 --> 04:07:43.739
Let's try this way.

04:07:43.799 --> 04:07:45.420
Starflight suggested.

04:07:45.540 --> 04:07:48.180
They followed winding passages that seem

04:07:48.180 --> 04:07:50.579
to be circling the council room, but he

04:07:50.579 --> 04:07:52.020
couldn't find any doors that might lead

04:07:52.020 --> 04:07:53.340
to the place where the queen had been

04:07:53.340 --> 04:07:53.639
hidden.

04:07:53.760 --> 04:07:56.340
But he did find one room with the door

04:07:56.340 --> 04:07:58.379
open, and it was empty when he peered

04:07:58.379 --> 04:07:58.620
inside.

04:07:58.739 --> 04:08:00.959
It was a strange room too.

04:08:01.020 --> 04:08:04.379
The space was dominated by a giant map on

04:08:04.379 --> 04:08:04.680
the wall.

04:08:04.739 --> 04:08:07.860
Pyria, but with more detail in it than

04:08:07.860 --> 04:08:09.479
he'd ever seen on any map before.

04:08:09.540 --> 04:08:13.139
Every inlet, every fjord was drawn with

04:08:13.139 --> 04:08:14.340
scientific precision.

04:08:14.399 --> 04:08:16.920
Even the rainforest sparkled with

04:08:16.920 --> 04:08:17.459
information.

04:08:17.520 --> 04:08:20.040
The location of the main rain wing

04:08:20.040 --> 04:08:22.500
village, all the rivers and streams that

04:08:22.500 --> 04:08:24.780
crisscrossed the jungle, and the 2

04:08:24.780 --> 04:08:26.940
tunnels that led to the kingdom of sand

04:08:26.940 --> 04:08:29.520
and the night wing island, each was

04:08:29.520 --> 04:08:31.020
marked and carefully labeled.

04:08:31.079 --> 04:08:34.379
Starflight noticed that the Sea Wings

04:08:34.379 --> 04:08:36.000
Summer Palace was noted on there as

04:08:36.000 --> 04:08:36.180
well.

04:08:36.239 --> 04:08:39.360
In ink that looked darker and newer than

04:08:39.360 --> 04:08:41.579
some of the other marks, and he wondered

04:08:41.579 --> 04:08:43.200
whether the night wings had only learned

04:08:43.200 --> 04:08:44.579
of its location when it burned.

04:08:44.639 --> 04:08:48.479
The deep palace was not on there, still a

04:08:48.479 --> 04:08:49.979
sea wing secret, apparently.

04:08:50.040 --> 04:08:53.459
But strangest of all, the map was covered

04:08:53.459 --> 04:08:55.440
with tiny squares that were each labeled

04:08:55.440 --> 04:08:57.000
scavenger den.

04:08:57.059 --> 04:08:59.760
There were 7 of them, from the outer

04:08:59.760 --> 04:09:02.040
islands of the kingdom of the sea, to the

04:09:02.040 --> 04:09:03.780
peninsula below the kingdom of sand.

04:09:03.840 --> 04:09:06.600
There was even one among the snowy wastes

04:09:06.600 --> 04:09:09.299
of the ice kingdom, and each one had a

04:09:09.299 --> 04:09:11.639
careful, deliberate X slashed across it

04:09:11.639 --> 04:09:12.719
in green ink.

04:09:13.079 --> 04:09:14.940
What are they doing?

04:09:15.000 --> 04:09:17.940
Starflight thought, staring at the map.

04:09:18.000 --> 04:09:20.700
Why track scavengers?

04:09:20.760 --> 04:09:21.899
What do the X's mean?

04:09:21.959 --> 04:09:25.260
What's a scavenger den?

04:09:25.319 --> 04:09:27.360
Fate speaker asked from behind him?

04:09:27.420 --> 04:09:30.180
Have you ever seen a scavenger?

04:09:30.239 --> 04:09:31.500
Starfly asked.

04:09:31.559 --> 04:09:32.879
She shook her head.

04:09:32.940 --> 04:09:35.459
There are these little creatures with

04:09:35.459 --> 04:09:37.860
hardly any fur, and they run around on 2

04:09:37.860 --> 04:09:40.260
legs, and they love to steal treasure

04:09:40.319 --> 04:09:43.379
kind of like magpies or raccoons, but

04:09:43.379 --> 04:09:43.920
bigger.

04:09:43.979 --> 04:09:46.620
And sometimes they get pointy sticks, and

04:09:46.620 --> 04:09:48.840
poke dragons with them, which means they

04:09:48.840 --> 04:09:49.920
can't be very intelligent.

04:09:49.979 --> 04:09:53.340
Oh, fate speaker said.

04:09:53.399 --> 04:09:54.360
Right.

04:09:54.420 --> 04:09:57.059
Like the scavenger who killed Queen Oasis

04:09:57.059 --> 04:09:58.860
and started the whole war in the 1st

04:09:58.860 --> 04:09:59.219
place.

04:09:59.340 --> 04:10:02.940
Exactly, Starflight said.

04:10:03.000 --> 04:10:05.639
He shivered, remembering the only ones

04:10:05.639 --> 04:10:08.340
he'd ever encountered, the 2 who'd tried

04:10:08.340 --> 04:10:09.959
to kill him in Scarlet's arena.

04:10:10.020 --> 04:10:13.020
In his nightmares, they always stared at

04:10:13.020 --> 04:10:15.780
him with big dragon like eyes, and even

04:10:15.780 --> 04:10:16.979
though he found them terrifying.

04:10:17.040 --> 04:10:19.799
He couldn't help thinking, they're in the

04:10:19.799 --> 04:10:20.760
same situation I am.

04:10:20.879 --> 04:10:23.459
They're just trying to survive this

04:10:23.459 --> 04:10:24.000
arena.

04:10:24.059 --> 04:10:28.260
So, these dens, that's where they live?

04:10:28.319 --> 04:10:31.319
Fate speaker reached up and traced the

04:10:31.319 --> 04:10:32.700
outline of one of the dens with her

04:10:32.700 --> 04:10:33.659
claw.

04:10:33.719 --> 04:10:36.299
I guess so, Starflight said.

04:10:36.360 --> 04:10:37.739
I've never seen one.

04:10:37.799 --> 04:10:41.340
I always imagined warns of tunnels.

04:10:41.399 --> 04:10:43.139
The scrolls say they like to live in big

04:10:43.139 --> 04:10:46.139
groups, like meerkats, but they try to

04:10:46.139 --> 04:10:47.879
keep their dens hidden according to what

04:10:47.879 --> 04:10:48.360
I've read.

04:10:48.420 --> 04:10:50.760
They're safer from predators that way.

04:10:50.879 --> 04:10:54.780
Predators like us, fate speaker said

04:10:54.780 --> 04:10:55.319
cheerfully.

04:10:55.379 --> 04:10:58.260
I have no idea why the Night Wings would

04:10:58.260 --> 04:10:58.739
care about them.

04:10:58.860 --> 04:11:01.739
Starflight said, scratching his head.

04:11:01.799 --> 04:11:04.260
A theory was bubbling at the back of his

04:11:04.260 --> 04:11:06.299
mind, but before he could put it together

04:11:06.360 --> 04:11:08.879
Fate speaker slid her talons along to the

04:11:08.879 --> 04:11:10.799
outer edge of the map and let out a

04:11:10.799 --> 04:11:11.219
yelp.

04:11:11.280 --> 04:11:13.860
Look, there's something behind here.

04:11:13.979 --> 04:11:17.159
She unpinned one corner of the map and

04:11:17.159 --> 04:11:19.920
lifted it up, and sure enough, there was

04:11:19.920 --> 04:11:21.360
a small tunnel hidden behind it.

04:11:21.420 --> 04:11:25.379
Let's go. she whispered, ducking into it

04:11:25.379 --> 04:11:26.340
with no hesitation.

04:11:26.399 --> 04:11:29.219
Starflight's heart was trying to clamber

04:11:29.219 --> 04:11:31.559
up his throat and strangle him, but what

04:11:31.559 --> 04:11:32.040
else could he do?

04:11:32.100 --> 04:11:34.500
If this tunnel led where it looked like

04:11:34.500 --> 04:11:36.899
it might, he couldn't leave fate speaker

04:11:36.899 --> 04:11:38.940
to face Queen Battle winner alone.

04:11:39.000 --> 04:11:42.780
If only tsunami were here, or clay.

04:11:42.840 --> 04:11:45.299
They'd at least be some use in a fight

04:11:45.299 --> 04:11:46.620
unlike him.

04:11:46.680 --> 04:11:49.319
His claws shook as he lifted the corner

04:11:49.319 --> 04:11:51.719
of the map, and slid into the dark tunnel

04:11:51.719 --> 04:11:52.799
behind fate speaker.

04:11:52.860 --> 04:11:55.500
I am having a vision.

04:11:55.559 --> 04:11:58.139
Fate speaker whispered dramatically in

04:11:58.139 --> 04:12:00.120
his ear, nearly making him leap out of

04:12:00.120 --> 04:12:00.659
his scales.

04:12:00.659 --> 04:12:03.899
Of us standing in front of Queen Battle

04:12:03.899 --> 04:12:06.120
Winner, this is going to work.

04:12:06.180 --> 04:12:10.260
You scared me half to death. he said

04:12:10.260 --> 04:12:11.219
clutching his chest.

04:12:11.280 --> 04:12:15.059
Sorry, she said, and even in the dark, he

04:12:15.059 --> 04:12:15.959
could sense her grinning.

04:12:16.020 --> 04:12:19.680
So, he whispered, as they started

04:12:19.680 --> 04:12:20.879
creeping forward.

04:12:20.940 --> 04:12:24.239
In your visions, there is a queen battle

04:12:24.239 --> 04:12:24.719
winner.

04:12:24.780 --> 04:12:25.920
She's alive?

04:12:25.979 --> 04:12:27.120
She exists?

04:12:27.180 --> 04:12:28.680
Of course.

04:12:28.739 --> 04:12:29.940
Fate speaker said.

04:12:30.000 --> 04:12:31.079
What?

04:12:31.139 --> 04:12:34.139
Nothing, Starfly said.

04:12:34.200 --> 04:12:37.319
It's just, I've been wondering, since no

04:12:37.319 --> 04:12:39.659
one ever sees her, and apparently no one

04:12:39.659 --> 04:12:41.159
even hears her accept greatness.

04:12:41.280 --> 04:12:43.680
Well, if she were dead.

04:12:43.739 --> 04:12:46.319
This would be a pretty clever plan is

04:12:46.319 --> 04:12:46.559
all.

04:12:46.620 --> 04:12:49.500
As long as greatness claims Battle winner

04:12:49.500 --> 04:12:52.139
is alive, she can issue orders and do all

04:12:52.139 --> 04:12:54.600
the things a queen might do, in Battle

04:12:54.600 --> 04:12:56.760
winner's name, but no one can challenge

04:12:56.760 --> 04:12:57.959
her to try to take the throne.

04:12:58.020 --> 04:13:03.420
That is way sneaky, fate speaker said.

04:13:03.479 --> 04:13:04.979
I would never have thought of that.

04:13:05.040 --> 04:13:07.379
I could be wrong.

04:13:07.440 --> 04:13:11.100
His nose bumped suddenly into stone.

04:13:11.159 --> 04:13:13.260
He stood up on his back talons and poked

04:13:13.260 --> 04:13:15.659
the low ceiling above their heads, then

04:13:15.659 --> 04:13:17.100
breathed out a plume of fire.

04:13:17.159 --> 04:13:20.100
The tunnel ended at a large boulder right

04:13:20.100 --> 04:13:20.819
in front of them.

04:13:20.879 --> 04:13:23.639
Fate speaker hissed, no way.

04:13:23.700 --> 04:13:25.139
This has to be it.

04:13:25.200 --> 04:13:28.260
Starflight gingerly felt around to the

04:13:28.260 --> 04:13:30.719
back of the boulder and realized there

04:13:30.719 --> 04:13:32.459
was empty space under his claws.

04:13:32.520 --> 04:13:36.239
The tunnel keeps going only smaller, I

04:13:36.239 --> 04:13:37.559
think, he said.

04:13:37.620 --> 04:13:40.500
There was a hole in the wall, hidden by

04:13:40.500 --> 04:13:42.659
the boulder, barely big enough for a

04:13:42.659 --> 04:13:43.500
dragon to fit through.

04:13:43.559 --> 04:13:46.920
He reached his talons inside, and guessed

04:13:46.920 --> 04:13:48.540
that the hidden tunnel led up in the

04:13:48.540 --> 04:13:49.379
right direction.

04:13:49.500 --> 04:13:53.760
Ooh, fate speaker said, sniffing at the

04:13:53.760 --> 04:13:54.059
darkness.

04:13:54.120 --> 04:13:57.239
I foresee that this is going to be mad

04:13:57.239 --> 04:13:57.719
scary.

04:13:57.780 --> 04:13:58.860
You go first.

04:13:58.920 --> 04:14:02.040
It felt like a volcano was about to

04:14:02.040 --> 04:14:03.780
explode out of Starflight's chest.

04:14:03.840 --> 04:14:08.100
Well, if anyone does catch us, they can't

04:14:08.100 --> 04:14:08.819
kill both of us.

04:14:08.879 --> 04:14:10.739
They need at least one of us alive.

04:14:10.799 --> 04:14:13.500
He didn't find that thought very

04:14:13.500 --> 04:14:16.020
reassuring as he climbed into the dark

04:14:16.020 --> 04:14:18.780
tunnel and felt sharp black rocks digging

04:14:18.780 --> 04:14:20.219
into his talons.

04:14:20.280 --> 04:14:22.260
The only thing that was oddly comforting

04:14:22.260 --> 04:14:24.780
was the sound of fate speaker clambering

04:14:24.780 --> 04:14:26.879
behind him, close enough to step on his

04:14:26.879 --> 04:14:27.899
tail a few times.

04:14:27.959 --> 04:14:31.379
The tunnel sloped up and around in a kind

04:14:31.379 --> 04:14:31.979
of spiral.

04:14:32.040 --> 04:14:34.739
When a last twist suddenly left them

04:14:34.739 --> 04:14:36.059
standing in an open cave.

04:14:36.120 --> 04:14:37.799
They were both caught by surprise.

04:14:37.860 --> 04:14:41.100
Starflight froze, and fate speaker

04:14:41.100 --> 04:14:42.000
blundered into him.

04:14:42.120 --> 04:14:43.860
This is it.

04:14:43.979 --> 04:14:48.059
On one wall, the circle shape punctured

04:14:48.059 --> 04:14:50.280
with holes, looking out over the council

04:14:50.280 --> 04:14:53.340
chamber, on another wall, the screen that

04:14:53.340 --> 04:14:55.799
faced the throne room, and then there was

04:14:55.799 --> 04:14:57.899
a 3rd wall with only a few carefully

04:14:57.899 --> 04:15:00.420
hidden eye holes for spying on something

04:15:00.420 --> 04:15:03.120
or someone, or somewhere without being

04:15:03.120 --> 04:15:03.479
noticed.

04:15:03.540 --> 04:15:06.299
But no queen.

04:15:06.360 --> 04:15:09.959
There were no dragons here, no signs of

04:15:09.959 --> 04:15:10.260
life.

04:15:10.319 --> 04:15:12.600
Where else could she be?

04:15:12.659 --> 04:15:14.280
Or am I right?

04:15:14.340 --> 04:15:16.020
Is she dead after all?

04:15:16.079 --> 04:15:19.559
In the center of the cave was an enormous

04:15:19.559 --> 04:15:22.559
cauldron full of lava, big enough for 2

04:15:22.559 --> 04:15:23.520
morrow's ears.

04:15:23.579 --> 04:15:26.940
It looked like a jagged black bowl that

04:15:26.940 --> 04:15:28.979
had been yanked and pummeled out of the

04:15:28.979 --> 04:15:29.879
volcanic stone.

04:15:29.940 --> 04:15:33.180
Molten lava filled it to the brim

04:15:33.180 --> 04:15:35.340
bubbling and spitting and gurgling

04:15:35.340 --> 04:15:35.879
weirdly.

04:15:35.940 --> 04:15:39.420
A few drops spattered over the side, and

04:15:39.420 --> 04:15:41.520
Starflight took a cautious step back

04:15:41.520 --> 04:15:43.500
remembering the stinging burn on his

04:15:43.500 --> 04:15:43.680
foot.

04:15:43.799 --> 04:15:47.399
The room was stiflingly hot, almost

04:15:47.399 --> 04:15:48.540
painfully so.

04:15:48.600 --> 04:15:51.180
Starflight slid around the cauldron

04:15:51.180 --> 04:15:53.760
hugging the walls, to peer through the

04:15:53.760 --> 04:15:55.620
secret eye holes across from the tunnel

04:15:55.620 --> 04:15:56.219
entrance.

04:15:56.280 --> 04:15:57.899
Fate speaker followed him

04:15:57.899 --> 04:15:59.879
uncharacteristically quiet.

04:16:00.059 --> 04:16:02.879
Starfly didn't recognize the room on the

04:16:02.879 --> 04:16:05.399
other side of the 3rd wall, but he could

04:16:05.399 --> 04:16:08.159
see a low table and the leftover bones of

04:16:08.159 --> 04:16:09.540
prey were strewn around the floor.

04:16:09.600 --> 04:16:12.899
I bet this is where the council members

04:16:12.899 --> 04:16:15.659
eat, he said quietly to fate speaker.

04:16:15.719 --> 04:16:18.899
It's a good time to spy on dragons, when

04:16:18.899 --> 04:16:20.879
they might say anything, if they don't

04:16:20.879 --> 04:16:21.840
realize she's watching.

04:16:21.899 --> 04:16:25.139
He glanced at the other 2 screens and

04:16:25.139 --> 04:16:25.739
shook his head.

04:16:25.799 --> 04:16:28.739
Then again, it looks like she's not doing

04:16:28.739 --> 04:16:29.879
much watching right now.

04:16:29.940 --> 04:16:32.700
He leaned in to peer through at the

04:16:32.700 --> 04:16:33.600
dining cave again.

04:16:33.659 --> 04:16:37.440
Maybe you're right about fate speaker

04:16:37.440 --> 04:16:37.920
started.

04:16:37.979 --> 04:16:40.319
Then cut herself off for the cry of

04:16:40.319 --> 04:16:42.959
terror and seized Starflight's shoulder

04:16:42.959 --> 04:16:45.239
at the same time, clutching him so hard

04:16:45.239 --> 04:16:46.680
he thought she might draw blood.

04:16:46.739 --> 04:16:48.780
Ow, what?

04:16:48.840 --> 04:16:52.379
He began, then turned and saw what she

04:16:52.379 --> 04:16:52.739
saw.

04:16:52.799 --> 04:16:57.840
A dragon was rising up out of the lava.
7189
04:16:57,899 --> 04:17:02,159	Chapter 16.

04:17:02.399 --> 04:17:05.819
Starflight had been terrified plenty of

04:17:05.819 --> 04:17:07.680
times since leaving the caves where he

04:17:07.680 --> 04:17:08.040
grew up.

04:17:08.100 --> 04:17:10.739
He thought nothing could ever be worse

04:17:10.739 --> 04:17:13.200
than the moment Queen Scarlet walked in

04:17:13.200 --> 04:17:15.659
with her guards, killed Dune, and took

04:17:15.659 --> 04:17:17.100
all the dragonette's prisoner.

04:17:17.159 --> 04:17:19.379
But then there was the moment he stood in

04:17:19.379 --> 04:17:22.020
her arena. knowing that she intended for

04:17:22.020 --> 04:17:24.000
him to be violently dead by the end of

04:17:24.000 --> 04:17:24.540
the day.

04:17:24.600 --> 04:17:27.120
That was followed by the moment Queen

04:17:27.120 --> 04:17:29.100
Coral had them thrown in her prison.

04:17:29.159 --> 04:17:31.559
Tsunamis plunge through the electric

04:17:31.559 --> 04:17:32.399
eels.

04:17:32.459 --> 04:17:34.200
The Sky Wing attack on the Summer

04:17:34.200 --> 04:17:34.799
Palace.

04:17:34.860 --> 04:17:37.260
Their frantic escape right through the

04:17:37.260 --> 04:17:39.299
middle of a battle, and perhaps the

04:17:39.299 --> 04:17:41.819
actual worst, when Sonny had disappeared

04:17:41.819 --> 04:17:43.920
right in front of him in the rainforest

04:17:43.920 --> 04:17:46.440
not to mention all the scary things he'd

04:17:46.440 --> 04:17:48.239
faced since being abducted by the night

04:17:48.239 --> 04:17:48.780
wings.

04:17:48.840 --> 04:17:51.780
In fact, he'd spent most of the last few

04:17:51.780 --> 04:17:53.639
weeks in a state of near constant

04:17:53.639 --> 04:17:54.120
terror.

04:17:54.239 --> 04:17:59.459
This was a whole other level, a level of

04:17:59.459 --> 04:18:01.440
that's not scientifically possible.

04:18:01.500 --> 04:18:05.040
And has it been under the lava this whole

04:18:05.040 --> 04:18:05.399
time?

04:18:05.459 --> 04:18:08.819
And that's not possible.

04:18:08.879 --> 04:18:12.000
And now this is really it.

04:18:12.059 --> 04:18:14.579
And there's no one to protect me, and I'm

04:18:14.579 --> 04:18:17.280
definitely, absolutely 100% going to die

04:18:17.280 --> 04:18:19.920
because that is a dragon who lives in

04:18:19.920 --> 04:18:20.639
lava.

04:18:20.700 --> 04:18:24.479
Its head and wings came first, and a

04:18:24.479 --> 04:18:27.120
fountain of gold and molten lava, and

04:18:27.120 --> 04:18:29.579
then a set of claws shot out, and

04:18:29.579 --> 04:18:31.200
clutched the side of the cauldron.

04:18:31.260 --> 04:18:33.959
The dragon shook itself, sending

04:18:33.959 --> 04:18:35.639
splatters of lava flying.

04:18:35.760 --> 04:18:38.700
Slowly the lava poured off her head

04:18:38.700 --> 04:18:41.700
revealing a thick set neck, a battle

04:18:41.700 --> 04:18:45.000
scarred snout, and black scales that

04:18:45.000 --> 04:18:47.520
gleamed like polished ebony against the

04:18:47.520 --> 04:18:49.139
orange yellow pool around her.

04:18:49.200 --> 04:18:50.819
Starflight?

04:18:50.879 --> 04:18:53.159
Starflight, Starflight, Fate speaker

04:18:53.159 --> 04:18:55.559
whispered in a panicked rush, shaking his

04:18:55.559 --> 04:18:56.520
arm violently.

04:18:56.700 --> 04:18:57.299
Do something?

04:18:57.420 --> 04:18:58.979
Like what?

04:18:59.100 --> 04:19:00.479
he whispered back.

04:19:00.540 --> 04:19:02.940
The tunnel was on the far side of the

04:19:02.940 --> 04:19:03.540
cauldron.

04:19:03.600 --> 04:19:05.579
They'd have to get past the dragon and

04:19:05.579 --> 04:19:07.680
the lava she was dripping everywhere if

04:19:07.680 --> 04:19:09.780
they wanted to run away, which was what

04:19:09.780 --> 04:19:12.059
he really, really wanted to do.

04:19:12.120 --> 04:19:18.659
The dragon in the lava leaned forward and

04:19:18.659 --> 04:19:19.739
glared at them.

04:19:19.799 --> 04:19:22.920
Buzzing white steam seemed to be rising

04:19:22.920 --> 04:19:23.760
from her scales.

04:19:23.819 --> 04:19:27.299
Her tongue flicked in and out as she

04:19:27.299 --> 04:19:29.879
studied the 2 dragonettes, and Starflight

04:19:29.879 --> 04:19:30.479
realized.

04:19:30.540 --> 04:19:33.120
There was a glint of icy blue in the

04:19:33.120 --> 04:19:34.680
depths of her dark eyes.

04:19:34.680 --> 04:19:37.739
When she opened her mouth, he spotted 2

04:19:37.739 --> 04:19:39.840
teeth that were the same shade of blue

04:19:39.840 --> 04:19:42.299
looking more like icicles than regular

04:19:42.299 --> 04:19:42.899
teeth.

04:19:42.959 --> 04:19:44.940
Hoo.

04:19:45.000 --> 04:19:47.219
She rasped suddenly.

04:19:47.340 --> 04:19:50.700
Her voice was hard to hear, creaky, and

04:19:50.700 --> 04:19:54.899
quiet, and rough, and eerie, like claws

04:19:54.899 --> 04:19:57.120
scraping on ice several caves away.

04:19:57.180 --> 04:19:59.940
No one?

04:20:00.000 --> 04:20:01.440
Starflight stammered.

04:20:01.559 --> 04:20:03.479
Please don't kill us.

04:20:03.540 --> 04:20:05.219
Fate speaker squeaked.

04:20:05.280 --> 04:20:11.520
Don't make me. said the lava dragon.

04:20:11.579 --> 04:20:12.959
She hissed again.

04:20:13.020 --> 04:20:15.120
Her claws flexing around the edge of the

04:20:15.120 --> 04:20:15.659
cauldron.

04:20:15.719 --> 04:20:17.819
How?

04:20:17.940 --> 04:20:19.979
How?

04:20:19.979 --> 04:20:21.540
Did we find you?

04:20:21.600 --> 04:20:23.280
Starflight filled in.

04:20:23.340 --> 04:20:26.520
We were looking for the queen, queen

04:20:26.520 --> 04:20:27.180
battle winner.

04:20:27.239 --> 04:20:30.780
I, said the dragon.

04:20:30.840 --> 04:20:32.700
Her eyes narrowed.

04:20:32.760 --> 04:20:34.379
You.

04:20:34.500 --> 04:20:38.159
We're, we're the dragonettes of the

04:20:38.159 --> 04:20:40.379
prophecy, fate speakers said.

04:20:40.440 --> 04:20:42.239
I'm fate speaker, and this is

04:20:42.239 --> 04:20:42.780
Starflight.

04:20:42.899 --> 04:20:45.239
Ah.

04:20:45.360 --> 04:20:48.899
The queen sank lower in the lava.

04:20:49.020 --> 04:20:51.120
Hmm.

04:20:51.239 --> 04:20:54.059
Unimpressive.

04:20:54.180 --> 04:20:57.479
How is this happening?

04:20:57.540 --> 04:20:59.219
Starflight burst out.

04:20:59.340 --> 04:21:01.979
Why aren't you dead?

04:21:02.040 --> 04:21:04.680
The temperature you're immersed in, the

04:21:04.680 --> 04:21:07.079
boiling point, the physical reaction of

04:21:07.079 --> 04:21:10.139
lava and scales, I saw what happened to

04:21:10.139 --> 04:21:11.100
vengeance.

04:21:11.159 --> 04:21:13.379
You can't be swimming in lava.

04:21:13.440 --> 04:21:15.899
It just isn't possible.

04:21:15.959 --> 04:21:19.319
Even dragons born from blood red eggs

04:21:19.319 --> 04:21:21.659
like clay, could probably only withstand

04:21:21.659 --> 04:21:23.520
that kind of heat for a minute or two.

04:21:23.639 --> 04:21:26.700
And as far as I know, night wings don't

04:21:26.700 --> 04:21:27.780
have eggs like that anyway.

04:21:27.840 --> 04:21:31.260
So, this can't be happening

04:21:31.260 --> 04:21:32.760
scientifically speaking.

04:21:32.819 --> 04:21:36.239
The queen let out a small, possibly

04:21:36.239 --> 04:21:39.239
amused snort, blowing bubbles across the

04:21:39.239 --> 04:21:40.379
surface of the lava.

04:21:40.440 --> 04:21:45.420
Masterminds, son.

04:21:45.479 --> 04:21:47.280
She rasped.

04:21:47.340 --> 04:21:50.280
She studied him for a moment, then leaned

04:21:50.280 --> 04:21:53.520
forward, opening her jaws as wide as they

04:21:53.520 --> 04:21:53.819
would go.

04:21:53.879 --> 04:21:55.799
For a moment.

04:21:55.860 --> 04:21:58.200
Starflight thought she was about to lunge

04:21:58.200 --> 04:21:59.940
out of the cauldron and bite their heads

04:21:59.940 --> 04:22:03.000
off, but then he realized, from her odd

04:22:03.000 --> 04:22:05.159
position, that she was actually holding

04:22:05.159 --> 04:22:06.899
herself so he could look inside her

04:22:06.899 --> 04:22:07.139
mouth.

04:22:07.200 --> 04:22:10.680
His fear slowly started to fade as

04:22:10.680 --> 04:22:12.899
curiosity took over, and he stepped

04:22:12.899 --> 04:22:13.260
closer.

04:22:13.319 --> 04:22:15.059
Starflight?

04:22:15.120 --> 04:22:17.280
Fate speaker whispered anxiously.

04:22:17.340 --> 04:22:19.559
This wasn't in any of my visions.

04:22:19.620 --> 04:22:21.180
I'm really not sure about this.

04:22:21.299 --> 04:22:26.700
Three moons, he said, his eyes widening.

04:22:26.819 --> 04:22:29.159
Fate speaker, look.

04:22:29.280 --> 04:22:31.559
You can see right down her throat.

04:22:31.620 --> 04:22:33.180
And it's blue.

04:22:33.239 --> 04:22:36.780
The walls of battle winner's throat were

04:22:36.780 --> 04:22:38.639
lined with what looked like pale blue

04:22:38.639 --> 04:22:42.000
froth, small swirling patterns that were

04:22:42.000 --> 04:22:44.520
feathery or sharp, and all glinted

04:22:44.520 --> 04:22:45.000
oddly.

04:22:45.059 --> 04:22:47.280
What is it?

04:22:47.340 --> 04:22:49.739
Starflight met Battle winner's eyes

04:22:49.739 --> 04:22:50.040
again.

04:22:50.100 --> 04:22:52.020
She snapped her mouth shut.

04:22:52.079 --> 04:22:55.200
I...

04:22:55.260 --> 04:22:58.680
The creak of her voice seemed to rattle

04:22:58.680 --> 04:22:59.639
her to her wingtips.

04:22:59.700 --> 04:23:02.459
She took a deep breath, tipped her whole

04:23:02.459 --> 04:23:04.680
head in the lava, and emerged again.

04:23:04.739 --> 04:23:06.780
Ice?

04:23:06.840 --> 04:23:08.340
Starflight echoed.

04:23:08.399 --> 04:23:11.219
His mind whirled into gear, trying to

04:23:11.219 --> 04:23:12.120
solve this mystery.

04:23:12.180 --> 04:23:14.520
Was this connected to the night wing

04:23:14.520 --> 04:23:15.959
bacteria that killed their prey?

04:23:16.020 --> 04:23:19.139
Or had she just swallowed a lot of ice to

04:23:19.139 --> 04:23:20.100
combat the lava?

04:23:20.159 --> 04:23:21.780
That made no sense.

04:23:21.840 --> 04:23:24.479
Where would the dragons even get ice out

04:23:24.479 --> 04:23:26.219
here on the island, where it was

04:23:26.219 --> 04:23:27.180
perpetually too warm?

04:23:27.239 --> 04:23:30.719
Queen Battle winner was watching him, as

04:23:30.719 --> 04:23:32.760
if this was a test, and she had decided

04:23:32.760 --> 04:23:34.799
to save her breath and see if he could

04:23:34.799 --> 04:23:35.340
figure it out.

04:23:35.399 --> 04:23:37.979
Her breath.

04:23:38.040 --> 04:23:40.440
Ice wings.

04:23:40.500 --> 04:23:42.120
Starflight burst out.

04:23:42.239 --> 04:23:43.620
Their weapon.

04:23:43.680 --> 04:23:45.239
The frost breath.

04:23:45.299 --> 04:23:48.659
Battle winner nodded, her heavy shoulders

04:23:48.659 --> 04:23:50.940
sliding up out of the lava and back down

04:23:50.940 --> 04:23:53.760
again, her black tongue flicked in and

04:23:53.760 --> 04:23:56.700
out again, and this time he saw that it

04:23:56.700 --> 04:23:59.100
also had a layer of thin, shimmering

04:23:59.100 --> 04:24:00.059
frost on it.

04:24:00.120 --> 04:24:05.100
You got blasted by an ice wing, he said

04:24:05.100 --> 04:24:05.579
slowly.

04:24:05.639 --> 04:24:08.819
You must have been on the continent when

04:24:08.819 --> 04:24:10.739
you ran into one.

04:24:10.860 --> 04:24:12.000
Is that it?

04:24:12.120 --> 04:24:15.420
And you fought, and it hit you.

04:24:15.479 --> 04:24:16.799
But not only outside.

04:24:16.860 --> 04:24:20.100
Maybe your mouth was open and it went

04:24:20.100 --> 04:24:22.500
right in and down your throat to freeze

04:24:22.500 --> 04:24:23.280
your insides.

04:24:23.399 --> 04:24:26.040
Which means you should have been dead

04:24:26.040 --> 04:24:26.940
within a day.

04:24:27.000 --> 04:24:29.579
The queen flicked her wings back

04:24:29.579 --> 04:24:32.219
scattering sizzling orange droplets

04:24:32.219 --> 04:24:32.579
around.

04:24:32.639 --> 04:24:36.239
Not so easy.

04:24:36.299 --> 04:24:38.579
She growled.

04:24:38.639 --> 04:24:42.000
To kill you, Starflight finished.

04:24:42.059 --> 04:24:43.860
You made it back here.

04:24:43.920 --> 04:24:46.139
And the lava.

04:24:46.200 --> 04:24:48.239
The lava stops the effects of the

04:24:48.239 --> 04:24:48.659
freezing.

04:24:48.719 --> 04:24:49.620
Is that it?

04:24:49.739 --> 04:24:52.200
Indeed.

04:24:52.319 --> 04:24:54.719
The queen hissed again.

04:24:54.780 --> 04:24:56.940
A balance.

04:24:57.000 --> 04:24:59.399
But how?

04:24:59.459 --> 04:25:00.959
Fate speaker said.

04:25:01.020 --> 04:25:03.299
I mean, how did you know the lava

04:25:03.299 --> 04:25:04.620
wouldn't just kill you right away?

04:25:04.680 --> 04:25:07.680
Starflight could imagine it clearly.

04:25:07.739 --> 04:25:10.739
Battle winner on the continent, perhaps

04:25:10.739 --> 04:25:12.059
looking for a new home for the night

04:25:12.059 --> 04:25:14.819
wings, running into an ice wing, and

04:25:14.819 --> 04:25:17.520
nearly dying in battle, but she staggered

04:25:17.520 --> 04:25:19.500
back through that long, awful flight to

04:25:19.500 --> 04:25:22.559
the island, feeling colder and colder and

04:25:22.559 --> 04:25:24.540
closer to death by the minute.

04:25:24.600 --> 04:25:26.639
The fire that burned inside fire

04:25:26.639 --> 04:25:29.159
breathing dragons, like night wings and

04:25:29.159 --> 04:25:30.899
sky wings, would have been working

04:25:30.899 --> 04:25:32.940
against the eyes to keep her alive for a

04:25:32.940 --> 04:25:34.799
while, but it wouldn't be enough to save

04:25:34.799 --> 04:25:35.040
her.

04:25:35.100 --> 04:25:38.040
By the time she'd made it to the island

04:25:38.040 --> 04:25:40.319
she would have been shivering violently

04:25:40.319 --> 04:25:43.079
and feeling terribly sick as her stomach

04:25:43.079 --> 04:25:45.299
and intestines began to freeze and fuse

04:25:45.299 --> 04:25:48.299
together, spreading the icy plague out

04:25:48.299 --> 04:25:49.920
from her organs toward her scales.

04:25:49.979 --> 04:25:52.979
At that point, he could imagine she felt

04:25:52.979 --> 04:25:56.219
so cold that diving into lava sounded

04:25:56.219 --> 04:25:58.319
better than anything, even if it killed

04:25:58.319 --> 04:25:59.100
her.

04:25:59.159 --> 04:26:01.020
And maybe she expected it to.

04:26:01.079 --> 04:26:03.180
It couldn't be worse than what she was

04:26:03.180 --> 04:26:03.719
already feeling.

04:26:03.780 --> 04:26:07.079
And instead, it saved her life.

04:26:07.139 --> 04:26:09.780
Queen Battle Winner was alive now.

04:26:09.840 --> 04:26:11.940
But the frost breath was still inside

04:26:11.940 --> 04:26:12.299
her.

04:26:12.360 --> 04:26:15.540
She could never leave the lava, or else

04:26:15.540 --> 04:26:16.559
it would finish its work.

04:26:16.620 --> 04:26:20.340
The rest was details, although he was

04:26:20.340 --> 04:26:22.620
still curious about all of it, like who

04:26:22.620 --> 04:26:25.260
knew her secret besides greatness, how

04:26:25.260 --> 04:26:27.299
this room had been built, and the screens

04:26:27.299 --> 04:26:29.940
put in, how the cauldron had been filled

04:26:29.940 --> 04:26:31.379
with lava and prepared for her.

04:26:31.440 --> 04:26:33.780
He wondered if she could still eat.

04:26:33.840 --> 04:26:36.540
Or if she existed in kind of a suspended

04:26:36.540 --> 04:26:38.879
state, right on the edge of death.

04:26:38.940 --> 04:26:41.760
The queen was watching him closely

04:26:41.760 --> 04:26:44.340
perhaps reading his mind as he put all

04:26:44.340 --> 04:26:45.239
the pieces together.

04:26:45.299 --> 04:26:47.760
He guessed that speaking was painful

04:26:47.760 --> 04:26:50.340
scraping and cracking the ice in her

04:26:50.340 --> 04:26:52.559
throat and mouth, and that was why she

04:26:52.559 --> 04:26:54.120
did as little of it as she possibly

04:26:54.120 --> 04:26:54.360
could.

04:26:54.420 --> 04:26:58.379
I'm sorry, he said to her finally.

04:26:58.440 --> 04:27:01.139
It seems like an awful thing.

04:27:01.200 --> 04:27:02.579
What's happened to you?

04:27:02.700 --> 04:27:06.479
Battle winner's head spikes flattened and

04:27:06.479 --> 04:27:08.219
her snout lifted.

04:27:08.280 --> 04:27:11.520
No pity, she snarled.

04:27:11.579 --> 04:27:14.520
Revenge soon.

04:27:14.639 --> 04:27:18.840
That sounded ominous, but worrying about

04:27:18.840 --> 04:27:20.040
ice wings would have to wait.

04:27:20.100 --> 04:27:22.440
Starflight reached out and took one of

04:27:22.440 --> 04:27:24.120
fate speaker's talons in his.

04:27:24.180 --> 04:27:27.479
We wanted to talk to you about the

04:27:27.479 --> 04:27:29.819
prophecy, he said hesitantly.

04:27:29.879 --> 04:27:33.420
We're afraid Morosier is being too cruel

04:27:33.420 --> 04:27:35.100
and interfering too much.

04:27:35.159 --> 04:27:37.680
The queen cut him off with a barking

04:27:37.680 --> 04:27:40.139
laugh and then doubled over in pain

04:27:40.139 --> 04:27:41.219
clutching her neck.

04:27:41.280 --> 04:27:44.219
After a moment, she recovered enough to

04:27:44.219 --> 04:27:44.940
glare at him.

04:27:45.000 --> 04:27:50.879
Do as he says, she hissed.

04:27:50.940 --> 04:27:55.500
The prophecy is everything.

04:27:55.559 --> 04:27:59.399
But he sent squid away to die today.

04:27:59.459 --> 04:28:02.579
Fate speaker pleaded, and he says he's

04:28:02.579 --> 04:28:05.100
going to kill me or Starflight, and the

04:28:05.100 --> 04:28:06.840
rain wing prisoners are being treated so

04:28:06.840 --> 04:28:07.440
terribly.

04:28:07.500 --> 04:28:10.440
Please, it doesn't have to be like this

04:28:10.440 --> 04:28:11.399
does it?

04:28:11.459 --> 04:28:15.239
Anything to...

04:28:15.239 --> 04:28:18.479
Save the tribe.

04:28:18.600 --> 04:28:20.340
Said the Queen.

04:28:20.399 --> 04:28:23.459
She began to sink down into the lava.

04:28:23.520 --> 04:28:26.280
Leave now.

04:28:26.340 --> 04:28:31.200
Wait, please, cried fate speaker.

04:28:31.260 --> 04:28:33.719
But lava was already closing over the

04:28:33.719 --> 04:28:34.920
dark dragon's head.

04:28:34.979 --> 04:28:36.540
She was gone.

04:28:36.600 --> 04:28:38.040
They had failed.
7496
04:28:38,100 --> 04:28:42,659	Chapter 17.

04:28:42.840 --> 04:28:46.739
Fate speaker and Starflight trudged back

04:28:46.739 --> 04:28:48.420
to the dormitory in weary silence.

04:28:48.540 --> 04:28:51.239
He hoped against hope that dawn was

04:28:51.239 --> 04:28:53.159
farther away than Deathbringer had said

04:28:53.159 --> 04:28:55.680
but he had a feeling Marosera would be

04:28:55.680 --> 04:28:58.079
breathing angry heat into his face within

04:28:58.079 --> 04:28:59.760
a horribly short span of time.

04:28:59.819 --> 04:29:02.100
Poor squid.

04:29:02.219 --> 04:29:05.100
Fate speaker said, pausing outside the

04:29:05.100 --> 04:29:06.059
dormitory entrance.

04:29:06.120 --> 04:29:08.579
I guess now we'll have to work with your

04:29:08.579 --> 04:29:09.540
sea wing instead.

04:29:09.600 --> 04:29:12.540
She sighed and headed back to her

04:29:12.540 --> 04:29:13.319
sleeping spot.

04:29:13.379 --> 04:29:16.440
Chills rippled through Starflight's

04:29:16.440 --> 04:29:18.840
scales, like the clouds billowing outside

04:29:18.840 --> 04:29:19.500
the skylight.

04:29:19.620 --> 04:29:21.600
Tsunami.

04:29:21.659 --> 04:29:24.180
That was who we had to warn.

04:29:24.239 --> 04:29:28.559
Maru Seer had said, We have another sea

04:29:28.559 --> 04:29:29.159
wing.

04:29:29.219 --> 04:29:31.739
We just have to retrieve her from the

04:29:31.739 --> 04:29:32.579
rainforest.

04:29:32.639 --> 04:29:35.219
Had they gone after her already?

04:29:35.280 --> 04:29:36.600
Had they tried?

04:29:36.659 --> 04:29:38.159
Was she all right?

04:29:38.219 --> 04:29:41.399
I can warn her, if it's not too late?

04:29:41.459 --> 04:29:44.700
He hurried to his bed, and scrabbled

04:29:44.700 --> 04:29:46.440
among the rocks until he found the tiny

04:29:46.440 --> 04:29:48.120
hole where he'd stashed the dream

04:29:48.120 --> 04:29:48.659
visitor.

04:29:48.780 --> 04:29:50.879
This time he'd find someone in the

04:29:50.879 --> 04:29:52.260
rainforest who would listen to him.

04:29:52.379 --> 04:29:53.459
He had to.

04:29:53.520 --> 04:29:56.340
He pulled the blanket over himself again

04:29:56.340 --> 04:29:59.219
and cupped the jewel in his talons, then

04:29:59.219 --> 04:30:00.059
pressed it to his head.

04:30:00.120 --> 04:30:01.979
Tsunami.

04:30:02.040 --> 04:30:03.360
Please be there.

04:30:03.420 --> 04:30:04.860
Tsunami.

04:30:04.920 --> 04:30:09.059
As always, his 1st thought was of Sonny

04:30:09.059 --> 04:30:11.040
and then the others flashed through his

04:30:11.040 --> 04:30:11.340
head.

04:30:11.399 --> 04:30:15.719
Tsunami, clay, glory, and then he was

04:30:15.719 --> 04:30:16.379
falling.

04:30:16.440 --> 04:30:18.959
Suddenly, through a bright, cloudless

04:30:18.959 --> 04:30:19.620
blue sky.

04:30:19.680 --> 04:30:22.559
He snapped his wings open, catching a

04:30:22.559 --> 04:30:24.180
rising wind, and looked up.

04:30:24.299 --> 04:30:27.959
Above him, glimmering in the sun, where 5

04:30:27.959 --> 04:30:28.379
shapes.

04:30:28.440 --> 04:30:31.079
He recognized Sonny immediately.

04:30:31.139 --> 04:30:33.420
Her golden scales couldn't be mistaken

04:30:33.420 --> 04:30:34.319
for anyone else's.

04:30:34.379 --> 04:30:36.899
She was playing a looping game of chase

04:30:36.899 --> 04:30:37.680
with clay.

04:30:37.739 --> 04:30:40.020
Her quick agility outmaneuvering his

04:30:40.020 --> 04:30:42.000
giant wings, both of them laughing.

04:30:42.059 --> 04:30:44.940
Tsunami and glory circled them, calling

04:30:44.940 --> 04:30:45.959
out suggestions.

04:30:46.020 --> 04:30:48.959
Glory's wings were dark purple, and she

04:30:48.959 --> 04:30:51.180
wore a small woven crown of iridescent

04:30:51.180 --> 04:30:53.459
ruby red flowers, and there was

04:30:53.459 --> 04:30:55.860
Starflight himself, flying along with the

04:30:55.860 --> 04:30:58.020
others and smiling, like nothing could

04:30:58.020 --> 04:30:58.680
ever be wrong.

04:30:58.739 --> 04:31:02.760
He looked different here, bigger, kinder

04:31:02.760 --> 04:31:04.079
warmer somehow.

04:31:04.139 --> 04:31:06.299
In fact, they all did.

04:31:06.360 --> 04:31:09.120
Tsunami and Glory rarely smiled so much

04:31:09.120 --> 04:31:10.020
in real life.

04:31:10.079 --> 04:31:12.780
Clay was almost never this fast or

04:31:12.780 --> 04:31:13.319
graceful.

04:31:13.379 --> 04:31:15.840
Whose dream is this?

04:31:15.959 --> 04:31:18.360
He wondered, but it wasn't hard to

04:31:18.360 --> 04:31:18.600
guess.

04:31:18.659 --> 04:31:21.420
Sunny darted away from the others I could

04:31:21.420 --> 04:31:23.340
dragonfly, and dropped toward him

04:31:23.340 --> 04:31:23.819
beaming.

04:31:23.879 --> 04:31:26.940
Two of you in one dream, she said

04:31:26.940 --> 04:31:27.479
happily.

04:31:27.540 --> 04:31:29.280
How weird is that?

04:31:29.399 --> 04:31:32.040
She flitted around him, brushed her wings

04:31:32.040 --> 04:31:34.079
against his. and then zipped back up to

04:31:34.079 --> 04:31:35.219
tug on Clay's tail.

04:31:35.280 --> 04:31:37.739
He couldn't bring himself to speak.

04:31:37.799 --> 04:31:40.799
Being near her, it all came rushing

04:31:40.799 --> 04:31:41.100
back.

04:31:41.159 --> 04:31:44.219
How he'd loved her his whole life, and

04:31:44.219 --> 04:31:46.920
how impossible the whole thing was, not

04:31:46.920 --> 04:31:48.059
least because they were from different

04:31:48.059 --> 04:31:48.719
tribes.

04:31:48.840 --> 04:31:51.120
If he could make himself talk.

04:31:51.180 --> 04:31:54.059
If he could warn her about tsunami, maybe

04:31:54.059 --> 04:31:54.719
she would listen.

04:31:54.780 --> 04:31:57.840
But the blue sky was abruptly swallowed

04:31:57.840 --> 04:32:00.120
in darkness, and he was falling again

04:32:00.120 --> 04:32:02.219
until he was surrounded by bubbles and

04:32:02.219 --> 04:32:04.799
cool green light, underwater.

04:32:04.860 --> 04:32:07.920
This must be tsunami's dream.

04:32:07.979 --> 04:32:11.579
He waved his wings and spun slowly in the

04:32:11.579 --> 04:32:11.819
water.

04:32:11.879 --> 04:32:15.120
Sure enough, there she was, with her

04:32:15.120 --> 04:32:16.680
claws wrapped around the neck of a

04:32:16.680 --> 04:32:17.940
skeletal green dragon.

04:32:18.000 --> 04:32:22.739
Gil, Starflight remembered, her father

04:32:22.739 --> 04:32:25.440
the one she killed in the arena, before

04:32:25.440 --> 04:32:26.700
she knew who he was.

04:32:26.940 --> 04:32:29.219
This was a nightmare.

04:32:29.340 --> 04:32:31.799
Her face was twisted in despair.

04:32:31.860 --> 04:32:33.959
She'd never hear him like this.

04:32:34.079 --> 04:32:37.739
Her little sister, Anemone, came swimming

04:32:37.739 --> 04:32:38.040
up.

04:32:38.100 --> 04:32:40.739
And seeing her, tsunami suddenly released

04:32:40.739 --> 04:32:44.159
the older dragon, he fell back, his jaws

04:32:44.159 --> 04:32:46.139
opening and closing pitifully.

04:32:46.200 --> 04:32:48.780
Tsunami turned to anemone with her talons

04:32:48.780 --> 04:32:51.180
outstretched, like she was apologizing.

04:32:51.239 --> 04:32:54.899
But then Anemone's eyes narrowed, and she

04:32:54.899 --> 04:32:57.239
lunged toward Gil, seizing his throat

04:32:57.239 --> 04:32:57.840
herself.

04:32:57.959 --> 04:33:01.260
Her tail smacked tsunami aside as her

04:33:01.260 --> 04:33:02.700
talons sank into his neck.

04:33:02.760 --> 04:33:05.700
Thick blood bubbled out staining the

04:33:05.700 --> 04:33:05.880
water.

04:33:05.939 --> 04:33:08.819
Tsunami grabbed anemone and tried to pull

04:33:08.819 --> 04:33:09.299
her away.

04:33:09.360 --> 04:33:10.619
But it was too late.

04:33:10.740 --> 04:33:13.380
Starflight closed his eyes.

04:33:13.439 --> 04:33:16.139
He understood what tsunami was worrying

04:33:16.139 --> 04:33:19.079
about, that anemone would turn evil if

04:33:19.079 --> 04:33:21.539
she used her anima's powers, and that

04:33:21.539 --> 04:33:23.159
there was nothing tsunami could do to

04:33:23.159 --> 04:33:23.459
save her.

04:33:23.520 --> 04:33:27.180
Just one more reason why we have to stop

04:33:27.180 --> 04:33:27.840
this war.

04:33:27.900 --> 04:33:31.200
If there was no war, there would be no

04:33:31.200 --> 04:33:32.939
one trying to force anemone into using

04:33:32.939 --> 04:33:33.540
her powers.

04:33:33.599 --> 04:33:34.859
She'd be safe.

04:33:34.919 --> 04:33:38.759
Crunch, crunch, crunch, crunch.

04:33:38.819 --> 04:33:40.919
Starflight opened his eyes again.

04:33:40.979 --> 04:33:44.700
He was sitting in a vast dry cave, with

04:33:44.700 --> 04:33:46.380
torches flickering along the walls.

04:33:46.439 --> 04:33:48.899
The floor was nearly covered with all

04:33:48.899 --> 04:33:52.259
kinds of prey, four, chickens, a cow

04:33:52.259 --> 04:33:55.439
several ducks, 2 deer, and a hippo.

04:33:55.500 --> 04:33:58.259
Some of them were still alive, wandering

04:33:58.259 --> 04:34:01.080
around, bumping into walls, oblivious to

04:34:01.080 --> 04:34:02.939
the 2 dragons in the cave with them.

04:34:03.000 --> 04:34:06.360
The other dragon was Clay, who sat with

04:34:06.360 --> 04:34:08.340
his tail curled around his back talons

04:34:08.340 --> 04:34:10.619
happily munching on something charred.

04:34:10.680 --> 04:34:15.479
Oh, hey, Starflight, he said, as if it

04:34:15.479 --> 04:34:17.159
were perfectly natural for his friends to

04:34:17.159 --> 04:34:18.479
suddenly pop into his dreams.

04:34:18.540 --> 04:34:20.639
Clay!

04:34:20.700 --> 04:34:21.779
Starfly cried.

04:34:21.840 --> 04:34:23.040
You can see me.

04:34:23.159 --> 04:34:25.080
Clay blinked a few times.

04:34:25.139 --> 04:34:28.860
Should I not be able to see you?

04:34:28.979 --> 04:34:32.939
This isn't just a dream, Starflight said

04:34:32.939 --> 04:34:33.299
quickly.

04:34:33.360 --> 04:34:34.500
I'm really here.

04:34:34.560 --> 04:34:36.779
I mean, I'm really talking to you.

04:34:36.840 --> 04:34:40.139
Of course you're really talking to me.

04:34:40.200 --> 04:34:42.180
Clay said cheerfully.

04:34:42.240 --> 04:34:43.319
Hungry?

04:34:43.380 --> 04:34:45.779
There's a great pheasant around here

04:34:45.779 --> 04:34:46.259
somewhere.

04:34:46.319 --> 04:34:49.139
He looked around, scratching his head.

04:34:49.259 --> 04:34:51.119
Oh, uh.

04:34:51.180 --> 04:34:53.279
I think I already ate it.

04:34:53.340 --> 04:34:54.360
Sorry.

04:34:54.479 --> 04:34:58.380
Starflight was hungry, but he knew dream

04:34:58.380 --> 04:34:59.880
food wouldn't do him any good.

04:34:59.939 --> 04:35:02.099
Clay, listen to me.

04:35:02.159 --> 04:35:04.500
I'm using a dream visitor.

04:35:04.560 --> 04:35:06.900
I'm talking to you from the Nightwing

04:35:06.900 --> 04:35:07.259
Kingdom.

04:35:07.319 --> 04:35:11.700
Very cool, Clay said in an agreeable

04:35:11.700 --> 04:35:12.119
voice.

04:35:12.180 --> 04:35:13.919
How about a pig?

04:35:14.040 --> 04:35:15.360
No, wait.

04:35:15.419 --> 04:35:16.919
I ate that too.

04:35:16.979 --> 04:35:19.200
I'm serious.

04:35:19.259 --> 04:35:21.779
Starflight said, lashing his tail.

04:35:21.840 --> 04:35:24.299
Don't you remember learning about dream

04:35:24.299 --> 04:35:24.959
visitors?

04:35:25.020 --> 04:35:27.659
There are these ancient sapphires that

04:35:27.659 --> 04:35:29.459
were animus touched generations ago.

04:35:29.520 --> 04:35:32.520
I found one, and I'm using it to visit

04:35:32.520 --> 04:35:34.380
your dream and tell you something really

04:35:34.380 --> 04:35:35.220
important.

04:35:35.279 --> 04:35:38.159
Clay's forehead was scrunched in a

04:35:38.159 --> 04:35:38.939
puzzled way.

04:35:39.000 --> 04:35:41.279
Sure, Starflight.

04:35:41.400 --> 04:35:44.099
I have dreams about you lecturing me all

04:35:44.099 --> 04:35:44.459
the time.

04:35:44.520 --> 04:35:47.459
That stopped Starflight for a moment.

04:35:47.520 --> 04:35:48.959
You do?

04:35:49.080 --> 04:35:52.380
Clay drew himself up and adopted a stuffy

04:35:52.380 --> 04:35:53.279
scolding voice.

04:35:53.340 --> 04:35:55.680
Weren't you listening?

04:35:55.799 --> 04:35:58.919
Didn't you read the scrolls?

04:35:58.979 --> 04:36:02.279
That was before the scalding?

04:36:02.340 --> 04:36:04.380
Everyone knows that?

04:36:04.439 --> 04:36:07.079
The scorching.

04:36:07.139 --> 04:36:09.180
Starflight corrected automatically.

04:36:09.240 --> 04:36:11.099
And I do not sound like that.

04:36:11.159 --> 04:36:14.520
Sure, Clay said.

04:36:14.580 --> 04:36:17.400
Anyway, Hippo?

04:36:17.459 --> 04:36:19.680
Starflight stamped one foot.

04:36:19.740 --> 04:36:22.020
Fine, but just listen.

04:36:22.080 --> 04:36:24.000
Tsunami is in danger.

04:36:24.060 --> 04:36:26.520
Morosier and the Night Wings are coming

04:36:26.520 --> 04:36:26.939
after her.

04:36:27.000 --> 04:36:28.860
Will you tell her that?

04:36:28.919 --> 04:36:32.219
Look, Clay said delightedly.

04:36:32.279 --> 04:36:34.379
My brothers and sisters.

04:36:34.500 --> 04:36:37.020
He jumped up and hurried to the cave

04:36:37.020 --> 04:36:39.540
entrance, where a small band of mud wings

04:36:39.540 --> 04:36:40.380
were coming in.

04:36:40.439 --> 04:36:43.079
The smallest dragonette jumped up to hug

04:36:43.079 --> 04:36:45.359
Clay's big neck, and the largest one

04:36:45.359 --> 04:36:47.039
inclined his head with a friendly smile.

04:36:47.099 --> 04:36:50.759
Starflight hadn't met Clay's siblings, but

04:36:50.759 --> 04:36:52.259
he'd heard about Clay's encounter with

04:36:52.259 --> 04:36:53.399
them in the mudwing village.

04:36:53.459 --> 04:36:55.740
They were all soldiers now in the great

04:36:55.740 --> 04:36:58.259
war, fighting under Queen Moorhen on

04:36:58.259 --> 04:37:00.540
Burns side, even though they weren't full

04:37:00.540 --> 04:37:01.020
grown yet.

04:37:01.080 --> 04:37:03.479
One of them had died in battle already.

04:37:03.599 --> 04:37:06.479
More dragons we need to save.

04:37:06.540 --> 04:37:07.680
He thought.

04:37:07.740 --> 04:37:10.259
Anxiety and fear turning his scales

04:37:10.259 --> 04:37:11.099
cold.

04:37:11.159 --> 04:37:13.259
He wasn't sure Clay had really listened

04:37:13.259 --> 04:37:13.560
to him.

04:37:13.619 --> 04:37:15.119
He had to keep trying.

04:37:15.180 --> 04:37:18.959
Glory, he thought, closing his eyes.

04:37:19.020 --> 04:37:21.840
The sound of paper rustling let him know

04:37:21.840 --> 04:37:23.819
that he was somewhere new, right before

04:37:23.819 --> 04:37:24.540
he opened them again.

04:37:24.599 --> 04:37:27.899
Glory sat at a low table in one of the

04:37:27.899 --> 04:37:30.539
treetop huts in the rainforest, studying

04:37:30.539 --> 04:37:30.959
a scroll.

04:37:31.020 --> 04:37:33.479
In her own dream she wasn't wearing a

04:37:33.479 --> 04:37:35.639
crown, and she looked more tired than

04:37:35.639 --> 04:37:36.060
anything else.

04:37:36.119 --> 04:37:39.359
Her scales were dark green and dappled

04:37:39.359 --> 04:37:41.279
with light, matching the leaves around

04:37:41.279 --> 04:37:41.819
her.

04:37:41.880 --> 04:37:43.979
The furry shape of her sloth curled

04:37:43.979 --> 04:37:44.520
around her neck.

04:37:44.580 --> 04:37:48.599
Glory, Starflight said, his voice

04:37:48.599 --> 04:37:49.380
breaking.

04:37:49.380 --> 04:37:50.520
Would she listen to him?

04:37:50.580 --> 04:37:53.340
He remembered what he'd heard Sonny say

04:37:53.340 --> 04:37:54.900
the last time he'd used the dream

04:37:54.900 --> 04:37:55.500
visitor.

04:37:55.560 --> 04:37:58.259
If Glory thought he was a traitor, she

04:37:58.259 --> 04:37:59.520
wouldn't have any reason to believe

04:37:59.520 --> 04:38:00.779
anything, he said.

04:38:01.080 --> 04:38:04.500
The new queen of the rain wings slowly

04:38:04.500 --> 04:38:05.819
raised her head and met his eyes.

04:38:05.880 --> 04:38:08.159
They stared at each other for a long

04:38:08.159 --> 04:38:10.740
moment, her green eyes searching for

04:38:10.740 --> 04:38:11.520
something in his face.

04:38:11.580 --> 04:38:14.520
Wow, she said.

04:38:14.580 --> 04:38:16.799
You found a dream visitor.

04:38:16.860 --> 04:38:18.360
He exhaled.

04:38:18.419 --> 04:38:20.759
Feeling relief flood through his scales.

04:38:20.819 --> 04:38:23.279
Of course, she remembered learning about

04:38:23.279 --> 04:38:24.060
them.

04:38:24.119 --> 04:38:25.619
He'd always wished he could remember

04:38:25.619 --> 04:38:28.259
things as easily as she did, instead of

04:38:28.259 --> 04:38:29.519
having to study so hard all the time.

04:38:29.580 --> 04:38:33.360
I didn't run off, he said in a rush.

04:38:33.419 --> 04:38:35.099
The night wings took me.

04:38:35.159 --> 04:38:37.560
I swear, glory, I would never have left

04:38:37.560 --> 04:38:37.979
you all.

04:38:38.040 --> 04:38:42.720
Morusir is, is testing me to see if I'm

04:38:42.720 --> 04:38:43.799
worthy of the prophecy.

04:38:43.860 --> 04:38:46.500
He has these other dragonettes that he

04:38:46.500 --> 04:38:47.400
wants to use instead.

04:38:47.459 --> 04:38:50.700
Only he needs a sea wing now, so tsunamis

04:38:50.700 --> 04:38:52.080
in danger, and I had to warn you.

04:38:52.139 --> 04:38:54.000
Stop, stop.

04:38:54.060 --> 04:38:56.939
Glory said, rolling up her scroll and

04:38:56.939 --> 04:38:57.659
leaning on the table.

04:38:57.720 --> 04:38:59.520
Tell me everything.

04:38:59.580 --> 04:39:01.500
So he did.

04:39:01.560 --> 04:39:03.720
From the moment he was abducted through

04:39:03.720 --> 04:39:05.400
the terrifying encounter with a night

04:39:05.400 --> 04:39:06.299
wing queen.

04:39:06.360 --> 04:39:09.119
At 1st he had that sinking sensation in

04:39:09.119 --> 04:39:11.279
his stomach again, worrying that he was

04:39:11.279 --> 04:39:12.119
betraying someone.

04:39:12.180 --> 04:39:14.220
This time his tribe.

04:39:14.279 --> 04:39:16.919
But then he thought of orchid, clamped to

04:39:16.919 --> 04:39:20.039
the wall, the sky wings burning, and

04:39:20.039 --> 04:39:23.099
squid flying slowly away to his death, and

04:39:23.099 --> 04:39:24.659
he squashed any guilty felt.

04:39:24.720 --> 04:39:26.939
He was sure now who deserved his

04:39:26.939 --> 04:39:27.419
loyalty.

04:39:27.479 --> 04:39:31.439
So, he finished, I'm worried about

04:39:31.439 --> 04:39:33.840
tsunami, please tell her to be careful.

04:39:33.900 --> 04:39:35.639
Glory laughed.

04:39:35.700 --> 04:39:37.080
Oh, sure.

04:39:37.139 --> 04:39:39.060
And you tell Clay to stop being hungry.

04:39:39.119 --> 04:39:42.000
Starflight felt a smile trying to

04:39:42.000 --> 04:39:43.020
struggle onto his face.

04:39:43.080 --> 04:39:46.200
He really does dream about food, it turns

04:39:46.200 --> 04:39:47.400
out, he said.

04:39:47.459 --> 04:39:51.360
Like, lots and lots of food.

04:39:51.419 --> 04:39:55.439
Oh, clay, glory said affectionately.

04:39:55.500 --> 04:39:58.860
Well, apparently I dream about homework

04:39:58.860 --> 04:40:00.840
even though there aren't any scrolls in

04:40:00.840 --> 04:40:01.500
the rainforest.

04:40:01.560 --> 04:40:04.259
She waved her talons at the dream table

04:40:04.259 --> 04:40:06.299
in front of her, and then her face turned

04:40:06.299 --> 04:40:07.740
serious again.

04:40:07.799 --> 04:40:10.200
I'll talk to tsunami and put some guards

04:40:10.200 --> 04:40:10.560
on her.

04:40:10.619 --> 04:40:12.360
But I'm more worried about you.

04:40:12.419 --> 04:40:15.479
We're not ready to attack yet, but if

04:40:15.479 --> 04:40:16.020
you're in danger.

04:40:16.200 --> 04:40:18.840
She carved a line in the table with one

04:40:18.840 --> 04:40:19.500
of her claws.

04:40:19.560 --> 04:40:23.400
I mean, it sounds like Morrow Seer might

04:40:23.400 --> 04:40:24.240
kill you at any moment.

04:40:24.299 --> 04:40:26.580
She looked out the window.

04:40:26.639 --> 04:40:28.860
Where glimmers of rainbow wings were

04:40:28.860 --> 04:40:30.779
visible in the trees around them.

04:40:30.840 --> 04:40:33.540
But my tribe, they're not ready.

04:40:33.599 --> 04:40:36.900
If I take them through today, they'll be

04:40:36.900 --> 04:40:37.380
slaughtered.

04:40:37.500 --> 04:40:41.099
I understand, Starflight said.

04:40:41.159 --> 04:40:43.080
Glory was a queen now.

04:40:43.139 --> 04:40:45.240
She had to think about protecting her

04:40:45.240 --> 04:40:46.860
tribe as much as taking care of her

04:40:46.860 --> 04:40:47.159
friends.

04:40:47.220 --> 04:40:49.979
Every single bit of him wanted to yell

04:40:49.979 --> 04:40:51.599
Forget the rain wings.

04:40:51.659 --> 04:40:52.619
Please rescue me.

04:40:52.680 --> 04:40:53.939
Come as soon as you can.

04:40:54.060 --> 04:40:56.400
But it was too easy for him to imagine

04:40:56.400 --> 04:40:58.020
everything glory was thinking.

04:40:58.080 --> 04:41:00.540
All the information she had to take into

04:41:00.540 --> 04:41:03.720
account. the pros and cons and best

04:41:03.720 --> 04:41:06.180
battle strategies, and unacceptable

04:41:06.180 --> 04:41:08.040
losses, and collateral damage.

04:41:08.099 --> 04:41:10.799
All the things they'd studied as distant

04:41:10.799 --> 04:41:12.659
theories, but never had to deal with

04:41:12.659 --> 04:41:13.200
themselves.

04:41:13.259 --> 04:41:17.279
So instead, he said, I'm all right.

04:41:17.340 --> 04:41:19.259
I'll take care of myself until you get

04:41:19.259 --> 04:41:19.500
here.

04:41:19.560 --> 04:41:22.799
Glory looked back at him, tilting her

04:41:22.799 --> 04:41:23.459
head to the side.

04:41:23.520 --> 04:41:26.639
Warm pink suffused with purple spread

04:41:26.639 --> 04:41:28.139
along the edges of her wings.

04:41:28.200 --> 04:41:29.819
Starflight.

04:41:29.880 --> 04:41:31.979
I think that might be the bravest thing

04:41:31.979 --> 04:41:32.639
you've ever said.

04:41:32.700 --> 04:41:35.819
He ducked his head, looking down at his

04:41:35.819 --> 04:41:36.360
talons.

04:41:36.419 --> 04:41:41.099
Well, he added, you know, don't take too

04:41:41.099 --> 04:41:41.400
long.

04:41:41.520 --> 04:41:45.119
She laughed again. and he felt a fierce

04:41:45.119 --> 04:41:47.639
awful longing to be back with his friends

04:41:47.639 --> 04:41:50.639
where, even if everything wasn't easy, At

04:41:50.639 --> 04:41:52.139
least he felt like he meant something to

04:41:52.139 --> 04:41:54.959
somebody, something more than a line in a

04:41:54.959 --> 04:41:55.500
prophecy.

04:41:55.560 --> 04:41:59.340
Her face went serious, and she toyed with

04:41:59.340 --> 04:42:00.659
a corner of one of the scrolls between

04:42:00.659 --> 04:42:01.319
her claws.

04:42:01.439 --> 04:42:05.340
So, Death Bringer is in trouble for

04:42:05.340 --> 04:42:05.819
helping me.

04:42:05.880 --> 04:42:06.959
She said.

04:42:07.020 --> 04:42:10.139
I'm sure he understood the risks when he

04:42:10.139 --> 04:42:12.540
decided to set you free, Starflight

04:42:12.540 --> 04:42:12.959
pointed out.

04:42:13.020 --> 04:42:16.680
Hmm, Glory said skeptically.

04:42:16.740 --> 04:42:19.139
I'm sure he thought he could charm his

04:42:19.139 --> 04:42:21.240
way out of anything, idiot.

04:42:21.299 --> 04:42:24.840
Well, he still might, Starflight said.

04:42:24.900 --> 04:42:27.360
I don't think greatness wants to execute

04:42:27.360 --> 04:42:27.599
him.

04:42:27.659 --> 04:42:29.819
Glory shook herself.

04:42:29.880 --> 04:42:32.220
Can you tell me anything else about the

04:42:32.220 --> 04:42:33.000
night wings?

04:42:33.060 --> 04:42:33.900
She asked.

04:42:33.959 --> 04:42:35.939
Anything that might help us when we do

04:42:35.939 --> 04:42:36.360
attack?

04:42:36.419 --> 04:42:39.840
Like, do they have mind readers posted at

04:42:39.840 --> 04:42:41.340
the tunnel entrance?

04:42:41.400 --> 04:42:43.139
That's what I would do, so they could

04:42:43.139 --> 04:42:45.419
sense anyone coming through, and maybe

04:42:45.419 --> 04:42:47.459
even read our battle plans before we got

04:42:47.459 --> 04:42:47.700
there.

04:42:47.759 --> 04:42:51.060
I want to send in a camouflaged scout

04:42:51.060 --> 04:42:53.040
just to see how many guards are in the

04:42:53.040 --> 04:42:54.900
cave now, but that's why I haven't yet.

04:42:54.959 --> 04:42:56.819
I don't dare.

04:42:56.880 --> 04:43:00.360
I don't know, Starflight said.

04:43:00.419 --> 04:43:01.560
I'm sorry.

04:43:01.619 --> 04:43:03.779
I don't know anything useful about what

04:43:03.779 --> 04:43:04.860
the Night Wings are doing.

04:43:04.919 --> 04:43:07.380
I bet you know more than you think.

04:43:07.439 --> 04:43:08.520
She said.

04:43:08.580 --> 04:43:10.680
Can you tell me more about the fortress

04:43:10.680 --> 04:43:13.439
or the layout of the island, or how we

04:43:13.439 --> 04:43:14.880
might get there if we flew from the

04:43:14.880 --> 04:43:16.380
continent instead of using the tunnel?

04:43:16.500 --> 04:43:18.299
His heart sank.

04:43:18.360 --> 04:43:21.299
You'd have to get through Mudwing and

04:43:21.299 --> 04:43:24.119
Skywing territory first, he pointed out.

04:43:24.180 --> 04:43:26.700
Before you could fly across the ocean to

04:43:26.700 --> 04:43:29.279
the island, even if I could find a way to

04:43:29.279 --> 04:43:30.000
describe the route.

04:43:30.119 --> 04:43:33.540
And that would take weeks, he thought.

04:43:33.599 --> 04:43:36.060
Weeks to travel the whole length of the

04:43:36.060 --> 04:43:36.419
continent.

04:43:36.540 --> 04:43:39.360
Can I survive for weeks on my own?

04:43:39.419 --> 04:43:43.439
Yeah, it's probably not the safest plan

04:43:43.439 --> 04:43:45.299
Glory said thoughtfully.

04:43:45.360 --> 04:43:48.119
Starflight shifted his wings.

04:43:48.180 --> 04:43:51.479
He felt chilly air against his scales, and

04:43:51.479 --> 04:43:53.520
it wasn't coming from Glory's rainforest

04:43:53.520 --> 04:43:54.299
dream.

04:43:54.360 --> 04:43:57.479
I think I have to go, he said in a

04:43:57.479 --> 04:43:58.319
panicked whisper.

04:43:58.380 --> 04:43:59.939
It must almost be dawn.

04:44:00.000 --> 04:44:03.540
All right, she said, standing up.

04:44:03.599 --> 04:44:05.939
But come back tomorrow night if you can.

04:44:06.000 --> 04:44:08.400
We can figure this out, Starflight.

04:44:08.459 --> 04:44:09.900
It's going to be all right.

04:44:10.020 --> 04:44:12.840
She stepped over the table and wrapped

04:44:12.840 --> 04:44:14.880
her wings around him, which didn't work

04:44:14.880 --> 04:44:16.380
very well since he wasn't really there

04:44:16.380 --> 04:44:18.840
but somehow, it was still comforting.

04:44:18.900 --> 04:44:20.639
See you soon.

04:44:20.759 --> 04:44:21.599
He said.

04:44:21.659 --> 04:44:23.939
Remember to watch out for tsunami.

04:44:24.000 --> 04:44:25.919
Glory rolled her eyes.

04:44:25.979 --> 04:44:29.040
At this point, I bet most of my tribe

04:44:29.040 --> 04:44:30.419
would invite the night wings to abduct

04:44:30.419 --> 04:44:30.599
her.

04:44:30.720 --> 04:44:33.900
She's not the calmest general empirea, I

04:44:33.900 --> 04:44:34.259
can tell you.

04:44:34.319 --> 04:44:37.319
Starflight smiled, and lifted the dream

04:44:37.319 --> 04:44:38.340
visitor to his forehead.

04:44:38.400 --> 04:44:40.799
The rainforest disappeared.

04:44:40.860 --> 04:44:44.220
He was back in the gloomy, dimly lit

04:44:44.220 --> 04:44:45.240
night wing dormitory.

04:44:45.299 --> 04:44:48.240
Had he heard a scrabble of claws right

04:44:48.240 --> 04:44:49.319
before he'd opened his eyes?

04:44:49.439 --> 04:44:52.860
Starflight glanced around, and realized

04:44:52.860 --> 04:44:55.319
that his blankets had shifted, so he

04:44:55.319 --> 04:44:56.580
wasn't as well hidden anymore.

04:44:56.639 --> 04:44:59.639
Or someone moved them.

04:44:59.700 --> 04:45:03.060
His talons, with a glowing sapphire

04:45:03.060 --> 04:45:04.439
trapped between them were visible.

04:45:04.500 --> 04:45:07.319
He pulled them back close to his chest

04:45:07.319 --> 04:45:09.419
then leaned over the side of the bed to

04:45:09.419 --> 04:45:11.220
tuck the jewel into its hiding spot.

04:45:11.279 --> 04:45:13.979
Sleepy mutters indicated that the other

04:45:13.979 --> 04:45:15.299
dragonettes were waking up.

04:45:15.360 --> 04:45:17.759
But when he looked around the room, he

04:45:17.759 --> 04:45:19.080
couldn't see anyone who looked awake

04:45:19.080 --> 04:45:19.319
yet.

04:45:19.380 --> 04:45:22.680
Did someone see the dream visitor?

04:45:22.740 --> 04:45:24.360
Was someone spying on me?

04:45:24.419 --> 04:45:26.880
Maybe I imagined it.

04:45:26.939 --> 04:45:29.880
But he couldn't shake the uneasy feeling

04:45:29.939 --> 04:45:32.520
that his secret might not be entirely

04:45:32.520 --> 04:45:33.360
safe anymore.
