04:45:33,419 --> 04:45:38,099	Chapter 18.

04:45:38.279 --> 04:45:41.639
Starflight lay curled on top of the

04:45:41.639 --> 04:45:43.680
blanket, trying to calm his pounding

04:45:43.680 --> 04:45:43.919
heart.

04:45:43.979 --> 04:45:46.500
I've done what I had to do.

04:45:46.560 --> 04:45:48.000
I warned glory.

04:45:48.119 --> 04:45:50.639
Now I just have to wait until they rescue

04:45:50.639 --> 04:45:50.880
me.

04:45:50.939 --> 04:45:53.340
Survive until they get here.

04:45:53.400 --> 04:45:55.139
Surely I can do that.

04:45:55.200 --> 04:45:59.639
Oh, snarled Maro Seer from the doorway.

04:45:59.700 --> 04:46:02.040
All the dragonettes in the dormitory

04:46:02.040 --> 04:46:04.319
scramble to their feet, neck spikes

04:46:04.319 --> 04:46:05.040
bristling.

04:46:05.099 --> 04:46:07.319
The Maro Sears gaze was fixed on the

04:46:07.319 --> 04:46:09.720
prophecy dragonettes, who came forward to

04:46:09.720 --> 04:46:10.500
stand in front of him.

04:46:10.560 --> 04:46:13.200
Starflight noticed that Flame kept his

04:46:13.200 --> 04:46:15.119
head down, so he didn't have to meet the

04:46:15.119 --> 04:46:16.380
Nightwing's eyes.

04:46:16.439 --> 04:46:20.639
Yesterday was stupendously unimpressive.

04:46:20.700 --> 04:46:22.500
Morosio growled.

04:46:22.560 --> 04:46:25.080
Starflight glanced over his shoulder and

04:46:25.080 --> 04:46:26.939
saw fierce teeth watching them with an

04:46:26.939 --> 04:46:27.900
alert expression.

04:46:27.959 --> 04:46:30.959
Next time you're in that kind of

04:46:30.959 --> 04:46:31.799
situation.

04:46:31.860 --> 04:46:33.419
The night wing went on.

04:46:33.479 --> 04:46:36.060
I want to be sure you can fight your way

04:46:36.060 --> 04:46:38.520
out of it, even without backup.

04:46:38.580 --> 04:46:42.659
So, today, battle training.

04:46:42.720 --> 04:46:45.599
Starflight's wings drooped.

04:46:45.720 --> 04:46:47.700
Battle training was always his least

04:46:47.700 --> 04:46:48.360
favorite thing.

04:46:48.419 --> 04:46:50.700
Next time?

04:46:50.819 --> 04:46:52.080
Viper snapped.

04:46:52.139 --> 04:46:54.180
I'm not stupid enough to go through that

04:46:54.180 --> 04:46:54.779
again.

04:46:54.840 --> 04:46:56.939
Marosir hissed at her.

04:46:57.000 --> 04:46:59.880
If you would like to take yourself back

04:46:59.880 --> 04:47:03.000
to the Thailands of peace too, there's

04:47:03.000 --> 04:47:03.479
the door.

04:47:03.599 --> 04:47:06.479
He swept his wing toward the outside.

04:47:06.540 --> 04:47:10.259
Viper hesitated, scowling, then ducked

04:47:10.259 --> 04:47:11.099
her head and stopped arguing.

04:47:11.220 --> 04:47:13.680
My throat hurts.

04:47:13.799 --> 04:47:16.139
Flame said tomorrow seer, without looking

04:47:16.139 --> 04:47:16.500
at him.

04:47:16.560 --> 04:47:19.919
There's water in the trough down there.

04:47:19.979 --> 04:47:22.680
Morris here waved at the other end of the

04:47:22.680 --> 04:47:23.279
dormitory.

04:47:23.400 --> 04:47:25.919
Catch up to us as fast as you can.

04:47:25.979 --> 04:47:29.400
The others followed Maro Seer out to the

04:47:29.400 --> 04:47:31.799
archway a few moments later, Flame caught

04:47:31.799 --> 04:47:33.900
up, coughing and scratching his throat.

04:47:34.020 --> 04:47:36.360
Maro Siera led them out to the prison

04:47:36.360 --> 04:47:38.819
caves side of the mountain, where a few

04:47:38.819 --> 04:47:41.040
rivers of lava flowed as swiftly as if

04:47:41.040 --> 04:47:42.419
they'd just erupted yesterday.

04:47:42.479 --> 04:47:45.419
The biggest was the one that ran in front

04:47:45.419 --> 04:47:46.979
of the rain wing prison caves.

04:47:47.040 --> 04:47:49.740
They landed a few lengths away from it

04:47:49.740 --> 04:47:52.380
and Starflight spotted guards in every

04:47:52.380 --> 04:47:54.779
cave mouth, bristling with armor and

04:47:54.779 --> 04:47:56.819
spears, and alarm gongs.

04:47:56.880 --> 04:47:59.939
I should remember to tell glory that to

04:47:59.939 --> 04:48:01.139
night, he noted.

04:48:01.200 --> 04:48:04.200
Looks like 2 guards for every rain wing

04:48:04.200 --> 04:48:04.560
prisoner.

04:48:04.619 --> 04:48:07.740
He saw Marosir and noticed the direction

04:48:07.740 --> 04:48:09.840
of his gaze, and hurriedly filled his

04:48:09.840 --> 04:48:10.680
mind with other thoughts.

04:48:10.740 --> 04:48:13.979
Aren't we a little close to the lava?

04:48:14.040 --> 04:48:16.799
Starflight asked, nodding at the golden

04:48:16.799 --> 04:48:18.659
orange liquid fire that flowed from the

04:48:18.659 --> 04:48:19.380
top of the mountain.

04:48:19.439 --> 04:48:23.340
Everywhere on this island is close to

04:48:23.340 --> 04:48:23.819
lava.

04:48:23.880 --> 04:48:25.500
Marasira growled.

04:48:25.560 --> 04:48:27.599
Let's begin with you two.

04:48:27.720 --> 04:48:30.959
He flicked his tail at ochre and flame. to

04:48:30.959 --> 04:48:31.979
Starflight's relief.

04:48:32.040 --> 04:48:35.759
Try to kill each other, and I'll step in

04:48:35.759 --> 04:48:36.840
when I think it's necessary.

04:48:36.900 --> 04:48:40.139
Okre regarded flame dubiously.

04:48:40.200 --> 04:48:43.319
Try to kill each other, he said.

04:48:43.380 --> 04:48:45.419
With no breakfast?

04:48:45.479 --> 04:48:49.200
Flame flexed his claws. fine by me.

04:48:49.259 --> 04:48:50.279
Any rules?

04:48:50.340 --> 04:48:53.880
There are no rules on the battlefield.

04:48:53.939 --> 04:48:55.740
Morrow Sierra pointed out.

04:48:55.799 --> 04:48:59.099
Flame immediately leaped at Ochre.

04:48:59.159 --> 04:49:01.619
His claws slashed across the mudwing's

04:49:01.619 --> 04:49:03.900
nose, leaving a bleeding gash, and then

04:49:03.900 --> 04:49:05.580
he spun and kicked the mudwing in the

04:49:05.580 --> 04:49:05.819
chest.

04:49:05.880 --> 04:49:07.439
Oh!

04:49:07.500 --> 04:49:10.259
Ogre roared, lunging at the sky wing.

04:49:10.319 --> 04:49:13.319
They grappled on the dark, rocky ground

04:49:13.319 --> 04:49:16.020
red and brown scales flashing and soon

04:49:16.020 --> 04:49:17.040
smeared with the blood.

04:49:17.099 --> 04:49:19.139
With a lava river so close.

04:49:19.259 --> 04:49:21.599
There wasn't a lot of room to maneuver or

04:49:21.599 --> 04:49:22.319
get out of the way.

04:49:22.380 --> 04:49:25.619
At one point, a burst of fire from flame

04:49:25.619 --> 04:49:28.380
nearly singed Starflight's wing, and

04:49:28.380 --> 04:49:30.840
Ochre stepped on Viper's foot, earning a

04:49:30.840 --> 04:49:31.979
ferocious hiss.

04:49:31.979 --> 04:49:36.060
Here, Fate speaker grabbed Starflight and

04:49:36.060 --> 04:49:37.259
tugged him up onto a tall boulder.

04:49:37.319 --> 04:49:40.139
He sank his claws into gaps in the rocks

04:49:40.139 --> 04:49:42.959
nervously eyeing the lava below, even

04:49:42.959 --> 04:49:44.880
from up here, he could feel the heat

04:49:44.880 --> 04:49:46.380
blasting along his scales.

04:49:46.439 --> 04:49:48.840
His fear should have helped keep him

04:49:48.840 --> 04:49:51.000
awake, but he was a little dizzy with

04:49:51.000 --> 04:49:52.919
exhaustion, and the heat made him

04:49:52.919 --> 04:49:53.459
drowsier.

04:49:53.580 --> 04:49:56.099
He rubbed his eyes, wondering what would

04:49:56.099 --> 04:49:57.060
happen if he fell asleep.

04:49:57.119 --> 04:49:59.459
He guessed he'd either tumble right off

04:49:59.459 --> 04:50:01.680
the boulder into the lava, or he'd wake

04:50:01.680 --> 04:50:04.380
up in Marrow Sears talons, dangling over

04:50:04.380 --> 04:50:04.979
the volcano.

04:50:05.040 --> 04:50:07.740
He tried to pay attention to the moves

04:50:07.740 --> 04:50:10.259
the 2 dragonets were using, but unlike

04:50:10.259 --> 04:50:12.119
Clay and Tsunami, he could never figure

04:50:12.119 --> 04:50:13.799
out what was going on in a fight like

04:50:13.799 --> 04:50:16.020
this, everyone was moving too fast.

04:50:16.080 --> 04:50:19.979
Oker suddenly burst into the air, winging

04:50:19.979 --> 04:50:22.380
in a circle around flame, yelling, stop

04:50:22.380 --> 04:50:22.680
it.

04:50:22.740 --> 04:50:23.819
I want to stop.

04:50:23.880 --> 04:50:26.040
Morris here snorted.

04:50:26.099 --> 04:50:28.979
An opponent on the battlefield wouldn't

04:50:28.979 --> 04:50:30.959
stop just because you asked them to.

04:50:31.020 --> 04:50:33.840
He's bleeding pretty seriously.

04:50:33.959 --> 04:50:35.639
Fate speaker pointed out.

04:50:35.700 --> 04:50:37.619
Look at the cut on his wing.

04:50:37.680 --> 04:50:39.299
Hmm.

04:50:39.299 --> 04:50:42.180
Maru seer said, studying ochre.

04:50:42.240 --> 04:50:44.639
All right, mud wing.

04:50:44.700 --> 04:50:47.400
You're out, and you're in.

04:50:47.459 --> 04:50:50.400
He seized fate speaker's shoulder and

04:50:50.400 --> 04:50:51.599
threw her toward flame.

04:50:51.659 --> 04:50:54.000
The Sky Wing didn't wait to be told

04:50:54.000 --> 04:50:54.419
twice.

04:50:54.479 --> 04:50:56.939
He jumped forward and sank his teeth into

04:50:56.939 --> 04:50:57.299
her neck.

04:50:57.360 --> 04:50:58.799
Yow!

04:50:58.860 --> 04:51:00.599
Fate speaker shrieked.

04:51:00.720 --> 04:51:02.639
She beat his head with her wings until he

04:51:02.639 --> 04:51:05.040
let go and fell back, and then she clawed

04:51:05.040 --> 04:51:06.720
the air in front of his face and darted

04:51:06.720 --> 04:51:06.900
away.

04:51:06.959 --> 04:51:11.279
Send me in too, Piper said tomorrow, Cyr.

04:51:11.340 --> 04:51:12.840
I want to bite her.

04:51:12.900 --> 04:51:14.340
I can definitely kill her.

04:51:14.400 --> 04:51:15.959
Just give me a chance.

04:51:16.020 --> 04:51:18.180
Go ahead and try.

04:51:18.240 --> 04:51:21.419
Morris Seer said, tilting his head at the

04:51:21.419 --> 04:51:22.319
small night wing.

04:51:22.380 --> 04:51:25.139
Viper hissed with delight and rushed

04:51:25.139 --> 04:51:27.599
forward with her tail raised, just like a

04:51:27.599 --> 04:51:28.560
scorpion attacking.

04:51:28.619 --> 04:51:31.439
Fate speaker yelped with dismay and shot

04:51:31.439 --> 04:51:33.479
behind the boulder, appearing around the

04:51:33.479 --> 04:51:35.279
other side as Viper chased her.

04:51:35.340 --> 04:51:39.000
That's not fair, Starfly cried.

04:51:39.060 --> 04:51:40.919
Fate speaker against both of them?

04:51:41.040 --> 04:51:44.880
Battles are never fair in real life.

04:51:44.939 --> 04:51:48.360
If she doesn't survive, well, we have

04:51:48.360 --> 04:51:48.720
you.

04:51:48.779 --> 04:51:52.080
Starflight clenched his talons, watching

04:51:52.080 --> 04:51:54.540
the writhing shapes below him anxiously.

04:51:54.599 --> 04:51:57.060
Viper and Flame were both so angry.

04:51:57.119 --> 04:52:00.060
They hated being here, and he wouldn't be

04:52:00.060 --> 04:52:01.560
surprised if they took it out on fate

04:52:01.560 --> 04:52:02.099
speaker.

04:52:02.159 --> 04:52:04.979
Flame shot a burst of fire at fate

04:52:04.979 --> 04:52:06.119
speaker's snout.

04:52:06.180 --> 04:52:08.639
She docked and rolled away, barely

04:52:08.639 --> 04:52:10.740
escaping before Viper's poisonous tail

04:52:10.740 --> 04:52:12.240
stabbed into the ground beside her.

04:52:12.299 --> 04:52:15.659
If she's even scratched by Viper's tail

04:52:15.659 --> 04:52:16.319
she could die.

04:52:16.380 --> 04:52:18.599
Starflight said tomorrow, seer.

04:52:18.720 --> 04:52:20.639
Maybe not right away, but the

04:52:20.639 --> 04:52:21.540
infection...

04:52:21.540 --> 04:52:24.000
He'd watch the wound blister had given to

04:52:24.000 --> 04:52:26.759
webs for days as it got worse and worse.

04:52:26.819 --> 04:52:29.819
Only a particular cactus from the kingdom

04:52:29.819 --> 04:52:32.099
of sand could reverse the effects, and

04:52:32.099 --> 04:52:33.479
there certainly wasn't any of it on this

04:52:33.479 --> 04:52:33.779
island.

04:52:33.840 --> 04:52:38.159
If you're so worried, jump in yourself

04:52:38.159 --> 04:52:41.220
Morris here said, he was studying the

04:52:41.220 --> 04:52:41.939
fight intently.

04:52:42.000 --> 04:52:45.419
Skywing, has nobody ever told you how to

04:52:45.419 --> 04:52:47.340
hold in your fire until it's at maximum

04:52:47.340 --> 04:52:48.959
temperature, like this.

04:52:49.020 --> 04:52:51.360
He shot a bolt of flames over their

04:52:51.360 --> 04:52:51.959
heads.

04:52:52.020 --> 04:52:54.360
By the moon's fate speaker.

04:52:54.419 --> 04:52:56.819
Stop rolling around and use your claws.

04:52:56.880 --> 04:52:59.639
Starflight, help me.

04:52:59.700 --> 04:53:01.080
Fate speaker yelped.

04:53:01.139 --> 04:53:02.639
He had no choice.

04:53:02.700 --> 04:53:05.040
It was beyond terrifying to think of

04:53:05.040 --> 04:53:08.459
facing Viper's tail and flames talons, but

04:53:08.459 --> 04:53:10.139
he couldn't leave her to fight alone.

04:53:10.200 --> 04:53:12.959
He knew what his friends would do if they

04:53:12.959 --> 04:53:13.259
were here.

04:53:13.319 --> 04:53:16.740
He closed his eyes, braced his legs, and

04:53:16.740 --> 04:53:18.540
vaulted off the boulder onto flames

04:53:18.540 --> 04:53:18.959
back.

04:53:19.020 --> 04:53:21.959
The sky wing roared and twisted, sending

04:53:21.959 --> 04:53:23.639
Starflight tumbling across the black

04:53:23.639 --> 04:53:26.759
rocks, sharp stone edges slashed his

04:53:26.759 --> 04:53:28.380
scales and the membranes of his wings.

04:53:28.439 --> 04:53:31.020
He struggled up, bleeding from several

04:53:31.020 --> 04:53:33.779
small cuts, and saw Viper knock fate

04:53:33.779 --> 04:53:36.000
speaker to the ground, and loom over her

04:53:36.000 --> 04:53:37.200
with her tail raised.

04:53:37.259 --> 04:53:40.560
Marosir watched, his claws tapping

04:53:40.560 --> 04:53:41.099
thoughtfully.

04:53:41.159 --> 04:53:42.659
Stop!

04:53:42.779 --> 04:53:45.659
Starfly cried, running at Viper.

04:53:45.720 --> 04:53:46.259
Leave her alone.

04:53:46.319 --> 04:53:49.020
This is your fault.

04:53:49.080 --> 04:53:51.360
Viper hissed at fate speaker.

04:53:51.419 --> 04:53:53.700
I could be back at camp with my parents

04:53:53.700 --> 04:53:56.279
if it weren't for your stupid tribe.

04:53:56.340 --> 04:54:00.000
Starflight smashed into Viper, just as

04:54:00.000 --> 04:54:01.860
her tail jabbed down toward fate

04:54:01.860 --> 04:54:02.639
speaker's neck.

04:54:02.700 --> 04:54:05.400
A sharp smell of venom filled his nose

04:54:05.400 --> 04:54:07.200
and his head collided with one of her

04:54:07.200 --> 04:54:07.560
wings.

04:54:07.619 --> 04:54:10.500
As she staggered back, her tail flew out

04:54:10.500 --> 04:54:12.779
for balance and sliced neatly across

04:54:12.779 --> 04:54:13.919
Flame's face.

04:54:13.979 --> 04:54:17.220
Flame roared with agony, clawed

04:54:17.220 --> 04:54:19.380
frantically at his snout, and slammed his

04:54:19.380 --> 04:54:21.060
body forward into Viper's side.

04:54:21.119 --> 04:54:23.400
The force of the blow sent her reeling

04:54:23.400 --> 04:54:23.819
away.

04:54:23.880 --> 04:54:27.360
Starflight watched in horror, as Viper

04:54:27.360 --> 04:54:30.060
teetered on the edge, and then fell with

04:54:30.060 --> 04:54:32.279
an ear splitting shriek right into the

04:54:32.279 --> 04:54:32.939
lava river.

04:54:33.000 --> 04:54:37.500
No, Morris here roared, leaping forward

04:54:37.500 --> 04:54:39.659
but he wasn't reaching for Viper.

04:54:39.720 --> 04:54:42.479
He seized Flame's head between his talons

04:54:42.479 --> 04:54:44.279
and glared at the wound she had

04:54:44.279 --> 04:54:44.759
inflicted.

04:54:44.819 --> 04:54:46.560
Skywing.

04:54:46.619 --> 04:54:47.340
Don't move.

04:54:47.400 --> 04:54:48.240
Can you see?

04:54:48.360 --> 04:54:51.479
Flame's only response was a keening

04:54:51.479 --> 04:54:52.680
guttural sound of agony.

04:54:52.740 --> 04:54:54.599
Viper.

04:54:54.659 --> 04:54:56.220
Fate speaker cried.

04:54:56.279 --> 04:54:58.319
Starflight followed her to the edge of

04:54:58.319 --> 04:55:00.599
the river, but the sand wing had vanished

04:55:00.599 --> 04:55:01.439
below the lava.

04:55:01.500 --> 04:55:03.060
Viper!

04:55:03.119 --> 04:55:04.799
Fate speaker screamed.

04:55:04.860 --> 04:55:07.919
Through his horror, Starflight's brain

04:55:07.919 --> 04:55:09.779
flashed him a message, and he whirled

04:55:09.779 --> 04:55:10.139
around.

04:55:10.259 --> 04:55:12.540
Ogre, you can go get her.

04:55:12.599 --> 04:55:13.500
He yelled.

04:55:13.560 --> 04:55:15.959
Maybe we can save her if you pull her out

04:55:15.959 --> 04:55:16.319
right away.

04:55:16.380 --> 04:55:20.580
Okre blinked, slow, painfully dull eyes

04:55:20.580 --> 04:55:21.180
at him.

04:55:21.240 --> 04:55:24.479
What in the 3 moons are you talking

04:55:24.479 --> 04:55:24.900
about?

04:55:24.959 --> 04:55:27.180
Your scales.

04:55:27.240 --> 04:55:29.880
Starflight grabbed Okra's forearm and

04:55:29.880 --> 04:55:31.380
tried to drag him toward the lava.

04:55:31.439 --> 04:55:34.439
The mud wings sat down firmly, as heavy

04:55:34.439 --> 04:55:35.639
as an entire fortress.

04:55:35.700 --> 04:55:39.540
Ogre, please, you have fireproof scales.

04:55:39.599 --> 04:55:41.459
You can go into the lava without getting

04:55:41.459 --> 04:55:41.759
hurt.

04:55:41.819 --> 04:55:43.740
You can find her and drag her out.

04:55:43.799 --> 04:55:45.360
Please, please just try.

04:55:45.479 --> 04:55:48.000
Fireproof scales?

04:55:48.119 --> 04:55:49.439
Fate speaker said.

04:55:49.560 --> 04:55:52.380
Because he was born from a red egg

04:55:52.380 --> 04:55:54.900
Starfly said, like it says in the

04:55:54.900 --> 04:55:57.900
prophecy, and that means fireproof scales

04:55:57.900 --> 04:55:59.400
come on, why are you moving?

04:55:59.459 --> 04:56:01.860
Let go of me.

04:56:01.919 --> 04:56:05.700
Oka growled, planting all his limbs even

04:56:05.700 --> 04:56:07.380
more solidly on the ground.

04:56:07.380 --> 04:56:11.159
I have no idea if my egg was red or

04:56:11.159 --> 04:56:14.040
whether my scales are fireproof, and I am

04:56:14.040 --> 04:56:16.500
certainly not jumping into a pit of lava

04:56:16.500 --> 04:56:17.279
to find out.

04:56:17.400 --> 04:56:21.060
But Starflight protested.

04:56:21.119 --> 04:56:24.540
But if you're in the prophecy, if you

04:56:24.540 --> 04:56:27.060
could be the mud wing, then you must have

04:56:27.060 --> 04:56:29.220
been born from a blood red egg just like

04:56:29.220 --> 04:56:29.939
clay.

04:56:30.000 --> 04:56:32.700
His heart wasn't in it anymore.

04:56:32.759 --> 04:56:35.220
He turned to look back at the lava

04:56:35.220 --> 04:56:36.840
knowing it was already too late.

04:56:36.900 --> 04:56:39.540
Viper hadn't even come up to the surface

04:56:39.540 --> 04:56:40.020
once.

04:56:40.080 --> 04:56:41.400
She was gone.

04:56:41.459 --> 04:56:46.200
Prophecy schmophasy, said Ogre.

04:56:46.259 --> 04:56:48.779
I wasn't hatched on the brightest night

04:56:48.779 --> 04:56:49.259
either.

04:56:49.319 --> 04:56:51.900
So I'm not going to base any life or

04:56:51.900 --> 04:56:54.540
death decisions on some old words in a

04:56:54.540 --> 04:56:54.900
scroll.

04:56:54.959 --> 04:56:58.560
Starflight pivoted it slowly to stare at

04:56:58.560 --> 04:56:59.159
the mudwing.

04:56:59.220 --> 04:57:02.759
You weren't hatched on the brightest

04:57:02.759 --> 04:57:03.180
night?

04:57:03.240 --> 04:57:04.259
he echoed.

04:57:04.319 --> 04:57:06.000
Okre shrugged.

04:57:06.060 --> 04:57:07.439
Neither was he.

04:57:07.500 --> 04:57:09.959
We had the same hatching day.

04:57:10.020 --> 04:57:13.020
A few weeks before the brightest night.

04:57:13.080 --> 04:57:15.900
He nodded at Flame, who was curled on the

04:57:15.900 --> 04:57:18.240
ground now, still making that horrible

04:57:18.240 --> 04:57:20.700
sound of pain with his talons pressed to

04:57:20.700 --> 04:57:20.939
his face.

04:57:21.000 --> 04:57:24.299
Morosir stood over him, lashing his tail

04:57:24.299 --> 04:57:24.959
furiously.

04:57:25.020 --> 04:57:29.099
But, Starflight's words failed him.

04:57:29.159 --> 04:57:32.520
Suddenly, everything seemed a lot clearer

04:57:32.520 --> 04:57:34.919
and yet more confusing at the same time.

04:57:34.979 --> 04:57:38.159
The alternate dragonettes weren't real.

04:57:38.220 --> 04:57:40.799
They couldn't be the dragonettes in the

04:57:40.799 --> 04:57:41.220
prophecy.

04:57:41.340 --> 04:57:43.740
They were entirely false.

04:57:43.799 --> 04:57:45.779
An illusion Marosir was trying to

04:57:45.779 --> 04:57:46.080
create.

04:57:46.139 --> 04:57:49.200
The giant night wing wasn't just

04:57:49.200 --> 04:57:50.400
tinkering with fate.

04:57:50.459 --> 04:57:52.979
He was trying to rewrite it entirely.
8324
04:57:53,040 --> 04:57:57,540	Chapter 19.

04:57:57.779 --> 04:58:01.560
Fate speaker was crumpled in a ball by

04:58:01.560 --> 04:58:03.540
the lava river, with her wings over her

04:58:03.540 --> 04:58:04.560
head, weeping.

04:58:04.619 --> 04:58:07.799
Viper and Squid were horrible to her from

04:58:07.799 --> 04:58:08.520
what I saw.

04:58:08.520 --> 04:58:09.900
Starflight thought.

04:58:09.959 --> 04:58:12.419
Viper was trying to kill her just a

04:58:12.419 --> 04:58:14.580
moment ago, and yet she's still

04:58:14.580 --> 04:58:15.779
devastated by losing them.

04:58:15.900 --> 04:58:18.659
Because she's not a heartless monster

04:58:18.659 --> 04:58:20.220
like some dragons.

04:58:20.279 --> 04:58:22.439
Get up.

04:58:22.500 --> 04:58:24.779
Moro CR snarled at Flame.

04:58:24.840 --> 04:58:26.639
You are not expendable.

04:58:26.700 --> 04:58:30.060
The Red Dragonette's only response was a

04:58:30.060 --> 04:58:30.599
low moan.

04:58:30.659 --> 04:58:34.020
Tsunami would yell at Maru Seer.

04:58:34.080 --> 04:58:34.799
Sonny.

04:58:34.919 --> 04:58:37.200
Sonny would probably try to reason with

04:58:37.200 --> 04:58:37.560
him.

04:58:37.619 --> 04:58:40.020
Starflight's wings were shaking

04:58:40.020 --> 04:58:41.099
uncontrollably.

04:58:41.159 --> 04:58:42.900
But he made himself step in front of

04:58:42.900 --> 04:58:43.680
Morosier.

04:58:43.740 --> 04:58:48.360
Pretend your tsunami, or clay, or glory

04:58:48.360 --> 04:58:49.020
or sunny.

04:58:49.080 --> 04:58:50.880
What are you doing?

04:58:50.939 --> 04:58:52.560
Starflight blurted.

04:58:52.619 --> 04:58:54.779
Maro seer glare down at him.

04:58:54.840 --> 04:58:58.080
Now is not a good time to annoy me.

04:58:58.139 --> 04:59:01.259
These dragonettes can't be in the

04:59:01.259 --> 04:59:03.240
prophecy, Starflight said.

04:59:03.299 --> 04:59:05.340
They don't even have their right hatching

04:59:05.340 --> 04:59:05.580
day.

04:59:05.639 --> 04:59:08.220
Is there anything about them that does

04:59:08.220 --> 04:59:08.520
fit?

04:59:08.580 --> 04:59:11.220
Was Viper's egg found on its own in the

04:59:11.220 --> 04:59:12.599
desert like Sunny's?

04:59:12.659 --> 04:59:15.180
Was Flames Egg the largest in the Sky

04:59:15.180 --> 04:59:15.779
Palace?

04:59:15.840 --> 04:59:18.060
Why are you pretending they could fulfill

04:59:18.060 --> 04:59:20.159
the prophecy when there's no way they can

04:59:20.159 --> 04:59:21.360
be the right dragonettes?

04:59:21.419 --> 04:59:24.060
You don't know what you're talking

04:59:24.060 --> 04:59:24.360
about.

04:59:24.419 --> 04:59:27.419
Maro seer bared his teeth.

04:59:27.479 --> 04:59:31.319
Maybe, said Starflight, but I want to

04:59:31.319 --> 04:59:31.500
know.

04:59:31.560 --> 04:59:33.599
Everything I ever read.

04:59:33.659 --> 04:59:36.299
All the scrolls written by Nightwings for

04:59:36.299 --> 04:59:39.659
generations said, don't mess with fate.

04:59:39.720 --> 04:59:41.819
Things will happen the way they're

04:59:41.819 --> 04:59:43.680
foretold, and nobody can change that.

04:59:43.740 --> 04:59:46.740
Prophecies aren't like treasure hoards

04:59:46.740 --> 04:59:48.540
where you can mix and match which gems

04:59:48.540 --> 04:59:50.459
you like, and trade out the ones you

04:59:50.459 --> 04:59:50.759
don't.

04:59:50.819 --> 04:59:53.340
I bet these dragonettes are dying because

04:59:53.340 --> 04:59:54.900
you're trying to force them into a

04:59:54.900 --> 04:59:56.340
destiny that's not meant for them.

04:59:56.400 --> 04:59:59.520
You should leave us all alone and let

04:59:59.520 --> 05:00:01.319
fate unfold the way it's supposed to.

05:00:01.380 --> 05:00:04.919
He took a deep breath, astonished and

05:00:04.919 --> 05:00:06.959
terrified at his audacity in talking

05:00:06.959 --> 05:00:08.159
tomorrow, see her this way.

05:00:08.220 --> 05:00:11.819
That's, that's what I think anyway.

05:00:11.880 --> 05:00:16.680
You are an ignorant dragonette, said

05:00:16.680 --> 05:00:20.639
Marusier, with no powers of your own, and

05:00:20.639 --> 05:00:22.020
no one will ever listen to you.

05:00:22.080 --> 05:00:25.439
Starflight felt as if he'd been stabbed

05:00:25.439 --> 05:00:26.700
in the heart by a sandwing.

05:00:26.759 --> 05:00:29.520
He stared up at Morrisier, unable to

05:00:29.520 --> 05:00:29.819
breathe.

05:00:29.880 --> 05:00:33.119
Did you think I wouldn't notice?

05:00:33.240 --> 05:00:35.159
Morosier snarled?

05:00:35.279 --> 05:00:38.159
It's obvious how useless you are.

05:00:38.220 --> 05:00:40.860
You'll never be a true night wing.

05:00:40.919 --> 05:00:43.680
You don't belong anywhere, least of all

05:00:43.680 --> 05:00:44.279
here.

05:00:44.340 --> 05:00:47.759
If he had read Starflight's mind.

05:00:47.819 --> 05:00:49.139
And maybe he had.

05:00:49.200 --> 05:00:51.360
He couldn't have found anything that

05:00:51.360 --> 05:00:52.799
would have hurt Starflight more.

05:00:52.860 --> 05:00:55.319
All his nightmares had centered around

05:00:55.319 --> 05:00:55.919
this moment.

05:00:55.979 --> 05:00:58.619
You are not a real night wing.

05:00:58.680 --> 05:01:01.080
There is something wrong with you, and

05:01:01.080 --> 05:01:02.459
you are a failure in every way.

05:01:02.520 --> 05:01:06.180
Starflight took a trembling step back, and

05:01:06.180 --> 05:01:08.220
felt fate speakers wings brush against

05:01:08.220 --> 05:01:08.520
his.

05:01:08.580 --> 05:01:10.799
He hadn't noticed her coming up behind

05:01:10.799 --> 05:01:11.159
him.

05:01:11.220 --> 05:01:15.060
Leave him alone, she said tomorrow, seer.

05:01:15.119 --> 05:01:16.979
He's only telling you the truth about the

05:01:16.979 --> 05:01:17.580
prophecy.

05:01:17.639 --> 05:01:20.220
I have the wrong hatching day too, and

05:01:20.220 --> 05:01:20.759
you know that.

05:01:20.880 --> 05:01:24.840
I know a lot more about prophecies than

05:01:24.840 --> 05:01:25.680
either of you.

05:01:25.740 --> 05:01:27.720
Marusir snarled.

05:01:27.779 --> 05:01:30.599
He shoved them aside and seized Flame's

05:01:30.599 --> 05:01:31.860
forearm, yanking him up.

05:01:31.919 --> 05:01:34.200
You're not allowed to die.

05:01:34.319 --> 05:01:36.299
We're going to the healers.

05:01:36.360 --> 05:01:37.319
The rest of you.

05:01:37.380 --> 05:01:40.080
Stay out of my way, or you'll be joining

05:01:40.080 --> 05:01:41.040
that sand wing.

05:01:41.159 --> 05:01:44.639
He glared at Flame's face, which the Sky

05:01:44.639 --> 05:01:45.900
Wing was still keeping hidden.

05:01:45.959 --> 05:01:48.180
Starflight could see blood dripping

05:01:48.180 --> 05:01:49.740
between the red dragon's claws.

05:01:49.799 --> 05:01:51.959
Moro Sears shook his head and muttered.

05:01:52.020 --> 05:01:55.259
Now we need that stunted sandwing too.

05:01:55.319 --> 05:01:57.180
I'm going to.

05:01:57.240 --> 05:01:58.380
Starfly didn't hear the rest.

05:01:58.439 --> 05:02:00.659
As Maro Cyril launched himself into the

05:02:00.659 --> 05:02:02.939
air, forcibly dragging flame along behind

05:02:02.939 --> 05:02:04.919
him, but he'd hurt enough.

05:02:04.979 --> 05:02:07.439
Sonny's in danger now too.

05:02:07.500 --> 05:02:11.099
He had to use the dream visitor again as

05:02:11.099 --> 05:02:11.880
soon as possible.

05:02:11.939 --> 05:02:15.060
He turned and found fate speakers staring

05:02:15.060 --> 05:02:17.099
at the lava, her wings drooping.

05:02:17.159 --> 05:02:19.740
The red gold light of the river reflected

05:02:19.740 --> 05:02:22.139
off her silver scales, making them glint

05:02:22.139 --> 05:02:23.159
like rubies.

05:02:23.220 --> 05:02:26.340
Well, said Ogre.

05:02:26.400 --> 05:02:30.000
If no one cares what I'm doing, I'm going

05:02:30.000 --> 05:02:32.819
to find some decent prey, if there is any

05:02:32.819 --> 05:02:34.020
on this stupid island.

05:02:34.020 --> 05:02:37.319
He backed away, as if waiting for one of

05:02:37.319 --> 05:02:39.540
them to argue with him, then stamped

05:02:39.540 --> 05:02:40.380
around and flew off.

05:02:40.439 --> 05:02:43.319
Starflight gently put one of his wings

05:02:43.319 --> 05:02:44.340
around fate's speaker.

05:02:44.400 --> 05:02:47.700
Let's go back to the dormitory and rest

05:02:47.700 --> 05:02:48.419
he said.

05:02:48.479 --> 05:02:51.060
You haven't had any sleep, right?

05:02:51.180 --> 05:02:52.619
How can I?

05:02:52.740 --> 05:02:53.819
She started.

05:02:53.880 --> 05:02:55.200
Then stopped herself.

05:02:55.259 --> 05:02:58.619
Actually, sleeping sounds like the only

05:02:58.619 --> 05:03:01.080
thing I could do right now, although I'm

05:03:01.080 --> 05:03:02.880
afraid it'll be nothing but nightmares.

05:03:02.939 --> 05:03:05.099
Starflight knew what she meant.

05:03:05.159 --> 05:03:07.860
He helped her up, and they flew side by

05:03:07.860 --> 05:03:09.000
side back to the fortress.

05:03:09.060 --> 05:03:10.979
The dormitory was deserted.

05:03:11.040 --> 05:03:13.560
Starflight guest, the other night wing

05:03:13.560 --> 05:03:15.840
dragonettes were at class, presumably

05:03:15.840 --> 05:03:18.060
learning something more useful then, how

05:03:18.060 --> 05:03:20.400
to push your friend into some lava, or

05:03:20.400 --> 05:03:21.959
your whole life is pointless.

05:03:22.020 --> 05:03:24.720
Fate speaker collapsed onto one of the

05:03:24.720 --> 05:03:26.220
stone hollows and closed her eyes.

05:03:26.279 --> 05:03:30.180
You're lucky, she said, just as

05:03:30.180 --> 05:03:31.380
Starflight was about to move away.

05:03:31.439 --> 05:03:33.180
He hesitated.

05:03:33.240 --> 05:03:34.319
I am?

05:03:34.380 --> 05:03:38.400
I mean, if what Maro Seer said is true.

05:03:38.520 --> 05:03:40.919
She opened her eyes again and looked at

05:03:40.919 --> 05:03:41.159
him.

05:03:41.220 --> 05:03:44.819
If you have no powers, I've always been

05:03:44.819 --> 05:03:46.680
so excited about being a night wing.

05:03:46.740 --> 05:03:49.020
I thought my powers must be the most

05:03:49.020 --> 05:03:51.900
amazing thing, but clearly they're

05:03:51.900 --> 05:03:52.680
totally useless.

05:03:52.740 --> 05:03:54.720
If they couldn't even warn me about what

05:03:54.720 --> 05:03:56.279
was going to happen to my friends.

05:03:56.340 --> 05:03:59.040
She curled her wings and tail in

05:03:59.040 --> 05:03:59.400
clothes.

05:03:59.459 --> 05:04:03.180
All my visions were walruses, and welcome

05:04:03.180 --> 05:04:05.520
home parties, and parents who were happy

05:04:05.520 --> 05:04:05.939
to meet me.

05:04:06.000 --> 05:04:07.799
So much for that.

05:04:07.860 --> 05:04:09.840
Have you?

05:04:09.840 --> 05:04:11.400
Starflight started.

05:04:11.459 --> 05:04:14.700
I mean, do you know who your parents

05:04:14.700 --> 05:04:15.119
are?

05:04:15.180 --> 05:04:16.380
Do any of you?

05:04:16.439 --> 05:04:19.860
Squid's dad is the leader of the talons

05:04:19.860 --> 05:04:21.119
of peace, she said.

05:04:21.180 --> 05:04:23.580
All of their parents are in the talons.

05:04:23.639 --> 05:04:27.060
That's why Maru Seer picked us. them

05:04:27.060 --> 05:04:28.919
because we were convenient.

05:04:29.040 --> 05:04:30.659
She frowned.

05:04:30.720 --> 05:04:32.759
I guess you are the only night wing

05:04:32.759 --> 05:04:34.380
dragonette who hatched on the brightest

05:04:34.380 --> 05:04:34.799
night.

05:04:34.919 --> 05:04:37.080
My egg hatched a couple of months later.

05:04:37.139 --> 05:04:38.459
Here, actually.

05:04:38.520 --> 05:04:40.680
I have this really vague memory of fire

05:04:40.680 --> 05:04:42.959
and rough scales rubbing my back.

05:04:43.020 --> 05:04:45.779
I didn't remember that until I smelled

05:04:45.779 --> 05:04:46.259
this place.

05:04:46.380 --> 05:04:49.560
She paused for a moment, then sighed.

05:04:49.619 --> 05:04:52.439
But Maru Sier took me to the talons when

05:04:52.439 --> 05:04:53.819
I was still newly hatched.

05:04:53.880 --> 05:04:56.700
I bet that was when they decided they

05:04:56.700 --> 05:04:59.340
needed a backup plan, Starflight said.

05:04:59.400 --> 05:05:01.979
Another set of dragonettes were close

05:05:01.979 --> 05:05:04.200
enough, just in case they didn't like how

05:05:04.200 --> 05:05:05.340
we turned out.

05:05:05.400 --> 05:05:08.520
He shifted his wings, which they sure

05:05:08.520 --> 05:05:09.180
don't.

05:05:09.240 --> 05:05:11.759
I like how you turned out.

05:05:11.819 --> 05:05:13.979
Fate speaker said softly.

05:05:14.040 --> 05:05:17.040
Starflight took her front talons in his

05:05:17.040 --> 05:05:17.939
and squeezed them.

05:05:18.000 --> 05:05:20.759
You too, he said.

05:05:20.819 --> 05:05:23.279
I like you much better than all the other

05:05:23.279 --> 05:05:25.080
night wings I've met who were raised

05:05:25.080 --> 05:05:25.619
properly.

05:05:25.680 --> 05:05:29.099
I think we're actually lucky, in a way

05:05:29.099 --> 05:05:31.139
that we didn't have to grow up here.

05:05:31.200 --> 05:05:34.500
She nodded, but she still looked sad.

05:05:34.560 --> 05:05:36.840
And I'm even luckier.

05:05:36.900 --> 05:05:39.060
Growing up with dragonettes like my

05:05:39.060 --> 05:05:39.599
friends.

05:05:39.659 --> 05:05:42.299
The cruelty of their guardians had been

05:05:42.299 --> 05:05:44.279
far outweighed by Clay's protective

05:05:44.279 --> 05:05:48.000
caring, tsunami's fierce loyalty, glory's

05:05:48.000 --> 05:05:50.220
insight, and humor, and Sonny's

05:05:50.220 --> 05:05:52.080
everything about Sonny.

05:05:52.139 --> 05:05:55.139
Feeling suddenly awkward and guilty.

05:05:55.259 --> 05:05:57.240
He let go of fate speaker's talons.

05:05:57.299 --> 05:06:00.419
You have the face you get when you're

05:06:00.419 --> 05:06:02.159
missing your friends, she said.

05:06:02.220 --> 05:06:05.099
He nodded, surprised that he was that

05:06:05.099 --> 05:06:05.819
transparent.

05:06:05.880 --> 05:06:09.060
Sometimes I think there might be no other

05:06:09.060 --> 05:06:11.159
dragons like them in all of Pyria.

05:06:11.279 --> 05:06:13.439
You're probably right.

05:06:13.500 --> 05:06:15.479
She said with a sigh.

05:06:15.540 --> 05:06:19.020
Well, there's fate speaker.

05:06:19.080 --> 05:06:21.479
He touched her shoulder lightly.

05:06:21.540 --> 05:06:23.159
Get some sleep.

05:06:23.220 --> 05:06:26.819
She obediently closed her eyes, and he

05:06:26.819 --> 05:06:28.200
moved back to his own side of the

05:06:28.200 --> 05:06:30.599
dormitory, waiting until he was sure she

05:06:30.599 --> 05:06:31.020
was asleep.

05:06:31.080 --> 05:06:34.259
After a few moments, her breathing evened

05:06:34.259 --> 05:06:36.060
out, and he reached for the hole where

05:06:36.060 --> 05:06:37.500
he'd hidden the dream visitor.

05:06:37.560 --> 05:06:39.060
Starflight?

05:06:39.119 --> 05:06:41.939
Star Light was so startled, he nearly hit

05:06:41.939 --> 05:06:42.360
the ceiling.

05:06:42.419 --> 05:06:45.180
He whirled around and saw mastermind

05:06:45.180 --> 05:06:47.340
standing in the doorway, staring

05:06:47.340 --> 05:06:48.659
curiously around the room.

05:06:49.020 --> 05:06:51.419
I haven't been back here in a while.

05:06:51.540 --> 05:06:53.819
Mastermind said with a chuckle.

05:06:53.880 --> 05:06:56.880
Marsier said this was where I'd probably

05:06:56.880 --> 05:06:57.299
find you.

05:06:57.360 --> 05:07:00.720
I'm in a bit of a conundrum, and I was

05:07:00.720 --> 05:07:01.500
hoping you could help me.

05:07:01.619 --> 05:07:05.340
Starflight edged toward the wall, trying

05:07:05.340 --> 05:07:06.659
not to look at his hiding spot.

05:07:06.720 --> 05:07:09.299
He didn't have time for a chat with his

05:07:09.299 --> 05:07:10.319
sociopathic father.

05:07:10.380 --> 05:07:13.200
He needed to contact Glory, or someone

05:07:13.200 --> 05:07:14.700
who could tell her to put a guard on

05:07:14.700 --> 05:07:15.119
Sonny.

05:07:15.180 --> 05:07:18.360
But Mastermind held out one wing, and

05:07:18.360 --> 05:07:20.759
Starflight realized that saying no wasn't

05:07:20.759 --> 05:07:22.919
an option, not without a lot of very

05:07:22.919 --> 05:07:24.240
convincing explanations.

05:07:24.360 --> 05:07:28.259
Walk with me. insisted the older

05:07:28.259 --> 05:07:28.979
Nightwing.

05:07:29.040 --> 05:07:31.919
Have you seen our marvelous library?

05:07:31.979 --> 05:07:35.099
Starflight reluctantly trailed after him

05:07:35.099 --> 05:07:37.139
casting a longing glance back at his

05:07:37.139 --> 05:07:37.319
bed.

05:07:37.380 --> 05:07:39.540
Soon, sonny.

05:07:39.599 --> 05:07:41.040
I'll make sure you're safe.

05:07:41.159 --> 05:07:42.479
I promise.
8602
05:07:42,599 --> 05:07:46,619	Chapter 20.

05:07:46.919 --> 05:07:50.580
Mastermind took a deep breath as they

05:07:50.580 --> 05:07:51.419
stepped into the library.

05:07:51.479 --> 05:07:54.540
There's something about the smell of

05:07:54.540 --> 05:07:58.139
scrolls that always calms me, he said

05:07:58.139 --> 05:07:59.520
waving one talent at the walls.

05:07:59.580 --> 05:08:01.319
Me too.

05:08:01.380 --> 05:08:03.540
Starflight admitted reluctantly.

05:08:03.599 --> 05:08:05.819
He didn't want to believe he had anything

05:08:05.819 --> 05:08:06.659
in common with his father.

05:08:06.779 --> 05:08:09.240
It frightened him to think of how he

05:08:09.240 --> 05:08:10.979
might have turned out, if he'd been

05:08:10.979 --> 05:08:12.240
raised on the Nightwing Island.

05:08:12.299 --> 05:08:14.939
Would Mastermind have taken him under his

05:08:14.939 --> 05:08:15.240
wing?

05:08:15.299 --> 05:08:18.000
Would Starflight be helping him torture

05:08:18.000 --> 05:08:20.639
rain wings without any guilt or remorse?

05:08:20.700 --> 05:08:23.159
Would he be inventing new, horrible

05:08:23.159 --> 05:08:24.659
experiments to try on them?

05:08:24.720 --> 05:08:26.639
Never thinking about how they were real

05:08:26.639 --> 05:08:28.020
dragons he was harming?

05:08:28.080 --> 05:08:31.439
He'd be eating rotting animals, and

05:08:31.439 --> 05:08:33.599
studying with the other night wings and

05:08:33.599 --> 05:08:36.419
arguing with fierce teeth, and he'd

05:08:36.419 --> 05:08:38.880
believe, like the rest of them did, that

05:08:38.880 --> 05:08:40.979
he was superior to all other dragons in

05:08:40.979 --> 05:08:41.279
the world.

05:08:41.340 --> 05:08:44.580
Except that Starflight had no powers.

05:08:44.639 --> 05:08:47.159
So he'd have been an outcast eventually

05:08:47.159 --> 05:08:48.599
even if he had grown up here.

05:08:48.659 --> 05:08:50.400
He never would have belonged.

05:08:50.520 --> 05:08:54.299
Not that he wanted to, but he didn't want

05:08:54.299 --> 05:08:55.139
to be useless either.

05:08:55.200 --> 05:08:59.400
Let's see, Mastermind said.

05:08:59.459 --> 05:09:01.799
Studying the large catalog scroll on the

05:09:01.799 --> 05:09:02.400
main table.

05:09:02.459 --> 05:09:04.799
Each end of the scroll was rolled around

05:09:04.799 --> 05:09:07.080
a spindle with a handle that could be

05:09:07.080 --> 05:09:08.580
turned to navigate quickly through the

05:09:08.580 --> 05:09:09.060
entire thing.

05:09:09.180 --> 05:09:12.180
Mastermind spun the scroll rapidly

05:09:12.180 --> 05:09:14.159
through to the M's, and paused on

05:09:14.159 --> 05:09:15.659
medicinal records.

05:09:15.779 --> 05:09:17.580
Hmm.

05:09:17.759 --> 05:09:20.459
He tapped his claws on the list, then

05:09:20.459 --> 05:09:21.840
turned to the niches in the wall.

05:09:21.900 --> 05:09:24.360
Help me brainstorm, son.

05:09:24.479 --> 05:09:27.419
The queen is very angry about what's

05:09:27.419 --> 05:09:29.279
happened to the Sky Wing Dragonette.

05:09:29.340 --> 05:09:32.040
I'm afraid he'll be dead by morning if we

05:09:32.040 --> 05:09:34.200
don't find some way to combat the sand

05:09:34.200 --> 05:09:36.659
wing poison, which is apparently my

05:09:36.659 --> 05:09:39.419
responsibility for some reason, as if I'm

05:09:39.419 --> 05:09:41.819
not already swamped trying to construct

05:09:41.819 --> 05:09:43.740
then improve helmets for the entire night

05:09:43.740 --> 05:09:46.740
wing tribe in 2 days, using only my

05:09:46.740 --> 05:09:49.740
regretfully flawed prototype, which the

05:09:49.740 --> 05:09:51.479
queen says will simply have to do for

05:09:51.479 --> 05:09:51.720
now.

05:09:51.779 --> 05:09:55.380
He paused for a breath, pulling scrolls

05:09:55.380 --> 05:09:57.180
out and tucking them under one wing.

05:09:57.240 --> 05:09:59.759
Did you say 2 days?

05:09:59.819 --> 05:10:02.220
Starflight echoed, trying to sound

05:10:02.220 --> 05:10:02.700
casual.

05:10:02.759 --> 05:10:05.639
In case the council votes to attack

05:10:05.639 --> 05:10:09.360
Mastermind answered with a snort, I try

05:10:09.360 --> 05:10:11.099
to tell them that my research is still

05:10:11.099 --> 05:10:13.619
incomplete, and I cannot guarantee that

05:10:13.619 --> 05:10:15.060
any operation will go smoothly.

05:10:15.119 --> 05:10:18.599
I'm pretty sure I can guarantee that it

05:10:18.599 --> 05:10:19.020
won't.

05:10:19.080 --> 05:10:21.659
Starflight thought, remembering the look

05:10:21.659 --> 05:10:22.619
on glory's face.

05:10:22.740 --> 05:10:24.900
Mastermind flicked his tail.

05:10:24.959 --> 05:10:28.860
So, if you have any ideas, let's hear

05:10:28.860 --> 05:10:29.099
them.

05:10:29.159 --> 05:10:31.860
The problem is that naturally, I've never

05:10:31.860 --> 05:10:34.860
studied sandwing venom, orders were to do

05:10:34.860 --> 05:10:36.840
nothing to antagonize our ally.

05:10:36.900 --> 05:10:39.959
But if it's anything like rain wing venom

05:10:39.959 --> 05:10:41.700
there is nothing that counteracts its

05:10:41.700 --> 05:10:42.180
effects.

05:10:42.240 --> 05:10:44.759
Starflight blinked with surprise.

05:10:44.819 --> 05:10:47.759
His father hadn't figured out that the

05:10:47.759 --> 05:10:50.580
antidote to a rain wings venom was venom

05:10:50.580 --> 05:10:51.540
from a blood relative.

05:10:51.599 --> 05:10:54.240
It was kind of impressive that none of

05:10:54.240 --> 05:10:56.159
the rain wing prisoners had revealed that

05:10:56.159 --> 05:10:56.759
information.

05:10:56.819 --> 05:10:59.340
Perhaps they were a little tougher and

05:10:59.340 --> 05:11:01.080
smarter than Starflight had given them

05:11:01.080 --> 05:11:01.560
credit for.

05:11:01.680 --> 05:11:04.680
It was also interesting that the

05:11:04.680 --> 05:11:05.939
Nightwing seemed to have so much

05:11:05.939 --> 05:11:06.479
knowledge.

05:11:06.540 --> 05:11:10.200
This entire library full of scrolls, and

05:11:10.200 --> 05:11:11.220
yet they didn't know something as

05:11:11.220 --> 05:11:13.319
essential as how to cure someone who'd

05:11:13.319 --> 05:11:14.520
been stabbed by a sandwing.

05:11:14.639 --> 05:11:16.799
Sunny had been able to get that

05:11:16.799 --> 05:11:18.659
information out of Blaze in a matter of

05:11:18.659 --> 05:11:18.959
minutes.

05:11:19.020 --> 05:11:22.619
Perhaps that's one downside to staying

05:11:22.619 --> 05:11:23.279
isolated.

05:11:23.340 --> 05:11:24.840
Starflight thought.

05:11:24.900 --> 05:11:27.360
They keep themselves separate to seem

05:11:27.360 --> 05:11:29.700
more powerful, and yet they're cut off

05:11:29.700 --> 05:11:31.319
from so much potential knowledge.

05:11:31.380 --> 05:11:34.080
If they didn't feel superior to all other

05:11:34.080 --> 05:11:36.360
dragons, maybe they'd be better at

05:11:36.360 --> 05:11:38.880
listening to them, and maybe they'd learn

05:11:38.880 --> 05:11:39.419
something new.

05:11:39.479 --> 05:11:43.500
Mastermind had his nose in a scroll and

05:11:43.500 --> 05:11:44.639
was muttering grimly.

05:11:44.700 --> 05:11:46.259
Unlikely.

05:11:46.319 --> 05:11:49.380
Try that on rain wing venom, and it

05:11:49.380 --> 05:11:49.740
didn't work.

05:11:49.799 --> 05:11:51.240
None of that nearby.

05:11:51.299 --> 05:11:52.619
Doubtful.

05:11:52.740 --> 05:11:56.340
Imagine how much we could know, if the

05:11:56.340 --> 05:11:57.599
Nightwing studied the right things.

05:11:57.720 --> 05:12:00.240
Like the medicinal properties of all the

05:12:00.240 --> 05:12:02.880
rainforest plants, instead of torturing

05:12:02.880 --> 05:12:05.040
dragons and obsessing over their secret

05:12:05.040 --> 05:12:05.580
plan.

05:12:05.639 --> 05:12:09.360
Starflight realized that the section they

05:12:09.360 --> 05:12:11.220
were standing in was labeled for

05:12:11.220 --> 05:12:12.479
Nightwing Eyes only.

05:12:12.599 --> 05:12:14.939
He pulled out one of the scrolls at

05:12:14.939 --> 05:12:16.200
Random, curious.

05:12:16.259 --> 05:12:19.259
It turned out to be a treatise by 2

05:12:19.259 --> 05:12:20.939
authors about the plan to take over the

05:12:20.939 --> 05:12:21.479
rainforest.

05:12:21.540 --> 05:12:24.720
One author argued in favor of killing all

05:12:24.720 --> 05:12:27.119
the rain wings right away, while the

05:12:27.119 --> 05:12:29.520
other author suggested that enslaving

05:12:29.520 --> 05:12:31.080
them would be more useful in the long

05:12:31.080 --> 05:12:31.380
term.

05:12:31.500 --> 05:12:35.520
Feeling ill, Starflight shoved the scroll

05:12:35.520 --> 05:12:37.080
back into its slot with so much force

05:12:37.080 --> 05:12:39.540
that it wrinkled and nearly ripped in

05:12:39.540 --> 05:12:39.720
half.

05:12:39.779 --> 05:12:42.419
His father looked up at him.

05:12:42.479 --> 05:12:45.360
Well, any thoughts?

05:12:45.419 --> 05:12:47.520
He barreled on without waiting for a

05:12:47.520 --> 05:12:47.880
response.

05:12:48.000 --> 05:12:51.419
We may have to contact blister, although

05:12:51.419 --> 05:12:53.040
I fear she'll want to trade information

05:12:53.040 --> 05:12:55.139
this valuable for something of equal

05:12:55.139 --> 05:12:58.799
worth to her, like the location of our

05:12:58.799 --> 05:12:59.159
island.

05:12:59.220 --> 05:13:02.520
Mastermind scratched his snout with a

05:13:02.520 --> 05:13:03.060
worried frown.

05:13:03.119 --> 05:13:05.880
Personally, I'm not sure it's advisable

05:13:05.880 --> 05:13:07.560
to give her any power over us.

05:13:07.619 --> 05:13:11.279
Definitely not, Starflight said.

05:13:11.340 --> 05:13:12.779
I don't trust her.

05:13:12.840 --> 05:13:14.759
Mastermind nodded.

05:13:14.819 --> 05:13:18.180
Well, alliances aren't always about trust

05:13:18.180 --> 05:13:18.840
I'm afraid.

05:13:18.900 --> 05:13:21.659
He picked up another scroll and unrolled

05:13:21.659 --> 05:13:21.900
it.

05:13:21.959 --> 05:13:24.299
Star Light shifted uncomfortably.

05:13:24.360 --> 05:13:25.799
Flexing his claws.

05:13:25.860 --> 05:13:28.979
He knew the antidote to sandwing venom

05:13:28.979 --> 05:13:30.959
but should he share it with mastermind?

05:13:31.020 --> 05:13:34.020
On the one talent, it seemed dangerous to

05:13:34.020 --> 05:13:35.700
hand the night wings any more secrets

05:13:35.700 --> 05:13:37.979
than they already had, he could easily

05:13:37.979 --> 05:13:40.799
imagine them abusing that information, by

05:13:40.799 --> 05:13:43.319
attacking sand wings, for instance, with

05:13:43.319 --> 05:13:45.299
no more fear of what their venom might do

05:13:45.299 --> 05:13:48.000
or they might take all the cacti in the

05:13:48.000 --> 05:13:50.220
desert and hoard it for themselves, so

05:13:50.220 --> 05:13:51.840
only night wings would have the ability

05:13:51.840 --> 05:13:53.520
to heal from a sand wing attack.

05:13:53.580 --> 05:13:56.700
Or, from what he'd seen of Nightwing so

05:13:56.700 --> 05:13:58.560
far, they'd probably come up with

05:13:58.560 --> 05:14:00.119
something even more horrible that

05:14:00.119 --> 05:14:01.799
Starflight would never be able to imagine

05:14:01.799 --> 05:14:02.939
on his own.

05:14:03.000 --> 05:14:05.759
But on the other talent, flame was

05:14:05.759 --> 05:14:06.060
dying.

05:14:06.119 --> 05:14:09.000
Without the cactus remedy, there was no

05:14:09.000 --> 05:14:09.479
hope for him.

05:14:09.540 --> 05:14:13.200
If Starflight told mastermind, there

05:14:13.200 --> 05:14:15.000
might still be time for someone to fly to

05:14:15.000 --> 05:14:17.099
the mainland and get what was needed to

05:14:17.099 --> 05:14:18.299
save the sky wing.

05:14:18.360 --> 05:14:20.159
Wasn't that the most important thing?

05:14:20.279 --> 05:14:22.500
Starflight couldn't let him die.

05:14:22.560 --> 05:14:25.319
His friends would choose to save flame no

05:14:25.319 --> 05:14:27.479
matter the consequences, wouldn't they?

05:14:27.540 --> 05:14:29.580
Sunny would.

05:14:29.580 --> 05:14:31.139
Claywood.

05:14:31.200 --> 05:14:32.400
Glory.

05:14:32.459 --> 05:14:33.959
I'm not sure.

05:14:34.080 --> 05:14:36.180
She might say to look at the bigger

05:14:36.180 --> 05:14:36.959
picture instead.

05:14:37.020 --> 05:14:39.540
And tsunami would say that this is

05:14:39.540 --> 05:14:40.740
classic Starflight.

05:14:40.799 --> 05:14:43.560
Dithering indecisively instead of doing

05:14:43.560 --> 05:14:44.099
something.

05:14:44.159 --> 05:14:45.659
So fine.

05:14:45.720 --> 05:14:48.659
If I can't make my own decision, then do

05:14:48.659 --> 05:14:49.439
what Sonny would do.

05:14:49.500 --> 05:14:52.380
Starflight opened his mouth to tell

05:14:52.380 --> 05:14:54.720
mastermind about the cure, but before he

05:14:54.720 --> 05:14:57.479
could, 3 night wings encased in armor

05:14:57.479 --> 05:14:58.740
came rushing into the library.

05:14:58.799 --> 05:15:00.959
Mastermind!

05:15:01.020 --> 05:15:02.040
one of them shouted.

05:15:02.099 --> 05:15:04.080
You'll need it in the council chamber

05:15:04.080 --> 05:15:04.680
immediately.

05:15:04.740 --> 05:15:07.979
Starflight's father sprang to his feet

05:15:08.040 --> 05:15:10.139
and started re shelving the scrolls with

05:15:10.139 --> 05:15:12.540
fast, neat movements, carefully checking

05:15:12.540 --> 05:15:14.040
their marks to make sure they went into

05:15:14.040 --> 05:15:14.819
the right niches.

05:15:14.880 --> 05:15:16.439
Why?

05:15:16.500 --> 05:15:18.119
He asked the guard at the same time.

05:15:18.180 --> 05:15:19.319
What's happened?

05:15:19.380 --> 05:15:22.799
The extraction was a failure, said one of

05:15:22.799 --> 05:15:23.759
the other night wings.

05:15:23.819 --> 05:15:25.860
They tried to jump through and snatch her

05:15:25.860 --> 05:15:27.599
while she was watching the tunnel, but

05:15:27.599 --> 05:15:28.860
there must have been about 40 other

05:15:28.860 --> 05:15:31.080
dragons hidden nearby, like they were

05:15:31.080 --> 05:15:32.040
guarding her or something.

05:15:32.099 --> 05:15:34.439
You should see what they did to the 3 we

05:15:34.439 --> 05:15:35.099
sent through.

05:15:35.220 --> 05:15:38.639
You say they, said the 3rd soldier.

05:15:38.759 --> 05:15:41.040
But we all know most of the damage was

05:15:41.040 --> 05:15:42.479
done by the sea wing herself.

05:15:42.540 --> 05:15:45.360
Starflight tried to contain the joy

05:15:45.360 --> 05:15:46.799
bursting under his scales.

05:15:46.860 --> 05:15:49.200
He hoped none of these dragons could

05:15:49.200 --> 05:15:50.459
sense it in his mind.

05:15:50.520 --> 05:15:52.740
They had to be talking about tsunami.

05:15:52.799 --> 05:15:54.060
She was safe.

05:15:54.119 --> 05:15:55.020
At least for now.

05:15:55.080 --> 05:15:56.819
His warning had helped.

05:15:56.880 --> 05:15:59.279
The 1st guard shook his head.

05:15:59.340 --> 05:16:02.700
I hope her majesty never sends me after

05:16:02.700 --> 05:16:03.599
that dragonette.

05:16:03.720 --> 05:16:06.180
I'd rather carve out my eyes than try to

05:16:06.180 --> 05:16:06.540
grab her.

05:16:06.599 --> 05:16:10.020
I heard she nearly bit wisdom's ear off

05:16:10.020 --> 05:16:10.979
said the second.

05:16:11.099 --> 05:16:13.319
The healers are there already.

05:16:13.380 --> 05:16:14.759
But the queen wants you too.

05:16:14.880 --> 05:16:16.799
The 3rd said to mastermind.

05:16:16.860 --> 05:16:17.759
Hurry up.

05:16:17.819 --> 05:16:21.299
Mastermind shelved the last scroll, and

05:16:21.299 --> 05:16:22.259
hurried after the guards.

05:16:22.319 --> 05:16:25.080
No one had told Starflight not to follow

05:16:25.080 --> 05:16:27.419
them, so he did, hoping he'd learn

05:16:27.419 --> 05:16:29.099
something before anyone noticed he was

05:16:29.099 --> 05:16:29.220
there.

05:16:29.279 --> 05:16:32.939
The council chamber echoed with the roars

05:16:32.939 --> 05:16:34.020
of angry dragons.

05:16:34.080 --> 05:16:36.959
Slumped by the entrance were 3 dragons

05:16:36.959 --> 05:16:38.700
who certainly looked as if they'd run

05:16:38.700 --> 05:16:40.439
into the sharper side of tsunami.

05:16:40.500 --> 05:16:42.959
Claw marks were slashed along their wings

05:16:42.959 --> 05:16:46.259
their tails looked bitten and dented, and

05:16:46.259 --> 05:16:48.060
all of their snouts were bleeding.

05:16:48.119 --> 05:16:50.099
Two other night wings were dabbing at

05:16:50.099 --> 05:16:52.439
their wounds with bandages, ointment, and

05:16:52.439 --> 05:16:53.400
disgusted expressions.

05:16:53.520 --> 05:16:57.540
The longer we delay, the stronger they

05:16:57.540 --> 05:17:00.119
get, shouted one of the council members.

05:17:00.180 --> 05:17:01.979
They could attack at any moment.

05:17:02.040 --> 05:17:05.220
We should block off the tunnel so they

05:17:05.220 --> 05:17:07.259
can't come through, cried another.

05:17:07.319 --> 05:17:08.700
It's the only way to be safe.

05:17:08.759 --> 05:17:12.060
Say, full few days, perhaps.

05:17:12.180 --> 05:17:14.939
Greatness interjected from her spot by

05:17:14.939 --> 05:17:15.599
the hidden queen.

05:17:15.659 --> 05:17:17.520
But what about the plan?

05:17:17.580 --> 05:17:20.279
What about the future of this tribe?

05:17:20.340 --> 05:17:22.740
We need that tunnel.

05:17:22.799 --> 05:17:26.759
What we should do is attack right now

05:17:26.819 --> 05:17:29.520
bellowed one of the old dragons on the

05:17:29.520 --> 05:17:29.880
ceiling.

05:17:29.939 --> 05:17:32.819
Without the sand wings.

05:17:32.880 --> 05:17:35.279
Maro Sear's voice interjected.

05:17:35.340 --> 05:17:38.159
Starflight realized that the giant night

05:17:38.159 --> 05:17:40.259
wing was perched not far from greatness

05:17:40.259 --> 05:17:42.419
but he didn't look in Starflight's

05:17:42.419 --> 05:17:42.720
direction.

05:17:42.779 --> 05:17:44.639
Perhaps he hadn't noticed him yet.

05:17:44.700 --> 05:17:47.880
Starflight ducked behind Mastermind, and

05:17:47.880 --> 05:17:49.979
the 3 guards, watching through the gaps

05:17:49.979 --> 05:17:50.700
between their wings.

05:17:50.819 --> 05:17:55.020
Our plan is proceeding as it's supposed

05:17:55.020 --> 05:17:55.380
to.

05:17:55.500 --> 05:17:57.479
Morris here insisted.

05:17:57.540 --> 05:18:00.360
We've chosen our ally, and we have.

05:18:00.479 --> 05:18:03.599
Well, we have most of the dragonettes of

05:18:03.599 --> 05:18:04.080
the prophecy.

05:18:04.139 --> 05:18:08.759
But we need time to get them ready and

05:18:08.759 --> 05:18:10.439
marshal our forces for the attack.

05:18:10.500 --> 05:18:13.020
The plan was supposed to give us 2 more

05:18:13.020 --> 05:18:13.319
years.

05:18:13.380 --> 05:18:15.720
Look at those soldiers.

05:18:15.779 --> 05:18:18.779
Another night wing shouted, gesturing at

05:18:18.779 --> 05:18:20.220
the wounded dragons by the door.

05:18:20.279 --> 05:18:21.779
We don't have 2 years.

05:18:21.900 --> 05:18:23.520
We don't have 2 days.

05:18:23.580 --> 05:18:25.560
Your dragonettes are out of control.

05:18:25.619 --> 05:18:27.779
They're making even the rain wings

05:18:27.779 --> 05:18:29.700
dangerous, and they're threatening the

05:18:29.700 --> 05:18:30.000
whole plan.

05:18:30.119 --> 05:18:31.979
We need to go in now.

05:18:32.040 --> 05:18:34.439
Take out the rain wings and contain the

05:18:34.439 --> 05:18:35.939
dragonettes before they do any more

05:18:35.939 --> 05:18:36.299
damage.

05:18:36.419 --> 05:18:41.099
We're not ready, growled the dragon with

05:18:41.099 --> 05:18:41.639
a missing tooth.

05:18:41.759 --> 05:18:45.000
Mastermind said, we still don't know

05:18:45.000 --> 05:18:46.619
enough about the rain wings.

05:18:46.680 --> 05:18:48.959
We know how to kill them.

05:18:49.080 --> 05:18:50.159
That's all we need to know.

05:18:50.220 --> 05:18:53.340
But where are our extra weapons?

05:18:53.400 --> 05:18:55.919
Where is our specially designed venom

05:18:55.919 --> 05:18:56.639
proof armor?

05:18:56.700 --> 05:18:58.740
Where are our helmets?

05:18:58.799 --> 05:19:00.900
What has mastermind been doing for the

05:19:00.900 --> 05:19:01.619
last 3 days?

05:19:01.680 --> 05:19:05.520
It takes a bit more than 3 days to make

05:19:05.520 --> 05:19:06.959
400 helmets.

05:19:07.080 --> 05:19:09.360
Mastermind called from the doorway

05:19:09.360 --> 05:19:10.259
bristling.

05:19:10.319 --> 05:19:12.360
Suddenly, greatness rose to her full

05:19:12.360 --> 05:19:14.099
height, and spread her wings.

05:19:14.159 --> 05:19:16.860
Silence fell almost instantly around the

05:19:16.860 --> 05:19:17.819
whole chamber.

05:19:17.880 --> 05:19:20.159
Every dragon turned to face the screen

05:19:20.159 --> 05:19:22.560
watching intently as she leaned in to

05:19:22.560 --> 05:19:24.000
listen to the queen's instructions.

05:19:24.060 --> 05:19:27.540
Starflight imagined the creaky rasp of

05:19:27.540 --> 05:19:29.759
Battle Winner's voice echoing through the

05:19:29.759 --> 05:19:30.240
Hidden Room.

05:19:30.299 --> 05:19:33.779
Finally, greatness straightened up and

05:19:33.779 --> 05:19:36.060
fixed the cavern full of dragons with a

05:19:36.060 --> 05:19:37.259
black eyed glare.

05:19:37.319 --> 05:19:41.040
Queen battle winner has made her decision

05:19:41.040 --> 05:19:41.880
she said.

05:19:41.939 --> 05:19:44.819
We cannot delay any longer.

05:19:44.880 --> 05:19:48.060
She looked around, as if daring anyone to

05:19:48.060 --> 05:19:49.619
argue back, but no one did.

05:19:49.740 --> 05:19:53.400
We must go through undercover of darkness

05:19:53.400 --> 05:19:56.340
kill all the rain wings, and take the

05:19:56.340 --> 05:19:57.540
rainforest as planned.

05:19:57.599 --> 05:20:01.020
Not a sound disturbed the terrifying

05:20:01.020 --> 05:20:02.159
stillness of the cavern.

05:20:02.220 --> 05:20:04.740
The night wings were frozen, listening.

05:20:04.860 --> 05:20:07.380
Greatness took a deep breath.

05:20:07.439 --> 05:20:10.439
Tonight, at midnight.

05:20:10.500 --> 05:20:12.119
We attack.

05:20:12.180 --> 05:20:16.560
Part three.

05:20:16.619 --> 05:20:18.180
The truth.
8965
05:20:18,240 --> 05:20:21,240	Chapter 21.

05:20:21.479 --> 05:20:24.599
Starflight raced through the empty

05:20:24.599 --> 05:20:25.080
halls.

05:20:25.139 --> 05:20:27.000
All the night wings in the fortress

05:20:27.000 --> 05:20:28.500
seemed to be clustered around the council

05:20:28.500 --> 05:20:30.779
chamber, trying to hear what was going on

05:20:30.840 --> 05:20:32.700
once he'd fought his way out through the

05:20:32.700 --> 05:20:33.060
crowd.

05:20:33.119 --> 05:20:35.520
The passages were clear all the way back

05:20:35.520 --> 05:20:36.299
to the dormitory.

05:20:36.360 --> 05:20:38.459
I can warn them.

05:20:38.520 --> 05:20:39.840
For once, I can really help.

05:20:39.900 --> 05:20:41.639
I just have to get through to my

05:20:41.639 --> 05:20:42.299
friends.

05:20:42.360 --> 05:20:44.520
Fate speaker was still asleep.

05:20:44.580 --> 05:20:47.400
Her wings tented over her, her side

05:20:47.400 --> 05:20:49.979
rising and falling with deep breaths.

05:20:50.040 --> 05:20:51.419
No one else was in the dormitory.

05:20:51.479 --> 05:20:54.000
Starflight had seen most of the night

05:20:54.000 --> 05:20:56.099
wing dragonettes in the crowd outside the

05:20:56.099 --> 05:20:57.000
council chamber.

05:20:57.060 --> 05:20:59.819
He bolted over to his bed and reached

05:20:59.819 --> 05:21:01.500
into the hole where he'd hidden the dream

05:21:01.500 --> 05:21:01.919
visitor.

05:21:01.979 --> 05:21:04.080
Even in the middle of the day.

05:21:04.139 --> 05:21:05.880
Someone will be asleep.

05:21:05.939 --> 05:21:07.799
Maybe Kinkaju again.

05:21:07.860 --> 05:21:09.840
Another rain wing if I have to.

05:21:09.900 --> 05:21:13.020
Maybe Glory will be having her suntime.

05:21:13.080 --> 05:21:14.759
I can get a message through to someone.

05:21:14.819 --> 05:21:17.279
I have to, or they'll all be killed

05:21:17.279 --> 05:21:17.700
tonight.

05:21:17.759 --> 05:21:21.119
His claws closed on empty space.

05:21:21.180 --> 05:21:24.840
Starflight's chest constricted, and he

05:21:24.840 --> 05:21:26.700
crouched, scrabbling through all the

05:21:26.700 --> 05:21:27.840
holes around his bed.

05:21:27.840 --> 05:21:30.240
He flung the blanket aside and searched

05:21:30.240 --> 05:21:32.220
from one end of the hollow to the other.

05:21:32.279 --> 05:21:34.799
He checked the beds on either side, his

05:21:34.799 --> 05:21:36.599
heart pounding faster and faster.

05:21:36.659 --> 05:21:38.340
But there was no doubt.

05:21:38.400 --> 05:21:40.319
The dream visitor was gone.

05:21:40.380 --> 05:21:43.319
No, he whispered.

05:21:43.380 --> 05:21:45.240
Scratching at the hiding spot again.

05:21:45.299 --> 05:21:47.340
How could it be gone?

05:21:47.580 --> 05:21:48.959
Someone must have seen him.

05:21:49.020 --> 05:21:51.840
Someone had lifted the blanket last night

05:21:51.840 --> 05:21:55.259
and realized what he had in his talons.

05:21:55.319 --> 05:21:57.060
Someone had watched from the shadows and

05:21:57.060 --> 05:21:58.139
taken it while he was away.

05:21:58.200 --> 05:21:59.700
But who?

05:21:59.759 --> 05:22:01.319
Could it be Marosier?

05:22:01.380 --> 05:22:03.479
Surely the large dragon would have

05:22:03.479 --> 05:22:05.700
punished Starfight severely if he'd

05:22:05.700 --> 05:22:06.959
caught him with a dream visitor.

05:22:07.020 --> 05:22:09.540
But maybe the punishment just hadn't

05:22:09.540 --> 05:22:10.020
landed yet.

05:22:10.020 --> 05:22:12.240
More important.

05:22:12.299 --> 05:22:13.919
What do I do now?

05:22:13.979 --> 05:22:16.139
Starflight?

05:22:16.200 --> 05:22:19.139
He whirled around and realized that fate

05:22:19.139 --> 05:22:21.060
speaker was awake and right behind him

05:22:21.119 --> 05:22:23.639
watching with a confused expression.

05:22:23.700 --> 05:22:26.159
She hopped up on the nearest bed and

05:22:26.159 --> 05:22:26.939
peered into his face.

05:22:27.000 --> 05:22:29.880
Why are you flapping around like a

05:22:29.880 --> 05:22:31.259
scavenger with its head bitten off?

05:22:31.319 --> 05:22:34.919
I lost something, Starflight said.

05:22:34.979 --> 05:22:37.860
I mean, I left it right here, but it's

05:22:37.860 --> 05:22:39.779
gone, and I really, really need it.

05:22:39.840 --> 05:22:41.880
Did you see anyone over here today?

05:22:41.939 --> 05:22:43.439
She shook her head.

05:22:43.500 --> 05:22:45.180
Why?

05:22:45.240 --> 05:22:46.080
What is it?

05:22:46.139 --> 05:22:49.319
It's, he hesitated.

05:22:49.380 --> 05:22:51.060
How much should he tell her?

05:22:51.119 --> 05:22:53.639
She seemed like the only dragon he could

05:22:53.639 --> 05:22:55.619
trust on this whole island, and he needed

05:22:55.619 --> 05:22:58.200
help, but would she be willing to betray

05:22:58.200 --> 05:22:58.740
her tribe?

05:22:58.799 --> 05:23:01.860
Do you want to help the rain wings?

05:23:01.979 --> 05:23:02.580
He asked.

05:23:02.639 --> 05:23:05.340
The sad dragons?

05:23:05.340 --> 05:23:06.540
she said blinking.

05:23:06.599 --> 05:23:08.040
Of course I do.

05:23:08.159 --> 05:23:11.459
Not just the prisoners here, he said.

05:23:11.520 --> 05:23:13.439
The whole tribe is in danger.

05:23:13.500 --> 05:23:15.659
The night wings are planning to invade

05:23:15.659 --> 05:23:17.279
their rainforest through that tunnel I

05:23:17.279 --> 05:23:17.700
told you about.

05:23:17.819 --> 05:23:20.099
They're going to kill all their rain

05:23:20.099 --> 05:23:22.319
wings, and they're doing it tonight.

05:23:22.380 --> 05:23:25.080
Fate speaker's eyes widened.

05:23:25.139 --> 05:23:26.459
Why?

05:23:26.520 --> 05:23:27.479
She cried.

05:23:27.540 --> 05:23:30.479
To steal the territory for their own, he

05:23:30.479 --> 05:23:30.779
said.

05:23:30.840 --> 05:23:33.060
That's the thing, fate speaker.

05:23:33.119 --> 05:23:35.819
If you help me help the rain wings, it

05:23:35.819 --> 05:23:37.560
means stopping the night wing plan.

05:23:37.619 --> 05:23:40.259
It means leaving our own tribe stuck on

05:23:40.259 --> 05:23:40.619
this island.

05:23:40.680 --> 05:23:42.180
It's hard.

05:23:42.299 --> 05:23:45.479
I can see how miserable they are here, but

05:23:45.479 --> 05:23:46.860
I can't let them do this to the rain

05:23:46.860 --> 05:23:47.340
wings.

05:23:47.400 --> 05:23:49.259
Me neither.

05:23:49.319 --> 05:23:51.240
Fate speaker said firmly.

05:23:51.299 --> 05:23:52.680
Tell me what I can do.

05:23:52.740 --> 05:23:57.360
Well, Starflight said, I have no idea.

05:23:57.419 --> 05:23:59.880
She smacked him with one of her wings.

05:23:59.939 --> 05:24:02.459
You can't get me all wild up and tell me

05:24:02.459 --> 05:24:03.119
there's no plan?

05:24:03.240 --> 05:24:05.279
We're going to warn the rain wings

05:24:05.279 --> 05:24:05.459
right?

05:24:05.520 --> 05:24:07.439
He turned back to his bed.

05:24:07.560 --> 05:24:10.860
That's what I was trying to do, but the

05:24:10.860 --> 05:24:12.479
dream visitor's missing and...

05:24:12.479 --> 05:24:14.520
He turned back around and found her

05:24:14.520 --> 05:24:15.419
halfway to the door.

05:24:15.479 --> 05:24:17.520
Wait, fate speaker.

05:24:17.580 --> 05:24:20.279
He leaped after her, caught her tail and

05:24:20.279 --> 05:24:21.419
dragged her back toward him.

05:24:21.479 --> 05:24:22.380
Where are you going?

05:24:22.500 --> 05:24:25.139
She looked at him as if he were crazy.

05:24:25.200 --> 05:24:28.020
To warn the rain wings, like we just

05:24:28.020 --> 05:24:28.560
decided.

05:24:28.560 --> 05:24:32.040
You mean, go to the rainforest?

05:24:32.099 --> 05:24:33.119
He said.

05:24:33.180 --> 05:24:35.639
His heart was hammering, and his legs

05:24:35.639 --> 05:24:37.080
felt as though they could barely hold him

05:24:37.080 --> 05:24:39.180
up, but something in his head was also

05:24:39.180 --> 05:24:42.659
shouting, yes, yes, this is what you have

05:24:42.659 --> 05:24:43.020
to do.

05:24:43.080 --> 05:24:44.279
Go do it.

05:24:44.340 --> 05:24:46.020
He started pacing.

05:24:46.080 --> 05:24:48.119
We can't fly there.

05:24:48.180 --> 05:24:49.380
It'll take too long.

05:24:49.439 --> 05:24:52.020
We have to go through the tunnel, but

05:24:52.020 --> 05:24:52.560
that's impossible.

05:24:52.619 --> 05:24:54.900
There will be a 1000000 dragons guarding

05:24:54.900 --> 05:24:55.020
it.

05:24:55.080 --> 05:24:57.419
I'm not clay or tsunami.

05:24:57.540 --> 05:25:00.599
I can't even fight one dragonette, let

05:25:00.599 --> 05:25:02.520
alone a whole squadron of full grown

05:25:02.520 --> 05:25:03.180
night wings.

05:25:03.180 --> 05:25:06.479
But we have to try, fate speaker said.

05:25:06.540 --> 05:25:07.979
So let's do it.

05:25:08.040 --> 05:25:10.740
She pressed her front talons to her head

05:25:10.740 --> 05:25:11.340
and smiled.

05:25:11.400 --> 05:25:14.099
My vision says we shall succeed.

05:25:14.159 --> 05:25:16.560
Let's charge the tunnel and see how far

05:25:16.560 --> 05:25:16.919
we get.

05:25:16.979 --> 05:25:19.080
Starflight winced.

05:25:19.139 --> 05:25:22.680
Not to argue with your visions, but I can

05:25:22.680 --> 05:25:25.380
tell you exactly how far we'll get, into

05:25:25.380 --> 05:25:27.659
the cell next to Death Bringers, if we're

05:25:27.659 --> 05:25:29.939
lucky, or tossed into the volcano, if

05:25:29.939 --> 05:25:30.360
we're not.

05:25:30.419 --> 05:25:32.639
She dropped her arms and looked

05:25:32.639 --> 05:25:33.599
thoughtful for a minute.

05:25:33.659 --> 05:25:38.040
So, what if I distract the guards and you

05:25:38.040 --> 05:25:38.459
sneak through?

05:25:38.520 --> 05:25:41.040
I have a vision that says that will

05:25:41.040 --> 05:25:42.000
totally work.

05:25:42.060 --> 05:25:43.740
He shook his head.

05:25:43.799 --> 05:25:46.860
That's how Death Bringer got clay here.

05:25:46.919 --> 05:25:48.659
I doubt they'll fall for that again.

05:25:48.720 --> 05:25:51.000
We have to do this the smart way.

05:25:51.060 --> 05:25:53.459
Maybe there's a way to trick them.

05:25:53.520 --> 05:25:55.680
Who would be allowed through the tunnel?

05:25:55.799 --> 05:25:58.080
He tapped his claws on the floor.

05:25:58.139 --> 05:26:01.080
The soldiers who tried to grab tsunami

05:26:01.080 --> 05:26:01.740
were allowed through.

05:26:01.799 --> 05:26:04.380
Perhaps we could say the queen sent us to

05:26:04.380 --> 05:26:05.159
kidnap Sonny.

05:26:05.220 --> 05:26:07.560
Fate speaker looked down at herself

05:26:07.560 --> 05:26:08.459
dubiously.

05:26:08.520 --> 05:26:10.200
Right.

05:26:10.259 --> 05:26:11.819
Two Dragonettes.

05:26:11.880 --> 05:26:13.259
They won't believe that at all.

05:26:13.319 --> 05:26:15.840
Starfly picked up a scroll from

05:26:15.840 --> 05:26:18.240
Mindreader's bed and turned it nervously

05:26:18.240 --> 05:26:19.020
between his talons.

05:26:19.139 --> 05:26:21.060
So who else?

05:26:21.119 --> 05:26:22.740
Or why else?

05:26:22.860 --> 05:26:25.439
It was like a thunderbolt hitting him.

05:26:25.500 --> 05:26:29.040
Ooh, you have an idea, fate speaker

05:26:29.040 --> 05:26:29.400
said.

05:26:29.459 --> 05:26:31.919
I do, Starflight said.

05:26:31.979 --> 05:26:34.799
It's worth a try, but we need one more

05:26:34.799 --> 05:26:35.939
dragon to make it work.

05:26:36.000 --> 05:26:39.419
In her nighttime wanderings.

05:26:39.479 --> 05:26:41.279
Fate speaker had found the healer's hall

05:26:41.279 --> 05:26:43.020
and she was able to lead the way back

05:26:43.020 --> 05:26:44.040
there without hesitation.

05:26:44.099 --> 05:26:46.439
Star Light glanced in first.

05:26:46.500 --> 05:26:49.560
As he'd hoped, the healers were still in

05:26:49.560 --> 05:26:51.180
the council chamber with the soldiers

05:26:51.180 --> 05:26:52.200
who'd fought tsunami.

05:26:52.259 --> 05:26:54.779
The large room was mostly deserted.

05:26:54.840 --> 05:26:56.759
A few dragons slept restlessly on the

05:26:56.759 --> 05:26:59.520
narrow stone beds, most of them with lava

05:26:59.520 --> 05:27:01.380
related injuries from the looks of it.

05:27:01.380 --> 05:27:04.020
Two of the night wings bore recent rain

05:27:04.020 --> 05:27:06.959
wing venom scars, and he realized those

05:27:06.959 --> 05:27:08.880
must have been the ones Gloria attacked

05:27:08.880 --> 05:27:10.020
during her escape.

05:27:10.139 --> 05:27:12.419
They smelled slightly of poppies and

05:27:12.419 --> 05:27:14.759
anise, and he guessed they were in some

05:27:14.759 --> 05:27:16.319
kind of medicine induced stupor.

05:27:16.380 --> 05:27:19.919
A fire blazed in a rough fireplace in the

05:27:19.919 --> 05:27:21.900
center of the wall, and in the bed

05:27:21.900 --> 05:27:25.319
closest to it was Flame, fast asleep.

05:27:25.500 --> 05:27:27.659
There was a strip of cloth tied around

05:27:27.659 --> 05:27:30.240
his head, but now Starflight could see a

05:27:30.240 --> 05:27:31.500
little more of what Viper had

05:27:31.500 --> 05:27:33.419
accidentally done to the sky wing.

05:27:33.479 --> 05:27:36.299
A vicious slash ran from one corner of

05:27:36.299 --> 05:27:38.880
his mouth, sideways and up across his

05:27:38.880 --> 05:27:41.520
face, straight through the opposite eye.

05:27:41.580 --> 05:27:44.880
It oozed blood, and something darker.

05:27:44.939 --> 05:27:47.099
Oh, flame.

05:27:47.159 --> 05:27:49.500
Fate speaker whispered, her voice

05:27:49.500 --> 05:27:50.040
breaking.

05:27:50.099 --> 05:27:53.639
It's not as bad as I thought, Starflight

05:27:53.639 --> 05:27:55.139
whispered to her, trying to be

05:27:55.139 --> 05:27:55.860
reassuring.

05:27:55.919 --> 05:27:58.080
Viper only hit one of his eyes.

05:27:58.139 --> 05:28:01.200
That means, hopefully, he'll still be

05:28:01.200 --> 05:28:03.180
able to see out of the other one, so he

05:28:03.180 --> 05:28:04.200
won't be completely blind.

05:28:04.259 --> 05:28:07.020
If we can save him.

05:28:07.080 --> 05:28:08.639
Fate speaker said.

05:28:08.700 --> 05:28:09.900
Right.

05:28:09.959 --> 05:28:11.700
He took a deep breath.

05:28:11.759 --> 05:28:14.880
I wish we didn't have to wake him, she

05:28:14.880 --> 05:28:15.479
whispered.

05:28:15.540 --> 05:28:16.740
I'll do it.

05:28:16.799 --> 05:28:19.439
He touched Flame's shoulder with one

05:28:19.439 --> 05:28:19.740
wing.

05:28:19.860 --> 05:28:21.119
Flame?

05:28:21.180 --> 05:28:22.500
Flame, wake up.

05:28:22.560 --> 05:28:23.520
It's important.

05:28:23.639 --> 05:28:26.459
The sky wing blearily opened his good

05:28:26.459 --> 05:28:26.939
eye.

05:28:27.000 --> 05:28:29.040
He moaned at the side of them and closed

05:28:29.040 --> 05:28:29.459
it again.

05:28:29.520 --> 05:28:32.819
You have to come with us, fate speaker

05:28:32.819 --> 05:28:33.180
said.

05:28:33.240 --> 05:28:36.479
We know how to save you, Starflight added

05:28:36.479 --> 05:28:38.819
but it'll only work if we go now.

05:28:38.880 --> 05:28:42.299
Flame mumbled something that sounded like

05:28:42.299 --> 05:28:44.459
why would you save me?

05:28:44.520 --> 05:28:47.939
Because you're my friend, and it's the

05:28:47.939 --> 05:28:48.599
right thing to do.

05:28:48.659 --> 05:28:53.099
Fate speaker said. muttered Flame.

05:28:53.159 --> 05:28:56.220
Starflight poked him in the side, because

05:28:56.220 --> 05:28:58.200
we can use your tragic phase to get us

05:28:58.200 --> 05:28:58.740
off this island.

05:28:58.799 --> 05:29:01.500
There was a pause.

05:29:01.560 --> 05:29:03.360
Flame lifted his head and squinted at

05:29:03.360 --> 05:29:03.900
Starflight.

05:29:03.959 --> 05:29:07.740
That sounds like a real reason, he said

05:29:07.740 --> 05:29:09.959
in a stronger voice. although it still

05:29:09.959 --> 05:29:12.180
had a blurry sound to it, and his head

05:29:12.180 --> 05:29:14.159
wobbled like his brain was wrapped in

05:29:14.159 --> 05:29:14.880
sheep's wool.

05:29:15.000 --> 05:29:17.639
Starflight held out his wing, and their

05:29:17.639 --> 05:29:19.860
red dragonette slowly slid off the bed

05:29:19.860 --> 05:29:21.959
resting his weight on Starflight's

05:29:21.959 --> 05:29:22.200
shoulder.

05:29:22.259 --> 05:29:24.900
Fate speaker hurried ahead to the door

05:29:24.900 --> 05:29:27.540
waved an all clear, and led the way to

05:29:27.540 --> 05:29:29.159
the nearest balcony overlooking the

05:29:29.159 --> 05:29:29.819
prison caves.

05:29:29.880 --> 05:29:32.819
Starflight paused on the edge of the

05:29:32.819 --> 05:29:33.959
balcony, looking out.

05:29:34.020 --> 05:29:36.659
Down there was the black sand beach.

05:29:36.720 --> 05:29:38.819
Down there was the tunnel to the

05:29:38.819 --> 05:29:39.720
rainforest.

05:29:39.720 --> 05:29:42.479
Down there was the gateway back to his

05:29:42.479 --> 05:29:43.200
friends.

05:29:43.259 --> 05:29:46.979
And down there, were an unknown number of

05:29:46.979 --> 05:29:49.020
Nightwing soldiers who might take one

05:29:49.020 --> 05:29:51.119
look at Starflight, Flame, and Fate

05:29:51.119 --> 05:29:53.400
speaker, and send them to the dungeon for

05:29:53.400 --> 05:29:56.279
life, or until the volcano erupted and

05:29:56.279 --> 05:29:56.939
killed them anyway.

05:29:57.000 --> 05:30:00.720
There's no time to be afraid, Starflight

05:30:00.720 --> 05:30:01.319
told himself.

05:30:01.380 --> 05:30:04.439
This is the only thing you can do, and

05:30:04.439 --> 05:30:05.520
you must do it.

05:30:05.580 --> 05:30:09.180
Supporting flame between them, Starflight

05:30:09.180 --> 05:30:11.159
and fate speaker launched themselves into

05:30:11.159 --> 05:30:13.380
the sky and flew toward the tunnel.
9261
05:30:13,439 --> 05:30:17,819	Chapter 22.

05:30:18.000 --> 05:30:21.299
It wasn't hard to guess where the tunnel

05:30:21.299 --> 05:30:22.380
to the rainforest was.

05:30:22.439 --> 05:30:24.900
Once they reached the Black Sand Beach

05:30:24.900 --> 05:30:27.599
the cluster of armed night wings gathered

05:30:27.599 --> 05:30:29.819
in the entrance of a certain cave was a

05:30:29.819 --> 05:30:30.479
fairly strong clue.

05:30:30.599 --> 05:30:32.819
Be confident.

05:30:32.939 --> 05:30:35.639
Starflight said to fate speaker, thinking

05:30:35.639 --> 05:30:37.619
of tsunami bluffing the seawing

05:30:37.619 --> 05:30:38.040
soldiers.

05:30:38.099 --> 05:30:40.560
Act like we're doing exactly what we're

05:30:40.560 --> 05:30:41.400
supposed to be doing.

05:30:41.459 --> 05:30:44.580
Not a problem, fate speaker said.

05:30:44.580 --> 05:30:46.080
I mean, we are.

05:30:46.139 --> 05:30:49.500
Starflight guessed that she rarely had

05:30:49.500 --> 05:30:50.520
trouble with her confidence.

05:30:50.580 --> 05:30:53.220
Now he just had to follow his own advice

05:30:53.220 --> 05:30:55.860
and he had to hope that the news hadn't

05:30:55.860 --> 05:30:57.540
gotten here from the council chamber yet

05:30:57.540 --> 05:30:59.759
that these guards wouldn't know about the

05:30:59.759 --> 05:31:00.779
planned attack tonight.

05:31:00.840 --> 05:31:04.020
They landed just inside the cave mouth.

05:31:04.080 --> 05:31:06.419
Staggering forward under Flame's weight.

05:31:06.479 --> 05:31:09.060
The red dragonette slid slowly to the

05:31:09.060 --> 05:31:09.299
ground.

05:31:09.360 --> 05:31:12.240
He looked groggy and close to fainting.

05:31:12.299 --> 05:31:13.860
Stay with us.

05:31:13.979 --> 05:31:16.619
Starflight said to him, squeezing one of

05:31:16.619 --> 05:31:17.520
Flame's talons.

05:31:17.580 --> 05:31:19.919
What is the meaning of this?

05:31:20.040 --> 05:31:22.500
Growled the biggest night wing guard?

05:31:22.560 --> 05:31:25.200
He paced forward to loom over them

05:31:25.200 --> 05:31:27.419
glaring at flame in particular.

05:31:27.479 --> 05:31:30.479
Here we go, Starfly thought.

05:31:30.599 --> 05:31:33.419
Maybe all those games of pretend we used

05:31:33.419 --> 05:31:35.220
to play will turn out to be useful after

05:31:35.220 --> 05:31:35.400
all.

05:31:35.459 --> 05:31:38.099
Didn't you get the message?

05:31:38.159 --> 05:31:40.740
I knew that would happen, he said.

05:31:40.799 --> 05:31:43.439
He wanted to sound bold and authoritative

05:31:43.439 --> 05:31:45.720
like tsunami, but his voice sounded

05:31:45.720 --> 05:31:47.520
higher and more anxious than he'd hoped.

05:31:47.580 --> 05:31:49.139
So work with that.

05:31:49.200 --> 05:31:51.599
It makes sense that I'd be anxious about

05:31:51.599 --> 05:31:52.080
this plan.

05:31:52.139 --> 05:31:54.959
If I can't be tsunami, then try to

05:31:54.959 --> 05:31:57.419
convince them as Starfight, the nervous

05:31:57.419 --> 05:31:57.959
know it all.

05:31:58.139 --> 05:31:59.759
He pointed at Flame.

05:31:59.819 --> 05:32:02.459
This is one of the dragonettes of the

05:32:02.459 --> 05:32:02.939
prophecy.

05:32:03.000 --> 05:32:05.459
As you can see, he was slashed by a

05:32:05.459 --> 05:32:06.479
sandwing tail today.

05:32:06.540 --> 05:32:09.479
Starflight peeled up the bandage a little

05:32:09.479 --> 05:32:11.520
so the guards could see the oozing wound

05:32:11.520 --> 05:32:12.060
underneath.

05:32:12.119 --> 05:32:14.880
All of them let out a collective gasp of

05:32:14.880 --> 05:32:16.259
horror and stepped back.

05:32:16.319 --> 05:32:18.840
Starflight straightened and folded his

05:32:18.840 --> 05:32:19.139
wings.

05:32:19.200 --> 05:32:21.959
The venom is extremely deadly.

05:32:22.020 --> 05:32:24.299
The queen has ordered us to take him

05:32:24.299 --> 05:32:26.340
through to the rainforest, and from there

05:32:26.340 --> 05:32:28.200
to the kingdom of sand to find a cure.

05:32:28.259 --> 05:32:32.700
You, said the head guard skeptically.

05:32:32.759 --> 05:32:34.080
I know.

05:32:34.139 --> 05:32:36.659
I was nervous about the whole idea too

05:32:36.659 --> 05:32:39.060
Starflight said, hoping they'd believe

05:32:39.060 --> 05:32:40.979
that was why his talons were shaking.

05:32:41.040 --> 05:32:43.979
But she said, I'm the only night wing who

05:32:43.979 --> 05:32:45.900
won't be attacked or chased away by the

05:32:45.900 --> 05:32:48.060
dragonettes in the rainforest.

05:32:48.119 --> 05:32:48.479
They know me.

05:32:48.540 --> 05:32:50.700
They'll think I'm on their side.

05:32:50.759 --> 05:32:52.080
Can you imagine?

05:32:52.139 --> 05:32:54.419
A night wing being friends with a sea

05:32:54.419 --> 05:32:58.500
wing or a mud wing or a rain wing of all

05:32:58.500 --> 05:32:59.099
creatures?

05:32:59.159 --> 05:33:02.639
A few of the guards were nodding, but the

05:33:02.639 --> 05:33:03.900
biggest one didn't look convinced.

05:33:04.020 --> 05:33:07.560
I'll have to verify this order. the big

05:33:07.560 --> 05:33:09.540
guard said, signaling one of the other

05:33:09.540 --> 05:33:10.500
dragons forward.

05:33:10.560 --> 05:33:14.759
Of course you do, Starflight said, letting

05:33:14.759 --> 05:33:16.439
his panic spill into his voice a little.

05:33:16.500 --> 05:33:18.779
I said this would happen.

05:33:18.840 --> 05:33:21.299
She's going to be so angry, he said to

05:33:21.299 --> 05:33:22.080
fate speaker.

05:33:22.139 --> 05:33:23.459
Then turned back to the guard.

05:33:23.520 --> 05:33:26.040
I told them you delay us by sending

05:33:26.040 --> 05:33:27.360
someone back to the fortress.

05:33:27.479 --> 05:33:30.240
I told them this Sky Wing would be dead

05:33:30.240 --> 05:33:32.279
before we got through, but nobody listens

05:33:32.279 --> 05:33:32.520
to me.

05:33:32.639 --> 05:33:36.119
Her majesty said, you'd take one look at

05:33:36.119 --> 05:33:38.220
him and understand the urgency, and that

05:33:38.220 --> 05:33:38.819
I shouldn't worry.

05:33:38.939 --> 05:33:42.299
He rung his claws together, but of course

05:33:42.299 --> 05:33:43.200
I was right to worry.

05:33:43.259 --> 05:33:45.840
I am always right about worrying.

05:33:45.900 --> 05:33:48.959
Um, said the guard.

05:33:49.020 --> 05:33:51.360
He was starting to look almost as nervous

05:33:51.360 --> 05:33:52.439
as Starfight felt.

05:33:52.500 --> 05:33:55.080
He's really that close to dead.

05:33:55.139 --> 05:33:59.099
It's all right, Starflight said, rubbing

05:33:59.099 --> 05:33:59.880
his head anxiously.

05:33:59.939 --> 05:34:02.220
I do exactly the same thing in your

05:34:02.220 --> 05:34:02.580
place.

05:34:02.639 --> 05:34:05.279
She'll probably kill all of us, but what

05:34:05.279 --> 05:34:05.880
else could you do?

05:34:06.000 --> 05:34:07.979
He nodded at the messenger.

05:34:08.099 --> 05:34:09.240
Go ahead.

05:34:09.299 --> 05:34:11.040
You can tell her it doesn't really matter

05:34:11.040 --> 05:34:12.779
since he'll be dead by the time you

05:34:12.779 --> 05:34:13.020
return.

05:34:13.139 --> 05:34:16.380
He nudged Flame with one toe.

05:34:16.439 --> 05:34:18.479
The Skywing obligingly looked even more

05:34:18.479 --> 05:34:20.220
like a dying fish.

05:34:20.279 --> 05:34:21.659
But he can't die.

05:34:21.720 --> 05:34:24.720
Fate speaker jumped in, as if she'd been

05:34:24.720 --> 05:34:26.520
having this argument with Starflight the

05:34:26.520 --> 05:34:26.939
whole way here.

05:34:27.000 --> 05:34:30.060
He's the only sky wing we've got without

05:34:30.060 --> 05:34:30.479
him?

05:34:30.540 --> 05:34:34.200
No prophecy, no plan, no rainforest home

05:34:34.200 --> 05:34:34.979
for our tribe.

05:34:35.099 --> 05:34:37.560
The guards behind the leader were

05:34:37.560 --> 05:34:39.659
starting to mutter, and crane their necks

05:34:39.659 --> 05:34:40.560
to peer at flame.

05:34:40.619 --> 05:34:44.220
But he has to check the order, Starflight

05:34:44.220 --> 05:34:44.819
argued back.

05:34:44.880 --> 05:34:46.200
What's he going to do?

05:34:46.259 --> 05:34:49.020
Just let 2 night wing dragonettes wander

05:34:49.020 --> 05:34:50.939
through the tunnel with a sky wing?

05:34:51.000 --> 05:34:53.520
Why, we might, we might...

05:34:53.639 --> 05:34:55.860
He paused, then looked at the guard.

05:34:55.919 --> 05:34:58.139
What are you worried we'll do?

05:34:58.200 --> 05:35:03.240
Well, I don't know, he said, shifting a

05:35:03.240 --> 05:35:04.560
spear from talent to talon.

05:35:04.619 --> 05:35:06.659
I'm just following protocol.

05:35:06.720 --> 05:35:08.220
See?

05:35:08.279 --> 05:35:10.200
Starflight said to fate speaker.

05:35:10.259 --> 05:35:11.400
Protocol.

05:35:11.459 --> 05:35:14.759
Flame wheezed in a dying gasp kind of

05:35:14.759 --> 05:35:14.939
way.

05:35:15.000 --> 05:35:18.419
We gotta let them through, chief. said

05:35:18.419 --> 05:35:19.080
one of the guards.

05:35:19.139 --> 05:35:20.459
The queen is right.

05:35:20.520 --> 05:35:22.860
This dragonette is the only one who can

05:35:22.860 --> 05:35:23.880
get into the rainforest.

05:35:23.939 --> 05:35:25.740
That's where we grabbed him from.

05:35:25.799 --> 05:35:27.779
He can get that sky wing to the cure.

05:35:27.840 --> 05:35:28.740
No one else can.

05:35:28.799 --> 05:35:31.680
Starflight gave her a grateful look that

05:35:31.680 --> 05:35:33.240
was entirely heartfelt.

05:35:33.299 --> 05:35:35.819
The head guard flexed his claws with an

05:35:35.819 --> 05:35:37.080
uneasy expression.

05:35:37.139 --> 05:35:41.279
No funny business, he said to Starflight

05:35:41.279 --> 05:35:43.740
you fix that sky wing and come back.

05:35:43.799 --> 05:35:47.520
We'll be back by nightfall, fate speaker

05:35:47.520 --> 05:35:48.540
promised.

05:35:48.599 --> 05:35:49.919
Maybe we'll even learn something about

05:35:49.919 --> 05:35:51.000
what they're planning over there.

05:35:51.060 --> 05:35:52.799
They'll probably tell this one

05:35:52.799 --> 05:35:53.279
everything.

05:35:53.340 --> 05:35:55.680
She jerked her head at Starflight.

05:35:55.740 --> 05:35:57.540
He's got them wrapped around his tail

05:35:57.540 --> 05:35:58.259
from what I hear.

05:35:58.380 --> 05:36:01.979
Makes sense, said another guard.

05:36:02.040 --> 05:36:05.099
Let him through. chorused 2 more.

05:36:05.159 --> 05:36:07.500
Their leader glanced toward the fortress

05:36:07.500 --> 05:36:10.860
again, and then finally, warily stepped

05:36:10.860 --> 05:36:11.639
back out of their way.

05:36:11.700 --> 05:36:15.180
Starflight heaved flame up, flopping the

05:36:15.180 --> 05:36:16.979
dragonette's red wing over one of his own

05:36:16.979 --> 05:36:19.500
shoulders, and then he and fate speaker

05:36:19.500 --> 05:36:21.479
dragged him down the long corridor to the

05:36:21.479 --> 05:36:24.119
back cave, where a dark hole in the wall

05:36:24.119 --> 05:36:27.360
radiated the wrongness, the Starflight

05:36:27.360 --> 05:36:28.619
remembered from the tunnels in the

05:36:28.619 --> 05:36:29.159
rainforest.

05:36:29.220 --> 05:36:32.159
The Nightwing guards stared at them as

05:36:32.159 --> 05:36:33.000
they went past.

05:36:33.000 --> 05:36:35.279
Starflight kept expecting one of them to

05:36:35.279 --> 05:36:36.720
yell, it's a trick.

05:36:36.779 --> 05:36:37.500
They're lying.

05:36:37.560 --> 05:36:39.840
He forced himself to concentrate on their

05:36:39.840 --> 05:36:40.139
story.

05:36:40.200 --> 05:36:43.319
Flame needs the cure for Sandwing Venom.

05:36:43.380 --> 05:36:45.240
We have to take him through to save him.

05:36:45.299 --> 05:36:48.360
It had the advantage of being true, which

05:36:48.360 --> 05:36:48.720
helped.

05:36:48.779 --> 05:36:51.659
As they reached the hole, one of the

05:36:51.659 --> 05:36:53.580
guards stepped forward suddenly, and

05:36:53.580 --> 05:36:55.740
Starflight just barely managed to stop

05:36:55.740 --> 05:36:57.419
himself from clenching away.

05:36:57.419 --> 05:36:59.819
It turned out, she was reaching to help

05:36:59.819 --> 05:37:01.619
them lift flame into the hole.

05:37:01.680 --> 05:37:04.200
Starflight nodded to her, and then hopped

05:37:04.200 --> 05:37:05.459
out to join the sky wing.

05:37:05.520 --> 05:37:08.520
We did it, but we're not safe yet.

05:37:08.580 --> 05:37:11.700
In the tunnel, there was just enough

05:37:11.700 --> 05:37:12.540
space to fly.

05:37:12.599 --> 05:37:16.020
Fate speaker went first, then flame at a

05:37:16.020 --> 05:37:18.540
wobbly flap that felt excruciatingly slow

05:37:18.540 --> 05:37:21.240
to Starflight, and they began the winding

05:37:21.240 --> 05:37:22.799
trek back toward the rainforest.

05:37:22.860 --> 05:37:26.759
The air grew warmer and wetter, and the

05:37:26.759 --> 05:37:28.979
sounds of insects and monkeys chittering

05:37:28.979 --> 05:37:30.540
began to reverberate off the walls.

05:37:30.599 --> 05:37:33.299
Fate speaker twisted to glance back at

05:37:33.299 --> 05:37:35.819
Starflight with a grin, but he couldn't

05:37:35.819 --> 05:37:38.939
force his mouth into a smile, not yet, not

05:37:38.939 --> 05:37:40.979
until he felt the jungle earth crumbling

05:37:40.979 --> 05:37:41.819
between his claws.

05:37:41.880 --> 05:37:44.639
Green sunlight shone up ahead of them.

05:37:44.700 --> 05:37:47.819
Fate speaker twitched in a happy way, and

05:37:47.819 --> 05:37:49.680
sped up without seeming to realize it.

05:37:49.799 --> 05:37:52.319
She shot out into the rainforest several

05:37:52.319 --> 05:37:53.700
lengths before flame.

05:37:53.759 --> 05:37:57.299
Starflight heard her scream, and then the

05:37:57.299 --> 05:37:58.919
scream abruptly cut off.

05:37:58.919 --> 05:38:01.619
He shoved flame forcefully out of the

05:38:01.619 --> 05:38:04.080
hole and burst out into a glorious warm

05:38:04.080 --> 05:38:04.380
day.

05:38:04.439 --> 05:38:07.200
Magenta pink flowers dripped from the

05:38:07.200 --> 05:38:09.779
trees, and a number of silvery sloths

05:38:09.779 --> 05:38:11.520
poked their heads through the leaves to

05:38:11.520 --> 05:38:12.540
examine the newcomers.

05:38:12.599 --> 05:38:15.360
A bird with long blue tail feathers

05:38:15.360 --> 05:38:18.299
strutted by, eyeing him beadly.

05:38:18.360 --> 05:38:20.939
Stop right there, a voice yelled.

05:38:21.000 --> 05:38:23.520
Don't move, and put your talons on your

05:38:23.520 --> 05:38:25.500
head and surrender, and claws where I can

05:38:25.500 --> 05:38:25.979
see them.

05:38:26.040 --> 05:38:28.500
Starflight wasn't sure which conflicting

05:38:28.500 --> 05:38:29.279
order to follow.

05:38:29.340 --> 05:38:31.619
He twisted rapidly in a circle and

05:38:31.619 --> 05:38:33.540
spotted fate speaker lying next to the

05:38:33.540 --> 05:38:36.119
stream, with an orange gold rain wing

05:38:36.119 --> 05:38:38.220
sitting cheerfully on top of her, wrapping

05:38:38.220 --> 05:38:39.299
vines around her snout.

05:38:39.360 --> 05:38:42.720
Another rain wing materialized slowly in

05:38:42.720 --> 05:38:45.180
front of him, her scales changing colors

05:38:45.180 --> 05:38:46.560
so she no longer blended into the

05:38:46.560 --> 05:38:47.040
background.

05:38:47.099 --> 05:38:49.500
You're my prisoner, she cried.

05:38:49.560 --> 05:38:50.520
Run for your life.

05:38:50.639 --> 05:38:52.740
Mango.

05:38:52.919 --> 05:38:55.380
You can't just yell things at random, said

05:38:55.380 --> 05:38:56.700
a familiar voice.

05:38:56.759 --> 05:38:58.380
Tsunami dropped down from one of the

05:38:58.380 --> 05:38:59.580
branches, frowning.

05:38:59.639 --> 05:39:02.040
Try to think about what comes out of your

05:39:02.040 --> 05:39:03.659
Starflight.

05:39:03.720 --> 05:39:06.060
She interrupted herself with a cry of

05:39:06.060 --> 05:39:06.360
joy.

05:39:06.419 --> 05:39:10.319
At the same time, another dragon cannoned

05:39:10.319 --> 05:39:12.419
out of the foliage and crashed right into

05:39:12.419 --> 05:39:14.759
Starflight, Starflight found himself

05:39:14.759 --> 05:39:17.639
circled by strong brown wings as Clay

05:39:17.639 --> 05:39:19.500
nearly flung him into the treetops with

05:39:19.500 --> 05:39:19.919
delight.

05:39:19.979 --> 05:39:21.479
You escaped.

05:39:21.540 --> 05:39:22.860
Tsunami yelped.

05:39:22.919 --> 05:39:25.560
Elbow and clay aside so she could wrap

05:39:25.560 --> 05:39:27.419
Starfly in her own blue wings.

05:39:27.479 --> 05:39:29.220
That's unbelievable.

05:39:29.279 --> 05:39:33.119
How, how, how, how?

05:39:33.180 --> 05:39:36.419
I'll tell you everything, but I have to

05:39:36.419 --> 05:39:39.119
see glory right away, Starflight said.

05:39:39.180 --> 05:39:41.880
He glanced around, hoping Sonny was also

05:39:41.880 --> 05:39:44.040
concealed in the bushes, but she didn't

05:39:44.040 --> 05:39:44.340
appear.

05:39:44.400 --> 05:39:46.979
He turned to Flame, who had collapsed

05:39:46.979 --> 05:39:47.819
unconscious.

05:39:47.880 --> 05:39:50.939
And this sky wing needs the cactus we got

05:39:50.939 --> 05:39:51.360
from the desert.

05:39:51.479 --> 05:39:53.819
He's been slashed with a sand wing tail.

05:39:53.880 --> 05:39:56.880
Oh, poor guy.

05:39:57.000 --> 05:40:00.419
Clay said, crouching beside Flame's inert

05:40:00.419 --> 05:40:00.959
form.

05:40:01.020 --> 05:40:03.959
The mud wing gently lifted flames snout

05:40:03.959 --> 05:40:05.159
and peered at the wound.

05:40:05.220 --> 05:40:08.040
He waved to the trees and 6 more rain

05:40:08.040 --> 05:40:09.659
wings popped into sight.

05:40:09.720 --> 05:40:11.819
In minutes, they had produced a kind of

05:40:11.819 --> 05:40:14.040
hammock net, which they tucked around

05:40:14.040 --> 05:40:15.840
flame so they could carry him off toward

05:40:15.840 --> 05:40:16.259
the village.

05:40:16.319 --> 05:40:19.500
To the healers, as fast as you can.

05:40:19.560 --> 05:40:21.119
Clay told them.

05:40:21.180 --> 05:40:23.939
Glory told us everything you said in her

05:40:23.939 --> 05:40:26.580
dream, which, by the way, is crazy

05:40:26.580 --> 05:40:29.340
visiting a dragon's dreams, tsunami said

05:40:29.340 --> 05:40:31.259
to Starflight, winding her tail around

05:40:31.259 --> 05:40:34.380
his, well, except she didn't tell me

05:40:34.380 --> 05:40:36.599
about the stealth rain wing bodyguards

05:40:36.599 --> 05:40:37.380
she put on me.

05:40:37.439 --> 05:40:39.959
That was pretty hilarious.

05:40:39.959 --> 05:40:42.240
Everyone should suddenly have the air

05:40:42.240 --> 05:40:45.119
turn into 7 bright purple dragons yelling

05:40:45.119 --> 05:40:46.799
hysterically whenever she gets attacked.

05:40:46.919 --> 05:40:50.099
Yeah, I wouldn't have minded something

05:40:50.099 --> 05:40:50.580
like that.

05:40:50.639 --> 05:40:52.259
Starflight said.

05:40:52.319 --> 05:40:55.200
The sunlight felt as if it was melting

05:40:55.200 --> 05:40:57.540
through his scales, chasing away all the

05:40:57.540 --> 05:40:59.099
darkness that had started to gather

05:40:59.099 --> 05:40:59.880
around his soul.

05:40:59.939 --> 05:41:02.580
You scared the moonshine out of those

05:41:02.580 --> 05:41:03.479
night wings.

05:41:03.540 --> 05:41:04.259
It was amazing.

05:41:04.319 --> 05:41:06.299
Tsunami beamed.

05:41:06.360 --> 05:41:07.979
Who's that?

05:41:08.099 --> 05:41:10.919
Clay asked, nodding at fate speaker.

05:41:10.979 --> 05:41:14.099
She's my friend, Starflight said

05:41:14.099 --> 05:41:16.139
realizing guiltily that she was still

05:41:16.139 --> 05:41:16.740
gagged.

05:41:16.799 --> 05:41:18.779
You can trust her.

05:41:18.840 --> 05:41:19.919
Her name is Faith Speaker.

05:41:19.979 --> 05:41:21.900
She's the alternate night wing.

05:41:21.959 --> 05:41:22.799
I told glory about.

05:41:22.919 --> 05:41:26.040
Tsunami signaled to the rain wing to let

05:41:26.040 --> 05:41:28.259
her up, and fate speaker came bounding

05:41:28.259 --> 05:41:30.479
over to them, unwrapping the vines from

05:41:30.479 --> 05:41:31.020
her snout.

05:41:31.080 --> 05:41:34.380
Hi, hi, this is the most beautiful place

05:41:34.380 --> 05:41:37.319
I've ever seen, she said, as soon as she

05:41:37.319 --> 05:41:37.979
could talk.

05:41:38.040 --> 05:41:40.200
I've never even had a vision of somewhere

05:41:40.200 --> 05:41:41.159
this pretty.

05:41:41.220 --> 05:41:43.200
No wonder the Nightwings want to live

05:41:43.200 --> 05:41:43.380
here.

05:41:43.439 --> 05:41:46.259
She seized Clay's front talons and shook

05:41:46.259 --> 05:41:46.979
them vigorously.

05:41:47.099 --> 05:41:48.419
What's edible?

05:41:48.479 --> 05:41:50.340
I haven't eaten in days.

05:41:50.400 --> 05:41:53.099
You wouldn't believe how hungry I am.

05:41:53.159 --> 05:41:56.279
Starflight felt his own empty stomach

05:41:56.279 --> 05:41:58.560
twist as she chattered on, but it was

05:41:58.560 --> 05:41:59.939
much more than food that was worrying

05:41:59.939 --> 05:42:00.180
him.

05:42:00.240 --> 05:42:02.520
War was coming to this peaceful

05:42:02.520 --> 05:42:04.919
rainforest, no matter what anyone tried

05:42:04.919 --> 05:42:05.639
to do to stop it.

05:42:05.700 --> 05:42:08.819
After tonight, would it be so beautiful?

05:42:08.880 --> 05:42:11.700
He remembered some of the awful things he

05:42:11.700 --> 05:42:13.500
and his friends had seen since leaving

05:42:13.500 --> 05:42:14.220
the caves.

05:42:14.279 --> 05:42:17.520
The violence in the Sky Palace Arena, the

05:42:17.520 --> 05:42:19.919
dead mud wings lying broken in the swamp

05:42:19.919 --> 05:42:22.319
the panicked sea wings crushing one

05:42:22.319 --> 05:42:24.479
another, as they tried to escape the fire

05:42:24.479 --> 05:42:26.159
bombs when the Summer Palace was

05:42:26.159 --> 05:42:26.459
attacked.

05:42:26.520 --> 05:42:29.459
It was hard to imagine any of that here

05:42:29.459 --> 05:42:32.040
hard to imagine anyone burning these

05:42:32.040 --> 05:42:34.500
trees, or hurting these harmless, happy

05:42:34.500 --> 05:42:37.740
go lucky dragons, but Starflight had seen

05:42:37.740 --> 05:42:39.959
the cruelty of night wings, and he knew

05:42:39.959 --> 05:42:41.639
how desperate they were for a new home.

05:42:41.700 --> 05:42:44.939
He believed they'd do anything, no matter

05:42:44.939 --> 05:42:47.159
how awful, to escape their volcanic

05:42:47.159 --> 05:42:47.520
island.

05:42:47.580 --> 05:42:50.819
Fate speaker was eating ravenously from

05:42:50.819 --> 05:42:52.560
the pile of fruit clay had offered her

05:42:52.560 --> 05:42:54.599
but Starflight didn't think he could

05:42:54.599 --> 05:42:56.700
possibly eat until he felt that his

05:42:56.700 --> 05:42:57.299
friends were safe.

05:42:57.419 --> 05:43:01.500
Although, that might be never, he

05:43:01.500 --> 05:43:02.639
realized ruefully.

05:43:02.700 --> 05:43:05.279
I have to see glory right now.

05:43:05.340 --> 05:43:08.340
He said to tsunami, the night wings are

05:43:08.340 --> 05:43:10.020
planning to attack tonight.

05:43:10.080 --> 05:43:13.200
She gasped, and the trees around her all

05:43:13.200 --> 05:43:14.340
gasped at the same time.

05:43:14.400 --> 05:43:17.279
Tsunami turned to frown at the apparently

05:43:17.279 --> 05:43:18.240
empty branches.

05:43:18.299 --> 05:43:20.819
I told you all you could go back to the

05:43:20.819 --> 05:43:21.299
village.

05:43:21.360 --> 05:43:22.139
She said.

05:43:22.200 --> 05:43:23.759
I don't need a bodyguard.

05:43:23.819 --> 05:43:25.500
I can take care of myself.

05:43:25.560 --> 05:43:26.939
Nobody answered.

05:43:27.000 --> 05:43:28.680
Tsunami side.

05:43:28.740 --> 05:43:31.919
You've never seen instant loyalty like

05:43:31.919 --> 05:43:34.500
these rain wings have for Queen Glory, she

05:43:34.500 --> 05:43:35.400
said to Starflight.

05:43:35.459 --> 05:43:37.560
Don't even try to convince them to

05:43:37.560 --> 05:43:38.220
disobey her.

05:43:38.279 --> 05:43:39.720
Never going to happen.

05:43:39.779 --> 05:43:44.639
That's great, Starflight said, pleased.

05:43:44.700 --> 05:43:47.099
At least one of us is fitting into her

05:43:47.099 --> 05:43:47.400
tribe.

05:43:47.520 --> 05:43:51.659
For her war strategy, yes, tsunami said.

05:43:51.720 --> 05:43:53.939
For the size of her head, no.

05:43:54.000 --> 05:43:57.180
She waved over the rain wing who had been

05:43:57.180 --> 05:43:58.380
sitting on fate speaker.

05:43:58.439 --> 05:44:01.139
Fate speaker eyed him warily, but his

05:44:01.139 --> 05:44:03.540
tangerine orange face was cheerful and

05:44:03.540 --> 05:44:04.860
extremely non-threatening.

05:44:04.919 --> 05:44:07.860
Take these night wings to the queen

05:44:07.860 --> 05:44:08.819
tsunami said.

05:44:08.880 --> 05:44:11.040
Clay and I have to stay on guard here.

05:44:11.099 --> 05:44:14.099
She explained to Starflight, especially

05:44:14.099 --> 05:44:16.619
on a really sunny day like this, I'm

05:44:16.619 --> 05:44:18.540
afraid rain wings have a tendency to fall

05:44:18.540 --> 05:44:19.740
asleep all over the place.

05:44:19.799 --> 05:44:22.740
Sure, Starflight said.

05:44:22.799 --> 05:44:25.319
But if there's any battle planning, I

05:44:25.319 --> 05:44:26.099
want to be involved.

05:44:26.220 --> 05:44:28.200
Tsunami added fiercely.

05:44:28.259 --> 05:44:31.740
Of course, Starflight said, spreading his

05:44:31.740 --> 05:44:32.099
wings.

05:44:32.159 --> 05:44:34.680
How long did they have until dark?

05:44:34.740 --> 05:44:36.599
Would the night wings even wait until

05:44:36.599 --> 05:44:37.200
midnight?

05:44:37.259 --> 05:44:39.540
Once they realized that Starflight had

05:44:39.540 --> 05:44:39.840
come through?

05:44:39.959 --> 05:44:42.479
Surely Maro Seer would guess that

05:44:42.479 --> 05:44:43.979
Starflight would warn his friends.

05:44:44.040 --> 05:44:46.139
What if that spurred them to attack

05:44:46.139 --> 05:44:48.659
sooner, they might invade at any moment?

05:44:48.720 --> 05:44:51.119
They might even be on their way right

05:44:51.119 --> 05:44:51.419
now.

05:44:51.479 --> 05:44:54.419
He cast a worried look back at the hole.

05:44:54.479 --> 05:44:57.599
Be careful, he said to tsunami.

05:44:57.659 --> 05:44:59.819
I'm ready for them, she said.

05:44:59.880 --> 05:45:01.139
Don't worry.

05:45:01.200 --> 05:45:03.840
She curled her claws menacingly.

05:45:03.900 --> 05:45:06.540
Starflight and fate speaker followed the

05:45:06.540 --> 05:45:08.279
orange gold rain wing up into the

05:45:08.279 --> 05:45:10.080
treetops, where there was even more

05:45:10.080 --> 05:45:10.680
sunlight.

05:45:10.740 --> 05:45:13.439
Fate speaker ducked as a flock of tiny

05:45:13.439 --> 05:45:15.659
purple birds exploded past her head.

05:45:15.720 --> 05:45:18.599
She kept twisting to watch the shimmering

05:45:18.599 --> 05:45:21.299
azure butterflies that flitted by, and

05:45:21.299 --> 05:45:23.759
once she startled a large spotted jungle

05:45:23.759 --> 05:45:25.740
cat, so he nearly fell off the branch

05:45:25.740 --> 05:45:26.520
where he was sleeping.

05:45:26.580 --> 05:45:30.180
I can't get over how amazing this place

05:45:30.180 --> 05:45:32.400
is, she said to Starflight.

05:45:32.459 --> 05:45:34.740
The rain wing village is really cool

05:45:34.740 --> 05:45:35.099
too.

05:45:35.159 --> 05:45:36.299
He said.

05:45:36.360 --> 05:45:38.700
It makes me feel sad for the night

05:45:38.700 --> 05:45:39.240
wings.

05:45:39.299 --> 05:45:41.880
Fate speaker tilted her head to catch

05:45:41.880 --> 05:45:43.740
more sunlight on her snout.

05:45:43.799 --> 05:45:46.380
I mean, what if they had grown up

05:45:46.380 --> 05:45:47.099
somewhere like this?

05:45:47.159 --> 05:45:49.319
Would they still be the way they are?

05:45:49.380 --> 05:45:52.319
Or would they be happy and kind, like the

05:45:52.319 --> 05:45:52.979
rain wings?

05:45:53.040 --> 05:45:55.439
It's not their fault they hatched in such

05:45:55.439 --> 05:45:56.220
a miserable place.

05:45:56.279 --> 05:45:58.200
Maybe they could have been good.

05:45:58.259 --> 05:46:01.799
Or at least better, if they'd lived

05:46:01.799 --> 05:46:02.459
somewhere else.

05:46:02.520 --> 05:46:05.459
Maybe, Starflight said.

05:46:05.580 --> 05:46:08.159
In fact, probably.

05:46:08.220 --> 05:46:10.860
But I think being a good dragon is about

05:46:10.860 --> 05:46:12.900
the choices you make, no matter where you

05:46:12.900 --> 05:46:15.119
are, or who raised you, or how.

05:46:15.180 --> 05:46:17.880
The Night Wings chose to kidnap and

05:46:17.880 --> 05:46:20.159
torture rain wings, that makes it hard

05:46:20.159 --> 05:46:21.360
for me to feel sorry for them.

05:46:21.419 --> 05:46:26.340
True, fate speaker said, and lapsed into

05:46:26.340 --> 05:46:28.200
uncharacteristic silence for the rest of

05:46:28.200 --> 05:46:28.740
the flight.

05:46:28.799 --> 05:46:32.220
The orange rain wing led them to a tree

05:46:32.220 --> 05:46:34.439
house that matched the one in the dream

05:46:34.439 --> 05:46:35.939
Starflight had stepped into.

05:46:36.000 --> 05:46:39.000
The walls were mostly open to the outside

05:46:39.000 --> 05:46:41.939
letting sunshine and fresh air pour in

05:46:41.939 --> 05:46:44.220
and Glory stood behind a wooden desk

05:46:44.220 --> 05:46:46.259
although there were no scrolls in front

05:46:46.259 --> 05:46:49.439
of her in real life. 3 small rain wings

05:46:49.439 --> 05:46:51.119
were lined up before her in varying

05:46:51.119 --> 05:46:53.459
shades of green, apparently relaying

05:46:53.459 --> 05:46:54.659
reports from around the forest.

05:46:54.720 --> 05:46:58.020
Glory saw Starflight coming and flared

05:46:58.020 --> 05:46:58.619
her wings.

05:46:58.680 --> 05:47:01.740
Starflight, she cried joyfully.

05:47:01.799 --> 05:47:03.900
She jabbed her own forearm with one of

05:47:03.900 --> 05:47:04.560
her claws.

05:47:04.619 --> 05:47:05.819
I'm not dreaming.

05:47:05.880 --> 05:47:06.900
You're really here.

05:47:06.959 --> 05:47:09.240
He landed beside her.

05:47:09.299 --> 05:47:11.040
We found a way out.

05:47:11.099 --> 05:47:14.400
Fate speaker and I, this is fate speaker

05:47:14.400 --> 05:47:16.860
because I had to come warn you, he said.

05:47:16.919 --> 05:47:19.319
His eyes drifted to the trees around

05:47:19.319 --> 05:47:19.619
them.

05:47:19.740 --> 05:47:21.240
We're sunny.

05:47:21.299 --> 05:47:24.119
Teaching a dragonette class how to read

05:47:24.119 --> 05:47:26.220
or helping the healers with webs, I

05:47:26.220 --> 05:47:26.400
think.

05:47:26.520 --> 05:47:28.979
Glory said, waving her claws.

05:47:29.040 --> 05:47:30.840
Warn me about what?

05:47:30.900 --> 05:47:33.479
The night wings are planning to attack

05:47:33.479 --> 05:47:34.799
you tonight at midnight.

05:47:34.860 --> 05:47:36.119
Starflight said.

05:47:36.180 --> 05:47:38.580
Maybe sooner, if they figure out where

05:47:38.580 --> 05:47:39.479
I've gone and why.

05:47:39.540 --> 05:47:41.279
Tonight?

05:47:41.340 --> 05:47:43.979
Glory rubbed her front talons over her

05:47:43.979 --> 05:47:44.220
head.

05:47:44.279 --> 05:47:47.819
Go get me mangrove, she said to one of

05:47:47.819 --> 05:47:50.520
the small rain wings, and you, find

05:47:50.520 --> 05:47:51.119
grandeur.

05:47:51.180 --> 05:47:53.400
The 2 of them nodded and flew off in a

05:47:53.400 --> 05:47:53.700
hurry.

05:47:53.759 --> 05:47:56.520
I have some ideas for defense.

05:47:56.580 --> 05:47:58.200
Starflight started.

05:47:58.259 --> 05:48:01.439
I hope one of those ideas is attack them

05:48:01.439 --> 05:48:03.959
first, Glory said, because that's my

05:48:03.959 --> 05:48:04.200
plan.

05:48:04.259 --> 05:48:06.779
She glanced out the window at the

05:48:06.779 --> 05:48:08.159
position of the sun in the sky.

05:48:08.220 --> 05:48:11.040
I can get my army ready to fly in an

05:48:11.040 --> 05:48:11.340
hour.

05:48:11.400 --> 05:48:14.639
Sure, organizing rain wings, no problem.

05:48:14.700 --> 05:48:17.040
It's only roughly as hard as getting a

05:48:17.040 --> 05:48:18.779
100 butterflies to fly in a straight

05:48:18.779 --> 05:48:19.080
line.

05:48:19.200 --> 05:48:21.299
Starflight?

05:48:21.360 --> 05:48:24.360
A glimmer of gold scales flashed in the

05:48:24.360 --> 05:48:26.580
corner of his eye, and Starflight felt

05:48:26.580 --> 05:48:28.979
his whole body fill with light as he

05:48:28.979 --> 05:48:30.959
turned around and came face to face with

05:48:30.959 --> 05:48:31.380
Sonny.
9796
05:48:31,500 --> 05:48:35,939	Chapter 23.

05:48:36.180 --> 05:48:40.200
Sunny spread her warm golden wings and

05:48:40.200 --> 05:48:42.060
Starflight fitted his own wings around

05:48:42.060 --> 05:48:43.080
hers for a hug.

05:48:43.139 --> 05:48:45.360
It always felt like exactly where he

05:48:45.360 --> 05:48:47.700
should be, even if just for a moment.

05:48:47.759 --> 05:48:51.900
I'm so glad you're all right, she said

05:48:51.900 --> 05:48:53.340
stepping back and examining him for

05:48:53.340 --> 05:48:53.759
injuries.

05:48:53.880 --> 05:48:56.639
I was checking on webs, and then this sky

05:48:56.639 --> 05:48:58.979
wing came in, of all things, and I was

05:48:58.979 --> 05:49:00.720
showing the healers how to get the cactus

05:49:00.720 --> 05:49:03.540
milk into his wound, when someone said 2

05:49:03.540 --> 05:49:05.700
night wings brought him in, and I knew it

05:49:05.700 --> 05:49:08.580
must be you, you know, I wanted to go

05:49:08.580 --> 05:49:10.380
through and find you, but glory said no.

05:49:10.439 --> 05:49:13.020
She wrinkled her snout at the new queen.

05:49:13.080 --> 05:49:15.119
Glory was right.

05:49:15.180 --> 05:49:17.759
It's too dangerous there, Starflight

05:49:17.759 --> 05:49:18.060
said.

05:49:18.119 --> 05:49:20.939
Oh, please, where have we been lately

05:49:20.939 --> 05:49:23.459
that isn't dangerous, Sonny said.

05:49:23.520 --> 05:49:25.680
All the more reason we should go rescue

05:49:25.680 --> 05:49:26.459
you.

05:49:26.520 --> 05:49:28.680
Although I wasn't really worried, because

05:49:28.680 --> 05:49:30.659
of course you had to be fine so we could

05:49:30.659 --> 05:49:31.740
fulfill the prophecy, right?

05:49:31.799 --> 05:49:34.860
And look, you rescued yourself, which is

05:49:34.860 --> 05:49:35.580
so impressive.

05:49:35.639 --> 05:49:39.060
Starflight guessed that a grin on his own

05:49:39.060 --> 05:49:41.580
face was probably a little goofy, but he

05:49:41.580 --> 05:49:42.599
couldn't seem to squelch it.

05:49:42.659 --> 05:49:44.700
And you are?

05:49:44.819 --> 05:49:47.759
Fate speaker interjected, clearing her

05:49:47.759 --> 05:49:50.099
throat and sidling so close to Starfly

05:49:50.099 --> 05:49:51.240
that she bumped one of his wings.

05:49:51.299 --> 05:49:54.659
I'm sunny, said the little sandwing.

05:49:54.720 --> 05:49:57.299
She tilted her head at fate speaker.

05:49:57.360 --> 05:50:01.020
Wow, your silver scales are so cool.

05:50:01.080 --> 05:50:03.959
That one looks like a bracelet, like you

05:50:03.959 --> 05:50:05.099
were born with your own treasure.

05:50:05.159 --> 05:50:07.979
Fate speaker's wings relaxed a little.

05:50:08.040 --> 05:50:10.380
She held out her talons to peer at the

05:50:10.380 --> 05:50:11.819
anklet of star bright scales.

05:50:11.880 --> 05:50:13.740
I never thought of it like that.

05:50:13.799 --> 05:50:16.439
I was about to say your scales are a

05:50:16.439 --> 05:50:16.860
great color.

05:50:16.919 --> 05:50:19.200
All the sand wings I've met were sort of

05:50:19.200 --> 05:50:20.580
pale and dusty looking.

05:50:20.639 --> 05:50:22.799
I know, I'm weird.

05:50:22.919 --> 05:50:24.779
Sonny said agreeably.

05:50:24.840 --> 05:50:27.119
You're the alternate night wing, right?

05:50:27.180 --> 05:50:29.400
Gloria said Starflight had lots of nice

05:50:29.400 --> 05:50:30.240
things to say about you.

05:50:30.299 --> 05:50:33.419
Fate speaker gave Starflight a delighted

05:50:33.419 --> 05:50:35.340
look that made him unaccountably

05:50:35.340 --> 05:50:35.759
nervous.

05:50:35.819 --> 05:50:38.700
What was it like growing up in the talons

05:50:38.700 --> 05:50:39.599
of peace camp.

05:50:39.659 --> 05:50:44.099
So bizarre, fate speaker said, folding

05:50:44.099 --> 05:50:45.720
her wings and leaning towards Sonny.

05:50:45.779 --> 05:50:48.060
We were always moving so no one could

05:50:48.060 --> 05:50:50.340
find us, and everyone talked about peas

05:50:50.340 --> 05:50:51.779
but it seemed like all we were doing was

05:50:51.779 --> 05:50:53.819
avoiding soldiers and waiting for the

05:50:53.819 --> 05:50:54.840
prophecy to come true.

05:50:54.900 --> 05:50:57.959
But it must have been amazing to live

05:50:57.959 --> 05:50:59.520
with so many dragons from different

05:50:59.520 --> 05:51:01.560
tribes, Sonny said.

05:51:01.619 --> 05:51:02.880
Her eyes shining.

05:51:03.000 --> 05:51:05.159
You'd get to see what really makes them

05:51:05.159 --> 05:51:05.580
different.

05:51:05.639 --> 05:51:07.560
And the ways they're all the same too.

05:51:07.619 --> 05:51:11.340
I was thinking about that, fate speaker

05:51:11.340 --> 05:51:11.700
said.

05:51:11.759 --> 05:51:14.700
I was the only nightwing, so I was always

05:51:14.700 --> 05:51:16.860
trying to figure out which other tribe I

05:51:16.860 --> 05:51:20.400
was most like, but you could find

05:51:20.400 --> 05:51:22.200
something in common with all of them

05:51:22.200 --> 05:51:23.340
Sonny guessed.

05:51:23.400 --> 05:51:24.479
Exactly.

05:51:24.540 --> 05:51:28.560
All right, Gloria interrupted.

05:51:28.619 --> 05:51:31.799
As strangely adorable as you 2 are, I

05:51:31.799 --> 05:51:33.540
need you to either go away and discover

05:51:33.540 --> 05:51:35.880
your twin souls somewhere else or focus

05:51:35.880 --> 05:51:37.139
on battle planning with me.

05:51:37.200 --> 05:51:39.240
Battle planning.

05:51:39.299 --> 05:51:41.159
Fate Speaker and Sonny said

05:51:41.159 --> 05:51:42.060
simultaneously.

05:51:42.119 --> 05:51:45.299
Glory gave Starflight an odd, somewhat

05:51:45.299 --> 05:51:47.880
amused look, and he shifted uncomfortably

05:51:47.880 --> 05:51:49.259
although he wasn't sure why.

05:51:49.319 --> 05:51:52.139
He liked that fate speaker and Sonny

05:51:52.139 --> 05:51:54.180
liked each other, but it also made him

05:51:54.180 --> 05:51:55.200
weirdly uneasy.

05:51:55.259 --> 05:51:59.159
Luckily, at that moment, Mangrove arrived

05:51:59.159 --> 05:52:01.380
with the elegant older dragon Starflight

05:52:01.380 --> 05:52:02.759
had seen in Kinkachu's dream.

05:52:02.819 --> 05:52:05.759
Let's take this meeting to the tunnel

05:52:05.759 --> 05:52:08.939
Glory said, I need tsunamis and clays

05:52:08.939 --> 05:52:09.479
input too.

05:52:09.599 --> 05:52:12.299
She gathered her wings and soared off the

05:52:12.299 --> 05:52:13.319
balcony into the trees.

05:52:13.380 --> 05:52:16.860
Fate speaker and Sonny went next, talking

05:52:16.860 --> 05:52:18.060
to each other as they flew.

05:52:18.180 --> 05:52:21.060
Starflight followed, trying to keep his

05:52:21.060 --> 05:52:23.099
mind on the impending attack.

05:52:23.159 --> 05:52:25.319
Only a few minutes of sunshine and fresh

05:52:25.319 --> 05:52:27.479
air, and he was already finding it hard

05:52:27.479 --> 05:52:29.279
to believe what he'd gone through on the

05:52:29.279 --> 05:52:31.919
Nightwing Island, or that an army of

05:52:31.919 --> 05:52:33.959
angry dragons was preparing to destroy

05:52:33.959 --> 05:52:36.119
all of this before the next sunrise.

05:52:36.180 --> 05:52:39.720
Once they were all gathered, within sight

05:52:39.720 --> 05:52:41.159
of the tunnel, but out of hearing

05:52:41.159 --> 05:52:44.040
distance to be safe, Glory had Starflight

05:52:44.040 --> 05:52:45.659
explain everything he'd heard in the

05:52:45.659 --> 05:52:46.439
council chamber.

05:52:46.500 --> 05:52:49.979
So at least some of them are afraid of us

05:52:49.979 --> 05:52:51.479
she said when he'd finished.

05:52:51.540 --> 05:52:55.020
I'd say most of them, Starflight said.

05:52:55.080 --> 05:52:57.659
I mean, I think that's the whole reason

05:52:57.659 --> 05:52:59.459
they've been kidnapping rain wings and

05:52:59.459 --> 05:53:01.560
studying them, and why they haven't

05:53:01.560 --> 05:53:02.099
attacked before.

05:53:02.159 --> 05:53:04.200
They are terrified of your venom.

05:53:04.259 --> 05:53:06.900
Glory showed her teeth and hissed.

05:53:06.959 --> 05:53:08.159
They should be.

05:53:08.220 --> 05:53:12.720
Yours, maybe, tsunami said, but the rest

05:53:12.720 --> 05:53:13.560
of these dragons?

05:53:13.680 --> 05:53:15.900
I really can't guarantee that any of them

05:53:15.900 --> 05:53:18.659
will use it on another dragon, even in a

05:53:18.659 --> 05:53:19.680
life or death situation.

05:53:19.740 --> 05:53:22.200
They've been told their whole lives to

05:53:22.200 --> 05:53:24.599
never, ever use it as a weapon.

05:53:24.659 --> 05:53:27.779
I've done my best, but you tried changing

05:53:27.779 --> 05:53:30.119
an entire tribal philosophy of life in 3

05:53:30.119 --> 05:53:30.360
days.

05:53:30.419 --> 05:53:34.740
I know, Glory said, starting to pace.

05:53:34.860 --> 05:53:38.520
Which I'm not even sure we should, Sonny

05:53:38.520 --> 05:53:39.119
interjected.

05:53:39.180 --> 05:53:41.220
I like their philosophy.

05:53:41.279 --> 05:53:43.500
I could do it.

05:53:43.560 --> 05:53:45.000
Grandeur said.

05:53:45.060 --> 05:53:47.880
Attack another dragon with my venom, I

05:53:47.880 --> 05:53:51.060
mean, for the sake of my tribe, but I

05:53:51.060 --> 05:53:52.740
agree that the others would have

05:53:52.740 --> 05:53:53.159
trouble.

05:53:53.220 --> 05:53:55.619
She glanced at Mangrove.

05:53:55.680 --> 05:53:58.439
I'd try, he said.

05:53:58.500 --> 05:54:00.000
For orchid.

05:54:00.060 --> 05:54:02.099
She's really still alive.

05:54:02.159 --> 05:54:04.020
He asked Starflight.

05:54:04.139 --> 05:54:05.939
And waiting for you.

05:54:06.000 --> 05:54:07.619
Fate speaker said.

05:54:07.680 --> 05:54:09.779
Starflight told her you were looking for

05:54:09.779 --> 05:54:12.299
her, and she said she'd survive until you

05:54:12.299 --> 05:54:12.540
came.

05:54:12.599 --> 05:54:15.900
A faint wave of pink rippled across

05:54:15.900 --> 05:54:17.159
mangroves scales.

05:54:17.220 --> 05:54:21.419
I'm worried about attacking first, Clay

05:54:21.419 --> 05:54:21.840
said.

05:54:21.900 --> 05:54:24.779
We'd have to come out the other end one

05:54:24.779 --> 05:54:25.439
at a time.

05:54:25.500 --> 05:54:28.919
If they're smart, they'll be waiting, and

05:54:28.919 --> 05:54:30.959
then they can pick us off one by one.

05:54:31.020 --> 05:54:34.080
But if we wait here and let them attack

05:54:34.080 --> 05:54:36.060
we could do that to them instead.

05:54:36.119 --> 05:54:38.700
We'd be in the stronger position.

05:54:38.759 --> 05:54:42.900
I don't want them in my rainforest, Glory

05:54:42.900 --> 05:54:43.319
snapped.

05:54:43.380 --> 05:54:46.080
If they think they're losing, they'll set

05:54:46.080 --> 05:54:47.639
the whole place on fire just to be

05:54:47.639 --> 05:54:48.000
horrible.

05:54:48.000 --> 05:54:51.419
Besides, we have to go there to rescue

05:54:51.419 --> 05:54:52.319
the rain wings.

05:54:52.380 --> 05:54:55.380
Even if we drive back their attack, we'd

05:54:55.380 --> 05:54:56.700
still have to go through at some point

05:54:56.700 --> 05:54:59.159
and we'll have wasted resources on our

05:54:59.159 --> 05:54:59.700
defense.

05:55:00.599 --> 05:55:02.099
No, we go to them first.

05:55:02.159 --> 05:55:04.500
We just have to find a way to get

05:55:04.500 --> 05:55:05.939
everyone past the guards at the

05:55:05.939 --> 05:55:06.240
entrance.

05:55:06.299 --> 05:55:09.599
I have an idea, Sonny said.

05:55:09.659 --> 05:55:13.200
Changing your scales will help, Tsunami

05:55:13.200 --> 05:55:14.040
said at the same time.

05:55:14.099 --> 05:55:16.500
They won't see the rain wings coming

05:55:16.500 --> 05:55:17.759
along the tunnel if you're all

05:55:17.759 --> 05:55:18.540
camouflaged.

05:55:18.599 --> 05:55:20.759
Then maybe we burst out and start

05:55:20.759 --> 05:55:22.919
attacking and hope we've surprised them.

05:55:22.979 --> 05:55:26.159
Doubtful, Starflight said.

05:55:26.220 --> 05:55:29.220
Once Maru seer figures out I went through

05:55:29.220 --> 05:55:31.380
they'll be on high alert to the tunnel

05:55:31.380 --> 05:55:31.619
opening.

05:55:31.680 --> 05:55:35.040
I think it's a good idea, said Sonny.

05:55:35.099 --> 05:55:36.659
The one I have, I mean.

05:55:36.720 --> 05:55:40.080
We need to choose the bravest rain wings

05:55:40.080 --> 05:55:42.779
for the 1st wave, Glory said.

05:55:42.840 --> 05:55:45.060
Tsunami, I want you to make a list for me

05:55:45.060 --> 05:55:46.799
based on what you've noticed during

05:55:46.799 --> 05:55:47.159
training.

05:55:47.220 --> 05:55:49.500
Tsunami snorted.

05:55:49.560 --> 05:55:52.380
A brave list might be asking a lot.

05:55:52.439 --> 05:55:54.779
You can have a less sleepy than the

05:55:54.779 --> 05:55:55.380
others list.

05:55:55.439 --> 05:55:58.680
One does not speak to a queen that way of

05:55:58.680 --> 05:55:59.340
her citizens.

05:55:59.459 --> 05:56:02.340
Glory said with mock haughtiness, then

05:56:02.340 --> 05:56:03.840
lapsed back into a regular voice.

05:56:03.900 --> 05:56:06.779
Anyway, I think their rain wings will

05:56:06.779 --> 05:56:07.319
surprise you.

05:56:07.380 --> 05:56:09.900
I've been meeting them all one by one, as

05:56:09.900 --> 05:56:12.000
fast as I can, and they're a lot more

05:56:12.000 --> 05:56:13.500
complicated than they seem.

05:56:13.560 --> 05:56:16.619
Doesn't anyone want to hear my idea?

05:56:16.740 --> 05:56:17.759
Sonny asked.

05:56:17.819 --> 05:56:20.580
I do, said Starflight.

05:56:20.639 --> 05:56:22.319
But glory was already speaking to

05:56:22.319 --> 05:56:22.979
Mangrove.

05:56:23.040 --> 05:56:25.740
We have to make sure that we pair up

05:56:25.740 --> 05:56:28.619
related rain wings in each squadron, so

05:56:28.619 --> 05:56:30.360
there's always someone to counteract the

05:56:30.360 --> 05:56:31.500
venom if there's an accident.

05:56:31.560 --> 05:56:34.139
I know Sonny's been taking notes on that

05:56:34.139 --> 05:56:36.540
so make sure we use her chart when we

05:56:36.540 --> 05:56:37.319
form the squadrons.

05:56:37.380 --> 05:56:39.659
With a stab of jealousy.

05:56:39.720 --> 05:56:42.599
Starflight saw Sonny lean toward clay and

05:56:42.599 --> 05:56:43.380
whisper in his ear.

05:56:43.439 --> 05:56:45.840
Sometimes it seemed to him as though

05:56:45.840 --> 05:56:48.540
Sonny and Clay were always together, like

05:56:48.540 --> 05:56:50.220
the mud wing was the one she could trust

05:56:50.220 --> 05:56:51.779
more than any other dragon.

05:56:51.900 --> 05:56:53.880
He wished he could be that for her

05:56:53.880 --> 05:56:57.000
instead, but he wasn't anything like clay

05:56:57.000 --> 05:56:59.340
and the truth was, if he had to choose

05:56:59.340 --> 05:57:01.919
someone to trust with his life, he'd pick

05:57:01.919 --> 05:57:03.479
clay over himself as well.

05:57:03.540 --> 05:57:06.540
I don't know how to prepare them to fight

05:57:06.540 --> 05:57:09.779
Nightwing Fire, tsunami said, a little

05:57:09.779 --> 05:57:10.319
hopelessly.

05:57:10.439 --> 05:57:12.840
Most of these dragons have never even

05:57:12.840 --> 05:57:13.680
seen fire.

05:57:13.740 --> 05:57:16.380
They'll probably think it's shiny and

05:57:16.380 --> 05:57:17.700
pretty and try to touch it.

05:57:17.759 --> 05:57:21.060
Glory coiled her tail and stared at the

05:57:21.060 --> 05:57:22.619
sky through the trees.

05:57:22.680 --> 05:57:24.419
Starflight guessed from her expression

05:57:24.419 --> 05:57:26.040
that she was thinking about how rain

05:57:26.040 --> 05:57:27.180
wings were going to die.

05:57:27.240 --> 05:57:29.040
There was no way to avoid it.

05:57:29.099 --> 05:57:32.159
Becoming queen of an entire tribe, all of

05:57:32.159 --> 05:57:34.500
a sudden was hard enough, but leading

05:57:34.500 --> 05:57:37.259
dragons into battle, especially woefully

05:57:37.259 --> 05:57:39.959
underprepared dragons, was something none

05:57:39.959 --> 05:57:42.119
of the dragonettes knew anything about or

05:57:42.119 --> 05:57:43.080
ever wanted to do.

05:57:43.139 --> 05:57:47.400
We wanted to stop the war, not start a

05:57:47.400 --> 05:57:47.939
whole new one.

05:57:48.000 --> 05:57:50.939
Do the rain wings have any chance against

05:57:50.939 --> 05:57:53.700
the armor clad, fiercely desperate

05:57:53.700 --> 05:57:56.159
violently unhappy night wings?

05:57:56.220 --> 05:57:58.380
Are we all going to die today?

05:57:58.439 --> 05:58:00.959
We're only dragonettes?

05:58:01.020 --> 05:58:02.759
We shouldn't be leading anyone to their

05:58:02.759 --> 05:58:03.180
deaths.

05:58:03.299 --> 05:58:05.700
But this is happening no matter what we

05:58:05.700 --> 05:58:06.000
do.

05:58:06.060 --> 05:58:07.919
We have no choice now.

05:58:07.979 --> 05:58:11.340
I tried to draw a map of what I could

05:58:11.340 --> 05:58:13.500
remember of the island, Glory said to

05:58:13.500 --> 05:58:14.099
Starflight.

05:58:14.159 --> 05:58:16.560
I want you to fill in as many details as

05:58:16.560 --> 05:58:16.860
you can.

05:58:16.919 --> 05:58:19.560
I guess we should have several dragons go

05:58:19.560 --> 05:58:21.659
straight to the prison caves and try to

05:58:21.659 --> 05:58:23.040
free the trapped rain wings.

05:58:23.099 --> 05:58:26.459
Queen Splendor is inside the fortress

05:58:26.459 --> 05:58:29.340
Starflight said. in the same dungeon as

05:58:29.340 --> 05:58:29.939
Deathbringer.

05:58:30.060 --> 05:58:34.319
Oh, Glory said, and several colors

05:58:34.319 --> 05:58:37.200
shifted across her scales at once, so

05:58:37.200 --> 05:58:38.520
another wing should go in there.

05:58:38.580 --> 05:58:40.860
Maybe tsunami can lead that group.

05:58:40.919 --> 05:58:43.200
Sleeping darts.

05:58:43.319 --> 05:58:45.599
Clay suddenly yelled, making everyone

05:58:45.599 --> 05:58:46.080
jump.

05:58:46.139 --> 05:58:47.759
Glory stared at him.

05:58:47.819 --> 05:58:48.659
What?

05:58:48.720 --> 05:58:52.259
Those sleeping darts the rain wings used

05:58:52.259 --> 05:58:53.220
to knock us out.

05:58:53.279 --> 05:58:56.580
When we 1st got to the rainforest, Clay

05:58:56.580 --> 05:58:56.880
said.

05:58:57.000 --> 05:58:58.799
He nudged Sonny forward.

05:58:58.860 --> 05:59:02.459
Sonny says, the healers have 100s of

05:59:02.459 --> 05:59:02.700
them.

05:59:02.759 --> 05:59:05.040
The rain wings use them all the time.

05:59:05.099 --> 05:59:07.919
They play this game where they try to

05:59:07.919 --> 05:59:09.419
sneak up on each other before getting

05:59:09.419 --> 05:59:10.139
shot.

05:59:10.200 --> 05:59:14.639
That's true, Mangrove said, lashing his

05:59:14.639 --> 05:59:14.939
tail.

05:59:15.000 --> 05:59:18.720
And we take turns patrolling so we can

05:59:18.720 --> 05:59:21.180
shoot strange dragons who come into the

05:59:21.180 --> 05:59:24.599
forest, like you 5, which is even more

05:59:24.599 --> 05:59:25.319
fun.

05:59:25.500 --> 05:59:28.619
Every rain wing already has a blow gun

05:59:28.619 --> 05:59:31.259
Sonny said. arm them all with as many

05:59:31.259 --> 05:59:33.540
sleeping darts as they can carry. and use

05:59:33.540 --> 05:59:34.619
those instead of fighting.

05:59:34.740 --> 05:59:36.900
That's it.

05:59:37.020 --> 05:59:40.200
Glory flared her wings, turning dark

05:59:40.200 --> 05:59:42.240
purple with lightning bolts of excited

05:59:42.240 --> 05:59:44.400
gold all along her scales.

05:59:44.400 --> 05:59:46.979
That's exactly how rain wings should

05:59:46.979 --> 05:59:47.220
fight.

05:59:47.279 --> 05:59:52.200
It was Sunny's idea, Clay said, nodding

05:59:52.200 --> 05:59:53.040
down at the sand wing.

05:59:53.099 --> 05:59:56.340
Maybe we can do this without casualties

05:59:56.340 --> 05:59:57.959
Glory said animatedly.

05:59:58.020 --> 06:00:00.060
Clay and Sonny.

06:00:00.119 --> 06:00:01.560
You're in charge of arming all the rain

06:00:01.560 --> 06:00:02.099
wings.

06:00:02.159 --> 06:00:04.259
Get all the sleeping darts you can find.

06:00:04.319 --> 06:00:06.479
Mangrove, grandeur.

06:00:06.540 --> 06:00:08.040
It's time to tell the village.

06:00:08.099 --> 06:00:09.900
Everyone who's willing to fight.

06:00:09.959 --> 06:00:12.060
Meet by the stream here in one hour.

06:00:12.119 --> 06:00:14.220
We're doing this before nightfall.

06:00:14.279 --> 06:00:16.860
She turned to Starflight as the others

06:00:16.860 --> 06:00:17.400
flew off.

06:00:17.459 --> 06:00:19.319
Let's review the map.

06:00:19.380 --> 06:00:20.580
Tell me everything you know.

06:00:20.639 --> 06:00:24.419
Tsunami unrolled a giant leaf with a

06:00:24.419 --> 06:00:26.099
sketchy map of the Nightwing Island

06:00:26.099 --> 06:00:28.020
marked out on it in some kind of dark

06:00:28.020 --> 06:00:28.860
fruit ink.

06:00:28.979 --> 06:00:31.080
War is coming.

06:00:31.139 --> 06:00:32.880
There's no time to be scared.

06:00:33.000 --> 06:00:36.000
Starflight told himself as he leaned over

06:00:36.000 --> 06:00:36.360
the map.

06:00:36.419 --> 06:00:39.840
You can't be the most cowardly dragon on

06:00:39.840 --> 06:00:40.619
Pyria right now.

06:00:40.680 --> 06:00:43.380
Remember, you've read all the history

06:00:43.380 --> 06:00:44.880
scrolls you could find about famous

06:00:44.880 --> 06:00:46.139
battles.

06:00:46.200 --> 06:00:47.220
Now use that knowledge.

06:00:47.279 --> 06:00:50.040
It's time to prove that you really do

06:00:50.040 --> 06:00:51.299
belong in this prophecy.
10147
06:00:51,360 --> 06:00:55,860	Chapter 24.

06:00:56.159 --> 06:01:00.479
Two hours later, Queen Glory's army was

06:01:00.479 --> 06:01:01.080
on the move.

06:01:01.139 --> 06:01:03.900
The sun was just starting to sink below

06:01:03.900 --> 06:01:04.380
the trees.

06:01:04.439 --> 06:01:07.080
It wasn't dark here yet, but it would be

06:01:07.080 --> 06:01:07.319
soon.

06:01:07.380 --> 06:01:10.380
Starflight dug his claws into the mud by

06:01:10.380 --> 06:01:12.540
the stream, trying to beat down his

06:01:12.540 --> 06:01:13.200
terror.

06:01:13.259 --> 06:01:16.020
The clearing bustled with activity, but

06:01:16.020 --> 06:01:18.599
it was unsettling activity, because most

06:01:18.599 --> 06:01:20.459
of the gathered dragons were essentially

06:01:20.459 --> 06:01:23.040
invisible, carefully camouflaged against

06:01:23.040 --> 06:01:23.700
the background.

06:01:23.759 --> 06:01:26.700
Starflight kept being bumped and jostled

06:01:26.700 --> 06:01:28.439
by what appeared to be empty air.

06:01:28.500 --> 06:01:31.200
Tsunami was trying to make all the rain

06:01:31.200 --> 06:01:33.599
wings face her and shut up, so she could

06:01:33.599 --> 06:01:35.279
give them a rousing battle speech.

06:01:35.340 --> 06:01:37.979
The fact that this was proving difficult

06:01:37.979 --> 06:01:40.380
did not bode well for the overall attack

06:01:40.380 --> 06:01:41.880
Starfly thought anxiously.

06:01:41.939 --> 06:01:46.080
Starflight, Glory said, materializing

06:01:46.080 --> 06:01:46.680
beside him.

06:01:46.740 --> 06:01:49.799
Her scales shimmered from dark green to a

06:01:49.799 --> 06:01:52.259
sort of worried looking pale blue and

06:01:52.259 --> 06:01:52.619
back.

06:01:52.680 --> 06:01:54.000
Are you all right?

06:01:54.060 --> 06:01:57.180
I guess, Starflight said.

06:01:57.240 --> 06:01:59.220
He shifted from one foot to another.

06:01:59.279 --> 06:02:01.439
You know, nervous.

06:02:01.500 --> 06:02:03.659
Do you want to stay here?

06:02:03.720 --> 06:02:05.340
She asked him quietly.

06:02:05.459 --> 06:02:07.259
I'd understand if you do.

06:02:07.380 --> 06:02:10.380
No, Starflight said.

06:02:10.439 --> 06:02:12.060
I mean, I shouldn't.

06:02:12.119 --> 06:02:13.139
I can't.

06:02:13.200 --> 06:02:16.200
He glanced at Sonny, who was sorting

06:02:16.200 --> 06:02:18.119
piles of sleeping darts into little bags

06:02:18.119 --> 06:02:20.459
that could go over the rain wings necks.

06:02:20.580 --> 06:02:22.860
She had none of the weapons other dragons

06:02:22.860 --> 06:02:26.220
had, no venom, no camouflage, no

06:02:26.220 --> 06:02:29.220
fireproof scales like clay, not even the

06:02:29.220 --> 06:02:31.380
poisonous tail barb a sand wing should

06:02:31.380 --> 06:02:31.619
have.

06:02:31.680 --> 06:02:33.900
He'd never let her go off to a battle

06:02:33.900 --> 06:02:34.439
without him.

06:02:34.500 --> 06:02:37.020
Stay behind while his friends threw

06:02:37.020 --> 06:02:37.979
themselves into danger.

06:02:38.040 --> 06:02:40.380
How could she ever love him if he made

06:02:40.380 --> 06:02:40.979
that choice?

06:02:41.040 --> 06:02:43.680
I promise, I won't be scared.

06:02:43.740 --> 06:02:47.520
It's normal to be scared, Glory said.

06:02:47.580 --> 06:02:49.020
I'm scared.

06:02:49.080 --> 06:02:50.880
You'd have to be crazy not to be.

06:02:51.000 --> 06:02:54.779
Well, crazy or tsunami, which is

06:02:54.779 --> 06:02:55.619
basically the same thing.

06:02:55.740 --> 06:02:58.500
You just have to push that aside and do

06:02:58.500 --> 06:02:59.459
what you have to anyway.

06:02:59.520 --> 06:03:02.520
But I meant, do you want to stay here

06:03:02.520 --> 06:03:04.500
because we're going to fight your tribe?

06:03:04.560 --> 06:03:07.560
If it's too much to ask, I understand if

06:03:07.560 --> 06:03:08.580
you want to sit this one out.

06:03:08.639 --> 06:03:11.220
They are not my tribe.

06:03:11.279 --> 06:03:12.900
Starflight said.

06:03:12.959 --> 06:03:14.159
You are.

06:03:14.220 --> 06:03:17.340
You and Sonny and Tsunami and Clay.

06:03:17.400 --> 06:03:22.439
Ah, you big sap, she said, but her

06:03:22.439 --> 06:03:24.840
wingtips went all rose colored, and he

06:03:24.840 --> 06:03:26.759
knew glory felt the same way, even if

06:03:26.759 --> 06:03:27.840
she'd never say it out loud.

06:03:27.959 --> 06:03:31.500
All right, she said, punching his

06:03:31.500 --> 06:03:31.860
shoulder.

06:03:31.919 --> 06:03:34.139
A rare gesture of physical affection from

06:03:34.139 --> 06:03:34.319
her.

06:03:34.380 --> 06:03:36.419
Let's go change the world.

06:03:36.479 --> 06:03:39.659
She bounded to the tunnel opening and

06:03:39.659 --> 06:03:42.000
summoned the 1st wave of rain wings with

06:03:42.000 --> 06:03:42.900
a flick of her tail.

06:03:42.959 --> 06:03:45.119
They huddled listening to her orders.

06:03:45.180 --> 06:03:47.700
Star Light looked around at Sonny again.

06:03:47.759 --> 06:03:49.979
I might die today.

06:03:50.040 --> 06:03:51.959
What if she never knows?

06:03:52.080 --> 06:03:54.779
What if I die without ever telling her

06:03:54.779 --> 06:03:55.380
how I feel?

06:03:55.439 --> 06:03:58.319
He lifted his face toward the setting

06:03:58.319 --> 06:03:58.619
sun.

06:03:58.680 --> 06:04:01.200
He'd bluffed the night wing guards.

06:04:01.259 --> 06:04:03.659
He'd escaped from the Nightwing Island.

06:04:03.720 --> 06:04:06.360
Surely he could say 3 words to one

06:04:06.360 --> 06:04:06.840
dragon.

06:04:06.900 --> 06:04:09.419
When he looked down again.

06:04:09.720 --> 06:04:10.919
Sonny was right in front of him.

06:04:10.979 --> 06:04:14.099
His heart seized, as though someone had

06:04:14.099 --> 06:04:15.540
wrapped fierce talons around it.

06:04:15.599 --> 06:04:19.439
We're going to be all right, she told him

06:04:19.439 --> 06:04:21.180
shaking out her wings.

06:04:21.240 --> 06:04:22.680
Just think of the prophecy.

06:04:22.740 --> 06:04:25.020
We have to be alive to stop the war

06:04:25.020 --> 06:04:25.200
right?

06:04:25.259 --> 06:04:27.060
So we can't die today.

06:04:27.119 --> 06:04:28.860
Isn't that comforting?

06:04:28.919 --> 06:04:32.700
I wish I had your optimism, he said.

06:04:32.759 --> 06:04:35.520
It's not optimism, she objected.

06:04:35.580 --> 06:04:36.900
It's faith.

06:04:36.959 --> 06:04:38.520
There's a reason we're here.

06:04:38.580 --> 06:04:41.759
What we do today is part of it, but

06:04:41.759 --> 06:04:43.979
there's more too, and we have to survive

06:04:43.979 --> 06:04:44.880
to make it all happen.

06:04:44.939 --> 06:04:48.360
Her smile made him feel as if lightning

06:04:48.360 --> 06:04:49.680
were crackling under his scales.

06:04:49.740 --> 06:04:53.340
Sunny, he said hesitantly.

06:04:53.400 --> 06:04:57.840
There's something, I mean, something I've

06:04:57.840 --> 06:04:58.380
wanted to tell you.

06:04:58.500 --> 06:05:00.000
For a long time.

06:05:00.060 --> 06:05:04.139
I'm listening, she said, tilting her

06:05:04.139 --> 06:05:04.380
head.

06:05:04.439 --> 06:05:07.560
Across the clearing, glory was flaring

06:05:07.560 --> 06:05:09.000
her wings and waiting for silence.

06:05:09.060 --> 06:05:12.540
It was now, or possibly never, depending

06:05:12.540 --> 06:05:13.500
on what happened today.

06:05:13.619 --> 06:05:16.860
I love you, he blurted.

06:05:16.919 --> 06:05:19.619
Sonny blinked. and then blinked a few

06:05:19.619 --> 06:05:19.979
more times.

06:05:20.040 --> 06:05:23.580
I, I love you too, Starflight.

06:05:23.639 --> 06:05:25.799
No, he said.

06:05:25.860 --> 06:05:29.159
I mean, I mean, you're all I think

06:05:29.159 --> 06:05:29.459
about.

06:05:29.520 --> 06:05:32.819
And I want to be near you, and it hurts

06:05:32.819 --> 06:05:33.299
when I'm not.

06:05:33.360 --> 06:05:37.200
And everything I do, I think, what would

06:05:37.200 --> 06:05:38.159
Sonny want me to do?

06:05:38.220 --> 06:05:41.040
And I think you're the only dragon who

06:05:41.040 --> 06:05:43.799
sees me the whole way I am and likes me

06:05:43.799 --> 06:05:44.099
anyway?

06:05:44.159 --> 06:05:48.060
He thought uncomfortably of fate speaker

06:05:48.060 --> 06:05:50.639
and spotted her at the same time, across

06:05:50.639 --> 06:05:53.099
the clearing near glory, watching the

06:05:53.099 --> 06:05:55.439
rain wing queen with her eyes wide and

06:05:55.439 --> 06:05:58.139
her head upturned, but his feelings for

06:05:58.139 --> 06:06:00.060
her and his feelings for Sonny.

06:06:00.119 --> 06:06:03.180
Well, they couldn't be the same.

06:06:03.240 --> 06:06:07.979
And I had to tell you, he hurried on, in

06:06:07.979 --> 06:06:09.479
case something happens to either one of

06:06:09.479 --> 06:06:12.299
us today, although if anything happens to

06:06:12.299 --> 06:06:14.340
you, I don't know how I'd be able to

06:06:14.340 --> 06:06:16.919
breathe or think or do anything ever

06:06:16.919 --> 06:06:17.220
again.

06:06:17.340 --> 06:06:21.959
Oh my gosh, Starflight, stop, Sonny said

06:06:21.959 --> 06:06:22.500
in a rush.

06:06:22.560 --> 06:06:27.060
This, right now, how can I say anything?

06:06:27.119 --> 06:06:30.659
let alone the right thing when we're, when

06:06:30.659 --> 06:06:32.880
everything, She spread her wings

06:06:32.880 --> 06:06:35.340
helplessly, indicating the mob of rain

06:06:35.340 --> 06:06:36.180
wings around them.

06:06:36.240 --> 06:06:40.080
It's all right, Starflight said, and

06:06:40.080 --> 06:06:41.279
realized that he meant it.

06:06:41.340 --> 06:06:43.259
Don't say anything.

06:06:43.319 --> 06:06:44.340
You don't have to.

06:06:44.400 --> 06:06:46.139
I just wanted you to know.

06:06:46.200 --> 06:06:47.639
Just in case.

06:06:47.759 --> 06:06:51.000
She wrinkled her forehead, as if that

06:06:51.000 --> 06:06:53.279
didn't seem right to her, but he twined

06:06:53.279 --> 06:06:55.560
his tail around hers, and looked down at

06:06:55.560 --> 06:06:57.540
their talons sinking into the riverbank.

06:06:57.599 --> 06:07:01.020
Just promise me you'll be safe, he said.

06:07:01.080 --> 06:07:03.779
I hardly get to do anything in this

06:07:03.779 --> 06:07:06.299
battle, she said fiercely.

06:07:06.360 --> 06:07:08.040
You promise me you'll be safe.

06:07:08.099 --> 06:07:11.639
He opened and closed his mouth, wishing

06:07:11.639 --> 06:07:13.979
he could promise that, and mean it.

06:07:14.040 --> 06:07:16.080
Exactly, she said.

06:07:16.139 --> 06:07:18.779
So stop talking like a scroll and just

06:07:18.779 --> 06:07:19.860
tell me you'll see me soon.

06:07:19.919 --> 06:07:20.759
Okay?

06:07:20.819 --> 06:07:24.000
I'll see you soon, he said.

06:07:24.060 --> 06:07:26.759
And for a moment, her certainty made him

06:07:26.759 --> 06:07:27.419
believe it too.

06:07:27.479 --> 06:07:29.340
Good luck.

06:07:29.400 --> 06:07:32.400
Kick a night wing for me, she said, as

06:07:32.400 --> 06:07:34.560
Starflight stepped away, and then she

06:07:34.560 --> 06:07:36.840
pulled him back for a quick hug, and a

06:07:36.840 --> 06:07:38.700
moment later, he found himself walking

06:07:38.700 --> 06:07:41.220
over to glory, his mind a daze.

06:07:41.279 --> 06:07:42.540
I did it.

06:07:42.599 --> 06:07:43.860
I told her.

06:07:43.919 --> 06:07:46.200
And the world didn't collapse.

06:07:46.259 --> 06:07:49.799
The queen of the rain wings flared her

06:07:49.799 --> 06:07:52.020
wings one more time and the clearing

06:07:52.020 --> 06:07:53.040
finally fell silent.

06:07:53.099 --> 06:07:56.580
You know I don't like giving speeches

06:07:56.580 --> 06:07:57.599
Glory said.

06:07:57.659 --> 06:07:59.700
So I'll just say this.

06:07:59.759 --> 06:08:02.580
We're going to save our fellow rain wings

06:08:02.580 --> 06:08:04.799
and we're going to make this rainforest

06:08:04.799 --> 06:08:07.860
safe, and we're going to do it like real

06:08:07.860 --> 06:08:08.759
rain wings.

06:08:08.819 --> 06:08:10.860
And by the 3 moons.

06:08:10.919 --> 06:08:13.860
Try not to talk or sneeze or fall asleep

06:08:13.860 --> 06:08:15.419
in the tunnel on the way there.

06:08:15.479 --> 06:08:16.139
All right?

06:08:16.200 --> 06:08:19.020
She turned to the dragon standing next to

06:08:19.020 --> 06:08:19.319
her.

06:08:19.380 --> 06:08:21.779
It took Starflight a moment to recognize

06:08:21.779 --> 06:08:23.400
Glory's brother, Jambu.

06:08:23.520 --> 06:08:25.979
He wasn't his usual vibrant raspberry

06:08:25.979 --> 06:08:26.340
color.

06:08:26.459 --> 06:08:29.400
But a rippling, shadowy black that would

06:08:29.400 --> 06:08:30.959
blend in well with a tunnel walls.

06:08:31.020 --> 06:08:33.299
He was apparently one of the best shots

06:08:33.299 --> 06:08:35.819
with a blowgun, and he'd volunteered to

06:08:35.819 --> 06:08:36.900
be the 1st one through the hole.

06:08:37.020 --> 06:08:39.299
Starflight wasn't sure if that was

06:08:39.299 --> 06:08:41.520
bravery, or just not knowing what he was

06:08:41.520 --> 06:08:43.979
getting himself into, but right now, it

06:08:43.979 --> 06:08:45.000
amounted to the same thing.

06:08:45.060 --> 06:08:48.119
Jamboo hopped up to the hole and slid

06:08:48.119 --> 06:08:48.360
in.

06:08:48.419 --> 06:08:51.479
Glory followed immediately behind him, and

06:08:51.479 --> 06:08:54.779
then Mangrove, Liana, grandeur, and 3

06:08:54.779 --> 06:08:56.819
other rain wings armed with blow guns.

06:08:56.819 --> 06:09:00.000
According to the plan, Starflight and

06:09:00.000 --> 06:09:01.139
Fate speaker were next.

06:09:01.200 --> 06:09:03.180
So that once the guards were knocked out

06:09:03.180 --> 06:09:05.220
they could lead the rain wings to the

06:09:05.220 --> 06:09:06.599
prison caves and the fortress.

06:09:06.659 --> 06:09:09.299
He took a deep breath and looked back

06:09:09.299 --> 06:09:11.099
hoping to catch Sonny's eye.

06:09:11.159 --> 06:09:14.220
She was watching him, her scales glowing

06:09:14.220 --> 06:09:15.240
in the fading sunlight.

06:09:15.299 --> 06:09:17.099
I can do this.

06:09:17.220 --> 06:09:20.520
Starflight clambered into the hole, and

06:09:20.520 --> 06:09:22.860
almost immediately fate speaker followed

06:09:22.860 --> 06:09:24.599
nearly stepping on his tail.

06:09:24.659 --> 06:09:27.180
Neither of them said anything, but he

06:09:27.180 --> 06:09:28.860
felt a little safer knowing she was at

06:09:28.860 --> 06:09:29.159
his back.

06:09:29.220 --> 06:09:32.819
It was stifling in the tunnel, and eerily

06:09:32.819 --> 06:09:33.180
quiet.

06:09:33.240 --> 06:09:35.400
The rain wings ahead of him were

06:09:35.400 --> 06:09:36.779
stealthier than he'd have expected.

06:09:36.840 --> 06:09:39.240
He wasn't sure how far ahead they were

06:09:39.240 --> 06:09:39.900
exactly.

06:09:39.959 --> 06:09:42.299
Even with his excellent night vision.

06:09:42.360 --> 06:09:44.099
Starflight couldn't make out the

06:09:44.099 --> 06:09:45.540
difference between shadows and here.

06:09:45.659 --> 06:09:48.659
The tunnel tilted down, and he crept

06:09:48.659 --> 06:09:51.060
along as fast as he dared, keeping his

06:09:51.060 --> 06:09:53.159
wings carefully folded to hide the silver

06:09:53.159 --> 06:09:53.580
scales.

06:09:53.639 --> 06:09:58.200
Ahead of him, he heard a quiet, and then

06:09:58.200 --> 06:10:00.540
another. and then 7 more in rapid

06:10:00.540 --> 06:10:01.200
succession.

06:10:01.259 --> 06:10:04.259
Sleeping darts fired from blow guns

06:10:04.259 --> 06:10:06.419
straight out of the shadows, hopefully

06:10:06.419 --> 06:10:08.459
knocking out all the guards by the hole

06:10:08.459 --> 06:10:10.319
before any of them noticed and sounded

06:10:10.319 --> 06:10:10.799
the alarm.

06:10:10.860 --> 06:10:15.240
Next, Starfly heard a muffled thump, as

06:10:15.240 --> 06:10:17.159
one rain wing after another jumped into

06:10:17.159 --> 06:10:19.439
the cave, and then he saw the flicker of

06:10:19.439 --> 06:10:19.860
firelight.

06:10:19.919 --> 06:10:22.680
A moment later, he climbed out of the

06:10:22.680 --> 06:10:24.959
tunnel and felt the warm rocks scraping

06:10:24.959 --> 06:10:25.979
below his scales.

06:10:26.040 --> 06:10:29.099
Nine Nightwing guards were lying around

06:10:29.099 --> 06:10:31.860
the cave, each looking as if he or she

06:10:31.860 --> 06:10:33.900
had just fallen asleep all of a sudden.

06:10:33.959 --> 06:10:36.540
Their chests rose and fell peacefully.

06:10:36.599 --> 06:10:38.819
Their spears rested harmlessly on the

06:10:38.819 --> 06:10:39.720
ground nearby.

06:10:39.779 --> 06:10:42.659
Glory turned to Mangrove and pointed at

06:10:42.659 --> 06:10:43.259
the spears.

06:10:43.319 --> 06:10:45.599
She made some kind of signal Starfly

06:10:45.599 --> 06:10:47.580
didn't follow, but Mangrove apparently

06:10:47.580 --> 06:10:47.819
did.

06:10:47.880 --> 06:10:50.099
He started gathering all the weapons in

06:10:50.099 --> 06:10:52.439
the cave, and passed them to the dragons

06:10:52.439 --> 06:10:53.520
still coming through the tunnel.

06:10:53.580 --> 06:10:56.220
They were handed back talon over talon

06:10:56.220 --> 06:10:58.020
until they were safely stashed in the

06:10:58.020 --> 06:11:00.419
rainforest, far away from night wing

06:11:00.419 --> 06:11:00.959
claws.

06:11:01.020 --> 06:11:03.240
The night wings are still dangerous.

06:11:03.360 --> 06:11:05.939
We can't take away their talents, or

06:11:05.939 --> 06:11:09.119
teeth, or fire, but one less weapon in a

06:11:09.119 --> 06:11:10.500
night wing's claws can't hurt.

06:11:10.560 --> 06:11:13.740
Jambu and grandeur had already crept

06:11:13.740 --> 06:11:14.159
ahead.

06:11:14.220 --> 06:11:17.040
If he strained his ears, Starfly could

06:11:17.040 --> 06:11:20.759
hear the, of the blow guns taking out the

06:11:20.759 --> 06:11:23.520
guards by the cave entrance, how long was

06:11:23.520 --> 06:11:24.119
this going to work?

06:11:24.180 --> 06:11:26.639
How many night wings could they send to

06:11:26.639 --> 06:11:28.020
sleep before somebody noticed?

06:11:28.080 --> 06:11:30.599
And once someone sounded the alarm?

06:11:30.659 --> 06:11:32.700
How soon before rain wings started

06:11:32.700 --> 06:11:33.119
dying?

06:11:33.180 --> 06:11:35.340
All clear.

06:11:35.400 --> 06:11:37.619
Grandeur's voice whispered along the

06:11:37.619 --> 06:11:39.299
tunnel, like leaves rustling.

06:11:39.360 --> 06:11:42.240
Glory's scales had shifted to gray and

06:11:42.240 --> 06:11:43.740
red and black to match the cave.

06:11:43.799 --> 06:11:46.919
Starflight couldn't see her, but he felt

06:11:46.919 --> 06:11:48.299
her wings lightly brush his.

06:11:48.360 --> 06:11:50.520
It was his turn to lead the way.

06:11:50.580 --> 06:11:53.580
He glanced back at the hole that led to

06:11:53.580 --> 06:11:54.360
the rainforest.

06:11:54.419 --> 06:11:57.119
Tsunami, and Clay, and Sunny, were

06:11:57.119 --> 06:11:58.740
supposed to stay out of sight during the

06:11:58.740 --> 06:11:59.279
1st wave.

06:11:59.340 --> 06:12:02.520
If anyone spotted blue or brown or gold

06:12:02.520 --> 06:12:04.979
scales on this island, They'd know the

06:12:04.979 --> 06:12:06.779
tunnel had been breached, and the night

06:12:06.779 --> 06:12:08.340
wings would be on them all immediately.

06:12:08.400 --> 06:12:11.520
So they were to stay hidden until the

06:12:11.520 --> 06:12:13.080
stealth campaign turned into a real

06:12:13.080 --> 06:12:13.619
battle.

06:12:13.680 --> 06:12:16.740
On the one talon, Starflight was relieved

06:12:16.740 --> 06:12:18.360
that he didn't have to worry about Sonny

06:12:18.360 --> 06:12:21.299
but on the other, he'd feel a lot better

06:12:21.299 --> 06:12:23.220
if Clay and tsunami were leading the

06:12:23.220 --> 06:12:24.180
charge instead of him.

06:12:24.240 --> 06:12:27.240
But this is the smart way to do it.

06:12:27.299 --> 06:12:29.520
The only way to do it.

06:12:29.580 --> 06:12:32.279
He padded down the tunnel with fate

06:12:32.279 --> 06:12:34.380
speaker beside him, stepping over the

06:12:34.380 --> 06:12:36.779
slumbering night wing guards, he could

06:12:36.779 --> 06:12:38.340
hear the sound of the ocean waves

06:12:38.340 --> 06:12:40.380
crashing on the black sand below

06:12:40.439 --> 06:12:41.639
outside.

06:12:41.700 --> 06:12:44.340
The sky was even more gray and ominous

06:12:44.340 --> 06:12:47.099
than before, with grim, lowering clouds

06:12:47.099 --> 06:12:49.799
that flickered with lightning, all lit by

06:12:49.799 --> 06:12:51.360
the red glow from the volcano.

06:12:51.360 --> 06:12:54.240
After the bright warmth of the rainforest

06:12:54.240 --> 06:12:56.580
the island air seemed even darker and

06:12:56.580 --> 06:12:57.060
smokier.

06:12:57.180 --> 06:12:59.700
As Starflight stepped out onto the cave

06:12:59.700 --> 06:13:00.119
ledge.

06:13:00.180 --> 06:13:02.279
He felt the ground tremble beneath his

06:13:02.279 --> 06:13:03.720
talons, then stop.

06:13:03.840 --> 06:13:07.200
That's unsettling, he thought.

06:13:07.259 --> 06:13:09.540
What a nightmare.

06:13:09.599 --> 06:13:12.000
Grandeur's voice whispered behind him.

06:13:12.060 --> 06:13:16.200
It's worse than I expected, said Jamboo.

06:13:16.259 --> 06:13:17.819
How can anyone live here?

06:13:17.880 --> 06:13:22.080
You carry this, Glory said, handing

06:13:22.080 --> 06:13:23.880
Starflight one of the guards' spears.

06:13:23.939 --> 06:13:26.459
We might need it, and it'll look less

06:13:26.459 --> 06:13:27.479
weird in your claws.

06:13:27.540 --> 06:13:29.759
If I hold it, it'll look like it's just

06:13:29.759 --> 06:13:31.439
flying around through the air by itself.

06:13:31.500 --> 06:13:34.560
Starflight knotted, although the weight

06:13:34.560 --> 06:13:36.599
of the spear felt extremely strange in

06:13:36.599 --> 06:13:37.979
his talons.

06:13:38.040 --> 06:13:40.139
It was more likely that he'd accidentally

06:13:40.139 --> 06:13:42.479
poke his own eye out than that he'd be

06:13:42.479 --> 06:13:43.619
able to use this to fight.

06:13:43.680 --> 06:13:46.080
He tried to hold it as far away from

06:13:46.080 --> 06:13:48.360
himself as possible as he lifted up into

06:13:48.360 --> 06:13:48.900
the sky.

06:13:48.959 --> 06:13:52.080
Take us to the prison caves first.

06:13:52.139 --> 06:13:54.419
Glory's voice said from the air beside

06:13:54.419 --> 06:13:54.659
him.

06:13:54.720 --> 06:13:57.599
Once Mangrove and the others are set up

06:13:57.599 --> 06:13:59.759
to free the prisoners, you and I can head

06:13:59.759 --> 06:14:00.419
for the fortress.

06:14:00.479 --> 06:14:03.180
You, Starflight said.

06:14:03.240 --> 06:14:05.639
It was really odd not being able to see

06:14:05.639 --> 06:14:05.880
her.

06:14:05.939 --> 06:14:08.159
He felt as if he were arguing with the

06:14:08.159 --> 06:14:08.700
air.

06:14:08.759 --> 06:14:11.880
That's the most dangerous part, as the

06:14:11.880 --> 06:14:13.860
queen, shouldn't you keep yourself safe?

06:14:13.919 --> 06:14:16.319
You can send someone else for splendor.

06:14:16.380 --> 06:14:18.840
He tilted his wings to soar toward the

06:14:18.840 --> 06:14:20.880
prison caves, and the lava river.

06:14:20.939 --> 06:14:23.700
He could feel air currents shifting

06:14:23.700 --> 06:14:26.040
around him as several invisible dragons

06:14:26.040 --> 06:14:26.880
flew alongside.

06:14:26.939 --> 06:14:29.700
He wasn't sure how many rain wings were

06:14:29.700 --> 06:14:31.919
following him, but he hoped none of the

06:14:31.919 --> 06:14:33.900
night wings would hear the wing beats and

06:14:33.900 --> 06:14:34.619
get suspicious.

06:14:34.680 --> 06:14:37.200
There were very few night wings in

06:14:37.200 --> 06:14:37.500
sight.

06:14:37.619 --> 06:14:40.259
One or 2 on the balconies of the fortress

06:14:40.259 --> 06:14:42.299
plus the guards in the cave entrances

06:14:42.299 --> 06:14:43.259
below.

06:14:43.319 --> 06:14:45.240
Starflight guessed that the rest were

06:14:45.240 --> 06:14:46.799
assembling in preparation for their

06:14:46.799 --> 06:14:47.819
planned attack tonight.

06:14:47.880 --> 06:14:51.419
I'm not going to be the kind of queen who

06:14:51.419 --> 06:14:53.700
sends other dragons into danger that I'm

06:14:53.700 --> 06:14:56.159
not willing to face myself, Glory said.

06:14:56.220 --> 06:14:58.919
And even if I could send someone for

06:14:58.919 --> 06:15:01.439
splendor, I can't send anyone else to

06:15:01.439 --> 06:15:02.520
face battle winner.

06:15:02.580 --> 06:15:05.340
Starflight sucked in a surprised breath.

06:15:05.400 --> 06:15:07.200
Battle winner?

06:15:07.200 --> 06:15:07.979
he said.

06:15:08.040 --> 06:15:09.959
Is that a good idea?

06:15:10.020 --> 06:15:12.360
Weren't you the one who suggested

06:15:12.360 --> 06:15:13.020
diplomacy?

06:15:13.080 --> 06:15:16.020
Glory said, and he could hear amusement

06:15:16.020 --> 06:15:16.560
in her voice.

06:15:16.619 --> 06:15:20.040
Yes, but that was before I knew anything

06:15:20.040 --> 06:15:21.540
about the night wings.

06:15:21.599 --> 06:15:24.240
Rescuing the prisoners is the top

06:15:24.240 --> 06:15:25.979
priority, she went on.

06:15:26.040 --> 06:15:28.020
But if I can threaten her somehow.

06:15:28.080 --> 06:15:30.599
Maybe if I tell her I'll expose her

06:15:30.599 --> 06:15:30.959
secret.

06:15:31.020 --> 06:15:33.659
Perhaps I can get her to leave us in the

06:15:33.659 --> 06:15:35.159
rainforest alone from now on.

06:15:35.220 --> 06:15:38.580
I doubt it, fate speaker said.

06:15:38.639 --> 06:15:40.619
The Night Wings really want your

06:15:40.619 --> 06:15:41.340
rainforest.

06:15:41.400 --> 06:15:43.080
Well, too bad.

06:15:43.139 --> 06:15:44.700
Glory snapped.

06:15:44.759 --> 06:15:46.919
Starflight said.

06:15:46.979 --> 06:15:48.840
They were approaching the 1st prison

06:15:48.840 --> 06:15:49.259
cave.

06:15:49.319 --> 06:15:51.720
He dipped his head toward it and fell to

06:15:51.720 --> 06:15:54.240
whoosh of wind as one of the rain wings

06:15:54.240 --> 06:15:55.080
dove past him.

06:15:55.139 --> 06:15:57.840
A moment later, the 2 guards in the cave

06:15:57.840 --> 06:15:59.819
entrance both reached for their necks

06:15:59.819 --> 06:16:02.459
looking confused, and then, in slow

06:16:02.459 --> 06:16:04.919
motion, they crumpled into slumbering

06:16:04.919 --> 06:16:05.220
heaps.

06:16:05.279 --> 06:16:08.459
We're lucky the caves line the river

06:16:08.459 --> 06:16:11.040
Starflight said, circling around in the

06:16:11.040 --> 06:16:11.520
sky.

06:16:11.580 --> 06:16:14.040
The guards at each entrance can't see any

06:16:14.040 --> 06:16:15.419
of the others get knocked out.

06:16:15.479 --> 06:16:17.939
He saw the guards in the next cave

06:16:17.939 --> 06:16:20.099
collapse to the ground, and then the next

06:16:20.099 --> 06:16:21.000
and the next.

06:16:21.060 --> 06:16:23.400
The rain wings were fanning out.

06:16:23.459 --> 06:16:25.619
Following instructions Glory had given

06:16:25.619 --> 06:16:27.299
them before leaving the rainforest.

06:16:27.360 --> 06:16:29.580
He saw the shimmer of scales and teeth

06:16:29.580 --> 06:16:32.099
here and there as the rain wings landed

06:16:32.099 --> 06:16:34.919
in pairs, shifted color, and darted into

06:16:34.919 --> 06:16:35.639
the prison caves.

06:16:35.700 --> 06:16:38.819
You said you saw orchid in one of these

06:16:38.819 --> 06:16:39.240
caves.

06:16:39.299 --> 06:16:41.159
Glory said to fate speaker.

06:16:41.220 --> 06:16:42.599
Do you remember which one?

06:16:42.659 --> 06:16:45.479
Fate speaker nodded and twisted into a

06:16:45.479 --> 06:16:48.000
dive, aiming for one of the caves closest

06:16:48.000 --> 06:16:49.020
to the fortress.

06:16:49.020 --> 06:16:51.720
As they approached, its 2 guards looked

06:16:51.720 --> 06:16:51.959
up.

06:16:52.080 --> 06:16:54.599
Although all they could see were 2

06:16:54.599 --> 06:16:56.700
Nightwing Dragonettes, one of them

06:16:56.700 --> 06:16:58.860
frowned a little, as if he sensed

06:16:58.860 --> 06:16:59.700
something was amiss.

06:16:59.700 --> 06:17:02.819
Starflight's stomach lurched as the guard

06:17:02.819 --> 06:17:04.500
reached for the gong that would summon

06:17:04.500 --> 06:17:05.459
the rest of the tribe.

06:17:05.580 --> 06:17:09.180
Then the air beside Starflight seer went

06:17:09.180 --> 06:17:10.439
zit, zit.

06:17:10.500 --> 06:17:12.540
And the 2 guards wobbled and went down.

06:17:12.599 --> 06:17:15.840
That was close, Starflight said.

06:17:15.900 --> 06:17:18.599
But after a moment, he realized he really

06:17:18.599 --> 06:17:20.220
was talking to empty air.

06:17:20.279 --> 06:17:22.439
Below him, the 2 guards were dragged

06:17:22.439 --> 06:17:24.840
aside, and as he landed, he heard the

06:17:24.840 --> 06:17:26.459
thump of talons hurrying to the back of

06:17:26.459 --> 06:17:26.880
the cave.

06:17:26.939 --> 06:17:30.419
I want to see this, fate speaker

06:17:30.419 --> 06:17:32.220
whispered, darting inside.

06:17:32.279 --> 06:17:34.619
Starflight followed just in time to see

06:17:34.619 --> 06:17:37.139
Mangrove appear in front of Orchid, his

06:17:37.139 --> 06:17:39.299
gray and black scales shifting all at

06:17:39.299 --> 06:17:42.299
once to a joyful pink, shot through with

06:17:42.299 --> 06:17:43.319
worried green.

06:17:43.319 --> 06:17:46.139
Orchid let out a cry of joy that was

06:17:46.139 --> 06:17:48.000
muffled by the iron muzzle around her

06:17:48.000 --> 06:17:48.360
jaws.

06:17:48.419 --> 06:17:51.240
She reached toward mangrove, and he

06:17:51.240 --> 06:17:53.639
leaped for her, wrapping his wings all

06:17:53.639 --> 06:17:55.860
the way around her and twining his tail

06:17:55.860 --> 06:17:56.279
with hers.

06:17:56.400 --> 06:17:58.139
I'm here.

06:17:58.200 --> 06:17:59.279
He said.

06:17:59.340 --> 06:18:00.779
I wouldn't give up.

06:18:00.840 --> 06:18:02.819
I'd never give up on you.

06:18:02.939 --> 06:18:06.479
She couldn't speak, but the rose colors

06:18:06.479 --> 06:18:08.459
of orchids, scales said everything.

06:18:08.520 --> 06:18:11.520
Let's get her out of here as fast as we

06:18:11.520 --> 06:18:12.959
can, Glory said.

06:18:13.020 --> 06:18:15.060
If they're all chained to the wall like

06:18:15.060 --> 06:18:16.860
this, we have extra work to do.

06:18:16.860 --> 06:18:18.840
Starflight, give me the spear.

06:18:18.900 --> 06:18:21.959
Starflight held the spear out, and it was

06:18:21.959 --> 06:18:22.860
whisked away from him.

06:18:22.919 --> 06:18:26.040
A glory shaped shadow approached orchid

06:18:26.040 --> 06:18:27.900
and carefully stuck the points of the

06:18:27.900 --> 06:18:29.880
spear into the lock on the mouthband.

06:18:29.939 --> 06:18:32.040
Liana, grandeur.

06:18:32.099 --> 06:18:33.180
Are you paying attention?

06:18:33.240 --> 06:18:34.080
Glory asked.

06:18:34.139 --> 06:18:35.220
Yes.

06:18:35.279 --> 06:18:37.560
Two voices said from the air.

06:18:37.619 --> 06:18:38.880
Starflight jumped.

06:18:38.939 --> 06:18:41.759
He hadn't realized the other 2 rain wings

06:18:41.759 --> 06:18:42.180
were with them.

06:18:42.240 --> 06:18:44.880
This is how you undo the locks.

06:18:44.939 --> 06:18:46.979
Glory said, twisting the spear.

06:18:47.099 --> 06:18:50.279
The muzzle fell off of a clank, and Glory

06:18:50.279 --> 06:18:51.779
set to work on the chains that bound

06:18:51.779 --> 06:18:52.860
orchid to the wall.

06:18:52.919 --> 06:18:54.659
I was afraid.

06:18:54.779 --> 06:18:57.060
You wouldn't care where I was.

06:18:57.180 --> 06:18:59.279
Orchid said to Mangrove.

06:18:59.340 --> 06:19:02.520
I thought you'd move on and find someone

06:19:02.520 --> 06:19:02.880
else.

06:19:02.939 --> 06:19:04.799
Never.

06:19:04.860 --> 06:19:06.299
Never, never.

06:19:06.419 --> 06:19:08.400
Mangrove said fiercely.

06:19:08.459 --> 06:19:12.720
Do you feel the earth shaking or get

06:19:12.720 --> 06:19:13.020
asked?

06:19:13.080 --> 06:19:15.000
I think that's me.

06:19:15.119 --> 06:19:18.119
Mangrove said, holding out his trembling

06:19:18.119 --> 06:19:18.720
claws.

06:19:18.779 --> 06:19:21.720
Like all the happiness inside us is

06:19:21.720 --> 06:19:22.740
trying to burst out.

06:19:22.799 --> 06:19:26.580
Actually, I'm pretty sure that was a real

06:19:26.580 --> 06:19:28.799
earthquake, Starflight thought.

06:19:28.860 --> 06:19:31.380
He'd felt the tremor in the earth as well

06:19:31.380 --> 06:19:33.599
rumbling up through his talons before it

06:19:33.599 --> 06:19:33.900
stopped.

06:19:33.959 --> 06:19:38.159
Done, Glory said, and the spear moved

06:19:38.159 --> 06:19:39.840
through the air, she handed it to one of

06:19:39.840 --> 06:19:40.680
the other rain wings.

06:19:40.740 --> 06:19:43.619
Orchid shook off the loose chains and

06:19:43.619 --> 06:19:46.200
spread her wings, beaming and glowing

06:19:46.200 --> 06:19:47.939
like a ball of pink sunshine.

06:19:48.000 --> 06:19:49.979
Orchid.

06:19:50.040 --> 06:19:53.759
This is our new queen, glory, said

06:19:53.759 --> 06:19:54.540
mangrove.

06:19:54.599 --> 06:19:58.080
She's the reason we found you, and she's

06:19:58.080 --> 06:20:00.180
the dragon who convinced everyone to come

06:20:00.180 --> 06:20:00.659
get you.

06:20:00.720 --> 06:20:04.380
It was really, thanks to Mangrove, said

06:20:04.380 --> 06:20:04.919
Glory.

06:20:04.979 --> 06:20:06.840
He's the one who knew you were missing

06:20:06.840 --> 06:20:08.279
and wouldn't shut up about it.

06:20:08.340 --> 06:20:10.680
If we hadn't brought an army to save you

06:20:10.680 --> 06:20:12.180
he'd have come over here and done it

06:20:12.180 --> 06:20:12.540
himself.

06:20:12.659 --> 06:20:16.020
Thank you, Your Majesty.

06:20:16.139 --> 06:20:18.180
Orchid said with a half bow.

06:20:18.299 --> 06:20:21.360
That is too weird.

06:20:21.419 --> 06:20:24.000
Starflight whisper to fate speaker.

06:20:24.060 --> 06:20:27.240
Hearing my friend called Your Majesty.

06:20:27.299 --> 06:20:30.779
I bet watching her lead an invasion is

06:20:30.779 --> 06:20:31.860
fairly strange too.

06:20:31.919 --> 06:20:33.779
Fate speaker whispered back.

06:20:33.840 --> 06:20:37.680
Grandeur, Liana, disguise yourselves as

06:20:37.680 --> 06:20:38.400
night wings.

06:20:38.459 --> 06:20:40.619
Take the guards, spears, and go to the

06:20:40.619 --> 06:20:41.159
other caves.

06:20:41.220 --> 06:20:42.360
Glory ordered.

06:20:42.419 --> 06:20:44.819
Show everyone how to free the prisoners.

06:20:44.880 --> 06:20:48.060
Move as quickly and quietly as you can

06:20:48.060 --> 06:20:49.380
then get everyone back to the tunnel.

06:20:49.439 --> 06:20:52.439
The most important thing is getting all

06:20:52.439 --> 06:20:53.880
14 prisoners home safe.

06:20:53.939 --> 06:20:55.259
Mangrove.

06:20:55.319 --> 06:20:57.599
You and Orchid take a moment to calm your

06:20:57.599 --> 06:20:59.580
scales down, and then you can head back

06:20:59.580 --> 06:21:00.419
to the rainforest too.

06:21:00.479 --> 06:21:04.560
I should come with you, Mangrove said.

06:21:04.619 --> 06:21:07.259
If you're going into the fortress.

06:21:07.319 --> 06:21:08.159
You'll need backup.

06:21:08.279 --> 06:21:11.040
I'll have it, Glory said.

06:21:11.099 --> 06:21:13.439
I hope she doesn't mean me.

06:21:13.500 --> 06:21:15.540
Starflight thought anxiously.

06:21:15.599 --> 06:21:18.299
But we went to a lot of trouble to

06:21:18.299 --> 06:21:20.580
reunite you and Orchid, so go be happy

06:21:20.580 --> 06:21:21.540
with her for a little while.

06:21:21.599 --> 06:21:23.279
We'll let you know if we need you.

06:21:23.340 --> 06:21:26.459
Mangrove and Orchid both bowed.

06:21:26.520 --> 06:21:29.159
Wings brushed against Starflight's

06:21:29.159 --> 06:21:30.900
shoulder, and he started back for a

06:21:30.900 --> 06:21:33.299
moment before he realized it was glory

06:21:33.299 --> 06:21:35.340
heading up the tunnel to the lava river.

06:21:35.400 --> 06:21:38.580
Come on, Starflight, she said from the

06:21:38.580 --> 06:21:38.939
darkness.

06:21:39.000 --> 06:21:41.459
Let's go have a talk with a night wing

06:21:41.459 --> 06:21:41.939
Queen.
10744
06:21:42,000 --> 06:21:46,500	Chapter 25.

06:21:46.799 --> 06:21:50.580
The fortress seemed eerily quiet as they

06:21:50.580 --> 06:21:51.299
flew toward it.

06:21:51.360 --> 06:21:53.939
The air felt thick with ashy smoke.

06:21:54.000 --> 06:21:56.520
Starflight's nose and throat hurt even

06:21:56.520 --> 06:21:58.860
worse than before, and occasionally he

06:21:58.860 --> 06:22:00.779
heard glory and fate speaker coughing

06:22:00.779 --> 06:22:01.139
behind him.

06:22:01.200 --> 06:22:04.319
He rubbed his stinging eyes, and stared

06:22:04.319 --> 06:22:06.659
at the fortress ahead, wondering where an

06:22:06.659 --> 06:22:08.759
entire night wing army would assemble.

06:22:08.819 --> 06:22:10.860
Queen Battle Winner wouldn't be able to

06:22:10.860 --> 06:22:12.840
lead it, since she couldn't leave the

06:22:12.840 --> 06:22:13.259
lava.

06:22:13.319 --> 06:22:15.479
Greatness would have to really make some

06:22:15.479 --> 06:22:17.819
queenly decisions if she was planning to

06:22:17.819 --> 06:22:18.479
lead their attack.

06:22:18.540 --> 06:22:21.119
Had Starflights absence been noticed

06:22:21.119 --> 06:22:21.299
yet?

06:22:21.360 --> 06:22:24.659
If not, surely at least Morrow's here

06:22:24.659 --> 06:22:26.040
would have gone to check on Flame and

06:22:26.040 --> 06:22:26.639
found him missing.

06:22:26.759 --> 06:22:28.380
How had he reacted?

06:22:28.500 --> 06:22:31.799
Maybe he'll think Flame tried to fly home

06:22:31.799 --> 06:22:32.400
to the continent.

06:22:32.520 --> 06:22:33.959
Starfly thought.

06:22:34.020 --> 06:22:37.139
We'd be in luck if Morrow Seer tried to

06:22:37.139 --> 06:22:37.500
follow him.

06:22:37.560 --> 06:22:40.259
He really did not want to encounter

06:22:40.259 --> 06:22:41.700
Morrow Seer in the halls of the

06:22:41.700 --> 06:22:42.119
fortress.

06:22:42.180 --> 06:22:45.540
Please tell me there's an invisible army

06:22:45.540 --> 06:22:46.020
with us.

06:22:46.080 --> 06:22:47.400
Starflight said.

06:22:47.459 --> 06:22:49.860
I'm your invisible army.

06:22:49.919 --> 06:22:51.360
Glory said cheerfully.

06:22:51.419 --> 06:22:54.659
I'm serious, Starflight said.

06:22:54.720 --> 06:22:57.299
We shouldn't go in there alone, just the

06:22:57.299 --> 06:22:57.840
3 of us.

06:22:57.900 --> 06:23:00.779
Tell me something, Glory said.

06:23:00.900 --> 06:23:02.580
The dungeons you saw.

06:23:02.639 --> 06:23:03.720
How do we get them open?

06:23:03.779 --> 06:23:06.419
Will those spears work on the doors, or

06:23:06.419 --> 06:23:07.020
do we need keys?

06:23:07.080 --> 06:23:10.380
Starflight closed his eyes for a moment

06:23:10.380 --> 06:23:11.580
picturing the dungeon.

06:23:11.700 --> 06:23:14.759
We need keys, I think, he said.

06:23:14.819 --> 06:23:17.340
So let's start with a queen.

06:23:17.400 --> 06:23:18.299
Glory said.

06:23:18.360 --> 06:23:20.340
We'll make her tell us where to find the

06:23:20.340 --> 06:23:20.700
keys.

06:23:20.759 --> 06:23:24.119
Starflight cannot imagine making battle

06:23:24.119 --> 06:23:27.299
winner do anything at all, but then glory

06:23:27.299 --> 06:23:30.240
was a lot more persuasive than he was, and

06:23:30.240 --> 06:23:32.099
even more so now that she had a queen's

06:23:32.099 --> 06:23:32.520
authority.

06:23:32.580 --> 06:23:34.799
He swerved down toward the entrance

06:23:34.799 --> 06:23:37.020
closest to the council chamber.

06:23:37.080 --> 06:23:39.419
The 3 of them padded silently through the

06:23:39.419 --> 06:23:39.900
hallways.

06:23:39.959 --> 06:23:42.659
Loud voices rang out from a few of the

06:23:42.659 --> 06:23:42.959
rooms.

06:23:43.080 --> 06:23:45.840
Starflight caught snippets of an argument

06:23:45.840 --> 06:23:48.240
about who would get to wear some shared

06:23:48.240 --> 06:23:50.639
armor, a monologue about another battle

06:23:50.639 --> 06:23:53.220
the storyteller had been in, and a

06:23:53.220 --> 06:23:55.259
conversation about how killing rain wings

06:23:55.259 --> 06:23:56.880
would have to be easier than killing mud

06:23:56.880 --> 06:23:57.299
wings.

06:23:57.360 --> 06:23:59.939
He'd forgotten all about the dead mud

06:23:59.939 --> 06:24:01.259
wings on the rainforest border.

06:24:01.380 --> 06:24:04.259
Why would the night wings kill them?

06:24:04.380 --> 06:24:05.880
He asked himself.

06:24:05.939 --> 06:24:09.000
And almost immediately, a possible answer

06:24:09.000 --> 06:24:09.659
came to him.

06:24:09.720 --> 06:24:12.240
To keep the mud wings out of the

06:24:12.240 --> 06:24:12.840
rainforest.

06:24:12.900 --> 06:24:15.419
If they believe there's a deadly monster

06:24:15.419 --> 06:24:17.939
lurking in there, that it's not safe to

06:24:17.939 --> 06:24:19.259
go anywhere near it.

06:24:19.319 --> 06:24:21.000
They won't be tempted to conquer their

06:24:21.000 --> 06:24:21.959
rainforest themselves.

06:24:22.020 --> 06:24:24.900
Leaving it untouched and ready for the

06:24:24.900 --> 06:24:26.939
night wings to move in any time.

06:24:27.000 --> 06:24:29.939
That explains the howler monkeys too.

06:24:30.000 --> 06:24:33.060
He remembered Jambu saying that the

06:24:33.060 --> 06:24:34.799
monkeys used to make a normal monkey

06:24:34.799 --> 06:24:37.080
sound, but then suddenly they started

06:24:37.080 --> 06:24:39.479
screaming like dying dragons instead.

06:24:39.540 --> 06:24:42.900
I bet my dad is responsible for that.

06:24:42.959 --> 06:24:45.659
I bet he did something to the monkeys so

06:24:45.659 --> 06:24:47.340
their screams would scare the mud wings

06:24:47.340 --> 06:24:47.580
away.

06:24:47.639 --> 06:24:51.360
Everything the Night Wings did was part

06:24:51.360 --> 06:24:53.340
of their grand plan of taking over the

06:24:53.340 --> 06:24:56.939
rainforest, Starflight side, and glanced

06:24:56.939 --> 06:24:58.380
at the map as he led the way into the

06:24:58.380 --> 06:24:59.520
room with his secret entrance.

06:24:59.580 --> 06:25:02.400
If only there was somewhere else, the

06:25:02.400 --> 06:25:04.740
night wings could go, but they'd clearly

06:25:04.740 --> 06:25:07.740
been all over Pyria, destroying scavenger

06:25:07.740 --> 06:25:10.080
dens for whatever reason, and if there

06:25:10.080 --> 06:25:11.580
had been somewhere else for them to live

06:25:11.580 --> 06:25:13.139
surely they would have found it.

06:25:13.200 --> 06:25:15.000
Someone's coming.

06:25:15.060 --> 06:25:16.439
Glory whispered.

06:25:16.500 --> 06:25:19.319
A heartbeat before Starflight heard claws

06:25:19.319 --> 06:25:21.779
tapping on stone, and smelled the rank

06:25:21.779 --> 06:25:23.279
odor of night wing breath.

06:25:23.340 --> 06:25:25.919
Fate speaker shot across the room to the

06:25:25.919 --> 06:25:28.380
map, but before she could lift the corner

06:25:28.380 --> 06:25:30.900
and duck underneath, scales slithered in

06:25:30.900 --> 06:25:33.060
the doorway, and they all whirled to see

06:25:33.060 --> 06:25:35.520
greatness staring at them, the ground

06:25:35.520 --> 06:25:36.720
rumbled under their feet.

06:25:36.779 --> 06:25:39.900
What are you doing in here?

06:25:39.959 --> 06:25:41.639
The night wing princess asked.

06:25:41.700 --> 06:25:44.580
Her glittering diamond necklace was askew

06:25:44.580 --> 06:25:46.680
as if she'd slept in it, and had

06:25:46.680 --> 06:25:47.639
forgotten it was on.

06:25:47.700 --> 06:25:50.819
Her eyes looked exhausted, red and raw

06:25:50.819 --> 06:25:51.840
from the smoke in the air.

06:25:51.900 --> 06:25:54.299
Why aren't you with the others?

06:25:54.360 --> 06:25:57.540
We got lost?

06:25:57.659 --> 06:25:59.279
Starflight tried.

06:25:59.340 --> 06:26:01.080
Greatness squinted at them.

06:26:01.139 --> 06:26:04.680
Oh, you're the 2 little prophecy

06:26:04.680 --> 06:26:05.459
dragonettes.

06:26:05.520 --> 06:26:08.220
Mozier was looking for you in quite a

06:26:08.220 --> 06:26:09.599
towering rage earlier.

06:26:09.720 --> 06:26:13.259
Listen, like I told him, the prophecy is

06:26:13.259 --> 06:26:15.299
important, but it's even more important

06:26:15.299 --> 06:26:16.979
that we win this battle tonight.

06:26:17.040 --> 06:26:19.439
So the whole tribe is going.

06:26:19.500 --> 06:26:21.060
No exceptions.

06:26:21.119 --> 06:26:23.400
Everyone else is in the great hall.

06:26:23.459 --> 06:26:26.520
If you follow this tunnel down and take

06:26:26.520 --> 06:26:29.340
the 4th left, you'll be halfway there and

06:26:29.340 --> 06:26:30.299
someone can guide you.

06:26:30.360 --> 06:26:32.459
What about you?

06:26:32.520 --> 06:26:34.200
Fate speaker asked.

06:26:34.259 --> 06:26:35.580
Why aren't you there?

06:26:35.639 --> 06:26:39.360
I'm going to speak with a queen first

06:26:39.360 --> 06:26:41.340
Greatness said.

06:26:41.400 --> 06:26:43.319
Her eyes darted involuntarily to the

06:26:43.319 --> 06:26:43.560
map.

06:26:43.619 --> 06:26:47.939
Actually, Glory's voice said from the air

06:26:47.939 --> 06:26:50.459
we're all going to speak with a queen.

06:26:50.520 --> 06:26:53.459
Greatness stiffened and pulled in her

06:26:53.459 --> 06:26:53.759
wings.

06:26:53.819 --> 06:26:56.880
Starflight saw a flash of scales changing

06:26:56.880 --> 06:26:59.459
color, as glory's claws rested on the

06:26:59.459 --> 06:27:01.080
artery in the night wing's throat.

06:27:01.139 --> 06:27:04.259
Don't call for help, Glory said.

06:27:04.319 --> 06:27:06.599
I'm not an ordinary rain wing.

06:27:06.659 --> 06:27:09.299
My venom is aimed at your eyes right now

06:27:09.299 --> 06:27:12.060
and I am not afraid to use it.

06:27:12.119 --> 06:27:14.279
The dangerous one.

06:27:14.400 --> 06:27:16.080
Greatness whispered.

06:27:16.139 --> 06:27:18.180
That's right, Glory said.

06:27:18.240 --> 06:27:21.419
Now, we're all going up the hidden tunnel

06:27:21.419 --> 06:27:23.639
to the queen, and you're leading the way

06:27:23.639 --> 06:27:25.680
and you're going to keep in mind that my

06:27:25.680 --> 06:27:27.419
fangs are right behind you.

06:27:27.479 --> 06:27:30.360
Greatness blinked and nodded several

06:27:30.360 --> 06:27:32.159
times. looking queasy.

06:27:32.220 --> 06:27:34.680
She hurried to the map and ducked into

06:27:34.680 --> 06:27:35.279
the tunnel.

06:27:35.340 --> 06:27:37.799
The rustle of wings indicated that glory

06:27:37.799 --> 06:27:38.340
had followed her.

06:27:38.459 --> 06:27:40.619
Fate speaker and Starflight were right

06:27:40.619 --> 06:27:40.979
behind them.

06:27:41.099 --> 06:27:43.680
The rocky floor felt hot under

06:27:43.680 --> 06:27:46.439
Starflights, talons, hotter than it had

06:27:46.439 --> 06:27:46.740
before.

06:27:46.799 --> 06:27:49.740
Another rumble shook the mountain as they

06:27:49.740 --> 06:27:50.520
pressed forward.

06:27:50.580 --> 06:27:54.840
Um, Starflight said, as a horrifying

06:27:54.840 --> 06:27:55.680
thought struck him.

06:27:55.740 --> 06:27:59.099
There's no chance this volcano is about

06:27:59.099 --> 06:28:00.000
to erupt.

06:28:00.060 --> 06:28:01.200
Is there?

06:28:01.259 --> 06:28:04.860
Up ahead in the shadows, the bulky figure

06:28:04.860 --> 06:28:06.540
of greatness paused and looked back.

06:28:06.599 --> 06:28:09.599
It shouldn't, she said.

06:28:09.659 --> 06:28:12.659
Our scientist predicted that we have at

06:28:12.659 --> 06:28:14.759
least 2 more years before another major

06:28:14.759 --> 06:28:15.479
eruption.

06:28:15.540 --> 06:28:18.119
How can they be sure?

06:28:18.180 --> 06:28:19.500
Fate speaker asked.

06:28:19.560 --> 06:28:21.180
Did someone have a vision?

06:28:21.240 --> 06:28:23.639
Greatness turned around and kept walking

06:28:23.639 --> 06:28:24.779
without answering?

06:28:24.900 --> 06:28:27.119
Starflight braced himself against another

06:28:27.119 --> 06:28:28.319
tremble in the ground.

06:28:28.380 --> 06:28:30.840
I don't like the feeling in the air.

06:28:30.900 --> 06:28:33.060
He whispered to fate speaker.

06:28:33.119 --> 06:28:36.000
I don't know much about volcanoes, but

06:28:36.000 --> 06:28:37.860
I'm pretty sure it's a bad sign when they

06:28:37.860 --> 06:28:38.520
start doing this.

06:28:38.580 --> 06:28:41.159
Poor Night Wings.

06:28:41.279 --> 06:28:42.959
Fate speaker said softly.

06:28:43.080 --> 06:28:47.759
Hmm, said Starflight, more like poor us

06:28:47.759 --> 06:28:49.439
if we don't get out of here soon.

06:28:49.560 --> 06:28:52.979
They abruptly came around the bend into

06:28:52.979 --> 06:28:54.119
the Queen's cave.

06:28:54.180 --> 06:28:57.000
Queen Battle Winner was sitting erect in

06:28:57.000 --> 06:28:59.759
her boiling lava cauldron, glaring at

06:28:59.759 --> 06:29:02.040
them with fierce eyes that reflected the

06:29:02.040 --> 06:29:03.419
red light around them.

06:29:03.479 --> 06:29:06.180
Starflight inhaled sharply as he spotted

06:29:06.180 --> 06:29:07.860
another dragon in the back corner of the

06:29:07.860 --> 06:29:08.220
cave.

06:29:08.279 --> 06:29:11.099
His father, mastermind.

06:29:11.159 --> 06:29:13.200
The scientist was fussing over several

06:29:13.200 --> 06:29:15.599
hunks of metal on the floor, and after a

06:29:15.599 --> 06:29:17.939
moment, Starflight remembered seeing them

06:29:17.939 --> 06:29:19.919
in the lab, all put together.

06:29:19.979 --> 06:29:22.020
They looked like a suit of armor that

06:29:22.020 --> 06:29:24.599
would fit over an entire dragon, with

06:29:24.599 --> 06:29:26.459
room to pour something in between the

06:29:26.459 --> 06:29:28.020
dragon's scales and the metal.

06:29:28.080 --> 06:29:30.060
Lava.

06:29:30.119 --> 06:29:31.380
He realized.

06:29:31.439 --> 06:29:34.560
This is how Battle winner plans to get to

06:29:34.560 --> 06:29:35.220
the rainforest.

06:29:35.340 --> 06:29:38.220
Mastermind has been building her a

06:29:38.220 --> 06:29:39.419
portable lava device.

06:29:39.479 --> 06:29:42.240
His brain immediately started taking

06:29:42.240 --> 06:29:43.619
apart the science of the idea.

06:29:43.680 --> 06:29:47.279
But how would it stay hot, away from the

06:29:47.279 --> 06:29:47.759
volcano?

06:29:47.819 --> 06:29:50.340
Can any metal really contain it?

06:29:50.459 --> 06:29:54.479
He also realized, tangentially, that his

06:29:54.479 --> 06:29:56.040
father had lied about not seeing the

06:29:56.040 --> 06:29:58.740
queen, he must be one of the few dragons

06:29:58.740 --> 06:30:00.840
who knew her secret and was working to

06:30:00.840 --> 06:30:01.380
help her keep it.

06:30:01.439 --> 06:30:05.040
Mastermind looked up as they came in, and

06:30:05.040 --> 06:30:06.419
locked eyes with Starflight.

06:30:06.479 --> 06:30:09.299
His expression was startled, but in a

06:30:09.299 --> 06:30:11.639
distracted way, as if he was dealing with

06:30:11.639 --> 06:30:12.900
something far more important.

06:30:12.959 --> 06:30:15.540
And after a moment, he bent back to the

06:30:15.540 --> 06:30:17.159
armor without saying anything to his

06:30:17.159 --> 06:30:17.400
son.

06:30:17.459 --> 06:30:20.340
Fool.

06:30:20.400 --> 06:30:22.799
Battle winner snarled at greatness.

06:30:22.860 --> 06:30:25.439
Greatness hung her head, looking less

06:30:25.439 --> 06:30:26.520
like a queen than ever.

06:30:26.580 --> 06:30:29.580
Preparations.

06:30:29.700 --> 06:30:32.400
The night wing queen hissed.

06:30:32.459 --> 06:30:36.000
Everyone is gathering, greatness said.

06:30:36.060 --> 06:30:38.279
But, mother, I can't lead them into

06:30:38.279 --> 06:30:39.540
battle by myself.

06:30:39.599 --> 06:30:41.279
Can't we postpone the attack?

06:30:41.400 --> 06:30:43.979
Mastermind says your armor isn't ready.

06:30:44.040 --> 06:30:46.500
It will be.

06:30:46.619 --> 06:30:48.840
Battle winner hissed.

06:30:48.959 --> 06:30:50.220
Tonight.

06:30:50.279 --> 06:30:52.860
I don't think so.

06:30:52.919 --> 06:30:55.439
Mastermind said anxiously from behind

06:30:55.439 --> 06:30:55.680
her.

06:30:55.740 --> 06:30:58.619
He dropped a curved tail plate with a

06:30:58.619 --> 06:30:59.819
loud clatter and winced.

06:30:59.880 --> 06:31:01.680
Your majesty.

06:31:01.740 --> 06:31:03.599
I don't understand why you have to go.

06:31:03.659 --> 06:31:06.299
I need more time to make sure this will

06:31:06.299 --> 06:31:06.599
work for you.

06:31:06.720 --> 06:31:08.880
Must.

06:31:09.000 --> 06:31:11.759
Do this, right?

06:31:11.819 --> 06:31:14.220
Battle winner snarled.

06:31:14.279 --> 06:31:19.139
Can't trust you to invade properly.

06:31:19.200 --> 06:31:22.439
She cast a scornful look at greatness.

06:31:22.500 --> 06:31:26.580
You shouldn't, greatness said, fingering

06:31:26.580 --> 06:31:27.659
the diamonds around her neck.

06:31:27.720 --> 06:31:30.119
I don't know what you want me to do.

06:31:30.180 --> 06:31:34.619
So I was coming to ask you, and then, And

06:31:34.619 --> 06:31:35.759
then she ran into me.

06:31:35.819 --> 06:31:37.139
Glory said.

06:31:37.200 --> 06:31:40.919
Mastermind let out a yelp of fright, as

06:31:40.919 --> 06:31:43.080
glory's scales shimmered into sight

06:31:43.080 --> 06:31:45.240
shifting from the camouflage of the

06:31:45.240 --> 06:31:48.299
shadows to a bold royal blue shot through

06:31:48.299 --> 06:31:49.259
with veins of gold.

06:31:49.380 --> 06:31:52.560
She looked regal and out of place in this

06:31:52.560 --> 06:31:54.060
smoky red and black cave.

06:31:54.119 --> 06:31:58.799
Well, she added, more accurately, she ran

06:31:58.799 --> 06:32:00.060
into my claws.

06:32:00.119 --> 06:32:02.880
She flexed her talons and narrowed her

06:32:02.880 --> 06:32:04.319
eyes at Queen Battle Winner.

06:32:04.380 --> 06:32:08.819
And you are, growled the queen.

06:32:08.880 --> 06:32:11.880
Queen glory of the rain wings.

06:32:11.939 --> 06:32:14.400
I have come to give you one chance to end

06:32:14.400 --> 06:32:16.080
this war before we destroy you.

06:32:16.139 --> 06:32:19.740
The dragon and the lava made an

06:32:19.740 --> 06:32:22.200
involuntary scoffing sound that clearly

06:32:22.200 --> 06:32:23.099
hurt her throat.

06:32:23.159 --> 06:32:26.279
She paused for a long moment, clutching

06:32:26.279 --> 06:32:28.259
her neck, then dipped her whole body

06:32:28.259 --> 06:32:30.180
under the lava and emerged again.

06:32:30.180 --> 06:32:34.439
Funny, she said finally.

06:32:34.560 --> 06:32:37.139
Not very, Glory said.

06:32:37.200 --> 06:32:39.540
If you think an ice wing attack is hard

06:32:39.540 --> 06:32:42.000
to live with, wait until you experience a

06:32:42.000 --> 06:32:44.340
little rain wing venom, I'm afraid your

06:32:44.340 --> 06:32:46.319
lava bath won't be able to help you with

06:32:46.319 --> 06:32:46.500
that.

06:32:46.619 --> 06:32:49.740
Smoke hissed softly through battle

06:32:49.740 --> 06:32:51.900
winners' nostrils as she stared at

06:32:51.900 --> 06:32:52.259
glory.

06:32:52.380 --> 06:32:57.659
Oh, 3 moons, greatness said anxiously

06:32:57.659 --> 06:32:58.799
wringing her talons.

06:32:58.860 --> 06:33:00.299
What do you want?

06:33:00.360 --> 06:33:04.020
We're taking our prisoners back, Glory

06:33:04.020 --> 06:33:04.319
said.

06:33:04.380 --> 06:33:07.680
You will never set foot in the rainforest

06:33:07.680 --> 06:33:08.040
again.

06:33:08.099 --> 06:33:10.259
You will leave the rain wings alone

06:33:10.259 --> 06:33:13.080
forever. will destroy the tunnel between

06:33:13.080 --> 06:33:13.740
our kingdoms.

06:33:13.799 --> 06:33:16.979
You'll call off the invasion, and we'll

06:33:16.979 --> 06:33:19.619
never even sniff, another night wing near

06:33:19.619 --> 06:33:21.720
our village for the next 12 generations.

06:33:21.840 --> 06:33:25.200
Starflight cleared his throat a few times

06:33:25.200 --> 06:33:28.020
significantly, and Glory glanced at him.

06:33:28.380 --> 06:33:31.680
Also, she added, you will stop meddling

06:33:31.680 --> 06:33:33.900
with a prophecy dragonettes, both the

06:33:33.900 --> 06:33:36.060
real ones and the fake ones.

06:33:36.119 --> 06:33:37.860
You'll let them save the world and stop

06:33:37.860 --> 06:33:39.540
the war however they decide to.

06:33:39.599 --> 06:33:43.799
Never, hissed Queen Battle Winner.

06:33:43.860 --> 06:33:44.939
Never.

06:33:45.060 --> 06:33:47.099
Never what?

06:33:47.159 --> 06:33:49.919
Glory said, because you don't have a lot

06:33:49.919 --> 06:33:50.580
of options here.

06:33:50.639 --> 06:33:53.939
I see one.

06:33:54.000 --> 06:33:57.540
Battle winner croaked, you die.

06:33:57.659 --> 06:34:01.200
Glory bared her teeth the night wing

06:34:01.200 --> 06:34:03.599
queen, but greatness interrupted, her

06:34:03.599 --> 06:34:07.560
voice pleading, please, listen, you're

06:34:07.560 --> 06:34:10.380
dooming us to a horrible end, she cried.

06:34:10.439 --> 06:34:13.500
The volcano is not only a future threat.

06:34:13.560 --> 06:34:15.000
It's killing us now.

06:34:15.060 --> 06:34:17.759
There's almost no prey left.

06:34:17.819 --> 06:34:19.380
We're all starving.

06:34:19.439 --> 06:34:22.979
Fewer dragonettes are born each year, and

06:34:22.979 --> 06:34:24.479
we're barely night wings anymore.

06:34:24.540 --> 06:34:26.220
Don't you see?

06:34:26.279 --> 06:34:27.959
The tribe is dying.

06:34:28.020 --> 06:34:30.060
We need a new home.

06:34:30.180 --> 06:34:34.319
Well, you can't have ours, you murderous

06:34:34.319 --> 06:34:35.520
entitled worms.

06:34:35.580 --> 06:34:36.840
Glory flared.

06:34:36.900 --> 06:34:38.639
Why not?

06:34:38.700 --> 06:34:40.380
Mastermind asked.

06:34:40.439 --> 06:34:42.180
Sounding genuinely confused.

06:34:42.240 --> 06:34:45.180
Because a whole tribe already lives

06:34:45.180 --> 06:34:45.360
there.

06:34:45.419 --> 06:34:48.180
Glory scales were flashing to red and

06:34:48.180 --> 06:34:50.520
orange in places, hints of her anger

06:34:50.520 --> 06:34:52.680
showing through, although she quelled

06:34:52.680 --> 06:34:53.099
them quickly.

06:34:53.159 --> 06:34:56.939
And if you try to hurt my rain wings, I

06:34:56.939 --> 06:34:58.080
will make you regret it.

06:34:58.139 --> 06:35:01.619
Wait, Starflight said.

06:35:01.740 --> 06:35:04.799
His brain was suddenly spinning forward, a

06:35:04.799 --> 06:35:07.380
new idea unfolding across his mind like a

06:35:07.380 --> 06:35:08.520
scroll rolling open.

06:35:08.580 --> 06:35:10.020
Wait.

06:35:10.080 --> 06:35:12.959
Maybe, maybe there's a way to

06:35:12.959 --> 06:35:13.619
compromise.

06:35:13.680 --> 06:35:15.000
Glory.

06:35:15.060 --> 06:35:16.139
Stop and think.

06:35:16.200 --> 06:35:18.659
There's lots of space in the rainforest.

06:35:18.720 --> 06:35:20.639
The rain wings say so all the time.

06:35:20.700 --> 06:35:23.279
What if we let the night wings move in

06:35:23.279 --> 06:35:25.740
and build their own village somewhere in

06:35:25.740 --> 06:35:28.500
the rainforest, but only if they all

06:35:28.500 --> 06:35:31.139
swear to accept you as their new queen.

06:35:31.259 --> 06:35:33.479
There was a shocked pause.

06:35:33.540 --> 06:35:35.520
What?

06:35:35.639 --> 06:35:37.560
Battle winner roared.

06:35:37.619 --> 06:35:39.840
Glory tilted her head at Starflight

06:35:39.840 --> 06:35:41.759
looking skeptical but intrigued.

06:35:41.819 --> 06:35:45.060
Think about it, Starflight said.

06:35:45.119 --> 06:35:48.119
A new home for the night wings, safe and

06:35:48.119 --> 06:35:50.580
peaceful, and all they have to do is give

06:35:50.580 --> 06:35:52.439
up their cruelty and violence and obey

06:35:52.439 --> 06:35:52.680
you.

06:35:52.740 --> 06:35:55.560
You know you'd be as great at being night

06:35:55.560 --> 06:35:57.779
wing queen as you are at rolling the rain

06:35:57.779 --> 06:35:58.319
wings.

06:35:58.380 --> 06:36:01.020
Hmm, Glory said.

06:36:01.080 --> 06:36:03.479
There would be something poetic about

06:36:03.479 --> 06:36:05.400
being the boss of a tribe that's always

06:36:05.400 --> 06:36:06.959
called me lazy and useless.

06:36:07.020 --> 06:36:08.880
Never.

06:36:08.939 --> 06:36:12.119
Battle winner shouted, then had to stop

06:36:12.119 --> 06:36:13.680
and double over coughing for a long

06:36:13.680 --> 06:36:14.040
minute.

06:36:14.099 --> 06:36:16.860
Uneasily, Starflight felt the ground

06:36:16.860 --> 06:36:19.259
shake again, much stronger this time.

06:36:19.319 --> 06:36:24.599
Will never bow to rain wings.

06:36:24.659 --> 06:36:27.000
Battle winner snarled finally.

06:36:27.060 --> 06:36:30.659
Actually, mother, greatness said

06:36:30.659 --> 06:36:31.259
nervously.

06:36:31.380 --> 06:36:34.020
It sounds like a decent plan to me.

06:36:34.080 --> 06:36:37.200
Battle winner spat out a shard of ice

06:36:37.200 --> 06:36:39.659
that sizzled into steam when it hit the

06:36:39.659 --> 06:36:40.380
lava.

06:36:40.439 --> 06:36:44.939
You never wanted to be queen, she

06:36:44.939 --> 06:36:45.479
rasped.

06:36:45.540 --> 06:36:48.299
You're a pathetic air.

06:36:48.360 --> 06:36:50.700
I know I am.

06:36:50.759 --> 06:36:52.080
Greatness said.

06:36:52.139 --> 06:36:53.939
Being queen is awful.

06:36:54.000 --> 06:36:57.540
Battle winner hissed again, loud and

06:36:57.540 --> 06:36:57.959
long.

06:36:58.020 --> 06:37:00.540
Starflight realized that he was also

06:37:00.540 --> 06:37:02.939
hearing something else, a far away

06:37:02.939 --> 06:37:04.740
rumbling that seemed to be getting louder

06:37:04.740 --> 06:37:05.639
and closer.

06:37:05.700 --> 06:37:09.000
What about our real queen?

06:37:09.060 --> 06:37:10.439
Mastermind asked.

06:37:10.500 --> 06:37:13.439
Starflight stared straight into the icy

06:37:13.439 --> 06:37:15.419
blue depths of battle winner's eyes.

06:37:15.479 --> 06:37:18.779
I think she knows she's not making it to

06:37:18.779 --> 06:37:19.380
the rainforest.

06:37:19.439 --> 06:37:22.319
There's nothing you can build that will

06:37:22.319 --> 06:37:23.580
work to keep her alive there.

06:37:23.639 --> 06:37:25.799
She's going to die here.

06:37:25.860 --> 06:37:28.680
Crushed by the volcano along with a

06:37:28.680 --> 06:37:29.459
nightwing home.

06:37:29.520 --> 06:37:31.919
And if she wants her tribe to survive.

06:37:32.040 --> 06:37:34.380
She needs to hand them over to Queen

06:37:34.380 --> 06:37:34.860
Glory.

06:37:34.919 --> 06:37:38.279
Battle winner's tale was thrashing hard

06:37:38.279 --> 06:37:40.799
enough to spill lava over the edges of

06:37:40.799 --> 06:37:43.139
the cauldron, splattering dangerously

06:37:43.139 --> 06:37:44.159
close to their talons.

06:37:44.220 --> 06:37:47.520
I am the queen.

06:37:47.580 --> 06:37:50.580
I am, she spat.

06:37:50.639 --> 06:37:52.979
Wait, Starflight.

06:37:53.040 --> 06:37:53.939
Glory said.

06:37:54.000 --> 06:37:55.619
I haven't agreed to this.

06:37:55.680 --> 06:37:58.259
How could we ever trust the night wings

06:37:58.259 --> 06:37:59.099
in our rainforest?

06:37:59.159 --> 06:38:01.860
These are the same dragons who've been

06:38:01.860 --> 06:38:03.540
abducting and torturing my tribe.

06:38:03.599 --> 06:38:05.459
How can we just forgive them?

06:38:05.520 --> 06:38:07.619
I don't want them anywhere near us.

06:38:07.740 --> 06:38:09.299
She shook her head.

06:38:09.360 --> 06:38:10.979
I don't think it'll work.

06:38:11.040 --> 06:38:14.040
Mastermind looked sick at the words

06:38:14.040 --> 06:38:16.380
abducting and torturing.

06:38:16.439 --> 06:38:18.959
He turned away from Starflight, staring

06:38:18.959 --> 06:38:20.520
down at the armor in his claws.

06:38:20.580 --> 06:38:22.619
It might work.

06:38:22.680 --> 06:38:24.540
Greatness said desperately.

06:38:24.599 --> 06:38:26.639
Give us a chance, please.

06:38:26.700 --> 06:38:28.500
I promise we can be better.

06:38:28.619 --> 06:38:30.900
Shameful.

06:38:30.959 --> 06:38:33.060
Battle winner snarled.

06:38:33.119 --> 06:38:36.900
It's not up to you, Starflight said to

06:38:36.900 --> 06:38:39.419
the Nightwing Queen, and realized his

06:38:39.419 --> 06:38:40.439
voice wasn't even shaking.

06:38:40.500 --> 06:38:41.759
He was right.

06:38:41.819 --> 06:38:44.400
He could feel it, and that helped him get

06:38:44.400 --> 06:38:45.060
past his fear.

06:38:45.119 --> 06:38:47.459
You're stuck here.

06:38:47.520 --> 06:38:49.680
We're negotiating with greatness now.

06:38:49.740 --> 06:38:52.439
He turned to the night wing princess.

06:38:52.500 --> 06:38:53.580
Come on.

06:38:53.639 --> 06:38:55.259
Let's talk about this somewhere else.

06:38:55.319 --> 06:38:59.159
No, Ward Battle Winner.

06:38:59.220 --> 06:39:01.080
You can't do this.

06:39:01.139 --> 06:39:04.319
I won't let you.

06:39:04.439 --> 06:39:07.259
She gripped the sides of the cauldron

06:39:07.259 --> 06:39:09.779
with glistening claws, and then, to

06:39:09.779 --> 06:39:12.419
Starflight's horror, she heaved herself

06:39:12.419 --> 06:39:15.779
up and out of the lava, her back talon

06:39:15.779 --> 06:39:18.060
crunched down on the edge of the cauldron

06:39:18.060 --> 06:39:21.119
her wings flared open, scattering molten

06:39:21.119 --> 06:39:22.619
orange droplets across the room.

06:39:22.680 --> 06:39:25.799
Her thick head swung back and forth

06:39:25.799 --> 06:39:27.299
glaring at all of them.

06:39:27.360 --> 06:39:31.319
She was massive, as big as morrow sere

06:39:31.319 --> 06:39:34.380
and glowing horribly, as lava dripped

06:39:34.380 --> 06:39:36.599
between her scales and claws and

06:39:36.599 --> 06:39:37.619
slithered off her tail.

06:39:37.680 --> 06:39:40.139
Mother, stop.

06:39:40.200 --> 06:39:41.400
Greatness cried.

06:39:41.459 --> 06:39:43.259
Your majesty.

06:39:43.319 --> 06:39:44.759
Mastermind shouted.

06:39:44.819 --> 06:39:46.139
You can't come out.

06:39:46.200 --> 06:39:48.240
Wait, my experiment.

06:39:48.299 --> 06:39:50.520
He scrabbled frantically at the armor

06:39:50.520 --> 06:39:50.880
around him.

06:39:50.939 --> 06:39:56.580
I will lead my tribe to safety.

06:39:56.639 --> 06:39:58.319
The queen hissed.

06:39:58.380 --> 06:40:00.840
She landed on the rocky ground with a

06:40:00.840 --> 06:40:03.900
thud, but the aftershocks went on too

06:40:03.900 --> 06:40:04.919
long to be caused by her.

06:40:05.040 --> 06:40:08.459
It was an earthquake, a serious one

06:40:08.459 --> 06:40:11.400
Starflight realized, as bits of the walls

06:40:11.400 --> 06:40:12.240
began to crumble.

06:40:12.299 --> 06:40:15.840
We have to get out of here. said to

06:40:15.840 --> 06:40:16.139
glory.

06:40:16.200 --> 06:40:18.959
Queen Battle Winner took a step toward

06:40:18.959 --> 06:40:21.119
glory and Starflight, then stopped

06:40:21.119 --> 06:40:22.259
clutching her neck again.

06:40:22.319 --> 06:40:25.919
She hissed in a frightening, hoarse way

06:40:25.919 --> 06:40:27.060
and took another step.

06:40:27.119 --> 06:40:30.540
Her tongue flicked out and in as she

06:40:30.540 --> 06:40:31.200
started to shake.

06:40:31.319 --> 06:40:33.779
When she stared around at all of them.

06:40:34.619 --> 06:40:36.360
Starflight could see the icy blue

06:40:36.360 --> 06:40:38.580
spreading rapidly over her eyeballs.

06:40:38.639 --> 06:40:41.400
Mother, greatness yelped.

06:40:41.459 --> 06:40:43.319
Get back in the lava.

06:40:43.380 --> 06:40:46.380
She darted to her mother's side and tried

06:40:46.380 --> 06:40:48.060
tugging on Battle Winner's wing.

06:40:48.119 --> 06:40:50.520
Mastermind dashed up on the other side

06:40:50.520 --> 06:40:52.919
and started wrapping bits of metal around

06:40:52.919 --> 06:40:54.180
the queen's limbs.

06:40:54.240 --> 06:40:56.580
But Starflight could tell that even if

06:40:56.580 --> 06:40:58.799
the armor would work, it was already too

06:40:58.799 --> 06:40:59.099
late.

06:40:59.159 --> 06:41:03.180
With a bone rattling shriek, Battle

06:41:03.180 --> 06:41:04.799
winner threw off her daughter and

06:41:04.799 --> 06:41:07.619
mastermind and surged toward glory.

06:41:07.619 --> 06:41:10.259
Glory took a step back, and the night

06:41:10.259 --> 06:41:12.060
wing queen collapsed on the floor in

06:41:12.060 --> 06:41:12.779
front of her.

06:41:13.080 --> 06:41:15.720
Her limbs twitched violently, her wings

06:41:15.720 --> 06:41:18.240
spasmed, her tail thrashed back and

06:41:18.240 --> 06:41:18.479
forth.

06:41:18.599 --> 06:41:21.900
White frost was starting to march between

06:41:21.900 --> 06:41:24.659
the scales of her neck, spreading rapidly

06:41:24.659 --> 06:41:25.200
across her body.

06:41:25.259 --> 06:41:29.220
Lava dripped off battle winner, faster

06:41:29.220 --> 06:41:31.919
and faster, as the ice started to win the

06:41:31.919 --> 06:41:32.700
battle for her body.

06:41:32.759 --> 06:41:35.279
Greatness pressed herself against the

06:41:35.279 --> 06:41:37.979
wall, whimpering, as far away from the

06:41:37.979 --> 06:41:39.060
dying queen as possible.

06:41:39.180 --> 06:41:42.299
Starflight wanted to look away, but

06:41:42.299 --> 06:41:43.200
somehow he couldn't.

06:41:43.259 --> 06:41:46.020
He felt fate speaker bury her face in his

06:41:46.020 --> 06:41:46.319
shoulder.

06:41:46.380 --> 06:41:50.159
The Nightwing Queen's neck froze solid

06:41:50.159 --> 06:41:53.459
first. then her chest, her ears, her

06:41:53.459 --> 06:41:56.520
wings, her snout, all the way out to her

06:41:56.520 --> 06:41:57.659
claws and her tail.

06:41:57.720 --> 06:42:00.779
Within moments, the dragon's entire body

06:42:00.779 --> 06:42:03.240
was encased in jagged whorls of ice.

06:42:03.299 --> 06:42:07.200
Her eyes were blue pools of rage, her

06:42:07.200 --> 06:42:10.139
mouth froze wide open, as if she'd wanted

06:42:10.139 --> 06:42:13.200
to end her life with a howl of fury, but

06:42:13.200 --> 06:42:13.740
it was too late.

06:42:13.799 --> 06:42:15.360
Nothing could come out.

06:42:15.419 --> 06:42:18.959
Greatness and mastermind stared down at

06:42:18.959 --> 06:42:22.380
the queen, disbelief and horror warring

06:42:22.380 --> 06:42:22.919
on their faces.

06:42:22.979 --> 06:42:27.599
Then, the entire island shook, as if a

06:42:27.599 --> 06:42:30.060
giant dragon had pounded his talons into

06:42:30.060 --> 06:42:32.580
it, and Starflight felt his stomach twist

06:42:32.580 --> 06:42:33.659
with terror.

06:42:33.720 --> 06:42:36.479
The volcano was about to erupt.
11314
06:42:36,599 --> 06:42:41,099	Chapter 26.

06:42:41.459 --> 06:42:43.740
We have to go.

06:42:43.799 --> 06:42:47.520
Now, Starflight said, grabbing glory and

06:42:47.520 --> 06:42:49.020
shoving her toward the door.

06:42:49.080 --> 06:42:51.180
He bundled fate speaker ahead of him too

06:42:51.180 --> 06:42:52.860
and they fled down the tunnel.

06:42:52.919 --> 06:42:54.479
Wait!

06:42:54.540 --> 06:42:57.419
He heard greatness yell as they ran, but

06:42:57.419 --> 06:42:59.040
when fate speaker tried to stop, he

06:42:59.040 --> 06:43:00.540
pushed her forward.

06:43:00.599 --> 06:43:02.220
There was no time for more diplomatic

06:43:02.220 --> 06:43:02.880
conversation.

06:43:02.939 --> 06:43:04.799
Feet thumped behind them.

06:43:04.860 --> 06:43:06.659
Greatness would have to talk to them

06:43:06.659 --> 06:43:09.540
somewhere else, such as not in the middle

06:43:09.540 --> 06:43:10.740
of an exploding volcano.

06:43:10.860 --> 06:43:14.340
The map caught on Starflight's horns and

06:43:14.340 --> 06:43:16.020
ripped away from the wall as he threw

06:43:16.020 --> 06:43:17.220
himself out of the hole at the end.

06:43:17.340 --> 06:43:20.459
He rolled forward, wrestling the map off

06:43:20.459 --> 06:43:23.040
his head, and bundling it in his talons.

06:43:23.639 --> 06:43:25.080
Without really thinking about it, he

06:43:25.080 --> 06:43:26.939
shoved it under one arm and carried it

06:43:26.939 --> 06:43:28.200
with him as he bolted for the door.

06:43:28.259 --> 06:43:31.740
Where are the dungeons, Glory shouted.

06:43:31.799 --> 06:43:34.860
There's no time, Starflight yelled.

06:43:34.919 --> 06:43:37.259
Couldn't she feel the volcano shaking?

06:43:37.319 --> 06:43:39.599
Ash was raining down all around them.

06:43:39.659 --> 06:43:42.060
Cracks were zipping across the fortress

06:43:42.060 --> 06:43:43.080
walls like lightning.

06:43:43.139 --> 06:43:45.779
We are not leaving Deathbringer.

06:43:45.840 --> 06:43:47.880
Glory grabbed fate speaker.

06:43:47.939 --> 06:43:50.459
Point the way, and I'll go by myself.

06:43:50.520 --> 06:43:52.139
Starflight, get out of here.

06:43:52.200 --> 06:43:53.700
Get everyone off the island.

06:43:53.759 --> 06:43:55.919
Death bringer?

06:43:55.979 --> 06:43:58.500
Starflight opened and closed his mouth.

06:43:58.560 --> 06:44:01.200
He hadn't realized that rescuing the

06:44:01.200 --> 06:44:03.180
Nightwing assassin was even on Glory's

06:44:03.180 --> 06:44:05.220
agenda, let alone that it was important

06:44:05.220 --> 06:44:07.500
enough to risk an erupting volcano for.

06:44:07.560 --> 06:44:09.659
But she's right.

06:44:09.720 --> 06:44:11.580
He risked everything for us.

06:44:11.639 --> 06:44:13.259
For her.

06:44:13.319 --> 06:44:15.959
Fate speaker pointed in the direction of

06:44:15.959 --> 06:44:18.060
the dungeons, and glory took off without

06:44:18.060 --> 06:44:19.259
waiting for any more arguments.

06:44:19.380 --> 06:44:21.720
I can't let her go by herself.

06:44:21.779 --> 06:44:24.299
Starflight's heart was trying to pound

06:44:24.299 --> 06:44:25.500
its way out of his chest.

06:44:25.560 --> 06:44:28.380
He remembered the night wing skeletons in

06:44:28.380 --> 06:44:29.340
the old treasure room.

06:44:29.400 --> 06:44:31.799
He thought of the lava flow that had

06:44:31.799 --> 06:44:34.439
consumed the old forest and the skulls

06:44:34.439 --> 06:44:35.220
sticking out of it.

06:44:35.279 --> 06:44:38.520
He could feel the heat of the volcano, as

06:44:38.520 --> 06:44:40.080
if it were trying to batter its way

06:44:40.080 --> 06:44:41.099
through the walls toward him.

06:44:41.159 --> 06:44:45.119
All he wanted to do, was fly as fast as

06:44:45.119 --> 06:44:47.700
he could to the tunnel and escape to the

06:44:47.700 --> 06:44:49.139
cool safety of the rainforest.

06:44:49.200 --> 06:44:51.959
But glory didn't know where she was going

06:44:51.959 --> 06:44:53.400
or what to do when she got there.

06:44:53.459 --> 06:44:56.459
He whirled around and found greatness

06:44:56.459 --> 06:44:58.680
behind them, wringing her talons again

06:44:58.680 --> 06:45:00.119
and looking utterly wrecked.

06:45:00.180 --> 06:45:03.540
Where are the keys to the dungeon prisons

06:45:03.540 --> 06:45:04.380
he yelled at her.

06:45:04.439 --> 06:45:09.299
The, oh, there's a set hidden in a coal

06:45:09.299 --> 06:45:11.520
niche on the dungeon stairs, she said.

06:45:11.580 --> 06:45:13.500
What are we going to do about the

06:45:13.500 --> 06:45:14.220
volcano?

06:45:14.279 --> 06:45:15.180
Is this it?

06:45:15.240 --> 06:45:16.979
The one that kills us all.

06:45:17.099 --> 06:45:19.020
Yes.

06:45:19.080 --> 06:45:22.799
Not necessarily, Starflight said. trying

06:45:22.799 --> 06:45:24.840
to sound far less panicked than he felt.

06:45:24.900 --> 06:45:28.259
Take fate speaker to the great hall and

06:45:28.259 --> 06:45:30.419
tell all the night wings our terms.

06:45:30.479 --> 06:45:33.299
If they'll swear loyalty to Queen Glory

06:45:33.299 --> 06:45:35.040
we'll consider letting them live in the

06:45:35.040 --> 06:45:35.580
rainforest.

06:45:35.639 --> 06:45:38.639
Anyone who agrees, send them through the

06:45:38.639 --> 06:45:39.900
tunnel as fast as you can.

06:45:39.959 --> 06:45:42.959
Anyone who doesn't, tell them to fly for

06:45:42.959 --> 06:45:44.159
the continent immediately.

06:45:44.220 --> 06:45:46.200
They need to get far away from here

06:45:46.200 --> 06:45:47.099
before the eruption.

06:45:47.159 --> 06:45:49.619
The lava and smoke could reach for

06:45:49.619 --> 06:45:49.860
miles.

06:45:49.979 --> 06:45:52.560
But glory didn't say yes.

06:45:52.619 --> 06:45:54.360
Fate speaker pointed out.

06:45:54.419 --> 06:45:56.159
I'll talk her into it.

06:45:56.220 --> 06:45:59.459
He promised grimly, go quickly.

06:45:59.520 --> 06:46:02.279
He wrapped his wings briefly around fate

06:46:02.279 --> 06:46:05.040
speaker, feeling her scales slide against

06:46:05.040 --> 06:46:07.560
his, and then let go, and ran after

06:46:07.560 --> 06:46:08.700
glory.

06:46:08.759 --> 06:46:10.619
He foundered the next intersection

06:46:10.619 --> 06:46:12.779
looking around in furious indecision.

06:46:12.840 --> 06:46:15.119
This way, he called.

06:46:15.180 --> 06:46:17.520
He ran past her toward the stairs that

06:46:17.520 --> 06:46:18.599
led down to the dungeon.

06:46:18.659 --> 06:46:21.540
There was no time to talk, and the

06:46:21.540 --> 06:46:23.400
rumbling of the volcano was now loud

06:46:23.400 --> 06:46:25.740
enough to drown out any attempt at

06:46:25.740 --> 06:46:26.639
conversation anyway.

06:46:26.700 --> 06:46:29.759
The heat increased as they went down and

06:46:29.759 --> 06:46:32.220
the noise grew, and the walls seemed to

06:46:32.220 --> 06:46:32.880
shake even more.

06:46:32.939 --> 06:46:37.080
We're going to die down here, Starfly

06:46:37.080 --> 06:46:39.180
thought, with absolute certainty.

06:46:39.240 --> 06:46:41.580
He stopped at each niche on the stairs

06:46:41.580 --> 06:46:43.979
feeling gingerly around the coals and

06:46:43.979 --> 06:46:45.659
singeing his talons more than once.

06:46:45.720 --> 06:46:48.840
Finally, in the last one, he felt

06:46:48.840 --> 06:46:51.000
something metal and heavy hanging from a

06:46:51.000 --> 06:46:52.979
hook inside the opening, and when he

06:46:52.979 --> 06:46:55.500
tugged on it, he found keys resting in

06:46:55.500 --> 06:46:55.919
his claws.

06:46:56.040 --> 06:46:59.159
In the dungeon, Splendor was awake

06:46:59.159 --> 06:47:01.380
shaking like a leaf in the middle of her

06:47:01.380 --> 06:47:03.180
cell, with her wings over her head.

06:47:03.240 --> 06:47:04.979
It's all right.

06:47:05.040 --> 06:47:07.979
Starflight called through the bars, trying

06:47:07.979 --> 06:47:09.840
keys in the lock one after another.

06:47:09.840 --> 06:47:10.919
We're here.

06:47:10.979 --> 06:47:12.240
We're rescuing you.

06:47:12.299 --> 06:47:13.560
You're going home.

06:47:13.619 --> 06:47:16.200
Splendor looked up, blinking.

06:47:16.259 --> 06:47:19.319
Her scales were bright acid green, and

06:47:19.319 --> 06:47:21.659
her expression was dazed with fear.

06:47:21.720 --> 06:47:23.759
Starflight glanced around and realized

06:47:23.759 --> 06:47:25.919
that glory had gone right past them.

06:47:25.979 --> 06:47:29.099
She was at Death Bringer's cage, grabbing

06:47:29.099 --> 06:47:29.580
the bars.

06:47:29.639 --> 06:47:30.900
As he watched.

06:47:30.959 --> 06:47:33.299
Deathbringer reached his talon through

06:47:33.299 --> 06:47:36.000
the bars and wrapped them around hers, and

06:47:36.000 --> 06:47:38.099
they exchanged a look that said, thank

06:47:38.099 --> 06:47:40.020
you, and a whole lot more.

06:47:40.080 --> 06:47:43.500
The lock finally turned under his claws

06:47:43.500 --> 06:47:44.880
and the door swung open.

06:47:44.939 --> 06:47:46.799
Splendor stumbled toward him.

06:47:46.860 --> 06:47:50.459
Wait here, he told her, hurrying to Death

06:47:50.459 --> 06:47:51.180
Bringer's door.

06:47:51.299 --> 06:47:53.279
Why aren't we leaving?

06:47:53.400 --> 06:47:54.900
Splendor wailed.

06:47:54.959 --> 06:47:57.540
Glory grabbed the keys from him and

06:47:57.540 --> 06:47:58.380
started trying them.

06:47:58.439 --> 06:48:00.540
It was hard to tell whether her talons

06:48:00.540 --> 06:48:02.759
were shaking from nerves too, or whether

06:48:02.759 --> 06:48:04.979
it just looked that way, because the

06:48:04.979 --> 06:48:06.659
whole mountain was quaking now without

06:48:06.659 --> 06:48:07.740
stopping.

06:48:07.799 --> 06:48:09.599
You don't have to do this.

06:48:09.659 --> 06:48:11.220
Deathbringer said.

06:48:11.279 --> 06:48:12.959
His gaze fixed on glory.

06:48:13.020 --> 06:48:14.819
Oh, I don't?

06:48:14.939 --> 06:48:17.220
Glory said, without looking up from the

06:48:17.220 --> 06:48:17.520
keys.

06:48:17.639 --> 06:48:19.439
That'll save me some time.

06:48:19.500 --> 06:48:21.000
Good luck with a volcano, then.

06:48:21.060 --> 06:48:24.060
Starflight glanced up at the ominous

06:48:24.060 --> 06:48:25.439
cracks appearing in the ceiling.

06:48:25.500 --> 06:48:27.599
He spotted a symbol at the top of

06:48:27.599 --> 06:48:30.240
Deathbringer's cage, a symbol he'd seen

06:48:30.240 --> 06:48:31.080
on one of the keys.

06:48:31.139 --> 06:48:35.340
Try this one, he said, reaching over and

06:48:35.340 --> 06:48:36.540
taking the keys from glory.

06:48:36.599 --> 06:48:38.880
He stuck the key with a symbol on it in

06:48:38.880 --> 06:48:39.779
the lock and turned it.

06:48:39.840 --> 06:48:41.159
The door swung open.

06:48:41.220 --> 06:48:44.400
Deathbringer yanked on his chains as they

06:48:44.400 --> 06:48:46.799
hurried into the cell, Splendor ran in

06:48:46.799 --> 06:48:48.900
behind them, flapping her wings in a

06:48:48.900 --> 06:48:50.159
frantic whirl of green.

06:48:50.220 --> 06:48:52.680
Something is coming through the walls.

06:48:52.740 --> 06:48:54.240
She shrieked.

06:48:54.299 --> 06:48:55.319
We're all going to die.

06:48:55.380 --> 06:48:58.500
Starflight looked out at the dungeon

06:48:58.500 --> 06:49:00.779
hallway and saw lava glowing in the

06:49:00.779 --> 06:49:01.680
cracks of the walls.

06:49:01.740 --> 06:49:04.979
She's right, he said quietly to glory.

06:49:05.040 --> 06:49:08.700
You 2 go ahead, she said, concentrating

06:49:08.700 --> 06:49:10.560
on the keys and death bringer's chains.

06:49:10.560 --> 06:49:11.939
We'll be right behind you.

06:49:12.000 --> 06:49:13.740
Let's go.

06:49:13.799 --> 06:49:14.580
Let's go.

06:49:14.639 --> 06:49:16.139
Splendor cried.

06:49:16.259 --> 06:49:19.500
One more minute, Starflight told her.

06:49:19.560 --> 06:49:21.779
He held his breath as glory tried key

06:49:21.779 --> 06:49:22.380
after key.

06:49:22.439 --> 06:49:25.319
We don't have any more minutes.

06:49:25.380 --> 06:49:26.939
Splendor sobbed.

06:49:27.000 --> 06:49:29.939
We're going to be exploded and covered in

06:49:29.939 --> 06:49:31.259
lava and melted and dead.

06:49:31.319 --> 06:49:34.919
A ferocious rumble answered her, knocking

06:49:34.919 --> 06:49:36.060
them all off their feet.

06:49:36.119 --> 06:49:38.639
Glory scrambled up and stuck the last key

06:49:38.639 --> 06:49:40.919
in the lock around Deathbringers' chains.

06:49:40.979 --> 06:49:42.299
That's it.

06:49:42.360 --> 06:49:45.419
She cried as they fell off, clanking and

06:49:45.419 --> 06:49:47.040
clattering like living things on the

06:49:47.040 --> 06:49:47.819
quaking floor.

06:49:47.880 --> 06:49:48.779
Come on.

06:49:48.840 --> 06:49:51.599
She seized Deathbringer's forearm and

06:49:51.599 --> 06:49:52.139
yanked him up.

06:49:52.200 --> 06:49:54.360
They took off down the hallway, with

06:49:54.360 --> 06:49:55.860
Starflight and splendor right behind

06:49:55.860 --> 06:49:56.099
them.

06:49:56.159 --> 06:49:59.580
The mountain was shaking so violently now

06:49:59.580 --> 06:50:00.959
that it was hard to run.

06:50:01.020 --> 06:50:03.900
Starflight kept getting thrown into walls

06:50:03.900 --> 06:50:05.220
or the other dragons.

06:50:05.279 --> 06:50:07.439
He concentrated on the stairs up ahead.

06:50:07.500 --> 06:50:09.240
Watch your feet.

06:50:09.299 --> 06:50:10.799
Deathbringer called.

06:50:10.860 --> 06:50:13.259
Hot coals were scattered across the steps

06:50:13.259 --> 06:50:15.060
where they had fallen from their niches.

06:50:15.119 --> 06:50:18.299
Glory swept several aside with her tail

06:50:18.299 --> 06:50:20.159
wincing, as even that brief contact

06:50:20.159 --> 06:50:21.360
burned her scales.

06:50:21.419 --> 06:50:24.779
They raced up the steps, covering their

06:50:24.779 --> 06:50:26.880
heads with their wings as bits of rock

06:50:26.880 --> 06:50:28.200
plummeted from the ceiling.

06:50:28.259 --> 06:50:31.259
Starflight stepped on a coal and bit back

06:50:31.259 --> 06:50:32.340
a yowl of pain.

06:50:32.400 --> 06:50:35.580
The stairs felt endless, like they were

06:50:35.580 --> 06:50:38.520
staggering upward for days, but finally

06:50:38.520 --> 06:50:40.319
they burst out onto a level floor.

06:50:40.439 --> 06:50:41.819
This way.

06:50:41.880 --> 06:50:44.520
Death Bringer hurtled down the hall in a

06:50:44.520 --> 06:50:46.139
direction Starflight hadn't been before.

06:50:46.200 --> 06:50:49.259
A loud crash sounded from the direction

06:50:49.259 --> 06:50:51.779
of the council chamber, and Starflight

06:50:51.779 --> 06:50:53.400
thought he heard a dragon screaming.

06:50:53.459 --> 06:50:55.560
He shoved Splendor ahead of him.

06:50:55.619 --> 06:50:57.540
Even glory was green now.

06:50:57.599 --> 06:51:00.119
Neither rain wing could camouflage their

06:51:00.119 --> 06:51:01.680
scales while their fear was so strong.

06:51:01.740 --> 06:51:04.380
They all raced after Deathbringer

06:51:04.380 --> 06:51:06.419
twisting through the fortress labyrinth

06:51:06.419 --> 06:51:09.900
until up ahead, they saw the sky, or at

06:51:09.900 --> 06:51:12.419
least, the dense cloud of ash and smoke

06:51:12.419 --> 06:51:13.979
that now surrounded the volcano.

06:51:14.040 --> 06:51:17.340
Try not to breathe, Glory said to

06:51:17.340 --> 06:51:17.819
Splendor.

06:51:17.880 --> 06:51:19.500
It's not far to the tunnel.

06:51:19.560 --> 06:51:22.619
Starflight flung his wings open and

06:51:22.619 --> 06:51:25.139
leaped off the ledge, flapping furiously

06:51:25.139 --> 06:51:25.860
through the thick air.

06:51:25.919 --> 06:51:28.860
He could see the lava river glowing and

06:51:28.860 --> 06:51:31.560
churning below him, faster and wider than

06:51:31.560 --> 06:51:31.740
ever.

06:51:31.799 --> 06:51:34.380
He could also see a growing crowd of

06:51:34.380 --> 06:51:36.959
black dragons down on the beach, some of

06:51:36.959 --> 06:51:38.520
them fighting one another, tooth and

06:51:38.520 --> 06:51:39.060
claw.

06:51:39.119 --> 06:51:41.759
We have to bring them to the rainforest.

06:51:41.819 --> 06:51:44.700
He called to glory, coughing and gasping

06:51:44.700 --> 06:51:47.220
or else the whole night wing tribe could

06:51:47.220 --> 06:51:48.000
be wiped out today.

06:51:48.060 --> 06:51:52.319
Serves them right, she called, but he

06:51:52.319 --> 06:51:53.819
could see from her face that she couldn't

06:51:53.819 --> 06:51:54.540
let that happen either.

06:51:54.659 --> 06:51:57.599
Chunks of fiery rocks were starting to

06:51:57.599 --> 06:52:00.060
shoot out of the volcano, blasting into

06:52:00.060 --> 06:52:02.099
the sky, and slamming into the ground

06:52:02.099 --> 06:52:03.479
with explosive force.

06:52:03.540 --> 06:52:06.540
One came so close to Starflight's wing

06:52:06.540 --> 06:52:08.759
that he felt the heat of it crackle along

06:52:08.759 --> 06:52:09.659
his scales.

06:52:09.720 --> 06:52:12.720
Glory twisted in the air, scanning the

06:52:12.720 --> 06:52:13.560
caves below her.

06:52:13.619 --> 06:52:16.139
I hope all my rain wings made it back

06:52:16.139 --> 06:52:16.500
safely.

06:52:16.560 --> 06:52:19.319
Starflight found himself making a

06:52:19.319 --> 06:52:21.900
decision that shocked him, but the words

06:52:21.900 --> 06:52:23.759
were out of his mouth before he could

06:52:23.759 --> 06:52:25.020
take them back.

06:52:25.080 --> 06:52:27.599
You go ahead to the rainforest, make sure

06:52:27.599 --> 06:52:29.459
they're all right and prepare them for

06:52:29.459 --> 06:52:30.900
what's coming, he said.

06:52:30.959 --> 06:52:33.419
I'll gather the night wings and bring

06:52:33.419 --> 06:52:33.779
them through.

06:52:33.840 --> 06:52:37.500
She gave him a surprised look, but didn't

06:52:37.500 --> 06:52:37.740
argue.

06:52:37.799 --> 06:52:40.740
We'll have our spears and fangs and

06:52:40.740 --> 06:52:42.540
sleeping darts ready, she said.

06:52:42.599 --> 06:52:44.099
Come on, you two.

06:52:44.220 --> 06:52:46.500
She flicked her tail at Death Bringer and

06:52:46.500 --> 06:52:48.119
Splendor, who sped after her.

06:52:48.180 --> 06:52:50.580
Starflight watched them all die for the

06:52:50.580 --> 06:52:53.459
cave entrance, where green scales flashed

06:52:53.459 --> 06:52:56.279
as 2 half camouflaged rain wings reached

06:52:56.279 --> 06:52:57.060
to welcome them in.

06:52:57.119 --> 06:53:00.240
Now Starflight could see a cluster of

06:53:00.240 --> 06:53:02.340
spears bristling in the air by the cave

06:53:02.340 --> 06:53:05.400
and he realized, with a sinking sensation

06:53:05.400 --> 06:53:07.560
that the rain wings probably weren't

06:53:07.560 --> 06:53:08.819
letting any night wings through.

06:53:08.880 --> 06:53:11.819
He'd sent fate speaker and greatness on

06:53:11.819 --> 06:53:13.979
that mission, but the rain wings didn't

06:53:13.979 --> 06:53:14.939
know them.

06:53:15.000 --> 06:53:17.159
They barely met fate speaker, and had no

06:53:17.159 --> 06:53:18.119
reason to trust them.

06:53:18.180 --> 06:53:20.700
They would listen to him though.

06:53:20.759 --> 06:53:23.159
If he could convince the night wings to

06:53:23.159 --> 06:53:25.860
accept glory as their queen, if he could

06:53:25.860 --> 06:53:27.180
lead them into the rainforest

06:53:27.180 --> 06:53:27.840
peacefully.

06:53:27.900 --> 06:53:32.099
But if he couldn't, there were a 1000000

06:53:32.099 --> 06:53:34.380
things that could go wrong, the rain

06:53:34.380 --> 06:53:36.479
wings might panic and attack the night

06:53:36.479 --> 06:53:38.819
wings as they came through, even with

06:53:38.819 --> 06:53:41.400
glory standing over them, or the night

06:53:41.400 --> 06:53:43.619
wings might lie to get to safety, and

06:53:43.619 --> 06:53:46.560
then attack the rain wings anyway, or the

06:53:46.560 --> 06:53:48.299
volcano might kill them all before they

06:53:48.299 --> 06:53:48.959
got anywhere.

06:53:49.020 --> 06:53:52.740
Another blast from the volcano sent sharp

06:53:52.740 --> 06:53:54.540
rock shards zinging around him.

06:53:54.599 --> 06:53:57.540
Starflight felt a stabbing pain in his

06:53:57.540 --> 06:53:59.639
side as one of them grazed his scales.

06:53:59.700 --> 06:54:03.060
No more time for worrying, he thought

06:54:03.060 --> 06:54:05.400
tucking his wings and diving toward the

06:54:05.400 --> 06:54:05.700
beach.

06:54:05.759 --> 06:54:09.479
We escape now together, or we all die.
11643
06:54:09,540 --> 06:54:14,279	Chapter 27.

06:54:14.520 --> 06:54:17.819
It looked as though the entire tribe

06:54:17.819 --> 06:54:19.139
might be gathered on the beach below

06:54:19.139 --> 06:54:19.500
him.

06:54:19.560 --> 06:54:22.979
Starflight flew in a wide circle, scanning

06:54:22.979 --> 06:54:25.200
the crowd, until he saw greatness and

06:54:25.200 --> 06:54:28.020
fate speaker standing on a boulder, waving

06:54:28.020 --> 06:54:29.459
their wings and trying to get everyone's

06:54:29.459 --> 06:54:29.819
attention.

06:54:29.880 --> 06:54:33.959
They'll never let us through, shrieked a

06:54:33.959 --> 06:54:35.880
night wing with long scratches along his

06:54:35.880 --> 06:54:36.240
side.

06:54:36.299 --> 06:54:39.419
We have to take the rainforest by force.

06:54:39.479 --> 06:54:42.180
We can't fight them, yelled another.

06:54:42.299 --> 06:54:45.180
They infiltrated the island, took out all

06:54:45.180 --> 06:54:46.919
our guards, and escaped with the

06:54:46.919 --> 06:54:48.479
prisoners, and we never even knew they

06:54:48.479 --> 06:54:48.779
were here.

06:54:48.840 --> 06:54:51.119
They'll kill us the moment we step into

06:54:51.119 --> 06:54:51.479
that tunnel.

06:54:51.599 --> 06:54:55.259
The volcano shot another blast of fiery

06:54:55.259 --> 06:54:57.599
rocks into the air, and many of the black

06:54:57.599 --> 06:54:59.520
dragons flung themselves to the ground

06:54:59.520 --> 06:55:00.779
with cries of terror.

06:55:00.900 --> 06:55:05.400
Listen to me, Starfly called, hovering

06:55:05.400 --> 06:55:06.299
above greatness.

06:55:06.360 --> 06:55:08.580
There is a way to escape safely.

06:55:08.639 --> 06:55:11.220
I promise you that the rain wings will

06:55:11.220 --> 06:55:12.060
show you mercy.

06:55:12.119 --> 06:55:14.340
If you accept glory as your queen.

06:55:14.459 --> 06:55:18.240
How can a rain wing lead our tribe?

06:55:18.240 --> 06:55:20.700
shouted a voice that Starflight

06:55:20.700 --> 06:55:22.200
recognized as his sister's.

06:55:22.259 --> 06:55:24.840
Fierce teeth flared her wings and shook

06:55:24.840 --> 06:55:25.799
her talons at him.

06:55:25.860 --> 06:55:28.799
Better than Queen Battle winner can.

06:55:28.919 --> 06:55:31.740
Starflight said, since she's dead.

06:55:31.799 --> 06:55:35.279
Shocked silence fell over the tribe.

06:55:35.400 --> 06:55:37.799
All of them stared at him in disbelief.

06:55:37.860 --> 06:55:41.400
Starflight spotted mastermind, hopping

06:55:41.400 --> 06:55:43.319
agitatedly from one foot to the other

06:55:43.319 --> 06:55:45.119
with his arms full of scrolls.

06:55:45.180 --> 06:55:48.180
And finally, Starflight saw Marsir at the

06:55:48.180 --> 06:55:49.740
back, glowering at him.

06:55:49.799 --> 06:55:53.040
The look on the giant dragon's face gave

06:55:53.040 --> 06:55:55.380
Starflight chills from his wings to the

06:55:55.380 --> 06:55:56.220
tip of his tail.

06:55:56.340 --> 06:55:58.259
But greatness.

06:55:58.319 --> 06:56:00.240
One of the night wings said half

06:56:00.240 --> 06:56:00.720
heartedly.

06:56:00.779 --> 06:56:03.959
I've already agreed to this plan.

06:56:04.020 --> 06:56:04.919
Greatness called.

06:56:04.979 --> 06:56:07.740
It is the only way for our tribe to

06:56:07.740 --> 06:56:07.979
survive.

06:56:08.040 --> 06:56:10.560
Glory will take care of you.

06:56:10.619 --> 06:56:12.540
Starflight said firmly.

06:56:12.599 --> 06:56:15.900
She will be a fair and just queen, and

06:56:15.900 --> 06:56:18.119
you'll be safe in the rainforest instead

06:56:18.119 --> 06:56:18.900
of trapped here.

06:56:18.900 --> 06:56:22.619
The smoke had gotten so dense that it was

06:56:22.619 --> 06:56:24.060
getting hard to see the dragons in front

06:56:24.060 --> 06:56:24.360
of him.

06:56:24.419 --> 06:56:28.080
Fine gray ash coated all their scales and

06:56:28.080 --> 06:56:30.779
made the sand slick beneath their claws.

06:56:30.840 --> 06:56:32.580
The volcano rumbled ominously.

06:56:32.639 --> 06:56:36.720
I'll do it, mighty Claus said from the

06:56:36.720 --> 06:56:37.439
front of the crowd.

06:56:37.500 --> 06:56:39.599
It has to be better than this.

06:56:39.720 --> 06:56:42.720
How do we know they won't kill us all?

06:56:42.720 --> 06:56:44.220
asked another dragon.

06:56:44.340 --> 06:56:47.700
I trust her, said greatness.

06:56:47.819 --> 06:56:50.639
And guess what really will kill you all?

06:56:50.759 --> 06:56:52.500
Fate speaker added, pointing.

06:56:52.560 --> 06:56:54.119
That volcano.

06:56:54.180 --> 06:56:56.099
So come on, let's get out of here.

06:56:56.159 --> 06:56:58.020
All hail queen glory.

06:56:58.139 --> 06:57:00.599
She took to the sky, flying toward the

06:57:00.599 --> 06:57:01.020
tunnel.

06:57:01.080 --> 06:57:05.400
Queen Glory, shouted mighty Claus, leaping

06:57:05.400 --> 06:57:05.759
into the air.

06:57:05.819 --> 06:57:09.720
Queen Glory, shouted another dragon, and

06:57:09.720 --> 06:57:10.799
then another and another.

06:57:10.860 --> 06:57:13.500
Starflight hoped that glory could hear

06:57:13.500 --> 06:57:13.740
them.

06:57:13.799 --> 06:57:16.680
This had to be the strangest thing that

06:57:16.680 --> 06:57:17.880
had ever happened to her.

06:57:17.939 --> 06:57:20.279
The tribe that was always supposed to be

06:57:20.279 --> 06:57:23.340
so superior, now bowing down to the most

06:57:23.340 --> 06:57:25.200
useless of the dragonettes.

06:57:25.259 --> 06:57:28.500
He darted ahead of them to the ledge, and

06:57:28.500 --> 06:57:29.939
found that their rain wings were gone.

06:57:30.000 --> 06:57:32.939
In their place were clay, tsunami, and

06:57:32.939 --> 06:57:35.279
sunny, and he felt himself breathe a

06:57:35.279 --> 06:57:36.360
little deeper when he saw them.

06:57:36.419 --> 06:57:38.700
I hope you know what you're doing.

06:57:38.759 --> 06:57:41.159
Tsunami said to Starflight as he landed

06:57:41.159 --> 06:57:41.639
beside her.

06:57:41.759 --> 06:57:43.740
This is a terrible plan.

06:57:43.799 --> 06:57:45.000
Night Wings can't be trusted.

06:57:45.060 --> 06:57:47.340
I think it's brilliant.

06:57:47.400 --> 06:57:48.840
Sonny said warmly.

06:57:48.900 --> 06:57:50.639
I think you're brilliant.

06:57:50.700 --> 06:57:52.740
I think it's the best idea in the world.

06:57:52.799 --> 06:57:55.860
Starflide hadn't even thought about what

06:57:55.860 --> 06:57:57.119
Sonny would think of his idea.

06:57:57.180 --> 06:57:58.439
For once.

06:57:58.500 --> 06:58:01.680
He gave her a shy smile, pleased that he

06:58:01.680 --> 06:58:03.419
had accidentally done something she was

06:58:03.419 --> 06:58:04.139
so excited about.

06:58:04.200 --> 06:58:08.819
We'd better hurry, Clay said, glancing up

06:58:08.819 --> 06:58:10.439
at the mountain, which was spitting

06:58:10.439 --> 06:58:12.299
bright orange sparks into the sky.

06:58:12.360 --> 06:58:14.939
Come on, quickly.

06:58:15.000 --> 06:58:17.279
He called to the approaching night wings

06:58:17.279 --> 06:58:18.599
holding out his talons.

06:58:18.720 --> 06:58:21.599
Mighty Claus was the 1st to land on the

06:58:21.599 --> 06:58:22.139
ledge.

06:58:22.259 --> 06:58:26.400
Queen Glory, he cried, charging past them

06:58:26.400 --> 06:58:26.939
down the tunnel.

06:58:27.000 --> 06:58:29.700
Starflight followed far enough to see the

06:58:29.700 --> 06:58:31.259
dragonette leap into the hole and

06:58:31.259 --> 06:58:31.680
disappear.

06:58:31.740 --> 06:58:35.459
Greatness was next, moving just as fast.

06:58:35.520 --> 06:58:38.700
She paused briefly beside Starflight, her

06:58:38.700 --> 06:58:40.860
wings filling the tunnel, her eyes

06:58:40.860 --> 06:58:42.659
darting anxiously back toward the

06:58:42.659 --> 06:58:43.799
smoldering volcano.

06:58:43.860 --> 06:58:47.340
I'm so glad I won't ever have to be queen

06:58:47.340 --> 06:58:49.740
she whispered to him. then hurried off.

06:58:49.799 --> 06:58:53.220
Escaping ahead of the rest of her tribe.

06:58:53.279 --> 06:58:56.279
Starfly thought, instead of waiting to

06:58:56.279 --> 06:58:57.479
make sure everyone else gets away

06:58:57.479 --> 06:58:57.959
safely.

06:58:58.020 --> 06:59:01.319
The night wings should all be glad she

06:59:01.319 --> 06:59:02.400
won't ever be their queen.

06:59:02.459 --> 06:59:05.939
He stepped back as a flood of night wings

06:59:05.939 --> 06:59:06.720
started coming through.

06:59:06.779 --> 06:59:10.080
To our new queen, he heard a few of them

06:59:10.080 --> 06:59:10.560
cry.

06:59:10.619 --> 06:59:12.180
Queen Glory.

06:59:12.240 --> 06:59:15.779
This is so wrong, somebody muttered.

06:59:15.900 --> 06:59:18.479
Think of all the food, said someone

06:59:18.479 --> 06:59:18.900
else.

06:59:18.959 --> 06:59:22.020
And the smell of the rainforest, have you

06:59:22.020 --> 06:59:22.439
been there?

06:59:22.439 --> 06:59:23.700
said another.

06:59:23.759 --> 06:59:24.540
It's amazing.

06:59:24.659 --> 06:59:27.060
Like the air itself is full of water and

06:59:27.060 --> 06:59:27.479
light.

06:59:27.540 --> 06:59:31.439
You'll finally get to try a coconut, one

06:59:31.439 --> 06:59:33.000
dragon said to another as they went by.

06:59:33.060 --> 06:59:35.220
Real trees.

06:59:35.340 --> 06:59:37.380
A few of the dragonettes were whispering

06:59:37.380 --> 06:59:37.799
to each other.

06:59:37.860 --> 06:59:41.159
Real sunshine, mangoes every day.

06:59:41.220 --> 06:59:44.159
Starflight pushed back through the tide

06:59:44.159 --> 06:59:46.319
of black dragons until he reached his

06:59:46.319 --> 06:59:47.520
friends on the outer ledge.

06:59:47.580 --> 06:59:50.880
The sky was full of boiling dark clouds

06:59:50.880 --> 06:59:53.700
and gray ash was raining down like snow.

06:59:53.700 --> 06:59:56.759
A new rivulet of lava had snaked out of

06:59:56.759 --> 06:59:58.860
the top of the volcano, and was bubbling

06:59:58.860 --> 06:59:59.520
down one side.

06:59:59.580 --> 07:00:02.639
The earthquakes were coming in waves now

07:00:02.639 --> 07:00:05.819
and getting stronger, like a giant dragon

07:00:05.819 --> 07:00:07.259
stamping its way toward them across the

07:00:07.259 --> 07:00:07.560
ocean.

07:00:07.619 --> 07:00:11.159
We're making all of them say Queen Glory

07:00:11.159 --> 07:00:13.500
on their way past, tsunami said to

07:00:13.500 --> 07:00:15.599
Starflight, grabbing one Nightwing's

07:00:15.599 --> 07:00:15.900
tale.

07:00:15.959 --> 07:00:17.580
Hey, you, speak up.

07:00:17.639 --> 07:00:21.779
Queen Glory, he grumbled, and Starflight

07:00:21.779 --> 07:00:24.180
recognized Strong Wings, his father's

07:00:24.180 --> 07:00:25.500
burly lab assistant.

07:00:25.560 --> 07:00:29.220
Once more, like you mean it. tsunami

07:00:29.220 --> 07:00:31.200
prodded, or you can discuss it with a

07:00:31.200 --> 07:00:31.979
volcano up there.

07:00:32.040 --> 07:00:34.919
The volcano obligingly growled.

07:00:34.979 --> 07:00:36.959
Queen glory.

07:00:37.020 --> 07:00:39.119
Strong wings blurted loudly.

07:00:39.180 --> 07:00:42.599
Better, tsunami said, letting him go.

07:00:42.659 --> 07:00:45.180
Starflight was startled to see one brown

07:00:45.180 --> 07:00:46.860
dragon approaching in the middle of all

07:00:46.860 --> 07:00:48.959
the black, and for a moment he thought it

07:00:48.959 --> 07:00:51.119
was clay, but clay was right next to

07:00:51.119 --> 07:00:51.900
him.

07:00:51.959 --> 07:00:54.779
Then, with a huge stab of guilt, he

07:00:54.779 --> 07:00:57.000
remembered Ocher, who had gone off to

07:00:57.000 --> 07:00:59.159
hunt earlier that morning, which felt

07:00:59.159 --> 07:01:00.419
like weeks and weeks ago.

07:01:00.479 --> 07:01:04.080
I might have left him here, I didn't even

07:01:04.080 --> 07:01:04.919
think to look for him.

07:01:04.979 --> 07:01:07.319
Oh.

07:01:07.380 --> 07:01:11.099
Hey, Ogre said, flapping onto the ledge

07:01:11.099 --> 07:01:12.540
and bobbing his head at Starflight.

07:01:12.599 --> 07:01:17.459
So, I'm not sure what's happening, but it

07:01:17.459 --> 07:01:20.580
seems like everyone's leaving in kind of

07:01:20.580 --> 07:01:23.340
a hurry, and someone said something about

07:01:23.340 --> 07:01:24.540
bananas this way.

07:01:24.659 --> 07:01:27.720
Just follow the others into the tunnel

07:01:27.720 --> 07:01:28.919
Starflight said.

07:01:28.979 --> 07:01:30.599
We'll explain everything later.

07:01:30.659 --> 07:01:32.159
Sure.

07:01:32.220 --> 07:01:34.799
All right, Ogre said.

07:01:34.860 --> 07:01:37.139
In a moment, he'd disappeared in the

07:01:37.139 --> 07:01:38.580
direction of the rainforest as well.

07:01:38.639 --> 07:01:40.680
Star flight.

07:01:40.740 --> 07:01:43.799
This dragon wanted to talk to you, Clay

07:01:43.799 --> 07:01:45.900
said, tugging Starfly aside.

07:01:45.959 --> 07:01:50.220
Oh, Starflight said, meeting his father's

07:01:50.220 --> 07:01:50.580
eyes.

07:01:50.639 --> 07:01:53.459
Clay, this is mastermind.

07:01:53.520 --> 07:01:55.439
My, my father.

07:01:55.500 --> 07:01:58.860
The thin black dragon still had several

07:01:58.860 --> 07:02:01.680
scrolls clutched to his chest, and he was

07:02:01.680 --> 07:02:03.240
fidgeting with his claws anxiously.

07:02:03.299 --> 07:02:06.240
He tried to reach for Starflight's talons

07:02:06.240 --> 07:02:08.819
dropped a few scrolls, gathered them up

07:02:08.819 --> 07:02:09.659
again, and blurted.

07:02:09.779 --> 07:02:12.540
It occurred to me at this rather

07:02:12.540 --> 07:02:15.360
inopportune juncture, that how new hosts

07:02:15.360 --> 07:02:18.180
may very well er hate me.

07:02:18.299 --> 07:02:19.439
What do you think?

07:02:19.500 --> 07:02:21.599
Should I be concerned?

07:02:21.659 --> 07:02:23.639
Will they really let me live there?

07:02:23.700 --> 07:02:25.680
After everything.

07:02:25.740 --> 07:02:28.860
I'm afraid they might have some

07:02:28.860 --> 07:02:29.520
grievances.

07:02:29.580 --> 07:02:32.939
Starflight sensed that his father wanted

07:02:32.939 --> 07:02:35.580
a reassuring lie, but it wasn't about to

07:02:35.580 --> 07:02:35.939
give him one.

07:02:36.000 --> 07:02:38.580
They probably do hate you.

07:02:38.639 --> 07:02:39.659
He said.

07:02:39.779 --> 07:02:42.419
I think they should, don't you?

07:02:42.479 --> 07:02:46.680
But, mastermind fretted, twisting a

07:02:46.680 --> 07:02:47.880
scroll between his claws.

07:02:47.939 --> 07:02:51.779
But, but science, and my orders, and

07:02:51.779 --> 07:02:55.380
Don't make excuses, Starflight said.

07:02:55.439 --> 07:02:58.439
When you get there, tell the queen you're

07:02:58.439 --> 07:03:00.599
sorry, and accept whatever punishment she

07:03:00.599 --> 07:03:00.959
gives you.

07:03:01.020 --> 07:03:02.939
That's my advice.

07:03:03.000 --> 07:03:05.759
Or don't come at all.

07:03:05.819 --> 07:03:07.979
Tsunami chimed in from behind him.

07:03:08.040 --> 07:03:10.380
Take your chances on the ocean instead.

07:03:10.439 --> 07:03:12.180
She nodded out to sea.

07:03:12.299 --> 07:03:15.360
Mastermind flicked his tail with a

07:03:15.360 --> 07:03:17.340
worried expression, watching the night

07:03:17.340 --> 07:03:20.159
wings pour past them into the cave, faster

07:03:20.159 --> 07:03:22.979
and faster, as the volcano's rumbles grew

07:03:22.979 --> 07:03:24.840
ever more ominous and closer together.

07:03:24.900 --> 07:03:29.520
I'll apologize, he said with a deep

07:03:29.520 --> 07:03:30.000
breath.

07:03:30.060 --> 07:03:32.340
To our new queen.

07:03:32.400 --> 07:03:33.540
He added.

07:03:33.599 --> 07:03:35.759
All right, go on.

07:03:35.819 --> 07:03:37.680
Tsunami said, stepping back.

07:03:37.740 --> 07:03:39.540
Take this with you.

07:03:39.659 --> 07:03:43.020
Starflight interjected, realizing he

07:03:43.020 --> 07:03:44.700
still had the map with all the scavenger

07:03:44.700 --> 07:03:45.299
dens on it.

07:03:45.360 --> 07:03:47.880
He tucked the folded paper in among the

07:03:47.880 --> 07:03:50.159
scrolls in his father's arms, and

07:03:50.159 --> 07:03:52.139
mastermind hurried into the tunnel with

07:03:52.139 --> 07:03:53.520
them all pressed to his chest.

07:03:53.580 --> 07:03:55.680
Just like you.

07:03:55.740 --> 07:03:58.560
When we had to escape the mountain, Sonny

07:03:58.560 --> 07:04:01.740
said, bumping Starflight side, trying to

07:04:01.740 --> 07:04:02.880
take all the scrolls.

07:04:02.939 --> 07:04:06.000
I hope we don't have anything else in

07:04:06.000 --> 07:04:06.299
common.

07:04:06.360 --> 07:04:09.180
Starflight said, with a flick of his

07:04:09.180 --> 07:04:09.419
tail.

07:04:09.479 --> 07:04:12.659
Don't give up on him yet, Sonny said.

07:04:12.720 --> 07:04:15.419
Starfly thought she must be the only

07:04:15.419 --> 07:04:17.819
dragon in the world who'd be willing to

07:04:17.819 --> 07:04:19.500
forgive what mastermind had done.

07:04:19.560 --> 07:04:22.919
Guys, tsunami said quietly.

07:04:22.979 --> 07:04:25.319
Look who the last night wing is.

07:04:25.380 --> 07:04:28.560
Starflight turned, already knowing the

07:04:28.560 --> 07:04:28.860
answer.

07:04:28.919 --> 07:04:32.159
The last few night wings hurried by

07:04:32.159 --> 07:04:33.959
blurting, The new queen.

07:04:34.020 --> 07:04:36.720
Queen Glory, as they ducked into the

07:04:36.720 --> 07:04:39.419
tunnel, and then the 4 dragonettes were

07:04:39.419 --> 07:04:42.360
left standing on the ledge, facing Morrow

07:04:42.360 --> 07:04:43.200
Seer as he landed.

07:04:43.259 --> 07:04:47.159
He loomed over them, terrifying and

07:04:47.159 --> 07:04:50.220
menacing and furious, looking exactly as

07:04:50.220 --> 07:04:51.959
he had when they 1st met him under the

07:04:51.959 --> 07:04:54.119
mountain, only a few weeks ago.

07:04:54.180 --> 07:04:58.259
Night Wings are superior to every other

07:04:58.259 --> 07:04:58.740
tribe.

07:04:58.799 --> 07:05:01.740
Starflight remembered him saying in their

07:05:01.740 --> 07:05:02.279
secret meeting.

07:05:02.400 --> 07:05:05.819
You have to act like a leader to be

07:05:05.819 --> 07:05:06.540
treated like one.

07:05:06.599 --> 07:05:09.659
Don't let anyone see your weaknesses.

07:05:09.720 --> 07:05:13.680
Don't have any weaknesses.

07:05:13.740 --> 07:05:16.860
All his life.

07:05:16.919 --> 07:05:18.360
Starflight had often felt like he was

07:05:18.360 --> 07:05:19.619
nothing but weaknesses.

07:05:19.680 --> 07:05:22.919
But after everything he'd done today, He

07:05:22.919 --> 07:05:24.599
was starting to think maybe he wasn't so

07:05:24.599 --> 07:05:27.720
useless after all, powers or no powers.

07:05:27.720 --> 07:05:31.259
This will never work.

07:05:31.319 --> 07:05:33.959
Maro seer growled down at them.

07:05:34.020 --> 07:05:37.200
Night Wings will never bow to a dragon

07:05:37.200 --> 07:05:40.020
from another tribe, least of all a rain

07:05:40.020 --> 07:05:40.439
wing.

07:05:40.500 --> 07:05:43.919
Once we're safe, we'll turn on you all.

07:05:43.979 --> 07:05:46.500
Then you'll end up back here.

07:05:46.560 --> 07:05:49.799
Tsunami spat, waving her talent at the

07:05:49.799 --> 07:05:51.840
ash covered blackened landscape behind

07:05:51.840 --> 07:05:53.279
him, or dead.

07:05:53.340 --> 07:05:55.319
Either would be fine with me.

07:05:55.380 --> 07:05:57.840
We made you.

07:05:57.900 --> 07:06:00.119
Maro seer snarled.

07:06:00.180 --> 07:06:02.459
You dragonheads are only important

07:06:02.459 --> 07:06:05.040
because of us, and we can destroy you

07:06:05.040 --> 07:06:05.939
just as easily.

07:06:06.000 --> 07:06:09.299
No, you can't, Sonny spoke up.

07:06:09.360 --> 07:06:12.119
We have a prophecy to fulfill, and

07:06:12.119 --> 07:06:13.500
there's nothing you can do to stop it

07:06:13.500 --> 07:06:14.459
from happening.

07:06:14.520 --> 07:06:16.560
Morosir barked a laugh.

07:06:16.619 --> 07:06:19.020
Stop it. he said.

07:06:19.080 --> 07:06:21.479
I've been trying to make it happen for

07:06:21.479 --> 07:06:22.500
almost 10 years.

07:06:22.560 --> 07:06:25.319
Prophecies don't work like that.

07:06:25.380 --> 07:06:26.880
Sonny insisted.

07:06:26.939 --> 07:06:28.919
You can't make them happen the way you

07:06:28.919 --> 07:06:29.279
want.

07:06:29.279 --> 07:06:31.860
Whatever's going to happen will happen.

07:06:31.919 --> 07:06:34.259
That's the whole point of destiny.

07:06:34.319 --> 07:06:37.919
The volcano shot a plume of lava into the

07:06:37.919 --> 07:06:40.080
air, and the ground shook hard enough

07:06:40.080 --> 07:06:42.240
that all the dragonettes had to clutch

07:06:42.240 --> 07:06:43.560
the rock walls to stay upright.

07:06:43.619 --> 07:06:46.200
On the contrary.

07:06:46.319 --> 07:06:49.740
I certainly can make my prophecy happen

07:06:49.740 --> 07:06:50.520
however I want.

07:06:50.580 --> 07:06:53.159
Marasier said silkily.

07:06:53.220 --> 07:06:56.459
Considering, I'm the one who made it up

07:06:56.459 --> 07:06:57.299
in the 1st place.
11989
07:06:57,419 --> 07:07:02,400	Chapter 28.

07:07:02.639 --> 07:07:06.000
The earth began to shake without stopping

07:07:06.000 --> 07:07:08.400
a continuous tremor that jarred

07:07:08.400 --> 07:07:10.680
Starflight's teeth in his head, and made

07:07:10.680 --> 07:07:12.360
him feel as though the ledge was about to

07:07:12.360 --> 07:07:13.259
drop out from under him.

07:07:13.319 --> 07:07:16.740
The volcano growled again, and another

07:07:16.740 --> 07:07:19.319
fountain of lava shot over the side, and

07:07:19.319 --> 07:07:21.119
started slithering down the craggy

07:07:21.119 --> 07:07:21.419
slope.

07:07:21.479 --> 07:07:25.139
Maro Seer's face was lit by the orange

07:07:25.139 --> 07:07:28.500
glow of the volcano, cruelty etched into

07:07:28.500 --> 07:07:29.759
every line of his snout.

07:07:29.819 --> 07:07:31.740
You what?

07:07:31.860 --> 07:07:33.060
Tsunami said.

07:07:33.119 --> 07:07:35.819
The prophecy isn't real.

07:07:35.880 --> 07:07:38.520
The words didn't make sense in

07:07:38.520 --> 07:07:39.479
Starflight's head.

07:07:39.540 --> 07:07:41.880
He couldn't fit them into the way the

07:07:41.880 --> 07:07:44.159
world worked, the way his world had

07:07:44.159 --> 07:07:44.880
always worked.

07:07:44.939 --> 07:07:48.779
The dragonette prophecy isn't real.

07:07:48.840 --> 07:07:52.560
That's not true, Sonny cried.

07:07:52.619 --> 07:07:54.599
You're just saying that to be awful.

07:07:54.720 --> 07:07:58.319
The volcano let out a roar, like 20

07:07:58.319 --> 07:08:00.479
dragons having their tails stepped on at

07:08:00.479 --> 07:08:00.720
once.

07:08:00.779 --> 07:08:03.720
Oh, it's completely true.

07:08:03.779 --> 07:08:06.000
Marosi or growled.

07:08:06.060 --> 07:08:08.819
Queen Battle Winner and I wrote it

07:08:08.819 --> 07:08:11.040
together after the last eruption

07:08:11.040 --> 07:08:12.540
destroyed part of the fortress.

07:08:12.599 --> 07:08:16.139
We knew we'd need a new home soon, and

07:08:16.139 --> 07:08:17.939
the prophecy was our plan to get it.

07:08:18.000 --> 07:08:19.860
How?

07:08:19.919 --> 07:08:22.799
Starfight asked, running the prophecy

07:08:22.799 --> 07:08:23.400
through his mind.

07:08:23.459 --> 07:08:26.159
What does the prophecy have to do with

07:08:26.159 --> 07:08:27.419
where the night wings live?

07:08:27.479 --> 07:08:31.319
The idea was that we would control the

07:08:31.319 --> 07:08:32.220
dragonettes.

07:08:32.279 --> 07:08:36.060
Marosier said, by including a night wing

07:08:36.060 --> 07:08:37.979
who naturally would be the leader of the

07:08:37.979 --> 07:08:38.220
group.

07:08:38.279 --> 07:08:42.240
You're abysmal failure in that department

07:08:42.240 --> 07:08:44.400
was our 1st problem.

07:08:44.459 --> 07:08:48.000
Then we'd choose a sand wing queen.

07:08:48.060 --> 07:08:50.759
And eventually the night wings would join

07:08:50.759 --> 07:08:51.240
the war.

07:08:51.360 --> 07:08:54.360
With our strength in numbers tipping the

07:08:54.360 --> 07:08:54.779
balance.

07:08:54.840 --> 07:08:57.599
So our ally would be sure to win.

07:08:57.720 --> 07:09:02.459
And then your ally, whoever you picked

07:09:02.459 --> 07:09:04.619
would help you take over the rainforest.

07:09:04.680 --> 07:09:07.259
Starflight puzzled out.

07:09:07.319 --> 07:09:08.759
It's all about you.

07:09:08.819 --> 07:09:11.340
But not in a way that anyone would

07:09:11.340 --> 07:09:11.700
notice.

07:09:11.759 --> 07:09:15.000
Darkness will rise to bring the light.

07:09:15.119 --> 07:09:16.979
That's the night wings.

07:09:17.099 --> 07:09:19.080
Exactly.

07:09:19.139 --> 07:09:21.959
The only really important part of the

07:09:21.959 --> 07:09:22.680
prophecy.

07:09:22.740 --> 07:09:25.680
We couldn't be too obvious about it, said

07:09:25.680 --> 07:09:26.580
Maro Seer.

07:09:26.639 --> 07:09:29.279
Behind him, dark smoke was pouring out of

07:09:29.279 --> 07:09:31.020
the volcano at an alarming rate.

07:09:31.080 --> 07:09:33.060
The rest of it.

07:09:33.119 --> 07:09:35.340
Smoke and mirrors.

07:09:35.400 --> 07:09:40.020
No, Sonny almost shouted, making the rest

07:09:40.020 --> 07:09:40.560
of them jump.

07:09:40.619 --> 07:09:42.779
The prophecy is real.

07:09:42.840 --> 07:09:46.139
We were born to end the fight to end the

07:09:46.139 --> 07:09:47.159
war and save everyone.

07:09:47.220 --> 07:09:51.959
Afraid not, Moros here said nastily.

07:09:52.020 --> 07:09:54.479
You'll just as ordinary as any other

07:09:54.479 --> 07:09:55.020
dragon.

07:09:55.080 --> 07:09:58.080
Wow. said Clay.

07:09:58.200 --> 07:10:01.500
No wonder I've always felt ordinary.

07:10:01.560 --> 07:10:03.659
But you're not.

07:10:03.720 --> 07:10:07.740
You're not ordinary, Sonny said, her

07:10:07.740 --> 07:10:08.819
voice full of tears.

07:10:08.880 --> 07:10:11.340
Star Light had never seen her so upset.

07:10:11.400 --> 07:10:14.279
He took a step toward her, reaching out

07:10:14.279 --> 07:10:16.439
with his wings, but she shoved him away.

07:10:16.500 --> 07:10:19.259
What about the red mud wing egg?

07:10:19.319 --> 07:10:21.840
What about my egg all alone in the

07:10:21.840 --> 07:10:22.139
desert?

07:10:22.200 --> 07:10:25.919
There are scientific passions to things

07:10:25.919 --> 07:10:28.619
like the appearance of blood eggs, said

07:10:28.619 --> 07:10:29.459
Morrow Seer.

07:10:29.520 --> 07:10:32.340
We study them, and use them in our

07:10:32.340 --> 07:10:34.439
prophecies, to impress our less

07:10:34.439 --> 07:10:35.880
scientific inferiors.

07:10:35.939 --> 07:10:38.340
As for the sand wing egg.

07:10:38.400 --> 07:10:40.319
We planned to set that up.

07:10:40.439 --> 07:10:43.740
But as it happened, we got a tip that

07:10:43.740 --> 07:10:44.700
yours was there already.

07:10:44.759 --> 07:10:47.159
A coincidence.

07:10:47.220 --> 07:10:49.319
No, it wasn't.

07:10:49.380 --> 07:10:52.680
It was fate, Sonny hiccuped.

07:10:52.740 --> 07:10:56.279
On the one talent, you are the worst

07:10:56.279 --> 07:10:58.680
tsunami said tomorrow, seer.

07:10:58.740 --> 07:11:02.099
But on the other, Sonny, think about what

07:11:02.099 --> 07:11:02.639
this means.

07:11:02.700 --> 07:11:04.619
We can live our own lives.

07:11:04.680 --> 07:11:07.139
We don't have to follow some plan that

07:11:07.139 --> 07:11:08.279
the stars laid out for us.

07:11:08.340 --> 07:11:10.139
We're free.

07:11:10.200 --> 07:11:14.520
But I want to stop the war, Sonny cried.

07:11:14.580 --> 07:11:16.560
All those dragons out there.

07:11:16.619 --> 07:11:18.599
They believe in the prophecy.

07:11:18.720 --> 07:11:20.040
They believe in us.

07:11:20.099 --> 07:11:22.979
If we give up, who will save them?

07:11:23.040 --> 07:11:26.819
No one. said Maro Seer.

07:11:26.880 --> 07:11:29.340
Now there's no point.

07:11:29.400 --> 07:11:30.959
The night wings are already in the

07:11:30.959 --> 07:11:31.680
rainforest.

07:11:31.740 --> 07:11:34.380
So we have no reason to join the war.

07:11:34.439 --> 07:11:36.540
It'll drag on endlessly.

07:11:36.599 --> 07:11:39.180
And more dragons will die every day

07:11:39.180 --> 07:11:42.900
probably for generations, all of them

07:11:42.900 --> 07:11:44.759
wondering what happened to the amazing

07:11:44.759 --> 07:11:47.279
dragonettes who were supposed to save

07:11:47.279 --> 07:11:49.860
them, but obviously failed.

07:11:49.919 --> 07:11:54.840
Sonny let out a furious sob, then whirled

07:11:54.840 --> 07:11:57.360
pushed past Starflight and fled up the

07:11:57.360 --> 07:11:59.639
tunnel, disappearing through the hole to

07:11:59.639 --> 07:12:00.360
the rainforest.

07:12:00.479 --> 07:12:03.900
Marosier took a step as if to follow her

07:12:03.900 --> 07:12:05.759
and Starflight jumped into his way.

07:12:05.819 --> 07:12:09.419
You can't come to the rainforest with us

07:12:09.419 --> 07:12:10.619
he said.

07:12:10.680 --> 07:12:13.139
His voice shaking as badly as the earth

07:12:13.139 --> 07:12:14.099
below his claws.

07:12:14.220 --> 07:12:17.400
Clay and tsunami closed rank on either

07:12:17.400 --> 07:12:18.000
side of him.

07:12:18.060 --> 07:12:20.639
He's right, tsunami said.

07:12:20.759 --> 07:12:23.400
Even if you pretended to swear allegiance

07:12:23.400 --> 07:12:25.259
to glory, we'd know you were lying.

07:12:25.319 --> 07:12:27.599
At this point, we wouldn't trust you

07:12:27.599 --> 07:12:28.259
about anything.

07:12:28.319 --> 07:12:32.040
You should go, Clay said.

07:12:32.159 --> 07:12:35.520
Fly across the sea, as fast as you can.

07:12:35.580 --> 07:12:38.520
Maybe you'll make it before the volcano

07:12:38.520 --> 07:12:39.360
really explodes.

07:12:39.419 --> 07:12:43.259
Not that we care, tsunami added.

07:12:43.319 --> 07:12:46.560
Maro Seer's expression was incredulous.

07:12:46.619 --> 07:12:49.080
And who's going to stop me?

07:12:49.139 --> 07:12:50.639
The 3 of you.

07:12:50.759 --> 07:12:54.180
Yes, Starflight said.

07:12:54.240 --> 07:12:58.200
And me, said fate speaker's voice from

07:12:58.200 --> 07:12:59.279
behind Starflight.

07:12:59.340 --> 07:13:01.919
He felt her tail brush against his as she

07:13:01.919 --> 07:13:02.759
slid up next to him.

07:13:02.819 --> 07:13:06.240
The giant Nightwing snorted, as if that

07:13:06.240 --> 07:13:07.439
only made things more amusing.

07:13:07.560 --> 07:13:11.939
Is all the dragonets I want dead anyway

07:13:11.939 --> 07:13:15.419
he said, in one convenient place.

07:13:15.479 --> 07:13:18.959
He opened his mouth, hissing up a fiery

07:13:18.959 --> 07:13:22.439
breath, and then the volcano exploded.

07:13:22.500 --> 07:13:25.439
It was like nothing Starflight had ever

07:13:25.439 --> 07:13:26.580
seen or imagined.

07:13:26.639 --> 07:13:29.400
It was like the earth turned inside out

07:13:29.400 --> 07:13:31.740
collapsing the top of the mountain and

07:13:31.740 --> 07:13:33.959
shooting a vast billowing cloud of

07:13:33.959 --> 07:13:37.259
flaming smoke into the air, which rose to

07:13:37.259 --> 07:13:39.900
the height of a 100 dragons, and then

07:13:39.900 --> 07:13:43.200
fell, sending all that fire and rock and

07:13:43.200 --> 07:13:46.080
ash and death, charging down the slope

07:13:46.080 --> 07:13:48.119
toward them faster than any dragon could

07:13:48.119 --> 07:13:48.299
fly.

07:13:48.419 --> 07:13:50.040
Run!

07:13:50.099 --> 07:13:53.159
Starfly yelled, turning and shoving fate

07:13:53.159 --> 07:13:54.060
speaker in front of him.

07:13:54.119 --> 07:13:56.520
They tore down the tunnel with tsunami

07:13:56.520 --> 07:13:58.919
right on his tail and clay behind her.

07:13:59.159 --> 07:14:01.139
The heavy footsteps of Marosea are

07:14:01.139 --> 07:14:03.119
thumped after them, but there was no time

07:14:03.119 --> 07:14:04.020
left to confront him.

07:14:04.080 --> 07:14:06.900
Fate speaker dove into the whole first.

07:14:06.959 --> 07:14:09.240
Starflight found himself turning and

07:14:09.240 --> 07:14:11.520
grabbing tsunami, shoving her in next.

07:14:11.639 --> 07:14:14.459
And so he was facing the cave entrance

07:14:14.459 --> 07:14:16.799
and he saw the fireball come barreling at

07:14:16.799 --> 07:14:19.259
them, filling the tunnel wall to wall

07:14:19.259 --> 07:14:20.819
with bright orange flames.

07:14:20.880 --> 07:14:24.180
Moro Seer's dark figure was silhouetted

07:14:24.180 --> 07:14:26.700
against the fire for a brief, horribly

07:14:26.700 --> 07:14:27.419
bright moment.

07:14:27.479 --> 07:14:30.720
And then suddenly, the huge night wing

07:14:30.720 --> 07:14:33.180
was gone, swallowed by the volcanic

07:14:33.180 --> 07:14:33.900
explosion.

07:14:33.959 --> 07:14:37.919
A 2nd later, Starflights scales were

07:14:37.919 --> 07:14:40.380
blasted with heat, as if he'd fallen into

07:14:40.380 --> 07:14:43.740
lava, a stab of blazing agony went

07:14:43.740 --> 07:14:45.779
through both eyes, and he closed them

07:14:45.779 --> 07:14:46.799
with a howl of pain.

07:14:46.860 --> 07:14:49.680
And then he felt wings wrap around him

07:14:49.680 --> 07:14:52.020
and he realized it was clay.

07:14:52.080 --> 07:14:54.599
Clay in his fireproof scales.

07:14:54.659 --> 07:14:57.959
The mud wing lifted him, shielding him

07:14:57.959 --> 07:14:59.939
with his whole body, and shot into the

07:14:59.939 --> 07:15:00.540
tunnel.

07:15:00.599 --> 07:15:03.000
Will the fire follow us?

07:15:03.060 --> 07:15:05.700
Starflight wondered dazedly.

07:15:05.759 --> 07:15:08.340
How does the animus magic work?

07:15:08.400 --> 07:15:11.400
Will we cross over to the rainforest side

07:15:11.400 --> 07:15:13.500
halfway through and be safe?

07:15:13.560 --> 07:15:15.900
Or can it reach all the way?

07:15:15.959 --> 07:15:20.040
Rain pattered down on his scales, sizzling

07:15:20.040 --> 07:15:22.560
softly, and he felt claws pull him from

07:15:22.560 --> 07:15:24.540
the tunnel, and lie him down on wet

07:15:24.540 --> 07:15:25.020
moss.

07:15:25.080 --> 07:15:28.080
Cool wet leaves pressed against his face

07:15:28.080 --> 07:15:30.779
and he heard the murmur of 100s of dragon

07:15:30.779 --> 07:15:33.060
voices, against a background of

07:15:33.060 --> 07:15:36.119
rainforest night sounds, sloths

07:15:36.119 --> 07:15:39.000
chirruping, insects and frogs singing

07:15:39.000 --> 07:15:39.959
their night songs.

07:15:40.020 --> 07:15:43.259
And among the talons, he was sure he felt

07:15:43.259 --> 07:15:44.040
sunnies.

07:15:44.099 --> 07:15:46.799
He felt the warmth of her scales that

07:15:46.799 --> 07:15:48.840
he'd know anywhere, even with his eyes

07:15:48.840 --> 07:15:49.560
closed.

07:15:49.619 --> 07:15:52.380
Or blind.

07:15:52.439 --> 07:15:55.259
And he felt her pressed close to him for

07:15:55.259 --> 07:15:56.279
a moment and whisper.

07:15:56.340 --> 07:15:59.520
But why did it sound like fate speaker's

07:15:59.520 --> 07:15:59.759
voice?

07:15:59.819 --> 07:16:01.979
Starflight?

07:16:02.040 --> 07:16:03.720
You were so brave.

07:16:03.779 --> 07:16:07.560
And then the warmth was gone, and he

07:16:07.560 --> 07:16:08.700
wondered if he'd imagined it.

07:16:08.819 --> 07:16:12.060
And then pain flared all along his body

07:16:12.060 --> 07:16:15.240
and he opened his mouth to scream, but it

07:16:15.240 --> 07:16:15.840
hurt too much.

07:16:15.900 --> 07:16:19.500
Something jabbed him in the neck, and he

07:16:19.500 --> 07:16:22.259
had a moment to think, sleeping dart.

07:16:22.319 --> 07:16:23.639
What a good idea.

07:16:23.759 --> 07:16:25.919
And then everything.

07:16:25.979 --> 07:16:27.479
Everything.

07:16:27.540 --> 07:16:31.560
The pain, the worry, sunny and fate

07:16:31.560 --> 07:16:34.919
speaker, the truth about the prophecy, the

07:16:34.919 --> 07:16:37.740
fear of the volcano, everything faded

07:16:37.740 --> 07:16:40.919
away, and Starflight dropped into

07:16:40.919 --> 07:16:43.200
darkness as black as a night wings

07:16:43.200 --> 07:16:44.040
scales.

07:16:44.279 --> 07:16:48.360
Epilogue.

07:16:48.419 --> 07:16:52.799
Snow was falling thick and fast, and the

07:16:52.799 --> 07:16:55.259
snowflakes spun across the icy ground in

07:16:55.259 --> 07:16:56.099
the freezing wind.

07:16:56.159 --> 07:16:59.040
A sand wing stood huddled by the walls

07:16:59.040 --> 07:17:02.159
outside her fort, wrapped in blankets, and

07:17:02.159 --> 07:17:03.779
trying to breathe fire into the air

07:17:03.779 --> 07:17:04.259
around her.

07:17:04.380 --> 07:17:07.560
Papa, please, can't we go inside?

07:17:07.680 --> 07:17:10.680
She said to the tall white dragon beside

07:17:10.680 --> 07:17:10.919
her.

07:17:10.979 --> 07:17:14.520
No, said Queen Glacier.

07:17:14.639 --> 07:17:17.099
No one can be trusted with this

07:17:17.099 --> 07:17:19.740
information until we make a decision.

07:17:19.799 --> 07:17:22.979
Her arctic blue eyes regarded the ice

07:17:22.979 --> 07:17:25.439
wing guards, who were positioned just out

07:17:25.439 --> 07:17:27.840
of hearing range, watching the skies for

07:17:27.840 --> 07:17:28.139
danger.

07:17:28.200 --> 07:17:31.139
Frost glittered along her wings and

07:17:31.139 --> 07:17:31.680
horns.

07:17:31.740 --> 07:17:34.619
The spikes at the end of her tail were as

07:17:34.619 --> 07:17:36.360
sharp and cold as icicles.

07:17:36.419 --> 07:17:38.700
Blaise sighed.

07:17:38.759 --> 07:17:42.119
You mean, until you make a decision.

07:17:42.240 --> 07:17:46.319
Your input is always welcome.

07:17:46.380 --> 07:17:48.599
Glacier said calmly.

07:17:48.659 --> 07:17:51.419
She knew there was no chance of the sand

07:17:51.419 --> 07:17:53.400
wing disagreeing with the ice wing

07:17:53.400 --> 07:17:53.700
queen.

07:17:53.759 --> 07:17:56.220
My neck hurts.

07:17:56.279 --> 07:17:59.459
Blaise stamped her feet and poked the

07:17:59.459 --> 07:18:00.240
bandage on her neck.

07:18:00.299 --> 07:18:01.680
Ow!

07:18:01.740 --> 07:18:03.360
Do you think it's going to scar?

07:18:03.419 --> 07:18:05.279
I'll be so mad if it scars.

07:18:05.340 --> 07:18:10.319
You're sure about what you heard, Glacier

07:18:10.319 --> 07:18:10.680
asked her.

07:18:10.740 --> 07:18:14.099
The Night Wings have chosen to side with

07:18:14.099 --> 07:18:16.380
a blister, and they're trying to force

07:18:16.380 --> 07:18:17.939
the Dragonettes to choose her as well.

07:18:18.000 --> 07:18:21.840
That's what it sounded like, Blaise said

07:18:21.840 --> 07:18:23.040
but more important?

07:18:23.099 --> 07:18:25.020
That nightwing tried to kill me.

07:18:25.080 --> 07:18:26.759
You're going to kill him, right?

07:18:26.880 --> 07:18:31.080
We're going to kill all of them, if we

07:18:31.080 --> 07:18:32.759
must. said Glacier.

07:18:32.819 --> 07:18:35.819
I have no objection to the idea of wiping

07:18:35.819 --> 07:18:36.599
out the night wings.

07:18:36.659 --> 07:18:38.939
But we should consider what to do about

07:18:38.939 --> 07:18:40.380
the dragonettes of the prophecy.

07:18:40.500 --> 07:18:42.659
They seemed nice.

07:18:42.720 --> 07:18:45.599
Blaise said, rubbing her talons together

07:18:45.599 --> 07:18:46.560
to warm them up.

07:18:46.680 --> 07:18:48.900
Some of them are a little funny looking

07:18:48.900 --> 07:18:51.060
and I still don't understand what that

07:18:51.060 --> 07:18:52.380
rain wing was doing with them.

07:18:52.439 --> 07:18:55.500
Besides, she was a little too pretty.

07:18:55.560 --> 07:18:57.959
I think it's better to be just the right

07:18:57.959 --> 07:18:59.340
amount of pretty, don't you?

07:18:59.400 --> 07:19:01.619
Too pretty is annoying.

07:19:01.680 --> 07:19:06.599
Indeed, said Glacier, barely listening.

07:19:06.659 --> 07:19:09.900
We don't want them telling anyone they've

07:19:09.900 --> 07:19:10.799
chosen blister.

07:19:10.860 --> 07:19:13.979
It would be very demoralizing for our

07:19:13.979 --> 07:19:14.459
dragons.

07:19:14.520 --> 07:19:17.880
But they can't possibly choose her now

07:19:17.880 --> 07:19:18.599
that they've met me.

07:19:18.659 --> 07:19:20.040
Blaze cried.

07:19:20.159 --> 07:19:22.259
Now they know I'm wonderful and would

07:19:22.259 --> 07:19:24.180
make a great queen, they'll definitely

07:19:24.180 --> 07:19:24.779
pick me.

07:19:24.840 --> 07:19:26.819
Hmm.

07:19:26.939 --> 07:19:29.340
Glacier said, non-committally.

07:19:29.400 --> 07:19:31.799
She didn't have quite the same faith in

07:19:31.799 --> 07:19:34.799
Blaze's persuasive abilities, or dazzling

07:19:34.799 --> 07:19:36.180
charisma that Blaze did.

07:19:36.299 --> 07:19:38.939
Her own alliance with Blaise was based

07:19:38.939 --> 07:19:41.099
less on the sand wings potential

07:19:41.099 --> 07:19:43.860
queenliness and more uncertain promises

07:19:43.860 --> 07:19:45.900
of future new territory for the ice

07:19:45.900 --> 07:19:46.380
wings.

07:19:46.439 --> 07:19:48.360
Well.

07:19:48.479 --> 07:19:51.900
Glacier said, just in case they're

07:19:51.900 --> 07:19:52.919
leaning in another direction.

07:19:53.040 --> 07:19:55.439
I think we should make an effort to find

07:19:55.439 --> 07:19:56.939
these dragonettes.

07:19:57.000 --> 07:19:59.159
I'd like to have a chat with them

07:19:59.159 --> 07:19:59.520
myself.

07:19:59.580 --> 07:20:01.560
Fine.

07:20:01.619 --> 07:20:04.680
All right, Blaise said, shivering

07:20:04.680 --> 07:20:05.159
violently.

07:20:05.220 --> 07:20:07.200
I'll tell you everything I know about

07:20:07.200 --> 07:20:09.000
what they looked like and what they said

07:20:09.000 --> 07:20:11.759
but can we please do that inside?

07:20:11.819 --> 07:20:15.540
Glacier nodded thoughtfully, and Blaze

07:20:15.540 --> 07:20:16.259
bolted for the door.

07:20:16.319 --> 07:20:19.080
The ice wing queen was good at putting

07:20:19.080 --> 07:20:21.240
together clues and figuring things out.

07:20:21.299 --> 07:20:24.900
She would find those dragonettes, and she

07:20:24.900 --> 07:20:26.939
really would start by talking to them

07:20:26.939 --> 07:20:28.799
just to see which way they were

07:20:28.799 --> 07:20:29.340
inclined.

07:20:29.459 --> 07:20:33.240
But of course, if it was the wrong way.

07:20:33.299 --> 07:20:37.200
Well, a few dead dragon ants here and

07:20:37.200 --> 07:20:38.939
there would hardly be noticed in a war

07:20:38.939 --> 07:20:39.360
like this.

07:20:39.419 --> 07:20:44.340
A serpentine figure paced in the darkness

07:20:44.340 --> 07:20:45.959
hissing softly.

07:20:46.020 --> 07:20:49.020
Below her mountain ledge, in a hidden

07:20:49.020 --> 07:20:51.479
valley, hints of firelight flickered in

07:20:51.479 --> 07:20:53.819
windows, most of them covered with black

07:20:53.819 --> 07:20:54.299
curtains.

07:20:54.360 --> 07:20:56.880
Blister narrowed her eyes at the

07:20:56.880 --> 07:20:57.779
scavenger den.

07:20:57.840 --> 07:21:00.180
Why did Maru Seer think she would care

07:21:00.180 --> 07:21:02.400
about a rat's nest full of crawling

07:21:02.400 --> 07:21:05.340
squeaking, pale, 2 legged creatures.

07:21:05.400 --> 07:21:06.599
She wasn't hungry.

07:21:06.659 --> 07:21:08.819
She didn't even feel like burning down

07:21:08.819 --> 07:21:10.020
their pathetic little huts.

07:21:10.139 --> 07:21:11.400
She was too angry.

07:21:11.459 --> 07:21:14.939
A whisper of wings on the wind made her

07:21:14.939 --> 07:21:17.700
twist around, tail poised to attack.

07:21:17.759 --> 07:21:21.479
But it wasn't an enemy, and it wasn't

07:21:21.479 --> 07:21:22.380
Maro's ear.

07:21:22.439 --> 07:21:24.599
It was that spineless leader of the

07:21:24.599 --> 07:21:27.779
talons of peace, the sea wing, and he had

07:21:27.779 --> 07:21:28.500
someone with him.

07:21:28.560 --> 07:21:30.360
She squinted as they landed.

07:21:30.419 --> 07:21:34.439
Forgive my lateness, queen blister

07:21:34.439 --> 07:21:36.180
Nautilus said with a bow.

07:21:36.299 --> 07:21:38.819
Where is Marosir?

07:21:38.880 --> 07:21:39.900
She demanded.

07:21:39.959 --> 07:21:43.200
I, I don't know, he stammered.

07:21:43.319 --> 07:21:45.060
I thought he would be here by now.

07:21:45.119 --> 07:21:47.880
I haven't seen him since he took the

07:21:47.880 --> 07:21:49.799
alternate dragonette from the talons of

07:21:49.799 --> 07:21:50.459
Peace Camp.

07:21:50.520 --> 07:21:52.919
But I knew he was supposed to be here to

07:21:52.919 --> 07:21:55.080
meet you tonight, and I had to speak with

07:21:55.080 --> 07:21:55.319
him.

07:21:55.380 --> 07:21:58.020
He squared his shoulders, obviously

07:21:58.020 --> 07:21:59.580
trying to look braver than he felt.

07:21:59.639 --> 07:22:03.119
Well, he's not here.

07:22:03.180 --> 07:22:04.380
Blister spat.

07:22:04.439 --> 07:22:05.340
Who is that?

07:22:05.400 --> 07:22:08.580
Nautilus drew the dragonette forward

07:22:08.580 --> 07:22:10.439
keeping one wing around him.

07:22:10.680 --> 07:22:13.259
It was another sea wing, stunted, and

07:22:13.259 --> 07:22:14.459
green and shivering.

07:22:14.520 --> 07:22:19.259
My son, Nautilus said quietly, touching

07:22:19.259 --> 07:22:20.340
the dragonette's head.

07:22:20.400 --> 07:22:21.779
Squid.

07:22:21.779 --> 07:22:24.779
Morosir left him to die in the mountains

07:22:24.779 --> 07:22:28.439
but by a miracle, one of our spies found

07:22:28.439 --> 07:22:28.860
him first.

07:22:28.979 --> 07:22:32.099
His eyes were cold and glittering in the

07:22:32.099 --> 07:22:33.659
light of the 2 moons that were full

07:22:33.659 --> 07:22:34.080
overhead.

07:22:34.139 --> 07:22:37.139
I hate night wings.

07:22:37.200 --> 07:22:38.580
Squid mumbled.

07:22:38.639 --> 07:22:41.220
I rather hate them too.

07:22:41.279 --> 07:22:42.419
Blister agreed.

07:22:42.479 --> 07:22:44.759
She'd always been irritated by this

07:22:44.759 --> 07:22:46.380
arrangement with Marosir.

07:22:46.439 --> 07:22:49.319
These meetings he called, at his choice

07:22:49.319 --> 07:22:51.840
of time and place, with no way for her to

07:22:51.840 --> 07:22:52.979
contact him in between.

07:22:53.040 --> 07:22:56.040
An alliance with the night wings, and

07:22:56.040 --> 07:22:58.139
control of the prophecy dragonettes

07:22:58.139 --> 07:22:59.700
should make all this annoyance

07:22:59.700 --> 07:23:00.540
worthwhile.

07:23:00.599 --> 07:23:03.299
But so far, she wasn't getting any of

07:23:03.299 --> 07:23:04.560
what she'd been promised.

07:23:04.619 --> 07:23:08.520
Worse yet, it almost seemed as if she was

07:23:08.520 --> 07:23:09.479
losing allies.

07:23:09.540 --> 07:23:12.959
Her small band of sand wings, hidden away

07:23:12.959 --> 07:23:15.599
safely in the Bay of a 1000 scales, were

07:23:15.599 --> 07:23:16.380
loyal, of course.

07:23:16.439 --> 07:23:18.479
She controlled them with careful

07:23:18.479 --> 07:23:21.180
precision, knowing every move they made

07:23:21.180 --> 07:23:22.560
and every thought they had.

07:23:22.619 --> 07:23:25.919
She tricked them all into spying on one

07:23:25.919 --> 07:23:29.159
another, by making each one think he or

07:23:29.159 --> 07:23:31.799
she was in an exclusive elite, who

07:23:31.799 --> 07:23:35.400
reported secretly to her, and any hint of

07:23:35.400 --> 07:23:38.220
insubordination, or weakness, was

07:23:38.220 --> 07:23:39.479
instantly punished with death.

07:23:39.599 --> 07:23:42.900
But the alliance she'd formed years ago

07:23:42.900 --> 07:23:45.060
with the sea wings, had slipped through

07:23:45.060 --> 07:23:46.799
her claws like ice melting.

07:23:46.919 --> 07:23:48.840
After the destruction of the Summer

07:23:48.840 --> 07:23:51.720
Palace, Queen Coral had fled with her

07:23:51.720 --> 07:23:54.779
tribe to their secret underwater home, and

07:23:54.779 --> 07:23:57.599
no one had seen her or any other sea

07:23:57.599 --> 07:23:58.380
wings since.

07:23:58.439 --> 07:24:00.900
Blister had gone to the wrecked summer

07:24:00.900 --> 07:24:03.060
palace almost every day since the attack

07:24:03.060 --> 07:24:04.799
but there were no messages.

07:24:04.860 --> 07:24:07.319
No dragons waiting to tell her what was

07:24:07.319 --> 07:24:10.439
happening, no apologetic scrolls from the

07:24:10.439 --> 07:24:11.340
sea wing queen.

07:24:11.400 --> 07:24:15.419
And if Marosir didn't show up, then what

07:24:15.419 --> 07:24:15.959
would she do?

07:24:16.020 --> 07:24:18.479
She had no idea where the Nightwing

07:24:18.479 --> 07:24:20.700
Island was, no way to send him a

07:24:20.700 --> 07:24:21.180
message.

07:24:21.240 --> 07:24:24.479
In effect, no night wing allies to speak

07:24:24.479 --> 07:24:25.020
of.

07:24:25.080 --> 07:24:27.659
Maybe she did feel like setting a

07:24:27.659 --> 07:24:29.400
scavenger den on fire after all.

07:24:29.459 --> 07:24:32.759
Nautilus sat with his wings wrapped

07:24:32.759 --> 07:24:34.500
around squid, brooding.

07:24:34.560 --> 07:24:37.680
His glow in the dark scales flashed dimly

07:24:37.680 --> 07:24:39.900
as if he were telling his son something

07:24:39.900 --> 07:24:41.759
private, over and over again.

07:24:41.819 --> 07:24:46.860
If Marosir doesn't show up, Blister said

07:24:46.860 --> 07:24:49.200
I have a strong suspicion I know whose

07:24:49.200 --> 07:24:49.860
fault it is.

07:24:49.919 --> 07:24:53.400
The sea wings both looked up, surprised.

07:24:53.459 --> 07:24:55.259
The dragonettes.

07:24:55.380 --> 07:24:56.580
She hissed.

07:24:56.639 --> 07:24:58.979
Not this weakling.

07:24:59.040 --> 07:25:00.299
The originals.

07:25:00.360 --> 07:25:02.580
They've been nothing but trouble since

07:25:02.580 --> 07:25:03.900
they escaped their captors.

07:25:03.959 --> 07:25:06.119
Nautilus winced.

07:25:06.180 --> 07:25:09.720
We called them guardians, he said.

07:25:09.779 --> 07:25:11.220
But you're right.

07:25:11.340 --> 07:25:13.919
Everywhere the dragonets go, they seem to

07:25:13.919 --> 07:25:15.119
leave chaos behind.

07:25:15.240 --> 07:25:18.599
Well, they've caused trouble for the

07:25:18.599 --> 07:25:19.500
wrong dragon.

07:25:19.619 --> 07:25:21.419
Blister snarled.

07:25:21.479 --> 07:25:23.880
She glowered down at the slumbering

07:25:23.880 --> 07:25:26.520
scavenger den, her claws twitching with

07:25:26.520 --> 07:25:27.360
dreams of revenge.

07:25:27.419 --> 07:25:29.220
Wherever they are.

07:25:29.279 --> 07:25:31.080
I will hunt them down.

07:25:31.139 --> 07:25:34.860
I will find them, and then, prophecy or

07:25:34.860 --> 07:25:37.979
no prophecy, I'm going to kill them all.

07:25:38.040 --> 07:25:43.680
The sun was hot. and blistering, beating

07:25:43.680 --> 07:25:46.319
down on the sand around the stronghold, as

07:25:46.319 --> 07:25:48.479
the squadron of sand wings landed in the

07:25:48.479 --> 07:25:49.020
courtyard.

07:25:49.080 --> 07:25:52.139
The smell of the decapitated heads on the

07:25:52.139 --> 07:25:54.000
walls was stronger than usual.

07:25:54.060 --> 07:25:56.400
Burn inhaled deeply.

07:25:56.520 --> 07:25:59.639
She enjoyed the decaying scent, but

07:25:59.639 --> 07:26:02.159
mostly, she enjoyed the unnerved looks on

07:26:02.159 --> 07:26:03.959
her soldiers' faces every time she did

07:26:03.959 --> 07:26:04.500
that.

07:26:04.560 --> 07:26:07.500
A dragon stepped out of the great hall

07:26:07.500 --> 07:26:09.959
darting across the hot stones toward

07:26:09.959 --> 07:26:10.200
her.

07:26:10.259 --> 07:26:12.959
The black diamond patterns on his wings

07:26:12.959 --> 07:26:15.240
always reminded Byrne of blister.

07:26:15.299 --> 07:26:17.700
So it was difficult not to glare at her

07:26:17.700 --> 07:26:19.919
brother every time she saw him, but he

07:26:19.919 --> 07:26:20.400
was used to that.

07:26:20.459 --> 07:26:24.060
I wasn't expecting you until tomorrow

07:26:24.060 --> 07:26:25.259
Smolder said.

07:26:25.319 --> 07:26:27.900
His forked tongue flicked in and out.

07:26:27.959 --> 07:26:30.060
She narrowed her eyes at him and waited.

07:26:30.119 --> 07:26:32.939
After a moment, he remembered and added

07:26:32.939 --> 07:26:34.979
Your majesty.

07:26:35.099 --> 07:26:37.979
I wasn't expecting you until tomorrow

07:26:37.979 --> 07:26:39.540
your majesty.

07:26:39.659 --> 07:26:42.479
She didn't appreciate the hint of sarcasm

07:26:42.479 --> 07:26:44.520
in his voice, but she wouldn't point it

07:26:44.520 --> 07:26:45.659
out in front of her soldiers.

07:26:45.720 --> 07:26:48.840
She'd discuss it with him later, somewhere

07:26:48.840 --> 07:26:51.240
private, where she could dig her claws

07:26:51.240 --> 07:26:53.639
into a scales and get a truly sincere

07:26:53.639 --> 07:26:54.479
apology.

07:26:54.779 --> 07:26:57.000
How is our guest?

07:26:57.060 --> 07:27:00.180
Burne asked, dismissing the soldiers with

07:27:00.180 --> 07:27:01.139
a flick of her tail.

07:27:01.200 --> 07:27:04.860
Still extraordinarily not pleased to be

07:27:04.860 --> 07:27:06.299
here, he said.

07:27:06.360 --> 07:27:09.599
You may want to move her to a more empty

07:27:09.599 --> 07:27:10.200
chamber.

07:27:10.259 --> 07:27:12.540
She's made a bit of a mess of what she

07:27:12.540 --> 07:27:14.040
could reach of your collection.

07:27:14.099 --> 07:27:15.779
Burn hissed.

07:27:15.840 --> 07:27:18.119
Ungrateful cow.

07:27:18.180 --> 07:27:21.119
Any word on the dragonettes?

07:27:21.180 --> 07:27:23.520
he asked, following her into the great

07:27:23.520 --> 07:27:23.880
hall.

07:27:23.939 --> 07:27:27.720
They vanished again, she said.

07:27:27.779 --> 07:27:30.540
Although there's a rumor going around the

07:27:30.540 --> 07:27:32.880
Sky Kingdom, that they are responsible

07:27:32.880 --> 07:27:35.819
for torching the northernmost outpost and

07:27:35.819 --> 07:27:38.880
killing all those Skywing soldiers, as

07:27:38.880 --> 07:27:40.860
some kind of revenge for what Queen

07:27:40.860 --> 07:27:42.000
Scarlet did to them.

07:27:42.060 --> 07:27:45.240
Smolder folded his wings back and looked

07:27:45.240 --> 07:27:45.659
up at her.

07:27:45.720 --> 07:27:47.639
Do you think that's likely?

07:27:47.700 --> 07:27:51.180
I don't know anything about them, she

07:27:51.180 --> 07:27:51.419
said.

07:27:51.479 --> 07:27:54.479
In the arena, they didn't seem fierce

07:27:54.479 --> 07:27:55.259
enough to kill anything.

07:27:55.319 --> 07:27:58.439
But then they attacked Scarlet, so

07:27:58.439 --> 07:28:00.360
they're clearly more dangerous than they

07:28:00.360 --> 07:28:00.540
look.

07:28:00.599 --> 07:28:04.200
She stopped at the long table loaded with

07:28:04.200 --> 07:28:05.639
the food that ran down the center of the

07:28:05.639 --> 07:28:05.880
hall.

07:28:05.939 --> 07:28:08.099
I do know.

07:28:08.159 --> 07:28:12.659
I don't like them, she muttered, and I

07:28:12.659 --> 07:28:15.060
wish I'd gotten my claws on all of their

07:28:15.060 --> 07:28:16.439
eggs before they hatched.

07:28:16.500 --> 07:28:19.979
She snatched up a dead hawk and ripped

07:28:19.979 --> 07:28:22.439
off its head with one bite, imagining

07:28:22.439 --> 07:28:25.139
doing the same to a certain sea wing, or

07:28:25.139 --> 07:28:27.060
that insidious rain wing.

07:28:27.119 --> 07:28:30.180
It's not going well with Ruby.

07:28:30.240 --> 07:28:31.560
Smolder asked.

07:28:31.619 --> 07:28:35.159
The supposed new queen of the sky wings

07:28:35.159 --> 07:28:36.659
is a bore and a nuisance.

07:28:36.720 --> 07:28:38.400
Burns snarled.

07:28:38.459 --> 07:28:41.520
She wants to restore order in the sky

07:28:41.520 --> 07:28:44.159
kingdom, and establish the stability of

07:28:44.159 --> 07:28:47.040
her own throne before engaging in any

07:28:47.040 --> 07:28:48.180
more battles at my side.

07:28:48.240 --> 07:28:50.580
She's even more difficult than her

07:28:50.580 --> 07:28:53.220
annoying mother, and she follows orders

07:28:53.220 --> 07:28:54.599
very poorly, if at all.

07:28:54.659 --> 07:28:57.419
We haven't had a satisfying battle in

07:28:57.419 --> 07:28:57.840
weeks.

07:28:57.900 --> 07:29:00.240
I'm considering getting rid of her.

07:29:00.299 --> 07:29:02.819
Sounds frustrating.

07:29:02.880 --> 07:29:05.700
Smolder slid a platter of dates toward

07:29:05.700 --> 07:29:07.560
himself and popped 2 in his mouth.

07:29:07.619 --> 07:29:09.240
It is.

07:29:09.299 --> 07:29:11.279
I really need to kill something.

07:29:11.340 --> 07:29:14.340
It's been too long since I last ripped

07:29:14.340 --> 07:29:15.540
out a dragon's throat.

07:29:15.659 --> 07:29:18.840
Her brother sidled a few steps away

07:29:18.840 --> 07:29:20.459
perhaps thinking he was being

07:29:20.459 --> 07:29:22.139
surreptitious, but failing.

07:29:22.200 --> 07:29:26.279
Well, he said, there's always your

07:29:26.279 --> 07:29:26.700
prisoner.

07:29:26.759 --> 07:29:30.840
No, no, Bern corrected him.

07:29:30.900 --> 07:29:34.380
Queen Scarlet is our guest for now.

07:29:34.439 --> 07:29:37.500
I may change my mind once I decide how

07:29:37.500 --> 07:29:38.459
useful she can be.

07:29:38.520 --> 07:29:41.639
She glanced out at the blazing sun

07:29:41.639 --> 07:29:43.919
reflecting off the courtyard stones.

07:29:44.040 --> 07:29:45.180
No.

07:29:45.240 --> 07:29:47.700
I have another victim in mind.

07:29:47.759 --> 07:29:49.319
Five of them, in fact.

07:29:49.380 --> 07:29:53.759
Of course, he said, ducking his head.

07:29:53.819 --> 07:29:55.740
You just have to find them first.

07:29:55.799 --> 07:29:59.099
Oh, I will, she said.

07:29:59.159 --> 07:30:03.180
Everyone will finally shut up about the

07:30:03.180 --> 07:30:05.939
wonderful dragonettes of destiny when I

07:30:05.939 --> 07:30:07.919
have their heads mounted on spikes on my

07:30:07.919 --> 07:30:08.279
walls.

07:30:08.340 --> 07:30:11.759
She bared her teeth at her brother, smoke

07:30:11.759 --> 07:30:13.319
rising from her nostrils.

07:30:13.380 --> 07:30:15.240
Mark my words.

07:30:15.299 --> 07:30:18.060
Soon we'll put an end to this prophecy

07:30:18.060 --> 07:30:19.740
nonsense once and for all.

07:30:43.860 --> 07:30:47.040
This is Shannon McManus.

